// 专利节点 批次 22
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'KR1020140061320'}) SET p.application_no = 'KR1020140061320', p.title_cn = '集成燃料电池系统的重整器', p.title_en = 'Integrated Reformer for Fuel Cell System', p.abstract_cn = '本发明集成式燃料电池系统的重整器分隔独立地被狗的定性反应腔室一与反应通道的燃料电池堆加湿结构高温废气的热量，在换热过程中产生的混合气产生氢气的混合气体生成，并加热至使信道并且该交错狗设置多个反应通道的定性反应效率和提高热效率的，即它的侧壁是由一种结构为紧凑。比℃]结束后的重整器催化剂，催化剂的寿命可轻易做到使用户能交换..内部形成领带本发明提供集成燃料电池系统在更低的重整上排出的高温废气中的热量回收加热通道(100)和，所述加热通道(100)中时与废气换热的热油和水的气体混合物被供给到内部加湿室(120)并产生狗中氢气的混合气体定性反应的反应室(130)内形成通道(110)在高度方向上两个外环(150)之间横向于所述多个上设置有重整器(10)；所述重整器(10)下部和上部，所述加热高温废气通道(100)的异常状态的油被供给到废气入口(20)和排气侧(30)；所述重整器(10)，它安装在一个上部，所述反应通道(110)内的水供给到多个喷射管(410)内形成会咬的流入部(40)；所述流入口部咬住(40)的重整器(10)的顶部上形成反射层构成，所述流入口部咬住(40)比位于所述反应通道(110)供应燃料的燃料供应的入口部(50)；所述重整器(10)，它安装在中心部分构成，所述反应通道(110)的室(120)，所述混合气体的加湿-狗转变成转化的定性反应室(130)中的搅拌件运动，以平衡气体(60)；所述重整器(10)耦合到所述一个表面侧的下表面，所述重整器(10)的反应通道(110)的同时，在氢气体的排放印刷的一侧(70)；所述重整器(10)耦合到所述下表面构成，所述氢气的一侧(70)具有上表面有一三角形比，盖(81)用(c)的反应通道中的催化剂(110)的喷射催化剂，它能减少引入和排出(80)，其特征在于包括。', p.abstract_en = 'An integrated reformer for a fuel cell system according to the present invention maximizes reforming efficiency and heat efficiency by arranging multiple heating channels and reaction channels to generate a mixed gas and generate a hydrogen gas from the mixed gas through heat exchange with heat of a high temperature exhaust gas generated in a fuel cell stack in the reaction channels including a moisturizing chamber and a reforming chamber having independent structure by a barrier,  not only has a compact structure,  but also includes a catalyst outlet to easily exchange a used catalyst.', p.application_date = '2014-05-22 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'KR101643536B1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'PL10765566'}) SET p.application_no = 'PL10765566', p.title_cn = '具有可变烟气流量的初级重整器', p.title_en = 'PRIMARY REFORMER HAVING VARIABLE SMOKE GAS FLOW', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种用于在高压下通过分裂管反应器和点火室用蒸汽催化烃类初级重整的方法。 在可使用催化剂材料的分裂管系统中，待重整的烃通过水蒸汽转化为合成气。 分体管系统由分体管之间的多个燃烧设备加热，分体管包括多个串联布置的燃烧器，燃烧器主要产生向下指向的火焰。 向相关的燃烧设备供应燃料和空气，空气从相关的供给器排出。 这样放出的烟道气从上到下通过燃烧室，并在燃烧室的下部区域进入水平布置的陶瓷烟道，该陶瓷烟道彼此平行延伸并垂直于垂直分裂管，并被分配给一个燃烧室。 设施各不相同。 烟气通过烟气通道的侧壁中的孔进入。 燃烧室出口处的烟道气通入热回收装置。 在每个烟道中，附加气体沿烟道气流方向被送入烟道的前侧，其中所述气体包含氧和不可燃气体，使得附加气体在燃烧室的整个长度上通过烟道。 调节通入烟道的附加气体的体积。', p.abstract_en = 'A method is disclosed for catalytic primary reformation of hydrocarbons with steam at elevated pressure by means of a split tube reactor and a firing chamber. In the split tube system which can use a catalyst material,  hydrocarbons to be reformed are converted by water steam to synthesis gas. The split tube system is heated by a plurality of firing facilities between the split tubes which include a plurality of burners arranged in series,  the burners generating mainly downwardly directed flames. The relevant firing facilities are supplied with fuel and air,  with the air being withdrawn from the relevant feeders. The flue gas thus evolving passes through the firing chamber from top to bottom and enters in the lower area of the firing chamber into horizontally arranged ceramic flue gas tunnels extending in parallel to each other and perpendicular to the vertical split tubes and being allocated to one firing facility each. The flue gas enters through apertures in the lateral walls of the flue gas tunnels. The flue gas at the exit of the firing chamber is passed into heat recovery devices. In each flue gas tunnel an additional gas is fed into the tunnel\'s front side,  in flue gas flow direction,  wherein the gas containing oxygen and a non-combustible gas,  so that the additional gas passes the flue gas tunnels over the entire length of the firing chamber. The volume of the additional gas passed into the flue gas tunnels is regulated.', p.application_date = '2010-06-24 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'PL2445830T3', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'DE102015201065'}) SET p.application_no = 'DE102015201065', p.title_cn = '电源方法具有反应器，用于从液体中释放氢的化合物', p.title_en = 'Method for power supply having a reactor for the release of hydrogen from liquid compounds', p.abstract_cn = '本发明的方法后，通过脱水操作的反应器生产氢气液，管或斜板装置的反应器中氢吸热反应的化合物，并升温至反应温度的载热液体介质保持热交换器，为了达到该目的，所述液体介质在一定距离上被沿着管或板的反应器中进行，其特征在于 : 所述量的控制或调节的热被传递到管或板的反应器的体积流量的减少在液体介质中。', p.abstract_en = 'After of the invention is a method of operating a reactor for the production of hydrogen by dehydrate a liquid,  hydrogen in tubes or plates of the reactor by means of a compound carrying endothermic reaction,  and brought to the reaction temperature by heat-bearing liquid medium are held a heat exchanger,  for which purpose the liquid medium over a certain distance is guided along on the tubes or plates of the reactor is carried out,  characterized in that a control or regulation of the quantity of heat to be transmitted to the tubes or plates of the reactor by a reduction of the volume flow of the liquid medium.', p.application_date = '2015-01-22 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'DE102015201065A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2015011458'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2015011458', p.title_cn = '所述除氨，除氨材料及其使用方法', p.title_en = 'AMMONIA REMOVAL MATERIAL AND AMMONIA REMOVAL METHOD USING THE SAME', p.abstract_cn = '所要解决的问题 : 铵盐可增加比例的氨和除氨材料具有优异的除氨的去除效率的方法及其使用。溶液 : 所述除氨材料，氢和碳颗粒具有颗粒的混合物铵盐，液氨或氨水，含氢和氮的含氢气体混合物中的气体通过，氨或氢气混合气体中包含的铵盐与咬合接触，氨或氢气的混合气体中包含的被去除。选择附图中 : 图。1', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To provide an ammonia removal material that can increase the mixed ratio of ammonium salts and has excellent ammonia removal efficiency,  and to provide an ammonia removal method using the ammonia removal material. SOLUTION :  An ammonia removal material,  in which granular ammonium salts containing hydrogen and granular carbon are mixed,  allows hydrogen gas containing ammonia or a mixed gas of hydrogen and nitrogen containing ammonia to pass therethrough,  whereby the ammonia contained in the hydrogen gas or the mixed gas is brought into contact with the ammonium salts to be occluded by the ammonium salts and the ammonium in the hydrogen gas or the mixed gas is removed. SELECTED DRAWING :  Figure 1 COPYRIGHT :  (C)2016, JPO&INPIT', p.application_date = '2015-01-23 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP2016135722A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/56', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2016511133'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2016511133', p.title_cn = '燃料供给装置', p.title_en = 'Fuel supply device', p.abstract_cn = '当反应的反应室，以提供燃料并产生符合生产流体燃料的发热物质，若干个分开且独立的燃料生产的流体室，和使加热器组件适于破裂，流体燃料制造用于产生燃料室流体选择性地供应到反应室中，本发明提供的燃料供给装置。', p.abstract_en = 'A fuel supply apparatus comprising;  a reaction chamber for hosting a reaction when a fuel generating fluid and a fuel generating substance are brought together to generate fuel,  a plurality of discrete fuel generating fluid chambers,  each chamber being separately rupturable;  and,  a heater assembly adapted to,  when in use,  selectively rupture the fuel generating fluid chambers to supply fuel generating fluid to the reaction chamber.', p.application_date = '2014-05-01 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP2016522143A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/06', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US15021105'}) SET p.application_no = 'US15021105', p.title_cn = '用于氢气储存和输送多区脱氢反应器和压载系统', p.title_en = 'MULTI-ZONE DEHYDROGENATION REACTOR AND BALLASTING SYSTEM FOR STORAGE AND DELIVERY OF HYDROGEN', p.abstract_cn = '一种用于从氢化有机载体释放氢的方法和系统。 所述方法包括提供包括第一反应区和第二反应区的反应器系统，所述第一反应区具有第一反应条件并且所述第二反应区具有第二反应条件，其中所述第一反应条件和所述第二反应条件不同。 还公开了一种镇流器系统和方法。 所述压载系统包括至少一个容器，所述容器包含能够选择性地存储来自所述含氢物流的氢的金属氢化物，以及选择性地向氢负载或脱氢系统中的一个或两个提供氢中的一个或两个。', p.abstract_en = 'A process and system for a process for releasing hydrogen from a hydrogenated organic carrier. The process including providing a reactor system comprising a first reaction zone and a second reaction zone,  the first reaction zone having a first reaction condition and the second reaction zone having a second reaction condition,  wherein the first reaction condition and the second reaction condition are different. A ballast system and method are also disclosed. The ballast system includes at least one vessel containing metal hydride capable of selectively storing hydrogen from the hydrogen-containing stream and one or both of selectively providing hydrogen to one or both of a hydrogen load or the dehydrogenation system.', p.application_date = '2014-10-20 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US20160214858A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/26', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US15089085'}) SET p.application_no = 'US15089085', p.title_cn = '自热重整(ATR)催化结构', p.title_en = 'Auto Thermal Reforming (ATR) Catalytic Structures', p.abstract_cn = '一种用于从液态烃、蒸汽和氧源产生氢气的自热重整催化结构。 自热重整催化结构包括载体结构和均匀分散在整个载体结构中的纳米尺寸混合金属氧化物颗粒。', p.abstract_en = 'An autothermal reforming catalytic structure for generating hydrogen gas from liquid hydrocarbons,  steam and an oxygen source. The autothermal reforming catalytic structure includes a support structure and nanosized mixed metal oxide particles dispersed homogenously throughout the support structure.', p.application_date = '2016-04-01 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US20160214859A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/48', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 2, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201410847245.8'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201410847245.8', p.title_cn = '一种氢气能源燃料', p.title_en = 'Hydrogen energy fuel', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公布了一种氢气能源燃料，其步骤为：其步骤为准备一个容器倒入适量水，在适量水中添加有主要原料铁粉末、铝矿石粉末，辅料为煤矸石粉末、氯化钠、乙酸、片碱、石灰水、稀硫酸、稀盐酸、氯化铵、待其加入添加剂后会产生气泡，气泡会不停地冒出，无毒无气味，用点燃物将气泡点燃, 此时发出红色火焰，燃烧期间，如果火焰逐渐减小时可以适量添加水，如果火焰太大可减少容器内制备好的液体。本发明无毒无害、安全无污染、节省能源，且具有取暖功效。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention discloses a hydrogen energy fuel. The hydrogen energy fuel is produced through the following steps :  preparing a container,  pouring a proper amount of water to the container,  adding main raw materials comprising iron powder and aluminum ore powder and auxiliary materials comprising gangue powder,  sodium chloride,  acetic acid,  caustic soda flakes,  limewater,  diluted sulfuric acid,  diluted hydrochloric acid and ammonium chloride to the proper amount of water,  and adding an additive to continuously generate bubbles. The bubbles are nontoxic and odorless,  and can be ignited through using an ignition material to emit red flame,  a proper amount of water can be added if the flame gradually reduces in the combustion period,  and a prepared liquid in the container can be reduced if the flame is too strong. The hydrogen energy fuel has the advantages of nontoxicity and innocuousness,  high safety,  no pollution,  energy saving and heating efficacy.', p.application_date = '2014-12-31 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105800551A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201410847375.1'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201410847375.1', p.title_cn = '一种快速制造氢气的方法', p.title_en = 'Method for rapidly producing hydrogen', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公布了一种快速制造氢气的方法，其技术要点是：(一)准备原料铝矿石、铁矿石及水，(二)按质量百分比在适量水中添加有稀硫酸、乙酸、烧碱、氧化铝、锌粒通过具体制取氢气的步骤制取出氢气。本发明制取氢气速度快、消除污染、制取出的氢气浓度纯、点燃火焰大，可广泛应用于化工、环境保护等行业。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention discloses a method for rapidly producing hydrogen. The method is characterized in that the method comprises the following steps :  1,  preparing raw materials comprising aluminum ores,  iron ores and water;  and 2,  adding diluted sulfuric acid,  acetic acid,  caustic soda,  alumina and zinc particles to a proper amount according to certain mass percentages,  and carrying out a concrete hydrogen production step to produce hydrogen. The method has the advantages of fast hydrogen production speed,  pollution elimination,  and pure concentration and large ignition flame of produced hydrogen,  and can be widely applied in chemical engineering and the environmental protection industry.', p.application_date = '2014-12-31 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105800552A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/08', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201610280376.1'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201610280376.1', p.title_cn = '一种外置联箱式水冷可控变换反应器', p.title_en = 'External header type water cooling controlled shift reactor', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种外置联箱式水冷可控变换反应器，反应器承压外筒体内部设置水冷管束、分布筒、集气筒，承压外筒体两端分别设置上外置联箱、下外置联箱，水冷管束通过上、下外置联箱互通。原料气通过工艺气进口进入筒体，经外分布筒进入催化剂床层进行CO变换，与水冷管束内的低温流体进行可控式换热，反应换热后的变换气通过内集气筒、出口中心管离开反应器。本发明采用外置联箱结构，能单独对水冷管束进行检查和维修，提高了变换系统核心反应器的安全性、可维护性。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention discloses an external header type water cooling controlled shift reactor. A water cooling tube bundle,  a distribution drum and a gas gathering drum are arranged in a bearing outer drum body of the reactor;  an upper external header and a lower external header are respectively arranged on two ends of the bearing outer drum body;  the water cooling tube bundle is interconnected through the upper external header and the lower external header. Feed gas enters into a drum body through a process gas inlet,  enters into a catalyst bed layer through the outer distribution drum to carry out CO shift,  and carries out controlled heat exchange with low temperature hydrothermal fluid in the water cooling tube bundle;  shift gas subjected to reaction heat exchange left the reactor through the inner gas gathering drum and an outlet center pipe. The external header type water cooling controlled shift reactor provided by the invention adopts an external header structure,  so that the water cooling pipe bundle can be independently checked and maintained,  and the safety and the maintainability of a shift system core reactor are improved.', p.application_date = '2016-04-29 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105800554A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/16', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201620123833.1'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201620123833.1', p.title_cn = '氨合成多联产甲醇合成用变换气的制取装置', p.title_en = 'Ammonia synthesis poly -generation methanol synthesis is with device of preparing of transform gas', p.abstract_cn = '本实用新型属一种氨合成多联产甲醇合成用变换气的制取装置；包括机械部分和控制部分，机械部分包括气化水洗塔，气化水洗塔出口通过管道与第二热量及冷凝液回收单元进口相连，气化水洗塔出口与第二热量及冷凝液回收单元之间的管道上依次安装有第五三通、第一自调阀、第一三通和第二三通，第二热量及冷凝液回收单元出口与第二洗氨塔中部进口相连，第二洗氨塔顶部气相出口通过管道与甲醇合成用变换气洗涤塔下部进口相连；控制部分包括第一在线分析计算显示仪、第二在线分析计算显示仪、第二自调阀、第三自调阀；具有配比效率和精度高，调节手段多，产生高品质蒸汽量较多，同时降低去甲醇洗变换气中COS含量的优点。', p.abstract_en = 'The utility model belongs to an ammonia synthesis poly -generation methanol synthesis is with device of preparing of transform gas,  including mechanical part and control section,  mechanical part is including the gasification water wash column,  the export of gasification water wash column links to each other with second heat and the import of condensate recovery unit through the pipeline,  install the 5th tee bend on the pipeline between the export of gasification water wash column and second heat and the condensate recovery unit in proper order,  first self -modulation valve,  first tee bend and second tee bend,  second heat and condensate recovery unit outlet wash the import of ammonia tower middle part with the second and link to each other,  the second is washed the ammonia top of the tower gas exports of portion and is passed through pipeline and methanol synthesis usefulness transform gas scrubbing tower imported linking to each other of lower part,  control section includes that a online analysis calculates the display instrument,  the 2nd online analysis calculates display instrument,  second self -modulation valve,  third self -modulation valve,  it is high to have ratio efficiency and precision,  and the regulating measure is many,  and it is more to produce high -quality steam volume,  reduces simultaneously and goes methyl alcohol to wash the advantage that alternaties COS content in the gas.', p.application_date = '2016-02-04 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN205398105U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/12', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201620123831.2'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201620123831.2', p.title_cn = '一种合成氨驰放气中氢气的回收装置', p.title_en = 'Recovery unit of hydrogen during synthetic ammonia speeds to exit', p.abstract_cn = '本实用新型属于一种合成氨驰放气中氢气的回收装置；包括合成系统驰放气管道、合成系统高压氮氢压缩机一段入口、LNG生产装置，合成系统驰放气管道通过氨回收装置和加热器的壳程与膜分离单元的首端膜分离装置的中部进口相连，所述膜分离单元的顶部的氢气出口通过管道与合成系统高压氮氢压缩机一段入口相连，膜分离单元末端膜分离装置的底部尾气出口通过管道与LNG生产装置相连；具有设备简单、操作方便、运行可靠、在节能降耗同时能够实现产品的有效利用、且可减少环境污染的优点。', p.abstract_en = 'The utility model belongs to a recovery unit of hydrogen during synthetic ammonia speeds to exit,  including synthesis system speed one section entry on gas pipeline,  the synthesis system high pressure nitrogen hydrogen compressor,  LNG apparatus for producing,  synthesis system speeds,  and to pass through the shell side of ammonia recovery device and heater imported continuous with membrane separation unit\'s head end membrane separation device\'s middle part for gas pipeline,  the hydrogen export at membrane separation unit\'s top links to each other through one section entry in the pipeline and synthesis system high pressure nitrogen hydrogen compressor,  and the terminal membrane separation device\'s of membrane separation unit bottom tail gas export links to each other with the LNG apparatus for producing through the pipeline,  have that equipment is simple,  convenient operation,  operation are reliable,  can realize effective utilization,  and reducible environmental pollution\'s the advantage of product simultaneously at energy saving and consumption reduction.', p.application_date = '2016-02-04 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN205398106U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/50', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CY121101135'}) SET p.application_no = 'CY121101135', p.title_cn = '对地下水和地下水的临时影响', p.title_en = 'REAGENT FOR SIMULTANEOUS SEPARATION OF HYDROGEN AND OXYGEN FROM WATER', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种从水生产氢气的装置使用热。本装置采用热分解水基本上无电工作。本发明基于的概念的膜反应器，两种膜允许氢气的分离同时以化学计量的量和氧从反应器体积。该装置具有特殊的几何形状，从而产生所述反应腔室内部的温度分布，以适应使用氢选择膜。该装置将有利于减少氢运输和储存的需要，因为它会相当紧凑现场使用在家庭，小型工厂或加油站。移动应用中使用的装置是可能的。所述的热源装置，如燃烧的碳氢化合物的多孔燃烧技术；然而该装置可以被修改以利用任何其它热源，特别是太阳辐射。', p.abstract_en = 'We disclose a device for the production of hydrogen from water using heat. The device employs thermal water splitting and works essentially without electricity. It is based on the concept of a membrane reactor with two kinds of membranes allowing the separation of hydrogen and oxygen simultaneously in stoichiometric quantities from the reactor volume. The device has a special geometry resulting in a temperature distribution inside the reaction chamber to accommodate the use of hydrogen selective membranes. The device will help to reduce the need for hydrogen transport and storage as it will be rather compact for on-site use in households,  small factories or gas stations. The use of the device in mobile applications is conceivable. The heat source of the device as described is combustion of a hydrocarbon using porous burner technology;  however the device can be modified to exploit any other heat source,  especially solar radiation.', p.application_date = '2012-11-23 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CY1113860T1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'EP09719518'}) SET p.application_no = 'EP09719518', p.title_cn = '从天然气生产液态烃的方法', p.title_en = 'PROCESS FOR PRODUCING LIQUID HYDROCARBONS FROM NATURAL GAS', p.abstract_cn = '在所谓的GTL从天然气生产合成气的方法，制备费托合成油品通过费-托合成得到的合成气制造液态烃燃料油，通过升级，从合成气制造工序中产生的合成气的部分分支之前对费-托合成油品的生产步骤和合成气进入分支线路进行水煤气变换反应的氢气浓度。随后，高纯度氢气的合成气体和残余气体隔离隔离后循环至合成气制造工序作为原料用于合成气生产。其结果是，显著提高了原料消耗方面可实现整个过程的产品。', p.abstract_en = 'In a so-called GTL process of producing synthesis gas from natural gas,  producing Fischer-Tropsch oil by way of Fischer-Tropsch synthesis of the obtained synthesis gas and producing liquid hydrocarbons containing fuel oil by upgrading,  the synthesis gas produced from the synthesis gas production step is partly branched off prior to getting to the Fischer-Tropsch oil production step and the synthesis gas entering the branch line is subjected to a water gas shift reaction to raise the hydrogen concentration thereof. Subsequently,  high-purity hydrogen is isolated from the synthesis gas and the residual gas left after the isolation is circulated to the synthesis gas production step and used as raw material for synthesis gas production. As a result,  a significant improvement can be achieved in terms of raw material consumption per product of the entire process.', p.application_date = '2009-03-11 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'EP2253585B8', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 2, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'EP11721237'}) SET p.application_no = 'EP11721237', p.title_cn = '获取氢气的装置及方法', p.title_en = 'INSTALLATION AND METHOD FOR OBTAINING HYDROGEN', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种获取氢气的装置和方法从含氢介质。所述设备(10)包括第第一和第第二电极组件16，18之间形成的间隙(20)，通过该含氢介质被引导。电压源(26)生成第一和第二之间的高电压电极组件16，18，以所述气隙中产生一个电场，其适用于从含氢的分子氢的分离介质。第一和/或第二电极组件16，18包括至少一个电极(22，24)，其具有圆形的，特别是球形，形状或横截面具有这样的形状。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to an installation and a method for obtaining hydrogen from a hydrogen-containing medium. The installation 10 comprises a first and a second electrode assembly 16,  18 between which a gap 20 is formed,  through which a hydrogen-containing medium is conducted. A voltage source 26 generates a high voltage between the first and second electrode assembly 16,  18 in order to generate in said gap an electric field which is suitable for separating hydrogen from molecules of the hydrogen-containing medium. The first and/or the second electrode assembly 16,  18 comprise at least one electrode 22,  24,  which has a rounded,  in particular spherical,  shape or a section having such a shape.', p.application_date = '2011-05-20 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'EP2571804B1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'BRPI0923552'}) SET p.application_no = 'BRPI0923552', p.title_cn = '精炼厂中的二氧化碳的减排方法', p.title_en = 'METHOD TO REDUCE EMISSIONS OF CARBON DIOXIDE IN A REFINERY', p.abstract_cn = '于一个精炼厂减少二氧化碳排放，在低压重整含烃进料以提高甲烷向氢气和一氧化碳的转化，从而降低未反应甲烷。所述含烃进料的全部或至少部分是由炼油厂废气。所得的重整流进行水-气变换来形成变换流，从该二氧化碳分离。作为分离和低压重整的结果，含氢的燃料气体流，其由此必然是贫二氧化碳和甲烷，用于点火燃烧蒸汽甲烷重整器和炼厂内的其他燃料用途，减少了二氧化碳的排放。可分离的二氧化碳封存或用于其它工艺，如提高石油采收率。', p.abstract_en = 'Carbon dioxide emissions within a refinery are reduced by reforming a hydrocarbon containing feed at low pressure to enhance the conversion of methane to hydrogen and carbon monoxide and thereby reduce methane slip. The hydrocarbon containing feed is composed entirely or at least in part of a refinery off gas. The resulting reformed stream is then subjected to water-gas shift conversion to form a shifted stream from which carbon dioxide is separated. As a result of the separation and the low pressure reforming,  hydrogen containing fuel gas streams,  that are thereby necessary lean in carbon dioxide and methane,  are used in firing the steam methane reformer and other fuel uses within the refinery to reduce carbon dioxide emissions. The carbon dioxide that is separated can be sequestered or used in other processes such as enhanced oil recovery.', p.application_date = '2009-12-31 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'BRPI0923552A2', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US13857951'}) SET p.application_no = 'US13857951', p.title_cn = '用于气相还原/氧化过程的方法和设备', p.title_en = 'Methods and apparatus for gas-phase reduction/oxidation processes', p.abstract_cn = '公开了一种用于气相还原/氧化方法和装置。 所述装置包括反应器，所述反应器包括至少一个反应器管或安全壳，在所述反应器管或安全壳内具有活性氧化还原材料，用于还原所述活性氧化还原材料的第一反应气体或真空，以及用于氧化所述活性氧化还原材料的第二反应气体。 该方法可以在基本等温的条件下运行和/或提供给设备的能量可以包括太阳能，太阳能可以被集中。', p.abstract_en = 'A method and apparatus for gas-phase reduction/oxidation is disclosed. The apparatus includes a reactor including at least one reactor tube or containment vessel with active redox material within the reactor tube or containment vessel,  a first reactant gas or vacuum for reducing the active redox material,  and a second reactant gas for oxidizing the active redox material. The method may be run under substantially isothermal conditions and/or energy supplied to the apparatus may include solar energy,  which may be concentrated.', p.application_date = '2013-04-05 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9399575B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/06', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'DK10719140'}) SET p.application_no = 'DK10719140', p.title_cn = '一种含氢产品气体的制备方法', p.title_en = 'Procedure for the production of a hydrogen-containing product gas', p.abstract_cn = '用于制造含氢产物气体的方法通过催化蒸汽-烃重整具有整体蒸汽与碳的摩尔比为1.5和2.4的过程。该工艺物流反应，反应之前在至少两个预转化炉中的含催化剂的管中，在顶烧转化炉。绝热预重整器第一中的过程物流反应，本发明的方法之前被引入物流被加热预重整器第二和/或第二加热预重整器。该方法避免了催化剂上的积碳在含催化剂的管中的主重整器。', p.abstract_en = 'A process for producing a hydrogen-containing product gas by catalytic steam-hydrocarbon reforming with an overall steam-to-carbon molar ratio between 1.5 and 2.4 for the process. The process stream is reacted in at least two prereformers prior to reaction in catalyst-containing tubes in a top-fired reformer furnace. The process stream is reacted adiabatically in the first prereformer,  while the process stream is heated prior to being introduced into the second prereformer and/or the second prereformer is heated. The process avoids carbon formation on the catalyst in the catalyst-containing tubes in the primary reformer.', p.application_date = '2010-04-15 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'DK2419375T3', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2015007373'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2015007373', p.title_cn = '氢生成装置和使用其的燃料电池系统及其操作方法', p.title_en = 'HYDROGEN GENERATION DEVICE AND FUEL CELL SYSTEM THEREWITH AND OPERATION METHOD THEREOF', p.abstract_cn = '所要解决的问题 : 当环境温度低，降低加热的加热器，较长的使用寿命，提供一种装置用于产生氢气的燃料电池系统。溶液 : 氢生成装置(400)，含烃原料产生含氢气体的重整反应器重整装置(100)，至少一部分所述反应器和加热器(20)，当环境温度较低时，当环境温度较高，使所述加热装置的加热量小于20和控制单元300，被提供。选择附图中 : 图。1', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To provide a hydrogen generation device which can be extended its life by lowering a heating amount of a heater when environmental temperature is low,  and a fuel cell system. SOLUTION :  A hydrogen generation device 400 comprises :  a reactor including a reformer 100 reforming raw materials containing hydrocarbons and producing hydrogen-containing gas;  a heater 20 heating at least a part of the reactor;  and a controller 300 controlling the heater 20 so that heating with a smaller heating amount than a case where the environmental temperature is relatively high when the environmental temperature is relatively low. SELECTED DRAWING :  Figure 1 COPYRIGHT :  (C)2016, JPO&INPIT', p.application_date = '2015-01-19 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP2016132585A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/34', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2015008210'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2015008210', p.title_cn = '氢生成装置及燃料电池系统', p.title_en = 'Hydrogen generator and fuel cell system', p.abstract_cn = '所要解决的问题 : hydrogenetated脱硫单元，其设置在用于供应原料气体回收气路从含氢气体吸入ejecters氢气发生器，本发明的氢生成装置用于在整个原料气的流量，燃气比例的原料气体在预定的流率范围hydrogenetion供给的燃料气体的脱硫装置。溶液 : 燃气管道5连接到燃料重整器4的分支部排出的气体原料供给路径(3)用于混合原料的流量气体和循环气体通道(6)，和原料供给通路3，设置在所述循环气体通道连接部分6和ejecters7，原料供给装置(2)和位于所述喷射器(7)从原料供给路(3)，不经过喷射器(7)hydrogenetion脱硫剂1份；所述原料气供应到上设有原料供给通路2，8和第一，一种第二原料气体引射器7，并且通过原料供给通路2，8。选择附图中 : 图。1', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To supply a fuel gas flow rate,  where the ratio of a fuel gas to a raw material gas is within a predetermined range over the whole area of a raw material gas flow rate used by a hydrogen generator,  to a hydrogenation desulfurizer,  in a hydrogen generator that sucks a hydrogen-containing gas from a recycle gas passage at an ejector installed in a passage for supplying the raw material gas to the hydrogenation desulfurizer. SOLUTION :  A hydrogen generator comprises :  a recycle gas passage 6 that branches from a fuel gas passage 5 to mix a part of a fuel gas discharged from a reformer 4 into a raw material gas flowing into a raw material supply passage 3;  an ejector 7 that is arranged at a merging part of the raw material supply passage 3 and the recycle gas passage 6;  and a second raw material supply passage 8 that branches from the raw material supply passage 3 located between a raw material feeder 2 and the ejector 7 to supply a part of the raw material gas to a hydrogenation desulfurizer 1 without through the ejector 7,  whereby the hydrogen generator is configured so that the raw material gas flows through the ejector 7 and the second raw material supply passage 8. SELECTED DRAWING :  Figure 1 COPYRIGHT :  (C)2016, JPO&INPIT', p.application_date = '2015-01-20 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP2016132592A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2015008212'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2015008212', p.title_cn = '氢生成装置及燃料电池系统及其操作方法', p.title_en = 'HYDROGEN GENERATION DEVICE AND OPERATION METHOD THEREOF AND FUEL CELL SYSTEM', p.abstract_cn = '所要解决的问题 : 煤在启动时升温除杂装置，由于所述解吸氢气的原料气的燃烧断火抑制。溶液 : 氢生成装置(8)，对荒煤气中的杂质吸附除去反应除杂装置1，含氢气体并产生重整气体发生器2，含氢气体的原料气体燃烧的燃烧室(3)和至少一个用于加热重整器2，燃烧器(3)供给燃烧用空气和空气供给装置(4)，和控制器5，除杂装置(1)的温度检测和温度检测器(6)和壳体(7)容纳它们。在开始，所述控制单元(5)，由温度检测器(6)，通过测量温度Tn除杂装置1，从多个测量获得的ΔTa和TN的温度变化率，一种除杂器1的温度变化ΔTn除杂装置(1)从原料气体的脱附量D确定，基于该值来控制燃烧空气的量。选择附图中 : 图。1', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To prevent flame off of a burner of a hydrogen generation device caused by detaching of source gas from an impurity eliminator due to a temperature rise at a time of charcoal start. SOLUTION :  A hydrogen generation device 8 comprises :  an impurity eliminator 1 eliminating impurities in source gas by adsorption reaction;  a reformer 2 producing hydrogen-containing gas from the source gas;  a burner 3 burning at least one of the source gas and the hydrogen-containing gas,  and heating the reformer 2;  an air feeding device 4 feeding combustion air to the burner 3;  a controller 5;  a temperature detector 6 detecting temperature of the impurity eliminator 1;  and a housing 7 holding them. At starting,  the controller 5 measures temperature Tn of the impurity eliminator 1 with the temperature detector 6 at any time,  determines detached raw material gas quantity d from the impurity eliminator 1 from a temperature rate of change ΔTa and a temperature variation ΔTn of the impurity eliminator 1 calculated from the measured plural Tn,  and controls combustion air volume on the basis of the value. SELECTED DRAWING :  Figure 1 COPYRIGHT :  (C)2016, JPO&INPIT', p.application_date = '2015-01-20 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP2016132593A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2015008349'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2015008349', p.title_cn = '氢发生装置及其制造方法，发电装置', p.title_en = 'HYDROGEN-GENERATING AGENT AND METHOD FOR PRODUCING THE SAME,  AND POWER GENERATOR', p.abstract_cn = '所要解决的问题 : 提高在运输时的抗震性能，或粉尘不会损伤到容器及其制造方法，氢气发生器，发电装置，适用于氢气发生器。溶液 : 氢气发生器1，B，瓶状容器，所述基材(51)含有与水反应的材料(52)含有氢化钙，容器B，捏合成型，固化，在氢源3和具有固体，该固态氢源3·3s，固定为一体的瓶状容器B，在同一时间，3g，容器B中形成的间隙。该固态氢源3·3s，颗粒或成型模具中，固态氢源附近的容器B中3·3s，提高孔隙率，在其附近产生的氢气的体积膨胀时的固态氢源3吸收的孔隙充满·3S。选择附图中 : 图。1', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To provide a hydrogen-generating agent and a method for producing the same which enhance resistance to vibration at the time of transportation and prevent dust and damage of a container;  and a power generator to which the hydrogen-generating agent is applied. SOLUTION :  A hydrogen-generating agent 1 includes :  a bottle-like container B;  and a solid hydrogen source 3 which contains a water-reactive substance (calcium hydride 52) in a base material 51 containing a resin,  and is kneaded,  molded and cured in the container B. The solid hydrogen sources 3 and 3S are integrated with and stuck to the bottle-like container B,  and simultaneously form a gap portion 3G in the container B. The solid hydrogen sources 3 and 3S are formed into a granular form or a thread form,  a void ratio in the vicinity of the solid hydrogen sources 3 and 3S in the container B after curing is enhanced,  and volume expansion at the time of hydrogen generation can be absorbed by satisfying the gap portion in the vicinity of the solid hydrogen sources 3 and 3S. SELECTED DRAWING :  Figure 1 COPYRIGHT :  (C)2016, JPO&INPIT', p.application_date = '2015-01-20 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP2016132595A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/06', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'FR11000055'}) SET p.application_no = 'FR11000055', p.title_cn = '用于产生能量的装置及相关方法', p.title_en = 'DEVICE FOR PRODUCING ENERGY AND ASSOCIATED METHODS', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种能量生产装置包含 : 一储存器(100, 200)，其包含至少一种化学化合物，该化合物能自吸氢能力。装置(300)的储存器(100, 200)热含量，装置(500，600，700，610，620，630，640)将所述蓄水池中的含氢气体的方式来控制气体的压力容器中，其特征在于 : 所述贮存器(100, 200)还含有至少一种化合物，其具有低功函数。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention deals with a device for producing energy comprizing :  - one reservoir (100, 200) containing at least a chemical compound able to ad-absorb hydrogen. - means (300) to heat the content of the reservoir (100, 200),  - means (500,  600,  700,  610,  620,  630,  640) to introduce an hydrogen containing gas in said reservoir and means to control the pressure of that gas in the reservoir,  characterized in that the reservoir (100, 200) contains also at least a chemical compound having a low work function.', p.application_date = '2011-01-07 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'FR2970244B1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'IN1398MUMNP2015'}) SET p.application_no = 'IN1398MUMNP2015', p.title_cn = '再生废的氢化物燃料', p.title_en = 'REGENERATION OF SPENT HYDRIDE FUEL', p.abstract_cn = '再生废氢燃料的方法包括以下步骤 : (1)从等离子体生成肼；例如，使用液氨中产生肼溶液中产生的等离子体辉光放电单元(2)使该废氢燃料与所述肼以及(3)将燃料从管嘴分离再生氢化。该方法可广泛用于再生失效的氢化物运输燃料，用于向例如燃料电池或内燃机。它特别可用于再生废氨硼烷等燃料，因氨硼烷的脱氢/聚合物复合燃料。', p.abstract_en = 'A process for regenerating spent hydride fuel comprises the steps of (1) generating hydrazine from a plasma;  for example generating a solution of hydrazine in liquid ammonia using a plasma generated in a glow discharge cell (2) contacting the spent hydride fuel with said hydrazine and (3) thereafter separating a regenerated hydride fuel therefrom. The process is widely applicable in regenerating spent hydride transportation fuels which are used to power for example a fuel cell or an internal combustion engine. It is especially useful in regenerating spent ammonia borane fuels such as those arising from the dehydrogenation of ammonia borane/polymer composite fuels.', p.application_date = '2015-06-01 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'IN1398MUMNP2015A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'IN201617003829'}) SET p.application_no = 'IN201617003829', p.title_cn = '生产甲醇的方法和系统使用一体化的氧迁移膜基重整系统', p.title_en = 'METHOD AND SYSTEM FOR PRODUCING METHANOL USING AN INTEGRATED OXYGEN TRANSPORT MEMBRANE BASED REFORMING SYSTEM', p.abstract_cn = '生产甲醇的方法和系统，它采用一个整体氧输送膜基重整系统的方法。所述氧气输送膜基重整系统进行初次转化过程的二次重整方法和合成气调节的，以产生合成气具有所需模块大约2.0和2.2之间的用于制甲醇工艺的甲醇厂从而优化的效率和生产率。', p.abstract_en = 'A method and system for producing methanol that employs an integrated oxygen transport membrane based reforming system is disclosed. The integrated oxygen transport membrane based reforming system carries out a primary reforming process a secondary reforming process and synthesis gas conditioning to produce synthesis gas having a desired module of between about 2.0 and 2.2 for a methanol production process thereby optimizing the efficiency and productivity of the methanol plant.', p.application_date = '2016-02-03 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'IN201617003829A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'IN201617009030'}) SET p.application_no = 'IN201617009030', p.title_cn = '收集器的导管以便共同去除工艺气体从重整器，其提供多个重整器管', p.title_en = 'COLLECTOR CONDUIT FOR COMMON REMOVAL OF PROCESS GASES FROM A REFORMER WHICH IS SUPPLIED BY A PLURALITY OF REFORMER TUBES', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种收集器的导管以便共同去除工艺气体从重整器，其通过多个重整器供给管(12，14)上述导管包括集液管(20)用于接收和输送工艺气体至少一个入口接管(24)之间，通过一个出料口(52)与收集器管(20)，其中所述入口配件(24)具有至少1/1进气连接(28)连通的出料口(52)和至少1/2进气连接(32)连通与所述出料口(52)的第一馈线(26)接合到第一进气连接(28)连接到重整器管(12)的第第二馈电线(30)连接第二，进气连接(32)连接到重整器管(14)和普通灵活型绝缘包带(34)环绕着第一馈线(26)，第二馈线(30)进行保温。由于第一馈线(26)和第二馈线(30)组合成一个共同进口接头(24)在一个公共的绝缘包层(34)轻微的热引入的负载尤其用于机械应力引起重整器由于热膨胀和/或增加的热重整器可以方便的下方通过设计简单的措施。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a collector conduit for common removal of process gases from a reformer which is supplied by a plurality of reformer tubes (12,  14) said conduit comprising a collector tube (20) for receiving and conveying the process gases at least one inlet fitting (24) communicating via a discharge opening (52) with the collector tube (20) wherein the inlet fitting (24) has at least one first intake connection (28) communicating with the discharge opening (52) and at least one second intake connection (32) communicating with the discharge opening (52) a first feed line (26) joined to the first intake connection (28) for connection to a reformer tube (12) a second feed line (30) joined to the second intake connection (32) for connection to a reformer tube (14) and a common flexibly shaped insulating cladding (34) surrounding both the first feed line (26) and the second feed line (30) for heat insulation. Due to the first feed line (26) and second feed line (30) combined to form a common inlet fitting (24) in a common insulating cladding (34) slight thermally induced loads caused by a reformer in particular mechanical stresses due to effects of thermal expansion and/or a buildup of heat below the reformer can be facilitated by simple design measures.', p.application_date = '2016-03-15 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'IN201617009030A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'IN6388DELNP2015'}) SET p.application_no = 'IN6388DELNP2015', p.title_cn = '一种储氢微丸', p.title_en = 'A HYDROGEN STORAGE PELLET', p.abstract_cn = '涂覆的储氢微丸；其中所述粒料包括储氢材料；该涂层包括氢气渗透聚合物，所述涂层具有的平均厚度小于50μm。', p.abstract_en = 'A coated hydrogen storage pellet;  wherein the pellet comprises a hydrogen storage material;  the coating comprises a hydrogen permeable polymer and the coating has a mean thickness of less than 50μm.', p.application_date = '2015-07-21 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'IN6388DELNP2015A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'SE201500034'}) SET p.application_no = 'SE201500034', p.title_cn = '用于形成的方法', p.title_en = 'Procedure for ångreformering', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种用于气态或液态燃料的蒸汽重整的方法，使用流化床，其中放置蒸汽重整管，蒸汽重整所需的热量从该流化床传递， 其中所述流化床包含载氧体颗粒，并且其中空气和燃料被加入到该流化床中。 所述方法也可应用于其它具有吸热反应的方法，例如将烃热裂解成有价值的化学品如乙烯和丙烯。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention concerns a method for steam reforming of a gaseous or liquid fuelthe use of fluidized bed wherein the steam reforming tubes are placed and from which the heat needed for steam reforming is transferred,  and where the said fluidized bed contains oxygen-carrier particles and where air and fuel are added to this fluidized bed. The said method could also be applied to other processes with endothermic reactions,  e.g. thermal cracking of hydrocarbons to valuable chemicals such as ethylene and propylene.', p.application_date = '2015-01-21 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'SE1500034A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/44', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'DE602010033932'}) SET p.application_no = 'DE602010033932', p.title_cn = '双流化床气化的系统和方法', p.title_en = 'SYSTEM AND METHOD FOR DUAL FLUIDIZED BED GASIFICATION', p.abstract_cn = '合成气深度脱硫的方法，包括将含碳材料和任选的蒸气到气化器中包括热传递介质，提取第一传热流包括传热介质和任选地未转化含碳材料从气化炉，和将至少一部分第一传热流至燃烧器，通入氧化剂，和任选的燃料到燃烧器中，提取第二传热流包括来自燃烧器的热传递介质，和将至少第二传热流的一部分进入气化器，可引入复合物与硫反应生成硫酸盐，硫化物或两个，提取净化流包含灰分，硫酸，卤化物，或其组合从第二传热流，提取烟气从燃烧器，和提取气化器的合成气产品流包括从气化炉出来的小于1000的硫。', p.abstract_en = 'A method for continuous dry reforming,  the method comprising :  introducing a feed comprising carbon dioxide and at least one selected from methane and propane into a fluid bed conditioner operated at a conditioning temperature,  wherein the fluid bed conditioner is one fluid bed of a dual fluidized bed loop and is configured to convert at least a portion of said feed into synthesis gas components;  extracting a first catalytic heat transfer stream comprising a catalytic heat transfer material and having a first temperature from the fluid bed conditioner and introducing at least a portion of the first catalytic heat transfer stream and a flue gas into a fluid bed combustor,  wherein the fluid bed combustor is configured to regenerate the catalyst via combustion;  extracting a second catalytic heat transfer stream comprising catalytic heat transfer material and having a second temperature from the fluid bed combustor and introducing at least a portion of the second catalytic heat transfer stream into the fluid bed conditioner;  and extracting synthesis gas from the fluid bed conditioner.', p.application_date = '2010-01-21 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'DE602010033932T2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/44', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2015004422'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2015004422', p.title_cn = '燃料重整装置', p.title_en = 'FUEL REFORMER', p.abstract_cn = '该燃料重整器(100)使在蒸汽重整反应的燃料和水在重整催化剂(111)，并具有燃料喷射装置(112)，用于将燃料供给到重整催化剂(111)，和一个喷射控制单元(123)，用于控制燃料喷射的燃料喷射量单元(112)。喷射控制单元(123)控制喷射量，使得重整催化剂的温度(111)不低于预先设定的规定温度。该燃料重整器(100)上还设有温度采集单元(121)，用于测量或估计温度重整催化剂(111)，与目标值计算单元(122)计算喷射量的目标值，使得温度注射后的重整催化剂(111)的燃料的燃料喷射装置(112)为大于或等于预定的温度。燃料喷射单元(112)执行控制，使得喷射量与目标值一致。', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To provide a fuel reformer which allows energy to be recovered efficiently by a water vapor reforming reaction. SOLUTION :  A fuel reformer 100 comprises a second injector 112 that injects fuel for supply to a reforming catalyst 111,  and an injection control unit 123 that controls an amount of fuel injected from the second injector 112. The injection control unit 123 controls an amount of fuel injected from the second injector 112 so that the temperature of the reforming catalyst 111 does not fall below a previously set lower limit temperature TL. SELECTED DRAWING :  Figure 1 COPYRIGHT :  (C)2016, JPO&INPIT', p.application_date = '2015-01-13 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP2016130185A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2015004426'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2015004426', p.title_cn = '燃料重整装置', p.title_en = 'FUEL REFORMER', p.abstract_cn = '该燃料重整器(100)使在蒸汽重整反应的燃料和水在重整催化剂(111)，并具有燃料喷射装置(112)，用于将燃料供给到重整催化剂(111)，一种温度测量单元(113)，121)来测量温度的重整催化剂(111)，以及判定单元(122)，其确定是否重整催化剂的再生处理(111)是否需要调整；判定部(122)的基础上作出所述确定的重整催化剂(111)中的温度变化时，蒸汽重整反应的发生。', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To provide a fuel reformer which can determine degradation of a reforming catalyst and the necessity of regeneration treatment without providing a sensor for detecting a gas component. SOLUTION :  A fuel reformer 100 comprises a second injector 112 that injects fuel for supply to a reforming catalyst 111,  a temperature sensor 113 that measures the temperature of the reforming catalyst 111,  and a determination unit 122 that determines the necessity of regeneration treatment to the reforming catalyst 111. The determination unit 122 performs determination on the basis of a change in temperature of the reforming catalyst 111 while water vapor reforming reaction is occurring. SELECTED DRAWING :  Figure 1 COPYRIGHT :  (C)2016, JPO&INPIT', p.application_date = '2015-01-13 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP2016130186A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2015004680'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2015004680', p.title_cn = '氢生成装置及燃料电池系统', p.title_en = 'Hydrogen generator and fuel cell system', p.abstract_cn = '所要解决的问题 : hydrogenetated脱硫剂原料气体供给路径，从循环气体的含氢气体抽入氢气产生装置具有喷射器，它能脱除硫化合物的稳定。溶液 : 脱硫剂hydrogenetated1穿过原料气含有氢的重整燃气4，将来自该重整装置(4)，用于排出燃料气体的燃料气体管道5，其分支从所述燃气通道5，原料气体从原料供给装置(3)的下游侧的融合原料供给路(2)，所述重整器(4)和排出部的燃料与原料气混合气，循环气体通道(6)，和原料供给路径(261和第二的回收气路和设置在所述合流ejecters部7，1和hydrogenetion喷射器(7)之间分支的脱硫剂，原料气体从原料供给装置(3)连接的上游侧，一种部分原料气供给原料供应单元(3)上设置有物料循环路径(8)。选择附图中 : 图。1', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To remove a stable sulfur compound in a hydrogen generator equipped with an ejector for sucking a hydrogen-containing gas from a recycled gas path in a passage for supplying a raw material gas to a hydrogenation desulfurizer. SOLUTION :  There is provided a hydrogen generator which comprises :  a reformer 4 for reforming a raw material gas passed through a hydrogenation desulfurizer 1 to generate a fuel gas containing hydrogen;  a fuel gas path 5 for discharging the fuel gas from the reformer 4;  a recycled gas path 6 which branches from the fuel gas path 5 and converges to a raw material supply path 2 at the downstream side of the flow of the raw material gas from a raw material supplier 3 and mixes a part of the fuel gas discharged from the reformer 4 with the raw material gas;  an ejector 7 disposed at a first converging portion where the raw material supply path 2 and the recycled gas path 6 are converged;  and a raw material circulation path 8 which branches from between the ejector 7 and the hydrogenation desulfurizer 1 and is connected to the upstream side of the flow of the raw material gas from the raw material supplier 3 and is configured so that a part of the raw material gas is supplied to the raw material supplier 3. SELECTED DRAWING :  Figure 1 COPYRIGHT :  (C)2016, JPO&INPIT', p.application_date = '2015-01-14 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP2016130191A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2015004682'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2015004682', p.title_cn = '氢生成装置及燃料电池系统及其操作方法', p.title_en = 'HYDROGEN GENERATOR,  FUEL CELL SYSTEM AND OPERATION METHOD THEREOF', p.abstract_cn = '所要解决的问题 : hydrogenetated，脱硫温度的原料气体提供给所述脱硫hydrogenetion预热到适宜的温度，脱硫剂hydrogenetated使整体温度均匀，hydrogenetated脱硫剂加载量的氢可抑制到最小。溶液 : 从原料气和蒸汽重整反应生成含氢气体产生重整装置5，hydrogenetion原料中脱除硫化合物的脱硫装置(6)设置在所述氢产生装置(100)，第一，第二，1，901，2预热通道，预热通道(902)hydrogenetion脱硫剂(6)由供给预热荒煤气气化的至少一部分设置的预热段9，根据所述原料气体供给量第一和第二预热通道1(901)荒煤气2预热通道902流动通过的流量控制，水供给脱硫剂6hydrogenetion温度。hydrogenetion脱硫的原料气预热到适宜的温度，整个hydrogenetion脱硫剂的温度的均匀化。选择附图中 : 图。1', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To provide a hydrogen generator capable of minimizing the loading amount of a hydrodesulfurization agent by preheating a raw material gas fed to a hydrogenation desulfurizer at a temperature suitable for hydrodesulfurization and making the temperature of the whole hydrodesulfurization agent uniform. SOLUTION :  There is provided a hydrogen generator 100 which comprises a reformer 5 for generating hydrogen-containing gas by a reforming reaction from a raw material gas and water vapor and a hydrogenation desulfurizer 6 for removing a sulfur compound contained in the raw material,  wherein the hydrogen generator comprises a preheating part 9 which is composed of a first preheating flow passage 901 and a second preheating flow passage 902 and preheats and supplies at least a part of the raw material gas to the hydrogenation desulfurizer 6 and preheats a raw material gas supplied to the hydrogenation desulfurizer 6 at a temperature suitable for hydrodesulfurization and makes the temperature of the whole hydrodesulfurization agent uniform by controlling the flow of the raw material gas flowing through the first preheating flow passage 901 and the second preheating flow passage 902 according to the supply amount of the raw material gas. SELECTED DRAWING :  Figure 1 COPYRIGHT :  (C)2016, JPO&INPIT', p.application_date = '2015-01-14 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP2016130192A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2015004684'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2015004684', p.title_cn = '氢生成装置和使用其的燃料电池系统及其操作方法', p.title_en = 'HYDROGEN GENERATOR,  FUEL CELL SYSTEM USING THE SAME AND OPERATION METHOD OF THE SAME', p.abstract_cn = '所要解决的问题 : 即使当原料的流速，具有可靠性和效率，并提供燃料电池系统产生氢气的装置。溶液 : 氢的重整含烃原料气100和含有，含氢气体中所含的CO氧化催化剂选择性氧化反应器中以减少的CO清除器150和充填，原料及原料供给装置31，CO选择性氧化脱除送风装置和送风单元，用于选择性氧化92，一氧化碳的装置及温度检测器90检测到的温度，以及控制单元(300)设置在所述氢产生装置(400)，所述控制单元(300)，原料的流量，第二原料流率1，当少于阈值时，选择氧化空气的流量控制在根据流率。原料，所述原料流率1，如果第第一阈值以上，选择预定温度和温度的选择氧化催化剂，以控制流速氧化空气。选择附图中 : 图。1', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To provide a hydrogen generator and a fuel cell system which achieve both efficiency and reliability even when a flow rate of a raw material is changed. SOLUTION :  There is provided a hydrogen generator 400 which comprises a reformer 100 for reforming a hydrocarbon-containing raw material to generate a hydrocarbon-containing gas,  a CO remover 150 in which a selective oxidation catalyst for reducing CO contained in the hydrocarbon-containing gas by a selective oxidation reaction is filled,  a raw material feeder 31 for feeding the raw material to the reformer,  a selective oxidation air feeder 92 for feeding selective oxidation air to the CO remover,  a temperature detector 90 for detecting the temperature of the CO remover,  and a controller 300,  wherein the controller 300 controls the flow rate of the selective oxidation air according to the flow rate of the raw material when the flow rate of the raw material is a first threshold or lower and controls the flow rate of the selective oxidation air so that the temperature of the selective oxidation air is a predetermined temperature when the flow rate of the raw material is larger than the first threshold. SELECTED DRAWING :  Figure 1 COPYRIGHT :  (C)2016, JPO&INPIT', p.application_date = '2015-01-14 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP2016130193A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2015004686'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2015004686', p.title_cn = '氢生成装置及燃料电池系统', p.title_en = 'HYDROGEN GENERATOR,  AND FUEL CELL SYSTEM', p.abstract_cn = '所要解决的问题 : 上游部分和下游部分通过减小温度梯度的重整催化剂，以减小量所述重整催化剂。解决手段 : 在排出通道(34)，和向改性部(10)相邻的部分(“A”部分图。1)，外部安装有保温材料41。外保温材料41穿过保温材料抑制由于热的传导和辐射，在“A”部分重整气体的排出通道(34)中的蒸汽转化段(10)和换热性能，在图中。1，“b”的排出通道(34)和重整气体供给通道(30)中的原料在燃气和蒸汽的混合物，所述换热部之间的性能(“B”)进行比较。选择附图中 : 图。1', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To reduce an amount of a reforming catalyst by reducing a temperature gradient between an upstream part and a downstream part of the reforming catalyst. SOLUTION :  An outside heat insulation material 41 is provided at a part (A part on the figure 1) adjacent to a reforming part 10 in a discharge flow passage 34. As an amount of conductive heat and radiant heat passing through the heat insulating material is suppressed by providing the outside heat insulation material 41,  a heat exchange performance between a reforming gas in the discharge flow passage 34 at A part and the reforming part 10 is reduced in comparison to a heat exchange performance (B part) between a reforming gas in the discharge flow passage 34 at B part on the figure 1 and a mixture gas of a raw material in a supply flow passage 30 and steam. SELECTED DRAWING :  Figure 1 COPYRIGHT :  (C)2016, JPO&INPIT', p.application_date = '2015-01-14 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP2016130194A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2015004687'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2015004687', p.title_cn = '氢气发生装置', p.title_en = 'HYDROGEN GENERATOR', p.abstract_cn = '所要解决的问题 : 本发明提供了可用于外取热器不产生氢气的高能效。溶液 : 原料供给至所述重整反应以产生重整气体的重整催化剂层3，至少一个所述原料与重整气体与燃烧空气和燃烧器6，发送，对燃烧器6燃烧的燃料和空气从发送，和燃烧室(11)，排出的燃烧废气，供应燃烧空气的燃烧器6的燃烧空气流路径，在燃烧废气从燃烧室(11)排出，热重整催化剂层(3)和燃烧废气流动路径，本发明提供燃烧废气流路，重整催化剂层包括对向的部分第一流路(1)的入口(15)，和使燃烧废气和燃烧用空气的热量交换，燃烧空气流道相邻设置，入口侧的重整催化剂层(3)的出口位置处设置。选择附图中 : 图。1', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To provide a hydrogen generator which can be used with high energy efficiency without providing a heat exchanger outside. SOLUTION :  There is provided a hydrogen generator which comprises a reforming catalyst layer 3 for generating a reformed gas by reforming reaction by supplying a raw material,  a burner 6 for feeding at least one of the raw material and the reformed gas and combustion air,  a combustion chamber 11 for burning a fuel and air fed from the burner 6 and discharging a combustion exhaust gas,  a combustion air flow passage for supplying combustion air to the burner 6 and combustion exhaust gas channels for discharging the combustion exhaust gas from the combustion chamber 11 and heating the reforming catalyst layer 3,  where a first channel 15 including a part facing an inlet of the reforming catalyst layer of the combustion exhaust gas channels is disposed adjacent to the combustion air flow passage so as to perform heat exchange between the combustion exhaust gas and the combustion air and disposed at the inlet side position from the outlet of the reforming catalyst layer 3. SELECTED DRAWING :  Figure 1 COPYRIGHT :  (C)2016, JPO&INPIT', p.application_date = '2015-01-14 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP2016130195A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2015004688'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2015004688', p.title_cn = '氢生成装置及燃料电池系统及其操作方法', p.title_en = 'HYDROGEN GENERATOR,  OPERATION METHOD OF THE SAME AND FUEL CELL SYSTEM', p.abstract_cn = '所要解决的问题 : 启动停止产生氢气的装置，以缩短处理时间，直到清洗完成。溶液 : 氢生成装置(100)，含烃原料气产生含有氢的重整气体的重整装置(1)，在重整器1供应原料气体供给装置(2)，正常停机处理，或者，它不同于正常停止处理和进行特殊处理，作为吹扫气体重整器1供应原料的氢生成装置(100)和控制装置(3)控制以停止，一种专用止动和输入的输入部(4)的外侧设置，所述控制单元(3)，在重整器1的正常停止的停止处理从净化开始到完成停止时间，特殊的处理和控制停止时间变短的问题。选择附图中 : 图。1', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To shorten the time from starting the stopping process of a hydrogen generator to the completion of purge. SOLUTION :  There is provided a hydrogen generator 100 which comprises a reformer 1 for reforming a hydrocarbon-containing raw material to generate a hydrocarbon-containing gas,  a raw material gas supplier 2 for supplying the raw material to the reformer 1,  a controller 3 which performs normal stop processing or special stop processing different from the normal stop processing and controls to stop the hydrogen generator 100 by supplying the raw material to the reformer 1 as a purge gas,  and an input part 4 for inputting from the outside to perform special stop processing,  wherein the controller 3 is configured to control so that the stopping time when performing special stop processing is shorter than the stopping time from starting stop processing when performing normal stop processing to the completion of purge of the reformer 1. SELECTED DRAWING :  Figure 1 COPYRIGHT :  (C)2016, JPO&INPIT', p.application_date = '2015-01-14 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP2016130196A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2015004690'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2015004690', p.title_cn = '一种氢氧发生器具有螺旋式波纹筒及其制造方法', p.title_en = 'SPIRAL WAVEFORM CYLINDER,  HYDROGEN GENERATION APPARATUS COMPRISING THE SAME,  AND PRODUCING METHOD THEREOF', p.abstract_cn = '所要解决的问题 : 一种制氢装置的流动路径中的蒸发器部分的切口很难发生，并且，不易出现故障。溶液 : 一种氢气发生器，应用于蒸发器中的螺旋波纹管(1)，在轴向方向的螺旋状向壁的机加工出凹槽，从而形成，在凸部的顶点部分2，以第一突起(2)的外周方向突出(4)，一种螺旋波纹管的内周面紧密接触处的外筒时间，第一突起(2)的至少一部分4被压坏，通过增加接触部分的表面压力，以及螺旋波纹管1可分配施加的应力。选择附图中 : 图。1', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To provide a hydrogen generation apparatus in which cut-off and destruction hardly occur at an attachment part of a flow path of an evaporator. SOLUTION :  There is provided a spiral waveform cylinder 1 for an evaporator of a hydrogen generation apparatus,  in which sidewall is machined so that the sidewall forms spiral uneven part directing to axis direction,  which comprises second projecting part 4 deformed so as to project in periphery direction at peak part of a projecting part 2,  surface pressure of attachment part is increased by squashing at least a part of the second projecting part 4 when the spiral waveform cylinder is attached to an inner peripheral surface of an outer syringe,  and stress on the spiral waveform cylinder 1 may be distributed. SELECTED DRAWING :  Figure 1 COPYRIGHT :  (C)2016, JPO&INPIT', p.application_date = '2015-01-14 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP2016130197A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'TR201314427'}) SET p.application_no = 'TR201314427', p.title_cn = '一种从海水或盐水中获取燃料的方法。', p.title_en = 'A method of obtaining fuel from seawater or salt water.', p.abstract_cn = '为了从水中产生能量; 生产单元(12)，其包含填充有海水或盐水的内部容积，并且其中通过在磁场前面放置障碍物来分解水，在所述生产单元(12)中加热海水或盐水，使得所述水分解。多个加热器(14)，; 向所述加热器(14)供给直流电的电源(13);  冷却由所述发电单元(12)中的加热器(14)加热的海水或盐; 它涉及一种系统(A)，该系统包括向生产单元(12)供应冷水的冷水单元(11)。', p.abstract_en = 'In order to produce energy from water;  A production unit (12),  which contains an interior volume filled with sea water or salt water and where the water is broken up by placing an obstacle in front of the magnetic field,  heating the sea water or salty water in the said production unit (12),  enabling the said water to break down. a multiple number of heaters (14);  a power source (13) feeding said heaters (14) with direct current;  to cool the sea water or salty water heated by the heaters (14) in said generation unit (12);  It relates to a system (A) comprising a cold water unit (11) supplying cold water to the production unit (12).', p.application_date = '2014-04-03 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'TR201314427B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US15003599'}) SET p.application_no = 'US15003599', p.title_cn = 'PFC溶液中储氢的新方法', p.title_en = 'Novel Methods for Storing Hydrogen in PFC Solutions', p.abstract_cn = '本发明描述了将固体和液体全氟化溶液用于储氢装置的新方法。', p.abstract_en = 'This invention describes novel methods for using solid and liquid perfluorinated solutions for hydrogen storage devices.', p.application_date = '2016-01-21 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US20160207764A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WOJP15006354'}) SET p.application_no = 'WOJP15006354', p.title_cn = '燃料重整器', p.title_en = 'FUEL REFORMER', p.abstract_cn = '该燃料重整器(100)使在蒸汽重整的燃料和水之间的反应在重整催化剂(111)，和具有燃料喷射单元(112)，用于将燃料供给到重整催化剂(111)，和喷射控制单元(123)，用于控制所喷射的燃料量的燃料喷射单元(112)。喷射控制单元(123)控制喷射量，使得温度的重整催化剂(111)不低于预先设定的规定温度。燃料重整器(100)上还设置有温度采集单元(121)，用于测量或估计温度重整催化剂(111)，和一目标值计算单元(122)，用于计算喷射量的目标值，使得温度重整催化剂的(111)注射后的燃料通过燃料喷射单元(112)是大于或等于预定的温度。燃料喷射单元(112)实行控制，使得喷射量与目标值一致。', p.abstract_en = 'This fuel reformer (100) brings about a steam reforming reaction between a fuel and water on a reforming catalyst (111),  and is provided with a fuel injection unit (112) for injecting fuel for supply to the reforming catalyst (111),  and an injection control unit (123) for controlling the amount of the fuel injected by the fuel injection unit (112). The injection control unit (123) controls the injection amount such that the temperature of the reforming catalyst (111) does not fall below a prescribed temperature set in advance. The fuel reformer (100) is further provided with a temperature acquisition unit (121) for measuring or estimating the temperature of the reforming catalyst (111),  and a target value calculation unit (122) for calculating a target value of the injection amount such that the temperature of the reforming catalyst (111) after injection of the fuel by the fuel injection unit (112) is greater than or equal to the prescribed temperature. The fuel injection unit (112) exercises control such that the injection amount coincides with the target value.', p.application_date = '2015-12-21 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016113811A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WOUS16013911'}) SET p.application_no = 'WOUS16013911', p.title_cn = '旋转的离心式颗粒分离器和具有其的气化炉', p.title_en = 'ROTATING CENTRIFUGAL PARTICLE SEPARATOR AND GASIFIER HAVING THE SAME', p.abstract_cn = '一种从气态物质中分离固体颗粒的方法，包括旋转旋转器绕旋转轴线在旋转方向。撒布器具有流体通道可操作地连接的气体进口环境气态出口环境。周向方向中延伸的流体通道相反的转动方向为径向向内延伸的流体通道。该方法还包括迫使沿径向向内气态物质通过旋转器通过建立压差，从而解决所述的气体进口环境的压力超过压力的气态流体出口。一种组件包括旋转器被配置成在旋转方向转动。撒布器具有流体通道可操作地连接的气体进口环境气态出口环境。加热元件位于相邻的撒布器的方式，使得颗粒甩从该旋转器撞击加热元件。', p.abstract_en = 'A method of separating solid particles from gaseous matter comprises rotating a spinner about a spinner axis in a rotational direction. The spinner has fluid passageways that operatively connect a gaseous inlet environment to a gaseous outlet environment. The fluid passageways circumferentially extending in a direction opposite the rotational direction as the fluid passageways extend radially inward. The method further comprises forcing gaseous matter radially inward through the rotating spinner by creating pressure differential that is such that the pressure of the gaseous inlet environment exceeds the pressure of the gaseous fluid outlet. An assembly comprises a spinner configured to rotate in a rotational direction. The spinner has fluid passageways that operatively connect a gaseous inlet environment to a gaseous outlet environment. A heating element is positioned adjacent to the spinner in a manner such that particles flung from the spinner can strike the heating element.', p.application_date = '2016-01-19 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016115568A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201610072892.5'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201610072892.5', p.title_cn = '火用泵式天然气改质系统', p.title_en = 'Exergy pump type natural gas modification system', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种火用泵式天然气改质系统，包括反应器(1)、加热器(2)、热管(3)，所述反应器(1)下部设置有天然气入口和热工质入口，所述热工质为二氧化碳或水蒸气，反应器(1)上部设置有热改质气出口，所述热管(3)的一部分设置在所述反应器(1)中，另一部分设置在加热器(2)中。本发明采用天然气与水蒸汽或二氧化碳等化学工质进行外热式改质反应，将低火用值热能提升为天然气改质气的高火用值化学能，本发明具有下述有益效果：(1)、天然气改质过程效率高，具有较高的节能效益。(2)、太阳能提升为燃气的化学能便于储存，既解决太阳能的储存问题，又解决了天然气的调峰问题。(3)、采用二氧化碳为化学工质，可达到减排二氧化碳的效果。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention discloses an exergy pump type natural gas modification system.The exergy pump type natural gas modification system comprises a reactor (1),  a heater (2) and a heat pipe (3).The lower portion of the reactor (1) is provided with a natural gas inlet and a hot working medium inlet,  wherein a hot working medium is carbon dioxide or water steam;  the upper portion of the reactor (1) is provided with a hot modified gas outlet.One part of the heat pipe (3) is arranged in the reactor (1),  and the other part of the heat pipe (3) is arranged in the heater (2).Natural gas and water steam or carbon oxide and other chemical working media are adopted for conducting an external heated modification reaction,  and low-exergy-value heat energy is improved into natural gas modified gas high-exergy-value chemical energy.The exergy pump type natural gas modification system has the advantages that the natural gas modification process efficiency is high,  and high energy-saving benefits are achieved;  solar energy is improved into gas chemical energy,  so that storage is convenient,  the storage problem of solar energy is solved,  and the peak pitching problem of natural gas is solved;  carbon dioxide is adopted as the chemical working medium,  and the effect of reducing carbon dioxide emission can be achieved.', p.application_date = '2016-02-02 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105776135A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/34', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201610087995.9'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201610087995.9', p.title_cn = '一种用液硫替换二硫化碳给CO变换催化剂补硫的方法', p.title_en = 'Method for supplementing sulfur to CO shift catalyst by replacing carbon disulfide with liquid sulfur', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种用液硫替换二硫化碳给CO变换催化剂补硫方法，在电石炉气制乙二醇的生产过程中，将硫回收工段生产的液硫输送到炉气变换工段的液硫储槽中，通过泵将液硫储槽中的液硫输送至脱毒塔入口，在脱毒塔中发生化学反应：H2+S====H2S，将脱毒塔中产生的H2S补入电石炉气的原料气中，使电石炉气中的H2S含量满足电石炉气变换和净化的工艺要求，避免了CO变换催化剂的反硫化，提高了电石炉气的变换效率和变换气的质量，降低了现场操作的危险因素。本发明设备少，工艺简单合理，易于实施，可广泛用于原料气缺硫的变换催化剂的生产。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a method for supplementing sulfur to a CO shift catalyst by replacing carbon disulfide with liquid sulfur.The method comprises the steps that in the production process of preparing ethylene glycol from calcium carbide furnace gas,  liquid sulfur produced in the sulfur recovery section is conveyed to a liquid sulfur storage tank of the furnace gas conversion section,  liquid sulfur in the liquid sulfur storage tank is conveyed to an inlet of a detoxification tower through a pump,  a chemical reaction is conducted in the detoxification tower (Please see the formula in the description.),  H2S produced in the detoxification tower is added to feed gas of the calcium carbide furnace gas,  the H2S content in the calcium carbide furnace gas meets the technology requirements of calcium carbide furnace gas conversion and purification,  desulfuration of the CO shift catalyst is avoided,  the conversion efficiency and the quality of converted gas of the calcium carbide furnace gas are improved,  and the risk factors on on-site operation are reduced.According to the method for supplementing sulfur to the CO shift catalyst by replacing carbon disulfide with liquid sulfur,  the number of devices is small,  the technology is simple,  reasonable and easy to implement,  and the method can be widely applied to production of the shift catalyst of which the feed gas lacks sulfur.', p.application_date = '2016-02-17 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105776137A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/50', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201610260408.1'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201610260408.1', p.title_cn = '一种合成气净化的方法', p.title_en = 'Method for purifying synthetic gas', p.abstract_cn = '本发明提供了一种合成气的净化方法，优先脱除硫，避免硫对后系统的催化剂造成毒害；使用的脱氧剂中含有特殊介质，不仅使用寿命长且脱氧效果极佳；设置了两个换热器，充分回收净化工艺中释放的热量，节能降耗。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention provides a method for purifying a synthetic gas. According to the method,  sulfur is preferentially removed,  so that a catalyst of a later system can be prevented from toxic damage caused by sulfur;  a used deoxidant contains special mediums,  so that not only is the service life long,  but also the deoxidation effect is very good;  due to arrangement of two heat exchangers,  heat released from a purification process can be sufficiently recycled,  and the purposes of energy saving and cost reduction can be achieved.', p.application_date = '2016-04-25 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105776138A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/50', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201620069034.0'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201620069034.0', p.title_cn = '一种转化炉用金属燃烧器', p.title_en = 'A metal burner used in conversion furnace', p.abstract_cn = '本实用新型公开了一种转化炉用金属燃烧器，包括金属壳体，壳体端头设有喷孔，在所述壳体轴线上由内及外依次设有氧气管、蒸汽管和冷却腔，蒸汽管外壁和壳体内壁构成冷却腔，氧气管的上端连接氧气入口，蒸汽管和位于壳体上端的蒸汽入口连通，氧气管和蒸汽管的下端位于壳体的喷孔位置处，在冷却腔内设有至少两个隔离板，所述隔离板将蒸汽管外壁和壳体外壁连接，将冷却腔分成至少两个分冷却腔，每个分冷却腔分别与冷却水进口或冷却水出口连通，在所述隔离板的下部设有用于供冷却水流通的缺口。本实用新型解决了冷却水流动性差，冷却效果差的问题，同时冷却腔内设有耐高温防腐涂料，避免燃烧器腐蚀，影响使用寿命，间接的降低经济成本。', p.abstract_en = 'The utility model discloses a metal burner used in conversion furnace,  which comprises a metal shell,  shell end is provided with a jet orifice,  the axis of the shell by the inner and the outer is provided with a hose,  and cooling cavity of the steam pipe,  the steam pipe a and the inner wall of the outer wall of the cooling cavity,  is connected with the upper end of an oxygen inlet,  a steam pipe and is located in the upper end of the casing is connected with the steam inlet,  an oxygen tube and the lower end of the steam pipe is located in position the spray hole of the shell,  the cooling cavity is provided with the at least two separation plate,  the separation plate and the outer wall of the steam pipe is connected with the outer wall of the shell,  the cooling chamber is divided into at least two sub-cooling chamber,  each of the sub-cooling chamber is respectively connected with the cooling water inlet or cooling water outlet is connected with the,  in the isolating plate is provided at the lower part of the cooling water circulation for the gap. The utility model solves the problem that the cooling water of poor fluidity,  the problem of poor cooling effect,  at the same time cooling cavity is provided with the high-temperature anti-corrosion coating,  to avoid corrosion of the burner,  to affect the service life,  indirect reduce the economic cost.', p.application_date = '2016-01-25 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN205387475U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201521106396.4'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201521106396.4', p.title_cn = '一种实现氯碱副产品中氢气有效利用的系统', p.title_en = 'Chlor-alkali by-products for realizing effective utilization of hydrogen in the system of the', p.abstract_cn = '本实用新型公开了一种实现氯碱副产品中氢气有效利用的系统，包括氢气洗涤塔、第一氢气压缩机、氢气冷却器、水雾捕沫器、往复式压缩机、氢气纯化装置、多晶硅尾气处理系统和多晶硅还原炉，氢气洗涤塔的出口和第一氢气压缩机的进口连接，第一氢气压缩机的出口和氢气冷却器的进口连接，氢气冷却器的出口和水雾捕沫器的进口连接，水雾捕沫器的出口和往复式压缩机的进口连接，往复式压缩机的出口与氢气纯化装置的进口连接，氢气纯化装置的出口与多晶硅还原炉的进口连接，多晶硅还原炉和与多晶硅尾气处理系统循环连接。本实用新型的系统主要针对烧碱用离子膜电解氢气的有效利用，避免氢气排空浪费，另外将烧碱副产品氢气用于多晶硅生产也可降低成本。', p.abstract_en = 'The utility model discloses a to realize effective utilization of hydrogen in the chlor-alkali by-product system,  include a hydrogen gas washing tower,  1st hydrogen compressor,  hydrogen cooler,  spray foam trap,  reciprocating compressor,  hydrogen purification apparatus,  the exhaust gas processing system and polycrystalline silicon polycrystalline silicon reduction furnace,  the outlet of the hydrogen gas washing tower and 1st is connected with the inlet of the hydrogen compressor,  hydrogen 1st and the outlet port of the compressor is connected with the inlet of hydrogen cooler,  the outlet of the hydrogen cooler is connected with the inlet of foam trap and the water fog,  foam trap and the outlet opening of the water mist is connected with the inlet of a reciprocating compressor,  the reciprocating compressor is connected with the inlet of the hydrogen purification device,  the outlet of the hydrogen purification apparatus is connected with the inlet of the reducing furnace of polycrystalline silicon,  polycrystalline silicon polycrystalline silicon reduction furnace and the circulating connection of the exhaust gas processing system. The system of the utility model is directed primarily to the caustic soda for effective utilization of ion-exchange membrane electrolytic hydrogen,  hydrogen emptying waste is avoided,  in addition,  the caustic soda spinoffs hydrogen used for polysilicon production also the cost can be reduced.', p.application_date = '2015-12-25 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN205387476U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/50', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'DE502004015256'}) SET p.application_no = 'DE502004015256', p.title_cn = '储氢装置', p.title_en = 'APPARATUS FOR HYDROGEN STORAGE', p.abstract_cn = '氢存储架，包括一个密封的压力容器(2)内填充有金属氢化物的氢可透膜盒(6)中(5)。这些焊接在一起，至少在朝向容器的侧壁。', p.abstract_en = 'Hydrogen store comprises a sealed pressure vessel (2) filled with metal hydride (6) in hydrogen-permeable cassettes (5). These are welded together,  at least on the sides facing the vessel walls.', p.application_date = '2004-02-16 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'DE502004015256T2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'EP04003367'}) SET p.application_no = 'EP04003367', p.title_cn = '储氢装置', p.title_en = 'APPARATUS FOR HYDROGEN STORAGE', p.abstract_cn = '氢存储架，包括一个密封的压力容器(2)内填充有金属氢化物的氢可透膜盒(6)中(5)。这些焊接在一起，至少在朝向容器的侧壁。', p.abstract_en = 'Hydrogen store comprises a sealed pressure vessel (2) filled with metal hydride (6) in hydrogen-permeable cassettes (5). These are welded together,  at least on the sides facing the vessel walls.', p.application_date = '2004-02-16 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'EP1454876B1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 2, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'EP13867894'}) SET p.application_no = 'EP13867894', p.title_cn = '氢气产生装置和燃料电池系统', p.title_en = 'HYDROGEN GENERATION DEVICE AND FUEL CELL SYSTEM', p.abstract_cn = '一种氢气发生器(100)包括 : 重整器(1)被配置成生成含氢气体的原料气体；加氢脱硫器(2)配置成去除原料中的硫化合物气体；再循环通道(3)，通过含氢气体的原料气体之前供给原料原料气进入加氢脱硫器(2)；喷射器(5)，其设置在原料气通道的上游侧的加氢脱硫器(2)，其中含氢气体从再循环通道(3)；和加热器(6)配置成加热喷射器(5)。', p.abstract_en = 'A hydrogen generator (100) includes :  a reformer (1) configured to generate a hydrogen-containing gas by using a raw material gas;  a hydro-desulfurizer (2) configured to remove a sulfur compound in the raw material gas;  a recycle passage (3) through which the hydrogen-containing gas is supplied to the raw material gas before the raw material gas flows into the hydro-desulfurizer (2);  an ejector (5) which is disposed on a raw material gas passage provided upstream of the hydro-desulfurizer (2) and into which the hydrogen-containing gas flows from the recycle passage (3);  and a heater (6) configured to heat the ejector (5).', p.application_date = '2013-10-09 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'EP2813466B1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'EP13873870'}) SET p.application_no = 'EP13873870', p.title_cn = '用于产生氢的方法与铝反应的装置', p.title_en = 'METHOD FOR GENERATING HYDROGEN BY MEANS OF REACTION WITH ALUMINIUM', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种用于产生氢气的方法通过一个与铝反应，基于与水反应的铝的氢氧化物溶液，包括添加的醇为溶剂的溶液。所述的醇具有较低的密度，较高气化温度和反应性较低，优选异丙醇，乙醇或生物乙醇，反应器第一填充铝和，随后，加入酒精使反应器完全充满。部分的醇然后，排空，使得它仅覆盖铝，与其余的空间被放空，将氢氧化物溶液然后被计量加入根据所述的氢气需求量。产生的氢气和醇的蒸气的热交换器中蒸馏。蒸馏出的酒精返回到反应器和氢气过滤和存储。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a method for generating hydrogen by means of a reaction with aluminium,  based on reacting aluminium with water in a hydroxide solution,  comprising the addition of alcohol as a solvent to the solution. The alcohol is of the type having a lower density,  higher vaporisation temperature and lower reactivity,  preferably isopropanol,  ethanol or bioethanol. The reactor is first filled with aluminium and,  subsequently,  the alcohol is added so that the the reactor is completely full. Part of the alcohol is then emptied such that it only covers the aluminium,  with the rest of the space being emptied,  The hydroxide solution is then metered according to the hydrogen demand. The hydrogen and the alcohol vapour generated are distilled in an exchanger. The distilled alcohol is returned to the reactor and the hydrogen is filtered and stored.', p.application_date = '2013-02-01 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'EP2952473A4', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/08', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2015069270'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2015069270', p.title_cn = '钠硅化物和钠硅胶材料用于氢产生的系统和方法', p.title_en = 'sodium silicide and sodium silica gel material is used for the hydrogen generating system and method', p.abstract_cn = '系统，装置和方法将反应物材料和水溶液产生氢气。所述反应物材料可为钠硅化物或钠硅胶。用于燃料电池的氢生成装置和其它工业应用。一种系统结合冷却，泵浦，储水和其它装置来感测和控制反应物材料和水溶液之间的反应产生氢气。不同布置几何形状的多个入口将水溶液输送到反应中。所述反应物材料和水溶液搅拌成控制反应状态。该水溶液可以回收并返回到反应中。一个系统则是在温度和压力范围内并且包括氢气分离装置；一种排热机构，和反应状态控制装置。本发明的系统，装置，产生氢气的方法提供了热稳定固体，与水溶液的近即时反应以及无毒液体副产物。', p.abstract_en = 'Systems,  devices,  and methods combine reactant materials and aqueous solutions to generate hydrogen. The reactant materials can be sodium silicide or sodium silica gel. The hydrogen generation devices are used in fuels cells and other industrial applications. One system combines cooling,  pumping,  water storage,  and other devices to sense and control reactions between reactant materials and aqueous solutions to generate hydrogen. Multiple inlets of varied placement geometries deliver aqueous solution to the reaction. The reactant materials and aqueous solution are churned to control the state of the reaction. The aqueous solution can be recycled and returned to the reaction. One system operates over a range of temperatures and pressures and includes a hydrogen separator,  a heat removal mechanism,  and state of reaction control devices. The systems,  devices,  and methods of generating hydrogen provide thermally stable solids,  near-instant reaction with the aqueous solutions,  and a non-toxic liquid by-product.', p.application_date = '2015-03-30 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP5953392B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/06', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2014555111'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2014555111', p.title_cn = '由于使用离子液体储氢', p.title_en = 'Because of the use of ionic liquid hydrogen storage', p.abstract_cn = '第一储氢的形成方法通过引入硼化物)在第二离子液体的离子液体阳离子和阴离子包括硼酸，形成第二从第一中释放氢离子液体离子液体用水和/或催化剂，该方法的特征在于，第一和第二的离子液体均与水混溶的第二离子液体分离，特别是进行盐析，分离诱导剂加入水中形成溶液；某些离子液体用于存储和释放氢的包括硼氢化物或用于制备一种用于存储和离子液体释放氢的含有硼酸盐；和用于存储氢和释放氢离子液体的制备方法包括硼氢化物。', p.abstract_en = 'Method of storing hydrogen by forming a first ionic liquid by inducing a borohydride in a second ionic liquid comprising a cation and an anion comprising borate,  and forming the second ionic liquid by releasing the hydrogen out of the first ionic liquid by using water and/or a catalyst,  which method is characterized in that the first and the second ionic liquid are both water miscible and the second ionic liquid is separated,  particularly is salted out,  from solution in water by adding a separation inducer;  certain ionic liquids for storing and releasing hydrogen comprising a borohydride or for preparing a ionic liquid for storing and releasing hydrogen comprising a borate;  and a process for preparing ionic liquids for storing and releasing hydrogen comprising a borohydride.', p.application_date = '2012-12-20 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP5953620B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'RU2013126499'}) SET p.application_no = 'RU2013126499', p.title_cn = '方法和用于生产乙炔和合成气的装置', p.title_en = 'METHOD AND DEVICE FOR PRODUCING ACETYLENE AND SYNTHESIS GAS', p.abstract_cn = '领域 : 化学物质 : 本发明涉及一种改进的生产乙炔和合成气的方法。本发明的方法生产乙炔和合成气的部分氧化烃与氧气，所述初始气体，进入含烃，和含氧流，第一，初步分别加热，然后在混合区，流经燃烧器使它们反应后燃烧室中，然后快速冷却。此时，以块燃烧器表面面向燃烧室的流洗涤气体流加入，该洗涤气体引入通过若干个孔通过燃烧器单元，所述有效区域的平均比燃烧器表面的单元数目的这些孔供气体冲洗流量在燃烧器为从5至100cm2，其中，平均燃烧器单元的有效面比这些数量的孔供气体燃烧器的冲洗液流量从比计算总有效表面的单元燃烧器的总气体冲洗的孔的数量和用于洗涤流程进行通孔使70-100体积%的气体分布装置供给的洗涤气流定向为平行于燃烧器单元侧朝向燃烧室的表面。效果 : 本发明允许产生合成气体与乙炔使用改进的烃的部分氧化的方法，防止沉积在表面的单元的燃烧器不需要使用机械treatment.7Cl，4的DWG，3EX', p.abstract_en = 'FIELD :  chemistry. SUBSTANCE :  invention relates to improved method of producing acetylene and synthetic gas. Disclosed is method of producing acetylene and synthetic gas by partial oxidation of hydrocarbons with oxygen,  wherein initial gases,  which enter stream containing hydrocarbon,  and flow containing oxygen,  first,  preliminary heated separately,  then mixed in mixing zone,  and after flowing via burners cause their reaction in combustion chamber,  then quickly cooled. At that,  to block of burners surface facing combustion chamber stream of washing gas flow is added. this washing gas is introduced via several holes through burner unit,  wherein averaged ratio of effective area of unit of burners surface to number of these holes for gas flushing flow in burners ranges from 5 to 100 cm2,  wherein averaged ratio of unit of burners effective surface to number of these holes for gas flushing flow in burners is calculated from ratio of total effective surface of unit of burners to total number of holes for gas flushing and carried out through holes for washing flow to gas distributing devices so that 70-100 vol% of supplied washing gas flow is directed parallel to surface of burners unit side facing combustion chamber. EFFECT :  invention allows to produce synthesis gas and acetylene using improved method of partial oxidation of hydrocarbons,  which prevents deposits on surface of unit of burners without using mechanical treatment. 7 cl,  4 dwg,  3 ex', p.application_date = '2011-10-27 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'RU2591940C2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/36', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'DE602009039111'}) SET p.application_no = 'DE602009039111', p.title_cn = '从天然气生产液态烃的方法', p.title_en = 'PROCESS FOR PRODUCING LIQUID HYDROCARBONS FROM NATURAL GAS', p.abstract_cn = '在所谓的GTL从天然气生产合成气的方法，生产费-托合成油通过费-托合成得到的合成气和含生产液态烃的燃料通过升级油，从合成气生产合成气生产步骤被部分地分支之前关闭取至费-托法油生产步骤和合成气进入分支线进行水煤气变换反应，提高氢的浓度。随后，高纯度氢气从合成气体隔离和隔离后留下的残余气体循环合成气生产步骤和作为用于合成气生产的原料。作为结果，显著的改进，可以实现在每产品的原料消耗的整个过程。', p.abstract_en = 'In a so-called GTL process of producing synthesis gas from natural gas,  producing Fischer-Tropsch oil by way of Fischer-Tropsch synthesis of the obtained synthesis gas and producing liquid hydrocarbons containing fuel oil by upgrading,  the synthesis gas produced from the synthesis gas production step is partly branched off prior to getting to the Fischer-Tropsch oil production step and the synthesis gas entering the branch line is subjected to a water gas shift reaction to raise the hydrogen concentration thereof. Subsequently,  high-purity hydrogen is isolated from the synthesis gas and the residual gas left after the isolation is circulated to the synthesis gas production step and used as raw material for synthesis gas production. As a result,  a significant improvement can be achieved in terms of raw material consumption per product of the entire process.', p.application_date = '2009-03-11 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'DE602009039111T2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'DE602013060790'}) SET p.application_no = 'DE602013060790', p.title_cn = '用于由氧化原料制氢的催化剂', p.title_en = 'CATALYSTS FOR HYDROGEN PRODUCTION FROM OXYGENATED FEEDSTOCKS', p.abstract_cn = '一种蒸汽重整的方法，其中发生一种反应，在该反应中，氧化进料与催化剂接触以产生氢气。 该反应的催化剂包括负载在高能晶格金属氧化物上的镍/过渡金属共混物催化剂上的金属/金属促进剂。', p.abstract_en = 'A method of steam reforming where a reaction occurs in which an oxygenated feed contacts a catalyst to produce hydrogen. The catalyst of the reaction comprises a metal/metal promoter on a nickel/transition metal blend catalyst supported on a high-energy lattice metal oxide.', p.application_date = '2013-11-05 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'DE602013060790T2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/36', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14149740'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14149740', p.title_cn = '用于收集碳氢化合物沉积物气体水合物转化系统', p.title_en = 'Gas hydrate conversion system for harvesting hydrocarbon hydrate deposits', p.abstract_cn = '在一个实施例中，提供了一种气体水合物转化系统，该系统包括浮式工厂、用于从海洋水合物沉积物中收集气体水合物的附件、以及一个或多个存储罐。 浮动工厂包括一个或多个热交换组件、一个或多个热泵组件和发动机。 在另一个实施方案中，提供了一种用于收集碳氢化合物沉积物的方法，该方法包括提供气体水合物转化系统； 诱导海洋水合物沉积物释放甲烷； 从初级甲烷捕获区和/或次级甲烷捕获区捕获甲烷； 并将甲烷转化为氢和碳。', p.abstract_en = 'In one embodiment,  a gas hydrate conversion system is provided comprising a floating factory,  an appendage for harvesting a gas hydrate from an oceanic hydrate deposit,  and one or more storage tanks. The floating factory comprises one or more heat exchange assemblies,  one or more heat pump assemblies and an engine. In another embodiment,  a method for harvesting hydrocarbon hydrate deposits is provided,  the method comprising providing a gas hydrate conversion system;  inducing release of methane from an oceanic hydrate deposit;  capturing the methane from a primary methane capture zone and/or a secondary methane capture zone;  and converting the methane to hydrogen and carbon.', p.application_date = '2014-01-07 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9394169B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/24', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 7, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14205864'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14205864', p.title_cn = '装有热交换器的反应器', p.title_en = 'Reactor incorporating a heat exchanger', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种包含热交换器的反应器，所述热交换器可以以并流或逆流流操作。 还公开了一种系统，其包括具有重整器和蒸发器的反应器、燃料供应器和供水器。 反应器包括燃烧气体源、操作用于接收重整产物的重整器和操作用于接收水的蒸发器。 重整器和汽化器各自包括由分离器垫片和通道垫片的组合形成的叠层组件。 分隔垫片和通道垫片以规则图案堆叠，以在堆叠组件内形成两组通道。 一组通道将在任一端具有竖直通道且在它们之间具有水平流动路径，而另一组通道仅具有水平流动路径。', p.abstract_en = 'A reactor containing a heat exchanger is disclosed,  which can be operated with co-current or counter-current flow. Also disclosed is a system that includes a reactor having a reformer and a vaporizer,  a fuel supply,  and a water supply. The reactor includes a source of combustion gas,  a reformer operative to receive reformate,  and a vaporizer operative to receive water. The reformer and vaporizer each include a stack assembly formed by a combination of separator shims and channel shims. The separator shims and channel shims are stacked in a regular pattern to form two sets of channels within the stack assembly. One set of channels will have vertical passageways at either end and a horizontal flowpath between them,  while the other set of channels has only a horizontal flowpath.', p.application_date = '2014-03-12 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9394170B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/26', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14589757'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14589757', p.title_cn = '具有用于生产氢基燃料和结构元件压力和传热特征的反应器容器以及相关系统和方法', p.title_en = 'Reactor vessels with pressure and heat transfer features for producing hydrogen-based fuels and structural elements,  and associated systems and methods', p.abstract_cn = '具有用于生产氢基燃料和结构元件的压力和传热特征的反应器容器，以及相关的系统和方法。 典型的反应器系统包括第一反应区和热路径、联接到第一反应区的反应物源、以及联接到第一致动器以对第一反应区循环加压的第一致动器。 第二反应区与第一反应区流体连通，阀连接在第一和第二反应区之间以控制第一和第二反应区之间的流速，第二致动器连接在第二反应区流体连通以对第二反应区循环加压。 第一和第二热交换器将热量从产物引导到反应区中的反应物。 控制器至少部分地基于来自第二反应区的第二产物的流速以协调的方式控制第一和第二致动器。', p.abstract_en = 'Reactor vessels with pressure and heat transfer features for producing hydrogen-based fuels and structural elements,  and associated systems and methods. A representative reactor system includes a first reaction zone and a heat path,  a reactant source coupled to the first reaction zone,  and a first actuator coupled to cyclically pressurize the first reaction zone. A second reaction zone is in fluid communication with the first,  a valve is coupled between the first and second reaction zones to control a flow rate therebetween,  and a second actuator is coupled in fluid communication with the second reaction zone to cyclically pressurize the second reaction zone. First and second heat exchangers direct heat from products to reactants in the reaction zones. A controller controls the first and second actuators in a coordinated manner based at least in part on a flow rate of the second product from the second reaction zone.', p.application_date = '2015-01-05 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9395081B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 7, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'KR1020157033393'}) SET p.application_no = 'KR1020157033393', p.title_cn = '催化剂将氢气与氨硼烷的生产方法', p.title_en = 'CATALYST AND PROCESS FOR THE PRODUCTION OF HYDROGEN FROM AMMONIA BORANES', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种氢的生产方法包括使至少一种配合物配方(Ⅰ)，(Ⅰ)其中 : X？是阴离子；M是金属，其选自Ru，Os，Fe，Co和Ni组成；D是任选存在的一种或多种单齿或多齿给体配位体；Y1选自CR13，B和N；═Z1和Z2各自独立地选自N，P═，nr14，pr15，O，S和Se；Z2各自独立地为直接键或碳环B和R4之间；每个A和B独立地为饱和的，不饱和或部分不饱和碳环烃环；R3和R4各自独立地选自H，C1-6-烷基，芳基，C1-6卤代烷基，和连接基团任选地附着于固体支持物；或R3和R4一起形成以下部分 : (ab)Y2是一个直接单键或双键，或者cr18；R1，R2，r5-13和r16-18各自独立地选自H，C1-6-烷基，C2-6链烯基，C2-6炔基，芳基，C1-6卤代烷基，nr19r20和连接基团任选地附着于固体支持物；或两个或多个所述r1-13和r16-18相连，与它们所连接的碳一起，以形成饱和或不饱和烃基；R14，R15，R19和R20各自独立地选自H，C1-6-烷基，C2-6链烯基，C2-6炔基，芳基，C1-6卤代烷基，和任选的连接基附着于固体支持物；与式(Ⅱ)的至少一个基板，r21r22nh-bhr23r24，R21~R24各自独立地选自H，C1-6-烷基，氟取代的C1-6-烷基，c6-14c6-14-芳基和芳烷基，R21或任意两种，R22，R23和R24)连接形成的C3-10亚烷基或C3-10亚链烯基，和/或硼原子与氮一起与它们所连接的呈环状基团；或基板包括两个，式(Ⅱ)的三个或四个基片通过其一个或多个桥接基团以形成二聚体，三聚体或四聚体物质，和其中所述桥接基团选自直链或支链的C1-6亚烷基任选地被一个或多个氟代基，硼，c6-14c6-14-芳基和芳烷基；或基板包括两个，式(Ⅱ)的三个或四个基材结合在一起以形成稠合的环状二聚体，三聚体或四聚体物质。本发明的另一个方面涉及一种氢气发生系统包括式(I)的配合物，式(Ⅱ)的基板和溶剂，并涉及使用式(I)的络合物的燃料电池。本发明的另一个方面涉及式(I)的新配合物。', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention relates to a process for the production of hydrogen comprising contacting at least one complex of formula (I),  (I) wherein :  X− is an anion;  M is a metal selected from Ru,  Os,  Fe,  Co and Ni;  D is optionally present and is one or more monodentate or multidentate donor ligands;  Y1 is selected from CR13,  B and N;  Z1 and Z2 are each independently selected from ═N,  ═P,  NR14,  PR15,  O,  S and Se;  or Z2 is a direct bond between carbocyclic ring B and substituent R4;  each of A and B is independently a saturated,  unsaturated or partially unsaturated carbocyclic hydrocarbon ring;  R3 and R4 are each independently selected from H,  C1-6-alkyl,  aryl and C1-6-haloalkyl,  and a linker group optionally attached to a solid support;  or R3 and R4 together form the following moiety :  (AB) Y2 is a direct single bond or double bond,  or is CR18;  R1,  R2,  R5-13 and R16-18 are each independently selected from H,  C1-6-alkyl,  C2-6-alkenyl,  C2-6-alkynyl,  aryl,  C1-6-haloalkyl,  NR19R20 and a linker group optionally attached to a solid support;  or two or more of said R1-13 and R16-18 groups are linked,  together with the carbons to which they are attached,  to form a saturated or unsaturated hydrocarbon group;  R14,  R15,  R19 and R20 are each independently selected from H,  C1-6-alkyl,  C2-6-alkenyl,  C2-6-alkynyl,  aryl,  C1-6-haloalkyl,  and a linker group optionally attached to a solid support;  with at least one substrate of formula (II),  R21R22NH—BHR23R24,  wherein R21 to R24 are each independently selected from H,  C1-6-alkyl,  fluoro-substituted C1-6-alkyl,  C6-14-aryl and C6-14-aralkyl,  or any two of R21,  R22,  R23 and R24 are linked to form a C3-10-alkylene group or C3-10-alkenylene group,  which together with the nitrogen and/or boron atoms to which they are attached,  forms a cyclic group;  or a substrate comprising two,  three or four substrates of formula (II) linked via one or more bridging groups so as to form a dimeric,  trim', p.application_date = '2014-04-23 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'KR1020160085701A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'NO20050326'}) SET p.application_no = 'NO20050326', p.title_cn = '托克斯夫林改造', p.title_en = 'Trykksvingsreformering', p.abstract_cn = '产生的合成气通过循环第一的方法，其中所述循环包括重整烃进料的步骤合成气在催化剂床的第一区和第二步骤中加热该第一区域。烃原料引入到床随CO2和任选的蒸汽在那里被重整为合成燃气。合成在床的第二区的气体进行收集和含氧气体被引入该床的第二区与燃料燃烧，从而将第一区再加热至足够的重整温度。此外，一种非燃烧气体也可以从第二引入第二区域移动的热区第一区。', p.abstract_en = 'Synthesis gas is produced though a cyclic method where the first step of the cycle includes reforming a hydrocarbon feed over a catalyst to synthesis gas in a first zone of a bed and the second step reheats this first zone. A hydrocarbon feed is introduced to a bed along with CO2 and optionally steam where it is reformed into synthesis gas. The synthesis gas is collected at a second zone of the bed and an oxygen-containing gas is then introduced to this second zone of the bed and combusted with a fuel,  thereby reheating the first zone to sufficient reforming temperatures. Additionally,  a non-combusting gas can also be introduced to the second zone to move heat from the second zone to the first zone.', p.application_date = '2005-01-20 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'NO338007B1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CA2878187'}) SET p.application_no = 'CA2878187', p.title_cn = '自调节氢气发生器', p.title_en = 'SELF REGULATING HYDROGEN GENERATOR', p.abstract_cn = '产生氢气的装置从可更换的铝的包装，它由铝和氢化混合物装入透气膜为升高和降低成的封闭水箱内所含流体接触与流体释放氢气的气体从铝。压力传感器和微处理器芯片提供了用于监测和调节氢气生产的速率通过接合和可逆电机离合升高和降低了铝包内托盘，托盘上驻留。', p.abstract_en = 'An apparatus for generating hydrogen gas from a replaceable aluminum pack comprising an aluminum and hydride mixture encased in a breathable membrane that is raised and lowered into a fluid contained within an enclosed tank wherein contact with the fluid releases hydrogen gas from the aluminum. A pressure transducer and microprocessor chip are provided for monitoring and regulating the rate of hydrogen production by engaging and disengaging a reversible motor that raises and lowers an inner tray on which the aluminum pack resides accordingly.', p.application_date = '2015-01-16 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CA2878187A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/08', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'ATE805089'}) SET p.application_no = 'ATE805089', p.title_cn = '从天然气生产液态烃的方法', p.title_en = 'PROCESS FOR PRODUCING LIQUID HYDROCARBONS FROM NATURAL GAS', p.abstract_cn = '在所谓的GTL从天然气生产合成气的方法，生产费-托合成油通过费-托合成得到的合成气和含生产液态烃的燃料通过升级油，从合成气生产合成气生产步骤被部分地分支之前关闭取至费-托法油生产步骤和合成气进入分支线进行水煤气变换反应，提高氢的浓度。随后，高纯度氢气从合成气体隔离和隔离后留下的残余气体循环合成气生产步骤和作为用于合成气生产的原料。作为结果，显著的改进，可以实现在每产品的原料消耗的整个过程。', p.abstract_en = 'In a so-called GTL process of producing synthesis gas from natural gas,  producing Fischer-Tropsch oil by way of Fischer-Tropsch synthesis of the obtained synthesis gas and producing liquid hydrocarbons containing fuel oil by upgrading,  the synthesis gas produced from the synthesis gas production step is partly branched off prior to getting to the Fischer-Tropsch oil production step and the synthesis gas entering the branch line is subjected to a water gas shift reaction to raise the hydrogen concentration thereof. Subsequently,  high-purity hydrogen is isolated from the synthesis gas and the residual gas left after the isolation is circulated to the synthesis gas production step and used as raw material for synthesis gas production. As a result,  a significant improvement can be achieved in terms of raw material consumption per product of the entire process.', p.application_date = '2009-03-11 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'ATE805089T1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'ATE805090'}) SET p.application_no = 'ATE805090', p.title_cn = '双流化床气化的系统和方法', p.title_en = 'SYSTEM AND METHOD FOR DUAL FLUIDIZED BED GASIFICATION', p.abstract_cn = '合成气深度脱硫的方法，包括将含碳材料和任选的蒸气到气化器中包括热传递介质，提取第一传热流包括传热介质和任选地未转化含碳材料从气化炉，和将至少一部分第一传热流至燃烧器，通入氧化剂，和任选的燃料到燃烧器中，提取第二传热流包括来自燃烧器的热传递介质，和将至少第二传热流的一部分进入气化器，可引入复合物与硫反应生成硫酸盐，硫化物或两个，提取净化流包含灰分，硫酸，卤化物，或其组合从第二传热流，提取烟气从燃烧器，和提取气化器的合成气产品流包括从气化炉出来的小于1000的硫。', p.abstract_en = 'A method for continuous dry reforming,  the method comprising :  introducing a feed comprising carbon dioxide and at least one selected from methane and propane into a fluid bed conditioner operated at a conditioning temperature,  wherein the fluid bed conditioner is one fluid bed of a dual fluidized bed loop and is configured to convert at least a portion of said feed into synthesis gas components;  extracting a first catalytic heat transfer stream comprising a catalytic heat transfer material and having a first temperature from the fluid bed conditioner and introducing at least a portion of the first catalytic heat transfer stream and a flue gas into a fluid bed combustor,  wherein the fluid bed combustor is configured to regenerate the catalyst via combustion;  extracting a second catalytic heat transfer stream comprising catalytic heat transfer material and having a second temperature from the fluid bed combustor and introducing at least a portion of the second catalytic heat transfer stream into the fluid bed conditioner;  and extracting synthesis gas from the fluid bed conditioner.', p.application_date = '2010-01-21 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'ATE805090T1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/44', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'ATE808945'}) SET p.application_no = 'ATE808945', p.title_cn = '从天然气中液态烃的制造方法', p.title_en = 'PROCESS FOR PRODUCING LIQUID HYDROCARBON FROM NATURAL GAS', p.abstract_cn = '在所谓的GTL生产液态烃的方法从天然气生产合成气的含有燃料油，随后从所得到的费-托合成油生产合成气通过费-托合成产生的费-托合成油的升级，从合成气制造工序中产生的合成气的开始阶段被部分地分支之前对费-托合成油品的生产步骤和高纯氢分离产生的合成气进入分支管路。所有被分离出来的高纯度的氢被供给到改质反应步骤和消耗的氢气的改质反应。此外，合成气进入分支线路进行水煤气变换反应的氢气浓度，之后分离生产高纯氢的步骤分离后留下的残余气体可以循环至合成气为原料生产合成气的生产工序。', p.abstract_en = 'In a so-called GTL process for producing liquid hydrocarbons containing fuel oil by producing synthesis gas from natural gas,  subsequently producing Fischer-Tropsch oil from the obtained synthesis gas by way of Fischer-Tropsch synthesis and upgrading the produced Fischer-Tropsch oil,  the synthesis gas produced from a synthesis gas production step is partly branched at a stage prior to getting to a Fischer-Tropsch oil production step and high-purity hydrogen is separated and produced from the synthesis gas entering the branch line. All the separated high-purity hydrogen is supplied to an upgrading reaction step and consumed as hydrogen for an upgrading reaction. Additionally,  the synthesis gas entering the branch line is subjected to a water gas shift reaction to raise the hydrogen concentration before the step of separating and producing high-purity hydrogen and the residual gas left after the separation may be circulated to the synthesis gas production step as raw material for producing synthesis gas.', p.application_date = '2009-03-25 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'ATE808945T1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'ATE810564'}) SET p.application_no = 'ATE810564', p.title_cn = '氢气纯化方法和系统', p.title_en = 'HYDROGEN PURIFICATION PROCESS AND SYSTEM', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种氢气发生系统，其包括燃料重整反应器产生富氢的重整气体的温度大于150℃，一种变压吸附(PSA)将重整气体中的氢精制装置成较纯的氢气流和一种废气流中，所述变压吸附单元，催化反应器的下游，其将含一氧化碳(CO)和氢气(H2)中相对纯的氢气物流转变成甲烷(CH4)和水蒸汽(H2O)。所述净化方法包括 : 产生富氢重整气中，在温度大于150℃燃料重整反应器，重整气体中分离成较纯的氢气流和废气流中的压力摆动吸附(psa)的氢精制装置，转换中所含一氧化碳(CO)和氢气(H2)的相对纯的氢气物流转变成甲烷(CH4)和水蒸汽(H2O)催化反应器中PSA装置的下游。所述氢可进一步纯化包括二次净化段下游的变压吸附装置和催化所述二次净化反应器级具有被水吸附材料吸附床的水汽H2O和氢吸收材料下游的优先吸水材料的吸氢气体，从而浓缩所述非氢气组分，例如CH4，进入排气流排出该层，所述吸收氢气再解吸出来以创建出非常纯的氢气流。', p.abstract_en = 'A hydrogen generation system is disclosed that includes a fuel reforming reactor generating a hydrogen-rich reformate gas at a temperature greater than 150 C,  a pressure swing adsorption (PSA) hydrogen purification unit that separates the reformate gas into a relatively pure hydrogen stream and an off-gas stream,  and a catalytic reactor down stream of the PSA unit that converts carbon monoxide (CO) and hydrogen (H2) contained in the relatively pure hydrogen stream into methane (CH4) and water vapor (H2O). The method of purification involves generating a hydrogen-rich reformate gas at a temperature greater than 150 C in a fuel reforming reactor,  separating the reformate gas into a relatively pure hydrogen stream and an off-gas stream in a pressure swing adsorption (PSA) hydrogen purification unit,  and converting carbon monoxide (CO) and hydrogen (H2) contained in the relatively pure hydrogen stream into methane (CH4) and water vapor (H2O) in a catalytic reactor down stream of the PSA unit. The hydrogen can be further purified by including a secondary purification stage downstream of the PSA unit and the catalytic reactor wherein the secondary purification stage has a water adsorbent material bed that adsorbs the water vapor H2O and a hydrogen absorbent material downstream of the water absorbent material that absorbs hydrogen gas preferentially,  thus concentrating the non-hydrogen components,  such as CH4,  into an exhaust stream that exits the bed,  wherein the absorbed hydrogen gas is then desorbed to create an exiting very pure hydrogen stream.', p.application_date = '2006-09-28 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'ATE810564T1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/34', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'ATE810565'}) SET p.application_no = 'ATE810565', p.title_cn = '用于生产氢的方法与共同生产和捕获二氧化碳', p.title_en = 'A PROCESS FOR THE PRODUCTION OF HYDROGEN WITH CO-PRODUCTION AND CAPTURE OF CARBON DIOXIDE', p.abstract_cn = '用于生产氢的方法和捕获二氧化碳的联产，其中，该方法包括蒸汽甲烷重整烃进料在燃烧的燃料和存在下维持(i)中使用蒸汽甲烷重整器单元，其包括蒸汽甲烷重整装置(SMR)，和(ii)水煤气变换单元，从而导致生产包括氢气和二氧化碳的重整气体流，和燃烧产物流。该方法包括以下步骤 : (a)分离和除去大部分或全部的氢的重整气体流；和然后(b)将回收的大部分或所有二氧化碳作为单独的缩合副产物流液态二氧化碳从气体物流；然后，(c)回收剩余气体从气体通过混合这些流的SMR进料气体流。主要使用的燃料氢气，例如，可以含有95摩尔%或更多的氢气的燃料进行测定以干基计。大于85%，通常大于99%，所述含碳进料流中的二氧化碳的回收处理和输出。', p.abstract_en = 'A process for the production of hydrogen with the co-production and capture of carbon dioxide,  wherein the process comprises steam methane reforming a hydrocarbon feedstock in the presence of a fuel and a combustion sustaining medium using (i) a steam methane reformer unit that comprises a steam methane reformer (SMR),  and (ii) a water gas shift unit,  so as to result in the production of a reformed gas stream comprising hydrogen and carbon dioxide,  and a combustion products stream. The process comprises the steps of :  (a) separating and removing most or all of the hydrogen from the reformed gas stream;  and then (b) recovering most or all of the carbon dioxide as a separate by-product stream by condensation of liquid carbon dioxide from the gas stream;  and then (c) recycling the remaining gases from the gas stream by mixing these gases with the SMR feed stream. The fuel used is principally hydrogen,  for example the fuel may contain 95 mol % or more hydrogen when measured on a dry basis. Greater than 85%,  typically greater than 99%,  of the carbon contained in the feed stream to the process is recovered and exported as carbon dioxide.', p.application_date = '2006-03-14 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'ATE810565T1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'ATE810566'}) SET p.application_no = 'ATE810566', p.title_cn = '用于生产氢的方法通过使用蒸汽重整烃，碳结合的捕获二氧化碳和蒸汽生产', p.title_en = 'METHOD FOR PRODUCING HYDROGEN BY REFORMING HYDROCARBONS USING STEAM,  COMBINED WITH CARBON DIOXIDE CAPTURE AND STEAM PRODUCTION', p.abstract_cn = '烃类蒸汽重整制氢的方法，结合二氧化碳捕集和产生蒸汽，它包括与蒸汽混合的烃类进行重整以产生用于重整原料，生成合成气；所生产的合成气冷却，富集H2和CO2，然后冷却；所述缩合物的分离方法以用于从所述合成气的方法，合成气经吸附饱和压力调节，从而产生氢气和含的气态流出物CPU单元中捕获CO2。所述缩合物从冷却的合成气在变换反应器的出口使用的方法用于生产不纯蒸汽的混合点供给；CPU单元还产生缩合物再循环到被处理的CPU与所述缩合物的方法。', p.abstract_en = 'A method for producing hydrogen by reforming hydrocarbons using steam,  combined with carbon dioxide capture and steam production,  which involves mixing the hydrocarbons to be reformed with steam in order to produce a feedstock for reforming,  generating a syngas;  the syngas produced is cooled,  enriched with H2 and CO2,  and then cooled;  the condensates of the method are separated from the syngas in order to be used in the method,  the saturated syngas being treated by adsorption with pressure modulation so as to produce hydrogen and a gaseous effluent containing CO2 that is captured in a CPU unit. The condensates from the cooling of the syngas at the outlet of the shift reactor are used in the method for producing impure steam supplying the mixing point;  the CPU unit also produces CPU condensates that are recycled to be treated jointly with the condensates of the method.', p.application_date = '2013-10-31 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'ATE810566T1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/48', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'ATE812145'}) SET p.application_no = 'ATE812145', p.title_cn = '水煤气转换反应过程', p.title_en = 'WATER GAS SHIFT REACTION PROCESS', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种提高氢气含量的合成气含有氢和碳氧化物和具有碳≧CO的含量45摩尔%的干气的基础上，包括以下步骤 : (i)将合成气与蒸汽形成富蒸汽进料气体混合物(Ⅱ)中使原料气体混合物在220-370℃范围内的温度下在铁基水-气变换催化剂形成富含氢气的气体混合物，其具有一氧化碳含量10摩尔%的干气的基础上，和(iii)回收所述富含氢气的气体混合物，其中富含氢气的气体混合物的一部分再循环到进料气体混合物。', p.abstract_en = 'A process for increasing the hydrogen content of a synthesis gas including hydrogen and carbon oxides and having a carbon monoxide content ≧45 mole % on a dry-gas basis,  including the steps of :  (i) combining the synthesis gas with steam to form a steam-enriched feed gas mixture (ii) passing the feed gas mixture at an inlet temperature in the range 220-370° C. over an iron-based water-gas shift catalyst to form a hydrogen-enriched shifted gas mixture having a carbon monoxide content 10 mole % on a dry gas basis,  and (iii) recovering the hydrogen-enriched shifted gas mixture,  where a portion of the hydrogen-enriched shifted gas mixture is recycled to the feed gas mixture.', p.application_date = '2010-10-14 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'ATE812145T1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/32', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'FR13052121'}) SET p.application_no = 'FR13052121', p.title_cn = '生产二氧化碳的方法和系统和氢气', p.title_en = 'METHOD AND SYSTEM FOR PRODUCING CARBON DIOXIDE AND HYDROGEN', p.abstract_cn = '过程中用于生产二氧化碳和氢气从气体流包含至少氢，至少一个含硫成分和二氧化碳始发从克劳斯单元供给有气体包括在至少50摩尔%的氧，气体流被压缩，以产生压缩后的干燥和干燥气体流量和压缩干燥后的气体流分离在低于环境温度以产生至少富含流体二氧化碳与相对于压缩和干燥气体流量和至少一种流体富含氢相对于压缩和干燥气体流。', p.abstract_en = 'In a process for the production of carbon dioxide and hydrogen from a gas flow comprising at least hydrogen,  at least one sulfur-comprising component and carbon dioxide originating from a Claus unit fed with a gas comprising at least 50 mol % of oxygen,  the gas flow is compressed and dried in order to produce a compressed and dried gas flow and the compressed and dried gas flow is separated at a subambient temperature in order to produce at least a fluid enriched in carbon dioxide with respect to the compressed and dried gas flow and at least a fluid enriched in hydrogen with respect to the compressed and dried gas flow.', p.application_date = '2013-03-08 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'FR3002930B1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/52', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'IN3236MUM2014'}) SET p.application_no = 'IN3236MUM2014', p.title_cn = '余热回收的改性家用液化石油气灶的锅支架', p.title_en = 'WASTE HEAT RECOVERY BY MODIFIED PAN SUPPORT OF DOMESTIC LPG STOVE', p.abstract_cn = '可以通过使用改性锅架余热回收。', p.abstract_en = 'It is possible to recover waste heat by use modified pan support.', p.application_date = '2014-10-13 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'IN3236MUM2014A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/48', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'DE502013003276'}) SET p.application_no = 'DE502013003276', p.title_cn = '用于生产乙炔和合成气的方法', p.title_en = 'METHOD FOR PRODUCING ACETYLENE AND SYNTHESIS GAS', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种方法用于生产乙炔和合成气的氧的部分氧化烃的方法。在所述方法中，一种第一输入流含有一种或多种烃和第二输入含氧流被分开地预热，从彼此，混合在比第二的质量流率的输入流的质量流率，第一输入对应的流程氧数λ小于或等于0.31，和经过燃烧器块至燃烧室。烃部分氧化燃烧室中。由此获得的裂化气体，它被急冷至80至90摄氏度下游的燃烧室通过将水性淬火介质。工艺水流量iliq和产物气体流获得Ig。该产物气体流冷却在冷却柱通过与冷却水直接换热的装置为了获得过程用水流的iiliq作为底流，产品气流量iig作为顶流，和侧流，电过滤器中烟灰的耗尽。一种工艺水流量iiiliq中出现的电滤波器。工艺水流入iliq，iiliq，和iiiliq合并和通过灰凹槽的表面进行粒子分离器以获得合并的方法水流ivliq。所述方法的特征在于，该合并过程中水流ivliq进行清洗的部分单级闪蒸罐中蒸发，该合并过程用水流ivliq的水分蒸发至一分数为0.01重量%至10重量%，在相对于其总重量，为了得到清洗后的工艺水流量vliq，其再循环到方法。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a method for producing acetylene and synthesis gas by partially oxidizing hydrocarbons by means of oxygen. In said method,  a first input flow containing one or more hydrocarbons and a second input flow containing oxygen are preheated separately from each other,  mixed at a ratio of the mass flow rate of the second input flow to the mass flow rate of the first input flow corresponding to an oxygen number lambda less than or equal to 0.31,  and fed via a burner block to a combustion chamber. The hydrocarbons are partially oxidized in the combustion chamber. A cracked gas is thereby obtained,  which is quenched to 80 to 90 degrees Celsius downstream of the combustion chamber by injecting an aqueous quenching medium. A process water flow Iliq and a product gas flow Ig are obtained. The product gas flow is cooled down in a cooling column by means of direct heat exchange with cooling water in order to obtain a process water flow IIliq as a bottom flow,  a product gas flow IIg as a top flow,  and a side flow,  which is depleted of soot in an electric filter. A process water flow IIIliq arises in the electric filter. The process water flows Iliq,  IIliq,  and IIIliq are merged and conducted via soot grooves having surface particle separators in order to obtain a merged process water flow IVliq. The method is characterized in that the merged process water flow IVliq is subjected to cleaning by means of partial evaporation in a single-stage flash tank,  the merged process water flow IVliq being evaporated to a fraction of 0.01 wt% to 10 wt%,  in relation to the total weight thereof,  in order to obtain a cleaned process water flow Vliq,  which is recycled into the method.', p.application_date = '2013-06-13 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'DE502013003276T2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/36', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'MX2011003999'}) SET p.application_no = 'MX2011003999', p.title_cn = '可燃气体发生器和使用本发明的双电层效应的方法用于分解水中的氢和氧气体和可燃气体的混合物。', p.title_en = 'GENERATOR OF COMBUSTIBLE GAS AND A PROCESS USING THE ELECTRIC DOUBLE-LAYER EFFECT FOR DISSOCIATING WATER IN HYROGEN AND OXYGEN GASES AND A MIXTURE OF COMBUSTIBLE GAS.', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种可燃气体发生器和用于分解水中的氢和氧的方法气体和水中还溶入气体通过设置不锈钢电极，其中通过电解单元形成串联的双电层效应部分提供内汽油内燃机，柴油生物柴油，乙醇，等性能，从而提高使用本发明的气体作为添加剂，消耗，并因此降低了污染，也可进一步基于应用的可燃气体氢气，水中先前溶解的氧气或其他气体的要求。', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention refers to a generator of combustible gas and a process for dissociating water in hydrogen and oxygen gases and further gases previously dissolved in water by means of an arrangement of stainless steel electrodes,  where electrolytic cells are formed in series by means of the electric double-layer effect for partially supplying an inner combustion engine of gasoline,  diesel biodiesel,  ethanol,  etc so as to improve the performance thereof using the inventive gas as an additive,  which reduces the consumption thereof and therefore the pollution,  also being used in further applications where combustible gas based on hydrogen,  oxygen or other gases previously dissolved in water is required.', p.application_date = '2011-04-14 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'MX340881B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/50', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14991775'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14991775', p.title_cn = '用涡流管进行仲正氢转化', p.title_en = 'Para-Orthohydrogen Conversion Using a Vortex Tube', p.abstract_cn = '一种准正氢转化装置，包括涡流管。 涡流管可包括设置在涡流管的第一端处的入口、设置在涡流管的内壁上的催化剂、包括在涡流管的第二端的周边上的开口的第一出口、设置在涡流管的第二端的中心处的止动件以及设置在涡流管的第一端上的第二出口。 一种方法包括当氢气移动通过涡流管时经由催化剂和旋转力将仲氢转化为正氢，使得冷却的富仲氢气体或液氢在涡流管的中心附近积聚。', p.abstract_en = 'A para-orthohydrogen conversion device comprises a vortex tube. The vortex tube may include an inlet disposed at a first end of the vortex tube,  a catalyst disposed on the interior wall of the vortex tube,  a first outlet comprising an opening on the perimeter of a second end of the vortex tube,  a stopper disposed at the center of the second end of the vortex tube,  and a second outlet disposed on the first end of the vortex tube. A method includes converting parahydrogen to orthohydrogen via the catalyst and rotational force as hydrogen gas moves through the vortex tube such that cooled parahydrogen-rich gas or liquid hydrogen accumulates near the center of the vortex tube.', p.application_date = '2016-01-08 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US20160200570A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14916650'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14916650', p.title_cn = '制氢装置、制氢方法、制氢用硅微粒及制氢用硅微粒制造方法', p.title_en = 'HYDROGEN PRODUCTION APPARATUS,  HYDROGEN PRODUCTION METHOD,  SILICON FINE PARTICLES FOR HYDROGEN PRODUCTION,  AND PRODUCTION METHOD FOR SILICON FINE PARTICLES FOR HYDROGEN PRODUCTION', p.abstract_cn = '根据本发明的示例性制氢设备100包括研磨单元10和氢发生器70，研磨单元10被配置为研磨硅片或硅研磨废料1以形成硅微粒2，氢发生器70被配置为通过使硅微粒2与水或水溶液接触并分散在水或水溶液中，或与水或水溶液接触或分散在水或水溶液中来产生氢。 氢产生装置100能够从通常被视为废物的硅芯片或硅研磨废料的起始材料可靠地产生实际上足够量的氢。 因此，该制氢设备有效地利用硅片或硅研磨废料，从而有助于环境保护以及显著降低在下一代中用作能源的氢的生产成本。', p.abstract_en = 'An exemplary hydrogen production apparatus 100 according to the present invention includes a grinding unit 10 configured to grind a silicon chip or a silicon grinding scrap 1 to form silicon fine particles 2,  and a hydrogen generator 70 configured to generate hydrogen by causing the silicon fine particles 2 to contact with as well as disperse in,  or to contact with or dispersed in water or an aqueous solution. The hydrogen production apparatus 100 can achieve reliable production of a practically adequate amount of hydrogen from a start material of silicon chips or silicon grinding scraps that are ordinarily regarded as waste. The hydrogen production apparatus thus effectively utilizes the silicon chips or the silicon grinding scraps so as to contribute to environmental protection as well as to significant reduction in cost for production of hydrogen that is utilized as an energy source in the next generation.', p.application_date = '2014-08-26 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US20160200571A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/06', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 2, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14912869'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14912869', p.title_cn = '一种高CO和高转化率等温转化反应器及其工艺', p.title_en = 'ISOTHERMAL CONVERSION REACTOR WITH HIGH CO AND HIGH CONVERSION RATE,  AND PROCESS THEREFOR', p.abstract_cn = '一种CO转化率高的等温一氧化碳变换反应器及其工艺技术，包括外压容器； 催化剂单元； 自卸车和下管板与水管和底部三通焊接； 所述外压容器的上端和下端均有密封头； 所述容器在上部具有水室和蒸汽室。 催化剂单元包括具有水管的上催化剂床。 在所述容器中设置有中心管，所述中心管的上端位于上催化剂床中，而下端位于下催化剂床中； 所述底三通具有进料气入口、反应变换气出口和汽水混合物入口； 所述中心管安装有汽水混合喷嘴； 该反应器适用于不同CO含量的原料气和废气的处理工艺。 低温、高CO进料含量、高变换转化率和低系统压降是本公开的直接结果。', p.abstract_en = 'An isothermal carbon monoxide (CO) shift reactor having high CO conversion and the process technology comprises the outside pressure vessel;  the catalyst unit;  tipper and lower tube sheets welded with water tubes and bottom tee joints;  the said outside pressure vessel has seal heads at the upper and lower ends;  the said vessel has a water chamber and a steam chamber at the upper section. The catalyst unit comprises the upper catalyst bed with water tubes. There is a central pipe that is located in the said vessel,  of which the upper end is located in the upper catalyst bed while the lower end is located in the lower catalyst bed;  the said bottom tee joint has an inlet for feed gas,  outlet for reacted shift gas and inlet for steam-water mixture;  the said central pipe is installed with spray nozzle for steam-water mixture;  the said reactor is applicable for process technologies for feed and effluent gas having different CO contents. Low temperature,  high CO feed content,  high shift conversion and low system pressure drop are direct results of this disclosure.', p.application_date = '2013-09-25 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US20160200572A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/16', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WOIB15059137'}) SET p.application_no = 'WOIB15059137', p.title_cn = '一种盒结构设计用于产生氢气', p.title_en = 'A CARTRIDGE STRUCTURE DESIGNED FOR GENERATION OF HYDROGEN GAS', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种盒体结构(100，200，300)设计用于产生氢气的气体通过产生氢的利用氢化物溶液(氢化钠，硼氢化锂，硼氢化钾，铵硼烷等)在催化剂的存在下。本发明的目的是提供一种盒体结构(100，200，300)用于产生氢气的设计通过使用连续供给氢化物溶液产生氢的存在下一种催化剂。', p.abstract_en = 'This invention relates to a cartridge structure (100,  200,  300) designed for generation of hydrogen gas by means of generating hydrogen using hydride solutions (sodium hydride,  lithium borohydride,  potassium borohydride,  ammonium borane,  etc.) in presence of a catalyser. The objective of this invention is to provide a cartridge structure (100,  200,  300) designed for generation of hydrogen gas by means of generating hydrogen using continuously fed hydride solutions in presence of a catalyser.', p.application_date = '2015-11-26 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016084025A3', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/06', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WOCN15099863'}) SET p.application_no = 'WOCN15099863', p.title_cn = '液态储氢体系', p.title_en = 'LIQUID HYDROGEN STORAGE SYSTEM', p.abstract_cn = '提供一种液态储氢体系，包括至少两种不同的储氢组分，该组分为不饱和芳香烃或杂环不饱和化合物，且至少一种组分为熔点低于80℃的低熔点化合物。该体系为多元混合液态稠杂环芳烃，并具有至少低于其中某一组分熔点的低共熔点，这使得储氢体系的共熔点下降至室温附近，从而在室温下呈现液态。', p.abstract_en = 'Provided is a liquid hydrogen storage system comprising at least two different hydrogen storage components,  the components being unsaturated aromatic hydrocarbons or heterocyclic unsaturated compounds,  and at least one of the components is a low-melting-point compound whose melting point is lower than 80°C. The system is multicomponent mixed liquid viscous heterocyclic aromatic hydrocarbons with an eutectic point that is lower than the melting point of at least one of the components,  so as to ensure the eutectic point of the hydrogen storage system to decrease to around the room temperature and make hydrogen storage system in a liquid state.', p.application_date = '2015-12-30 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016110215A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WOIB15060030'}) SET p.application_no = 'WOIB15060030', p.title_cn = '金属沉积方式，用碘化钾用于光催化剂的制备', p.title_en = 'METAL DEPOSITION USING POTASSIUM IODIDE FOR PHOTOCATALYSTS PREPARATION', p.abstract_cn = '光催化剂和光催化剂的使用方法用于生产氢和氧从水中被公开。该光催化剂包括一种碘化改性光敏材料具有导电材料连接到碘离子。', p.abstract_en = 'Photocatalysts and methods of using photocatalysts for producing hydrogen and oxygen from water are disclosed. The photocatalysts include an iodide modified photoactive material having an electrically conductive material attached to the iodide ions.', p.application_date = '2015-12-29 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016110773A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WOJP15086057'}) SET p.application_no = 'WOJP15086057', p.title_cn = '氢生成设备的操作方法以及氢生成设备', p.title_en = 'METHOD FOR OPERATING HYDROGEN GENERATION APPARATUS AND HYDROGEN GENERATION APPARATUS', p.abstract_cn = '在本发明，气体流道具有一封闭的循环回路，其绕过氢净化单元，使得气体返回循环通过泵送装置，以脱硫剂，重整器，和CO转化器，按此顺序，和吹扫气体供给通道，用于将吹扫气体到气体流道的上游泵送装置设置。关机操作之前，清洗步骤进行，其中气体在气体流道与所述吹扫气体更换和气体流道填充与所述吹扫气体。在启动之前执行的操作，氢气提纯操作，其中的温度气体流路中的气体提高操作的加热装置，增压步骤的进行是其中封闭循环回路内的压力增加供给吹扫气体以闭合循环回路的从吹扫气体供给通路。', p.abstract_en = 'In the present invention,  a gas flow passage has a closed circulation circuit which bypasses a hydrogen purification unit so that gas is returned and circulated therethrough by a pumping device to a desulfurizer,  a reformer,  and a CO shift converter,  in this order,  and a purge gas supply passage for supplying purge gas to the gas flow passage upstream of the pumping device is provided. Prior to a shutdown operation,  a purge step is performed in which the gas in the gas flow passage is replaced with the purge gas and the gas flow passage is filled with the purge gas. In a startup operation which is performed prior to a hydrogen purification operation and in which the temperature of the gas in the gas flow passage is raised by operating a heating means,  a pressure increasing step is performed in which the pressure inside the closed circulation circuit is increased by supplying the purge gas to the closed circulation circuit from the purge gas supply passage.', p.application_date = '2015-12-24 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016111184A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WOUS16012737'}) SET p.application_no = 'WOUS16012737', p.title_cn = '对正氢变换使用涡流管', p.title_en = 'PARA-ORTHOHYDROGEN CONVERSION USING A VORTEX TUBE', p.abstract_cn = '一种对正氢转换装置，包括涡流管。涡流管可以包括进口设置在涡流管的第一端，催化剂设置在涡流管的内壁，一种第一出口包括开口的周界上的涡流管的第二端，止挡件，设置在所述中心涡流管的第二端，和第二出口设置在涡流管的第一端。一种方法包括 : 将仲氢通过催化剂和旋转力到正氢作为氢气体移动通过涡流管使得冷却仲氢的富气或液氢的附近积存涡流管的中心。', p.abstract_en = 'A para-orthohydrogen conversion device comprises a vortex tube. The vortex tube may include an inlet disposed at a first end of the vortex tube,  a catalyst disposed on the interior wall of the vortex tube,  a first outlet comprising an opening on the perimeter of a second end of the vortex tube,  a stopper disposed at the center of the second end of the vortex tube,  and a second outlet disposed on the first end of the vortex tube. A method includes converting parahydrogen to orthohydrogen via the catalyst and rotational force as hydrogen gas moves through the vortex tube such that cooled parahydrogen-rich gas or liquid hydrogen accumulates near the center of the vortex tube.', p.application_date = '2016-01-08 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016112345A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201610275552.2'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201610275552.2', p.title_cn = '一种制氢转化炉', p.title_en = 'Hydrogen production conversion furnace', p.abstract_cn = '一种制氢转化炉，包括带衬里壳体、转化炉管、余热回收系统、燃烧器和燃料气精制系统，燃烧器布置于炉底，分布在转化炉管两侧，其火焰向上；转化炉管为内管与外管组成的套管；所述内管与外管之间的环隙中装有转化反应所需的催化剂；燃料气经过余热回收系统预热并脱硫后通入炉体内燃烧。该转化炉通过套管式结构使环隙内的原料气双面加热，确保高转化温度和高转化率，同时降低出口温度，使得出口管系更安全可靠；燃料气和空气双预热，可进一步提高热效率；燃料气预热前脱硫避免余热回收设备发生硫酸露点腐蚀；该转化炉还具有能耗低、操作弹性大、占地面积小和投资少等特点。', p.abstract_en = 'A hydrogen production conversion furnace comprises a shell with a lining,  conversion furnace tubes,  a waste heat recovery system,  burners and a fuel gas refining system.The burners are arranged on the furnace bottom and distributed on the two sides of the conversion furnace tubes,  and the flames of the burners face upwards;  casing tubes composed of inner tube bodies and outer tube bodies are adopted as the conversion furnace tubes;  an annular gap formed between each inner tube body and the corresponding outer tube body is filled with a catalyst needed by a conversion reaction;  fuel gas is preheated through the waste heat recovery system,  desulfurized and then introduced into a furnace body to be burnt.According to the hydrogen production conversion furnace,  the raw material gas in the annular gaps is bilaterally heated through the casing tube type structure,  the high conversion temperature and the high conversion rate are guaranteed,  and meanwhile the outlet temperature is lowered,  so that an outlet tube system is safer and more reliable;  the heat efficiency can be further improved through double preheating of the fuel gas and air;  the fuel gas is desulfurized before being preheated,  and therefore the phenomenon that waste heat recovery equipment generates sulfuric acid dew point corrosion is avoided.The conversion furnace further has the advantages of being low in energy consumption,  high in operating flexibility,  small in occupying area,  little in investment and the like.', p.application_date = '2016-04-29 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105752929A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201480063850.4'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201480063850.4', p.title_cn = '预重整器旁路', p.title_en = 'PREREFORMER BYPASS', p.abstract_cn = '本发明提供了改善的用于包含烃的流体的重整的设备和方法。所述生产方法包括以下步骤：在第一蒸汽混合点将第一量的蒸汽添加至工艺流，获得“第一物流混合物”，和将第一物流混合物供应至预重整器。在第二蒸汽混合点将第二量的蒸汽添加至预重整器流出物，由此获得“第二物流混合物”，随后进行一个或多个后续的重整步骤。', p.abstract_en = 'A plant and a process for improved reforming of fluids comprising hydrocarbons. Said production process comprising the steps of :  at a first steam mixing point adding a first amount of steam to a process stream obtaining a first stream mix and supplying the first stream mix to a prereformer. At a second steam mixing point adding a second amount of steam to the effluent of the prereformer thereby obtaining a second stream mix followed by one or more subsequent reforming step.', p.application_date = '2014-11-26 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105764841A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201620103188.7'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201620103188.7', p.title_cn = '一种合成氢燃气的制备装置', p.title_en = 'Synthetic hydrogenous fuel gas \'s preparation facilities', p.abstract_cn = '本实用新型属于新能源领域，具体为一种合成氢燃气的制备装置，包括反应釜，反应釜的顶部排气口依次连有气体干燥机、一级气体压缩机和二级气体压缩机，一级气体压缩机连接有气态混合气瓶，二级气体压缩机连接有液态混合气瓶；反应釜的上部进水口连接有补水机构；反应釜的下部连接有氮气置换装置，氮气置换装置连接有氮气瓶；反应釜的底部连接有排液除渣机构，排液除渣机构中设置有用于将固体残渣与废液分开的过滤网；反应釜的中部设置有分别用于补充正极电极的和负极电极的一对对称分布的电极补充机构，两电极补充机构分别与电极输送机构连接。本实用新型的合成氢燃气的制备装置，用普通水为原料，通过高温电弧裂解制备合成氢燃气，耗能低，产量高。', p.abstract_en = 'The utility model belongs to the new forms of energy field specifically is a synthetic hydrogenous fuel gas\'s preparation facilities,  including reation kettle,  reation kettle\'s top gas vent links in proper order has gas drying machine,  one -level gas compressor and second grade gas compressor,  and one -level gas compressor is connected with the mixed gas cylinder of gaseous state,  and second grade gas compressor is connected with the liquid gas cylinder that mixes,  reation kettle\'s upper portion water inlet is connected with moisturizing mechanism,  reation kettle\'s sub -unit connection has nitrogen gas replacement device,  and nitrogen gas replacement device is connected with the nitrogen cylinder,  reation kettle\'s bottom is connected with flowing back slagging -off mechanism,  is provided with in the flowing back slagging -off mechanism to be used for solid residue and waste liquid detached filter screen,  reation kettle\'s middle part is provided with and is used for replenishing the additional mechanism of electrode that distributes with a pair of symmetry negative electrode anode electrode respectively,  and two electrodes replenish the mechanism and are connected with electrode conveying mechanism respectively. The utility model discloses a synthetic hydrogenous fuel gas\'s preparation facilities uses the light water as the raw materials,  through the synthetic hydrogenous fuel gas of high temperature electric arc schizolysis preparation,  consumes energy and hangs down,  and output is high.', p.application_date = '2016-02-01 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN205381952U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201521075263.5'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201521075263.5', p.title_cn = '一种从水煤气中提取氢气的装置', p.title_en = 'Draw device of hydrogen in follow water gas', p.abstract_cn = '本实用新型涉及一种新型锅炉循环利用装置，一种从水煤气中提取氢气的装置，包括水、油污、粉尘和甲烷的过滤装置、粗脱硫装置、气体缓冲罐、气液增压机、热量转化器、液态水分离装置、精脱硫装置、变压吸附装置、氢气缓冲罐、氧气分离装置、氢气净化装置、氢气罐，过滤装置、粗脱硫装置、气体缓冲罐、气液增压机、热量转化器、液态水分离装置、精脱硫装置、变压吸附装置、氢气缓冲罐、氧气分离装置、氢气净化装置、氢气罐依次通过管道连通。本实用新型能提取高纯度的氢气、杂质含量少，且整个过程操作简单，能耗低、成本低廉。', p.abstract_en = 'The utility model relates to a novel boiler circulation utilizes the device,  a draw device of hydrogen in follow water gas,  including water,  the greasy dirt,  the filter equipment of dust and methane,  thick desulphurization unit,  gas buffer tank,  the gas -liquid booster compressor,  the heat converter,  liquid water separator,  smart desulphurization unit,  pressure swing adsorption unit,  hydrogen buffer tank,  oxygen separator,  hydrogen purifying device,  the hydrogen jar,  filter equipment,  thick desulphurization unit,  gas buffer tank,  the gas -liquid booster compressor,  the heat converter,  liquid water separator,  smart desulphurization unit,  pressure swing adsorption unit,  hydrogen buffer tank,  oxygen separator,  hydrogen purifying device,  the hydrogen jar loops through the pipeline intercommunication. The utility model discloses hydrogen,  the impurity content that can draw the high -purity are few,  and whole process operation is simple,  and the energy consumption is low,  low cost.', p.application_date = '2015-12-22 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN205381953U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/50', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201521079036.X'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201521079036.X', p.title_cn = '一种新型从焦炉煤气中提取出氢气和甲烷的装置', p.title_en = 'A new kind of from coke-oven gas is extracted in the device of the hydrogen gas and methane', p.abstract_cn = '本实用新型涉及一种新型从焦炉煤气中提取出氢气和甲烷的装置，包括水、油污、粉尘过滤装置、气体缓冲罐、脱硫装置、气液增压机、预热器、加热炉、变换炉、液态水分离装置、第一变压吸附装置、第二变压吸附装置、氢气缓冲罐、氢气净化装置、复式压缩机、脱硫塔、分离罐、溶剂再生系统；所述的水、油污、粉尘过滤装置、气体缓冲罐、脱硫装置、气液增压机、预热器、液态水分离装置、第一变压吸附装置、第二变压吸附装置、氢气缓冲罐、氢气净化装置通过管道连接。本实用新型能提取高纯度的氢气和甲烷，杂质含量少，且整个过程操作简单，能耗低、成本低廉。', p.abstract_en = 'The utility model relates to a novel extracted from coke oven gas of hydrogen gas and methane device,  including water,  oil,  dust filtering device,  gas buffer tank,  desulfurization device,  [...] compressor,  pre-heater,  heating furnace,  converting furnace,  liquid water separating device,  pressure swing adsorption device 1st,  2nd pressure swing adsorption apparatus,  hydrogen buffer tank,  hydrogen purification device,  reciprocating compressor,  thionizer,  separating tank,  solvent regeneration system;  said water,  oil,  dust filtering device,  gas buffer tank,  desulfurization device,  press [...],  preheater,  liquid water separating device,  pressure swing adsorption device 1st,  2nd pressure swing adsorption apparatus,  hydrogen buffer tank,  is connected by a pipe to hydrogen gas purification apparatus. The utility model is capable of extracting high purity hydrogen and methane,  less impurity content,  and the whole process is simple in operation,  low energy consumption,  low cost.', p.application_date = '2015-12-23 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN205381954U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/56', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'EP02708746'}) SET p.application_no = 'EP02708746', p.title_cn = '用于生产氢的方法和装置用于供给氢', p.title_en = 'METHOD FOR PRODUCING HYDROGEN AND APPARATUS FOR SUPPLYING HYDROGEN', p.abstract_cn = '有生产氢气的方法，采用铁或氧化铁接触水，水蒸汽，或含水蒸气的气体，一种氢气发生介质，其具有高的氢气发生反应速率和氧化-还原的耐重复而不损害其活性，提供了一种通过添加不同于铁的金属(例如Ti，Zr，V，铌(Nb)，Cr，Mo，Al，Ga，Mg，Sc，Ni，Cu等)以外的铁的铁或氧化铁。', p.abstract_en = 'With a method producing hydrogen by making iron or iron oxide contact water,  water vapor,  or a gas including water vapor,  a hydrogen generating medium,  which has a high hydrogen generation reaction rate and is resistant to a repetition of oxidation-reduction without degrading its activity,  is provided by adding a different metal (such as Ti,  Zr,  V,  Nb,  Cr,  Mo,  Al,  Ga,  Mg,  Sc,  Ni,  Cu,  etc.) other than the iron to the iron or the iron oxide.', p.application_date = '2002-04-01 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'EP1386881B1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/06', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'EP10766327'}) SET p.application_no = 'EP10766327', p.title_cn = '水煤气转换反应过程', p.title_en = 'WATER GAS SHIFT REACTION PROCESS', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种提高氢气含量的合成气含有氢和碳氧化物和具有碳≧CO的含量45摩尔%的干气的基础上，包括以下步骤 : (i)将合成气与蒸汽形成富蒸汽进料气体混合物(Ⅱ)中使原料气体混合物在220-370℃范围内的温度下在铁基水-气变换催化剂形成富含氢气的气体混合物，其具有一氧化碳含量10摩尔%的干气的基础上，和(iii)回收所述富含氢气的气体混合物，其中富含氢气的气体混合物的一部分再循环到进料气体混合物。', p.abstract_en = 'A process for increasing the hydrogen content of a synthesis gas including hydrogen and carbon oxides and having a carbon monoxide content ≧45 mole % on a dry-gas basis,  including the steps of :  (i) combining the synthesis gas with steam to form a steam-enriched feed gas mixture (ii) passing the feed gas mixture at an inlet temperature in the range 220-370° C. over an iron-based water-gas shift catalyst to form a hydrogen-enriched shifted gas mixture having a carbon monoxide content 10 mole % on a dry gas basis,  and (iii) recovering the hydrogen-enriched shifted gas mixture,  where a portion of the hydrogen-enriched shifted gas mixture is recycled to the feed gas mixture.', p.application_date = '2010-10-14 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'EP2496517B1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/32', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2015529963'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2015529963', p.title_cn = '该氢气产生组件', p.title_en = 'The hydrogen generating assembly', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种产生氢的制氢装置和方法。在一些实施例中，该方法可以包括接收进料流中的燃料加工组件的制氢组件；生成产品氢气流中从所接收的馈送流的燃料加工组件。生成产品氢气流可能，在一些实施例中，包括产生输出数据流从接收到的氢产生区的进料流，生成产品氢气流中净化区从所述输出流。该方法还可以包括接收所产生的产品氢蒸汽中产生的氢气缓冲罐组件，经由一槽和缓冲罐内压力检测传感器组件。该方法可以进一步包括 : 停止所述产品氢蒸汽中产生当检测到燃料加工组件缓冲罐内的压力高于预定的最大压力。', p.abstract_en = 'Hydrogen generation assemblies and methods of generating hydrogen are disclosed. In some embodiments,  the method may include receiving a feed stream in a fuel processing assembly of the hydrogen generation assembly;  and generating a product hydrogen stream in the fuel processing assembly from the received feed stream. Generating a product hydrogen stream may,  in some embodiments,  include generating an output stream in a hydrogen generating region from the received feed stream,  and generating the product hydrogen stream in a purification region from the output stream. The method may additionally include receiving the generated product hydrogen stream in a buffer tank of the hydrogen generation assembly;  and detecting pressure in the buffer tank via a tank sensor assembly. The method may further include stopping generation of the product hydrogen stream in the fuel processing assembly when the detected pressure in the buffer tank is above a predetermined maximum pressure.', p.application_date = '2013-08-27 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP5950376B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'MX2014007344'}) SET p.application_no = 'MX2014007344', p.title_cn = '用于产生合成气的方法和系统。', p.title_en = 'PROCESS AND SYSTEM FOR GENERATING SYNTHESIS GAS.', p.abstract_cn = '一种方法和系统，用于生成合成气的烃和水被描述。在进一步的细节的方法和系统合成气CO产生任何所需比例的氢气和/或合成的官能化和/或非官能化的烃。通过这种方法，含烃流体可具有可变转换为合成气的氢含量而不产生显著量CO2。此外，可获得氢气和一氧化碳的各种形式作为副产品。', p.abstract_en = 'A process and a system for generating synthesis gas from hydrocarbons and water are described. In further details of the process and the system,  synthesis gases are generated in any desired ratios of CO to hydrogen and/or synthetic functionalized and/or non-functionalized hydrocarbons. By means of this process,  a hydrocarbon-containing fluid can be converted into a synthesis gas having a variable hydrogen content without generating significant amounts of CO2. Furthermore,  hydrogen and carbon in various forms can be obtained as byproducts.', p.application_date = '2012-12-20 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'MX340534B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/24', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CA2659547'}) SET p.application_no = 'CA2659547', p.title_cn = '高度集成的氢气重整烃进料生产工艺', p.title_en = 'HIGHLY INTEGRATED HYDROGEN PRODUCTION PROCESS BY REFORMING A HYDROCARBON FEED', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种方法用于生产高集成的氢气热重整烃原料，包括步骤一种在空气或水的流动，其温度下通过至少200°C到燃烧器内的燃烧温度，从所述燃烧器与流出物混合，所述流出降低温度至小于725°C，步骤B所述步骤得到的混合进入第一热交换器，功能以过热水蒸汽的至少一个流和/或气态的烃原料，所述流和通过间接热交换过热直接注塑在重整反应器，在那里可用于作为燃料，和工序C，步骤B的混合物进入第二热交换器的蒸发，充分流液体水和/或烃类进料。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention concerns a highly thermally integrated hydrogen production process by reforming a hydrocarbon feed including a step a in which a flow of air or water,  whose temperature is lower by at least 200 .degree.C than the combustion temperature inside a burner,  is mixed to the effluent from the said burner,  in order to reduce the temperature of this effluent to less than 725 .degree.C,  a step b in which the mixture from step a enters into a first heat exchanger,  used to overheat at least one flow of steam and/or a hydrocarbon feed in gaseous form,  the said flow thus overheated by indirect heat exchange being directly injected into a reforming reactor where it is used as fuel,  and a step c in which the mixture from step b enters a second heat exchanger and is used to totally evaporate a flow of liquid water and/or hydrocarbon feed.', p.application_date = '2009-03-24 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CA2659547C', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/22', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CA2665050'}) SET p.application_no = 'CA2665050', p.title_cn = '用于制备合成气的过程从黑液', p.title_en = 'PROCESS FOR THE PREPARATION OF SYNTHESIS GAS FROM BLACK LIQUOR', p.abstract_cn = '所述的调节方法产生的合成气体在高温度下黑液气化器，包括(a)产生气化炉的流出物物流的黑液通过鼓风；(b)淬的气化器排出物(A)与水的料流，形成原合成气；(c)进一步冷却，清洗和分离粗合成气体以形成纯化的未处理合成气与适当的H2/CO比；(d)部分地将所述纯化的合成气二甲醚合成段中，生产DME和富含氢的产物流吹扫气流处理的合成气；(e)分流和回收分体式流处理或未处理的合成气体(A)；和回收副产物产生的CO2流在步骤(d)中部分或完全到步骤(a)。', p.abstract_en = 'A process for the adjustment of a synthesis gas produced in a high temperature downflow black liquor gasifier,  comprising (a) generating a gasifier effluent stream from black liquor by means of a blast;  (b) quenching the gasifier effluent of (a) with a water stream to form a raw synthesis gas;  (c) further cooling,  cleaning and separating the raw synthesis gas to form a purified unprocessed synthesis gas with an appropriate H2/CO ratio;  (d) partly converting the purified synthesis gas to dimethyl ether in a synthesis section,  producing a product stream of DME and a hydrogen rich purge stream of processed synthesis gas; (e) splitting and recycling split streams of the processed or the unprocessed synthesis gas to (a);  and recycling a by-product stream of CO2 being generated in step (d) in part or completely to step (a).', p.application_date = '2009-04-30 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CA2665050C', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/32', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CA2829552'}) SET p.application_no = 'CA2829552', p.title_cn = '合成气体与纳米碳制造方法和生产系统', p.title_en = 'SYNTHESIS GAS AND NANOCARBON PRODUCTION METHOD AND PRODUCTION SYSTEM', p.abstract_cn = '合成气体与纳米碳制造方法具有 : 一种轻烃分解步骤，其中的轻质烃分解产生氢和纳米碳；一种二氧化碳还原步骤，其中一些所述产生纳米的与二氧化碳反应以生成碳一氧化碳；和混合步骤，其中所产生的氢和一氧化碳在预定的比例混合得到合成气。这些步骤使得可以容易地同时制造纳米碳和合成气具有所需气体的比例。', p.abstract_en = 'A synthetic gas and nanocarbon production method has :  a light hydrocarbon decomposition step in which light hydrocarbons are decomposed to generate a hydrogen and nanocarbon;  a carbon dioxide reduction step in which some of the generated nanocarbons are reacted with carbon dioxide to produce carbon monoxide;  and a mixing step in which the generated hydrogen and carbon monoxide are mixed at a predetermined ratio to obtain synthetic gas. These steps enable simultaneous and easy production of nanocarbon and synthetic gas having a desired gas ratio.', p.application_date = '2012-03-09 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CA2829552C', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/26', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US13326427'}) SET p.application_no = 'US13326427', p.title_cn = '用于气化烃原料的系统和方法', p.title_en = 'Systems and methods for gasifying a hydrocarbon feedstock', p.abstract_cn = '提供了用于气化烃原料的系统和方法。 烃原料可在一种或多种颗粒存在下气化以产生合成气和一种或多种含碳颗粒。 一种或多种含碳颗粒的至少一部分碳可在烃原料气化外部的燃烧过程中燃烧以产生燃烧气体。 燃烧气体可以在烃原料气化外部的一个或多个过程中使用。', p.abstract_en = 'Systems and methods for gasifying a hydrocarbon feedstock are provided. The hydrocarbon feedstock can be gasified in the presence of one or more particulates to produce a syngas and one or more carbon-containing particulates. At least a portion of the carbon of the one or more carbon-containing particulates can be combusted in a combustion process external to the gasifying of the hydrocarbon feedstock to produce a combustion gas. The combustion gas can be utilized in one or more processes external to the gasifying of the hydrocarbon feedstock.', p.application_date = '2011-12-15 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9388980B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/36', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 3, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'TW103131670'}) SET p.application_no = 'TW103131670', p.title_cn = '燃料重组蜂巢触媒反应装置', p.title_en = 'HONEYCOMB CATALYST REACTOR FOR FUEL REFORMATION', p.abstract_cn = '一种燃料重组蜂巢触媒反应装置，具有高活性与热稳定性，其包括反应器主体，所述反应器主体包括加热管体、甲烷气体入口、三通水气入口以及富氢气体出口，其中三通水气入口处接近加热管体，可提供重组反应所需之热量，减少电量加热之耗费，并且选用英高镍系列作为加热管体之材料，使整体反应可在极高温度下进行；加热管体内设有经由涂布奈米碳管及热处理而增加内部表面积之蜂巢状载体(堇青石)，其上系承载Pt/CeO2/α-Al2O3触媒，并置於反应器主体之加热管体内，蜂巢状载体具有与加热管体主轴平行之蜂巢状孔道加热管体前後端以法兰连接，确保管线衔接之气密性，并於必要时可拆开反应器主体以更换蜂巢状触媒因此，本发明具有结构简单、体积小、操作灵活、且设备及操作成本低，并可简易地将此反应装置以并联方式加以扩充，明显具有便携型产氢设备与较大规模经济优势等优点', p.abstract_en = 'A honeycomb catalyst reactor is provided for fuel reformation,  which achieves high activity and heat stability. The reactor comprises a reactor body. The reactor body comprises a heating pipe,  a methane gas inlet,  a steam tee-inlet and a hydrogen-rich gas outlet. Therein,  the steam tee-inlet is close to the heating pipe to provide the heat required for the reformation and thus reduce power consumption for heating. Inconel material is used to make the heating pipe so that the overall reaction may be carried out at a very high temperature. The heating pipe is set with a honeycomb carrier (cordierite),  where the honeycomb carrier is coated with carbon nanotubes through heat treatment to increase internal surface area. The honeycomb carrier has a Pt/CeO2/α-Al2O3 catalyst;  placed in the heating pipe of the reactor body;  and has honeycomb channels parallel with the spindle of the heating pipe. The front and rear ends of the heating pipe are connected with flanges to ensure convergence of pipeline tightness and,  when necessary,  open the reactor body to replace the honeycomb catalyst. Accordingly,  the present invention has a simple structure,  a small size,  flexible operation,  and low equipment and operating costs. The present invention can be easily expanded through parallel connections;  and is,  thus,  clearly a portable hydrogen production equipment with a large-scale economic advantage.', p.application_date = '2014-09-12 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'TWI541192B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'RU2015156450'}) SET p.application_no = 'RU2015156450', p.title_cn = '合成气的生产装置', p.title_en = 'DEVICE FOR PRODUCTION OF THE SYNTHESIS - GAS', p.abstract_cn = '1。用于生产合成气的装置，含有第一的甲烷氧化加热室与液态金属热载体，降低气泡供给管中甲烷，第一室的气体管道上设有出料的反应产物，其特征在于 : 加热室中还含有第二的氧化液态金属冷却剂，表示合金，其中用气泡管供气，降低气体管道上设置有排出废气，所述腔室上，下管道相互连接，在上位于流局部通风机，和氧化液腔相连的甲烷氧化金属热载体和气体分析仪。2。根据权利要求1的装置，其特征在于 : 使用铅铋合金作为液态金属热载体。3。根据权利要求2的装置，其特征在于 : 使用铅铋合金作为液态金属热载体的共晶组合物。4。根据权利要求1的装置，其特征在于 : 为使用螺杆泵流量搅拌机。', p.abstract_en = 'An AutoAbstract The utility model relates to equipment for production of synthesis - gas and can be used in the petrochemical industry for preparation of motor fuels. Proposed by device for production of the synthesis - gas,  containing first heated chamber of oxidation of methane with liquid metal heat carrier,  in which is lowered bubble supply tube methane,  the first heated chamber is equipped with gas line for discharge of reaction products. The specific feature of the offered device is,  that it has second heated chamber with liquid metal heat carrier,  in which is lowered bubble tube for air supply and equipped with gas line for removing exhaust gases. The chamber are interconnected upper and lower pipelines,  in upper is positioned flow booster,  and chambers oxidation of alloy and of methane oxidation are connected with gas analyzer. EFFECT - increase of yield of finished product due to possibility of operative control modes of operation,  and also due to continuous mode of operation of the device. 5 Internet. U. 2 cl,  2 ill.', p.application_date = '2015-12-28 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'RU163221U1', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/24', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'RU2015150555'}) SET p.application_no = 'RU2015150555', p.title_cn = 'ksidov铝和氢水制造装置', p.title_en = 'DEVICE FOR PRODUCING HYDRO KSIDOV ALUMINIUM AND HYDROGEN', p.abstract_cn = 'ksidov铝水制氢装置，盛有溶剂的反应器，反应器中的碱性水供应管道泵，管道排气是氢，用于收集ksida加氢反应器中获得吊点复杂的铝和控制器，其特征在于在反应器位于所述入口，它具有装置，和门侧柱上连接有用于控制通过控制器借助于齿条的相对线性位移机构与电动驱动和相对角位移其水平轴线的驱动链机构的帮助下，中和釜体为形式的n个烧瓶，至少，两个，固定在开口槽运行的冷水中，其工作的过程中，使反应体积的自来水下永久层，颈烧瓶与固定安装在它们之上并设计用于封闭瓶胶塞，上述水龙头与内置管道，它是由刚硬的，并且相对于所述龙门架的上横档固定，所述管道上设有排气氢，其内部安装红外传感器，报警反应烧瓶中，碱水阀门和供水管路，导入泵中的氢。', p.abstract_en = 'Device is intended for realization of the method of producing hydro ksidov aluminum with the use of waste of aluminium and/or its alloys in the form of chips and small pieces of different shape in as initial raw material. Reactor (1) device is installed inside of the portal (2) and represents a row of flasks (5),  secured in tank (6) with running cold water. Working volume in lower cone-shaped part bulb (5) is used for performing aluminium oxidation and reception of charged through neck (9) initial materials. Throats flasks (9) (5) in the initial position of the device are open,  and in the process of its operation interact with mounted above them stationary and designed for closing flasks rubber plugs (10) with built-in taps pipeline (11) supply of alkaline solution and pipeline (13) O hydrogen from reactor. Pipelines and their branches are made of solid plastic,  and pipelines with the help of intermediate means are secured on upper cross piece (4) portal - it provides for stationary position plugs (10) at a certain distance above cells. Closing/opening flasks (5) plugs (10) and transfer produced in the result of exothermic reaction content drawn flasks in tank (26),  is effected due to controlled controller displacement tank (6),  secured on posts (3) of the portal (2) with the help of drive mechanisms :  upwards/downwards along posts - rack,  and turning on 180° relative to horizontal axis - chain. EFFECT - increase the operational safety device and minimising circuit collection obtained in reaction suspension complex hydro ksida aluminium. EFFECT - reduced fraction of manual labor.', p.application_date = '2015-11-26 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'RU163349U1', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/08', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'IN201647002120'}) SET p.application_no = 'IN201647002120', p.title_cn = '含烯烃的预重整方法以rbon流，预重整催化剂和所述催化剂的制备方法', p.title_en = 'METHOD FOR PRE-REFORMING OLEFIN-CONTAINING HYDROCARBON STREAMS,  PRE-REFORMING CATALYST AND METHOD FOR PREPARING THE CATALYST', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种蒸汽烃预改造其配方中含有镍和稀土催化剂是负载于氧化铝镁或铝酸钙等提高抗积炭和一种催化剂的制备方法。此外本发明涉及一种制造氢或合成气体的方法通过在存在含烯烃的烃类蒸汽预转化得到的催化剂根据本发明。', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention relates to a vapour hydrocarbon pre reforming catalyst containing in its formulation nickel and rare earths that are supported on alumina magnesium or calcium aluminates such as to increase resistance to coke deposition and to a method for preparing the catalyst. In addition the present invention relates to a method for producing hydrogen or synthesis gas by vapour pre reforming of olefin containing hydrocarbons in the presence of the catalyst obtained according to the present invention.', p.application_date = '2016-01-20 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'IN201647002120A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/32', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'IN9442DELNP2014'}) SET p.application_no = 'IN9442DELNP2014', p.title_cn = '生物活性炭和制备方法和使用', p.title_en = 'BIOGENIC ACTIVATED CARBON AND METHODS OF MAKING AND USING SAME', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了生物活性炭组合物包含至少55重量%的碳，其中的一些可以作为石墨烯具有高表面积(如碘)的数量大于2000。一些实施方案提供了生物活性碳，其响应于磁场。连续逆向接触生物活性炭的制造方法，包括通过机械方法，使原料与蒸汽料流。包括活性剂包括水和/或二氧化碳；去除水汽从所述反应区；将至少某些所述分离的蒸汽料流或其热处理形式的入口反应区(一个或多个)和/或原料；从反应区回收固体(一个或多个)作为生物活性炭。本发明公开了一种生物活性炭的使用方法。', p.abstract_en = 'Biogenic activated carbon compositions disclosed herein comprise at least 55 wt% carbon some of which may be present as graphene and have high surface areas such as Iodine Numbers of greater than 2000. Some embodiments provide biogenic activated carbon that is responsive to a magnetic field. A continuous process for producing biogenic activated carbon comprises countercurrently contacting by mechanical means a feedstock with a vapor stream comprising an activation agent including water and/or carbon dioxide;  removing vapor from the reaction zone;  recycling at least some of the separated vapor stream or a thermally treated form thereof to an inlet of the reaction zone(s) and/or to the feedstock;  and recovering solids from the reaction zone(s) as biogenic activated carbon. Methods of using the biogenic activated carbon are disclosed.', p.application_date = '2014-11-10 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'IN9442DELNP2014A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/08', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'AU2012301583'}) SET p.application_no = 'AU2012301583', p.title_cn = 'FT系统的集成和合成气产生', p.title_en = 'Integration of FT system and syn-gas generation', p.abstract_cn = '在一些实现方式中，一种分离组分的方法包括接收废气从费-托烃合成反应过程。离的气体进行洗涤，与轻质油在至少接近大气温度，以基本上除去的混合物C', p.abstract_en = 'In some implementations,  a method for separating components includes receiving off-gas from a Fischer-Tropsch hydrocarbon synthesis reaction process. The off-gas is scrubbed with a light oil at least proximate atmospheric temperature to substantially remove a mixture of C', p.application_date = '2012-09-04 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'AU2012301583B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/24', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'GR20160200013'}) SET p.application_no = 'GR20160200013', p.title_cn = '氢气发生系统', p.title_en = 'HYDROGEN GENERATION SYSTEM', p.abstract_cn = '氢气发生系统包括制氢电解槽(1)和直流电源(20，连接到控制单元(3)。压力传感器(4)的出口连接到控制单元(3)和所述传感器放置在出口管(5)，以允许所产生的氢气达到该机构由其供电，和电平电解质传感器(6)，固定连接于上电解液容器(7)。所述电解液容器(7)的出口连接至电解槽的电解液进口(1)通过可调单向阀(8)，和使瓶口的压力设定单元(9)连接到所述控制单元根据所述参数(3)的供电装置，和脉冲调制器(10)的操作方式连接到控制单元(3)调节电流供电的电解槽(1)，根据系统内的压力。', p.abstract_en = 'The hydrogen generation system includes an electrolyser (1) for producing hydrogen and DC power supply (20,  connected to a contol unit (3). The outlets of a pressure sensor (4) are attached to the control unit (3) and the sensor is put in an outlet tube (5) to let the produced hydrogen reach the mechanism powered by it,  and a level electrolyte sensor (6),  fixed to on an electrolyte container (7). The outlet of the electrolyte container (7) is connected to an inlet of an electrolyte of the electrolyser (1) through an adjustable one-way valve (8),  and the oulet of a unit for setting the pressure (9) is connected to the control unit (3) according to the parameters of the powered appliance,  and a pulse modulator (10) is attached in operation mode to the control unit (3) to regulate the amperage that powers the electrolyser (1),  according to the pressure in the system.', p.application_date = '2016-02-05 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'GR2003073Y', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2014261394'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2014261394', p.title_cn = '氢气制造方法，氢气制造装置以及电池', p.title_en = 'HYDROGEN PRODUCTION METHOD,  HYDROGEN PRODUCTION APPARATUS,  AND BATTERY', p.abstract_cn = '要解决的问题 : 能够制氢的能量低。溶液 : 生产氢，碱金属作为负极，碱金属的正极，利用碳或金属小电池反应，碱金属及碱土金属电子发射碳或金属的电化学氧化-还原工艺生产的熔体，电化学氧化还原过程中利用发射的电子通过氢和制氢工艺，通过加热融合，碱金属和碳或金属和热化学还原法，提供。选择附图中 : 图。1', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To provide a hydrogen production method in which hydrogen can be produced by low energy. SOLUTION :  The hydrogen production method comprises :  an electrochemical oxidation-reduction step of performing a cell reaction by using an alkali metal as a negative electrode and a metal having the ionization tendency smaller than that of carbon or the alkali metal as a positive electrode so that an electron is emitted from the alkali metal and a fused product of the alkali metal with the carbon or the metal is produced;  a hydrogen generation step of electrolyzing water by utilizing the electron emitted at the electrochemical oxidation-reduction step to generate hydrogen;  and a thermochemical reduction step of heating/reducing the fused product to the alkali metal and the carbon or the metal. SELECTED DRAWING :  Figure 1 COPYRIGHT :  (C)2016, JPO&INPIT', p.application_date = '2014-12-24 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP2016121036A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WOEP15081344'}) SET p.application_no = 'WOEP15081344', p.title_cn = '热反应器', p.title_en = 'THERMAL REACTOR', p.abstract_cn = '本发明提供一种热驱动的反应器包括反应室上方待加热的耐受500a°C和耐受内50大气压以上压力，其中所述反应室包括壁和所述壁的至少一部分被配置成传递热能成反应室，反应物与反应室流体连通的入口和至少一个吸附剂元件的位置之间移动在反应室和解吸室中的位置在连通的反应室，与反应室流体连通的使解吸室是可关闭的能够减压，不影响反应室中的压力，和至少一种反应产物流体连通的导管与解吸室通过一个可封闭的反应产物出口，和进行热反应的方法。', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention provides a thermal driven reactor comprising a reaction chamber tolerating to be heated above 500°C and tolerating an internal pressure of above 50 atm,  wherein the reaction chamber comprises walls and at least part of said walls are configured to transfer heat energy into the reaction chamber,  a reactant inlet in fluid communication with the reaction chamber and at least one sorber element movable between a position within the reaction chamber and a position in a desorption chamber in communication with the reaction chamber,  and the fluid communication with the reaction chamber is closable so that the desorption chamber can be depressurized without influencing the pressure in the reaction chamber,  and at least one reaction product conduit in fluid communication with the desorption chamber via a closable reaction product outlet,  and a method for performing thermal reaction.', p.application_date = '2015-12-29 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016107868A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201180021112.X'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201180021112.X', p.title_cn = '氢的制造方法', p.title_en = 'Method for producing hydrogen', p.abstract_cn = '本发明提供可以使用水在与以往相比低温低压的条件下容易地由水获取氢的氢的制造方法。在容器(60)内装入水、铝(76)和碳酸氢钠或碳酸钠中的至少一个。通过加热装置(90)将容器(60)内的水加热到60℃以上。可以通过容器(60)内的铝(76)和水在容器(60)内大量产生氢。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention provides a method for producing hydrogen capable of easily obtaining hydrogen from water under lower temperature and pressure conditions as compared with a conventional method. Water,  aluminium 76 and at least one of sodium bicarbonate or sodium carbonate are fed into a container 60. Water in the container 60 is heated to 60° C. or higher by a heating means 90. A large amount of hydrogen can be generated in the container 60 from the aluminium 76 and the water contained therein.', p.application_date = '2011-04-22 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN102869605B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/08', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201410054505.6'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201410054505.6', p.title_cn = '低温热解煤气制氢联产LNG的方法', p.title_en = 'Low-temperature pyrolysis gas hydrogen manufacturing method for co-production of LNG', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种低温热解煤气制氢联产LNG的方法，先将煤气先经除尘初加压和压缩后分成2部分，一部分经脱硫、转化和变换反应后，进行PSA提氢，另一分别用于直接制氢和制备氢气联产LNG。该方法可根据用氢量的多少，灵活调节氢气产量，具有投资和运行成本低、能耗低、能量利用率高等优点。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention discloses a low-temperature pyrolysis method of coal gas for hydrogen production and co-production of LNG (liquefied natural gas),  which comprises the steps of firstly performing dust removal and preliminary pressurization and compression on the coal gas,  and dividing into two parts,  wherein one part is subjected to PSA hydrogen extraction after desulfurization,  conversion and transformation reactions,  and the other part is applied to direct hydrogen production and preparation of hydrogen co-product LNG. The method can flexibly adjust the hydrogen output according to the amount of hydrogen,  and has the advantages of low investment and operation cost,  low energy consumption,  high energy utilization rate and the like.', p.application_date = '2014-02-18 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN103803492B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/50', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201410211019.0'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201410211019.0', p.title_cn = '一种污泥与生物质共混气化制氢的方法', p.title_en = 'A kind of mud and biomass blend gasification process for production of hydrogen', p.abstract_cn = '本发明提供了一种污泥与生物质共混气化制氢的方法与装置，装置包括气化炉、裂解炉和催化重整炉，利用所述装置先将高湿污泥与生物质共混制成颗粒进行气化，然后气化生成的焦油气和水蒸气在高温裂解炉内进行热裂解，将大部分重质焦油转化为轻质焦油，裂解未完全的焦油气和水蒸气进入催化重整炉进一步分催化重整。本发明是将城市污泥与城市有机生活垃圾、农林废弃物、塑料共混气化制氢，由于利用低成本、可再生的生物质或其气化燃气作为污泥气化及焦油气裂解和催化重整所需热源，能够充分发挥生物质能和污泥资源的经济价值，污泥中的水分在气化过程中受热蒸发，产生的水蒸汽作为气化和催化重整所需要的气化剂和氢源，实现污泥中的有机物成分的回收、利用，并转化为高品位、高价值的氢能。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention provides a method and a device for producing hydrogen through blending and gasifying of sludge and biomass. The device comprises a gasification furnace,  a cracking furnace and a catalytic reforming furnace. Highly humid sludge and biomass are firstly blended by the device so as to prepare into particles for gasifying,  then thermal cracking is carried out on tar gas and vapor produced by gasification in the high-temperature cracking furnace,  most heavy tar is converted into light tar,  and the tar gas and vapor which are not cracked completely enter the catalytic reforming furnace for further catalytic reforming. According to the invention,  municipal sludge,  municipal organic household garbage,  forestry and agricultural waste and plastic are blended and gasified to produce hydrogen. Low-cost and renewable biomass or gasified fuel gas thereof is used as a heat source for gasification of the sludge and splitting and catalytic reforming of the tar gas,  so that the economic value of the biomass energy and sludge resource can be fully used;  moisture in the sludge is heated and evaporated in gasification,  and the generated vapor is taken as a gasification agent and hydrogen source for gasification and catalytic reforming,  so that organic matters in the sludge are recycled and are converted into high-grade and high-value hydrogen energy.', p.application_date = '2014-05-20 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN103979491B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/26', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 2, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201410334818.7'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201410334818.7', p.title_cn = '一种等离子体甲烷重整制备合成气的方法', p.title_en = 'A plasma methane reforming process for the preparation of synthesis gas', p.abstract_cn = '本发明属于等离子体化学领域，涉及一种等离子体甲烷重整制备合成气的方法。反应器的两极间距为0.5～18mm；采用管板式反应器时，以金属管或者有孔圆形金属箔片作为高压电极和接地电极，两极间可以互换；采用管管式反应器时，高压电极和接地电极均为金属管。混合气体在反应区的停留时间为0.01～100s；放电反应温度为25～600℃；放电反应压力为-0.06～0.5MPa；混合气体包括甲烷、二氧化碳和氧气。当采用甲烷、氧气、二氧化碳进料时，O2添加气的目的是克服已有研究中的放电积碳问题，通过改变混合气的进料比从而调节产物中合成气的氢碳比，长时间运转没有任何积碳生成，综合利用甲烷和二氧化碳两种温室气体。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention belongs to the chemical field of plasmas,  and relates to a method for preparing synthesis gas through methane reforming with the plasma. The distance between two electrodes of a reactor is 0.5-18 mm;  when a tube-plate type reactor is adopted,  metal pipes or circular metal foil sheets with holes are used as a high voltage electrode and a grounding electrode,  and the two electrodes can realize exchange;  when a tube-tube reactor is adopted,  both the high voltage electrode and the grounding electrode adopt metal pipes;  the residence time of mixed gas at a reaction zone is 0.01-100 s;  the electric discharge reaction temperature is 25-600 DEG C;  the electric discharge reaction pressure is -0.06-0.5 MPa;  the mixed gas comprises methane,  carbon dioxide and oxygen;  when methane,  oxygen and carbon dioxide are adopted for feeding,  adding O2 in the gas aims to overcome an electric discharge and carbon deposition problem in the conventional research,  the ratio of hydrogen to carbon in the synthesis gas product is adjusted by changing the feeding ratio of the mixture gas,  no deposited carbon is generated after long-time operation,  and two greenhouse gases of methane and carbon dioxide are comprehensively utilized.', p.application_date = '2014-07-14 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN104071747B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/34', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201610007603.3'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201610007603.3', p.title_cn = '一种高容量锅炉烟气粘结镁基储氢材料的制备方法', p.title_en = 'Preparation method of high capacity boiler flue gas adhered magnesium based hydrogen storage material', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种高容量锅炉烟气粘结镁基储氢材料的制备方法，属于新能源领域。该方法利用高温裂解法制得氧化石墨纳米薄片作为催化剂，连同锅炉烟气包覆后的镁粉，以及微晶碳作助磨剂，经机械研磨混合后热反应制得高容量锅炉烟气粘结镁基储氢材料，以自制氧化石墨纳米薄片代替过渡金属化合物催化剂，利用其能提供大量的缺陷空位和活性位点来改善金属镁的吸放氢性能，最终提高储氢容量，既解决了传统储氢材料储氢容量低，稳定性不足的缺陷，又解决了过渡金属化合物少量添加就会提高很大质量百分比的不足，制备过程简单易操作，原料易得，成本低廉，具有高效的储氢性能。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a preparation method of a high capacity boiler flue gas adhered magnesium based hydrogen storage material,  and belongs to the field of new energy. According to the preparation method,  oxidized graphite nano sheets,  which are obtained through a high temperature pyrolysis method,  are taken as the catalyst;  boiler flue gas coated magnesium powder and microcrystal carbon are taken as the grinding aid;  raw materials are mechanically grinded and mixed,  and finally raw materials carry out thermal reactions to obtain the high capacity boiler flue gas adhered magnesium based hydrogen storage material. The self-made oxidized graphite nano sheets are used to replace the transition metal compound catalyst;  oxidized graphite nano sheets can provide a large amount of vacancy defects and active sites to improve the hydrogen absorbing/discharging performance of magnesium,  and thus the hydrogen storage capacity is increased finally. The shortages of conventional hydrogen storage materials such as low hydrogen storage capacity,  bad stability,  and the like are overcome. At the same time,  the shortage that a little amount of added transition metal compounds can increase a large mass percentage is also overcome. Moreover,  the preparation process and the operation are easy,  the raw materials are easily available,  the cost is low,  and the material has an efficient hydrogen storage performance.', p.application_date = '2016-01-07 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105731373A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201610212907.3'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201610212907.3', p.title_cn = '一种基于化学工质循环的外热式甲烷改制系统', p.title_en = 'External heating type methane modification system based on chemical working medium circulation', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种基于化学工质循环的外热式甲烷改制系统，包括甲烷改制反应器1，热管吸热器2，热管3以及燃气燃烧应用装置5，所述甲烷改制反应器1与热管吸热器2通过隔板组为一体，所述热管3穿过隔板两端分别置于甲烷改制反应器1和热管吸热器2中，所述甲烷改制反应器1下、上端分别设置有一次能源进口管和粗燃气出口管，所述粗燃气出口管与燃气燃烧应用装置5连接，所述改制气燃烧应用装置5设置有改制气排除口和烟气排出口。本发明公开的外热式甲烷改制系统的效率比常规气化反应器或改制反应器的效率高，具有较高的潜在节能效益。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention discloses an external heating type methane modification system based on chemical working medium circulation.The system comprises a methane modification reactor 1,  a heat pipe absorber 2,  a heat pipe 3 and a gas combustion application device 5,  wherein the methane modification reactor 1 and the heat pipe absorber 2 are integrated through a partition board,  the heat pipe 3 penetrates through the two ends of the partition board to be placed in the methane modification reactor 1 and the heat pipe absorber 2,  a primary energy inlet pipe and a crude gas outlet pipe are arranged at the lower end and upper end of the methane modification reactor 1 respectively,  the crude gas outlet pipe is connected with the gas combustion application device 5,  and the gas combustion application device 5 is provided with a modified gas discharge outlet and an exhaust gas discharge outlet.The exergy efficiency of the external heating type methane modification system is higher than that of conventional gasification reactors or modification reactors and has high potential energy-saving benefits.', p.application_date = '2016-04-07 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105731374A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/34', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201410742418.X'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201410742418.X', p.title_cn = '一种小规模生产超高纯氢气的方法', p.title_en = 'Method for small-scale production of ultra-pure hydrogen', p.abstract_cn = '本发明提供一种小规模生产超高纯氢气的方法，采用高透氢选择性的金属钯管氢气纯化器，将99.999％的高纯氢气提纯成99.999999％的超高纯氢，高纯氢气依次通过过滤器和换热器后进入金属钯管氢气纯化器，获得纯度大于99.999999％的超高纯氢气，其中杂质含量小于5ppb，同时由于金属钯管的高氢气透量，氢气回收率大于90％，产品气产量大于30m3/h。利用该方法生产的超高纯氢气可广泛应用于电子信息、半导体、LED、多晶硅光伏发电等战略性新兴产业。', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention provides a method for small-scale production of ultra-pure hydrogen gas A hydrogen purifier with metallic Pd tube with high hydrogen permeability selectivity is used Purifying 99.999% high-purity hydrogen into 99.999999% ultra-high-purity hydrogen,  passing the high-purity hydrogen through the filter and heat exchanger in turn,  and then entering the metal palladium tube hydrogen purifier to obtain ultra-high-purity hydrogen with a purity greater than 99.999999%,  in which the impurity content is less than 5ppb. At the same time,  due to the high hydrogen permeability of the metal palladium tube,  the hydrogen recovery rate is greater than 90%,  and the product gas output is greater than 30m3/h The ultra-pure hydrogen produced by this method can be widely used in strategic emerging industries such as electronic information,  semiconductors,  LEDs,  and polycrystalline silicon photovoltaic power generation.', p.application_date = '2014-12-08 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105731377A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/50', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201521012958.9'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201521012958.9', p.title_cn = '利用SOFC余热气化液氨装置', p.title_en = 'Utilize SOFC waste heat gasification liquid ammonia device', p.abstract_cn = '本实用新型涉及一种利用SOFC余热气化液氨装置，特点是包括气化室、减压阀、第一及第二电磁调节阀、散热结构、上隔离盘及下隔离盘；上隔离盘及下隔离盘将气化室分成三个相互隔离的室即废气出气室、热交换室及废气入气室，热交换室的下部及下部分别与氨贮蓄罐及燃料电池的进气口连通，在废气出气室上设有与外界相通的废气排气口，废气入气室与燃料电池的排气口连通；减压阀及第一电磁调节阀均设在热交换室与氨贮蓄罐的连接管上；第二电磁调节阀设在热交换室与燃料电池的连接管上；散热结构设在热交换室内，散热结构包括一根以上的散热管，每根散热管将废气出气室及废气入气室连通。其优点为：利用燃料电池产生的余热，加热液氨，提高了加热的效率，节约能源，环保。', p.abstract_en = 'The utility model relates to an utilize SOFC waste heat gasification liquid ammonia device,  characteristics are including vaporizer,  relief pressure valve,  first and the 2nd solenoid valve,  heat radiation structure on,  separator and separator down,  go up the separator and down the separator be waste gas outlet chamber,  heat -exchanging chamber and waste gas income air chamber with the room that the vaporizer falls into three mutual isolation,  heat -exchanging chamber\'s lower part and lower part respectively with ammonia save jar and fuel cell\'s air inlet intercommunication,  be equipped with on waste gas outlet chamber with external communicating exhaust gas discharge port,  air chamber and fuel cell\'s gas vent intercommunication is gone into to waste gas,  a relief pressure valve and a solenoid valve all establish on heat -exchanging chamber stores up the connecting pipe of jar with ammonia,  the 2nd solenoid valve establishes on heat -exchanging chamber and fuel cell\'s connecting pipe,  heat radiation structure establishes in heat -exchanging chamber,  and heat radiation structure includes the cooling tube more than,  and every cooling tube is with waste gas outlet chamber and waste gas income air chamber intercommunication. Its advantage does :  the waste heat that utilizes fuel cell to produce,  heating fluid ammonia has improved the efficiency of heating,  energy saving,  environmental protection.', p.application_date = '2015-12-09 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN205367722U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'EP01105476'}) SET p.application_no = 'EP01105476', p.title_cn = '制造合成气的方法', p.title_en = 'Method of manufacturing synthesis gas', p.abstract_cn = '制造合成气的方法，利用合成的植物包括 : 重整器(10)具有蒸汽重整反应筒(11)，燃烧辐射部分(12)围绕反应管(11)，用于加热反应管(11)，部分(13)以及连通燃烧室和对流辐射部(12)。蒸汽含天然气由天然气流。所述包含蒸汽的天然气通过将天然气通过对流预热部(13)的重整器(10)，天然气预热，然后再输送到反应管(11)。在对流预热后部分(13)，二氧化碳送入反应管(11)，由此产生含氢和一氧化碳的合成气。', p.abstract_en = 'A method of manufacturing a synthesis gas,  which makes use of a synthesis plant comprising a reformer (10) having a steam reforming reaction tube (11),  a combustion radiation portion (12) provided around the reaction tube (11),  for heating the reaction tube (11),  and a convection portion (13) communicating the combustion radiation portion (12). A steam-containing natural gas is prepared by adding stream to a natural gas. The steam-containing natural gas is preheated by passing the natural gas through a convection portion (13) of reformer (10),  the natural gas preheated being subsequently fed to the reaction tube (11). After being preheated in the convection portion (13),  carbon dioxide is fed to the reaction tube (11),  thereby producing a synthesis gas containing hydrogen and carbon monoxide.', p.application_date = '2001-03-14 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'EP1180495B1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'EP06710075'}) SET p.application_no = 'EP06710075', p.title_cn = '用于生产氢的方法与共同生产和捕获二氧化碳', p.title_en = 'A PROCESS FOR THE PRODUCTION OF HYDROGEN WITH CO-PRODUCTION AND CAPTURE OF CARBON DIOXIDE', p.abstract_cn = '用于生产氢的方法和捕获二氧化碳的联产，其中，该方法包括蒸汽甲烷重整烃进料在燃烧的燃料和存在下维持(i)中使用蒸汽甲烷重整器单元，其包括蒸汽甲烷重整装置(SMR)，和(ii)水煤气变换单元，从而导致生产包括氢气和二氧化碳的重整气体流，和燃烧产物流。该方法包括以下步骤 : (a)分离和除去大部分或全部的氢的重整气体流；和然后(b)将回收的大部分或所有二氧化碳作为单独的缩合副产物流液态二氧化碳从气体物流；然后，(c)回收剩余气体从气体通过混合这些流的SMR进料气体流。主要使用的燃料氢气，例如，可以含有95摩尔%或更多的氢气的燃料进行测定以干基计。大于85%，通常大于99%，所述含碳进料流中的二氧化碳的回收处理和输出。', p.abstract_en = 'A process for the production of hydrogen with the co-production and capture of carbon dioxide,  wherein the process comprises steam methane reforming a hydrocarbon feedstock in the presence of a fuel and a combustion sustaining medium using (i) a steam methane reformer unit that comprises a steam methane reformer (SMR),  and (ii) a water gas shift unit,  so as to result in the production of a reformed gas stream comprising hydrogen and carbon dioxide,  and a combustion products stream. The process comprises the steps of :  (a) separating and removing most or all of the hydrogen from the reformed gas stream;  and then (b) recovering most or all of the carbon dioxide as a separate by-product stream by condensation of liquid carbon dioxide from the gas stream;  and then (c) recycling the remaining gases from the gas stream by mixing these gases with the SMR feed stream. The fuel used is principally hydrogen,  for example the fuel may contain 95 mol % or more hydrogen when measured on a dry basis. Greater than 85%,  typically greater than 99%,  of the carbon contained in the feed stream to the process is recovered and exported as carbon dioxide.', p.application_date = '2006-03-14 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'EP1858803B1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'EP06815768'}) SET p.application_no = 'EP06815768', p.title_cn = '氢气纯化方法和系统', p.title_en = 'HYDROGEN PURIFICATION PROCESS AND SYSTEM', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种氢气发生系统，其包括燃料重整反应器产生富氢的重整气体的温度大于150℃，一种变压吸附(PSA)将重整气体中的氢精制装置成较纯的氢气流和一种废气流中，所述变压吸附单元，催化反应器的下游，其将含一氧化碳(CO)和氢气(H2)中相对纯的氢气物流转变成甲烷(CH4)和水蒸汽(H2O)。所述净化方法包括 : 产生富氢重整气中，在温度大于150℃燃料重整反应器，重整气体中分离成较纯的氢气流和废气流中的压力摆动吸附(psa)的氢精制装置，转换中所含一氧化碳(CO)和氢气(H2)的相对纯的氢气物流转变成甲烷(CH4)和水蒸汽(H2O)催化反应器中PSA装置的下游。所述氢可进一步纯化包括二次净化段下游的变压吸附装置和催化所述二次净化反应器级具有被水吸附材料吸附床的水汽H2O和氢吸收材料下游的优先吸水材料的吸氢气体，从而浓缩所述非氢气组分，例如CH4，进入排气流排出该层，所述吸收氢气再解吸出来以创建出非常纯的氢气流。', p.abstract_en = 'A hydrogen generation system is disclosed that includes a fuel reforming reactor generating a hydrogen-rich reformate gas at a temperature greater than 150 C,  a pressure swing adsorption (PSA) hydrogen purification unit that separates the reformate gas into a relatively pure hydrogen stream and an off-gas stream,  and a catalytic reactor down stream of the PSA unit that converts carbon monoxide (CO) and hydrogen (H2) contained in the relatively pure hydrogen stream into methane (CH4) and water vapor (H2O). The method of purification involves generating a hydrogen-rich reformate gas at a temperature greater than 150 C in a fuel reforming reactor,  separating the reformate gas into a relatively pure hydrogen stream and an off-gas stream in a pressure swing adsorption (PSA) hydrogen purification unit,  and converting carbon monoxide (CO) and hydrogen (H2) contained in the relatively pure hydrogen stream into methane (CH4) and water vapor (H2O) in a catalytic reactor down stream of the PSA unit. The hydrogen can be further purified by including a secondary purification stage downstream of the PSA unit and the catalytic reactor wherein the secondary purification stage has a water adsorbent material bed that adsorbs the water vapor H2O and a hydrogen absorbent material downstream of the water absorbent material that absorbs hydrogen gas preferentially,  thus concentrating the non-hydrogen components,  such as CH4,  into an exhaust stream that exits the bed,  wherein the absorbed hydrogen gas is then desorbed to create an exiting very pure hydrogen stream.', p.application_date = '2006-09-28 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'EP1996533B1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/34', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'EP13805448'}) SET p.application_no = 'EP13805448', p.title_cn = '用于生产氢的方法通过使用蒸汽重整烃，碳结合的捕获二氧化碳和蒸汽生产', p.title_en = 'METHOD FOR PRODUCING HYDROGEN BY REFORMING HYDROCARBONS USING STEAM,  COMBINED WITH CARBON DIOXIDE CAPTURE AND STEAM PRODUCTION', p.abstract_cn = '烃类蒸汽重整制氢的方法，结合二氧化碳捕集和产生蒸汽，它包括与蒸汽混合的烃类进行重整以产生用于重整原料，生成合成气；所生产的合成气冷却，富集H2和CO2，然后冷却；所述缩合物的分离方法以用于从所述合成气的方法，合成气经吸附饱和压力调节，从而产生氢气和含的气态流出物CPU单元中捕获CO2。所述缩合物从冷却的合成气在变换反应器的出口使用的方法用于生产不纯蒸汽的混合点供给；CPU单元还产生缩合物再循环到被处理的CPU与所述缩合物的方法。', p.abstract_en = 'A method for producing hydrogen by reforming hydrocarbons using steam,  combined with carbon dioxide capture and steam production,  which involves mixing the hydrocarbons to be reformed with steam in order to produce a feedstock for reforming,  generating a syngas;  the syngas produced is cooled,  enriched with H2 and CO2,  and then cooled;  the condensates of the method are separated from the syngas in order to be used in the method,  the saturated syngas being treated by adsorption with pressure modulation so as to produce hydrogen and a gaseous effluent containing CO2 that is captured in a CPU unit. The condensates from the cooling of the syngas at the outlet of the shift reactor are used in the method for producing impure steam supplying the mixing point;  the CPU unit also produces CPU condensates that are recycled to be treated jointly with the condensates of the method.', p.application_date = '2013-10-31 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'EP2931655B1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/48', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2013539925'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2013539925', p.title_cn = '用于燃料电池的系统和方法，用于检测泄漏硫硫检漏结构', p.title_en = 'For use in a fuel cell system and method for detecting leakage sulfur sulfur leakage detection structure', p.abstract_cn = '硫燃料的使用突破监测中使用的组件如此脱硫的燃料中含硫化合物的检测系统，所述监控组件，包括 : 如此脱硫的燃料加热到预定温度的加热器，所述预定温度为450℃和600℃之间，一种穿透硫检测器适于接收来自加热器的加热燃料，并且包括至少一个重整催化剂床。用于加热燃料重整和多个温度传感器，包括第一温度传感器，用于感测温度。所述加热燃料在燃料被输送通过该重整催化剂床和第二温度传感器，用于感测重整催化剂床内的温度，和控制器，用于确定是否燃料中含硫化合物的浓度超过第第一规定浓度基于温度的输出第一和第二个温度传感器。', p.abstract_en = 'A sulfur breakthrough monitoring assembly for use in a fuel utilization system for detecting sulfur-containing compounds in desulfurized fuel,  said monitoring assembly comprising :  a heater for heating desulfurized fuel to a predetermined temperature,  the predetermined temperature being between 450° C. and 600° C.,  a sulfur breakthrough detector adapted to receive heated fuel from the heater and including at least a reforming catalyst bed for reforming the heated fuel and a plurality of temperature sensors including a first temperature sensor for sensing temperature of the heated fuel before the fuel is conveyed through the reforming catalyst bed and a second temperature sensor for sensing temperature in the reforming catalyst bed,  and a controller for determining whether concentration of the sulfur-containing compounds in the fuel exceeds a first predetermined concentration based on temperature outputs from the first and second temperature sensors.', p.application_date = '2011-11-14 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP5947804B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2012088966'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2012088966', p.title_cn = '氢气发生装置', p.title_en = 'The hydrogen generating device', p.abstract_cn = '所要解决的问题 : 提供一种氢气发生器中的部分加氢脱硫催化剂的加氢脱硫层位于靠近入口整个井和温度未冷却的加氢脱硫催化剂得到几乎均匀。溶液 : 氢气发生器包括 : 一种加氢脱硫与加氢脱硫催化剂填充的容器包含在原料气体中去除硫化合物的加氢脱硫；和氢气发生容器产生燃烧气体以氢气为主要成分的原料气体。加氢脱硫容器具有出口，入口用于供应原料气体，预热原料气预热通道，加氢脱硫路径填充有加氢脱硫催化剂，原料气出口排出。利用这种配置，低温原料进行预热，经预热的加热路径将热量从氢发生器容器和加热后进入加氢脱硫层具有几乎相同的温度；加氢脱硫层。', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To provide a hydrogen generator in which part of a hydrodesulfurization catalyst located near the inlet of a hydrodesulfurization layer is not cooled well and the temperature of the whole of the hydrodesulfurization catalyst gets nearly uniform.SOLUTION :  A hydrogen generator includes :  a hydrodesulfurization vessel packed with a hydrodesulfurization catalyst removing sulfur compounds included in a raw material gas by hydrodesulfurization;  and a hydrogen generation vessel generating fuel gas with hydrogen as the major component from the raw material gas. The hydrodesulfurization vessel has an inlet for supplying the raw material gas,  a preheating path preheating the raw material gas,  hydrodesulfurization paths packed with the hydrodesulfurization catalyst,  and an outlet discharging the raw material gas. With this configuration,  the low temperature raw material is preheated by passing through the preheating path heated by the heat from the hydrogen generation vessel and flows into the hydrodesulfurization layer after being heated to have nearly the same temperature as that of the hydrodesulfurization layer.', p.application_date = '2012-04-10 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP5948605B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'BRPI112012011076'}) SET p.application_no = 'BRPI112012011076', p.title_cn = '用于制备低级烯烃产品的集成方法和系统。', p.title_en = 'integrated process and system for the preparation of a lower olefin product.', p.abstract_cn = '一种制备包含乙烯和/或丙烯的烯烃产品的方法，该方法包括以下步骤：a)在裂解区中，在裂解条件下裂解包含C2-C5链烷烃的链烷烃原料，以获得包含烯烃的裂解器流出物； b)在含氧化合物-烯烃转化系统中转化含氧化合物原料，该系统包括反应区，其中含氧化合物原料在含氧化合物转化条件下与含氧化合物转化催化剂接触，以获得包含乙烯和/或丙烯的转化流出物； c)合并至少部分裂化器流出物和至少部分转化流出物以获得合并流出物， 和从合并的流出物中分离包含乙烯和/或丙烯的烯烃产物流， 其中裂化器流出物和/或转化流出物包括含有不饱和物的C4部分，并且其中该方法还包括至少部分氢化至少部分C4部分，以获得至少部分氢化的C4原料； 以及将至少部分氢化的C4原料的至少一部分作为再循环原料再循环到步骤a)和/或步骤b)，以及用于执行该方法的集成系统。', p.abstract_en = 'A process for the preparation of an olefin product comprising ethylene and/or propylene,  which process comprises the steps of a) cracking a paraffin feedstock comprising C2-C5 paraffins under cracking conditions in a cracking zone to obtain a cracker effluent comprising olefins;  b) converting an oxygenate feedstock in an oxygenate-to-olefins conversion system,  comprising a reaction zone in which an oxygenate feedstock is contacted with an oxygenate conversion catalyst under oxygenate conversion conditions,  to obtain a conversion effluent comprising ethylene and/or propylene;  c) combining at least part of the cracker effluent and at least part of the conversion effluent to obtain a combined effluent,  and separating an olefin product stream comprising ethylene and/or propylene from the combined effluent,  wherein the cracker effluent and/or the conversion effluent comprises a C4 portion comprising unsaturates,  and wherein the process further comprises at least partially hydrogenating at least part of the C4 portion,  to obtain an at least partially hydrogenated C4 feedstock;  and recycling at least part of the at least partially hydrogenated C4 feedstock as recycle feedstock to step a) and/or step b),  and an integrated system for performing the process.', p.application_date = '2010-11-08 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'BR112012011076A2', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/22', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'BRPI112012011078'}) SET p.application_no = 'BRPI112012011078', p.title_cn = '烯烃的生产方法', p.title_en = 'process for production of olefins', p.abstract_cn = '本发明提供了一种生产烯烃的方法，包括：a。 在裂解条件下，在裂解区中裂解含乙烷的进料，以至少获得烯烃和氢气； b. 在含氧化合物-烯烃区中转化含氧化合物原料以至少获得烯烃； 其中至少部分含氧化合物原料是通过将步骤a)中获得的氢气和含有一氧化碳和/或二氧化碳的进料提供给含氧化合物合成区并合成含氧化合物而获得的。', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention provides a process for producing olefins,  comprising :  a. cracking an ethane-comprising feed in a cracking zone under cracking conditions to obtain at least olefins and hydrogen;  b. converting an oxygenate feedstock in an oxygenate-to-olefin zone to obtain at least olefins;  wherein at least part of the oxygenate feedstock is obtained by providing hydrogen obtained in step a) and a feed containing carbon monoxide and/or carbon dioxide to an oxygenate synthesis zone and synthesizing oxygenates. In another aspect the invention provides an integrated system for producing olefins.', p.application_date = '2010-11-08 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'BR112012011078A2', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/22', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2013113196'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2013113196', p.title_cn = '该氢制造方法及氢制造系统.', p.title_en = 'The method of producing hydrogen and hydrogen production system', p.abstract_cn = '本发明提供了一种制氢方法及其制氢系统. 在其中的每一个可提高氢气收率. 氢气生产方法，根据本发明的一个方面包括 : (第一)含卤素有机化合物的脱氢反应制氢. 以及第二步骤，其仍然是溶解在液体中分离氢的有机化合物的液体产生的所述脱氢. 制氢系统的一个实施例中，根据本发明设置有 : 一种脱氢反应器(2)的有机卤化物混合以生产氢和脱氢的有机化合物. 和气体/液体分离器(脱气装置(8)，其仍然是溶解在液体中分离氢的有机化合物的液体.', p.abstract_en = 'Provided are a hydrogen production method and a hydrogen production system,  in each of which the rate of collection of hydrogen can be improved. The hydrogen production method according to one aspect of the present invention comprises :  a first step of dehydrogenating an organic halide to produce hydrogen;  and a second step of separating hydrogen that is still dissolved in a liquid of an organic compound produced by the aforementioned dehydrogenation from the liquid. One embodiment of the hydrogen production system according to the present invention is equipped with :  a dehydrogenation reactor (2) for dehydrogenating an organic halide to produce hydrogen and an organic compound;  and a gas/liquid separator (a deaeration apparatus (8)) for separating hydrogen that is still dissolved in a liquid of the organic compound from the liquid.', p.application_date = '2013-05-29 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP5945521B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/26', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2012182516'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2012182516', p.title_cn = '用于产生氢气的方法从烷基肼化合物。', p.title_en = 'A method for generating hydrogen from alkylhydrazine compd.', p.abstract_cn = '所要解决的问题 : 提供一种方法，利用可控的条件下能够高效产生氢. 作为氢发生源. 一种肼化合物例如肼或肼衍生物. 提供一种氢气发生器和适合的方法. 方案是 : 制氢的方法，包括 : 将正极极柱和负极极柱为含肼水溶液产生氢气的化合物作为原料化合物. 再由外部电路的两极电连接. 及根据需求。. 两极间施加电压. 所述正极极柱，包括 : . 作为阳极催化剂. 至少一种选自组(1)由第9族元素的金属和(2)含有金属络合物. 作为金属构件. 一种8族元素或第9族元素. 和作为配体. 一种含氮多环化合物. 本发明能够高效地产生氢气这种情况下，产氢量，可以利用氢气发生器，用于执行所述方法的控制.', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To provide a method which can efficiently generate hydrogen under controllable conditions by using,  as a hydrogen generating source,  a hydrazine compound such as hydrazine or a hydrazine derivative,  and to provide a hydrogen generator suitable for the method.SOLUTION :  The hydrogen generating method includes immersing an anode pole and a cathode pole into an aqueous solution containing a hydrazine compound as a raw material compound for generating hydrogen,  then electrically connecting both poles by an external circuit,  and as occasion demands,  applying a voltage between both poles. The anode pole includes,  as an anode catalyst,  at least one selected from the group comprising (1) metals composed of group 9 elements and (2) metal complexes each containing,  as a metal component,  a group 8 element or group 9 element,  and as a ligand,  a nitrogen-containing polycyclic compound. It is possible to efficiently generate hydrogen under such a condition that the hydrogen generation amount can be controlled by using the hydrogen generator for executing the method.', p.application_date = '2012-08-21 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP5946038B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14638992'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14638992', p.title_cn = '连续液体燃料生产方法、系统和装置', p.title_en = 'Continuous liquid fuel production methods,  systems,  and devices', p.abstract_cn = '提供了用于连续燃料生产的方法、系统和装置。 一些实施方案可以利用两个热解平台，其可以利用生物质作为原料。 一个平台通常可以利用高温热解工艺，该工艺可以产生至少氢和一氧化碳。 该高温气体物流可以作为覆盖气体进料到低温快速热解物流中。 热覆盖气体可以与快速热解蒸汽加氢处理反应，而蒸汽仍然可以是热的，分子仍然可以是小的。 然后可在冷却时蒸馏反应产物。 这可以为从生物质或包括碳-氧-氢(C-O-H)化合物的其它化合物生产液体燃料提供快速连续的方法。', p.abstract_en = 'Methods,  systems,  and devices for continuous fuel production are provided. Some embodiments may utilize two pyrolysis platforms,  which may utilize biomass as a feedstock. One platform may generally utilize a high temperature pyrolysis process that may generate at least hydrogen and carbon monoxide. This high temperature gas stream may be fed into a lower temperature fast pyrolysis stream as a cover gas. The hot cover gas may react with the fast pyrolysis vapors hydrotreating while the vapors may still be hot and the molecules may still be small. The reacted product may then be distilled on the cool down. This may provide a rapid continuous process for the production of liquid fuels from biomass or other compounds that include carbon-oxygen-hydrogen (C—O—H) compounds.', p.application_date = '2015-03-04 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9382482B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14352692'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14352692', p.title_cn = '气化反应器', p.title_en = 'Gasification reactor', p.abstract_cn = '气化反应器和通过部分燃烧含碳原料生产合成气的方法。 该反应器包括具有一个或多个燃烧器的反应器室和至少一个延伸到反应器室中的油喷枪。 例如，油枪可以位于燃烧器下方或上方1.5米或更低的水平处。', p.abstract_en = 'Gasification reactor and process for the production of synthesis gas by partial combustion of a carbonaceous feed. The reactor comprises a reactor chamber with one or more burners and at least one oil lance extending into the reactor chamber. The oil lances can for instance be located at a level 1.5 meters or less below or above the burners.', p.application_date = '2012-10-17 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9382488B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/24', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 2, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'IDP00201504994'}) SET p.application_no = 'IDP00201504994', p.title_cn = '从使用的气体中结合二氧化碳的方法和装置', p.title_en = 'A method and apparatus for combining carbon dioxide from a gas used', p.abstract_cn = '一种从废气中接管二氧化碳并将其作为回收气体再利用而无需担心排放问题的方法和装置，包括：给出一种气源，该气源分为10个工艺气体和一个废气；将工艺气体与碳氢化合物混合，并将产生的原料气送入转化器，以对原料气进行固定并形成还原气；以及将所述废气中的至少一部分送入所述二氧化碳洗涤器，以将所述废气中的至少一部分二氧化碳移出并形成还原物。可选地，该方法还包括将废气的至少一部分送入二氧化碳洗涤器，以从与气体混合的二氧化碳压缩气体的废气中移动至少一部分二氧化碳，并在添加碳氢化合物后形成气体燃料，这些气体被送入转化器。可选地，气体源和还原气体与直接还原过程相关联，该还原炉可选地在多次修改后利用还原气体，将氧化铁从金属中转化为铁，并产生气体源。', p.abstract_en = 'A method and apparatus for receiving carbon dioxide from a waste gas and reusing it as a recovered gas without worrying about emission problems,  comprising :  providing a gas source which is divided into 10 process gases and a waste gas;  Mixing the process gas with a hydrocarbon and feeding the resulting feed gas to a converter to fix the feed gas and form a reduction gas;  And feeding at least a portion of the waste gas to the carbon dioxide scrubber to remove at least a portion of the carbon dioxide from the waste gas and form a reduced product. Optionally,  the method further includes passing at least a portion of the exhaust gas to a carbon dioxide scrubber to move at least a portion of the carbon dioxide from the exhaust gas of the carbon dioxide compressed gas mixed with the gas and to form a gaseous fuel after addition of hydrocarbons,  which gases are passed to the converter. Optionally,  the gas source and the reducing gas are associated with a direct reduction process,  the reduction furnace using the reducing gas,  optionally after multiple modifications,  to convert iron oxide from metal to iron,  and to produce the gas source.', p.application_date = '2015-08-14 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'IDP00201504994A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/24', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'IN10CHENP2015'}) SET p.application_no = 'IN10CHENP2015', p.title_cn = '气体加热的重整烃源的方法和相关设备', p.title_en = 'A PROCESS FOR GAS HEATED REFORMING OF A HYDROCARBON SOURCE AND A RELATED PLANT', p.abstract_cn = '一种烃类蒸汽重整的方法和设备的源气体中烃源气体和蒸汽过流部分重整的同时中束管(13)的重整器(10)与催化活性内表面；部分转化产物气体(18)离开所述氧化剂混合管(19)和对燃烧过程；一种燃烧部分重整气体(20)引入所述重整器壳体内侧，并且进一步通过触头与在所述管(13)外的面管的所述外表面也具有催化活性。', p.abstract_en = 'A process and equipment for steam reforming of a hydrocarbon source gas where the hydrocarbon source gas and a steam flow are partially reformed while passing in a bundle of tubes (13) of a reformer (10) with a catalytically active inner surface;  a partially reformed product gas (18) leaving said tubes is mixed with an oxidation agent (19) and subject to a combustion process;  a combusted partially reformed gas (20) is introduced in the shell side of said reformer and further reformed by contact with the outer s urface of said tubes (13) said outer surface of the tubes being also catalytically active.', p.application_date = '2015-01-01 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'IN10CHENP2015A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'IN1222CHENP2015'}) SET p.application_no = 'IN1222CHENP2015', p.title_cn = '筒监视器和用于重整器中或过程测量和控制', p.title_en = 'TUBE MONITOR AND PROCESS MEASUREMENT AND CONTROL IN OR FOR A REFORMER', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种方法和装置实时监测温度条件下在重整器(1)包括 : 测量转化管的长度(3)和使用该测量温度计算的长度。所述过程控制数据随后被用于优化过热保护和改善的蠕变损伤与疲劳寿命的预测。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to methods and apparatus of monitoring real time temperature conditions within a reformer (1) comprising measuring a length of a reformer tube (3) and calculating the temperature using the measured length. The data is then used for process control optimisation overheat protection and improved creep damage and fatigue life prediction.', p.application_date = '2015-02-27 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'IN1222CHENP2015A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'IN1812CHENP2015'}) SET p.application_no = 'IN1812CHENP2015', p.title_cn = '用于生产合成气的燃烧器', p.title_en = 'BURNER FOR THE PRODUCTION OF SYNTHESIS GAS', p.abstract_cn = '燃烧器适合在化学计量燃烧的烃源包括喷嘴(2)的形成扩散火焰燃烧器的外部和所述喷嘴(2)，它包括一个(20)或更多(21，22)的管状体限定通道(25)或多个的同轴导管(23，24)的各个反应物流，其中所述或每个所述管状体构成，所述喷嘴(2)的工艺的陶瓷材料制成。', p.abstract_en = 'A burner suitable for the over stoichiometric combustion of a hydrocarbon source comprising a nozzle (2) for the formation of a diffusion flame outside the burner and said nozzle (2) comprising one (20) or more (21 22) tubular bodies which define a channel (25) or a plurality of coaxial channels (23 24) for respective reactant streams wherein the or each of the tubular bodies forming said nozzle (2) are made of a technical ceramic material.', p.application_date = '2015-03-30 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'IN1812CHENP2015A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/36', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'IN201647011771'}) SET p.application_no = 'IN201647011771', p.title_cn = '用于生产氨的方法和设备组成气体生产氢气体的蒸汽重整', p.title_en = 'PROCESS AND PLANT FOR THE PRODUCTION OF AMMONIA MAKE UP GAS INCLUDING PRODUCTION OF A HYDROGEN GAS BY STEAM REFORMING', p.abstract_cn = '一种化妆合成气的生产方法和设备(20)包含氨的合成 : 重整烃原料(10)在蒸汽重整装置(SMR)所述产品得到氢气合成气净化气体添加适量的氮(19)对所述氢气的合成气，其中所述净化系统包括分离主分离单元(S1)中的氢产生氢的尾气流(14)和(15)，并且其中还从所述尾气回收氢的额外分离单元(15)中(S2)；一些实施例提供了一个用于气体产品(24)也被送给至所述未分离单元；相应的方法，所述氨厂改造的前端还公开了。', p.abstract_en = 'A process and plant for producing a makeup synthesis gas (20) for the synthesis of ammonia comprising :  reforming of a hydrocarbon feedstock (10) in a steam reformer (SMR) purification of said gas product obtaining a hydrogen synthesis gas addition of a suitable amount of nitrogen (19) to said hydrogen synthesis gas wherein said purification includes separation of hydrogen in a main separation unit (S1) which produces a hydrogen current (14) and a tail gas (15) and wherein further hydrogen is recovered from the said tail gas (15) in an additional separation unit (S2);  some embodiments provides that an amount of gas product (24) is also fed to said a dditional separation unit;  a corresponding method for the revamping of a front end of an ammonia plant is also disclosed.', p.application_date = '2016-04-04 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'IN201647011771A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'IN4102DEL2015'}) SET p.application_no = 'IN4102DEL2015', p.title_cn = '一种甲烷氧化催化剂的操作方法和排气后处理系统', p.title_en = 'METHOD FOR OPERATING A METHANE OXIDATION CATALYST AND THE EXHAUST AFTER TREATMENT SYSTEM', p.abstract_cn = '在甲烷氧化催化剂的操作方法(13)中的废气后处理系统内燃发动机(10)，甲烷氧化催化剂暴露于气体成分，WH ICH的甲烷氧化催化剂的再活化作用，由此增加实现甲烷氧化催化剂的活性。', p.abstract_en = 'In a method for operation of a methane oxidation catalyst (13) in an exhaust gas after-treatment system of an internal combustion engine (10),  the methane oxidation catalyst is exposed to a gas composition,  wh ich acts on reactivating the methane oxidation catalyst,  whereby an increase in the activity of the methane oxidation catalyst is achieved.', p.application_date = '2015-12-14 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'IN4102DEL2015A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'IN6051CHE2015'}) SET p.application_no = 'IN6051CHE2015', p.title_cn = '方法和设备用于制备一种或多种反应产物', p.title_en = 'PROCESS AND PLANT FOR PREPARATION OF ONE OR MORE REACTION PRODUCTS', p.abstract_cn = '提出了一种用于制备一个或多个工艺反应产物，其中富含甲烷的进料流第一(B)进行部分氧化过程和/或自热重整方法(1)和富含甲烷的进料流第二(e)(3)进行蒸汽重整的方法，和其中含第一的合成气通过输出(D)形成所述部分氧化方法和/或自热重整过程(1)和含第二的合成气通过输出流(G)形成蒸汽重整过程(3)，其中(D)和合成气的合成气从第第一输出从第二输出流(G)的用于形成集体的合成气物流(h)集体ESI合成气体流中的流体(H)进行分子量增反应中进料料流(I)的合成，得到合成输出流(k)含有二氧化碳和反应产物(一个或多个)。至少一个富含二氧化碳的碳第一的再循环流(P)形成从流体从所述合成输出流(k)再循环流中的流体在第一(p)进行蒸汽重整的方法(3)。本发明同样提供一种相应的装置(100)。(图1)', p.abstract_en = 'A process is proposed for preparing one or more reaction products,  in which a first methane -rich feed stream (b) is subjected to a partial oxidation process and/or an autothermal reforming process (1) and a second methane -rich feed stream (e) is subjected to a steam reforming process (3),  and in which a first synthesis gas -containing output stream (d) is formed by means of the partial oxidation process and/or the autothermal reforming process (1) and a second synthesis gas -containing output stream (g) is formed by means of the steam reforming process (3),  where synthesis gas from the first output stream (d) and synthesis gas from the sec ond output stream (g) are used to form a collective synthesis gas stream (h) and fluid from the collective synth esis gas stream (h) is subjected to a molecular weight-increasing reaction in a synthesis feed stream (i) to obtain a synthesis output stream (k) comprising carbon dioxide and the reaction product(s). At least one carbon dioxide-rich first recycle stream (p) is formed from fluid from the synthesis output stream (k) and fluid from the first recycle stream (p) is subjected to the steam reforming process (3). The present invention likewise provides a corresponding plant (100). (Figure 1)', p.application_date = '2015-11-09 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'IN6051CHE2015A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'IN6717CHENP2014'}) SET p.application_no = 'IN6717CHENP2014', p.title_cn = '在CO和/或H2的生产方法交替运行两种工作模式之间', p.title_en = 'METHOD FOR PRODUCING CO AND/OR H2 IN AN ALTERNATING OPERATION BETWEEN TWO OPERATING MODES', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种用于制备合成气的方法中交替运行两种工作模式之间。该方法具有以下步骤 : 提供流动反应器中；吸热二氧化碳，水和/或氢气与烃流反应器中至少一氧化碳的形成该产品的作用下，产生的热量由一个或多个加热元件(110，111，112，113)；在同时发生放热反应烃的一氧化碳和/或氢气作流反应器中反应物。放热反应释放的热量Q1组成的电加热反应器释放的热量Q2，放热反应的反应器和电加热操作，使得Q1和Q2的总和热量大于或等于Q3，所需要的平衡的产率Y作图吸热反应=90%。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a method for producing syngas in an alternating operation between two operating modes. The method ha s the steps of providing a flow reactor;  endothermically reacting carbon dioxide with hydrocarbons water and/or hydrogen in the flow reactor at least carbon monoxide being formed as the product under the effect of heat generated electrically by one or more heating elements (110 111 112 113);  and at the same time exothermically reacting hydrocarbons carbon monoxide and/or hydrogen as reactants in the flow reactor. The exothermic reaction releases a heat quantity Q1 the electric heating of the reactor releases a heat quantity Q2 and the exothermic reaction and the electric heating of the reactor are operated such that the sum of Q1 and Q2 is greater than or equal to the heat quantity Q3 which is required for an equilibrium yield Y of the endothermic reaction of = 90%.', p.application_date = '2014-09-09 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'IN6717CHENP2014A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'IN6927CHENP2014'}) SET p.application_no = 'IN6927CHENP2014', p.title_cn = '生产氨合成气的方法和相关的前端氨合成设备', p.title_en = 'PROCESS FOR PRODUCING AMMONIA SYNTHESIS GAS AND A RELATED FRONT END OF AN AMMONIA PLANT', p.abstract_cn = '一种从烃源生产氨合成气的方法，包括 : 烃源转换为原料合成气(14)的ATR或POX反应器(11)中被触发的与氧气(12)或富氧空气(28)；一种水煤气转换处理的粗合成气(14)的流体介质的温度改变(15)200300°C的温度下得到转换的合成气(16)；纯化所述转换的合成气(16)包括至少一个步骤的变压吸附(17)以除去残余的碳氧化物和甲烷的合成气获得纯化的合成气(18)和(19)任选添加氮所述纯化后的合成气(18)，从而获得氨合成气与所希望的氢氮比。', p.abstract_en = 'A process for producing ammonia synthesis gas from a hydrocarbon source comprising :  conversion of the hydrocarbon source into a raw synthesis gas (14) in ATR or POX reactor (11) which is fired with oxygen (12) or oxygen enriched air (28);  a water gas shift treatment of the raw synthesis gas (14) which consist of a medium temperature shift (15) at a temperature of 200 300 °C thus obtaining a shifted synthesis gas (16);  purification of said shifted synthesis gas (16) including at least a step of pressure swing adsorption (17) to remove residual carbon oxides and methane from the synthesis gas obtaining a purified synthesis gas (18) and optionally addition of nitrogen (19) to said purified synthesis gas (18) thus obtaining ammonia synthesis gas with a desired hydrogen to nitrogen ratio.', p.application_date = '2014-09-19 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'IN6927CHENP2014A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'IN716CHENP2015'}) SET p.application_no = 'IN716CHENP2015', p.title_cn = '分布式氢提取系统', p.title_en = 'DISTRIBUTED HYDROGEN EXTRACTION SYSTEM', p.abstract_cn = '一种提氢系统被提供。所述系统可以包括含有氢气的气体混合物进行压缩的压缩机和脱硫单元，接收压缩气体混合物。所述系统还可包括用于接收降低的硫混合气提氢装置，氢气存储装置用于接收N中提取氢气体。从气体混合物中提取氢气的方法，包括确定天然气和氢的方法还提供能源价格。', p.abstract_en = 'A hydrogen extraction system is provided. The extraction system can comprise a compressor for compressing a gas mixture comprising hydrogen and a desulfurization unit for receiving the compressed gas mixture. The system can also comprise a hydrogen extraction device for receiving a reduced sulfur gas mixture and a hydrogen storage device for receiving an extracted hydroge n gas. A method of extracting hydrogen from a gas mixture comprising natural gas and hydrogen and a method of determining an energy price are also provided.', p.application_date = '2015-02-04 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'IN716CHENP2015A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'IN745CHENP2014'}) SET p.application_no = 'IN745CHENP2014', p.title_cn = '平行制备氢气的方法和含碳产品', p.title_en = 'METHOD FOR THE PARALLEL PRODUCTION OF HYDROGEN AND CARBON CONTAINING PRODUCTS', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种平行制备氢气的方法(3)和一个或多个含碳产物(8)。在该方法中烃进料(2)引入反应室(R)中并热分解成碳和氢的在存在富碳的颗粒状材料(W)。本发明的特征在于，至少一部分所述热分解所需的能量rocarbons中引入所述反应室(R)中经由气态热传递介质。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a method for the parallel production of hydrogen (3) and of one or a plurality of carbon containing products (8). In the method hydrocarbons (2) are introduced into a reaction chamber (R) and are thermally decomposed into carbon and hydrogen in the presence of a carbon rich granulated material (W). The invention is characterised in that at least a portion of the thermal energy necessary for the decomposition of the hyd rocarbons is introduced into the reaction chamber (R) via a gaseous heat transfer medium.', p.application_date = '2014-01-29 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'IN745CHENP2014A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/28', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'IN7521CHENP2015'}) SET p.application_no = 'IN7521CHENP2015', p.title_cn = '本发明涉及一种生产氨合成气与高温位移及较低的蒸汽-碳比，', p.title_en = 'A PROCESS FOR PRODUCING AMMONIA SYNTHESIS GAS WITH HIGH TEMPERATURE SHIFT AND LOW STEAM-TO-CARBON RATIO', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种从含烃的原料生产氨合成气在前端包括以下步骤 : 所述原料的蒸汽重整获得合成气的含有氢气，一氧化碳和二氧化碳；所述的合成气，包括转化处理的一氧化碳，然后除去二氧化碳，其中所述转变所述合成气体中含有与铁基高温变换催化剂和温度下大于300℃，前端全局蒸汽与碳的比例为2.6或更低；相应的装置和方法，用于将氨厂的前端上，尚可利用的方法。', p.abstract_en = 'A process for producing ammonia synthesis gas from a hydrocarbon containing feedstock in a front end comprising the steps of steam reforming of said feedstock obtaining a synthesis gas comprising hydrogen carbon monoxide and carbon dioxide;  a treatment of said synthesis gas including shift of carbon monoxide and subsequent removal of carbon dioxide wherein the shift of the synthesis gas includes high temperature shift with an iron based catalyst and at a temperature greater than 300 °C and the global steam to carbon ratio of the front end is 2.6 or less;  a corresponding plant and a method for revamping a front end of an ammonia plant are a lso disclosed.', p.application_date = '2015-12-08 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'IN7521CHENP2015A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'IN752CHENP2015'}) SET p.application_no = 'IN752CHENP2015', p.title_cn = '合成气的净化方法和系统特别用于氨合成', p.title_en = 'METHOD AND SYSTEM FOR PURIFYING SYNTHESIS GAS IN PARTICULAR FOR AMMONIA SYNTHESIS', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种尤其用于氨合成气的净化方法合成其中部分流(26)富H的特定的含CO的合成气物流中燃烧，产生电能，其中，至少一个其他的H中所含的成分丰富的含CO的合成气物流(26)在特定的形式二氧化碳甲醇和/或水吸收后低温吸附器，其中所述吸收构件对于从吸附器(33)在较高温度下使用氮气冲洗。根据本发明的富H的部分流束(26)与用该氮气；(35)用的前冲洗，被烫伤。本发明还涉及一种系统(1)，尤其用于合成氨合成气的净化。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a method for purifying synthesis gas in particular for ammonia synthesis wherein a partial stream (26) of an H rich CO containing synthesis gas stream is burned in particular to generate electrical energy and wherein at least one component contained in the remaining H rich CO containing synthesis gas stream (26a) in particular in the form of carbon dioxide methanol and/or water is absorbed by an adsorber at low temperatures after which said absorbed component is desorbed from the adsorber by flushing using nitrogen (33) at higher temperatures. According to the invention the H rich partial stream (26) is diluted using th e nitrogen (35) used for the flushing before being burned. The invention further relates to a system (1) for purifying synthesis gas in particular for ammonia synthesis.', p.application_date = '2015-02-06 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'IN752CHENP2015A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'IN7705CHENP2014'}) SET p.application_no = 'IN7705CHENP2014', p.title_cn = '氢气产生装置和氢气产生单元以及能使用该方法的系统', p.title_en = 'HYDROGEN GENERATING DEVICE AND HYDROGEN GENERATING UNIT AND ENERGY SYSTEM USING SAME', p.abstract_cn = '本发明提供一种氢气产生装置和氢气产生单元，其中使用该方法的能源系统多个氢产生单元被布置在具有高度差的位置关系和连接系列当从液体电解质的流动以使产生的氢气和氧气的混合问题引起的偏振气泡附着在电极表面，同时克服了液体电解质的流体压力。该氢气产生装置中液体电解液流道在多个燃料电池的氢气发生装置单独提供一种氢气发生侧和氧气发电侧。在所述多个液体电解质的氢气产生单元通过所述液体流道的流量，而电解液内部从上至下而氢气发生细胞的液体电解质的液流通道，通过该通道电解液的流量，而从底立铣刀的顶部。一种随产生的气体或大气的接触点此外，本发明提出的路径中的液体电解质LS流通道。', p.abstract_en = 'Provided are a hydrogen generating device and hydrogen generating unit and an energy system using the same in which a plurality of hydrogen generating cells are disposed in a positional relationship having a difference in elevation and are connected in series as viewed from a liquid electrolyte flow whereby the problems of mixing of generated hydrogen and oxygen polarization due to adhesion of bubbles on an electrode surface and fluid pressure of the liquid electrolyte are simultaneously overcome. In the hydrogen generating device liquid electrolyte flow channels between the plurality of hydrogen generating cells constituting the device are provided separately for a hydrogen generating side and an oxygen generating side. Between the plurality of hydrogen generating cells a liquid electrolyte flow channel through which the liquid electrolyte flows is formed leading from top to bottom whereas inside the hydrogen generating cells a liquid electrolyte flow channel through which the liquid electrolyte flows is formed leading from bottom t o top. A point of contact with generated gas or the atmosphere is furthermore provided in a path of the liquid electrolyte flow channe ls.', p.application_date = '2014-10-20 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'IN7705CHENP2014A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'IN8406CHENP2014'}) SET p.application_no = 'IN8406CHENP2014', p.title_cn = '方法用于生产甲醇合成气的合成气的H2和CO废气尤其是从乙炔', p.title_en = 'METHOD FOR PRODUCING CO H2 AND METHANOL SYNTHESIS GAS FROM A SYNTHESIS GAS IN PARTICULAR FROM ACETYLENE OFF GAS', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种方法，用于生产甲醇合成气的产物流(2)H产物流(3)。和CO产物物流(4)从含H和CO的合成气物流(5)尤其是中AOG形式的方法包括以下步骤 : 所述的合成气物流(5)分离成第一和第二的合成气分流(51，52)，其中只有CO包含在第一的合成气分流(51)hwith转变成CO和水蒸气混合到第一合成为分流(51)。两个第一的合成气分流(51)和杆部(52)第二的合成气分流(52)晾干一种擦洗剂含有胺(102)以CO，其中洗涤洗脱剂的两列具体在再生器的接合柱。该甲醇合成气产物流(2)由第一转换部(51)的洗涤合成气分流(51)和/或另一部分(52)中未转化的第二的合成气分流(52)中的并且如果可应用从残余气体(9)和H(111)，使得粗的比例(Co)/(CO+CO2)作为必需的甲醇合成特别是在从2.0至2.1的范围内的甲醇合成气产物流中建立其中该经洗涤的一部分(52)第二未转化的合成气分流(52)，用于产生CO产物流(4)和所述产品流(3)的另一部分(51)和洗涤后的转换第一的合成气体分流(51)用于产生hproduct流(3)。本发明还涉及一种装置用于从合成气生产上述产品特别是由AOG之前分离成两个子流(51，52)被压缩到合适压力和下游不饱和烃的清除和O2的下游。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a method for producing a methanol synthesis gas product stream (2) an H product stream (3) and a CO product stream (4) from a synthesis gas stream (5) containing H and CO in particular in the form of AOG the method comprising the following steps :  Separating the synthesis gas stream (5) into a first and a second synthesis gas substream (51 52) wherein only CO contained in the first synthesis gas substream (51) is converted to CO and Hwith water vapor mixed into the first synthesis g as substream (51). Both the first synthesis gas substream (51) and portion (52a) of the second synthesis gas substream (52) are scrubbed with a scrubbing agent containing amine (102) in order to elute CO wherein the scrubbing agent of both columns in particular is regenerated in a joint column. The methanol synthesis gas product stream (2) is composed of a portion (51a) of the washed converted first synthesis gas substream (51) and/or the other portion (52b) of the unconverted second synthesis gas substream (52) and if applicable of DWA residual gas (9) and crude H (111) such that a ratio of (H CO)/(CO+CO) as necessary for the methanol synthesis in particular in a range from 2.0 to 2.1 is established in the methanol synthesis gas product stream wherein the scrubbed one portion (52a) of the second unconverted synthesis gas substream (52) is utilized for producing the CO product stream (4) and the H product stream (3) and the other portion (51b) of the scrubbed converted first synthesis gas substream (51) is used for producing the Hproduct stream (3). The invention further relates to a device for producing the above mentioned products from a synthesis gas in particular from AOG which prior to separation into the two substreams (51 52) is compressed to a suitable pressure and downstream is cleared of unsaturated hydrocarbons and O2 downstream.', p.application_date = '2014-11-19 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'IN8406CHENP2014A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/12', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'IN8728CHENP2014'}) SET p.application_no = 'IN8728CHENP2014', p.title_cn = '氨厂的改造方法与天然气输送', p.title_en = 'METHOD OF REVAMPING OF AN AMMONIA PLANT FED WITH NATURAL GAS', p.abstract_cn = '一种氨厂的改造方法，供给天然气，包括主重整器(11)和副重整器(12)的干预方法包括至少如下 : 降低出口(17)流出的气体温度从所述初级重整器；加入基本上为纯氧的进料线(30)引导至所述二段转化炉(12)至少部分取代燃烧处理气；加入氮气注入管道(31)组成一个必须的量，得到BLE氨气体适合大规模生产。合成。', p.abstract_en = 'A method of revamping of an ammonia plant fed with natural gas comprising a primary reformer (11) and a secondary reformer (12) the method comprising at least the following interventions :  reducing the outlet temperature of the gas (17) flowing out from said primary reformer;  adding a feeding line of substantially pure oxygen (30) directed to said secondary reformer (12) to at least partially replace the comburent process air;  adding a nitrogen injection line (31) in an amount necessary to obtain a make up gas suita ble for ammonia synthesis.', p.application_date = '2014-12-02 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'IN8728CHENP2014A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'IN9018CHENP2014'}) SET p.application_no = 'IN9018CHENP2014', p.title_cn = '用于对烃类进行重整的方法和启动过程中的气液方法', p.title_en = 'PROCESS FOR REFORMING HYDROCARBONS AND PROCESS FOR STARTING UP A GAS TO LIQUID PROCESS', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种用于生产合成气的方法通过使用自热重整或催化部分氧化，其中在除去ATR或CPO水流出气体再循环到进料该ATR或CPO。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a process for the production of synthesis gas by the use of autothermal reforming or catalytic partial oxidation in which after removal of water effluent gas from the ATR or CPO is recycled to the feed of the ATR o r CPO.', p.application_date = '2014-12-15 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'IN9018CHENP2014A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'IN9078CHENP2014'}) SET p.application_no = 'IN9078CHENP2014', p.title_cn = '用于对烃类进行重整的方法', p.title_en = 'PROCESS FOR REFORMING HYDROCARBONS', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及生产合成气的装置，尤其涉及一种串联布置的换热重整和自热重整阶段，其中所述重整反应所需的热量在热交换重整级提供的热流出物的合成气从自热重整阶段。更具体地，本发明涉及优化的操作和控制的热交换重整装置自热重整阶段引入额外的余热锅炉。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to the production of synthesis gas by means of particularly a series arrangement of heat exchange reforming and autothermal reforming stages in which the heat required for the reforming reactions in the heat exchange reforming stage is provided by hot effluent synthesis gas from the autothermal reforming stage. More particularly the invention relates to optimisation of the operation and control of an arrangement of heat exchange reforming and autothermal reforming stages and introduction of an additional waste heat boiler.', p.application_date = '2014-12-17 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'IN9078CHENP2014A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'IN9353CHENP2014'}) SET p.application_no = 'IN9353CHENP2014', p.title_cn = '燃料处理器，其具有一浮动催化剂', p.title_en = 'FUEL PROCESSOR WITH A FLOATING CATALYST', p.abstract_cn = '一种燃料处理器，其具有一浮动催化剂具有反应气体通道和产物气体通道隔开，无分隔壁，一端固定在另一端，以允许不同的热膨胀。所述的催化剂为接收插件IDE所述分隔壁的自由端附近。外壁至少部分地围绕着隔离壁和可分离的固定端壁连接到外壁。燃料处理器可以包括多个同心管可以包括第三管位于分离器壁。所述气体通道上设置有透气的支撑结构，例如turbulizers或翅片，分离的P口与内壁相对的外壁，而且支撑结构，以允许仅仅粘结到一个管所述壁的热膨胀差异。', p.abstract_en = 'A fuel processor with a floating catalyst has a reactant gas passage and a product gas passage separated by a separating wall which is fixed at one end and free at the other end to permit differential thermal expansion. The catalyst is received ins ide the separating wall proximate to the free end. An outer wall at least partially surrounds the separating wall and the fixed end of the separating wall may be joined to the outer wall. The fuel processor may comprise a plurality of concentric tubes and may include a third tube located inside the separator wall. The gas passages are provided with gas permeable support structures such as turbulizers or fins which sup port the separating wall relative to the outer wall but the support structures are bonded to only one tube in order to permit differential thermal expansion of the walls.', p.application_date = '2014-12-26 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'IN9353CHENP2014A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/32', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'TW103144440'}) SET p.application_no = 'TW103144440', p.title_cn = '储氢复材与其形成方法', p.title_en = 'HYDROGEN STORAGE COMPOSITE AND METHOD FOR MANUFACTURING THE SAME', p.abstract_cn = '本发明提供之储氢复材，包括：储氢材料；碳材载体，镶嵌至储氢材料之表面；以及触媒，披覆於碳材载体之表面上，其中碳材载体之至少一维的尺寸介於10nm至100nm之间', p.abstract_en = 'Disclosed is a hydrogen storage composite,  including a hydrogen storage material,  a carbon support embedded on a surface of the hydrogen storage material,  and a catalyst covering the carbon support,  wherein the carbon support has at least one dimension of 10nm to 100nm.', p.application_date = '2014-12-19 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'TW201623140A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'AU2012328159'}) SET p.application_no = 'AU2012328159', p.title_cn = '用于实现光催化或光电催化反应的方法', p.title_en = 'Method for effecting a photocatalytic or photoelectrocatalytic reaction', p.abstract_cn = '本发明提供了一种方法用于实施光催化或光电催化反应的反应物，包括使金属材料具有电导电率为10', p.abstract_en = 'The invention provides a method for effecting a photocatalytic or photoelectrocatalytic reaction of a reactant comprising contacting a metallic material having an electrical conductivity of 10', p.application_date = '2012-10-25 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'AU2012328159B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'BYa20120695'}) SET p.application_no = 'BYa20120695', p.title_cn = '水分解制取氢气和氧气的方法', p.title_en = 'The method of producing hydrogen and oxygen by decomposition of water', p.abstract_cn = '', p.abstract_en = '', p.application_date = '2012-05-03 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'BY20148C1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/06', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'GC201117834'}) SET p.application_no = 'GC201117834', p.title_cn = '生产合成气的方法', p.title_en = 'PROCESS FOR THE PRODUCTION OF SYNTHESIS GAS', p.abstract_cn = '本发明的主题是一种用于生产合成气的循环方法，包括：-第一步骤，氧化作为载氧体的可氧化固体; -第二吹扫步骤; -产生CO2的第三燃烧步骤; -第四合成气生产步骤; -第五净化步骤。图2。', p.abstract_en = 'A subject of the invention is a cyclic process for the production of synthesis gas comprising : –	a first step of oxidation of an oxidizable solid which is an oxygen carrier; –	a second purge step; –	a third combustion step with production of CO2; –	a fourth synthesis gas production step; –	a fifth purge step.Figure 2.', p.application_date = '2011-02-22 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'GC201117834A0', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'GC201119542'}) SET p.application_no = 'GC201119542', p.title_cn = '碳氧化物的捕获', p.title_en = 'CAPTURE OF CARBON OXIDES', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及(聚)氧亚甲基二烷基醚作为捕集碳氧化物、CO和/或CO2的试剂的用途。本发明还涉及使用至少一种选自所述(聚)氧亚甲基二烷基醚的吸收剂捕集碳氧化物的方法。', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention relates to the use of (poly)¬oxymethylene dialkyl ethers as agents for capturing carbon oxides,  CO and/or CO2.The invention also relates to the process for capturing carbon oxides using at least one absorption agent chosen from said (poly)oxymethylene dialkyl ethers.Fig. :  None', p.application_date = '2011-10-17 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'GC201119542A0', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/52', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'IDW00201204475'}) SET p.application_no = 'IDW00201204475', p.title_cn = '从脱除的氨气中回收氢气和氮气', p.title_en = 'Hydrogen and nitrogen are recovered from the removed ammonia gas', p.abstract_cn = '公开了氨炼厂，其中氨净化气体(20)，被送到低温回收单元，所述回收单元包括制冷设备(102、202、302、402、502)和高压相分离器(103、203、303、403、503)，在循环压力下工作；在所述单元内，净化气体(20)以低温冷却，实现甲烷和氩气的部分液化；高压相分离器将冷流分离为气态流和基液；气态流在热交换器的一个轨道上被再加热；然后，该单元可以在回路压力下排出含氮和氢的气态流(123、223、323、423、523)，这些气态流可以在回路的循环器(4)的吸入侧重新输入。', p.abstract_en = 'An ammonia refinery is disclosed in which ammonia purified gas (20) is sent to a cryogenic recovery unit comprising refrigeration equipment (102, 202, 302, 402, 502) and a high pressure phase separator (103, 203, 303, 403, 503) operating at cycle pressure;  In said unit,  the purge gas (20) is cooled at a low temperature to effect partial liquefaction of methane and argon;  The high-pressure phase separator separates the cold flow into a gaseous flow and a base liquid;  The gaseous stream is reheated on one of the rails of the heat exchanger;  The unit may then discharge gaseous streams (123, 223, 323, 423, 523) containing nitrogen and hydrogen at loop pressure,  which may be reintroduced on the suction side of the circulator (4) of the loop.', p.application_date = '2010-05-17 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'IDP000042030B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2014256957'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2014256957', p.title_cn = '氢发生装置及其制造方法. 一种发电装置.', p.title_en = 'HYDROGEN GENERATING AGENT,  MANUFACTURING METHOD THEREOF AND POWER GENERATOR', p.abstract_cn = '所要解决的问题 : 提高抗震性能的氢生成装置及其制造方法. 氢气发生器，应用于发电装置. 方案 : 氢气发生器1. B，瓶状容器. 该水反应性材料含有树脂的基材中含有固化的氢源3和具有固体. 固体氢源3. B在所述瓶状容器的底部. 抗振动，在运输时可改进. 选择附图中 : 图. 1.', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To provide a hydrogen generating agent having enhanced tolerance to vibration during transportation and a manufacturing method thereof,  and a powder generator to which the hydrogen generating agent is applied. SOLUTION :  A hydrogen generating agent 1 has a bottle shape container B and a solid hydrogen source 3 by containing a water reactive material in a base material containing a resin and solidifying it and the solid hydrogen source 3 is fastened to a bottom in the bottle shape container B. Tolerance to vibration during transportation is enhanced. SELECTED DRAWING :  Figure 1 COPYRIGHT :  (C)2016, JPO&INPIT', p.application_date = '2014-12-19 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP2016117601A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/08', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2014256959'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2014256959', p.title_cn = '氢发生装置及其制造方法. 一种发电装置.', p.title_en = 'HYDROGEN GENERATING AGENT,  MANUFACTURING METHOD THEREOF AND POWER GENERATOR', p.abstract_cn = '所要解决的问题 : 在使用相对低纯度的产氢源. 以低成本抑制中毒. 可抑制劣化unreversibly氢气发生器的发电单元及其制造方法. 氢气发生器，应用于发电装置. 溶液 : 1A·包括氢气发生器. 并包括树脂基材(51). 和(52)氢化钙与水反应的材料. 水反应性物质中所含的杂质去除剂(氨水)和(500)上设置. 它包括底座51，剥离剂500和水反应性材料. 选择附图中 : 图. 4.', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To provide a hydrogen generation agent suppressing poisoning at low cost while using a hydrogen generation source with relatively low purity and capable of suppressing irreversible deterioration of a powder generating cell and a manufacturing method thereof,  and a powder generator to which the hydrogen generation agent is applied. SOLUTION :  Hydrogen generation agents 1A and 1B have a base material containing a resin 51,  a water reactive material (hydrogenated calcium 52) and a remover 500 for removing predetermined impurities contained in the water reactive material (ammonia) and the base material containing a resin 51 contains the water reactive material and the remover 500. SELECTED DRAWING :  Figure 4 COPYRIGHT :  (C)2016, JPO&INPIT', p.application_date = '2014-12-19 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP2016117602A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/06', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2014258530'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2014258530', p.title_cn = '制备氢气和氢气发生容器装置.', p.title_en = 'HYDROGEN PRODUCTION APPARATUS,  AND HYDROGEN GENERATING VESSEL', p.abstract_cn = '所要解决的问题是 : 利用铝与水反应产生氢气. 总生成量的氢气继续进行长时间而不降低可产生氢. 此外，. 一种用于生产氢气和制氢装置，便于操作用于产生氢气的容器. 溶液 : 本发明的氢生成装置1. 发电机(10)和氢气. 产生的氢气通过氢气发生器(10)，用于从氢气中除去杂质的净化单元(20). 净化后的30和储氢单元. 和连接它们的配管类43-45. 氢气发生器10. 用于产生氢气的氢气发生器容器11和容器11和冷却器12用于冷却. 所述上部容器11中产生的氢气. 所述气体入口13. 气体出口14. 安全阀口(15). 每个喷射口(16)为1. 所述温度检测器40，其用于将所述探头的端口173. 选择附图中 : 图. 1.', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To provide a hydrogen production apparatus and a hydrogen generating vessel,  capable of generating hydrogen continuously for a long time without reducing a total generation amount of hydrogen when producing hydrogen using a reaction between water and aluminum,  and easy to handle a material for generating hydrogen. SOLUTION :  A hydrogen production apparatus 1 is constituted by :  a hydrogen generator 10;  a hydrogen purifier 20 for removing impurities from hydrogen generated in the hydrogen generator 10;  a hydrogen reservoir 30 for reserving hydrogen after purifying;  and pipes 43-45 connecting them. The hydrogen generator 10 is constituted by a hydrogen generating vessel 11,  and a cooler 12 for cooling the hydrogen generating vessel 11. One gas inlet 13,  one gas outlet 14,  one safety valve port 15 and one water filler 16,  and three attachment ports 17 for attaching a probe of a temperature detector 40 are provided on the upper part of the hydrogen generating vessel 11. SELECTED DRAWING :  Figure 1 COPYRIGHT :  (C)2016, JPO&INPIT', p.application_date = '2014-12-22 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP2016117620A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/08', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2014258551'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2014258551', p.title_cn = '催化剂结构的制造方法及装置.', p.title_en = 'APPARATUS AND METHOD FOR MANUFACTURING CATALYST STRUCTURE', p.abstract_cn = '所要解决的问题 : 气体并产生重整气体的重整原料. 一种高效的重整气体. 该催化剂能够稳定. 溶液 : 重整制氢原料气产生含有氢的重整气体的重整气体中分离催化剂的生产装置结构. 在多孔质部的筒状体的外表面上设有透氢膜分离单元与支撑件. 含重整催化剂的重整原料气喷嘴和喷射流体材料. 由支撑部分支撑氢分离装置，用于在相对移动上述喷嘴和运动部件. 所述喷嘴的相对移动的相对移动时，所述或每个喷嘴. 所述喷嘴的外表面上的流体材料的氢分离装置中排出至少一部分的外表面露出透氢膜形成含重整催化剂的催化剂层. 选择附图中 : 图. 3.', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To provide a catalyst structure that can generate a reformed gas by reforming a raw material gas and can separate hydrogen from the reformed gas efficiently and stably. SOLUTION :  An apparatus for manufacturing a catalyst structure that reforms a raw material gas to generate a reformed gas containing hydrogen and separates the hydrogen in the reformed gas comprises :  a support part that supports hydrogen separation means provided with a hydrogen permeable film on an outer surface of a porous part of a cylindrical body;  a nozzle that discharges a flowable material containing a reforming catalyst reforming the raw material gas;  and a moving part that relatively moves the nozzle with respect to hydrogen separation means supported by the support part. The nozzle discharges the flowable material to an outer surface of the hydrogen separation means at each relative movement of the nozzle or during the relative movement of the nozzle to form a catalyst layer containing the reforming catalyst with at least a part of an outer surface of the hydrogen permeable film being exposed. SELECTED DRAWING :  Figure 3 COPYRIGHT :  (C)2016, JPO&INPIT', p.application_date = '2014-12-22 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP2016117621A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2014267265'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2014267265', p.title_cn = '重整反应器.', p.title_en = 'MODIFICATION REACTOR', p.abstract_cn = '所要解决的问题 : 该装置制造的氢的氢及其建站成本及成本高的一种外加热式点心的处理方法用于重整反应器中进行反应管内部热式辐射管燃烧器的用于生产氢. 该RTB重整反应器需消耗大量昂贵的RTB重整反应器的生产成本和故障的成本. 溶液 : offgass分别安装至所述重整反应器的燃烧炉. 并减少了价格昂贵的RTB offgass由所述燃料热值或尺寸的传热管. 热交换器管的长度选择不受限制地在进行最佳设计的反应器以降低成本. 选择附图中 : 图. 1.', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To solve a problem of a hydrogen production device for hydrogen station,  that,  construction cost thereof is expensive,  so that as one of solutions for reducing cost,  an internal heating type hydrogen production method using a radiant tube burner is proposed,  to a modification reactor using a conventional external heating reaction tube,  but,  for the modification reactor having RTB,  many and expensive RTBs are required,  resulting in hindrance of significant cost reduction of production cost of the modification reactor. SOLUTION :  An additional off-gas burning furnace is installed on a modification reactor,  thereby a number of expensive RTBs is reduced,  there is no limitation about a heat generation amount of off-gas serving as fuel,  and selection of size and length of a heat transfer tube,  so that,  optimal design of the heat transfer tube is achieved and cost of the reactor is reduced. SELECTED DRAWING :  Figure 1 COPYRIGHT :  (C)2016, JPO&INPIT', p.application_date = '2014-12-22 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP2016117635A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'MYPI2012004188'}) SET p.application_no = 'MYPI2012004188', p.title_cn = '用于生产合成气的方法和系统', p.title_en = 'METHOD AND SYSTEM FOR PRODUCING SYNTHESIS GAS', p.abstract_cn = '一种生产合成气的方法，包括：1)预处理生物质原料; 2)进行低温炭化，得到热解气和木炭，木炭在炭化炉的出口冷却，冷却后的木炭输送到木炭储存仓; 3)将热解气与炭粉分离; 4)分离出的热解气一部分送入燃烧床燃烧，另一部分加热，加热后的热解气送入炭化炉：换热后的废热烟气送入生物质原料预处理部分进行干燥; 将分离出的炭粉输送到储炭仓; 5)将炭粉进行制粉，制得炭浆; 6)用高压炭浆泵将炭浆引入气化炉进行气化。图1', p.abstract_en = 'A METHOD FOR PRODUCING SYNTHESIS GAS,  INCLUDING :  1) PRE-TREATING A BIOMASS RAW MATERIAL;  2) CARRYING OUT LOW-TEMPERATURE CARBONIZATION TO OBTAIN PYROLYSIS GAS AND CHARCOAL,  COOLING THE CHARCOAL AT AN OUTLET OF AN CARBONIZATION FURNACE,  AND CONVEYING THE COOLED CHARCOAL TO A CHARCOAL STORAGE BIN;  3) SEPARATING THE PYROLYSIS GAS FROM CHARCOAL POWDER;  4) DELIVERING PART OF A SEPARATED PYROLYSIS GAS TO A COMBUSTION BED FOR COMBUSTION,  HEATING THE OTHER PART OF THE SEPARATED PYROLYSIS GAS,  AND DELIVERING A HEATED PYROLYSIS GAS TO THE CARBONIZATION FURNACE :  DELIVERING A WASTE HOT FLUE GAS AFTER HEAT EXCHANGE TO A PRETREATMENT PART FOR THE BIOMASS RAW MATERIAL FOR DRYING;  CONVEYING THE SEPARATED CHARCOAL POWDER TO THE CHARCOAL STORAGE BIN;  5) MILLING THE CHARCOAL POWDER TO PREPARE A CHARCOAL SLURRY;  AND 6) USING HIGH-PRESSURE CHARCOAL SLURRY PUMP,  INTRODUCING THE CHARCOAL SLURRY TO A GASIFICATION FURNACE FOR GASIFICATION. FIGURE 1', p.application_date = '2011-03-23 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'MY156930A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'MYPI2012002104'}) SET p.application_no = 'MYPI2012002104', p.title_cn = '由生物质生产富氢气体的方法', p.title_en = 'PROCESS OF PRODUCING HYDROGEN-RICH GAS FROM BIOMASS', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种由生物质生产富氢气体的方法，包括以下步骤：将生物质连续进料到气化单元(115)中，其中所述生物质是干燥的、研磨的形式; 在气化单元(115)中在二氧化碳吸附剂的存在下在600℃至750℃的温度下用过热蒸汽气化生物质; 将气化单元产生的产物气体加压，然后经过气体纯化单元(130)以生产富氢气体，其中气化反应在蒸汽与生物质的比率为2.0和二氧化碳吸附剂与生物质的比率为1.0的条件下进行。图解最多的示意图：图1', p.abstract_en = 'THE PRESENT INVENTION RELATES TO A PROCESS OF PRODUCING HYDROGEN-RICH GAS FROM BIOMASS COMPRISING THE STEPS OF CONTINUOUSLY FEEDING BIOMASS INTO A GASIFICATION UNIT (115),  WHEREIN SAID BIOMASS IS IN DRIED,  GROUND FORM;  GASIFYING THE BIOMASS WITH SUPERHEATED STEAM IN THE GASIFICATION UNIT (115) IN THE PRESENCE OF A CARBON DIOXIDE ADSORBENT AT TEMPERATURE RANGING FROM 600?C TO 750?C;  AND PRESSURIZING PRODUCT GAS RESULTED FROM THE GASIFICATION UNIT PRIOR TO BEING SUBJECTED TO A GAS PURIFICATION UNIT (130) FOR HYDROGEN-RICH GAS PRODUCTION,  WHEREIN THE GASIFICATION REACTION IS CARRIED OUT UNDER A CONDITION WHERE THE STEAM-TO-BIOMASS RATIO IS OF 2.0 AND THE CARBON DIOXIDE ADSORBENT-TO BIOMASS RATIO OF 1.0. MOST ILLUSTRATED DIAGRAM :  FIGURE 1', p.application_date = '2012-05-11 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'MY157067A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WOEP15075039'}) SET p.application_no = 'WOEP15075039', p.title_cn = '方法和用于生产合成气的植物', p.title_en = 'METHOD AND PLANT FOR THE PRODUCTION OF SYNTHESIS GAS', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种用于生产合成气的方法和设备(3)从烃(1)。在该方法中，在第一步骤，烃类是分体的，使用等离子体气体在高温下，成氢气(6)和碳(5)。所述产品与蒸汽混合，(8)和二氧化碳(9)，和碳(5)几乎完全转化为氢和一氧化碳在温度范围从800A°C以17a～°C热(10)供给的转化最大化。产品然后淬灭(13)。合成气(3)可部分(3a)的反馈和作为等离子气。在进一步的步骤，例如费-托合成，合成气(3)进一步转化，然后将其分离成各种馏分。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a method and plant for producing synthesis gas (3) from hydrocarbons (1). In the method,  in a first step,  hydrocarbons are split,  using a plasma gas at high temperatures,  into hydrogen (6) and carbon (5). Said product is mixed with steam (8) and carbon dioxide (9),  and the carbon (5) is almost entirely converted to hydrogen and carbon monoxide in a temperature range from 800° C to 1700° C. Heat (10) is supplied to maximize the conversion. The product is then quenched (13). Synthesis gas (3) can be partially (3a) fed back and used as plasma gas. In further steps,  such as Fischer-Tropsch synthesis,  the synthesis gas (3) is further converted and then separated into various fractions.', p.application_date = '2015-10-28 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016066716A8', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/24', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WOJP15082740'}) SET p.application_no = 'WOJP15082740', p.title_cn = '制氢装置和氢发生器容器', p.title_en = 'HYDROGEN PRODUCTION DEVICE AND HYDROGEN GENERATION VESSEL', p.abstract_cn = '本发明的氢气制造装置1包括一种氢生成装置(10)，一种氢气纯化装置20，用于除去杂质从氢中产生的氢生成装置(10)，氢存储装置30，用于存储后的氢气净化，和用于连接这些设备的管道43至45。氢生成装置(10)被配置为从氢气发生容器11和冷却装置12，用于冷却氢气发生容器11。在该氢生成的上部容器11的一个中的每个气体入口13，气体出口14，安全阀口15，和注水口16，和三个安装端口17，用于安装探针从温度检测器40。在使用之间的反应生产氢气水和铝，本发明允许连续地产生氢气在长的时间，而降低整体量产生的氢气。', p.abstract_en = 'This hydrogen production device 1 comprises a hydrogen generation apparatus 10),  a hydrogen purification apparatus 20 for removing impurity from the hydrogen generated in the hydrogen generation apparatus 10,  a hydrogen storage apparatus 30 for storing the hydrogen after the purification,  and plumbing 43 to 45 for connecting these apparatuses. The hydrogen generation apparatus 10 is configured from a hydrogen generation vessel 11 and a cooling apparatus 12 for cooling the hydrogen generation vessel 11. On the upper portion of the hydrogen generation vessel 11 are one each of a gas inlet 13,  a gas outlet 14,  a safety valve port 15,  and a water injection port 16,  and three mounting ports 17 for mounting probes from a temperature detector 40. When producing hydrogen using the reaction between water and aluminum,  the present invention allows hydrogen to be generated continuously over a long time period without decreasing the overall amount of hydrogen produced.', p.application_date = '2015-11-20 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016104007A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/08', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WORU15000927'}) SET p.application_no = 'WORU15000927', p.title_cn = '用于生产合成过程液态烃的天然气', p.title_en = 'PROCESS FOR PRODUCING SYNTHETIC LIQUID HYDROCARBONS FROM NATURAL GAS', p.abstract_cn = '[本发明方法中使用的合成C5及其以上烃的天然气通过中间转换的天然气合成气后续转化的CO和H2通过费-托合成。该方法包括蒸汽重整天然气蒸汽重整反应器中以形成合成气体，从合成气中分离二氧化碳由液体吸收法对残余的二氧化碳含量在合成气超过5体积。%，分离过量的氢气从合成气的氢可渗透膜装置的H2 : CO摩尔比在1.9至2.3的范围内和从合成气合成液态烃的费-托合成。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention is used in a process for synthesizing C5 and higher hydrocarbons from natural gas through intermediate conversion of natural gas to synthesis gas and subsequent conversion of CO and H2 by Fischer-Tropsch synthesis. The process comprises steam reforming of natural gas in a steam reforming reactor to form synthesis gas,  separating carbon dioxide from the synthesis gas by a liquid absorption method to a residual carbon dioxide content in the synthesis gas no more than 5 vol. %,  separating an excess of hydrogen from the synthesis gas by a hydrogen-permeable membrane apparatus to a H2 : CO molar ratio in the range of 1.9 to 2.3 and synthesizing liquid hydrocarbon from the synthesis gas by Fischer-Tropsch synthesis.', p.application_date = '2015-12-25 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016105253A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/34', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201410267625.4'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201410267625.4', p.title_cn = '电场诱导制备氢气的方法', p.title_en = 'Method of preparing hydrogen induced by electric field', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种电场诱导制备氢气的方法。该方法以水为基础原料，以电场诱导反应器为反应设备，利用电场诱导作用，使水解离生成氢自由基和羟基自由基，继而，氢自由基结合生成氢气；以过渡金属离子为催化剂，使羟基自由基转化为水和氧气。该方法能显著提高氢自由基的生产效率和速率，能耗小，能够产生更多数量的氢气。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention discloses a method for preparing hydrogen through electric field inducing. According to the method,  water is used as a base material,  an electric field inducing reactor is taken as reaction equipment,  water is decomposed to generate hydrogen radicals and hydroxyl radicals by using the inducing action of an electric field,  then,  the hydrogen radicals are combined to generate hydrogen;  transition metal ions are taken as catalysts,  so that the hydroxyl radicals are converted into water and oxygen. By adopting the method,  the production efficiency and speed of the hydrogen radicals can be obviously improved,  the energy consumption is less,  and more hydrogen can be produced.', p.application_date = '2014-06-16 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN104016301B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201380011813.4'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201380011813.4', p.title_cn = '氢的连续制备方法', p.title_en = 'Method for continuous production of hydrogen', p.abstract_cn = '本发明提供一种氢的连续制备方法，该方法能够简便地连续制备作为清洁能源的氢而不使用以往的氨，且安全性非常高。氢的连续制备方法的发明由下述工序构成：氢的制备工序，其通过将钙铝石(Mayenite：Ca12Al14O33)与氢氧化钙[Ca(OH)2]投入到水中，使它们与水反应产生氢，同时生成加藤石[Katoite：Ca3Al2(OH)12]；再生工序，其对所生成的加藤石进行焙烧，使钙铝石和氢氧化钙再生；循环工序，其使再生的钙铝石和氢氧化钙返回到氢的制备工序中。在氢的制备工序中，水的温度为50～100℃，钙铝石与氢氧化钙的摩尔比优选为1 : 9。此外在再生工序中，加藤石的焙烧温度优选为300～500℃。', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention provides a method for continuously producing hydrogen,  which can easily and continuously produce hydrogen as a clean energy source without using conventional ammonia,  and is very safe The invention of the continuous hydrogen production method consists of the following steps :  a hydrogen production step in which Mayenite (Ca12Al14O33) and calcium hydroxide [Ca (OH) 2] are put into water and reacted with water to produce hydrogen.,  while generating Katoite [Katoite :  Ca3Al2 (OH) 12]; a regeneration step of calcining the generated katenite to regenerate the calcareous stone and calcium hydroxide; a recycling step of returning the regenerated calcareous stone and calcium hydroxide to the hydrogen production step In the hydrogen preparation process,  the temperature of water is 50 to 100 °C,  and the molar ratio of calcinite to calcium hydroxide is preferably 1 :  9. In addition,  in the regeneration step,  the roasting temperature of katenite is preferably 300 to 500 °C.', p.application_date = '2013-01-11 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN104302573B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 2, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201610251886.6'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201610251886.6', p.title_cn = '利用高硫石油焦制备氢气的方法', p.title_en = 'Method for preparing hydrogen gas from high-sulfur petroleum coke', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开一种利用高硫石油焦制备氢气的方法，包括如下步骤：(10)原料混合：将氢氧化钾固体粉末与高硫石油焦颗粒成比例混合，搅拌均匀；(20)煅烧活化：将氢氧化钾与高硫石油焦颗粒混合物在500～800℃下煅烧活化3～6小时，收集煅烧活化过程中产生的硫化氢气体；(30)硫化氢分解：向硫化氢气体中加入浓硫酸，单独收集生成的单质硫，共同收集生成的二氧化硫气体和水；(40)氢碘酸生成：向共同收集的二氧化硫气体和水中加入碘液，分别收集反应生成的硫酸和氢碘酸；(50)氢碘酸分解：将氢碘酸加热分解，收集得到的氢气和碘液。本发明的氢气制备方法，能耗低、环境友好，且能生成有益附产品，高硫石油焦资源化利用。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention discloses a method for preparing hydrogen gas from high-sulfur petroleum coke. The method comprises the following steps :  (10) raw material mixing :  proportionally mixing potassium hydroxide solid powder and high-sulfur petroleum coke particles,  and stirring uniformly;  (20) calcination activation :  carrying out calcination activation on the potassium hydroxide/high-sulfur petroleum coke particle mixture at 500-800 DEG C for 3-6 hours,  and collecting hydrogen sulfide gas generated in the calcination activation process;  (30) hydrogen sulfide decomposition :  adding concentrated sulfuric acid into the hydrogen sulfide gas,  independently collecting the generated simple substance sulfur,  and collecting the generated sulfur dioxide gas and water together;  (40) hydriodic acid generation :  adding an iodine solution into the collected sulfur dioxide gas and water,  and respectively collecting sulfuric acid and hydriodic acid generated by the reaction;  and (50) hydriodic acid decomposition :  heating to decompose the hydriodic acid,  and collecting the obtained hydrogen gas and iodine solution. The preparation method has the advantages of low energy consumption and environment friendliness,  can generate beneficial byproducts,  and can recover the high-sulfur petroleum coke.', p.application_date = '2016-04-21 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105712295A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201480062004.0'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201480062004.0', p.title_cn = '氢气制造用硅原料A、氢气制造用硅原料B、氢气制造用硅原料A的制造方法、氢气制造用硅原料B的制造方法、氢气制造方法和氢气制造装置', p.title_en = 'Silicon material a for hydrogen gas production,  silicon material b for hydrogen gas production,  method for producing silicon material a for hydrogen gas production,  method for producing silicon material b for hydrogen gas production,  method for producing hydrogen gas,  and device for producing hydrogen gas', p.abstract_cn = '[课题]基于硅颗粒与碱水溶液的反应的氢气制造中，适当抑制硅颗粒与碱水溶液的反应，从而连续地得到氢气。[解决手段]本发明的氢气制造用硅原料A包含硅颗粒和油分。油分为硅颗粒的0.1重量％～10重量％。本发明的氢气制造用硅原料A的制造方法包括如下工序：准备包含硅颗粒、油分和水的硅屑(108)的工序；将硅屑(108)进行离心分离或过滤，制造包含硅颗粒、油分和少量的水的固态物A(112)的工序；将固态物A(112)干燥，制造包含硅颗粒和油分的固态物B(115)的工序；在固态物B(115)中混合水(116)而得到泥浆A(117)的工序。', p.abstract_en = 'In a method for producing a hydrogen gas by the reaction of silicon particles and an alkaline aqueous solution,  to continuously obtain the hydrogen gas by moderately inhibiting the reaction of the silicon particles and the alkaline aqueous solution. This silicon material A for hydrogen gas production comprises silicon particles and oil. The oil content is 0.1 to 10 weight% of the silicon particles. This method for producing the silicon material A for hydrogen gas production comprises :  a step of preparing silicon waste (108) which includes the silicon particles,  oil and water;  a step of centrifuging or filtrating the silicon waste (108) to produce a solid (A112) which includes the silicon particles,  oil and a small amount of water;  a step of drying the solid (A112) to produce a solid (B112) which includes the silicon particles and oil;  and a step of mixing water (116) into the solid (B112) to obtain sludge (A117).', p.application_date = '2014-09-17 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105722785A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/06', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201520848659.2'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201520848659.2', p.title_cn = '一种碳基燃料重整制氢装置', p.title_en = 'Carbon back fuel reformation hydrogen plant', p.abstract_cn = '本实用新型涉及一种碳基燃料重整制氢装置，属于氢能源技术领域，该装置包括列管反应器、上端盖板、环形套管、下端盖板、气化装置、加热装置；其中，气化装置嵌在列管反应器的内部，加热装置安装在气化装置内；环形套管套在列管反应器的外部；上端盖板、下端盖板分别连接在列管反应器的上下两端。该装置结构紧凑，设计小巧，加工方便，成本较低，适合应用推广。', p.abstract_en = 'The utility model relates to a carbon back fuel reformation hydrogen plant belongs to hydrogen energy source technical field,  and the device is including being listed as reactor,  upper end apron,  annular sleeve pipe,  lower extreme apron,  gasification equipment,  heating device,  wherein,  gasification equipment inlays in the inside that is listed as reactor,  and heating device installs in gasification equipment,  annular cover pipe box is in the outside that is listed as reactor,  upper end apron,  lower extreme apron are connected at the upper and lower both ends that are listed as reactor respectively. The device compact structure designs small and exquisitely,  and processing is convenient,  and the cost is lower,  is fit for application promotion.', p.application_date = '2015-10-29 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN205346827U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201620124444.0'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201620124444.0', p.title_cn = '氢气水雾搜集器', p.title_en = 'Ware is collected to hydrogen water smoke', p.abstract_cn = '本实用新型涉及水雾搜集器技术领域，是一种氢气水雾搜集器；包括立式容罐和除雾元件，立式容罐下部设有进气口，立式容罐上端设有出气口，立式容罐下端设有排液口，立式容罐的上端通过设备法兰固定安装有椭圆封头，立式容罐上部内设有连接花板，连接花板上设有至少一个通孔，除雾元件的上端固定安装在通孔内。本实用新型结构合理而紧凑，使用方便，通过对氢气缓冲罐内部进行改造，实现本实用新型氢气水雾搜集器，加入连接花板和除雾元件，增加滤水功能，从而增加了清洗灯头的周期，减少了劳动量，降低了操作风险。', p.abstract_en = '(B,  ) the utility model relates to a ware technical field is collected to water smoke,  is a ware is collected to hydrogen water smoke,  (B,  ) (b) is equipped with the air inlet including vertical appearance jar and defogging component,  vertical appearance jar lower part,  and vertical appearance jar upper end is equipped with the gas outlet,  and vertical appearance jar lower extreme is equipped with the leakage fluid dram,  and there is the elipse head upper end of vertical appearance jar through flange of the equipment fixed mounting,  is equipped with the connection card in the vertical appearance jar upper portion,  is equipped with at least one through -hole on the connection card,  and the upper end fixed mounting of defogging component is in the through -hole. The utility model has the advantages of reasonable and compact structure,  convenient to use through reforming transform hydrogen gas buffer inside,  realizes the utility model discloses ware is collected to hydrogen water smoke adds and connects card and defogging component,  increases the drainage function to the cycle of wasing the lamp holder that has increased has reduced the amount of labour,  has reduced operational risk. (B,  )', p.application_date = '2016-02-17 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN205346828U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/56', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2010085725'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2010085725', p.title_cn = '用于从氢气发生器产生氢气的水', p.title_en = 'Water for generating hydrogen from the hydrogen generator', p.abstract_cn = '所要解决的问题是： 本发明提供一种强度高，能够有效地得到大量的氢的氢生成装置。 该氢气发生装置， 具有外筒1， 54为壳体，其中心为炉筒2， 51设置成点燃燃烧器6， 多个圆筒形催化剂室设置在其周围，来自炉筒的热空气通过与催化剂室相连的热空气管，以加热催化剂室并提高催化剂的活性。 将催化剂，碱金属熔盐注入到催化剂室中，并在催化剂上部的反应空间S，54中供应蒸汽，以从蒸汽中获得氢气。', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To provide a hydrogen generation unit large in strength and capable of efficiently obtaining a large quantity of hydrogen.SOLUTION :  This hydrogen generation unit,  has an outer cylinder 1,  54 as a casing and at the center of it a furnace cylinder 2,  51 is set to fire a burner 6,  and a plurality of cylindrical catalyst cells 3,  56 are set around it,  and hot air from the furnace cylinder 2,  51 is passed through a hot air pipe 8,  57 attached to the catalyst cell to heat the catalyst cell and enhance the activity of the catalyst. The catalyst,  an alkali metal melt salt,  is injected into the catalyst cell,  and steam is supplied in the reaction space S,  54 at the upper part of the catalyst to obtain hydrogen from the steam.', p.application_date = '2010-04-02 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP5940759B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'SG11201403415U'}) SET p.application_no = 'SG11201403415U', p.title_cn = '用于将二氧化碳转化为一氧化碳的方法和系统', p.title_en = 'PROCESS AND SYSTEM FOR CONVERSION OF CARBON DIOXIDE TO CARBON MONOXIDE', p.abstract_cn = '描述了使用烃将二氧化碳CO2转化为一氧化碳CO的方法和装置。 在进一步细节中，描述了用于产生合成气的工艺和装置，并且描述了用于使用CO2和烃将合成气转化为合成官能化和/或非官能化烃的工艺和装置。 通过所述方法和装置，可以转化工业过程中排放的二氧化碳，并且可以减少释放到大气中的二氧化碳的量。', p.abstract_en = 'A process and a device for converting carbon dioxide CO2 to carbon monoxide CO,  using hydrocarbons are described. In further details,  processes and devices are described for generating synthesis gases and processes and devices are described for converting synthesis gases to synthetic functionalized and/or non-functionalized hydrocarbons,  using CO2 and hydrocarbons. By means of the processes and the devices,  carbon dioxide emitted from industrial process can be converted and the amount of carbon dioxide released into the atmosphere can be decreased.', p.application_date = '2012-12-20 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'SG11201403415UB', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/24', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'SG11201604070R'}) SET p.application_no = 'SG11201604070R', p.title_cn = '发电系统及其相关方法', p.title_en = 'POWER GENERATION SYSTEMS AND METHODS REGARDING SAME', p.abstract_cn = '还提供了提供热能和电能中的至少一种如直接电或热-电的固体燃料电源，其为动力系统提供动力，所述动力系统包括(i)至少一个用于催化原子氢以形成分数氢的反应电池，(ii)包含至少两种选自以下的组分的化学燃料混合物 : H20催化剂源或H20催化剂; 原子氢或原子氢的源; 形成H20催化剂源或H20催化剂和原子氢源或原子氢的反应物; 引发原子氢催化的一种或多种反应物; 和使固体燃料具有高导电性的材料，(iii)至少一组限制燃料的电极和电源，该电源提供短时间的低电压、高电流电能以引发分数氢反应的快速动力学和由于形成分数氢而获得的能量，(iv)产物回收系统，例如冷凝器，(v)再加载系统，(vi)水合、热、化学和电化学系统中的至少一种以从反应产物再生燃料， (vii)散热器，其接受来自产生功率的反应的热，(viii)功率转换系统，其可包括直接等离子体到电转换器，例如等离子体动力转换器、磁流体动力转换器、电磁直接(交叉场或漂移)转换器、直接转换器和电荷漂移转换器，或热到电功率转换器，例如兰金或布雷顿型发电厂。', p.abstract_en = 'A solid fuel power source that provides at least one of thermal and electrical power such as direct electricity or thermal to electricity is further provided that powers a power system comprising (i) at least one reaction cell for the catalysis of atomic hydrogen to form hydrinos,  (ii) a chemical fuel mixture comprising at least two components chosen from :  a source of H20 catalyst or H20 catalyst;  a source of atomic hydrogen or atomic hydrogen;  reactants to form the source of H20 catalyst or H20 catalyst and a source of atomic hydrogen or atomic hydrogen;  one or more reactants to initiate the catalysis of atomic hydrogen;  and a material to cause the solid fuel to be highly conductive,  (iii) at least one set of electrodes that confine the fuel and an electrical power source that provides a short burst of low-voltage,  high-current electrical energy to initiate rapid kinetics of the hydrino reaction and an energy gain due to forming hydrinos,  (iv) a product recovery systems such as a condenser,  (v) a reloading system,  (vi) at least one of hydration,  thermal,  chemical,  and electrochemical systems to regenerate the fuel from the reaction products,  (vii) a heat sink that accepts the heat from the power-producing reactions,  (viii) a power conversion system that may comprise a direct plasma to electric converter such as a plasmadynamic converter,  magnetohydrodynamic converter,  electromagnetic direct (crossed field or drift) converter,  direct converter,  and charge drift converter or a thermal to electric power converter such as a Rankine or Brayton-type power plant.', p.application_date = '2014-01-10 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'SG11201604070RA', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US13715007'}) SET p.application_no = 'US13715007', p.title_cn = '金属氢化物及其在储氢应用中应用', p.title_en = 'Metal hydrides and their use in hydrogen storage applications', p.abstract_cn = '本公开涉及新型金属氢化物、其制备方法及其在储氢应用中的应用。', p.abstract_en = 'This disclosure relates to novel metal hydrides,  processes for their preparation,  and their use in hydrogen storage applications.', p.application_date = '2012-12-14 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9376316B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 3, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14465274'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14465274', p.title_cn = '产氢方法', p.title_en = 'Method of generating hydrogen', p.abstract_cn = '催化剂寿命长，能有效地将氢与水分离。 在碱金属氢氧化物或碱土金属氢氧化物中熔化用于切断氢氧结合的第一金属元素Ni、Pd、Pt和用于帮助第一金属元素发挥作用的第二金属元素Cr、Mo、W、Fe，以使混合物在高于氢氧化物熔点的温度下加热，以从液体表面喷射出细颗粒，使蒸汽与细颗粒接触。 取而代之的是，在高于碱金属氢氧化物熔点的温度下加热碱金属氢氧化物和金属氧化物的混合物以制备其中至少两种金属元素熔化的金属化合物，并从金属化合物的表面喷射细颗粒以使其与蒸汽接触。', p.abstract_en = 'A catalyst has a long life span and efficiently separates hydrogen from water. A first metal element (Ni,  Pd,  Pt) for cutting the combination of hydrogen and oxygen and a second metal element (Cr,  Mo,  W,  Fe) for helping the function of the first metal element are melted in alkaline metal hydroxide or alkaline earth metal hydroxide to make a mixture heated at a temperature above the melting point of the hydroxide to eject fine particles from the liquid surface,  bringing steam into contact with the fine particles. Instead of this,  a mixture of alkaline metal hydroxide and metal oxide is heated at a temperature above the melting point of the alkaline metal hydroxide to make metal compound in which at least two kinds of metal elements are melted,  and fine particles are ejected from the surface of the metal compound to be brought into contact with steam.', p.application_date = '2014-08-21 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9376317B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/10', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'RU2014148574'}) SET p.application_no = 'RU2014148574', p.title_cn = '方法和装置用于生产合成气', p.title_en = 'METHOD AND DEVICE FOR PRODUCTION OF SYNTHESIS OF-GAS', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种生产合成气的方法和装置(5)通过蒸汽重整，其中氮气分离从原料(1)包含烃类和氮以产生低氮进料(4)的燃烧器的燃烧蒸汽重整器(D)，形成含烃的残余气体(2)随后作为燃料(6)。氮气中分离出吸附(N)从该起始材料和含有残留气体的烃(2)用于点火燃烧蒸汽重整器(D)。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a process and an apparatus for producing synthesis gas (5) by steam reforming,  in which nitrogen is separated off from a starting material (1) containing hydrocarbons and nitrogen in order to produce a low-nitrogen feed (4) for a burner-fired steam reformer (D),  with formation of a hydrocarbon-containing residual gas (2) which subsequently serves as fuel (6). Nitrogen is separated off adsorptively (N) from the starting material and the hydrocarbon-containing residual gas (2) is used for firing the steam reformer (D).', p.application_date = '2014-12-02 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'RU2014148574A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/56', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'RU2013137381'}) SET p.application_no = 'RU2013137381', p.title_cn = '用于处理气体的流量的方法和装置', p.title_en = 'METHOD AND DEVICE FOR PROCESSING GAS FLOW', p.abstract_cn = '领域 : 燃气行业的物质。本发明涉及一种用于处理的方法和装置在溶解过程中氢气释放的金属与酸或碱。方法包括将氢气释放的气体在通过反应器含有氧化剂的氧化氢气体到水中，然后回收氧化剂。氧化剂与一种惰性稀释剂稀释。装置包括反应器与氧化剂，所述反应器至少部分地浸没在浴氧化铝。效果 : 保证了降低成本，延长使用氧化agent.18Cl，3的DWG', p.abstract_en = 'FIELD :  gas industry.SUBSTANCE :  invention relates to a method and apparatus for processing hydrogen gas released during dissolution of metal with acid or alkali. Method comprises feeding hydrogen gas released through a reactor containing oxidant gas for oxidising hydrogen to water and then recovery of oxidant. Oxidant is diluted with an inert diluent. Apparatus comprises a reactor with an oxidant,  wherein reactor is at least partially immersed in a bath of alumina.EFFECT :  ensures cost reduction and prolonged use of oxidising agent.18 cl,  3 dwg', p.application_date = '2012-01-11 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'RU2588219C2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/08', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'VN1201601081'}) SET p.application_no = 'VN1201601081', p.title_cn = '氢气调制方法', p.title_en = 'Hydrogen preparation method', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及对甲醇等烃类化合物进行不完全氧化反应和水蒸气重整聚合反应生成氢气的制氢方法，该方法可延长催化剂的使用寿命，制氢长期稳定。 由甲醇和水组成的液态原燃料在蒸汽气化炉(1)中蒸发，由气化炉储存器组成的气态原燃料被蒸发，氧气被送入反应器(2a)，通过进行甲醇的不完全氧化反应和水蒸气重整反应(分解反应)生成氢气。 给出用于汽化装置(2A)中液体原燃料蒸发的热源，利用在气体燃烧室(9)中产生的燃烧热。 在气体燃烧室(9)中产生的燃烧热是利用从氢气分离器(3)以多级方式解吸的解吸气体作为燃烧气体通过燃烧产生的。 氢气分离器(3)使解吸气体逸出，同时改变解吸气体的逸出量。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a hydrogen production method for generating hydrogen by performing incomplete oxidation reaction and steam reforming polymerization reaction on hydrocarbon compounds such as methanol,  which can prolong the service life of a catalyst and stabilize hydrogen production for a long time. A liquid raw fuel composed of methanol and water is evaporated in a steam gasifier (1),  a gaseous raw fuel composed of a gasifier reservoir is evaporated,  oxygen is fed to a reactor (2a),  and hydrogen gas is generated by performing an incomplete oxidation reaction of methanol and a steam reforming reaction (decomposition reaction). A heat source for vaporize that liquid raw fuel in the vaporizing device (2A) is provide,  utilizing the combustion heat generated in the gas combustion chamber (9). The combustion heat generated in the gas combustion chamber (9) is generated by combustion using desorption gas desorbed from the hydrogen separator (3) in a multi-stage manner as combustion gas. The hydrogen separator (3) escapes the desorption gas while changing the escaping amount of the desorption gas.', p.application_date = '2016-03-25 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'VN47641A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'IN5132CHE2013'}) SET p.application_no = 'IN5132CHE2013', p.title_cn = '生产氢气和水的集成方法', p.title_en = 'INTEGRATED PROCESS FOR THE PRODUCTION OF HYDROGEN AND WATER', p.abstract_cn = '含产品氢的制造方法和一种或多种液态水利用催化蒸汽-烃重整产品。在该方法中，所述补充水一部分被加热的重整的补充水，另一部分加热的燃烧产物气体，然后将除氧器的补充水。燃烧产物气体中的水被冷凝形成液态水的产品。本方法可集成有热海水淡化过程。', p.abstract_en = 'Process for producing a hydrogen-containing product and one or more liquid water products using catalytic steam-hydrocarbon reforming. In the process,  a portion of the make-up water is heated by the reformate and another portion of the make-up water is heated by the combustion product gas prior to introducing the make-up water to a deaerator. Water in the combustion product gas is condensed to form a liquid water product. The process may be integrated with a thermal water desalination process.', p.application_date = '2013-11-12 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'IN5132CHE2013A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'IN6387DELNP2015'}) SET p.application_no = 'IN6387DELNP2015', p.title_cn = '一种储氢材料', p.title_en = 'A HYDROGEN STORAGE MATERIAL', p.abstract_cn = '一种含氨硼烷储氢材料和聚环氧乙烷)，其中所述聚(环氧乙烷)具有的重均分子量大于或等于imda和小于或等于9的MDA。', p.abstract_en = 'A hydrogen-storage-material comprising ammonia borane and polyethylene oxide),  wherein the poly(ethylene oxide) has a weight average molecular weight of greater than or equal to IMDa and of less than or equal to 9MDa.', p.application_date = '2015-07-21 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'IN6387DELNP2015A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'KR1020150093758'}) SET p.application_no = 'KR1020150093758', p.title_cn = '甲烷水蒸气重整，以镍/氧化铝纳米复合催化剂或镍/氧化硅-氧化铝混合纳米复合材料催化剂', p.title_en = 'Methane steam reforming,  using nickel/alumina nanocomposite catalyst or nickel/silica-alumina hybrid nanocomposite catalyst', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及镍/氧化铝纳米方法涉及一种用于蒸汽甲烷重整，熔融镍支撑体通过浸渍具有金属纳米粒子均匀，承受高负载的镍/氧化铝纳米复合通过使用该催化剂空速高或者相对小的供给水蒸汽即使在极端的反应条件优良的甲烷转化率进行蒸汽重整甲烷的方法和催化剂也就是一种。此外，在本发明所述熔体进行每当一种催化剂生产1号2号至ED B催化剂为催化剂，镍的二氧化硅轭壳催化剂混合的镍/氧化硅-氧化铝混杂纳米复合材料的时间蒸汽加热器和然后催化剂甲烷蒸汽重整时相同的应用，催化活性甚至700°C或更高温度下甲烷优异的记录物进行蒸汽重整的甲烷转化比可反应的发生。', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention relates to a methane steam reforming method using a nickel/alumina nanocomposite catalyst. More particularly,  the present invention relates to a method for carrying out steam reforming of methane with a high methane conversion ratio,  even under a relatively severe reaction condition including a high space velocity or low steam supply,  by using a nickel/alumina nanocomposite catalyst including a support in which nickel metal nanoparticles are supported uniformly at a high content through a melt impregnation process,  and a catalyst used therefor. In addition,  according to the present invention,  the catalyst obtained by the melt impregnation process is used as a first catalyst and mixed with a nickel silica yoke-shell catalyst as a second catalyst to provide a nickel/silica-alumina hybrid nanocatalyst. When applying the hybrid nanocatalyst to a methane steam reforming reaction,  it is possible to obtain higher catalytic activity even at a higher temperature of 700&deg; C or more,  and thus to carry out steam reforming of methane with a high methane conversion ratio.COPYRIGHT KIPO 2016', p.application_date = '2015-06-30 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'KR101634946B1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/40', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'KR1020140089001'}) SET p.application_no = 'KR1020140089001', p.title_cn = '产生氢的方法使用固态化学氢化物', p.title_en = 'METHOD OF HYDROGEN GENERATION USING SOLID-STATE CHEMICAL HYDRIDE', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种使用固体化学氢化物制氢的方法，所述方法包括以下步骤 : 存放固态化学氢化物氢发生器内；将碳酸氢钠(NaHCO3)内的化学氢化物氢发生器中的存储；化学氢化物制氢的反应与碳酸氢钠。本发明的目的是提供一种使用固体化学氢化物制氢的方法，该方法能够产生氢气的存放固态化学氢化物氢发生器内，提供一种燃料电池运行时所必需的碳酸氢钠水溶液，从而直接降低固态化学氢化物。', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention relates to a hydrogen generating method using solid chemical hydride,  the method comprising the steps of :  storing solid-state chemical hydride inside a hydrogen generator;  supplying sodium bicarbonate (NaHCO3) inside the hydrogen generator in which the chemical hydride is stored;  and generating hydrogen by reacting the chemical hydride with the sodium bicarbonate. The purpose of the present invention is to provide a hydrogen generating method using solid chemical hydride,  the method enabling the generation of hydrogen by storing solid-state chemical hydride inside a hydrogen generator,  and supplying a sodium bicarbonate aqueous solution when fuel cell operation is necessary,  thereby directly degrading the solid-state chemical hydride.', p.application_date = '2014-07-15 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'KR101635129B1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/06', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'NZ625687'}) SET p.application_no = 'NZ625687', p.title_cn = '二氧化碳的方法和系统用于转换到一氧化碳', p.title_en = 'Process and system for conversion of carbon dioxide to carbon monoxide', p.abstract_cn = '一用于转化二氧化碳的方法和装置使用烃类的CO2注入一氧化碳CO被描述。在进一步的实施方案，用于产生合成气的方法和装置和方法和装置用于将合成气到合成官能化和/或非官能化描述了使用CO2和烃的烃。该方法和装置适于将排放的CO2工业过程，从而二氧化碳排放到大气中的量可以减少。', p.abstract_en = 'A process and an apparatus for converting carbon dioxide CO2 into carbon monoxide CO using hydrocarbons are described. In further embodiments,  processes and apparatuses for generating synthesis gas and processes and apparatuses for converting synthesis gas into synthetic functionalised and/or non-functionalised hydrocarbons using CO2 and hydrocarbons are described. The processes and apparatuses are adapted to convert CO2 emitted by industrial processes,  and thus the amount of carbon dioxide emitted into the atmosphere may be reduced.', p.application_date = '2012-12-20 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'NZ625687A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/24', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'UAU201513084'}) SET p.application_no = 'UAU201513084', p.title_cn = '从碱性溶液中电催化释放氢的方法', p.title_en = 'METHOD OF ELECTROCATALYTIC RELEASE OF HYDROGEN FROM ALKALINE SOLUTIONS', p.abstract_cn = '从碱性溶液中电催化释放氢的方法，其中反应在电极上由无定形合金在KON溶液中发生。作为电极材料，使用非晶合金FeNbGdB，其另外在Τ=823 K的温度下热处理1小时，并且在(295 ÷ 305)K的温度下加热5.0 Μ水溶液KON。', p.abstract_en = 'The method of electrocatalytic release of hydrogen from alkaline solutions,  in which the reaction occurs on an electrode from an amorphous alloy in a solution of KON. As an electrode material,  the amorphous alloy FeNbGdB is used,  which is additionally heat treated at a temperature of Τ = 823 K for 1 hour,  and 5.0 Μ Aqueous solution KON is heated at a temperature (295÷305) K.', p.application_date = '2015-12-30 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'UA107948U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/54', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'UAA201409311'}) SET p.application_no = 'UAA201409311', p.title_cn = '背景 : AMIXI，AMISTI，ABO.AMOZOTU，VODNYAMIAKU。', p.title_en = 'METHOD OF PURIFICATION OF AMMONIA,  MIXTURES OF NITROGEN AND HYDROGEN,  OR NITROGEN,  HYDROGEN AND AMMONIA', p.abstract_cn = '氨的精制方法或氮和氢的混合物，或氮气，氢气和氨，其中氨或从0.1至25兆帕压力下的气体混合物通过柱填充有氧化铝具有较大的比表面积，气体氨或其混合物，然后通过柱子与CaO，NaOH，KOH或NaOH的聚合物熔体，单独或混合物，在20至70℃下，压力为从0.1至25兆帕，与氨或气体混合物通过填充有活性炭具有比表面积与钠的100-3000/g，钾，铯，镁，钙，锶，钡或硝酸铈(Ⅴ)或硝酸根(Ⅲ)在其表面沉积，单独或混合物。', p.abstract_en = 'Method for purification of ammonia or mixtures of nitrogen and hydrogen,  or nitrogen,  hydrogen and ammonia,  where ammonia or a mixture of gases under pressure of from 0.1 to 25 MPa is passed through a column packed with aluminum oxide with a large specific surface area,  the ammonia or mixture of gases is then passed through a column packed with CaO,  NaOH,  KOH or an NaOH/KOH melt,  separately or in a mixture,  at 20 to 70° C. and under pressure of from 0.1 to 25 MPa,  and the ammonia or mixture of gases is passed through a column packed with activated carbon having a specific area of 100-3000 m2/g with sodium,  potassium,  caesium,  magnesium,  calcium,  strontium,  barium or cerium nitrates(V) or nitrates(III) deposited on its surface,  separately or in a mixture.', p.application_date = '2013-06-07 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'UA111880C2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'UAA201411968'}) SET p.application_no = 'UAA201411968', p.title_cn = '对COCOCOSOGO的动态和动态的研究', p.title_en = 'METHOD OF OBTAINING NITROGEN MIXTURE FROM REVERSE COKE OVEN GAS IN AMMONIA PRODUCTION', p.abstract_cn = '本发明属于氮肥生产，具体是一种氨生产。 氨生产中由可逆焦炉煤气制备氮杂混合物的方法，顺序包括回流焦炉煤气的加入和加料，用于精炼； 含硫杂质对可逆焦炉煤气的净化； 向往复式焦炉煤气中引入水蒸气； 往复式焦炉煤气加热； 供风给热； 空气加热； 往复式焦炉煤气的蒸汽气转化； 水蒸气转化法净化从一氧化碳中制得的氮酮混合物； 用水碱溶液洗涤二氧化碳中的氮混合物，并通过其甲烷化最终净化一氧化碳中的氮混合物。 该方法的特点是利用部分制氮混合气经含硫杂质处理后送入可逆焦炉煤气，在进行其蒸汽转化时进行可逆焦炉煤气成分调整，再转化前对可逆焦炉煤气进行再转化，分别为3.0~3.5 MPa和3.5 MPa。 本发明为该方法的实现提供了一种降低能源和资金成本的方法，并使可逆焦炉煤气的合理使用成为可能。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention belongs to the production of nitrogen fertilizers,  in particular to the production of ammonia. Method of obtaining nitrogen-water mixture from reverse coke oven gas in ammonia production,  which consistently includes compression and supply of reverse coke oven gas for purification;  purification of reverse coke oven gas from sulfur impurities;  introduction of water vapor into reverse coke oven gas;  heating of reverse coke oven gas;  air supply for heating;  air heating;  vapor-air conversion of return coke oven gas;  purification of the resulting nitrogen-water mixture from carbon monoxide by steam conversion;  purification of nitrogen mixture from carbon dioxide by washing with water alkaline solutions and final purification of nitrogen mixture from carbon monoxide by throwing it. The method is characterized by the fact that the composition of the reverse coke oven gas is regulated when carrying out its vapor-air conversion by using part of the resulting nitrogen-water mixture,  which is fed into reverse coke oven gas after its purification from sulfur impurities,  and the compression and heating of reverse coke oven gas before its vapor-air conversion is carried out in accordance with 3.0-3.5 MPa and . The invention reduces the energy and capital costs for the implementation of the method and makes it possible to rationally use reverse coke oven gas.', p.application_date = '2014-11-05 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'UA111896C2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'AU2014364748'}) SET p.application_no = 'AU2014364748', p.title_cn = '生产氨合成气的方法', p.title_en = 'Process for producing ammonia synthesis gas', p.abstract_cn = '一种方法和相关设备，用于从含烃进料生产氨合成气(20)，所述方法包括以下步骤 : 一次重整的蒸汽(21)，二次重整与氧化剂流(23)，纯化的流出物，所述二次转化，本发明的净化方法包括以下步骤 : (13)一氧化碳变换，所述的合成气(25)通过所述二级蒸汽转化中进行温度漂移过的铜基催化剂，以及所述全局过程中蒸汽与碳的比例不大于2。', p.abstract_en = 'A process and a related equipment for producing ammonia synthesis gas from a hydrocarbon-containing feedstock (20),  the process comprising the steps of :  primary reforming with steam (21),  secondary reforming with an oxidant stream (23),  and purification of the effluent of said secondary reforming,  said purification comprising a step of shift conversion (13) of carbon monoxide,  wherein the synthesis gas (25) produced by said secondary reforming is subject to a medium-temperature shift over a copper-based catalyst,  and the global steam to carbon ratio of the process is not greater than 2.', p.application_date = '2014-12-16 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'AU2014364748A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CA2969887'}) SET p.application_no = 'CA2969887', p.title_cn = '脱胶反应器', p.title_en = 'REACTOR FOR DEGUMMING', p.abstract_cn = '反应器提高收率，降低了植物油进行脱胶的磷脂。所述反应器包括环形堵塞的具有多个周向隔垫物围绕中心主体，该主体具有形成环的间隙锥形表面。周向隔垫物和环的间隙与油相混合形成的爆炸减压脱胶剂。杂质被转移到所述脱胶剂的部件可以进行进一步分离，以产生精制后的油品。', p.abstract_en = 'A reactor is used for degumming vegetable oil to increase yield and reduce phosphatides. The reactor includes an annular obstruction with multiple circumferential spacers that form ring gaps around a center body having a tapered surface. The circumferential spacers and ring gaps form decompression stages for explosively mixing the oil with degumming agents. Impurities are transferred to the degumming agents and further separation of the components can be carried out to produce a refined oil product.', p.application_date = '2014-12-15 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CA2969887A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'DE602010039683'}) SET p.application_no = 'DE602010039683', p.title_cn = '燃料电池系统', p.title_en = 'FUEL CELL SYSTEM', p.abstract_cn = '燃料电池系统(100)按照本发明包括 : 一种氢气发生器(1)被配置成产生燃料气体用的原燃料通过重整反应；燃料电池(7)，被配置为利用燃气发电；燃烧器(2)，被构造用以加热所述氢气发生器(1)；至少一个在开关阀(9a，9b)构造成打开/阻塞气体通道(9)，通过它发出的气体从氢气发生器(1)供给到燃烧器(2)；和燃烧用空气供给装置(4)被配置成供应燃烧空气的燃烧器(2)；点火装置(5)设置在所述燃烧室(2)，和控制器(30)。所述燃烧器(2)被配置为进行燃烧发电的燃料电池(7)时利用气体通过气体供给通道(9)。在意外熄火的情况发生，在燃烧器(2)中的发电燃料电池(7)，控制器(30)进行点火的点火操作装置(5)与通断阀(9a，9b)保持打开。', p.abstract_en = 'A fuel cell system (100) according to the present invention includes :  a hydrogen generator (1) configured to generate a fuel gas through a reforming reaction by using a raw fuel;  a fuel cell (7) configured to generate power by using the fuel gas;  a combustor (2) configured to heat the hydrogen generator (1);  at least one on-off valve (9A,  9B) configured to open/block a gas passage (9) through which the gas that is sent out from the hydrogen generator (1) is supplied to the combustor (2);  and a combustion air supply device (4) configured to supply combustion air to the combustor (2);  an ignition device (5) provided at the combustor (2),  and a controller (30). The combustor (2) is configured to perform combustion during power generation of the fuel cell (7) by using the gas supplied through the gas passage (9). In a case where accidental flame extinction has occurred at the combustor (2) during the power generation of the fuel cell (7),  the controller (30) performs an ignition operation of the ignition device (5) with the on-off valve (9A,  9B) kept opened.', p.application_date = '2010-03-26 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'DE602010039683T2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WOBR15050242'}) SET p.application_no = 'WOBR15050242', p.title_cn = '氢制造方法和非腐蚀性的碱性离子化合物；碱性电解液；和非corrovise碱性离子性化合物', p.title_en = 'METHOD FOR PRODUCING HYDROGEN AND NON-CORROSIVE ALKALINE IONIC COMPOUND;  ALKALINE ELECTROLYTIC SOLUTION;  AND NON-CORROVISE ALKALINE IONIC COMPOUND', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种新氢和强碱性离子化合物的制造方法，以水解反应打断水分子，所述温度维持在一定范围内允许规则和平稳释放氢气，蒸汽替代氢气，其得到的共水解反应制氢的方法。更具体地，本发明涉及一种在工业规模制备氢气的方法，现在已知的这种类型的方法不同，只在实验室规模制氢。该方法包括将至少一种离子化合物(贱和/或碱性盐)，水，至少一种酸和至少一种金属。本发明还涉及碱性电解液和一种强碱性离子化合物，会产生自相矛盾，无腐蚀性。', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention relates to a new method for producing hydrogen and a strongly alkaline ionic compound,  using a hydrolysis reaction to break water molecules,  the temperature being maintained within limits which allow a regular and stable release of hydrogen gas,  instead of hydrogen vapour,  which is obtained by the common method for producing hydrogen by hydrolysis reactions. More specifically,  the invention relates to a method for producing hydrogen gas on an industrial scale,  unlike the methods of this type that are known today,  which produce hydrogen only on a laboratory scale. The method consists in combining at least one ionic compound (a base and/or a basic salt),  water,  at least one acid and at least one metal. The present invention also relates to an alkaline electrolytic solution and to a strongly alkaline ionic compound which,  paradoxically,  is not corrosive.', p.application_date = '2015-12-10 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016094998A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/06', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WOUS14070302'}) SET p.application_no = 'WOUS14070302', p.title_cn = '脱胶反应器', p.title_en = 'REACTOR FOR DEGUMMING', p.abstract_cn = '反应器提高收率，降低了植物油进行脱胶的磷脂。该反应器包括一个具有多个周向间隔的环形堵塞的中心体四周的空隙构成环具有锥形表面。周向隔垫物和环的间隙与油相混合形成的爆炸减压脱胶剂。杂质被转移到所述脱胶剂的成分可以进一步分离精制后的油品进行生产。', p.abstract_en = 'A reactor is used for degumming vegetable oil to increase yield and reduce phosphatides. The reactor includes an annular obstruction with multiple circumferential spacers that form ring gaps around a center body having a tapered surface. The circumferential spacers and ring gaps form decompression stages for explosively mixing the oil with degumming agents. Impurities are transferred to the degumming agents and further separation of the components can be carried out to produce a refined oil product.', p.application_date = '2014-12-15 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016099440A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WOUS15066279'}) SET p.application_no = 'WOUS15066279', p.title_cn = '带有浮力的气体发生器催化剂载体', p.title_en = 'GAS GENERATOR WITH BUOYANT CATALYST CARRIER', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种气体发生器，包括反应液反应产生的气体在催化剂的存在下。所述催化剂包含在载体中的浮子是漂浮在所述液体反应物。该气体发生器还具有至少一个载波的位置的移动限制构件，其适于有选择地控制载体，和至少一个含有气体的体积可压缩体。第一的配置中，当内部气体压力的内部压力低于发生器，可压缩体可压缩体体积增加，在气体发生器第二配置在当内部压力高于所述可压缩体内部压力，可压缩减小体积。载体第一中的移动的移动限制构件限制所述载体结构。', p.abstract_en = 'Disclosed herein is a gas generator that contains a liquid reactant that reacts to produce a gas in the presence of a catalyst. The catalyst is contained in a carrier that is buoyant in the liquid reactant. The gas generator also has at least one carrier movement restraining member adapted to selectively control the location of the carrier,  and at least one compressible body containing a volume of gas. In a first configuration,  when an internal pressure of the gas generator is lower than an internal pressure of the compressible body,  the compressible body increases in volume,  and in a second configuration when the internal pressure of the gas generator is higher than the internal pressure of the compressible body,  the compressible body decreases in volume. The carrier movement restraining member restricts the carrier\'s movement in the first configuration.', p.application_date = '2015-12-17 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016100613A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201380031048.2'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201380031048.2', p.title_cn = '制备乙炔和合成气的方法', p.title_en = 'Preparation of acetylene and synthesis gas', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种通过烃和氧气的部分氧化反应制备乙炔和合成气的方法实现。在所述方法中，将含有一种或多种烃的第一进料料流和含有氧气的第二进料料流分别地预加热，按照第二进料料流与第一进料料流的质量流速比率对应于小于或等于0.31的氧气比率λ进行混合，并且经由烧嘴砖供应到燃烧室。在所述燃烧室中进行烃的部分氧化反应。获得裂解气体，其在燃烧室的下游通过注射含水骤冷介质被骤冷到80-90℃，得到工艺水料流Iliq和产物气体料流Ig。所述产物气体料流在冷却塔中通过与冷却水的直接热交换而冷却，得到作为底部料流的工艺水料流IIliq、作为顶部料流的产物气体料流IIg和侧料流，所述侧料流在静电过滤器中贫化烟灰。在静电过滤器中得到工艺水料流IIIliq。工艺水料流Iliq、IIliq和IIIliq进行合并，并从具有表面颗粒沉淀剂的烟灰通道通过，得到合并的工艺水料流IVliq。此方法的特征在于包括将合并的工艺水料流IVliq通过在一步闪蒸装置中的部分蒸发进行清洁，所述合并的工艺水料流IVliq是按照基于其总重量计的0.01-10重量％的比率蒸发，从而得到清洁的工艺水料流Vliq，其被循环到工艺中。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a method for producing acetylene and synthesis gas by partially oxidizing hydrocarbons by means of oxygen. In said method,  a first input flow containing one or more hydrocarbons and a second input flow containing oxygen are preheated separately from each other,  mixed at a ratio of the mass flow rate of the second input flow to the mass flow rate of the first input flow corresponding to an oxygen number lambda less than or equal to 0.31,  and fed via a burner block to a combustion chamber. The hydrocarbons are partially oxidized in the combustion chamber. A cracked gas is thereby obtained,  which is quenched to 80 to 90 degrees Celsius downstream of the combustion chamber by injecting an aqueous quenching medium. A process water flow Iliq and a product gas flow Ig are obtained. The product gas flow is cooled down in a cooling column by means of direct heat exchange with cooling water in order to obtain a process water flow IIliq as a bottom flow,  a product gas flow IIg as a top flow,  and a side flow,  which is depleted of soot in an electric filter. A process water flow IIIliq arises in the electric filter. The process water flows Iliq,  IIliq,  and IIIliq are merged and conducted via soot grooves having surface particle separators in order to obtain a merged process water flow IVliq. The method is characterized in that the merged process water flow IVliq is subjected to cleaning by means of partial evaporation in a single-stage flash tank,  the merged process water flow IVliq being evaporated to a fraction of 0.01 wt% to 10 wt%,  in relation to the total weight thereof,  in order to obtain a cleaned process water flow Vliq,  which is recycled into the method.', p.application_date = '2013-06-13 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN104379501B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/36', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201510051811.9'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201510051811.9', p.title_cn = '一种将石油炼厂解析废气转化成制氢工艺原料气的方法', p.title_en = 'A analyzing petroleum refinery waste gas into hydrogen production process method of the raw material gas', p.abstract_cn = '本发明提供一种将石油炼厂解析废气转化成制氢工艺原料气的方法，通过解析废气，经过预处理后，分成两个部分，第一部分直接送入甲烷二氧化碳重整反应器，第二部分送入自热重整反应器；甲烷二氧化碳重整反应器采用流化床的型式，反应器顶部采用旋风分离器分离重整后气体中的催化剂，催化剂进入自热重整反应器的燃烧段。自热重整反应器中通入氧气在燃烧段进行不完全燃烧，烧掉甲烷二氧化碳重整催化剂上的积碳，进行催化剂再生；再生后的催化剂和不完全燃烧的气体进入旋风分离器后进行催化剂分离，催化剂返回甲烷二氧化碳重整反应器使用，剩余气体进入自热重整反应器转化段进行重整，使甲烷转化为氢气。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention provides a method for converting desorbed waste gases from a petroleum refinery to feed gases used in a hydrogen production process. The method comprises the steps that after being pretreated,  the desorbed waste gases are divided into two parts,  the first part is directly sent to a carbon dioxide reforming reactor of methane and the second part is sent to an autothermal reforming reactor;  the carbon dioxide reforming reactor of methane adopts a form of fluidized bed and a cyclone separator is adopted at the top of the reactor to separate a catalyst in the reformed gases;  the catalyst enters a combustion section of the autothermal reforming reactor;  oxygen is pumped into the autothermal reforming reactor so as to carry out incomplete combustion on the combustion section to burn out carbon deposits on a carbon dioxide reforming catalyst of methane to regenerate a catalyst;  the regenerated catalyst and the gases characterized by incomplete combustion enter the cyclone separator and then the catalyst is separated and returns to the carbon dioxide reforming reactor of methane to be used;  the residual gases enter a conversion section of the autothermal reforming reactor to be reformed so as to convert methane to hydrogen.', p.application_date = '2015-01-30 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN104609368B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/34', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201410714748.8'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201410714748.8', p.title_cn = '制备合成氨原料气的系统及方法', p.title_en = 'System and method for preparing synthetic ammonia raw gas', p.abstract_cn = '本发明提供了一种制备合成氨原料气的系统及方法。所述系统包括：膜反应器；密封于膜反应器中的透氧膜；分别装填于透氧膜两侧的催化剂模块I和催化剂模块II；用于向透氧膜一侧导入原料气的气体导入装置I，以及向透氧膜的相对侧导入吹扫气的气体导入装置II；作为原料气的水蒸气和空气的混合气，以及作为吹扫气的还原性气体。通过调节通入膜反应器中空气和还原性气体的流速，可得到不同氢氮比的原料气。使用本发明的系统及方法，以水和空气为初始原料在膜反应器中直接制备合成氨原料气。产品中不含有一氧化碳且该方法的操作、装置都十分简单，大大减少了制备合成氨原料气的工序，节省了大量的能源。同时还能获得其它有价值的化工产品。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention provides a system and method for preparing a synthetic ammonia raw gas. The system includes a membrane reactor,  an oxygen permeation membrane sealed in the membrane reactor,  a catalyst module I,  a catalyst module II,  a gas guide device I for guiding raw gas to one side of the oxygen permeation membrane,  a gas guide device II for guiding sweeping gas to the opposite side of the oxygen permeation membrane,  water vapor and air mixed gas as the raw gas,  and a reducing gas as the sweeping gas,  wherein two sides of the oxygen permeation membrane are filled with the catalyst module I and the catalyst module II respectively. Through adjusting the flow rate of air and the reducing gas introduced to the membrane reactor,  the raw gases with different hydrogen/nitrogen ratios can be obtained. By using the system and the method,  the synthetic ammonia raw gas is directly prepared with water and the air as initial raw materials in the membrane reactor. The product does not contain carbon monoxide,  the operation of the method and the operation of the device are both quite simple,  and the processes of preparing the synthetic ammonia raw gas are greatly reduced,  and a large amount of energy is saved. At the same time,  other valuable chemical products can also be obtained.', p.application_date = '2014-11-28 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105692548A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201410709667.9'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201410709667.9', p.title_cn = '制备高纯度氢气的系统及方法', p.title_en = 'A system for preparing high-purity hydrogen and a method therefor', p.abstract_cn = '本发明提供了一种制备高纯度氢气的系统及方法。所述系统包括：膜反应器；密封于膜反应器中的透氧膜；分别装填于透氧膜两侧的催化剂模块I和催化剂模块II；用于向透氧膜一侧导入原料气的气体导入装置I，以及向透氧膜的相对侧导入吹扫气的气体导入装置II；作为原料气的水蒸气，以及作为吹扫气的低纯度氢气。本发明制备高纯度氢气的方法是以低纯度氢气为原料在混合导体透氧膜反应器中分离得到高纯度氢气。该方法的氢气的分离速率和所获得氢气的纯度可与钯膜相媲美，且该方法所用的膜材料易于制备且价格低廉，有望取代价格昂贵的钯膜来制备高纯度氢气。', p.abstract_en = 'A system for preparing high-purity hydrogen and a method therefor are provided. The system comprises a membrane reactor,  an oxygen permeable membrane sealed in the membrane reactor,  a catalyst moduleI disposed at one side of the oxygen permeable membrane,  a catalyst module II disposed at the other side of the oxygen permeable membrane,  a gas feeding device I used for feeding raw material gas intoone side of the oxygen permeable membrane,  a gas feeding device II used for feeding purge gas to the opposite side of the oxygen permeable membrane,  water vapor adopted as the raw material gas and low-purity hydrogen adopted as the purge gas. The method includes separating a raw material that is the low-purity hydrogen in the mixed-conductor oxygen permeable membrane reactor to obtain the high-purity hydrogen. The hydrogen separation rate and purity of the hydrogen prepared by the method are comparable with those of a palladium membrane. A membrane material used in the method is easily prepared and low in cost,  and is hoped to replace the expensive palladium membrane to prepare the high-purity hydrogen.', p.application_date = '2014-11-28 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105692549A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201520836127.7'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201520836127.7', p.title_cn = '雾化式光催化分解水制氢装置', p.title_en = 'Atomizing formula light catalytic decomposition water hydrogen plant', p.abstract_cn = '雾化式光催化分解水制氢装置，由反射盖与空心半球组成一个封闭结构，空心半球固定在箱体上，空心半球底部出口通过循环管道连接循环泵进口，循环管道出口伸入到反射盖内部，在循环管道出口接有雾化喷头，紫外LED灯光源固定在雾化喷头上，在反射盖上有氮气入口，在反射盖顶部接有冷凝管，且冷凝管出口作为气体出口，在空心半球上接有气压表。本实用新型将反应液与催化剂颗粒经过雾化处理，提高了光催化水制氢的效率。', p.abstract_en = 'Atomizing formula light catalytic decomposition water hydrogen plant,  constitute an enclosed construction by the reflection lid with hollow hemisphere,  hollow hemisphere is fixed on the box,  the circulating pump import is connected through the circulating line to the export of hollow hemisphere bottom,  it is inside that the reflection lid is stretched into in the circulating line export,  the atomizer has been connect in the circulating line export,  ultraviolet LED light source is fixed on the atomizer,  the nitrogen gas entry has been covered in the reflection,  the portion has connect the condenser pipe at the reflection caping,  and the condenser pipe export is as the gas outlet,  the barometer has been connect on hollow hemisphere. The utility model discloses liquid and catalyst granules process atomizing processing will be reacted,  the efficiency of photocatalysis water preparing hydrogen improved.', p.application_date = '2015-10-27 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN205328606U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201521068475.0'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201521068475.0', p.title_cn = '一种用于大型甲醇水蒸气重整制氢装置用甲醇转化器', p.title_en = 'Be used for large -scale for methanol steam reforming hydrogen plant methyl alcohol converter', p.abstract_cn = '本实用新型公开了一种用于大型甲醇水蒸气重整制氢装置用甲醇转化器，涉及一种MSR制氢装置，包括转化器壳体，转化器壳体内通过转化器管板固定有转化管束，沿转化管束设有若干折流板，以及与转化器壳体内连通的导热介质进、出口，与转化管束连通的反应气进、出口，还包括设于反应气进口的原料气进口导流筒，在反应气进口端的转化器管板上设有缓冲颗粒堆积层，在缓冲颗粒堆积层与原料气进口导流筒之间，正对原料气进口导流筒处还设有防冲挡板。本实用新型是一种用于大型甲醇水蒸气重整制氢装置用甲醇转化器，特别是单台产能超过20000Nm3/h。', p.abstract_en = 'The utility model discloses a be used for large -scale for methanol steam reforming hydrogen plant methyl alcohol converter relates to a MSR hydrogen plant,  including the converter casing,  be fixed with the conversion tube bank through the converter tube sheet in the converter casing,  be equipped with a plurality of baffling boards along the conversion tube bank,  and with the converter casing in the intercommunication heat -conducting medium advance,  the export,  advance with the reaction gas of conversion tube bank intercommunication,  the export,  still including the feed gas import draft tube of locating the import of reaction gas,  be equipped with buffering granule accumulation horizon on the converter tube sheet of reaction gas entrance point,  between buffering granule accumulation horizon and feed gas import draft tube,  just locate still to be equipped with the scour protection baffle to feed gas import draft tube. The utility model relates to a be used for large -scale for methanol steam reforming hydrogen plant methyl alcohol converter,  especially separate unit productivity exceedes 20000Nm3h.', p.application_date = '2015-12-18 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN205328607U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/26', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201620069028.5'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201620069028.5', p.title_cn = '一种甲烷转化炉', p.title_en = 'Methane reborner', p.abstract_cn = '本实用新型公开了一种甲烷转化炉，包括壳体、设在壳体内壁上的真空隔热层和催化剂床层，所述壳体和真空隔热层构成炉体，在炉体上方设有原料气入口和燃烧器，在所述催化剂床层的上部和底部分别设蜂窝板和支撑台，转化气出口设在炉内支撑台的下方，并在转化气出口处设置有气流控制阀。本实用新型结构合理，使用方便，实用性强，安全可靠，催化剂使用寿命长，隔温效果好，延长了转化炉的使用寿命，节省了人力物力，保证了转化炉长周期运转，提高了原料气制合成氨，合成甲醇的经济效益，便于进行推广。', p.abstract_en = 'The utility model discloses a methane reborner,  include the casing,  establish vacuum heat insulation layer and catalyst bed on shells inner wall,  casing and vacuum heat insulation layer constitute the furnace body,  are equipped with feed gas inlet and combustor above the furnace body honeycomb panel and brace table are established respectively to the upper portion and the bottom of catalyst bed,  and the reforming gas exports the below of establishing brace table in the stove to be provided with the pneumatic control valve in the reforming gas exit. The utility model discloses it is rational in infrastructure,  convenient to use,  the practicality is strong,  safe and reliable,  catalyst long service life,  it is effectual to separate the temperature,  has prolonged the life of reborner,  has saved manpower and materials,  has guaranteed the operation of reborner long period,  has improved feed gas system synthetic ammonia,  synthesizes the economic benefits of methyl alcohol,  is convenient for promote.', p.application_date = '2016-01-25 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN205328608U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201620072389.5'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201620072389.5', p.title_cn = '一种环己醇生产装置含氢尾气回收利用系统', p.title_en = 'Hydrogeneous tail gas recycle system of cyclohexanol apparatus for producing', p.abstract_cn = '本实用新型属于一种环己醇生产装置含氢尾气回收利用系统，包括依次串联的尾气收集罐、第一压缩机、吸附塔、第一氢气进气管、氢气缓冲罐、第二压缩机和环己醇生产装置；还包括有氢气罐，氢气罐通过第二氢气进气管与第一氢气进气管连接。采用本实用新型可以极大的减小环己醇生产装置中氢气的浪费，具有极大的环境和经济效益。', p.abstract_en = 'The utility model belongs to a hydrogeneous tail gas recycle system of cyclohexanol apparatus for producing,  including exhaust gas collection jar,  the first compressor,  adsorption tower,  first hydrogen intake pipe,  hydrogen gas buffer,  second compressor and the cyclohexanol apparatus for producing of establishing ties in proper order,  still including the hydrogen jar,  the hydrogen jar passes through second hydrogen intake pipe and first hydrogen intake -tube connection. Adopt the utility model discloses the waste that reduces hydrogen in the cyclohexanol apparatus for producing that can be very big has very big environment and economic benefits.', p.application_date = '2016-01-26 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN205328609U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/56', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'DE602014075612'}) SET p.application_no = 'DE602014075612', p.title_cn = '发电系统和用于运行发电系统的方法', p.title_en = 'POWER GENERATION SYSTEM AND METHOD FOR OPERATING POWER GENERATION SYSTEM', p.abstract_cn = '一种发电系统(100)，包括：构造成燃烧燃料的燃烧器(1)； 发电部(50)，其在发电时利用从燃烧器(1)获得的能量； 燃料供给部(19)，其向燃烧器(1)供给燃料； 空气供应单元(9)，其被配置为向燃烧器(1)供应燃烧空气； 排出气体通道(3)，来自燃烧器(1)的排出气体流经该排出气体通道； CO检测器(4)，被配置为检测排出气体中的CO； 温度检测器(6)，被配置为检测排出气体的温度； 以及控制器(7)，其被配置为， 当排出气体流过排出气体通道时， 执行以下操作中的至少一个：基于温度检测器(6)的检测温度与由加热器加热的排出气体的被加热量之间的差值之间的差值来检测排出气体通道(3)的异常；以及执行以下操作中的至少一个： 基于相对于燃料供给单元(19)和空气供给单元(9)中的至少一个的输出之间的差的温度检测器(6)的检测温度之间的差，排出气体通道(3)的异常。', p.abstract_en = 'A power generation system (100) includes :  a combustor (1) configured to combust a fuel;  a power generation unit (50) configured to utilize energy obtained from the combustor (1) when generating electric power;  a fuel supply unit (19) configured to supply the fuel to the combustor (1);  an air supply unit (9) configured to supply combustion air to the combustor (1);  a discharged gas passage (3) through which a discharged gas from the combustor (1) flows;  a CO detector (4) configured to detect CO in the discharged gas;  a temperature detector (6) configured to detect a temperature of the discharged gas;  and a controller (7) configured to,  when the discharged gas is flowing through the discharged gas passage,  performs at least one of an operation of detecting an abnormality of the discharged gas passage (3) based on a difference between detected temperatures of the temperature detector (6) relative to a difference between heated amounts of the discharged gas heated by a heater and an operation of detecting the abnormality of the discharged gas passage (3) based on the difference between the detected temperatures of the temperature detector (6) relative to a difference between outputs of at least one of the fuel supply unit ( 19) and the air supply unit (9).', p.application_date = '2014-05-30 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'DE602014075612T2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/34', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'EP15000896'}) SET p.application_no = 'EP15000896', p.title_cn = '用于生产合成气的方法和装置', p.title_en = 'PROCESS AND APPARATUS FOR THE PRODUCTION OF SYNTHESIS GAS', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种用于生产合成气的方法和装置(4)，所述含烃燃料气体(2)和氧化剂(1)(z)(R)引入反应空间的反应器中，以产生在所述燃料气消耗所述释放装置(2)中通过部分氧化含氢和一氧化碳和烃的能量，支撑在随后的催化重整。这里一个特征是用重整催化剂被支撑，在支撑结构中形成的整体的规整填料和/或(m)是适当的。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a method and a device for the production of synthesis gas (4),  wherein hydrocarbons containing fuel gas (2) and an oxidizing agent (1) (Z) (R) of a reactor in the reaction space are introduced,  so as to generate in the fuel gas is consumed by Partial oxidation of the release (2) hydrogen and carbon monoxide and hydrocarbons contained energy,  the catalytically supported upon a subsequent reforming. One characteristic here is that the reforming by a catalyst is supported,  on a support structure in the form of a structured packing and/or of a monolith (M) is appropriate.', p.application_date = '2015-03-26 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'EP3034464A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2012189273'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2012189273', p.title_cn = '制氢装置', p.title_en = 'Hydrogen production device', p.abstract_cn = '所要解决的问题 : 得到的氢制造装置能够独立操作中，通过使用除氢后的尾气. 溶液 : 氢气制造装置包括 : 重整部(1)原料进行重整成含氢重整气和二氧化碳蒸汽转化原料. 和氢分离部(2)分离得到的产氢的重整气体转化为氢和含二氧化碳的废气. 还包括 : 一种废气供给流路L4，将废气中获得的氢分离部(2)的燃烧器(12)和重整部(1)中燃气. 一种烟气流量检测器35，用于检测流量的废气流经废气l4供应通道. 和控制装置(40)控制下自主操作量的AB含氧气体. 供应到燃烧装置(12)l30B通过含氧气体供给通路. 基于流量的尾气通过尾气流量检测器35检测.', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To obtain a hydrogen production apparatus capable of autonomous operation by using off-gas obtained after removing hydrogen.SOLUTION :  The hydrogen production apparatus comprises :  a reforming section 1 for reforming a raw material into a reformed gas containing hydrogen and carbon dioxide by steam reforming the raw material;  and a hydrogen separation section 2 for producing hydrogen by separating the obtained reformed gas into hydrogen and an off-gas containing carbon dioxide,  and further comprises :  an off-gas supply passage L4 for sending the off-gas obtained in the hydrogen separation section 2 to a combustion device 12b provided in the reforming section 1 as a fuel gas;  an off-gas flow rate detector 35 for detecting the flow rate of the off-gas flowing through the off-gas supply passage L4;  and control means 40ab under autonomous operation which controls the amount of an oxygen-containing gas,  supplied to the combustion device 12b through an oxygen-containing gas supply passage L30,  based on the flow rate of the off-gas detected by the off-gas flow rate detector 35.', p.application_date = '2012-08-29 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP5936491B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2012084553'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2012084553', p.title_cn = '氢气发生器', p.title_en = 'The hydrogen generator', p.abstract_cn = '所要解决的问题 : 提供一种氢气发生器，可继续操作，即使在氢气通道连通到加氢脱硫器变得阻塞干扰合适的氢供给. 溶液 : 本发明提供了一种氢气发生器(31)具有切换原料气体通道部(7)切换至脱硫堵检测部分中的线22的情况下，(6)检测堵塞供给原料气体供给时通过旁路管道23. 通过第一脱硫部分1. 脱硫部(2)供给至第二. 由此. 即使第二脱硫部分2失效脱硫工艺. 通过第一脱硫的原料气脱硫部分1设置在脱硫路线可提供给重整部. 重整催化剂在重整部分. 因此. 可防止中毒而劣化的硫化合物.', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To provide a hydrogen generator capable of continuing operation even when a hydrogen gas passage leading to a hydrodesulfurizer becomes blocked to disturb an appropriate supply of hydrogen.SOLUTION :  There is provided a hydrogen generator 31 has a switching part 7 for switching a raw material gas passage to a desulfurization line 22 in case a blocking detection part 6 detects a blockage when the supplied raw material gas is supplied through a bypass line 23,  not through a first desulfurization part 1,  for supplying to a second desulfurization part 2. Thereby,  even if the second desulfurization part 2 fails to desulfurize,  the raw material gas desulfurized through the first desulfurization part 1 disposed in the desulfurization line can be supplied to a reforming part. The reforming catalyst in the reforming part,  therefore,  can be prevented from being poisoned and deteriorated by a sulfur compound.', p.application_date = '2012-04-03 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP5938557B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2012140489'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2012140489', p.title_cn = '一种氢气发生器，氢气产生装置和填充催化剂的方法', p.title_en = 'A hydrogen generator,  a hydrogen generation device and a catalyst filling method', p.abstract_cn = '所要解决的问题是 : 能防止塌陷的进展的催化剂设置在所述下侧. 从开口处落造成催化剂的分隔构件(支承构件)安装在氢气发生器. 方案 : 一种氢生成装置具备第第一支承部件(53)安装在反应器容器以支撑催化剂. 和突出部开口第一的周边上设有支撑构件在重力方向并向上凸出. 支撑件具有支撑部的开口大于催化剂颗粒和所述突起的突出部开口大于催化剂颗粒. 该催化剂能抑制掉，以防止容量降低的氢气发生器下方坍塌所带来的催化剂.', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To prevent the progression of collapse of a catalyst disposed on the lower side,  caused by a fallen catalyst from an opening of a partition member (supporting member) installed in a hydrogen generator.SOLUTION :  A hydrogen generator includes a first supporting member 53 installed in a reactor vessel to support a catalyst,  and a projection that is arranged on the periphery of an opening of the first supporting member and projects upward in the gravity direction. The supporting member has a supporting part opening larger than catalyst particles and the projection has a projection part opening larger than catalyst particles. The catalyst is thus suppressed from falling to prevent capacity degradation of the hydrogen generator caused by collapse of a catalyst below.', p.application_date = '2012-06-22 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP5938563B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2012140482'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2012140482', p.title_cn = '氢气发生装置', p.title_en = 'The hydrogen generating device', p.abstract_cn = '所要解决的问题 : 其所要解决的问题 : 加氢脱硫剂的温度在进气侧的气体通道连通到低加氢脱硫剂由于剂流动的温度等于室温. 所述加氢脱硫剂在气体出口侧的温度变高时由于重整催化剂的温度上升，通过内保温材料. 使整个加氢脱硫剂不能保持在大致均匀的温度. 从而使负载增加的加氢脱硫剂. 方案 : 一种氢发生器包括 : 加氢脱硫催化剂中加氢脱硫剂原料中去除含硫化合物的气体。. 其中原料气的重整器. 从所述去除含硫化合物. 重整以产生含氢气体. 和内氢气发生容器之间设有保温材料和加氢脱硫剂. 所述加氢脱硫剂包括进口，原料气供应和原料气出口排出. 所述的内保温材料被配置成使入口设置保温材料保温性能的加氢脱硫剂入口之间的部分中所述重整器变得低于出口设置保温材料保温性能的加氢脱硫剂出口之间的部分中和的重整器.', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To solve a problem in which :  the temperature of a hydrodesulfurization agent on a gas inlet side is low in a gas passage leading to a hydrogenation desulfurizer because the agent flows in with the temperature equal to room temperature;  the temperature of the hydrodesulfurization agent on a gas outlet side becomes high because the temperature of a reforming catalyst rises through an inner heat insulation material;  and the whole hydrodesulfurization agent cannot be maintained at about the uniform temperature,  thereby causing the load of the hydrodesulfurization agent to be increased.SOLUTION :  A hydrogen generator includes :  a hydrogenation desulfurizer in which a hydrodesulfurization catalyst that removes a sulfur compound contained in a raw material gas is filled;  a reformer in which the raw material gas,  from which the sulfur compound is removed,  is reformed to generate a hydrogen-containing gas;  and an inner heat insulation material arranged between a hydrogen generation vessel and the hydrogenation desulfurizer. The hydrogenation desulfurizer includes an inlet into which the raw material gas is supplied and an outlet that discharge the raw material gas,  and the inner heat insulation material is configured so that thermal insulation performance of an inlet heat insulation material arranged in a part between an inlet of the hydrogenation desulfurizer and the reformer becomes lower than thermal insulation performance of an outlet heat insulation material arranged in a part between an outlet of the hydrogenation desulfurizer and the reformer.', p.application_date = '2012-06-22 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP5938580B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'KR1020157025918'}) SET p.application_no = 'KR1020157025918', p.title_cn = '高热值煤气制造工艺', p.title_en = 'HIGH-CALORIE GAS MANUFACTURING PROCESS', p.abstract_cn = '本发明的目的是提供一种高热值煤气的制造方法，通过该高热值气体可通过热解制造的甘油。本发明是一种高热值煤气的制造方法，该方法包括 : 用铁矿石进行甘油裂解；从而获得高热值煤气具有热值3, 000大卡/米3以上。', p.abstract_en = 'The purpose of the present invention is to provide a high-calorie gas manufacturing process by which a high-calorie gas can be manufactured through pyrolysis of glycerol. The present invention is a high-calorie gas manufacturing process which comprises :  subjecting glycerol to pyrolysis using iron ore;  and thus obtaining a high-calorie gas having a net calorific value of 3, 000 kcal/m 3 or more.', p.application_date = '2014-03-27 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'KR101634513B1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/22', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'BR102014031369'}) SET p.application_no = 'BR102014031369', p.title_cn = '氢产生系统和氧气，化学过程用于dosagem¨dosagem¨调制管理', p.title_en = 'SYSTEM OF HYDROGEN GENERATION AND OXYGEN,  AND PROCESS OF CHEMICAL MODULATION FOR dosagem¨DOSAGEM¨ MANAGEMENT', p.abstract_cn = '发明专利摘要：“氢氧发生系统，以及剂量管理的化学调制过程”。 本发明旨在创造一种通过将由进料器管理的化学过程产生5氢和氧的系统，所述进料器将在单独的隔室中存储在催化剂电解质的组成过程中使用的每种物质，所述催化剂电解质用于电解、原电池或放热储能池中，用于产生氢气和氧气或电能。 10', p.abstract_en = 'Patent Abstract of Invention :  "Hydrogen and oxygen generation system,  and chemical modulation process for dosage management". The present invention aims to create a system of generation of 5 hydrogen and oxygen,  through a chemical process that will be managed by a feeder,  which will store in a separate compartment each of the substances to be used in the process of composition of the catalyst electrolyte,  to be used in electrolytic,  galvanic or exothermic igneous cells,  for the generation of hydrogen and oxygen gases or electrical energy. 10', p.application_date = '2014-12-15 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'BRPI1431369A2', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CA2651959'}) SET p.application_no = 'CA2651959', p.title_cn = '获得磁铁矿的方法', p.title_en = 'METHOD FOR OBTAINING MAGNETITE', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种利用赤泥获得有价值的产品的方法，其在拜耳法溶出铝的制造。根据本发明的方法包括以下步骤 : a)的至少一个部分还原的铁(Ⅲ)氧化物和/或铁(Ⅲ)氢氧化物采用至少一种还原剂包含至少一个烃；和b)至少一种固相的分离反应混合物从至少一个液体和/或气态时，所述固态和/或液态和/或气态相包括至少一件有价值产物至少含有其中所述还原剂包含甲烷和/或天然气和/或乙醇和/或碳。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a method for obtaining valuable products using red mud,  which accumulates during the manufacture of aluminium by the Bayer method. The method according to the invention comprises the steps :  a) reduction of at least one part of the iron(III) oxide and/or iron(III) hydroxide using at least one reductant that contains at least one hydrocarbon;  and b) separation of at least one solid phase of the reaction mixture from at least one liquid and/or gaseous phase,  the solid and/or liquid and/or gaseous phase comprising at least one valuable product that at least contains magnetite and the reductant comprising methane and/or natural gas and/or ethanol and/or carbon.', p.application_date = '2007-04-25 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CA2651959C', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/32', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'TR201606937'}) SET p.application_no = 'TR201606937', p.title_cn = '生产含H2气体和纯水的系统和方法。', p.title_en = 'System and process for producing H2-containing gas and pure water.', p.abstract_cn = '用于从集成的H2生产重整器和热水纯化工艺生产含有纯水和H2的产物气体的方法和系统。通过与来自产生H2的重整过程的重整产物的间接热传递来加热原水，例如盐水，以在高效蒸馏过程中纯化原水。', p.abstract_en = 'Process and system for producing product gas containing pure water and H2 from the integrated H2 producing reformer and thermal water purification process. Raw water,  such as brine,  is heated by indirect heat transfer with the reformate from the H2-producing reforming process to purify the raw water in a highly efficient distillation process.', p.application_date = '2013-10-23 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'TR201606937T4', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14361654'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14361654', p.title_cn = '金属氧化物复合物及其形成方法', p.title_en = 'Metal oxide composite and a method of forming thereof', p.abstract_cn = '一种形成金属氧化物复合物的方法，所述方法包括混合金属氧化物、至少两种单体和分散剂以产生浆料； 凝胶浇铸所述浆料以产生绿色金属氧化物复合物； 以及烧结所述生坯金属氧化物复合物以制备所述金属氧化物复合物。 根据该方法形成的金属氧化物复合物。 金属氧化物复合物的用途，用于催化金属硼氢化物的水解以产生氢。', p.abstract_en = 'A method of forming a metal oxide composite,  the method comprising mixing a metal oxide,  at least two monomers and a dispersant to produce a slurry;  gel casting the slurry to produce a green metal oxide composite;  and sintering the green metal oxide composite to produce the metal oxide composite. A metal oxide composite formed according to the method. Use of the metal oxide composite,  for catalyzing hydrolysis of metal borohydride to produce hydrogen.', p.application_date = '2013-02-18 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9370767B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US12747334'}) SET p.application_no = 'US12747334', p.title_cn = '生产焦炭和燃气的工艺和设备', p.title_en = 'Process and plant for producing char and fuel gas', p.abstract_cn = '一种生产焦炭和燃料气体方法，包括在流化床反应器中，在高于约1000°C的温度和约1巴至约40巴的压力下，用含氧气体使含碳材料脱气。 调节流化床反应器内的氧气供应，以回收炭产品中碳质材料中大于60%的固定碳，并且流化床反应器的下部或底部区域中的氧利用率小于流化床反应器的上部区域中的氧利用率的80%。', p.abstract_en = 'A method for producing char and fuel gas includes degasifying a carbonaceous material with oxygen-containing gases in a fluidized bed reactor at a temperature of more than about 1000° C. and at a pressure of from about 1 bar to about 40 bar. A supply of oxygen within the fluidized bed reactor is adjusted so as to recover more than 60% of fixed carbon in the carbonaceous material in a char product,  and an oxygen availability in a lower or bottom region of the fluidized bed reactor is less than 80% of an oxygen availability in an upper region of the fluidized bed reactor.', p.application_date = '2007-12-12 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9371487B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/36', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 5, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2014248717'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2014248717', p.title_cn = '复合储氢材料及其制造方法', p.title_en = 'HYDROGEN STORAGE MATERIAL COMPOSITE AND METHOD FOR PRODUCING THE SAME', p.abstract_cn = '要解决的问题 : 重量份。储氢密度高，释放温度低，和，填充密度高和制造该复合储氢材料的方法。溶液 : 该复合储氢材料，V0/V3+3，M(AlH3OR14)含N。一种然而，μm，Li，Na，K，1Mg，Ca中选择从所组成的组中的一个或多个元件，在N，M的化合价，V0/V3+3和M(AlH3OR14)N，V0/V3+3的摩尔比(x)，0.2≦x[1.0是优选的。alh3，α型是优选的。这种复合储氢材料，在非氧化性气氛，，V0/V3+3和M(AlH3OR14)N，并且，通过研磨，粉碎后的各粉末混合得到。选择的绘图 : 图。1', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To provide a hydrogen storage material composite that has a high weight hydrogen storage density,  a low hydrogen adsorption temperature and a high packing density and to provide a method for producing the hydrogen storage material composite. SOLUTION :  The hydrogen storage material composite includes AlH3 and M(AlH4)n,  provided that M is at least any one of elements selected from the group consisting of Li,  Na,  K,  Mg and Ca and n is a valence of M. The molar ratio (x) of AlH3 to AlH3 and M(AlH4)n is preferably 0.2≤x<1.0. AlH3 is preferably α-type. The hydrogen storage material composite is produced in a non-oxidative atmosphere by pulverizing AlH3 and M(AlH4)n respectively and mixing each of the powders produced after pulverization. SELECTED DRAWING :  Figure 1 COPYRIGHT :  (C)2016, JPO&INPIT', p.application_date = '2014-12-09 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP2016108196A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2014255591'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2014255591', p.title_cn = '用于生产氢和氧的方法和装置，产生蒸气通过photodecomposable', p.title_en = 'METHOD AND APPARATUS FOR PRODUCING HYDROGEN AND OXYGEN BY PHOTODECOMPOSITION OF STEAM', p.abstract_cn = '要解决的问题 : 氢和氧的光解产生的蒸汽提供一种技术，用于高效。溶液 : 蒸汽真空的分解体1到真空的真空泵5，产生蒸汽的蒸汽发生器(2)到真空分解蒸汽从主体1，通过微调的蒸汽阀3，由普通·不饱和。通过还原减少了蒸汽。饱和蒸汽通过远紫外线发生器4作为饱和蒸汽photodecomposable的功能，远小于波长190纳米的光照射紫外线。远紫外线的分子键能高于蒸气分子键能multiphotons，氢气和氧气和臭氧分解的真空泵5供给到分离罐6。分离罐6上测量。然后为氢气，氧气和臭氧分离下和较重。氧气和臭氧通过臭氧分解的热分解装置10产生氧气。选择的绘图 : 图。1', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To provide a technology for efficiently producing hydrogen and oxygen by photodecomposition of steam. SOLUTION :  Steam produced by steam generator 2 is introduced through a fine adjustment valve 3 for steam introduction into a vacuum tank 1 for steam decomposition vacuumed by a vacuum pump 5. The vacuum tank 1 for steam decomposition is subjected to pressure and temperature reduction to produce saturated steam of ordinary temperature. The saturated steam is irradiated by a far-ultraviolet ray generator 4 with far-ultraviolet rays of a wave length less than 190 nm that is able to photodecompose the saturated steam. Since the photon energy of the far-ultra violet rays is high enough to cut a molecular bond of the steam,  the steam is decomposed into hydrogen,  oxygen,  and ozone,  which are sent to a separation tank 6 by the vacuum pump 5. The hydrogen sent to the separation tank 6 is so light to go up to the upper zone,  while the oxygen and ozone are so heavy to go down to the lower zone. The separated oxygen and ozone are decomposed in an ozone decomposition unit 10 to produce oxygen. SELECTED DRAWING :  Figure 1 COPYRIGHT :  (C)2016, JPO&INPIT', p.application_date = '2014-12-01 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP2016108211A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'RU2015143326'}) SET p.application_no = 'RU2015143326', p.title_cn = '合成气的生产装置', p.title_en = 'DEVICE FOR PRODUCTION OF THE SYNTHESIS-GAS', p.abstract_cn = '1。发电机的合成气，含有壳体和位于其内的空腔或多腔基体的体积/矩阵，材料制成，透过气体与氧化剂的混合物；烃类原料的混合物与内腔中的氧化剂/基质腔/矩阵进行通过可渗透壁的空腔，和输出的转化产品通过上段的空腔，其特征在于，内腔/空间基体的体积/矩阵由两个平行的平表面从材料，可渗透气体与氧化剂的混合物，位于距离彼此不低于15。2。根据权利要求1，其特征在于 : 母线之间从材料模具空腔的平行的平表面，可渗透气体的混合物与氧化剂，放置固体或多孔筛上的耐火材料。3。根据权利要求1，其特征在于 : 平行的平表面，模具的成型腔，耐火材料是由以下组成 : 泡沫塑料，金属毡，压丝，金属网，带孔陶瓷。4。根据权利要求1，其特征在于 : 起始组分的 : 天然气和氧化剂的初步混合后进入换热器，位于所述的空腔上段，从该加热的混合物供给到可渗透的壁的空腔。5。根据权利要求1，其特征在于，出口合成气水换热器中冷却。6。根据权利要求1，其特征在于 : 比供给原料中氧/甲烷在于在从0.7至1.4的范围内。', p.abstract_en = 'Useful model relates to devices for production of synthesis-gas by conversion of hydrocarbons,  and in other words,  their oxidative conversion of. Special device contains casing and located in it cavity or several cavities volume of matrix/matrices,  made from material,  permeable for the mixture of gas with oxidant,  ;  mixture of hydrocarbon raw material with oxidant in inner cavity/matrix cavity/matrices is performed through permeable wall of the cavity/cavities of,  and output of conversion products-through upper section of cavity/cavities,  in which the inner cavity/space volume of matrix/matrices are formed by two flat parallel surfaces from material,  permeable for the mixture of gas with oxidant,  located on a distance of not less than 15 mm from each other. Technical result of the proposed utility model is the possibility of use of matrices with large area of working surface and relatively small internal volume,  that allows to reach more high volumetric productivity synthetic gas.', p.application_date = '2015-10-13 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'RU162650U1', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/34', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'DE602013056930'}) SET p.application_no = 'DE602013056930', p.title_cn = '从水产生能量到氢系统', p.title_en = 'GENERATING ENERGY FROM WATER,  TO HYDROGEN SYSTEM', p.abstract_cn = '一种通过水的解离产生氢气的系统，其特征在于 : 一个用于从含有电解质的水中产生氢气的氢气产生室； 射频电磁能源，用于提供能量以驱动水的解离； 以及控制单元，用于控制能源以及液体和气体的流动。', p.abstract_en = 'A system for generating hydrogen by dissociation of water,  characterized by a hydrogen generation chamber for generating hydrogen from water containing electrolytes;  a source of radiofrequency electromagnetic energy for providing energy to drive the dissociation of the water;  and a control unit for controlling the energy source and liquid and gas flow.', p.application_date = '2013-10-23 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'DE602013056930T2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'GR20150402615'}) SET p.application_no = 'GR20150402615', p.title_cn = '气-固相反应', p.title_en = 'GAS-SOLID PHASE REACTION', p.abstract_cn = '准连续执行的化学反应，由至少两个顺序的可逆步骤包括并行操作两个辐射加热的反应室和循环调节交流反应室中的反应条件。独立权利要求包括光反应器用于执行化学反应的准连续执行从两个顺序可逆步骤。', p.abstract_en = 'The quasi-continuous execution of a chemical reaction,  consisting of at least two sequential reversible steps comprises parallely operating two radiation heated reaction chambers and cyclically adjusting alternating reaction conditions in the reaction chambers. INDEPENDENT CLAIM is included for photoreactor for the execution of quasi-continuous execution of chemical reaction from two sequential reversible steps.', p.application_date = '2005-07-19 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'GR20150402615T3', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/06', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'IN7831DELNP2015'}) SET p.application_no = 'IN7831DELNP2015', p.title_cn = '集成发电和碳捕获燃料电池的使用', p.title_en = 'INTEGRATED POWER GENERATION AND CARBON CAPTURE USING FUEL CELLS', p.abstract_cn = '系统和方法被提供用于捕获CO2从燃烧源(mcfcs)应用熔融碳酸盐燃料电池。被操作而具有降低的燃料电池阳极燃料利用率。可选的至少一部分阳极排气被再循环用作用于燃烧的燃料源。任选的第二部分的阳极排气被再循环用作阳极的一部分输入流的装置。这样能够允许用于减少燃料电池所需要的量的CO燃烧源耗尽和/或修改怎样运行的燃料电池。', p.abstract_en = 'Systems and methods are provided for capturing CO2 from a combustion source using molten carbonate fuel cells (MCFCS). The fuel cells are operated to have a reduced anode fuel utilization. Optionally at least a portion of the anode exhaust is recycled for use as a fuel for the combustion source. Optionally a second portion of the anode exhaust is recycled for use as part of an anode input stream. This can allow for a reduction in the amount of fuel cell area required for separating CO from the combustion source exhaust and/or modifications in how the fuel cells are operated.', p.application_date = '2015-09-01 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'IN7831DELNP2015A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/50', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'KR1020140186306'}) SET p.application_no = 'KR1020140186306', p.title_cn = '能量还原效率高，水煤气变换反应系统', p.title_en = 'ENERGY REDUCTION HIGH EFFICIENCY WATER GAS SHIFT REACTION SYSTEM', p.abstract_cn = '根据本发明的一个实施例的节能水煤气反应系统表面，减少铁矿粉预还原流程形式，在上部，所述降低的五个手指F排出原料气体从半导体制造装置(雾 : 废气FINEX)水通过储罐循环换热器1号转换到蒸汽，所述1号气体和五个手指F在所述热交换器使用从上数1得到的蒸汽氢在板温度条件下产生气体包括1号，分配相同的高温度的重整器，和所述高温转化器数量1排出的气体从半导体制造装置为水循环通过储罐2号转换到蒸汽和包括热交换器，所述数字2，所述热交换器销管式所得的水蒸汽的至少一部分。可重新使用所述高温重整器中。', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention relates to an energy saving type water gas reaction system. The water gas reaction system comprises :  a fluidized reduction furnace for reducing powder type iron ore;  a first heat exchanger for converting water into water vapor by using the heat of FOG (finex off gas) gas discharged from the top of the fluidized reduction furnace;  a high-temperature reforming device producing and discharging a first gas containing hydrogen at a predetermined first temperature by using the FOG gas and the vapor generated from the first heat exchanger;  and a second heat exchanger converting water into water vapor by using the heat of the first gas discharged from the high-temperature reforming device,  wherein at least a part of the water vapor generated from the second heat exchanger can be reused in the high-temperature reforming device.', p.application_date = '2014-12-22 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'KR101632888B1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/12', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'DE102014018375'}) SET p.application_no = 'DE102014018375', p.title_cn = '反应器', p.title_en = 'Reactor', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种方法和装置生产的合成气(4)，所述含烃燃料气体(2)和氧化剂(1)(z)(R)反应空间的反应器引入，以产生在所述燃料部分氧化气体消耗的释放器(2)氢和碳一氧化碳和烃类所含的能量，催化支承在一后续重整。一个特征是通过催化剂重整支撑，在支撑结构的形式的规整填料和/或整料(M)的合适的。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a method and a device for the production of synthesis gas (4),  wherein hydrocarbons containing fuel gas (2) and an oxidizing agent (1) (Z) (R) of a reactor in the reaction space are introduced,  so as to generate in the fuel gas is consumed by Partial oxidation of the release (2) hydrogen and carbon monoxide and hydrocarbons contained energy,  the catalytically supported upon a subsequent reforming. One characteristic here is that the reforming by a catalyst is supported,  on a support structure in the form of a structured packing and/or of a monolith (M) is appropriate.', p.application_date = '2014-12-15 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'DE102014018375A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'DE102014018471'}) SET p.application_no = 'DE102014018471', p.title_cn = '与烃转化装置的等离子体焊炬和用于转化烃类的方法', p.title_en = 'hydrocarbon converter with a plasma torch and method for converting hydrocarbons', p.abstract_cn = 'H的制备方法2/C-气雾剂，包括如下步骤 : 将含烃流体到流体含有烃转化装置与等离子体炬和拆分烃通过供给能量的碳和氢，所述等离子体炬产生等离子体的装置与借助于一个等离子气体的碳一氧化碳或一氧化碳和氢气的混合物操作。', p.abstract_en = 'A process for the preparation of H 2/C- aerosol is disclosed,  comprising the steps of :  introducing a hydrocarbon-containing fluid into a fluid containing hydrocarbon converter with a plasma torch and splitting the hydrocarbon to carbon and hydrogen by a supply of energy,  wherein the plasma torch is generated by means of a plasma with the aid of a plasma gas of carbon monoxide or a mixture of carbon monoxide and hydrogen is operated.', p.application_date = '2014-12-12 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'DE102014018471A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/24', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'DE102014226072'}) SET p.application_no = 'DE102014226072', p.title_cn = '用于固定设施的电源系统与反应器用于释放的氢从液体化合物', p.title_en = 'A power supply system for stationary installations with a reactor for the release of hydrogen from liquid compounds', p.abstract_cn = '本发明的后用于固定的装置包括反应器，用于从含氢的电源释放氢，液体化合物，与反应器容器，其中至少一个功能的提供的氢气可以进行，所述反应器容器从至少一个容器与氢气轴承，液体化合物的供给，其特征在于 : 一个第一热交换器和向反应器容器引入容器第二热热交换器热量的释放。', p.abstract_en = 'After of the invention is for a stationary installation comprising a reactor for a power supply from a hydrogen bearing release of hydrogen,  liquid compound,  with a reactor vessel,  in which at least one function for providing of the hydrogen can be carried out,  wherein the reactor vessel from at least one container with the hydrogen bearing,  liquid compound is supplied,  characterized in that a first heat exchanger and into the reactor vessel is incorporated into the container a second heat exchanger for heat release.', p.application_date = '2014-12-16 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'DE102014226072A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'DE602010033131'}) SET p.application_no = 'DE602010033131', p.title_cn = '合成气的生产方法和氢气从试剂包含液体烃， 气态烃类和/或含氧化合物，也衍生自生物质，通过非集成膜反应器', p.title_en = 'PROCESS FOR THE PRODUCTION OF SYNGAS AND HYDROGEN STARTING FROM REAGENTS COMPRISING LIQUID HYDROCARBONS,  GASEOUS HYDROCARBONS,  AND/OR OXYGENATED COMPOUNDS,  ALSO DERIVING FROM BIOMASSES,  BY MEANS OF A NON-INTEGRATED MEMBRANE REACTOR', p.abstract_cn = '合成气的生产方法和氢气从液体烃，气态烃和/或含氧化合物，还由衍生自生物质，及其混合物，设想即架构中所使用膜反应器连续反应和分离阶段。该方法包括在一段预加热的试剂，若干段短接触时间的催化部分氧化制造合成气和氢气的数量产生的氢气通过膜阶段以及后续的分离，热回收段，产生的二氧化碳除去部分和部分进行冷却和清除冷凝液。任选地，该方法包括一段获得的氢气通过变压吸附(PSA)净化，并产生净化气体介质热值。此外，所述的试剂和方法包括加氢脱硫段可以包括CO2转化段通过倒水生成氢气和(rwgs)水煤气变换反应。', p.abstract_en = 'A process for the production of syngas and hydrogen starting from liquid hydrocarbons,  gaseous hydrocarbons and/or oxygenated compounds,  also deriving from biomasses,  and mixtures thereof,  envisages recourse to a membrane reactor in an architecture that uses a succession of reaction and separation stages. The process includes a section for pre-heating the reagents,  a number of sections for short-contact-time catalytic partial oxidation for producing syngas and hydrogen in a number of stages followed by separation of hydrogen produced via membranes,  a thermal-recovery section,  a section for removing produced carbon dioxide,  and a section for cooling and removing condensate. Optionally,  the process includes a section for purifying obtained hydrogen via pressure-swing adsorption (PSA) and generating purge gas with medium calorific value. Furthermore,  the process includes a section for hydrodesulphuration of the reagents and could include a section for conversion of the CO2 and H2 produced by a reverse-water-gas-shift (RWGS) reaction.', p.application_date = '2010-11-04 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'DE602010033131T2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'KR1020150070856'}) SET p.application_no = 'KR1020150070856', p.title_cn = '一种燃烧式氢气发生装置', p.title_en = 'A combustion typed hydrogen generating apparatus', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种燃烧型氢气发生器，该燃烧型氢气发生器可以使用诸如铝、镁等的水反应性金属，通过在高温高压条件下去除金属表面上的氧化物涂层以加速诸如铝、镁等的水反应性金属的反应，通过金属与水之间的反应来产生高纯度氢气。', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention relates to a combustion type hydrogen generator which can generate high purity hydrogen using hydro-reactive metal such as aluminum,  magnesium,  etc.,  through a reaction between the metal and water by removing an oxide coating on the surface of the metal to expedite a reaction of hydro-reactive metal such as aluminum,  magnesium,  etc.,  at the condition of high temperature and high pressure.', p.application_date = '2015-05-21 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'KR101632576B1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14942045'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14942045', p.title_cn = '具有混合元件氧化铝成型精炼工艺管', p.title_en = 'ALUMINA FORMING REFINERY PROCESS TUBES WITH MIXING ELEMENT', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及可用作在高温下处理气相烃工艺物流的炼油厂工艺中的传热管的焊接件。 本公开还涉及可用于在高温下处理气相烃工艺物流的精炼工艺中的管。 焊接件包括管状构件和至少一个混合元件。 管状构件包括含铝合金。 混合元件包括含铝合金。 混合元件的含铝合金可以与管状构件的含铝合金相同或不同。 本公开的其它方面涉及在高温下处理气相烃工艺物流的炼油厂工艺，其包括这种焊接。', p.abstract_en = 'This disclosure relates to weldments useful as heat transfer tubes in refinery processes dealing with gas phase hydrocarbon process streams at high temperatures. This disclosure also relates to tubes that are useful in refinery processes dealing with gas phase hydrocarbon process streams at high temperatures. The weldments include a tubular member and at least one mixing element. The tubular member comprises an aluminum-containing alloy. The mixing element comprises an aluminum-containing alloy. The mixing element\'s aluminum-containing alloy can be the same as or different from the tubular member\'s aluminum-containing alloy. Other aspects of the disclosure relate to refinery processes dealing with gas phase hydrocarbon process streams at high temperatures which include such weldments.', p.application_date = '2015-11-16 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US20160167009A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/34', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US15047797'}) SET p.application_no = 'US15047797', p.title_cn = '氨氧化/分解催化剂', p.title_en = 'AMMONIA OXIDATION/DECOMPOSITION CATALYST', p.abstract_cn = '本发明提供了一种氨氧化/分解催化剂，其能够降低载体的还原温度，所述催化剂需要具有在室温下活化的性质，并且还能够在低于室温的温度下提供活化的性质。 本发明的氨氧化/分解催化剂是氨氧化/分解催化剂，包括 : 由氧化铈和氧化锆的复合氧化物组成的催化剂载体； 和至少一种选自作为沉积在其上的催化活性金属的第6a族、第7a族、第8族和第1b族金属的金属，其特征在于，所述催化剂载体中氧化锆的摩尔浓度为10-90%。', p.abstract_en = 'Provided is an ammonia oxidation/decomposition catalyst which can decrease the reduction temperature of a support,  which is required for the catalyst to have a property of being activated at room temperature,  and also can render a property of being activated at a temperature lower than room temperature. The ammonia oxidation/decomposition catalyst of the present invention is an ammonia oxidation/decomposition catalyst,  comprising :  a catalyst support composed of a composite oxide of cerium oxide and zirconium oxide;  and at least one metal selected from the group consisting of metals of group 6A,  group 7A,  group 8,  and group 1B as a catalytically active metal deposited thereon,  characterized in that the molar concentration of zirconium oxide in the catalyst support is from 10 to 90%.', p.application_date = '2016-02-19 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US20160167962A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US15047917'}) SET p.application_no = 'US15047917', p.title_cn = '烃分解催化剂、使用该催化剂分解烃方法、使用该催化剂生产氢的方法和发电系统', p.title_en = 'HYDROCARBON-DECOMPOSING CATALYST,  METHOD FOR DECOMPOSING HYDROCARBONS USING THE CATALYST,  PROCESS FOR PRODUCING HYDROGEN USING THE CATALYST,  AND POWER GENERATION SYSTEM', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种烃分解催化剂，其包含镁、铝和镍作为构成元素，基于催化剂的重量含有0.001至20重量%(以Si计)的硅，并且基于催化剂的重量具有0.1至40重量%(以金属镍计)的镍含量； 以及烃分解催化剂，其包含多孔载体和载体上负载的催化活性金属，所述多孔载体包含镁和铝作为组成元素，并包含0.001至20重量%(以Si计)的硅，所述催化活性金属包含细金属镍颗粒，所述细金属镍颗粒的含量为0.1至40重量%(以金属镍计)，以催化剂的重量计。 本发明的烃分解催化剂价格较低，能够表现出能够分解C1以上烃的优异的催化活性，即使在较少的蒸汽条件下也具有良好的抗结焦性，即使使用含氮烃燃料也具有减少副产氨的量的良好效果，并且能够在催化剂内部发生结焦时具有能够防止催化剂破碎和破碎的足够强度，并且具有优异的耐久性。', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention relates to a hydrocarbon-decomposing catalyst comprising magnesium,  aluminum and nickel as constitutional elements,  containing silicon in an amount of 0.001 to 20% by weight (calculated as Si) based on the weight of the catalyst,  and having a nickel content of 0.1 to 40% by weight (calculated as metallic nickel) based on the weight of the catalyst;  and a hydrocarbon-decomposing catalyst comprising a porous carrier and a catalytically active metal carried on the carrier,  said porous carrier comprising magnesium and aluminum as constitutional elements and containing silicon in an amount of 0.001 to 20% by weight (calculated as Si) based on the weight of the catalyst,  and said catalytically active metal comprising fine metallic nickel particles,  a content of said fine metallic nickel particles being 0.1 to 40% by weight (calculated as metallic nickel) based on the weight of the catalyst. The hydrocarbon-decomposing catalyst of the present invention is less expensive,  and can exhibit an excellent catalytic activity capable of decomposing C1 or more hydrocarbons,  a good anti-coking property even under a less steam condition,  a good effect of reducing an amount of ammonia by-produced even upon using nitrogen-containing hydrocarbon fuels,  and a sufficient strength capable of preventing the catalyst from being crushed and broken even upon occurrence of coking inside thereof,  and an excellent durability.', p.application_date = '2016-02-19 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US20160167963A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/26', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'ATE803777'}) SET p.application_no = 'ATE803777', p.title_cn = '用于生产乙炔和合成气的方法', p.title_en = 'METHOD FOR PRODUCING ACETYLENE AND SYNTHESIS GAS', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种方法用于生产乙炔和合成气的氧的部分氧化烃的方法。在所述方法中，一种第一输入流含有一种或多种烃和第二输入含氧流被分开地预热，从彼此，混合在比第二的质量流率的输入流的质量流率，第一输入对应的流程氧数λ小于或等于0.31，和经过燃烧器块至燃烧室。烃部分氧化燃烧室中。由此获得的裂化气体，它被急冷至80至90摄氏度下游的燃烧室通过将水性淬火介质。工艺水流量iliq和产物气体流获得Ig。该产物气体流冷却在冷却柱通过与冷却水直接换热的装置为了获得过程用水流的iiliq作为底流，产品气流量iig作为顶流，和侧流，电过滤器中烟灰的耗尽。一种工艺水流量iiiliq中出现的电滤波器。工艺水流入iliq，iiliq，和iiiliq合并和通过灰凹槽的表面进行粒子分离器以获得合并的方法水流ivliq。所述方法的特征在于，该合并过程中水流ivliq进行清洗的部分单级闪蒸罐中蒸发，该合并过程用水流ivliq的水分蒸发至一分数为0.01重量%至10重量%，在相对于其总重量，为了得到清洗后的工艺水流量vliq，其再循环到方法。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a method for producing acetylene and synthesis gas by partially oxidizing hydrocarbons by means of oxygen. In said method,  a first input flow containing one or more hydrocarbons and a second input flow containing oxygen are preheated separately from each other,  mixed at a ratio of the mass flow rate of the second input flow to the mass flow rate of the first input flow corresponding to an oxygen number lambda less than or equal to 0.31,  and fed via a burner block to a combustion chamber. The hydrocarbons are partially oxidized in the combustion chamber. A cracked gas is thereby obtained,  which is quenched to 80 to 90 degrees Celsius downstream of the combustion chamber by injecting an aqueous quenching medium. A process water flow Iliq and a product gas flow Ig are obtained. The product gas flow is cooled down in a cooling column by means of direct heat exchange with cooling water in order to obtain a process water flow IIliq as a bottom flow,  a product gas flow IIg as a top flow,  and a side flow,  which is depleted of soot in an electric filter. A process water flow IIIliq arises in the electric filter. The process water flows Iliq,  IIliq,  and IIIliq are merged and conducted via soot grooves having surface particle separators in order to obtain a merged process water flow IVliq. The method is characterized in that the merged process water flow IVliq is subjected to cleaning by means of partial evaporation in a single-stage flash tank,  the merged process water flow IVliq being evaporated to a fraction of 0.01 wt% to 10 wt%,  in relation to the total weight thereof,  in order to obtain a cleaned process water flow Vliq,  which is recycled into the method.', p.application_date = '2013-06-13 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'ATE803777T1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/36', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201410345917.5'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201410345917.5', p.title_cn = '一氧化碳变换工艺', p.title_en = 'Carbon monoxide conversion process', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种一氧化碳变换工艺，解决了现有一氧化碳变换工艺复杂、流程长、系统温度控制不稳定、催化剂易失活的问题。技术方案包括粗煤气经煤气分离器气液分离后送煤气过滤器过滤，然后送入蒸汽混合器中与中压蒸汽混合，混合气送入煤气预热气与出等温反应器的反应气换热升温，升温后的混合气送入等温反应器进行反应，使原料气的反应转化率达90％以上，反应后的反应气送入所述煤气预热器与混合气换热降温后再送入低温绝热反应器进一步充分反应得到变换气。本发明工艺流程极其简单、控制可靠、设备投资低、运行成本低、节能降耗、可获得高品位蒸汽。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a carbon monoxide shifting process,  and is used for solving the problems that existing carbon monoxide shifting processes are complex and are long in flows,  system temperatures are instable to control and catalysts are easy to inactivate. The carbon monoxide shifting process comprises the steps that the raw gas is sent to a gas filter to be filtered after undergoing gas-liquid separation in a gas separator and then is sent to a steam mixer to be mixed with medium pressure steam,  the gas mixture is sent to a gas preheater to exchange heat with the reaction gas coming out of an isothermal reactor to be heated,  the heated gas mixture is sent to the isothermal reactor to react,  so that the reaction conversion rate of the raw gas is above 90%,  and the reaction gas after reaction is sent to the gas preheater to exchange heat with the gas mixture to be cooled and then is sent to a low-temperature adiabatic reactor to further fully react,  thus obtaining the shift gas. The process has the advantages of extremely simple flow,  reliability in control,  low equipment investment,  low operating cost,  energy conservation and consumption reduction and capability of obtaining high-grade steam.', p.application_date = '2014-07-21 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN104150439B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/12', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201410827170.7'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201410827170.7', p.title_cn = '制备生物合成气的装置和方法', p.title_en = 'Preparing biological synthesis gas apparatus and method', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种制备生物合成气的装置和方法，制备生物合成气的装置，包括气化炉，在气化炉内的中部设置有催化床隔板，中上部设置有气体分布板，顶部设置有混合室，储水罐通过管道依次与第一泵、第二预热器连、混合室连接，液相类生物质储罐通过管道依次与第二泵、第三预热器、混合室连接，气化炉的底部通过管道与气液分离器连接，气液分离器与液体收集瓶连接，液体收集瓶通过管道依次与洗气瓶，滤气管，第二气体流量计，气体取样阀连接后再与产品集气容器活动连接，载气瓶通过管道依次与减压阀，第一截止阀，背压阀，第一气体流量计，第一预热器连接后再与混合室的顶部连接。本发明的装置可用于处理所有液相类生物质，对原料的适应性极强。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention discloses a device and a method for preparing biological synthesis gas. The device for preparing the biological synthesis gas comprises a gasifier,  wherein a catalytic bed partition plate is arranged in the middle inside the gasifier;  a gas distribution plate is arranged at the middle-upper part inside the gasifier;  a mixing chamber is arranged on the top of the gasifier;  a water storage tank is connected with a first pump,  a second preheater and the mixing chamber through pipelines in sequence;  a liquid-phase biomass storage tank is connected with a second pump,  a third preheater and the mixing chamber through pipelines in sequence;  the bottom of the gasifier is connected with a gas-liquid separator through a pipeline;  the gas-liquid separator is connected with a liquid collection bottle;  the liquid collection bottle is connected with a gas-washing bottle,  a gas filter pipe,  a second gas flowmeter and a gas sampling valve through pipes in sequence and then movably connected with a product gas collection container;  and a gas carrying bottle is connected with a pressure reducing valve,  a first stop valve,  a back pressure valve,  a first gas flowmeter and a first preheater through pipelines in sequence and then connected with the top of the mixing chamber. The device provided by the invention can be used for treating all liquid-phase biomass and has very strong adaptability to raw materials.', p.application_date = '2014-12-26 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN104528645B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201511018159.7'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201511018159.7', p.title_cn = '潜水式锌镓合金制氢装置工作方法', p.title_en = 'Submerged Zn/Ga alloy hydrogen producing apparatus working method', p.abstract_cn = '潜水式锌镓合金制氢装置工作方法属于新能源、减少温室气体排放及军事领域，减少古生物能源的使用，减缓南极、北极及全球永久冰盖消溶的速度，减小厄尼诺现象对人类危害，可以将潜水式锌镓合金制氢装置工作方法制氢所得到的新能源来满足全人类在经济发展中对能源的依赖，在军事领域可以用氢氧燃料电站为军用设备服务，此项制氢及氢使用过程都不会有温室气体排放，从而达到减少温室气体排放、减缓南极、北极和全球永久性冰盖消溶及海平面上升速度，氢是非常清洁的能源，美国最新发明了铝镓合金制氢技术，使用80％的锌加上20％的镓(无需高纯度)的合金，就能使锌在常温下极快与水发生化学反应，因此开辟了制氢新路径。', p.abstract_en = 'A submerged Zn/Ga alloy hydrogen producing apparatus working method belongs to novel energy resources,  reduction on greenhouse gas emission and military field,  reduction on consumption on paleontological energy resources,  reduction on speed on permanent ice cap melting in the Antarctic and Arctic poles and the whole world,  and reduction on the damage of the El Nino phenomenon on human being. New energy produced through hydrogen production with the method can satisfies dependency on energy resources in economic development of the whole human being. In the military field,  a hydrogen/oxygen fuel power plant can be used for serving military equipment. The hydrogen producing and using process is free of greenhouse gas emission,  thereby reducing the greenhouse gas emission and alleviating the speed on permanent ice cap melting and sea level raise. Hydrogen is very clean energy. In America,  an Al/Ga alloy hydrogen producing technology is invented,  wherein an alloy of 80% zinc and 20% gallium (without necessity on high purity) is employed for carrying out a chemical reaction to the zinc with water very quickly at normal temperature,  so that a novel method of producing hydrogen is developed.', p.application_date = '2015-12-29 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105668516A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/08', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201610017699.1'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201610017699.1', p.title_cn = '一种高温含烃气体制备合成气的方法', p.title_en = 'Method for preparing synthetic gas from high temperature hydrocarbon-containing gas', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种高温含烃气体制备合成气的方法，该方法主要由工艺烧嘴、高温含烃气体入口腔和转化炉三部分，通过转化炉内的非催化部分氧化反应过程，将高温含烃气体中的甲烷以及焦油、苯、酚等进一步转化为CO和H2为主的合成气。高温含烃气体来源广泛，可以是垃圾、生物质、褐煤、烟煤等热解或者固定床气化的气相产物，通过该方法生产的合成气可用于制氢、合成氨、甲醇、乙二醇、FT合成等工艺，用途极为广泛。该方法环境友好，合成气洗涤过程中的废水不含有机物；高温含烃气体的转化率可达99％以上；工艺流程和设备结构简单，投资省。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a method for preparing synthetic gas from high temperature hydrocarbon-containing gas. The method utilizes a technical burner,  a high temperature hydrocarbon-containing gas inlet chamber and a reforming furnace. Through a non-catalytic partial oxidation reaction process in the reforming furnace,  methane in high-temperature hydrocarbon-containing gas,  tar,  benzene and phenol are further transformed to form synthetic gas mainly containing CO and H2. The high-temperature hydrocarbon-containing gas has a wide source and comprises pyrolysis or fixed bed gasification gas products such as garbage,  biomass,  brown coal and soft coal. The synthetic gas can be used for preparation of hydrogen,  synthetic ammonia,  methanol,  glycol and FT and has wide purposes. The method is environmentally friendly. The waste water of synthetic gas washing does not contain organic matters. The high-temperature hydrocarbon-containing gas has a conversion rate of 99% or more. The method has a simple process,  a simple structure and a low investment.', p.application_date = '2016-01-12 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105668517A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/36', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201520906497.3'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201520906497.3', p.title_cn = '一种液态金属辅助铝块直接制氢装置', p.title_en = 'Direct hydrogen plant of supplementary aluminium pig of liquid metal', p.abstract_cn = '本实用新型涉及一种液态金属辅助铝块直接制氢装置，包括铝块、液态金属罐、水溶液罐、氢气收集罐、废液回收池、旋转喷头、升降台，所述旋转喷头通过管路分别连接液态金属罐和水溶液罐，旋转喷头下方设置所述铝块，铝块放置在升降台上，升降台位于废液回收池内。本实用新型提供的液态金属辅助铝板水溶液直接制氢装置，首次实现了固体铝在室温下的直接、连续快速产氢，该连续制氢过程无需提前将铝与液态金属配制成固相合金或液相合金，避免了以往方法中提前配制合金时会因储存受潮产氢继而出现爆炸的潜在风险。', p.abstract_en = 'The utility model relates to a direct hydrogen plant of supplementary aluminium pig of liquid metal,  including aluminium pig,  liquid metal jar,  water -soluble fluid reservoir,  hydrogen collection tank,  waste liquor recovery pond,  rotatory nozzle,  elevating platform,  rotatory nozzle passes through the pipeline and connects liquid metal jar and water -soluble fluid reservoir respectively,  and the rotatory nozzle below sets up aluminium pig,  aluminium pig are placed on the elevating platform,  and the elevating platform is located the waste liquor recovery pond. The utility model provides a supplementary aluminum plate aqueous solution of liquid metal direct hydrogen plant,  realized first solid aluminium under the room temperature direct,  produce hydrogen fast in succession,  this continuous hydrogen manufacturing process need not to prepare into solid phase alloy or liquid phase alloy with aluminium with liquid metal in advance,  can make moist because of the storage when having avoided in the past in the method in advance the alloyage and produce the hydrogen potential risk that explodes of appearance then.', p.application_date = '2015-11-12 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN205313077U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/08', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201521140404.7'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201521140404.7', p.title_cn = '半水煤气节能变换装置', p.title_en = 'Energy -conserving converting means of semiwater gas', p.abstract_cn = '本实用新型涉及一种合成氨制备装置，具体涉及一种半水煤气节能变换装置，包括饱和塔和热交换器，热交换器包括预热交换器和主热交换器，预、主热交换器均包括腔体和换热管，饱和塔出口顺次与预热交换器和主热交换器的换热管相连，主热交换器的换热管出口连接至中变炉入口，中变炉出口顺次与主热交换器和预热交换器的腔体相连，预热交换器的腔体出口顺次通过调温器I和脱氯塔连接至低变炉I进口，低变炉I出口通过调温器II连接至低变炉II进口，低变炉I设置在低变炉II上方，低变炉II出口通过水加热器顺次连接热水塔、软水加热器和冷却器。本实用新型有效提高变换率，减小占地面积和施工难度，延长低变催化剂的使用寿命，节约成本。', p.abstract_en = 'The utility model relates to a synthetic ammonia preparation facilities,  concretely relates to energy -conserving converting means of semiwater gas,  including saturator and heat exchanger,  heat exchanger includes heat exchanger and main heat exchanger in advance,  in advance,  main heat exchanger all includes cavity and heat exchange tube,  saturator export links to each other with heat exchanger and main heat exchanger\'s heat exchange tube in advance in order,  main heat exchanger\'s heat exchange tube exit linkage to well change stove entry,  well change outlet of still is continuous with main heat exchanger and heat exchanger\'s in advance cavity in order,  heat exchanger\'s cavity exports and is connected to the low stove I import that becomes through thermoregulator I and dechlorination tower in order in advance,  the export of low change stove I is connected to the low stove II import that becomes through thermoregulator II,  the low stove I that becomes sets up in the low stove II top that becomes,  the hot water tower is connected through water heater in order to the export of low change stove II,  soft water heater and cooler. The utility model discloses effectively improving the interconversion rate,  reducing the area and the construction degree of difficulty,  the low life who becomes the catalyst of extension practices thrift the cost.', p.application_date = '2015-12-31 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN205313078U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/16', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201620076328.6'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201620076328.6', p.title_cn = '一种用于部分氧化系统的氮气无循环升温装置', p.title_en = 'A nitrogen gas does not have a circulation rising temperature device for partial oxidation system', p.abstract_cn = '一种用于部分氧化系统的氮气无循环升温装置。本实用新型涉及一种升温装置，具体涉及一种用于部分氧化系统的氮气无循环升温装置。本实用新型为解决现有甲醇生产装置在部分氧化工序升温过程中由于停车造成的能源浪费及产量减少的问题。一种用于部分氧化系统的氮气无循环升温装置中的氮气输送管道通过第一连接管道由前至后依次穿过原料气预热器、混合气预热器、加热炉和转化炉，转化炉的排气端连接有废热锅炉，废热锅炉的排气端连接有第二连接管道，第二连接管道由前至后依次穿过混合气预热器、锅炉给水预热器、原料气预热器、除盐水预热器和水冷器，水冷器的排气端与分离器连接，分离器的排气端上设有放空阀。本实用新型用于氮气升温。', p.abstract_en = 'The utility model provides a nitrogen gas does not have a circulation rising temperature device for partial oxidation system. The utility model relates to a rising temperature device,  concretely relates to a nitrogen gas does not have a circulation rising temperature device for partial oxidation system. The utility model discloses a solve current methyl alcohol product installation at partial oxidation process intensification in -process because the problem that the energy is extravagant and output reduces of parkking and causing. A nitrogen gas pipeline through first connecting tube by the preceding feed gas pre -heater that passes in proper order after to of among a nitrogen gas does not have a circulation rising temperature device for partial oxidation system,  the gas mixture pre -heater,  heating furnace and reborner,  the exhaust end of reborner is connected with waste heat boiler,  waste heat boiler\'s exhaust end is connected with the second connecting tube,  the second connecting tube is by the preceding gas mixture pre -heater that passes in proper order after to,  the boiler feed water pre -heater,  the feed gas pre -heater,  demineralized water pre -heater and water cooler,  the exhaust end and the separator of water cooler are connected,  be equipped with the atmospheric valve on the exhaust end of separator. The utility model is used for nitrogen gas heaies up.', p.application_date = '2016-01-26 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN205313079U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/36', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201521087465.1'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201521087465.1', p.title_cn = '一种粗苯加氢生产工艺中用的循环氢气控制装置', p.title_en = 'Circulation hydrogen controlling means who uses in crude benzene hydrogenation production technology', p.abstract_cn = '一种粗苯加氢生产工艺中用的循环氢气控制装置，氢气回收系统包括回气管、脱硫塔和压缩机，脱硫塔下端的侧壁上设置有气体入口和液体出口，液体出口位于气体入口下方，脱硫塔的顶部设置有气体出口和液体入口，液体入口位于气体出口下方，回气管上也设置有阀门，回气管的进口伸入到粗苯加氢反应罐内并位于液面上方，回气管的出口与脱硫塔的气体入口连通，脱硫塔的气体出口与压缩机的进口连通，压缩机的出口氢气罐连通。多余的氢气经过回气管进入脱硫塔内进行除杂，由脱硫塔排出的纯净氢气经过压缩机后返回到氢气罐内再次使用，这就可以将多余的氢气回收利用，节省能源，避免造成资源的浪费，结构简单，使用方便。', p.abstract_en = 'The utility model provides a circulation hydrogen controlling means who uses in crude benzene hydrogenation production technology,  the hydrogen recovery system includes the muffler,  desulfurizing tower and compressor,  be provided with gas access and liquid outlet on the lateral wall of desulfurizing tower lower extreme,  the liquid outlet is located the gas access below,  the top of desulfurizing tower is provided with gas outlet and liquid inlet,  liquid inlet is located the gas outlet below,  also be provided with the valve on the muffler,  the import of muffler is stretched into in the crude benzene hydrogenation retort and is lain in the liquid level top,  the export of muffler and the gas access of desulfurizing tower intercommunication,  the gas outlet of desulfurizing tower and the import intercommunication of compressor,  the export hydrogen jar intercommunication of compressor. Unnecessary hydrogen carries out the edulcoration in the muffler gets into the desulfurizing tower,  reuse in returning the hydrogen jar behind the pure hydrogen process compressor of desulfurizing tower exhaust,  and this just can utilize unnecessary hydrogen recovery,  and the energy can be saved avoids causing the waste of resource,  simple structure,  convenient to use.', p.application_date = '2015-12-24 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN205313080U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/50', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201520984176.5'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201520984176.5', p.title_cn = '氢气回收水洗装置', p.title_en = 'Hydrogen recovery water washing device', p.abstract_cn = '本实用新型公开了氢气回收水洗装置，包括氢气进管、氢气出管道，所述氢气进管及氢气出管道分别设置在一个U形管的首末端，所述U形管内放置的是纯净水，所述U形管的两端头分别设置疏水透气膜。所述氢气进管中设置至少一道过滤网。本实用新型不但可以将才生产线上下来的带有一定温度的氢气进行降温，并且能够讲氢气中已经夹杂的颗粒物浮尘清洗掉，得到相对纯净的氢气气体。并且，本装置能够大量节约氢气的使用量，在很大程度上节约了钼酸制品的生产成本，增加了产品的价格竞争力。', p.abstract_en = 'The utility model discloses a hydrogen recovery water washing device,  including hydrogen advance tub,  hydrogen goes out the pipeline,  hydrogen advances the pipe and hydrogen play pipeline sets up the first end at a U -shaped pipe respectively,  the U -shaped is intraductal,  and what place is the pure water,  the both ends head of U -shaped pipe sets up hydrophobic ventilated membrane respectively. During advancing to manage,  hydrogen sets up one at least filter screen. The utility model discloses the hydrogen that has an uniform temperature that not only just now gets off on the production line is lowered the temperature to can say that the particulate matter floating dust that has mix with washs in the hydrogen,  it is gaseous to obtain hydrogen net relatively. And the use amount of hydrogen can be practiced thrift in a large number to this device,  practiced thrift the manufacturing cost of molybdic acid goods at to a great extent,  increased the price competitive power of product.', p.application_date = '2015-12-02 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN205313081U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/52', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201521069904.6'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201521069904.6', p.title_cn = '一种尾气中二氧化碳以及氢气回收装置', p.title_en = 'Carbon dioxide and hydrogen recovery device in tail gas', p.abstract_cn = '本实用新型公开了一种尾气中二氧化碳以及氢气回收装置，包括二氧化碳回收单元以及氢气回收单元，二氧化碳回收单元包括连接于尾气输送系统的洗涤器，洗涤器连接有若干第一吸附塔，第一吸附塔上设有第一气体出口以及解吸出口，解吸出口连接有真空泵，真空泵依次连接有二氧化碳缓冲罐以及增压泵，增压泵分别通过阀门连接有火炬系统以及二氧化碳应用系统；氢气回收单元包括混合气缓冲罐，混合气缓冲罐连接有若干第二吸附塔，第二吸附塔设有第二气体出口以及吸附气体出口，第二气体出口连接于氢气应用系统，吸附气体出口连接于火炬系统。通过二氧化碳回收单元以及氢气回收单元，能够回收尾气中二氧化碳以及氢气，提高经济效益，降低环境污染的风险。', p.abstract_en = 'The utility model discloses a carbon dioxide and hydrogen recovery device in tail gas,  including carbon dioxide recovery unit and hydrogen recovery unit,  carbon dioxide recovery unit is including connecting in tail gas conveying system\'s scrubber,  and the scrubber is connected with a plurality of first adsorption towers,  is equipped with first gas outlet and desorption export on the first adsorption tower,  and the desorption exit linkage has the vacuum pump,  and the vacuum pump has connected gradually carbon dioxide buffer tank and booster pump,  and the booster pump is connected with flare system and carbon dioxide application system through the valve respectively,  the hydrogen recovery unit includes the gas mixture buffer tank,  and the gas mixture buffer tank is connected with a plurality of second adsorption towers,  and the second adsorption tower is equipped with second gas outlet and adsorbed gas export,  and the second gas outlet is connected in hydrogen application system,  adsorbed gas exit linkage in flare system. Retrieve unit and hydrogen recovery unit through carbon dioxide,  can retrieve carbon dioxide and hydrogen in the tail gas,  improve economic benefits,  reduce environmental pollution\'s risk.', p.application_date = '2015-12-17 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN205313082U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/56', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'EP13865205'}) SET p.application_no = 'EP13865205', p.title_cn = '氢气产生装置', p.title_en = 'HYDROGEN GENERATION DEVICE', p.abstract_cn = '一种氢气发生器(1)包括 : 重整器(6)被配置成产生燃料气体，含有氢作为主要成分，从原料气体；一种燃烧器被构造以热重整器；一种加氢脱硫器(3)，被配置为加热重整器原料中去除含硫化合物材料气体的加氢脱硫反应；和冷却器(19)配置成冷却所述加氢脱硫剂。该重整器包括低温部分和高温部分温度较高，比低温部分。冷却器设置在对应位置的重整器的高温部分。', p.abstract_en = 'A hydrogen generator (1) includes :  a reformer (6) configured to generate a fuel gas,  containing hydrogen as a major component,  from a raw material gas;  a combustor configured to heat the reformer;  a hydro-desulfurizer (3) configured to be heated by the reformer to remove a sulfur compound contained in the raw material gas by a hydrodesulfurization reaction;  and a cooler (19) configured to cool down the hydro-desulfurizer. The reformer includes a low temperature portion and a high temperature portion higher in temperature than the low temperature portion. The cooler is provided at a position corresponding to the high temperature portion of the reformer.', p.application_date = '2013-12-16 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'EP2933226A4', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'EP14771940'}) SET p.application_no = 'EP14771940', p.title_cn = '二氧化碳优先氧化反应器', p.title_en = 'REACTOR FOR PREFERENTIAL OXIDATION OF CARBON MONOXIDE', p.abstract_cn = '本发明可包括在反应器和CO优先氧化的技术领域，更具体地，在优先氧化反应器中形成用于随后的一部分乙醇处理系统中使用的进料燃料电池舰艇或航海应用，包括至少三个热交换器用于冷却气体流具有高的H2浓度，通过水流和至少三个优先氧化反应器的模块具有催化剂床，其特征在于总数量的管(15)的热交换器(1，10，12)集成在单个圆筒形壳体(14)和所述重整气体进气歧管(2)设置在底座上的圆柱形壳体，在出口歧管收集流出的重整气的管，并将它应用到每个所述CO优先氧化的模块(5，11，13)设置在圆柱形壳体的另一底座。', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention can be included in the technical field of CO preferential oxidation reactors and,  more specifically,  in preferential oxidation reactors that form part of an ethanol processing system for subsequently feeding a fuel cell used in naval or marine applications,  which comprises at least three heat exchangers for cooling a gas stream with a high H2 concentration by means of a water stream and at least three preferential oxidation reactor modules having a catalyst bed,  characterised in that the total number of tubes (15) of the heat exchangers (1,  10,  12) is integrated in a single cylindrical shell (14) and wherein an inlet manifold for the reformate gas (2) is disposed on one base of the cylindrical shell,  while an oulet manifold that collects the reformate gas that flows out of the tubes and feeds it to each of the CO preferential oxidation modules (5,  11,  13) is disposed on the other base of the cylindrical shell.', p.application_date = '2014-08-04 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'EP3031776A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/58', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'BRPI112013003046'}) SET p.application_no = 'BRPI112013003046', p.title_cn = '称取的氢或氢的制备方法以及使用该方法的Orgnnicos化合物的氢化(质子0，氘0或氚0)', p.title_en = '"process for making hydrogen or hydrogens weighed,  and hydrogenation (protiação,  deuteração or tritiação) of orgnânicos compounds using the same"', p.abstract_cn = '本发明的目的是提供一种不需要大型设备就能方便地提供氢或重质氢的方法，以及一种不使用昂贵的试剂和特殊的催化剂就能方便地进行氢化(质子化，氘化或氚化)反应的方法。 该生产方法包括一种生产氢或重质氢的方法， 包括在催化剂金属存在下使水或重水进行机械化学反应，以及一种制备氢化(质子化，氘化或氚化)有机化合物的方法，包括在催化剂金属存在下使有机化合物与水或重水进行机械化学反应。', p.abstract_en = 'An object is to provide a process for providing hydrogen or heavy hydrogens conveniently without the necessity of large-scale equipment and a process capable of performing hydrogenation (protiation,  deuteration or tritiation) reaction conveniently without the use of an expensive reagent and a special catalyst. The production process includes a process for producing hydrogen or heavy hydrogens,  containing subjecting water or heavy water to mechanochemical reaction in the presence of a catalyst metal,  and a process for producing a hydrogenated (protiated,  deuterated or tritiated) organic compound,  containing subjecting an organic compound and water or heavy water to mechanochemical reaction in the presence of a catalyst metal.', p.application_date = '2011-08-16 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'BR112013003046A2', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'BR112013003046'}) SET p.application_no = 'BR112013003046', p.title_cn = '称取的氢或氢的制备方法，以及使用该方法制备的相同组合物的氢原', p.title_en = '\'\' PROCESS TO PRODUCE HYDROGEN OR hidrogêniosHIDROGÊNIOS WEIGHED,  AND hidrogenaçãoHIDROGENAÇÃO (protiaçãoPROTIAÇÃO,  deuteraçãoDEUTERAÇÃO OR tritiaçãoTRITIAÇÃO) OF SAME COMPOSITES orgnânicosORGNÂNICOS USING \'\'', p.abstract_cn = '本发明的目的是提供一种不需要大型设备就能方便地提供氢或重质氢的方法，以及一种不使用昂贵的试剂和特殊的催化剂就能方便地进行氢化(质子化，氘化或氚化)反应的方法。 该生产方法包括一种生产氢或重质氢的方法， 包括在催化剂金属存在下使水或重水进行机械化学反应，以及一种制备氢化(质子化，氘化或氚化)有机化合物的方法，包括在催化剂金属存在下使有机化合物与水或重水进行机械化学反应。', p.abstract_en = 'An object is to provide a process for providing hydrogen or heavy hydrogens conveniently without the necessity of large-scale equipment and a process capable of performing hydrogenation (protiation,  deuteration or tritiation) reaction conveniently without the use of an expensive reagent and a special catalyst. The production process includes a process for producing hydrogen or heavy hydrogens,  containing subjecting water or heavy water to mechanochemical reaction in the presence of a catalyst metal,  and a process for producing a hydrogenated (protiated,  deuterated or tritiated) organic compound,  containing subjecting an organic compound and water or heavy water to mechanochemical reaction in the presence of a catalyst metal.', p.application_date = '2011-08-16 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'BRPI1303046A2', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'KR1020140167258'}) SET p.application_no = 'KR1020140167258', p.title_cn = '热交换器型反应器，其具有涂有不同的催化剂', p.title_en = 'Heat Exchanger-Type Reactor Having Plates Coated with Different Catalysts', p.abstract_cn = '用于根据本发明的固体氧化物燃料电池蒸汽重整的圆柱形空心圆柱状的反应器本体(10)，所述反应器主体(10)间隔开的内部设有催化剂反应段(20)，所述催化剂的反应区(20)设置在燃烧器单元和栅极层间介电插入管(50)，所述反应器主体(10)下，所述反应釜本体(10)和所述催化剂的反应区(20)，其插入到轴承壳体之间的空间催化剂进气管(80)，所述的反应器壳体(10)中的状态放置在顶部燃烧气体，狗定性催化剂气体和燃烧器的电流和通风单元，用于将排出部(70)包括，所述催化剂的反应区(20)接收输入的接触面积比现有产品的蒸汽加热的气体燃烧器狗定性催化剂气体和预滤波信号，以增加管式折叠成。', p.abstract_en = 'According to the present invention,  a cylindrical steam reforming reactor for a solid oxide fuel cell includes :  a reactor body (10) having a hollow cylindrical shape;  a catalytic reaction unit (20) disposed inside the reactor body (10) to be spaced apart from the reactor body (10);  a burner pipe unit (50) inserted in the catalytic reaction unit (20) from a lower portion of the catalytic reaction unit (20);  a catalytic gas inlet pipe (80) inserted into a space between the reactor body (10) and the catalytic reaction unit (20) through a lower portion of the reactor body (10);  and a discharge unit (70) disposed on the reactor body (10) and allowing a reforming catalyst gas and a burner combustion gas to be discharged,  wherein the catalytic reaction unit (20) is a bellows type so as to increase a contact area for heat exchange between an introduced reforming catalyst gas and a burner combustion gas.', p.application_date = '2014-11-27 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'KR101632119B1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/32', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14428053'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14428053', p.title_cn = '从硫化氢中回收氢的方法', p.title_en = 'Method for recovering hydrogen from hydrogen sulfide', p.abstract_cn = '本发明提供了一种使用负载银催化剂从硫化氢中回收氢的方法，以及一种使用这种催化剂净化含硫化氢的气流的方法。', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention provides a method for recovering hydrogen from hydrogen sulfide using a supported silver catalyst,  and a method for purifying a gas stream containing hydrogen sulfide using such a catalyst.', p.application_date = '2013-08-15 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9364789B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/08', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 2, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14258469'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14258469', p.title_cn = '水煤气变换反应过程', p.title_en = 'Water gas shift reaction process', p.abstract_cn = '一种用于增加包括氢和碳氧化物并具有一氧化碳含量≥45mol%的基于干气的合成气的氢含量的方法， 包括以下步骤 : (i)将合成气与蒸汽合并以形成富蒸汽的原料气混合物；(ii)在220-370°C范围内的入口温度下使原料气混合物通过铁基水煤气变换催化剂以形成基于干气的一氧化碳含量为10摩尔%的富氢的变换气混合物；以及(iii)回收富氢的变换气混合物，其中一部分富氢的变换气混合物再循环到原料气混合物中。', p.abstract_en = 'A process for increasing the hydrogen content of a synthesis gas including hydrogen and carbon oxides and having a carbon monoxide content ≧45 mole % on a dry-gas basis,  including the steps of :  (i) combining the synthesis gas with steam to form a steam-enriched feed gas mixture(ii) passing the feed gas mixture at an inlet temperature in the range 220-370° C. over an iron-based water-gas shift catalyst to form a hydrogen-enriched shifted gas mixture having a carbon monoxide content 10 mole % on a dry gas basis,  and(iii) recovering the hydrogen-enriched shifted gas mixture,  where a portion of the hydrogen-enriched shifted gas mixture is recycled to the feed gas mixture.', p.application_date = '2014-04-22 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9365421B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/32', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14098731'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14098731', p.title_cn = '用于在基于氧传输膜的重整系统中生产合成气的方法和系统，其中所生产的合成气被再循环', p.title_en = 'Method and system for producing a synthesis gas in an oxygen transport membrane based reforming system with recycling of the produced synthesis gas', p.abstract_cn = '一种用于在基于氧传输膜的重整系统中生产合成气的方法和系统，所述重整系统使用具有约1.6至3.0的蒸汽/碳比和约500°C至750°C的温度的组合进料物流。所述组合进料物流包括预重整烃进料、过热蒸汽和通过含氢物流在氧传输膜元件的渗透侧与渗透氧反应而产生的反应产物物流，其中所述含氢物流是合成气的再循环部分。', p.abstract_en = 'A method and system for producing a synthesis gas in an oxygen transport membrane based reforming system that utilizes a combined feed stream having a steam to carbon ratio between about 1.6 and 3.0 and a temperature between about 500° C. and 750° C. The combined feed stream is comprised a pre-reformed hydrocarbon feed,  superheated steam,  and a reaction product stream created by the reaction of a hydrogen containing stream reacted with the permeated oxygen at the permeate side of the oxygen transport membrane elements and wherein the hydrogen containing stream is a recycled portion of the synthesis gas.', p.application_date = '2013-12-06 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9365422B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/24', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14056528'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14056528', p.title_cn = '一种降低煤气化炉耗氧的方法', p.title_en = 'Method of reducing oxygen requirement of a coal gasifier', p.abstract_cn = '对煤气化炉进行改造以实现多种优点，例如减少氧消耗、CO2和NOx排放、更好的H : C比、更好的碳转化等。这是通过将煤划分为至少两个区并对气化炉进行改造并如所述操作来实现的。 将煤注入第一区，配置成使注入的煤的大部分脱挥发分，以产生煤焦和挥发物。 调节操作以基本上消耗注入第一区中的氧化剂。 将低热值、高氧化剂原料注入气化器的第二区。 低热值、高氧化剂含量原料的脱挥发分提供了使在第一区中产生的煤焦的至少一部分气化的含氧化合物。', p.abstract_en = 'A coal gasifier is retrofitted to achieve multiple advantages such as reduced oxygen consumption,  reduced CO2 and NOx emissions,  better H : C ratio,  better carbon conversion etc. This is achieved by dividing the coal into at least two zones and modifying the gasifier and operating it as described. The coal is injected into a first zone,  configured to devolatilize a substantial portion of the injected coal to produce coal char and volatiles. The operation is tuned to substantially consume the oxidant injected in the first zone. A low-calorific-value,  high oxidant feedstock is injected in second zone of the gasifier. The devolatilization of the low-calorific-value,  high oxidant content feedstock provides the oxygen containing compounds which gasify at least a portion of the coal char generated in the first zone.', p.application_date = '2013-10-17 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9365784B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/36', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US13449476'}) SET p.application_no = 'US13449476', p.title_cn = '一种处理动物粪便的方法及系统', p.title_en = 'Method and system for processing animal waste', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种处理动物粪便的方法和系统。 在特定实施例中，所述方法包括将动物废物转移到气化器以燃烧所述动物废物，使水循环通过气化器的烟道堆中的热交换器以产生热水，以及将所述热水泵送到有机朗肯循环系统以产生电、辐射加热器或其任何组合。在一个特定实施例中，所述方法包括将动物废物转移到气化器以燃烧所述动物废物，使水循环通过所述气化器的烟道堆中的热交换器以产生热水，以及将所述热水泵送到有机朗肯循环系统以产生电、辐射加热器或其任何组合。 此外，该方法包括使热水循环通过有机朗肯循环系统的蒸发器以蒸发制冷剂，并使来自蒸发器的蒸发制冷剂循环通过涡轮机以发电。 此外，该方法包括使用粪肥撒布器以变化的进料速率将动物废物供给气化器，该变化的进料速率基于同时计算供给气化器的动物废物的英国热量单位(BTU)。', p.abstract_en = 'A method and system of processing animal waste is disclosed. In a particular embodiment,  the method includes transferring animal waste to a gasifier to burn the animal waste,  circulating water through a heat exchanger in a flue stack of the gasifier to generate heated water,  and pumping the heated water to either an organic Rankine cycle system to generate electricity,  a radiant heater,  or any combination thereof. In addition,  the method includes circulating the heated water through an evaporator of the organic Rankine cycle system to vaporize a refrigerant,  and circulating the vaporized refrigerant from the evaporator,  through a turbine to generate the electricity. Also,  the method includes using a manure spreader to feed the animal waste to the gasifier at a varying feed rate that is based on contemporaneously calculating a British thermal units (BTU) of the animal waste being fed to the gasifier.', p.application_date = '2012-04-18 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9366429B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/36', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'IDW00201300537'}) SET p.application_no = 'IDW00201300537', p.title_cn = 'None', p.title_en = 'None', p.abstract_cn = '', p.abstract_en = '', p.application_date = '2013-02-08 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'IDP000041644B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/36', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'AU2012275561'}) SET p.application_no = 'AU2012275561', p.title_cn = '还原性气体发生器和产生还原性气体的方法', p.title_en = 'Reducing gas generators and methods for generating reducing gas', p.abstract_cn = '本发明的一个实施例是一种独特的还原性气体发生器。另一个实施例是一种独特的方法用于产生还原气体。其它实施例包含设备，系统，装置，硬件，方法，和组合，用于产生还原气体。进一步的实施例，形式，特征，方面，益处，本发明的优点将从描述中变得显而易见，这里提供的附图。', p.abstract_en = 'One embodiment of the present invention is a unique reducing gas generator. Another embodiment is a unique method for generating a reducing gas. Other embodiments include apparatuses,  systems,  devices,  hardware,  methods,  and combinations for generating reducing gas. Further embodiments,  forms,  features,  aspects,  benefits,  and advantages of the present application will become apparent from the description and figures provided herewith.', p.application_date = '2012-06-26 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'AU2012275561B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/36', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'AU2014351491'}) SET p.application_no = 'AU2014351491', p.title_cn = '发电系统和有关的方法', p.title_en = 'Power generation systems and methods regarding same', p.abstract_cn = '固体燃料动力源，其提供至少一个热，电等动力的直接电或热到电上还设置供电电源系统，包括 : (i)至少一个反应单元用于催化原子氢形成分数氢的，(ii)化学燃料混合物包含至少两个选自以下的组分 : 源的H2O催化剂或H2O催化剂；原子氢源或原子氢；反应物形成源的H2O催化剂或H2O催化剂和原子氢源或原子氢；一个或多个反应物引发催化原子氢；和材料，使固态燃料是高导电的，(Ⅲ)的至少一个电极组是限制燃料和电动力源是提供一种短突发低电压，大电流电能启动的快速动力学的分数氢反应和能量增益由于形成分数氢，(iv)的产物回收系统，例如冷凝器，(v)换装系统，(vi)至少一个水合，热，化学，和电化学系统再生燃料从反应产物，(viii)的热沉，其接受从电源产生热反应，(viii)一种功率转换系统，其可包括直流等离子体电转换器，例如能量转换器，磁流体动力转换器，电磁直(交叉场或漂移)转换器，直接转换器，和电荷迁移的转换器或热到电力转换器，例如朗肯或等压式动力装置。', p.abstract_en = 'A solid fuel power source that provides at least one of thermal and electrical power such as direct electricity or thermal to electricity is further provided that powers a power system comprising (i) at least one reaction cell for the catalysis of atomic hydrogen to form hydrinos,  (ii) a chemical fuel mixture comprising at least two components chosen from :  a source of H20 catalyst or H20 catalyst;  a source of atomic hydrogen or atomic hydrogen;  reactants to form the source of H20 catalyst or H20 catalyst and a source of atomic hydrogen or atomic hydrogen;  one or more reactants to initiate the catalysis of atomic hydrogen;  and a material to cause the solid fuel to be highly conductive,  (iii) at least one set of electrodes that confine the fuel and an electrical power source that provides a short burst of low-voltage,  high-current electrical energy to initiate rapid kinetics of the hydrino reaction and an energy gain due to forming hydrinos,  (iv) a product recovery systems such as a condenser,  (v) a reloading system,  (vi) at least one of hydration,  thermal,  chemical,  and electrochemical systems to regenerate the fuel from the reaction products,  (vii) a heat sink that accepts the heat from the power-producing reactions,  (viii) a power conversion system that may comprise a direct plasma to electric converter such as a plasmadynamic converter,  magnetohydrodynamic converter,  electromagnetic direct (crossed field or drift) converter,  direct converter,  and charge drift converter or a thermal to electric power converter such as a Rankine or Brayton-type power plant.', p.application_date = '2014-01-10 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'AU2014351491A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CA2968730'}) SET p.application_no = 'CA2968730', p.title_cn = '本发明涉及一种消除挥发性有机化合物和氨中的有害气体污染物', p.title_en = 'A PROCESS FOR THE ELIMINATION OF VOLATILE ORGANIC COMPOUNDS AND HAZARDOUS AIR POLLUTANTS IN AMMONIA PLANTS', p.abstract_cn = '过程中用于消除挥发性有机物(VOCs)及危险的空气污染物(HAP)形成为副产物在所述的变位段(β氨厂，一种二氧化碳(CO2)流从排气线，它设有移段和下游的CO2脱除段，再循环至主重整器(TR)制氨设备中。这样，所述含氧化合物中所含的二氧化碳出孔中时，分解所述初级重整器燃烧器，所述总发射的VOC和HAP将明显降低。', p.abstract_en = 'In a process for the elimination of volatile organic compounds (VOCs) and hazardous air pollutants (HAPs) formed as by-products in the shift section (SS) of an ammonia plant,  a carbon dioxide (C02) stream from a vent line,  which is arranged downstream from the shift section and the C02 removal section,  is recycled to the primary reformer (TR) of the ammonia plant. This way,  the oxygenates contained in the carbon dioxide vent will be decomposed in the primary reformer burners,  and the total emission of VOCs and HAPs will be considerably reduced.', p.application_date = '2015-11-25 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CA2968730A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'ES13189958'}) SET p.application_no = 'ES13189958', p.title_cn = '系统和含H2气和纯净水的制造方法', p.title_en = 'System and process for producing a gas containing H2 and purified water', p.abstract_cn = '系统和方法用于制造含H[2]产品由组合的H2气体与纯净水生产重整和热水纯化过程。原水，如盐水，间接热传递加热从2产生重整的重整产物的纯化方法，多效蒸馏过程中的原水。', p.abstract_en = 'System and process for producing a H 2 -containing product gas and purified water from an integrated H 2 -producing reforming and thermal water purification process. Raw water,  such as salt water,  is heated by indirect heat transfer with reformate from the H 2 -producing reforming process for purifying raw water in a multiple effect distillation process.', p.application_date = '2013-10-23 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'ES2573652T3', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WOEP15077598'}) SET p.application_no = 'WOEP15077598', p.title_cn = '一种消除挥发性有机化合物的方法和合成氨厂中有害的空气污染物', p.title_en = 'A PROCESS FOR THE ELIMINATION OF VOLATILE ORGANIC COMPOUNDS AND HAZARDOUS AIR POLLUTANTS IN AMMONIA PLANTS', p.abstract_cn = '过程中用于消除挥发性有机化合物(VOCs)及有害空气污染物(HAP)形成为副产物在所述的变位段(β氨厂，一种二氧化碳(CO2)流从排气线，其下游设置有从移段和CO2脱除段，再循环至主重整器(TR)氨设备。这样，二氧化碳出孔中所含含氧化合物会分解在主重整器的燃烧器，和总VOC和HAP的排放明显降低。', p.abstract_en = 'In a process for the elimination of volatile organic compounds (VOCs) and hazardous air pollutants (HAPs) formed as by-products in the shift section (SS) of an ammonia plant,  a carbon dioxide (C02) stream from a vent line,  which is arranged downstream from the shift section and the C02 removal section,  is recycled to the primary reformer (TR) of the ammonia plant. This way,  the oxygenates contained in the carbon dioxide vent will be decomposed in the primary reformer burners,  and the total emission of VOCs and HAPs will be considerably reduced.', p.application_date = '2015-11-25 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016087275A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WOEP15078097'}) SET p.application_no = 'WOEP15078097', p.title_cn = 'SOFC的SOFC系统的操作的系统和方法', p.title_en = 'SOFC SYSTEM AND METHOD OF OPERATING A SOFC SYSTEM', p.abstract_cn = 'SOFC系统(1)包括 : -燃料重整的重整器(102)用于气态烃流(100)和蒸汽(404)到富氢气体(103)，-一种固体氧化物燃料电池堆(2)包括阳极(4)和阴极(3)用于电化学反应的氢富气(103)和阴极空气流(204)以产生电，阳极排气流(104)和阴极耗损了的空气流(205)，所述阳极排气流(104)和阴极耗损了的空气流(205)保持分离，-燃烧器(105)，用于燃烧的混合物的阳极排气流(104)和新鲜空气流(300)燃烧充分，产生的热能用于所述重整器(102)，-控制单元(601)，风机(302)，控制单元(601)控制所述风机(302)，用于控制质量流率的新鲜空气流(300)提供热量给重整器(102)，以气态烃流(100)和产生的燃烧器排气装置流(106)，和一热交换器(107)，所述冷凝水(403)从阳极废气流(104)或燃烧器废气流(106)加热产生蒸汽(404)。', p.abstract_en = 'The SOFC system (1) comprising :  - a fuel reformer (102) for reforming a gaseous hydrocarbon stream (100) and steam (404) into a hydrogen rich gas (103),  - a solid oxide fuel cell stack (2) including an anode (4) and a cathode (3) for electrochemically reacting the hydrogen rich gas (103) and a cathode air stream (204) to produce electricity,  an anode exhaust stream (104) and a cathode depleted air stream (205),  wherein the anode exhaust stream (104) and the cathode depleted air stream (205) are kept separate,  - a burner (105) for combusting a mixture of the anode exhaust stream (104) and a fresh air stream (300) to complete combustion and produce heat for the reformer (102),  - a control unit (601) and a blower (302),  the control unit (601) controlling the blower (302) for controlling the mass flow rate of the fresh air stream (300) to provide heat to the reformer (102) to reform the gaseous hydrocarbon stream (100) and to produce a burner exhaust stream (106),  - and a heat exchanger (107),  wherein condensed water (403) from the anode exhaust stream (104) or the burner exhaust stream (106) is heated to generate steam (404).', p.application_date = '2015-11-30 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016087389A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/48', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WOGB15053664'}) SET p.application_no = 'WOGB15053664', p.title_cn = '氢生成方法', p.title_en = 'HYDROGEN GENERATION METHOD', p.abstract_cn = '产生氢气的方法，从细长筒含氢化物的燃料，具有气体出口点设置在其一端的特征在于步骤 : (1)直接加热氢化物燃料在一个或多个位置(S)沿长轴墨盒以使氢气的析出位置处(S)；(2)使氢气气体的析出位置处(S)流沿所述轴线向所述出口点和(3)引起热前的位置处产生(S)沿轴线传播的料筒加热的任何剩余的氢化物燃料间接。该方法允许速率输送氢的气体例如内燃发动机或燃料电池可变化以满足所需的载荷。', p.abstract_en = 'A method of generating hydrogen gas from an elongate cartridge containing a hydride fuel and having a gas exit-point arranged at one end thereof characterised by the steps of (1) directly heating the hydride fuel at one or more location(s) along the major axis of the cartridge to cause hydrogen gas to be evolved at the location(s);  (2) causing hydrogen gas evolved at the location(s) to flow along the axis towards the exit-point and (3) causing a heat front generated at the location(s) to propagate along the axis of the cartridge to heat any remaining hydride fuel indirectly. The method allows the rate of delivery of hydrogen gas to e.g. an internal combustion engine or fuel cell to be varied to meet the load required.', p.application_date = '2015-12-01 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016087839A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WOGB15053665'}) SET p.application_no = 'WOGB15053665', p.title_cn = '氢发生器', p.title_en = 'HYDROGEN GENERATOR', p.abstract_cn = '一种氢气发生器，其特征在于包括 : 一种库(1)适于存储多个氢化物的燃料管或棒(2)；氢释放位置(3)适于接收所述氢化物的燃料卡盒，在该盒被支撑和氢气可释放；传动装置(4)，(5)，(6)，用于使未使用的氢化物燃料盒连接到氢释放位置；盒密封装置，用于形成氢气-之间的气密性密封盒体或棒和氢气的处理管道(11)和顶出装置，用于从氢化物的燃料卡盒移除用过的氢释放位置(5)，(8)，(19)和(20)。', p.abstract_en = 'A hydrogen generator is characterised by comprising :  a magazine (1) adapted to store a plurality of hydride fuel cartridges or sticks (2);  a hydrogen-releasing location (3) adapted to receive the hydride fuel cartridges at which the cartridge is supported and hydrogen can be released;  a transmission means (4),  (5),  (6) for moving unused hydride fuel cartridges to the hydrogen-releasing location;  a cartridge sealing means for forming a hydrogen gas-tight seal between the cartridge or stick and hydrogen gas-handling pipework (11) and an ejection means for removing the spent hydride fuel cartridges from the hydrogen-releasing location (5),  (8),  (19) and (20).', p.application_date = '2015-12-01 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016087840A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201280033679.3'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201280033679.3', p.title_cn = '通过多步铜-氯热化学循环的氢气产生方法', p.title_en = 'The thermochemical cycle-chloro step copper the hydrogen generating method', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种用于通过包括铜和氯化合物的反应的低温、多步、封闭的循环铜-氯(Cu-Cl)工艺从水中产生氢气和氧气的热化学方法。一种用于通过Cu-Cl热化学循环产生氢气的方法包括四个热反应和一个电化学反应以及一个单元操作。该循环包括六个步骤：(1)氢气产生步骤；(2)铜产生步骤；(3)干燥步骤；(4)氯化氢产生步骤；(5)分解步骤；(6)氧气产生步骤。顺序工艺的净反应是水分解成氢气和氧气。作为通过热化学铜-氯(Cu-Cl)循环产生氢气的一部分，产生氧化铜的方法包含使氯化铜颗粒与过热蒸汽接触，并且产生氧气的方法包含氧化铜与干燥氯气的反应。这些反应是在高温和大气压下在作为固定床类型的流通型石英反应器中进行。', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention discloses a method for thermochemical production of hydrogen and oxygen from water by a low temperature,  multi-step,  closed,  cyclic copper-chlorine (Cu—Cl) process involving the reactions of copper and chlorine compounds. A method for production of hydrogen via Cu—Cl thermochemical cycle consists of four thermal reactions and one electrochemical reaction and one unit operation. The cycle involves six steps :  (1) hydrogen production step;  (2) copper production step;  (3) drying step;  (4) hydrogen chloride production step;  (5) decomposition step;  (6) oxygen production step. The net reaction of the sequential process is the decomposition of water into hydrogen and oxygen. The methods for production of copper oxide which comprises contacting copper chloride particles with superheated steam and production of oxygen comprises reaction of copper oxide with dry chlorine as a part of hydrogen production by thermochemical Copper-Chlorine (Cu—Cl) cycle. The reactions are performed in a flow through type quartz reactor as fixed bed type at high temperature and atmospheric pressure.', p.application_date = '2012-07-09 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN103930365B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/08', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201410440172.0'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201410440172.0', p.title_cn = '透氧膜、透氢膜交替分解水制取氢气的装置', p.title_en = 'Oxygen permeable film,  hydrogen permeable film alternate water decomposition apparatus for producing hydrogen', p.abstract_cn = '本发明提供了一种透氧膜、透氢膜交替分解水制取氢气的装置。该装置包括：扁平状盒体，其内部分成若干个间隔排列的透氧腔室和透氢腔室；以及内管道，在各个透氧腔室和透氢腔室内延伸，相邻腔室的内管道通过外管道首尾相连，内管道和外管道共同构成连通的蛇形蒸汽通道，透氧腔室中的内管道由透氧膜制成，透氢腔室中的内管道由透氢膜制成，透氢腔室中内管道透氢膜内外两侧以及透氧腔室中内管道透氧膜内外两侧均具有化学势差，在化学势差的作用下，氧气透过透氧膜，氢气通过透氢膜，分别进入内管道和相应腔室内壁之间的区域。本发明中，蒸汽通路由透氧膜内管道和透氢膜内管道交替连接而成，水蒸汽分解率比通过单一透氧膜或者单一透氢膜时高很多。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention provides a device for alternately decomposing water to make hydrogen by oxygen permeating membranes and hydrogen permeating membranes. The device comprises a flat box body and inner pipelines,  wherein the internal part of the flat box body is divided into a plurality of oxygen permeating chambers and hydrogen permeating chambers which are arranged at intervals;  the inner pipelines extend inside all the oxygen permeating chamber and hydrogen permeating chamber;  the inner pipelines of the adjacent chambers are connected with each other end to end through an outer pipeline;  the inner pipelines and the outer pipeline form communicated serpentine steam channel;  the inner pipelines in the oxygen permeating chambers are made of the oxygen permeating membranes;  the inner pipelines in the hydrogen permeating chambers are made of the hydrogen permeating membranes;  chemical potential difference exists between the inner and outer sides of the hydrogen permeating membranes of the inner pipelines in the hydrogen permeating chambers and chemical potential difference also exists between the inner and outer sides of the oxygen permeating membranes of the inner pipelines in the oxygen permeating chambers;  and oxygen and hydrogen respectively enter the regions between the inner pipelines and the inner walls of the corresponding chambers through the oxygen permeating membranes and the hydrogen permeating membranes under the action of the chemical potential differences. According to the device,  the steam channel is formed by alternate connection of the inner pipelines of the oxygen permeating membranes and the hydrogen permeating membranes,  and the water vapor decomposition rate is much higher than that the situation of use of only oxygen permeating membranes or hydrogen permeating membranes.', p.application_date = '2014-09-01 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN104163399B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201410851664.9'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201410851664.9', p.title_cn = '一种使用膜分离与变压吸附联合处理炼厂气的方法和系统', p.title_en = 'Using a membrane separation and pressure swing adsorption joint processing refinery gas method and system', p.abstract_cn = '本发明提供了一种使用膜分离与变压吸附联合处理炼厂气的方法和系统。该方法是根据膜分离装置和变压吸附装置对原料气组成和压力要求的不同，将多股炼厂气分为：重整氢气、低压贫氢气体、低压富氢气体、高压贫氢气体、高压富氢气体。重整氢气通过膜分离装置或变压吸附装置回收氢气，低压贫氢气体、高压贫氢气体通过膜分离装置预提纯后再经变压吸附装置回收氢气，高压富氢气体、低压富氢气体通过变压吸附装置回收氢气。本发明还提供了用于上述方法的系统。本发明提供的方法和系统具有氢气纯度高、回收率高的特点，且适用于旧装置增产，操作弹性大，回收氢气纯度可达99vol％以上，回收率高于95％。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention provides a method and a system for jointly treating a refinery gas by adopting membrane separation and pressure swing adsorption. According to the method,  multiple refinery gases are sorted as reforming hydrogen,  a low-pressure hydrogen-poor gas,  a low-pressure hydrogen-rich gas,  a high-pressure hydrogen-poor gas and a high-pressure hydrogen-rich gas according to different requirements of a membrane separation device and a pressure swing adsorption device on the composition and pressure of a feed gas;  hydrogen is recovered from the reforming hydrogen through the membrane separation device or the pressure swing adsorption device;  the low-pressure hydrogen-poor gas and the high-pressure hydrogen-poor gas are purified through the membrane separation device and then hydrogen is recovered through the pressure swing adsorption device;  and hydrogen is recovered from the high-pressure hydrogen-rich gas and the low-pressure hydrogen-rich gas through the pressure swing adsorption device. The invention also provides a system for the method. The method and system which are provided by the invention have the characteristics of high hydrogen purity and high recovery rate,  are suitable for the yield increase of an old device and high in operating flexibility and can achieve the recovered hydrogen purity more than 99vol/% and the recovery rate more than 95%.', p.application_date = '2014-12-31 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN104495752B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/56', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201510990831.2'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201510990831.2', p.title_cn = '一种氢化铝储氢材料及其制备方法', p.title_en = 'Aluminum hydride hydrogen storage material and preparation method thereof', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种氢化铝储氢材料及其制备方法，储氢材料由氢化铝和催化剂制成；所述的催化剂的通式为M或者MxOy，M代表过渡金属Sc、Ti、V、Cr、Mn、Fe、Cu、Nb中的一种或两种以上，x＝1或2；y＝1，2，3，4或5；所述的氢化铝和催化剂的摩尔比为100：0.1～10。本发明还公开了一种氢化铝储氢材料的制备方法，将氢化铝和催化剂，密封于球磨罐中进行机械球磨，球磨后得到氢化铝储氢材料。本发明采用该方法改性的氢化铝储氢材料能够降低氢化铝储氢材料放氢温度，不仅能够在60℃的温度下开始放氢，而且放氢量也较高，可达8.0wt％，该放氢量比现有技术改性的氢化铝储氢材料高。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention discloses an aluminum hydride hydrogen storage material and a preparation method thereof. The hydrogen storage material is made from aluminum and a hydrogenation catalyst. The catalyst has a general formula of M or MxOy;  M represents one or more transition metals selected from Sc,  Ti,  V,  Cr,  Mn,  Fe,  Cu and Nb;  x equals to 1 or 2;  y equals to 1, 2, 3, 4 or 5;  and the molar ratio of the hydride hydrogen and the catalyst is 100 : 0.1-10. The invention also discloses a preparation method of the aluminum hydride hydrogen storage material. The method is as below :  sealing aluminum hydride and the catalyst in a ball milling tank for mechanical milling to obtain the aluminum hydride hydrogen storage material. The aluminum hydride hydrogen storage material modified by the method can reduce hydrogen desorption temperature of the aluminum hydride hydrogen storage material,  can release hydrogen at the temperature of 60 DEG C,  has high hydrogen desorption amount up to 8.0 wt%,  which is higher than that of the aluminum hydride hydrogen storage material modified by the prior art.', p.application_date = '2015-12-24 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105645351A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201511000646.0'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201511000646.0', p.title_cn = '核能激光炭的镍铁氧体(CNF)制氢氧方法', p.title_en = 'Method for preparing oxyhydrogen from carbon nickel ferrite (CNF) through using nuclear energy laser', p.abstract_cn = '一种核能激光炭的镍铁氧体(CNF)制氢氧方法是新能源及减少温室气体排放环境保护及军事领域，将核能转换更加便于实用的氢氧能源，将核电站发出的电能，用激光发生装置转换成激光，用光缆将激光导入水下，将炭的镍铁氧体(CNF)加热到300摄氏度，生产出的氢气与氧气，每个小室直径只能象蜂巢的直径大小，只能用1根光纤，避免高热产生，产生的氢氧在水的作用下会迅速降温及上浮，上部有锥顶桶体将其收集并马上分离，锥顶桶体中总保持最少的氢氧状态并远离人员和其它设备，整个制氢氧过程都是在水下进行的，制氢氧设备的阀门是气动阀，仪控用的是不易产生火花的低压电，可自行下潜，驱动制氢氧设备上浮是压缩空气，因此是安全的。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention discloses a method for preparing oxyhydrogen from carbon nickel ferrite (CNF) through using nuclear energy laser,  and belongs to the fields of new energy,  reduction of discharge of greenhouse gases,  environment protection and military affairs. The method is characterized in that nuclear energy is transited into oxyhydrogen energy convenient to use,  electric energy emitted by a nuclear power station is transited into laser by using a laser generation device,  the laser is introduced to underwater by a cable,  the CNF is heated to 300DEG C to produce hydrogen and oxygen,  the diameter of every small chamber is similar to the diameter of a honeycomb,  only one fiber is used to avoid generation of high heat,  the generated oxyhydrogen is rapidly cooled under the action of water and floats upward,  an above conic top barrel body collects the oxyhydrogen and immediately separates hydrogen and oxygen,  the conic top barrel body keeps a smallest oxyhydrogen amount and is far from personnel and other devices,  the whole oxyhydrogen production process is carried out underwater,  the valve of an oxyhydrogen production device is a pneumatic valve,  a low potential source difficulty generating spark is used by an instrument controller and can implement self diving,  and compressed air is used to drive the oxyhydrogen production device to float upward,  so the method is safe.', p.application_date = '2015-12-26 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105645352A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201511017654.6'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201511017654.6', p.title_cn = '潜水式钙镓合金制氢装置工作方法', p.title_en = 'Working method of submersible type calcium-gallium alloy hydrogen making device', p.abstract_cn = '潜水式钙镓合金制氢装置工作方法属于新能源、减少温室气体排放及军事领域，减少古生物能源的使用，减缓南极、北极及全球永久冰盖消溶的速度，减小厄尼诺现象对人类危害，可以将潜水式钙镓合金制氢装置工作方法制氢所得到的新能源来满足全人类在经济发展中对能源的依赖，在军事领域可以用氢氧燃料电站为军用设备服务，此项制氢及氢使用过程都不会有温室气体排放，从而达到减少温室气体排放、减缓南极、北极和全球永久性冰盖消溶及海平面上升速度，氢是非常清洁的能源，美国最新发明了铝镓合金制氢技术。使用80％的钙加上10％的镓(无需高纯度)的合金，就能使钙在常温下极快与水发生化学反应，因此开辟了制氢新路径。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention discloses a working method of a submersible type calcium-gallium alloy hydrogen making device,  and belongs to the fields of new energy resources,  reduction of greenhouse gas emission and military. According to the working method of the submersible type calcium-gallium alloy hydrogen making device,  disclosed by the invention,  the using of paleontological energy resources is reduced,  the melting speed of permanent ice sheets in the South Pole,  the North Pole and the globe can be slowed down,  and the damage to human beings due to the EI Nino phenomenon can be reduced;  the dependency on energy resources of all human beings during economic development can be met by the new energy resource obtained during a hydrogen making process of the working method of the submersible type calcium-gallium alloy hydrogen making device;  an oxygen-hydrogen fuel power station can be used to serve military equipment in the field of military,  and the greenhouse gas emission does not exist in a hydrogen making and hydrogen using process,  so that the greenhouse gas emission is reduced,  and the melting speed of the permanent ice sheets in the South Pole,  the North Pole and the globe,  and the sea level rising speed are slowed down;  hydrogen is a very clean energy resource,  and an aluminium-gallium alloy hydrogen making technology is newly developed in America. By using an alloy prepared from 80 percent of calcium and 10 percent of gallium (without high-purity gallium),  calcium is enabled to extremely rapidly react with water under normal temperature,  so that a new hydrogen making path is developed.', p.application_date = '2015-12-29 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105645353A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/08', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201410635593.9'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201410635593.9', p.title_cn = '氢气的富甲烷气等离子合成工艺', p.title_en = 'Methane-rich gas plasma synthesis process of hydrogen', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种氢气的富甲烷气等离子合成工艺，将富甲烷气先与反应高温尾气换热，再与等离子裂解气化反应器器壁换热，后进入等离子裂解气化反应器内与等离子发生器产生的等离子体射流相作用，生成以氢气为主要成分的气体。该方法克服了传统工艺需要催化剂，催化剂易发生析碳, 硫、卤素、砷中毒的难题，同时也解决了等离子体制氢过程中能耗较高以及反应器器壁的保护的问题。本发明工艺流程短、操作简单、热效率高, 环境污染小，适用于燃气化工领域与等离子化工领域。', p.abstract_en = 'Within the present invention discloses a methane-rich gas plasma synthesis process of hydrogen. According to the process,  methane-rich gas is subjected to heat exchange with reaction high-temperature tail gas,  and then is subjected to heat exchange with the wall of a plasma pyrolysis gasification reactor,  and the obtained gas enters the plasma pyrolysis gasification reactor and acts with the plasma jet flow produced by a plasma generator to generate the gas adopting hydrogen gas as the main component. According to the present invention,  the difficult problems that the traditional process requires the catalyst and the catalyst easily produces carbon precipitation,  sulfur poisoning,  halogen poisoning and arsenic poisoning are overcome,  and the problems of the high energy consumption and the reactor wall protection during the plasma-to-hydrogen process are solved;  and the process has characteristics of short process,  simple operation,  high thermal efficiency and low environmental pollution,  and is suitable for the fuel gas chemical industry field and the plasma chemical industry field.', p.application_date = '2014-11-13 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105645355A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/34', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201480056831.9'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201480056831.9', p.title_cn = '制备包括乙二醇的流的方法', p.title_en = 'Process for producing a stream comprising ethylene glycol', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种通过源自木质纤维素生物质原料的液体糖流制备包括乙二醇和丙二醇的低沸点混合物的方法。该液体糖流在氢气存在下催化转化为混合物，将其至少分离成包括甘油的高沸点混合物和低沸点混合物。该高沸点混合物通过重整转化为氢气，将该重整氢气用于催化步骤中。优选地，该转化方法中所用的所有氢气都是由该高沸点多元醇混合物的水相重整生成的。', p.abstract_en = 'It is disclosed a process for producing a low boiling mixture comprising ethylene glycol and propylene glycol from a liquid sugar stream derived from a ligno-cellulosic biomass feedstock. The liquid sugar stream is catalytically converted in the presence of hydrogen to a mixture,  which is separated into at least a high boiling mixture,  comprising glycerol,  and the low boiling mixture. The high boiling mixture is converted to hydrogen by reforming and the reforming hydrogen is used in the catalytical steps. Preferably,  all the hydrogen used in the conversion process is generated by aqueous phase reforming of the high boiling polyols mixture.', p.application_date = '2014-10-16 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105658571A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/22', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201520964484.1'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201520964484.1', p.title_cn = '一种氢气发生装置', p.title_en = 'Hydrogen generating device', p.abstract_cn = '本实用新型公开了一种氢气发生装置，其包括密封接合的储液室和产氢室，所述储液室内腔和产氢室内腔之间经弹性膜分隔，同时所述储液室的出液口与产氢室的入液口连通，所述产氢室上还设有气体出口。本实用新型的氢气发生装置使用弹性膜将储液室和产氢室分隔，利用弹性膜的形变，引入气压反馈，可以让产氢过程自动进行，并可避免产氢室气压过高，同时提高产氢原料利用率。', p.abstract_en = 'The utility model discloses a hydrogen generating device,  its stock solution room and product hydrogen chamber that includes the sealing compound,  through the elastic membrane partition,  simultaneously between indoor chamber of stock solution and the product hydrogen chamber inner chamber the liquid outlet of stock solution room and the income liquid mouth intercommunication of producing hydrogen chamber,  still be equipped with the gas outlet on the product hydrogen chamber. The utility model discloses a hydrogen generating device uses the elastic membrane to separate stock solution room and product hydrogen chamber,  utilizes the deformation of elastic membrane,  introduces the atmospheric pressure feedback,  can let product hydrogen process go on automatically to it is too high to avoid producing hydrogen chamber atmospheric pressure,  improves simultaneously to produce the hydrogen raw utilization ratio.', p.application_date = '2015-11-26 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN205294831U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201520964724.8'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201520964724.8', p.title_cn = '反应可控的氢气发生装置及其物料输送装置', p.title_en = 'Controllable hydrogen generating unit reacts and material conveyor thereof', p.abstract_cn = '本实用新型公开了一种反应可控的氢气发生装置及其物料输送装置，其包括物料输送管，所述物料输送管一端与所述氢气发生装置的产氢室的物料入口密封连接，同时，所述物料输送管内还设有可于第一位置和第二位置之间移动的活塞，所述活塞与所述物料输送管之间还设有弹性元件，其中当活塞分别位于第一位置和第二位置处时，所述弹性元件分别呈未压缩状态和压缩状态，并且所述物料输送管上于该第一位置和第二位置之间或临近第一位置处分布有物料入口，所述物料入口上密封连接有可供产氢物料或产氢物料链通过的供料管。本实用新型不仅反应可控，提高了物料的利用率，还大大节省了人力，提高了工作效率，利于工业化生产。', p.abstract_en = 'The utility model discloses a controllable hydrogen generating unit reacts and material conveyor thereof,  it includes material conveying pipe,  material conveying pipe one end with hydrogen generating unit\'s product hydrogen chamber\'s matter entrance sealing connection,  simultaneously,  still be equipped with the piston that can remove in the material conveying pipe between the primary importance and the second place,  the piston with still be equipped with elastic element between the material conveying pipe,  wherein when the piston is located primary importance and second place department respectively,  elastic element is not compression state and compression state respectively,  and material conveying pipe is last between this primary importance and the second place or close on primary importance punishment cloth and have matter entrance,  the last sealing connection of matter entrance has and can supply to produce the hydrogen material or produce the feeder sleeve that hydrogen material chain passes through. The utility model discloses not only react controllable,  improved the utilization ratio of material,  still saved the manpower greatly,  improved work efficiency,  do benefit to the industrial production.', p.application_date = '2015-11-26 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN205294832U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'EP10738944'}) SET p.application_no = 'EP10738944', p.title_cn = '双流化床气化的系统和方法', p.title_en = 'SYSTEM AND METHOD FOR DUAL FLUIDIZED BED GASIFICATION', p.abstract_cn = '合成气深度脱硫的方法，包括将含碳材料和任选的蒸气到气化器中包括热传递介质，提取第一传热流包括传热介质和任选地未转化含碳材料从气化炉，和将至少一部分第一传热流至燃烧器，通入氧化剂，和任选的燃料到燃烧器中，提取第二传热流包括来自燃烧器的热传递介质，和将至少第二传热流的一部分进入气化器，可引入复合物与硫反应生成硫酸盐，硫化物或两个，提取净化流包含灰分，硫酸，卤化物，或其组合从第二传热流，提取烟气从燃烧器，和提取气化器的合成气产品流包括从气化炉出来的小于1000的硫。', p.abstract_en = 'A method for continuous dry reforming,  the method comprising :  introducing a feed comprising carbon dioxide and at least one selected from methane and propane into a fluid bed conditioner operated at a conditioning temperature,  wherein the fluid bed conditioner is one fluid bed of a dual fluidized bed loop and is configured to convert at least a portion of said feed into synthesis gas components;  extracting a first catalytic heat transfer stream comprising a catalytic heat transfer material and having a first temperature from the fluid bed conditioner and introducing at least a portion of the first catalytic heat transfer stream and a flue gas into a fluid bed combustor,  wherein the fluid bed combustor is configured to regenerate the catalyst via combustion;  extracting a second catalytic heat transfer stream comprising catalytic heat transfer material and having a second temperature from the fluid bed combustor and introducing at least a portion of the second catalytic heat transfer stream into the fluid bed conditioner;  and extracting synthesis gas from the fluid bed conditioner.', p.application_date = '2010-01-21 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'EP2379447B1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/44', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'EP15731484'}) SET p.application_no = 'EP15731484', p.title_cn = '装置和能量的方法和物质转化通过热释电材料生产的裂解产物从流体', p.title_en = 'DEVICE AND METHOD FOR ENERGY AND SUBSTANCE CONVERSION BY MEANS OF PYROELECTRIC MATERIALS FOR PRODUCING CLEAVAGE PRODUCTS FROM FLUIDS', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种装置和一种方法，用于能量和物质转化通过热释电材料用于生产裂解产物从流体，所述装置(1)包括至少两个热释电转换器(20，22)彼此相连接的相对于受控阀装置(8)和各具有一漏极线(11，23)；至少一个线路(14)相关联的第一的热释电转换器(20)，用于排出裂解产物(48，52)；至少一个线路(24)相关联的第二的热释电转换器(22)，用于排出裂解产物(52，48)，其中热释电转换器(20)包含至少一个热交换器(2)，其连接到供电线(7)，其中阀装置(8)用于输送至少分配一个流体流(9)具有高温度Th和至少一个流体流(10)具有温度TK低于温度Th，所述热交换器具有至少一个漏极线(11)连接到供电线(7)和通过热交换器吸热流体(50)流动，与被切割；至少一个反应器(3)，用于流体(50)的裂解成裂解产物(48)，所述反应器(3)具有至少一个热释电材料(12)具有预定的居里温度Tc；一种装置(5)，从该至少的线(14)的至少一个LED，用于排出裂解产物(48)产生在反应器(3)；一种控制循环泵(6)，其设置在电路(15)与热交换器(2)，反应器(3)，和装置(5)属于电路(15)和彼此连接，并将流入的流体(50)与被切割到电路(15)通过线路系统(16)连接电路(15)，循环泵(6)连接到受控阀装置(8)外通过控制单元(18)。该装置(1)包括至少一个分离单元(43)相关联的有热释电转换器(20，22)限定的分离的最终裂解产物(48，52)排出的装置(5)的下游设置各个反应器(3)，和线(14，24)用于控制放电的裂解产物(48，52)通入到所述分离单元(43)，从至少线(25，26)，用于排出明确地分离的最终裂解产物(48，52)延伸。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a device and to a method for energy and substance conversion by means of pyroelectric materials for producing cleavage products from fluids,  wherein the device (1) comprises at least two pyroelectric converters (20,  22) which are connected to one another in relation to a controlled valve device (8) and each have a drain line (11,  23);  at least one line (14) associated with the first pyroelectric converter (20) for discharge of cleavage products (48,  52);  at least one line (24) associated with the second pyroelectric converter (22) for discharge of cleavage products (52,  48),  wherein a pyroelectric converter (20) contains at least a heat exchanger (2),  which is connected to a supply line (7) to which the valve device (8) is assigned for delivering at least one fluid stream (9) having a high temperature TH and at least one fluid stream (10) having a temperature TK lower than the temperature TH,  wherein the heat exchanger has at least one drain line (11) connected to the supply line (7) and through which heat exchanger a heat-absorbing fluid (50) flows which is to be cleaved;  at least one reactor (3) for cleavage of the fluid (50) into cleavage products (48),  wherein the reactor (3) has at least one pyroelectric material (12) having a predetermined Curie temperature TC;  an apparatus (5),  out of which at least the line (14) is led for discharge of at least one cleavage product (48) produced in the reactor (3);  a controlled circulation pump (6),  which is disposed within a circuit (15) with the heat exchanger (2),  reactor (3),  and apparatus (5) which belong to the circuit (15) and are connected to one another,  and which supplies flowing fluid (50) to be cleaved to the circuit (15) via a line system (16) connecting the circuit (15),  the circulation pump (6) being connected to the controlled valve device (8) externally via a control unit (18). The device (1) comprises at least one separation unit (43) associated with the pyroelec', p.application_date = '2015-03-11 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'EP3027551A2', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'EP14814997'}) SET p.application_no = 'EP14814997', p.title_cn = '一种方法，所述烯烃的生产通过基于费-托合成', p.title_en = 'A PROCESS FOR THE PRODUCTION OF OLEFINS THROUGH FISCHER-TROPSCH BASED SYNTHESIS', p.abstract_cn = '本发的揭示内容和明涉及一种方法，包括 : a)将一种天然气；b)重整天然气；所述转化步骤包括使天然气与蒸汽反应以产生合成气；c)将所述合成气引入到产物混合物包括至少一种烯烃和副产物包括石蜡和一种汽油；其中，上述转换步骤包括使合成气与一钴/锰催化剂；和d)将副产物转化为合成气。', p.abstract_en = 'The present disclosures and inventions relate to a method comprising :  a) introducing a natural gas;  b) reforming the natural gas;  wherein the reforming step comprises contacting the natural gas with steam to produce a syngas;  c) converting the syngas to a product mixture comprising at least one olefin and a byproduct comprising a paraffin and a gasoline;  wherein the converting step comprises contacting the syngas with a Co/Mn catalyst;  and d) converting the byproduct to syngas.', p.application_date = '2014-07-28 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'EP3027553A2', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/34', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'KR1020160030763'}) SET p.application_no = 'KR1020160030763', p.title_cn = '使用催化剂和余热产生氢气的装置', p.title_en = 'Apparatus for generating hydrogen using catalyst and waste heat', p.abstract_cn = '本发明制取氢气的装置，紧位置进入具有外部壳体和内部空间，所述外部壳体的内部空间和加热装置固定，上热燃烧的氢被配置成产生所述的加热装置安装在顶部的气体燃烧器，当安装在所述的燃气燃烧器的顶部设置从外部对水进行加热和蒸发室和蒸气转换的数字“1”，用于产生氢气的催化剂进入内部，蒸汽蒸发室的所述数量1接收从用户接收的和从所述接触时，该催化剂用于产生氢气和氧气的离解氢室和分离1的数，所述多个晶片1分离的斜侧在氢气和氧气的所述气体供给管输送的气体燃烧器，当安装在所述腔室的顶部从外部提供的所述数量是1分离的加热和蒸发室和汽水转换的数字“2”，用于产生氢气的催化剂蒸发室2进入内部的所述数量由其获得的蒸汽与催化剂接触生成当由该分离的气体氢气体的氢和氧离解包括室2的数。', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention relates to an apparatus for generating hydrogen which provides a maximized effect of water dissociation. The apparatus for generating hydrogen comprises :  an outer housing having a vertically standing inner space;  a heating unit mounted at the lower part of the inner space of the outer housing;  a gas burner mounted at top of the heating unit for generating heat upwardly through the combustion of hydrogen;  a first evaporation chamber mounted at top of the gas burner for heating water supplied from the outside to be converted into vapor;  a first dissociation chamber including a catalyst for generating hydrogen therein so that the vapor transferred from the first evaporation chamber is in contact with the catalyst for generating hydrogen when the vapor is introduced to the inner part and is dissociated into hydrogen gas and oxygen gas;  a gas feed line for transferring the hydrogen gas and oxygen gas generated in the first dissociation chamber to the gas burner;  a second evaporation chamber mounted at the top of the first dissociation chamber for heating water supplied from the outside to be converted into vapor;  and a second dissociation chamber including a catalyst for generating hydrogen therein so that the vapor transferred from the second evaporation chamber is in contact with the catalyst for generating hydrogen when the vapor is introduced to the inner part and is dissociated into hydrogen gas and oxygen gas.', p.application_date = '2016-03-15 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'KR101630374B1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'KR1020160030760'}) SET p.application_no = 'KR1020160030760', p.title_cn = '用于产生氢的催化剂室', p.title_en = 'Apparatus for generating hydrogen using catalyst chamber', p.abstract_cn = '本发明制取氢气的装置，具有内空间的水平纵向设置的倾斜位置的内电极连为一体，简化了结构，在所述外部壳体和平行，所述条状物的外部平稳地移动容纳所述风机至少为两体分离多个通气口内侧的内壳，所述外壳体和内壳体之间安装有壳体和中断进行绝热功能，安装在所述内壳体的内部从外部提供的水被加热和蒸发室上以将其转换成蒸汽，安装在所述...内的用于产生氢气的催化剂[]流体从所述蒸发器内的蒸汽供应到氢气与催化剂接触生成所述催化剂室，蒸汽与催化剂接触产生氢气，所述氢气和氧气的离解室及解离的入口，所述半导体制造装置排出作为室通过收集细矿石解离的氢和氧气体，其连接到所述气体曲柄的外箱体注射单元，在通气口，所述内盒时，所述蒸发室内部安装所述蒸发室向所述热交换器之间，包括有燃烧器的热量散发出去设置有气体。', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention relates to an apparatus for generating hydrogen which increases a water dissociation rate to produce a larger amount of hydrogen promptly. The apparatus for generating hydrogen comprises :  an outer housing having a horizontal inner space provided with an opening at one side in the longitudinal direction thereof and a blower fan at the inner side of the inner space;  an inner housing installed inside the outer housing and provided with a plurality of blowing ports at the side opposite to the blower fan;  a middle housing installed between the outer housing and the inner housing to carry out insulation;  an evaporation chamber mounted in the inner part of the inner housing for heating water supplied from the outside to be converted into vapor;  a catalyst chamber including a catalyst for generating hydrogen so that the vapor generated from the evaporation chamber and introduced to the inner part may be in contact with the catalyst for generating hydrogen;  a dissociation chamber to which the vapor dissociated into hydrogen gas and oxygen gas after the contact with the catalyst for generating hydrogen is introduced;  a gas spraying unit for collecting the hydrogen gas and oxygen gas discharged from the dissociation chamber to the outside of the outer housing;  and a burner mounted between the blower and the evaporation chamber in the inner part of the inner housing to emit heat toward the evaporation chamber.', p.application_date = '2016-03-15 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'KR101630376B1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'SA515370126'}) SET p.application_no = 'SA515370126', p.title_cn = '一种高温变换低汽碳比制氨合成气工艺', p.title_en = 'A process for producing ammonia synthesis gas with high temperature shift and low steam-to-carbon ratio', p.abstract_cn = '一种在前端由含烃原料生产氨合成气的方法，包括以下步骤：所述原料的蒸汽重整，获得包含氢气、一氧化碳和二氧化碳的合成气; 所述合成气的处理，包括一氧化碳的变换和随后的二氧化碳的去除，其中所述合成气的变换包括用铁基催化剂和在大于300℃的温度下的高温变换，并且前端的总体蒸汽碳比为2.6或更小; 还公开了相应的设备和用于改造氨设备的前端的方法。图1', p.abstract_en = 'A process for producing ammonia synthesis gas from a hydrocarbon-containing feedstock in a front-end,  comprising the steps of steam reforming of said feedstock,  obtaining a synthesis gas comprising hydrogen,  carbon monoxide and carbon dioxide;  a treatment of said synthesis gas including shift of carbon monoxide and subsequent removal of carbon dioxide,  wherein the shift of the synthesis gas includes high-temperature shift with an iron-based catalyst and at a temperature greater than 300 °C and the global steam-to-carbon ratio of the front end is 2.6 or less;  a corresponding plant and a method for revamping a front-end of an ammonia plant are also disclosed. Fig. 1', p.application_date = '2014-05-05 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'SA515370126A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'BRPI0517762'}) SET p.application_no = 'BRPI0517762', p.title_cn = '甲烷的改造方法的蒸汽', p.title_en = 'method of methane reform the vapor', p.abstract_cn = '蒸汽甲烷重整方法，其中进料流反应器中处理含有催化剂是可促进氢化反应和部分氧化反应。反应器操作在催化加氢的方式将烯烃转化为饱和烃和/或化学还原硫物质转化为硫化氢或催化氧化方式利用氧气和蒸汽prereform进料和因此，增加氢含量的合成气产生的蒸汽甲烷重整装置。该方法适用于处理的进料流含至少15%体积%的烃与两个或更多个碳原子和/或3%体积%的烯烃，如炼厂废气。在这种情况下，催化氧化方式进行蒸汽与碳的比例小于0.5，氧碳比小于0.25，反应温度约500A°C。至约86a～°C。到限制供给到蒸汽甲烷重整器体积干浓度小于大约0.5%用于烯烃和小于大约10%有两个或更多个碳原子的烷烃。', p.abstract_en = 'A steam methane reforming method in which a feed stream is treated in a reactor containing a catalyst that is capable of promoting both hydrogenation and partial oxidation reactions. The reactor is either operated in a catalytic hydrogenation mode to convert olefins into saturated hydrocarbons and/or to chemically reduce sulfur species to hydrogen sulfide or a catalytic oxidative mode utilizing oxygen and steam to prereform the feed and thus,  increase the hydrogen content of a synthesis gas produced by a steam methane reformer. The method is applicable to the treatment of feed streams containing at least 15% by volume of hydrocarbons with two or more carbon atoms and/or 3% by volume of olefins,  such as a refinery off-gas. In such case,  the catalytic oxidative mode is conducted with a steam to carbon ratio of less than 0.5,  an oxygen to carbon ratio of less than 0.25 and a reaction temperature of between about 500° C. and about 860° C. to limit the feed to the steam methane reformer to volumetric dry concentrations of less than about 0.5% for the olefins and less than about 10% for alkanes with two or more carbon atoms.', p.application_date = '2005-11-07 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'BRPI0517762B1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CA2670795'}) SET p.application_no = 'CA2670795', p.title_cn = '工艺制备氢和一氧化碳的混合物从液烃原料含有一定量的灰', p.title_en = 'PROCESS TO PREPARE A MIXTURE OF HYDROGEN AND CARBON MONOXIDE FROM A LIQUID HYDROCARBON FEEDSTOCK CONTAINING A CERTAIN AMOUNT OF ASH', p.abstract_cn = '工艺制备包括氢气和一氧化碳的合成气混合物从一种液态的碳氢化合物原料中含有0.1和4重量%的灰进行部分氧化烃进料(4)使用多喷孔的燃烧器(2)设有单独的共环形通道的布置，所述烃流通过的通道燃烧器，氧化剂气体(3)流过分离通道的燃烧器，其中，所述通道的烃类进料，氧化剂气体的分离装置的通道由通道，通过该缓和剂气体(5)流过并且其中所述调节气体的出口速度大于该出口速度的氧化剂气体。', p.abstract_en = 'Process to prepare a synthesis gas mixture comprising hydrogen and carbon monoxide from a liquid hydrocarbon feedstock containing between 0.1 and 4 wt% ash by performing a partial oxidation on a hydrocarbon feed (4) using a multi-orifice burner (2) provided with an arrangement of separate co-annular passages,  wherein the hydrocarbon flows through a passage of the burner,  an oxidiser gas (3) flows through a separate passage of the burner and wherein the passage for hydrocarbon feed and the passage for oxidiser gas are separated by a passage through which a moderator gas (5) flows and wherein the exit velocity of the moderator gas is greater than the exit velocity of the oxidiser gas.', p.application_date = '2007-11-30 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CA2670795C', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/36', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CA2840297'}) SET p.application_no = 'CA2840297', p.title_cn = '用于产生合成气的方法和设备', p.title_en = 'METHOD AND PLANT FOR GENERATING SYNTHESIS GAS', p.abstract_cn = '方法和一种系统，用于生成合成气的烃和水被描述。在进一步的细节的方法和系统，合成气体产生的任何期望比例的CO氢和/或合成的官能化和/或非官能化的烃。通过该方法，一种含烃流体能转换成具有可变的合成气的氢含量而不产生显著量CO2。另外，各种形式的氢和碳可获得作为副产物。', p.abstract_en = 'A process and a system for generating synthesis gas from hydrocarbons and water are described. In further details of the process and the system,  synthesis gases are generated in any desired ratios of CO to hydrogen and/or synthetic functionalized and/or non-functionalized hydrocarbons. By means of this process,  a hydrocarbon-containing fluid can be converted into a synthesis gas having a variable hydrogen content without generating significant amounts of CO2. Furthermore,  hydrogen and carbon in various forms can be obtained as byproducts.', p.application_date = '2012-12-20 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CA2840297C', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/24', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14131124'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14131124', p.title_cn = '氢和含碳产品的平行生产方法', p.title_en = 'Method for the parallel production of hydrogen and carbon-containing products', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种平行制备氢和一种或多种含碳产物的方法，其中将烃引入反应空间(R)中，并在富碳颗粒(W)的存在下热分解成碳和氢。 本发明的特征在于，烃分解所需的热能的至少一部分通过气态热载体引入反应空间(R)。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a process for parallel preparation of hydrogen and one or more carbonaceous products,  in which hydrocarbons are introduced into a reaction space (R) and decomposed thermally to carbon and hydrogen in the presence of carbon-rich pellets (W). It is a feature of the invention that at least a portion of the thermal energy required for the hydrocarbon decomposition is introduced into the reaction space (R) by means of a gaseous heat carrier.', p.application_date = '2012-07-05 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9359200B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/24', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US13387841'}) SET p.application_no = 'US13387841', p.title_cn = '自热式换热器填充床气体重整制氢', p.title_en = 'Hydrogen production by an autothermal heat exchanger packed-bed membrane gas reformer', p.abstract_cn = '一种从天然气生产氢气的方法，所述方法包括以下步骤 : (i)提供自热换热器填充床膜重整器(APBMR)，包括 : (a)细长的外部气体氧化室，包括入口、出口和填充的氧化催化剂颗粒，所述入口和出口分别位于所述外部气体氧化室的一端； (b)细长的内部气体蒸汽重整室，其包括入口、出口和填充的蒸汽重整催化剂颗粒，所述入口和出口分别位于所述内部气体蒸汽重整室的一端； (c)一个或多个位于所述蒸汽重整室中的氢分离膜，所述氢分离膜基本上平行于所述蒸汽重整室的纵向轴线； (d)围绕所述外部隔室的一个绝缘层； 以及，任选地，(e)一个或多个细长的内部气体氧化室，所述细长的内部气体氧化室位于所述蒸汽重整室中，基本上平行于所述气体蒸汽重整内部室的纵向轴线，并且包括入口、出口和填充的氧化催化剂颗粒，所述入口和出口各自位于所述内部气体氧化室的末端； (ii)向所述重整器的所述气体氧化室供应包含所述天然气和空气的混合物； 和(iii)将包含所述天然气和水的混合物供应到所述气体蒸汽重整室，其中水与气体的摩尔比在2和4之间，并且其中水可以在供应到所述气体蒸汽重整室之前被预汽化；和(iii)将包含所述天然气和水的混合物供应到所述气体蒸汽重整室，其中水与气体的摩尔比在2和4之间，并且其中水可以在供应到所述气体蒸汽重整室之前被预汽化； 从而产生适于直接馈入发电装置(PGD)以产生电力的氢，或在进一步使用之前储存在适当的容器中的氢。', p.abstract_en = 'A process for producing hydrogen from natural gas,  said process comprises the steps of :  (i) providing an autothermal heat exchanger packed-bed membrane reformer (APBMR) comprising :  (a) an elongated external gas oxidation compartment comprising an inlet,  an outlet and packed oxidation catalyst particles,  said inlet and outlet being located each at one extremity of said external gas oxidation compartment;  (b) an elongated internal gas steam-reforming compartment comprising an inlet,  an outlet and packed steam-reforming catalyst particles,  said inlet and outlet being located each at one extremity of said internal gas steam-reforming compartment;  (c) one or more hydrogen-separating membrane(s) positioned in said steam-reforming compartment substantially parallel to the longitudinal axis of said steam-reforming compartment;  (d) one insulation layer surrounding said external compartment;  and,  optionally,  (e) one or more elongated internal gas oxidation compartment(s) positioned in said steam-reforming compartment substantially parallel to the longitudinal axis of said gas steam-reforming internal compartment,  and comprising an inlet,  an outlet and packed oxidation catalyst particles,  said inlet and outlet being located each at an extremity of said internal gas oxidation compartment(s);  (ii) supplying a mixture comprising said natural gas and air to said gas oxidation compartment(s) of said reformer;  and (iii) supplying a mixture comprising said natural gas and water to said gas steam-reforming compartment,  wherein the water-to-gas molar ratio is of between 2 and 4,  and wherein the water may be pre-vaporized before being supplied into said gas steam-reforming compartment;  thereby producing hydrogen suitable to be directly fed into a power generating device (PGD) to generate an electrical power,  or to be stored into a suitable container before further use.', p.application_date = '2010-08-02 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9359201B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'IN11350DELNP2015'}) SET p.application_no = 'IN11350DELNP2015', p.title_cn = '合成和锰氢化物储氢性能', p.title_en = 'SYNTHESIS AND HYDROGEN STORAGE PROPERTIES OF MANGANESE HYDRIDES', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种新型锰制备它们的方法和它们在氢化物储氢应用。本发明还涉及具有高纯度锰二烷基酯化合物的制备方法以及它们制备中的用途锰氢化物具有增强的储氢容量。', p.abstract_en = 'This disclosure relates to novel manganese hydrides processes for their preparation and their use in hydrogen storage applications. The disclosure also relates to processes for preparing manganese dialkyl compounds having high purity and their use in the preparation of manganese hydrides having enhance hydrogen storage capacity.', p.application_date = '2015-12-14 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'IN11350DELNP2015A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'IN3122MUMNP2015'}) SET p.application_no = 'IN3122MUMNP2015', p.title_cn = '燃料供给装置', p.title_en = 'FUEL SUPPLY APPARATUS', p.abstract_cn = '一种燃料供给装置，它包括；反应室和用于容纳燃料时产生的反应流体和燃料一起产生物质产生多个离散的燃料的燃料产生流体腔室，每一个腔室分别可破裂；和加热器组件，其适于在使用时有选择地破裂产生流体室供给燃料的燃料产生流体输送到反应室中。', p.abstract_en = 'A fuel supply apparatus comprising;  a reaction chamber for hosting a reaction when a fuel generating fluid and a fuel generating substance are brought together to generate fuel a plurality of discrete fuel generating fluid chambers each chamber being separately rupturable;  and a heater assembly adapted to when in use selectively rupture the fuel generating fluid chambers to supply fuel generating fluid to the reaction chamber.', p.application_date = '2015-10-29 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'IN3122MUMNP2015A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/06', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'DE602010032569'}) SET p.application_no = 'DE602010032569', p.title_cn = '氢生成系统及热水生产系统', p.title_en = 'HYDROGEN GENERATION SYSTEM AND HOT WATER PRODUCTION SYSTEM', p.abstract_cn = '氢气产生系统(2A)包括氢产生部(201)保持第第一液含有水和 : 允许部分的第一液中含有的水分解成氢气和氧气，和至少第一的一部分待加热液体，通过照射太阳光，一种第一热交换器(207)进行冷却的第一液氢中加热生成单元(201)和加热第二之间通过热交换液第一液和第二液，和机构(例如，一种循环管路(204)和泵(205))，其将第一液体第一中冷却热交换器(207)入的氢气产生单元(201)。', p.abstract_en = 'A hydrogen generation system (2A) includes a hydrogen generation unit (201) that holds a first liquid containing water and that allows a part of the water contained in the first liquid to be decomposed into hydrogen and oxygen,  and at least a part of the first liquid to be heated,  by being irradiated with sunlight,  a first heat exchanger (207) that cools the first liquid heated in the hydrogen generation unit (201) and heats the second liquid by heat exchange between the first liquid and the second liquid,  and a mechanism (for example,  a circulation line (204) and a pump (205)) that introduces the first liquid cooled in the first heat exchanger (207) into the hydrogen generation unit (201).', p.application_date = '2010-05-21 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'DE602010032569T2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2014555866'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2014555866', p.title_cn = '该氢气产生系统和方法使用凝胶体物质和钠钠硅化物', p.title_en = 'The hydrogen generating system and method utilizing a gel substance and sodium sodium silicide', p.abstract_cn = '系统，装置，和方法，该反应性材料和热稳定的组合水溶液，无毒液体产品和产生氢气。该反应性材料，硅胶或钠硅化物。该氢气产生装置，用于燃料电池和其它工业应用。该系统中，冷却，泵浦，储水，和其它装置的组合，和反应的控制和传感水溶液之间的反应性材料。，产生氢气。弹簧和其它压力机构，加压水溶液，反应。止回阀和其它压力控制机构，基于所述特性的加压机构，反应的燃料在受控的压力输送水的反应器。，稳定阻尼的相关于所施加的压力，输送压力的水溶液可以调节。压力控制机构，用于氢气被偏转可以防止压力调节机构。', p.abstract_en = 'Systems,  devices,  and methods combine thermally stable reactant materials and aqueous solutions to generate hydrogen and a non-toxic liquid by-product. The reactant materials can sodium silicide or sodium silica gel. The hydrogen generation devices are used in fuels cells and other industrial applications. One system combines cooling,  pumping,  water storage,  and other devices to sense and control reactions between reactant materials and aqueous solutions to generate hydrogen. Springs and other pressurization mechanisms pressurize and deliver an aqueous solution to the reaction. A check valve and other pressure regulation mechanisms regulate the pressure of the aqueous solution delivered to the reactant fuel material in the reactor based upon characteristics of the pressurization mechanisms and can regulate the pressure of the delivered aqueous solution as a steady decay associated with the pressurization force. The pressure regulation mechanism can also prevent hydrogen gas from deflecting the pressure regulation mechanism.', p.application_date = '2013-02-07 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP2015505529A5', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/06', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14617120'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14617120', p.title_cn = '一种制备铝/水体系制氢催化剂的方法及其用途', p.title_en = 'Method of preparing a catalyst for Producing Hydrogen from Al/water system and utility thereof', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种铝/水体系制氢催化剂的制备方法。 本发明是一种制备铝/水制氢催化剂的方法，铝/水制氢催化剂的产氢速率远高于工业氢氧化铝。 因此，该催化剂能快速催化铝/水体系制氢。 采用特殊合成的氢氧化铝作催化剂，可以快速制氢，不需使用任何合金元素或极端的腐蚀条件，可以实现快速制氢。', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention discloses a method of preparing a catalyst for producing Hydrogen from Al/water system. The present invention is preparing a catalyst for producing Hydrogen from Al/water system,  the rate which the catalyst for producing Hydrogen from Al/water system is far better than the commercial aluminum hydroxide. So the catalyst can quickly catalyze Al/water system for producing Hydrogen. By using special synthetic aluminum hydroxide as a catalyst to generate hydrogen can be very fast,  without using any alloying elements or extreme corrosion conditions,  can be realized.', p.application_date = '2015-02-09 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US20160152468A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/08', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14556833'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14556833', p.title_cn = '使用具有二次重整的基于氧传输膜的重整系统生产氢的方法和系统', p.title_en = 'METHOD AND SYSTEM FOR PRODUCING HYDROGEN USING AN OXYGEN TRANSPORT MEMBRANE BASED REFORMING SYSTEM WITH SECONDARY REFORMING', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种使用基于氧传输膜的重整系统生产氢的方法和系统，所述方法和系统在重整反应器内进行初级重整工艺，以及在具有或不具有辅助热源的反应驱动的含催化剂的氧传输膜反应器内进行次级重整工艺，以支持重整反应器内的初级重整工艺，从而首先形成合成气产品。 辅助热源设置在氧传输膜基重整系统内，靠近重整反应器，并包括辅助氧传输膜反应器或陶瓷燃烧器。 合成气产物在单独的高温水煤气变换反应器中进一步处理，并任选地在单独的低温水煤气变换反应器中进一步处理。 使用氢气变压吸附从得到的富氢气体中产生氢气。', p.abstract_en = 'A method and system for producing hydrogen using an oxygen transport membrane based reforming system is disclosed that carries out a primary reforming process within a reforming reactor,  and a secondary reforming process within a reactively driven and catalyst containing oxygen transport membrane reactor with or without an auxiliary source of heat to support primary reforming process within the reforming reactor to first form a synthesis gas product. The auxiliary source of heat is disposed within the oxygen transport membrane based reforming system proximate to the reforming reactors and comprises an auxiliary oxygen transport membrane reactor or a ceramic burner. The synthesis gas product is further treated in a separate high temperature water gas shift reactor and optionally in a separate low temperature water gas shift reactor. Hydrogen is produced from the resulting hydrogen-enriched gas using hydrogen PSA.', p.application_date = '2014-12-01 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US20160152469A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/48', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WOEP15071995'}) SET p.application_no = 'WOEP15071995', p.title_cn = '用于氨厂的改造方法', p.title_en = 'A METHOD FOR REVAMPING AN AMMONIA PLANT', p.abstract_cn = '一种方法用于改造合成氨厂，包括蒸汽系统，所述蒸汽系统包括至少一个高压段工作在第一压力和中压段工作在第二压力低于所述第一压力，此改造将包括 : 提供至少一个附加的热回收通过蒸汽流在第三的压力，所述第一和第二之间的中间压力，和提供的蒸汽出口线，设置成向外输出的至少一部分氨设备所述蒸汽流在所述第三压力。', p.abstract_en = 'A method for revamping an ammonia plant including a steam system,  said steam system comprising at least a high-pressure section operating at a first pressure and a medium-pressure section operating at a second pressure lower than said first pressure,  the revamping including :  the provision of at least one additional heat recovery by means of a steam flow at a third pressure which is intermediate between said first and second pressure,  and the provision of a steam export line arranged to export outside the ammonia plant at least a portion of said steam flow at said third pressure.', p.application_date = '2015-09-24 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016082973A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WOEP15077600'}) SET p.application_no = 'WOEP15077600', p.title_cn = '一种工艺用于产生合成气通过烟道气再循环', p.title_en = 'A PROCESS FOR GENERATION OF SYNTHESIS GAS BY FLUE GAS RECYCLE', p.abstract_cn = '用于生成合成气的新方法包括处理烃类进料在初级重整(PR)，压缩至少部分烟气从主压缩机中的重整器(C1)，和将压缩的烟气二次(sr)在一起与主重整器的重整器流出物。过程中，富氧空气(Ea)加到所述初级重整器，二次重整器或两者。所述方法特别适用于联产氨和甲醇或氨或甲醇的生产。总CO2排放，大大降低了利用本发明的方法。', p.abstract_en = 'A novel process for synthesis gas generation comprises treating a hydrocarbon feed in a primary reformer (PR),  compressing at least part of the flue gas from the primary reformer in a compressor (C1),  and feeding the compressed flue gas to a secondary reformer (SR) together with the primary reformer effluent. In the process,  enriched air (EA) is added either to the primary reformer,  to the secondary reformer or both. The process is especially suited for co-production of ammonia and methanol or for production of either ammonia or methanol. The total CO2 emission is lowered considerably by using the process of the invention.', p.application_date = '2015-11-25 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016083434A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/34', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201210133963.X'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201210133963.X', p.title_cn = '一种脱碳和脱氢双重强化甲烷水蒸汽重整制氢的方法及装置', p.title_en = 'A decarburization and dehydrogenation double reinforced methane steam reforming hydrogen production method and apparatus', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种脱碳和脱氢双重强化甲烷水蒸汽重整制氢的方法，包括：(1)将复合催化剂添加至固定床钯膜反应器内，通入氢气和氮气的混合气体，还原复合催化剂；(2)甲烷、水蒸汽经过预热后通入固定床钯膜反应器中，在复合催化剂作用下进行重整制氢反应，生成的氢气透过钯膜，得到纯度大于99.0％的高纯氢气；(3)当复合催化剂需要脱附再生时，停止通入甲烷、水蒸汽，进行催化剂升温脱附再生；(4)复合催化剂再生后，通入甲烷和水蒸汽进行制氢反应；循环进行(2)～(3)步骤。本发明还公开了一种采用上述方法进行甲烷水蒸汽重整制氢的固定床钯膜反应器。本发明制得的氢气纯度高，能耗低，同时也提高了钯膜的使用寿命。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention discloses a decarburization and dehydrogenation double-intensification methane and steam reforming hydrogen production method. The method comprises the following steps of :  (1) adding a composite catalyst into a fixed bed palladium membrane reactor,  introducing mixed gas of hydrogen and nitrogen,  and reducing the composite catalyst;  (2) preheating methane and steam,  introducing into the fixed bed palladium membrane reactor,  performing a reforming hydrogen production reaction under the action of the composite catalyst,  and allowing the generated hydrogen to permeate a palladium membrane to obtain high-purity hydrogen with the purity of more than 99.0 percent;  (3) when the composite catalyst is required to be desorbed and regenerated,  stopping introducing the methane and the steam,  and heating the catalyst for desorption and regeneration;  and (4) after the composite catalyst is regenerated,  introducing the methane and the steam for the hydrogen production reaction,  and circulating the steps from (2) to (3). The invention also discloses the fixed bed palladium membrane reactor for reforming hydrogen production of the methane and the steam by the method. By the method and the reactor,  the prepared hydrogen is high in purity,  the energy consumption is low,  and the service life of the palladium membrane is prolonged at the same time.', p.application_date = '2012-04-28 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN102674247B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/40', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201410011007.3'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201410011007.3', p.title_cn = '含轻质油水煤气变换方法和含轻质油水煤气变换系统', p.title_en = 'Containing light oil-water gas shift process and containing light oil-water gas conversion system', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了含轻质油水煤气变换方法和含轻质油水煤气变换系统。其中，含轻质油水煤气变换方法包括：(1)将含轻质油水煤气通入具有催化剂的变换炉内并发生氧化还原反应，以便得到含有二氧化碳、氢气、水蒸气和气态轻质油的混合气体；(2)将混合气体进行第一冷却处理，以便得到水、轻质油和二氧化碳、氢气、水蒸气以及气态轻质油的第一气液混合物；(3)将气液混合物进行第一气液分离，以便得到含有水和液态轻质油的第一液体混合物和含有二氧化碳、氢气的第一煤气。利用上述方法对含轻质油水煤气进行处理能够显著减少过热蒸汽的消耗，能耗少、成本低。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention discloses a transformation method and a transformation system of a water gas containing light oil. The transformation method comprises the following steps :  (1) leading the water gas containing light oil into a transformation furnace in which a catalyst exists and performing an oxidation-reduction reaction on the water gas containing light oil so as to obtain a mixed gas containing carbon dioxide,  hydrogen,  water vapor and gaseous light oil;  (2) performing first cooling treatment on the mixed gas so as to obtain a first gas-liquid mixture of water,  the light oil,  carbon dioxide,  hydrogen,  water vapor and the gaseous light oil;  (3) performing first gas-liquid separation on the gas-liquid mixture so as to obtain a first liquid mixture containing the water and the gaseous light oil and a first gas containing carbon dioxide and hydrogen. The method used for treating the water gas containing light oil is capable of obviously reducing the consumption of superheated vapor,  and is less in energy consumption and low in cost.', p.application_date = '2014-01-09 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN103771338B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/16', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201410314989.3'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201410314989.3', p.title_cn = '一种微波液相等离子体醇类制氢方法', p.title_en = 'A microwave phase plasma alcohol method for hydrogen production', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种微波液相等离子体醇类制氢方法，属于非热放电醇类制氢领域。其特征在于具有如下步骤：将配制的体积分数为4-50％的醇类水溶液储存于原料储存罐中，之后注入到反应器中；将所述反应器中的空气排出，使所述反应器内的压强控制在1000-8000Pa；启动微波发生器，产生的微波经波导同轴电缆注入到位于所述反应器中液相放电电极，在所述醇类水溶液中产生等离子体，等离子体中的高能粒子对醇类分子进行碰撞分解，即可产生含有氢气的混合气体；待所述反应器及连接管路中残留的少量空气排出后进行所述混合气体的收集储存。本发明具有氢气制取速率快，放电装置设计小型化，可以随时随地简单方便的制取氢气的优点。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention discloses a microwave liquid phase plasma alcohol hydrogen preparation method and belongs to the hydrogen preparing field of athermal discharge alcohol hydrogen preparation. The method is characterized by comprising the following steps that a prepared alcohol aqueous solution with the volume fraction ranging from 4 percent to 50 percent is stored in a raw material storage tank and then injected into a reactor;  air in the reactor is discharged out,  and the intensity of pressure in the reactor is controlled to range from 1000 Pa to 8000 Pa;  a microwave generator is started,  generated microwaves are injected to a liquid phase discharging electrode in the reactor through a waveguide coaxial cable,  plasma is generated in the alcohol aqueous solution,  and high-energy particles in the plasma collide with alcohol molecules to decompose the alcohol molecules so that mixed gas with hydrogen can be generated;  after a small amount of air remaining in the reactor and a connecting pipe is discharged out,  the mixed gas is collected and stored. The method has the advantages that the hydrogen preparing speed is high,  a discharging device is designed to be small,  and hydrogen can be easily and conveniently prepared at any place and any time.', p.application_date = '2014-07-02 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN104030242B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/22', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201410220909.8'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201410220909.8', p.title_cn = '回收轻烯烃后炼厂干气中高收率高纯度提氢方法及装置', p.title_en = 'Recovery of light olefins in the dry gas latter refinery high purity in a high yield method and apparatus for extracting hydrogen from', p.abstract_cn = '回收轻烯烃后炼厂干气中高收率高纯度提氢方法，包括如下步骤：步骤1.一段膜分离；步骤2.一级变压吸附；步骤3.二级变压吸附；步骤4.二段膜分离。及回收轻烯烃后炼厂干气中高收率高纯度提氢装置，包括第一膜分离装置、第二膜分离装置、第一变压吸附塔、第二变压吸附塔和第一、第二加压装置。采用本发明所述的回收轻烯烃后炼厂干气中高收率高纯度提氢方法及装置，采用变压吸附、膜分离二者结合的技术，弥补了两种工艺各自存在的纯度和回收率低的缺陷，实现了对回收轻烯烃后的炼厂干气中氢气的高收率，高纯度的回收，回收氢气后的剩余气体可直接进入炼厂燃烧气管网燃烧。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a hydrogen purifying method for refinery dry gas after recovery of light olefins with high yield and high purity. The method comprises the following steps :  S1,  first section membrane separation;  S2,  primary pressure swing adsorption;  S3,  second pressure swing adsorption;  S4,  second section membrane separation. The invention further relates to a hydrogen purifying device for refinery dry gas after recovery of light olefins with high yield and high purity. The device comprises a first membrane separating device,  a second membrane separating device,  a first pressure swing adsorption tower,  a second pressure swing adsorption tower and first and second pressurizing devices. According to the hydrogen purifying method and device for refinery dry gas after recovery of light olefins with high yield and high purity provided by the invention,  by adopting a technology combining pressure swing adsorption and membrane separation,  the deficiencies on purity and low recovery rate of the two processes are remedied,  so that hydrogen in the refinery dry gas after recovery of light olefins is recovered with high yield and purity,  and the residual gas after hydrogen recovery can directly enter a burning gas pipe network to combust.', p.application_date = '2014-05-23 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN104030245B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/50', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201410626866.3'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201410626866.3', p.title_cn = '一种甲烷二氧化碳催化制氢装置及方法', p.title_en = 'A methane carbon dioxide catalytic hydrogen production apparatus and method', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种甲烷二氧化碳催化制氢装置及方法，属于化工技术领域。主要分为两步：1)甲烷、二氧化碳在合成气产生段重整生成合成气；2)水蒸汽与1)中合成气在水煤气转化及氢气分离段反应，再通过氢气膜分离组件分离出氢气。本发明原料来源广泛且价格低廉，对于节能减排有重要意义；且制备工艺简单，设备投资低，膜分离性能好，氢气产率高；适用于石油、化工及燃料电池领域。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention discloses a device and a method for catalytic hydrogen preparation from methane and carbon dioxide,  and belongs to the technical field of chemical industry. The method mainly comprises the following two steps :  (1) reforming methane and carbon dioxide in a synthetic gas generation section to generate a synthetic gas;  and (2) performing reaction on water vapor and the synthetic gas in the step (1) in a section for water gas conversion and hydrogen separation,  and separating hydrogen by virtue of a hydrogen membrane separation component. Raw materials of the method disclosed by the invention are wide in source and low in price,  which is of great significance for energy conservation and emission reduction;  moreover,  the preparation process is simple,  the equipment investment is low,  the membrane separation performance is good,  and the hydrogen yield is high;  and the device and the method are suitable for fields of petroleum,  chemical industry and fuel batteries.', p.application_date = '2014-11-10 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN104445066B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201410587219.6'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201410587219.6', p.title_cn = '一种金属胺类储氢材料及其制备方法', p.title_en = 'Metal amine hydrogen storage material and preparation method thereof', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开一种新型金属胺类储氢材料及其制备方法，该材料是胺类材料，包括有机胺、部分硼代有机胺或硼胺类等胺类化合物，与氢化锂、氢化镁或氢化钛等金属氢化物混合制备的化合物或混合物。制备方法是将胺类化合物与一定数量比的金属氢化物混合均匀，可以预先热处理进行一定程度反应，也可以加入一定量过渡金属化合物作为催化剂，即可得到该储氢材料。本发明制得的储氢材料制备方法简单，原料简单易得，价格低廉，储氢量大，放氢温度低，且结构性能可调易调，非常接近或者已经达到美国DOE的储氢材料标准，是储氢材料中非常有前途的一类，适合于未来大规模生产应用，具有广泛的市场前景。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention discloses a novel metal amine hydrogen storage material and a preparation method thereof. The material is an amine material,  and comprises a compound or mixture prepared through mixing organic amine,  partially boron-substituted organic amine or boron-amine or other amine compounds with lithium hydride,  magnesium hydride,  titanium hydride or other metal hydrides. The preparation method comprises the following steps :  uniformly mixing the amine compound with the metal hydride according to a certain quantity ratio,  preheating the obtained mixture to carry out a certain degree reaction,  and adding a certain amount of a transition metal compound as a catalyst to obtain the hydrogen storage material. The hydrogen storage material prepared in the invention has the advantages of simple preparation method,  simple and easily available raw materials,  low price,  large hydrogen storage capacity,  and adjustable and easily-adjusted structure and performances,  is very close to or has already reaches hydrogen storage material standards of American DOE,  is a very promising hydrogen storage material,  is suitable for large-scale production and application in the future,  and has wide market prospect.', p.application_date = '2014-10-28 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105621356A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/06', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201380080293.2'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201380080293.2', p.title_cn = '由水光催化氢生产和用于其的光解系统', p.title_en = 'Photocatalytic hydrogen production from water,  and photolysis system for the same', p.abstract_cn = '在一个实施方式中，用于在光化辐射影响下由含氢前体生成双原子氢的光催化剂包括：SrTi03和Ti02的半导体载体，其中，半导体载体中SrTi03和Ti02的摩尔比是至少0.01；和所述半导体载体上的金和钯合金。本文包括了光催化剂系统、制造双原子氢的方法和制造光催化剂的方法的实施方式。', p.abstract_en = 'In an embodiment,  a photocatalyst for the generation of diatomic hydrogen from a hydrogen containing precursor under the influence of actinic radiation comprises :  a semiconductor support of SrTi03 and Ti02,  wherein a molar ratio of SrTi03 and Ti02 in the semiconductor support is at least 0.01;  and a gold and palladium alloy on said semiconductor support. Included herein are embodiments of a photocatalyst system,  methods of making diatomic hydrogen,  and methods of making the photocatalyst.', p.application_date = '2013-10-17 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105636901A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201521012604.4'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201521012604.4', p.title_cn = '分解氨的装置', p.title_en = 'Device that decomposes ammonia', p.abstract_cn = '本实用新型涉及一种分解氨的装置，特点是包括分解室、多孔螺旋陶瓷气道构件及测温器；在所述分解室的下部设有进气口，所述进气口与外界氨气连通，在分解室上部设有排气口，所述排气口与外界连通；所述多孔螺旋陶瓷气道构件设在分解室内，从而在分解室内形成螺旋气道，多孔螺旋陶瓷气道构件的入气口与分解室的进气口相通，多孔螺旋陶瓷气道构件的出气口与分解室的排气口相通；在多孔螺旋陶瓷气道构件的表面二次烧结有镍触媒；所述测温器设在分解室内，测温器位于分解室的排气口旁。其优点为：增加了氨气在分解室内的气路运行行程，大幅提高氨气与镍触媒接触反应时间，提高氨制氢的效率。', p.abstract_en = 'The utility model relates to a device that decomposes ammonia,  characteristics are including decomposition chamber,  porous spiral pottery air flue component and thermoscope,  the lower part of decomposition chamber is equipped with the air inlet,  air inlet and external ammonia intercommunication is equipped with the gas vent on decomposition chamber upper portion,  gas vent and external intercommunication,  porous spiral pottery air flue component is established in the decomposition chamber to form the spiral air flue in the decomposition chamber,  the income gas port of porous spiral pottery air flue component communicates with each other with the air inlet of decomposition chamber,  and the gas outlet of porous spiral pottery air flue component communicates with each other with the gas vent of decomposition chamber,  surperficial double sintering at porous spiral pottery air flue component has the nickel catalyst,  the thermoscope is established in the decomposition chamber,  and the thermoscope is located by the gas vent of decomposition chamber. Its advantage does :  increase the gas circuit operation stroke of ammonia in the decomposition chamber,  improved ammonia and nickel catalyst contact reaction time by a wide margin,  improved the efficiency of ammonia hydrogen manufacturing.', p.application_date = '2015-12-09 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN205275200U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201620011785.7'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201620011785.7', p.title_cn = '一种烟气循环自热式甲醇制氢机', p.title_en = 'Flue gas recirculation self -heating methyl alcohol hydrogen manufacturing machine', p.abstract_cn = '本实用新型涉及一种制氢机，具体涉及一种烟气循环自热式甲醇制氢机，该系统中燃烧室(7)内安装有燃烧器(6)，所述烟气回流室(5)连接有空气预热器(10)、空气入口管(12)和空气出口管(13)，燃烧室(7)连接有燃料管(14)，空气经过空气入口管(12)在空气预热器(10)预热后从空气出口管(13)进入到燃烧室(7)和燃料混合燃烧，所述对流室(8)内安装有汽化器(2)和过热器(3)等特征。本实用新型的作用是：取掉了现有技术中体积庞大的导热油系统，减少了占地和投资，减少了运行成本费用；烟气循环自热系统与制氢机距离较近，输送热量损失小，能耗低。', p.abstract_en = 'The utility model relates to a hydrogen manufacturing machine,  concretely relates to flue gas recirculation self -heating methyl alcohol hydrogen manufacturing machine installs combustor (6) in combustion chamber in this system (7),  flue gas return passage (5) are connected with air heater (10),  air inlet tube (12) and air outlet tube (13),  and combustion chamber (7) are connected with fuel line (14),  and the air preheats the back through air inlet tube (12) at air heater (10) and enters into combustion chamber (7) and fuel co -combustion from air outlet tube (13),  install vaporizer (2) and over heater characteristics such as (3) in convection chamber (8). The utility model discloses an effect is :  get conduction oil system bulky among the prior art,  reduced and taken up an area of and the investment,  reduced the running cost expense,  the flue gas recirculation is nearer with hydrogen manufacturing machine distance from the thermal system,  carries calorific loss little,  and the energy consumption is low.', p.application_date = '2016-01-07 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN205275201U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/32', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201521068990.9'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201521068990.9', p.title_cn = '沼气发酵废液联合贫煤成浆共气化系统', p.title_en = 'Biogas fermentation waste liquid is united meager coal and is become thick liquid gasification system altogether', p.abstract_cn = '本实用新型公开了一种沼气发酵废液联合贫煤成浆共气化系统，包括具有沼气池的沼气池恒温发酵系统，沼气池具有生物能入口，沼气池的发酵废液出口连接废液磨浆机，磨浆机的液体出口接入气化系统中，气化系统具有贫煤磨煤机和气化炉，气化系统将磨浆机的液体与贫煤混合后送入气化炉，沼气池和气化炉的气体出口均连接合成器反应器，合成反应器连接储气罐和燃气轮机组，本系统的原料供应为生物质能源和燃烧效率不高的贫煤资源，将两者结合通过沼气发酵技术、气化技术、合成气技术生产清洁的合成气资源。', p.abstract_en = 'The utility model discloses a biogas fermentation waste liquid is united meager coal and is become thick liquid gasification system altogether,  including having the methane -generating pit constant temperature fermentation system of methane -generating pit,  the methane -generating pit has the biological energy source entry,  the fermented waste liquid exit linkage waste liquid fiberizer of methane -generating pit,  the liquid outlet of fiberizer inserts among the gasification system,  gasification system has meager coal coal pulverizer and gasifier,  after mixing the liquid of fiberizer and meager coal,  gasification system sends into the gasifier,  the synthesizer reactor is all connected to the gas outlet of methane -generating pit and gasifier,  synthesis reactor connects gas holder and gas turbine group,  the raw material supply of this system is biomass energy source and the not high meager coal resource of combustion efficiency,  combine the technique through biogas fermentation with both,  the gasification technique,  the clear synthetic gas resource of synthetic gas technique production.', p.application_date = '2015-12-19 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN205275202U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/34', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'DE502013005510'}) SET p.application_no = 'DE502013005510', p.title_cn = '一种提高重质原油的可移植性的方法', p.title_en = 'METHOD FOR IMPROVING THE TRANSPORTABILITY OF HEAVY CRUDE OIL', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种改善重质原油的可移植性的方法。从已知的现有技术的缺点，要设计出的方法，其中降粘剂，其能够廉价地制造的可以较小的力加到重质原油，不会导致在后续的精制提纯工艺为常规汽油的不利影响。这是这样实现的 : 一种量为10至40wt。%的原油从分支运输石油重质原油的区域中原位沉积并转换为水的含烃主要是C4至C12链长的混合物，所述混合物不含有含氧烃化合物，通过中间步骤，生产合成气，甲醇合成，和生产二甲醚/甲醇/水混合物。所述烃混合物加入到重质原油的脱气过程后，和轻质原油得到的重质原油通过管线输送到炼油厂。在随后的轻质原油精炼过程为常规汽油，含烯烃的烃混合物在水中所含的烃的一部分成为所生成的汽油量。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a method for improving the transportability of heavy crude oil. Proceeding from the disadvantages of the known prior art,  a method is to be devised with which a viscosity-reducing agent is provided that can be produced inexpensively,  can be added to the heavy crude oil with little effort,  and does not lead to disadvantageous effects during the subsequent refining process into conventional gasoline. This is achieved in that a quantity of 10 to 40 wt.% of crude oil is branched off from the transported heavy crude oil in the region of a petroleum deposit and converted in situ into a water-containing hydrocarbon mixture with a chain length of predominantly C4 to C12,  said mixture not containing oxygen-containing hydrocarbon compounds,  via intermediate steps,  a syngas production,  a methanol synthesis,  and a production of a dimethyl ether/methanol/water mixture. The hydrocarbon mixture is added to the heavy crude oil after a degassing process,  and a light crude oil obtained from the heavy crude oil is transported to a refinery via lines. During the subsequent refining process of the light crude oil into conventional gasoline,  the hydrocarbons contained in the water-containing hydrocarbon mixture become a part of the produced gasoline quantity.', p.application_date = '2013-08-22 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'DE502013005510T2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/34', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'EP13728203'}) SET p.application_no = 'EP13728203', p.title_cn = '用于生产乙炔和合成气的方法', p.title_en = 'METHOD FOR PRODUCING ACETYLENE AND SYNTHESIS GAS', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种方法用于生产乙炔和合成气的氧的部分氧化烃的方法。在所述方法中，一种第一输入流含有一种或多种烃和第二输入含氧流被分开地预热，从彼此，混合在比第二的质量流率的输入流的质量流率，第一输入对应的流程氧数λ小于或等于0.31，和经过燃烧器块至燃烧室。烃部分氧化燃烧室中。由此获得的裂化气体，它被急冷至80至90摄氏度下游的燃烧室通过将水性淬火介质。工艺水流量iliq和产物气体流获得Ig。该产物气体流冷却在冷却柱通过与冷却水直接换热的装置为了获得过程用水流的iiliq作为底流，产品气流量iig作为顶流，和侧流，电过滤器中烟灰的耗尽。一种工艺水流量iiiliq中出现的电滤波器。工艺水流入iliq，iiliq，和iiiliq合并和通过灰凹槽的表面进行粒子分离器以获得合并的方法水流ivliq。所述方法的特征在于，该合并过程中水流ivliq进行清洗的部分单级闪蒸罐中蒸发，该合并过程用水流ivliq的水分蒸发至一分数为0.01重量%至10重量%，在相对于其总重量，为了得到清洗后的工艺水流量vliq，其再循环到方法。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a method for producing acetylene and synthesis gas by partially oxidizing hydrocarbons by means of oxygen. In said method,  a first input flow containing one or more hydrocarbons and a second input flow containing oxygen are preheated separately from each other,  mixed at a ratio of the mass flow rate of the second input flow to the mass flow rate of the first input flow corresponding to an oxygen number lambda less than or equal to 0.31,  and fed via a burner block to a combustion chamber. The hydrocarbons are partially oxidized in the combustion chamber. A cracked gas is thereby obtained,  which is quenched to 80 to 90 degrees Celsius downstream of the combustion chamber by injecting an aqueous quenching medium. A process water flow Iliq and a product gas flow Ig are obtained. The product gas flow is cooled down in a cooling column by means of direct heat exchange with cooling water in order to obtain a process water flow IIliq as a bottom flow,  a product gas flow IIg as a top flow,  and a side flow,  which is depleted of soot in an electric filter. A process water flow IIIliq arises in the electric filter. The process water flows Iliq,  IIliq,  and IIIliq are merged and conducted via soot grooves having surface particle separators in order to obtain a merged process water flow IVliq. The method is characterized in that the merged process water flow IVliq is subjected to cleaning by means of partial evaporation in a single-stage flash tank,  the merged process water flow IVliq being evaporated to a fraction of 0.01 wt% to 10 wt%,  in relation to the total weight thereof,  in order to obtain a cleaned process water flow Vliq,  which is recycled into the method.', p.application_date = '2013-06-13 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'EP2861527B1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/36', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2012137504'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2012137504', p.title_cn = '氢气发生装置', p.title_en = 'The hydrogen generating device', p.abstract_cn = '要解决的问题 : 吸附脱硫装置与一种简单的结构用于抑制冷凝水的回流至该氢的产生装置。溶液 : 以降低浓度的硫化合物的吸附脱硫剂2和，通过使用所述富氢气体，以减少硫化合物的浓度hydrogenetion脱硫剂10和，由重整原料，以产生一种富氢气体和一种重整反应器11，原料供应源和连接该抽吸脱硫剂2和1原料路径1，和吸附脱硫剂2hydrogenetion脱硫剂10和连接该材料路径2，3，重整反应器11从一种富氢气体和排出气体通道4，第二的排气气体路径分支部15是支链从本发明的一个部分富氢气体，原料的第一方式路径2，3是合并与所述合并部分6，所述富氢气体hydrogenetion脱硫剂10和一个循环路径7，设置在第一路线原料1，1，和所述电源-关阀8关闭时，是提供，第二路2原料3，和一种吸附脱硫剂2之间的合并部分6，合并部分6侧为低; 使该抽吸脱硫剂2为高，一水平差异是提供具有一通道9。选自拉拔 : 图。1。', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To provide a hydrogen generating apparatus of a simple structure that suppresses a condensate backflow to an adsorption desulfurizer. SOLUTION :  A hydrogen generating apparatus includes :  an adsorption desulfurizer 2 to reduce the concentration of a sulfur compound;  a hydrogenation desulfurizer 10 to reduce the concentration of a sulfur compound using a hydrogen-rich gas;  a reforming reactor 11 to generate the hydrogen-rich gas by reforming a raw material;  a first raw-material passage 1 to connect a raw material source and the adsorption desulfurizer 2;  a second raw-material passage 3 to connect the adsorption desulfurizer 2 and the hydrogenation desulfurizer 10;  an exhaust gas passage 4 to discharge the hydrogen-rich gas from the reforming reactor 11;  a recycle passage 7 to take out a part of the hydrogen-rich gas from a first branch part 5 on the exhaust gas passage,  merging it into a merging part 6 on the second raw-material passage 3 to supply the hydrogen-rich gas to the hydrogen desulfurizer 10;  and an on-off valve 8 that is installed on the first raw-material passage 1 and closed during power source cutoff. The second raw-material passage 3 includes a passage 9 that is installed between the merging part 6 and the adsorption desulfurizer 2 and has difference of elevation so that the merging part 6 side is low and the adsorption desulfurizer 2 is high. COPYRIGHT :  (C)2014, JPO&INPIT', p.application_date = '2012-06-19 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP5927498B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2013540653'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2013540653', p.title_cn = '脱硫装置hydrogenetion，氢气发生器和燃料电池系统', p.title_en = 'The desulfurization device hydrogenetion,  hydrogen generator and fuel cell system', p.abstract_cn = '一种加氢脱硫装置(2)包括加氢脱硫器(3)，被配置为从原料除去硫成分和加热器(4)配置成加氢脱硫器(3). 其中，所述加氢脱硫器(3)包括多个块(31)划分而形成在周向中心呈环状配置的加热器(4)的外周. 其中，所述加氢脱硫器(3)被配置为使得所述原料已经通过在每个所述块(31)移动到其相邻块(31)。. 并且其中所述加氢脱硫剂被构造成使得相邻块(31)彼此连通的原料物流(31)在相反方向上相邻块中.', p.abstract_en = 'A hydrodesulfurization device (2) comprises a hydro-desulfurizer (3) configured to remove a sulfur component from a raw material and a heater (4) configured to heat the hydro-desulfurizer (3);  wherein the hydro-desulfurizer (3) includes a plurality of blocks (31) formed by division in a circumferential direction and disposed annularly around an outer periphery of the heater (4);  wherein the hydro-desulfurizer (3) is configured such that the raw material having passed through inside of each of the blocks (31) moves to its adjacent block (31);  and wherein the hydro-desulfurizer is configured such that adjacent blocks (31) are communicated with each other and the raw material flows in the adjacent blocks (31) in opposite directions.', p.application_date = '2012-10-23 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP5927572B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/36', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'TW105201205'}) SET p.application_no = 'TW105201205', p.title_cn = '碳纤维缠绕铝合金氢气瓶', p.title_en = 'Hydrogen bottle made from aluminum alloy winded by carbon fiber', p.abstract_cn = '本创作系提供一种碳纤维缠绕铝合金氢气瓶，其包含瓶体以及碳纤维缠绕层瓶体系由7075系列铝合金制成，例如7075-T6；碳纤维缠绕层形成於瓶体上藉此，本创作突破先前技术瓶颈，采用7075系列铝合金瓶进行碳纤维缠绕所制成的碳纤维缠绕铝合金氢气瓶具有重量较轻之优势此外，本创作适用於极低温度下，但於室温下时可提升其抗拉强度；降伏点可达到约略9.3kgf；焊道及基底金属之平均硬度经填料焊接及热处理後分别增加43%及22%，而经不填料焊接及热处理後则分别增加39%及19%；液压测试可达到60kgf/cm; 2，其为没有任何的碳纤维缠绕的铝合金瓶的3倍', p.abstract_en = 'This creation is to offer a kind of carbon fiber winding aluminum alloy hydrogen gas bottle,  which comprises a bottle body and the carbon fiber winding layer. The bottle body is composed of a 7075 aluminum alloy series,  such as 7075-T6;  carbon fiber winding layer formed on the bottle body. Therefore,  the bottleneck in the prior art,  adopts the 7075 aluminum alloy series of bottle made of carbon fiber winding the carbon fiber winding aluminum alloy hydrogen gas bottle has the advantage of light weight. Furthermore,  suitable for the creation of the very low temperature,  but when at room temperature and the tensile strength can be improved;  vanquish point can reach approximately 9.3kgf;  bead and the average hardness of the base metal by the filler welding and after the heat treatment increased 43% and 22%,  and the non-filler welding and after the heat treatment is increased,  respectively,  39% and 19% ;  hydraulic test can reach 60kgf/cm 2,  without any carbon fiber winding the aluminum alloy of the bottle of 3 times.', p.application_date = '2016-01-27 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'TWM522940U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'BR112013001833'}) SET p.application_no = 'BR112013001833', p.title_cn = '用于部分氧化的燃烧器与方法液conbustívelconbustíVEL I竞争碳', p.title_en = 'BURNER AND PROCESS FOR THE PARTIAL OXIDATION OF LIQUID conbustívelCONBUSTÍVEL I CONTEND CARBON', p.abstract_cn = '一种用于部分氧化液体的燃烧器， 含有蒸汽和含氧气体的含碳燃料A以及使用该燃烧器的方法， 其中燃烧器的出口孔口朝向燃烧室的部分全部或部分设有涂层或扩散层，以防止热负荷和/或腐蚀。', p.abstract_en = 'A burner for the partial oxidation of liquid,  carbonaceous fuel with steam and an oxygen-containing gas a well as the process in which this burner is used,  wherein the parts of the outlet orifice of the burner directed towards the combustion chamber are wholly or partly provided with a coating or with a diffusion layer for protection against thermal load and/or corrosion.', p.application_date = '2011-03-24 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'BRPI1301833A2', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/36', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'GC201221704'}) SET p.application_no = 'GC201221704', p.title_cn = '生产合成气的方法', p.title_en = 'PROCESS FOR PRODUCING SYNTHESIS GAS', p.abstract_cn = '生产合成气(3)的方法，其中将甲烷和二氧化碳(2)引入反应室(R)中，并在高温下在固体(W)存在下反应生成氢气和一氧化碳。甲烷和二氧化碳被引导通过含碳颗粒(W)并在高温区(H)中反应。', p.abstract_en = 'Process for producing synthesis gas (3),  where methane and carbon dioxide (2) are introduced into a reaction chamber (R) and are reacted in the presence of a solid (W) at elevated temperatures to give hydrogen and carbon monoxide. Methane and carbon dioxide are guided through carbon-containing granules (W) and are reacted in a high-temperature zone (H).', p.application_date = '2012-07-07 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'GC0004156A', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'GCP20065945'}) SET p.application_no = 'GCP20065945', p.title_cn = '制备一氧化碳和氢气的混合物的方法', p.title_en = 'PROCESS TO PREPARE A MIXTURE OF CARBON MONOXIDE AND HYDROGEN', p.abstract_cn = '由包含甲烷、乙烷和任选的较高碳数烃(3)的烃的气态混合物制备氢气和一氧化碳的混合物的方法，通过进行以下步骤：(a)在合适的重整催化剂存在下预重整(4)烃混合物，以将乙烷和任选的较高碳数烃转化为甲烷、二氧化碳和氢气，(b)将步骤(a)中获得的气态混合物加热(6)至大于650℃的温度，(c)通过使步骤(b)的加热混合物与氧源(9)在反应器燃烧器中接触进行部分氧化(11)，产生反应器流出物(12)。', p.abstract_en = 'Process to prepare a mixture of hydrogen and carbon monoxide from a gaseous mixture of hydrocarbons comprising methane,  ethane and optional higher carbon number hydrocarbons (3) by performing the following steps :  (a) pre-reforming (4) the hydrocarbon mixture in the presence of a suitable reforming catalyst to convert ethane,  and the optional higher carbon number hydrocarbons to methane,  carbon dioxide and hydrogen,  (b) heating (6) the gaseous mixture obtained in step (a) to a temperature greater than 650 °C,  (c) performing a partial oxidation (11) by contacting the heated mixture of step (b) with a source of oxygen (9) in a reactor burner yielding a reactor effluent (12).', p.application_date = '2006-03-13 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'GC0004183A', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US13094574'}) SET p.application_no = 'US13094574', p.title_cn = '将浓缩的VOC燃料流转化为重整物并将重整物供给能量转换装置', p.title_en = 'Reforming concentrated VOC fuel stream into reformate and supplying reformate to energy conversion device', p.abstract_cn = '一种用于从烃气源生产重整燃料的装置和方法。 本发明能够将稀烃气体转化为更易消耗的重整产物燃料。 使用浓缩器将具有低浓度烃的气体浓缩成气态或液态浓缩的VOC燃料。 然后使用重整器将浓缩的VOC燃料转化为重整产物。 重整产物更容易被能量转换装置消耗，所述能量转换装置例如内燃机、燃料电池、斯特林发动机或将化学能转换成动能或电能的类似装置。 该重整器使通常不适合在能量转换装置中使用的复合烃燃料能够转化成重整产物。 重整产物可直接供应到能量转换装置中。', p.abstract_en = 'A device and method for producing a reformate fuel from a hydrocarbon gas source. The invention enables the conversion of a dilute hydrocarbon gas into a more easily consumable reformate fuel. Gases having low concentrations of hydrocarbons are concentrated using a concentrator into a gaseous or liquid concentrated VOC fuel. The concentrated VOC fuel is then converted into a reformate using a reformer. The reformate is more easily consumed by an energy conversion device such as a combustion engine,  fuel cell,  sterling engine or similar device that converts chemical energy into kinetic or electrical energy. The reformer enables complex hydrocarbon fuels that are not normally suitable for use in an energy conversion device to be converted into a reformate. The reformate may be directly supplied into the energy conversion device.', p.application_date = '2011-04-26 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9352266B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/36', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 3, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14661679'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14661679', p.title_cn = '使用具有二次重整的基于氧传输膜的重整系统生产合成气的方法和系统', p.title_en = 'Method and system for producing a synthesis gas using an oxygen transport membrane based reforming system with secondary reforming', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种用于在基于氧传输膜的重整系统中生产合成气的方法和系统，所述方法和系统执行一次重整工艺、二次重整工艺。', p.abstract_en = 'A method and system for producing a synthesis gas in an oxygen transport membrane based reforming system is disclosed that carries out a primary reforming process,  a secondary reforming process.', p.application_date = '2015-03-18 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9352296B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/26', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14390307'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14390307', p.title_cn = '降低含碳材料气化中焦油含量的方法和装置', p.title_en = 'Method and apparatus for reduction of tar in gasification of carbonaceous materials', p.abstract_cn = '一种用于从含碳材料气化生产基本上不含焦油的产物气体的方法和组件。 所述组件优选地包括第一级气化器和第二级气化器，所述第一级气化器产生焦炭灰和含焦油的产物气体，所述第二级气化器具有焦炭灰加热区、至少一个旋风分离器和至少一个立管，以允许选择性地将焦炭灰输送到焦炭灰加热区。 优选利用焦炭灰氧化的焦炭灰加热区，这导致转化焦油所需的热量、产物气体的额外产率和氧化的活性炭表面，以促进提升管中的焦油转化，从而降低实现所需焦油转化所需的温度。 可选地，外部热量被供应到加热区。', p.abstract_en = 'A method and assembly for producing substantially tar free product gas from gasification of carbonaceous material. The assembly preferably includes a first stage gasifier to produce char-ash and tar laden product gas and a second stage gasifier which has a char-ash heating zone,  at least one cyclone,  and at least one standpipe for the purpose of allowing selective delivery of char-ash to the char-ash heating zone. A char-ash heating zone that utilizes oxidation of char-ash is preferred and this results in the heat required to convert tar,  additional yield of product gas,  and an oxidized,  activated carbon surface to facilitate tar conversion in the riser,  thereby reducing the temperature required to achieve the desired tar conversion. Alternatively,  external heat is supplied to the heating zone.', p.application_date = '2012-04-03 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9353321B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'HUE09716244'}) SET p.application_no = 'HUE09716244', p.title_cn = '用于分离异物的方法和装置通过变压吸附的气体，减少有用气体', p.title_en = 'METHOD AND DEVICE FOR THE SEPARATION OF FOREIGN GASES FROM A REDUCING USEFUL GAS BY PRESSURE SWING ADSORPTION', p.abstract_cn = '本发明描述了一种用于净化合成气通过变压吸附单元的解吸，真空产生的所谓的喷射器，其产生的蒸汽驱动的热交换器，利用热烟气管道中或可用于油气管道中产生蒸汽。所述变压吸附单元吸附有利，在环状圈的过大压力下，降压解吸和真空解吸，解吸出的气体通过冷却器内冷却，使顶含有可冷凝蒸汽排出，也有利地返回到合成气生产的原料气。杂质气体解吸的变压吸附单元，至少部分地包含未消耗的燃料气体，再循环到燃料气体。在一个有利的实施例中，来自喷射器的真空被存储在中间罐和施加到所述变压吸附单元一种真空解吸循环。还公开了用于运行该方法的装置。', p.abstract_en = 'A process is described for purifying synthesis gas by means of a pressure swing adsorption unit which is desorbed by a vacuum produced by a so-called ejector,  which is driven by steam generated by a heat exchanger which uses the heat in the flue gas duct or in the useful-gas duct for the generation of steam. The pressure swing adsorption unit is operated advantageously in cyclic turns of adsorption under excess pressure,  depressurization desorption and vacuum desorption and the gas desorbed by the ejector being cooled in a cooler so that the contained steam can be condensed and discharged or is advantageously returned to the feed gas for the synthesis gas production. The foreign gas desorbed by the pressure swing adsorption unit,  which contains at least partly not yet consumed fuel gas,  is recycled to the fuel gas. In an advantageous embodiment,  the vacuum from the ejector is stored in an intermediate tank and applied to the pressure swing adsorption unit according to the vacuum desorption cycle. Also disclosed is a device for running this process.', p.application_date = '2009-02-17 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'HUE026169T2', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/34', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'IDW00201302895'}) SET p.application_no = 'IDW00201302895', p.title_cn = '闭式循环能量输运系统', p.title_en = 'Closed cycle energy transport system', p.abstract_cn = '本发明关于能源系统(Sanner循环)，其包括设置在第一地理位置的第一能量转换精炼厂和设置在第二地理位置的第二能量转换精炼厂，其中，第一能量转换精炼厂被配置为使用从非化石能源获得的能量从至少一种耗能化合物中生产携带能量的至少一种化合物，其中第二能量转换炼油厂被配置为通过反应至少一个能量转换化合物来生产电力、电力和/或热能，以形成至少一个能量转换化合物，其中该能量系统还包括输送系统，该输送系统被配置为将在第一能量转换炼油厂中产生的至少一个能量转换化合物输送到第二能量转换炼油厂中产生的至少一个能量转换化合物输送到第一能量转换炼油厂中。本发明的特征在于，所述能量系统通过与第一和第二能量转换炼油厂上产生的载能和耗能化合物相关而形成闭环，其中在第一炼油厂上产生的至少一个载能化合物在闭环上输送到第二炼油厂上形成反应物，在第二炼油厂上产生的至少一个耗能化合物在闭环上输送到第一炼油厂上形成反应物。能量转换精炼厂也可以通过运载能量和消耗能量的化合物的运输组织到电网中，同时形成桑纳电网循环。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to an energy system (Sanner cycle),  It includes a first energy conversion refinery disposed at a first geographic location and a second energy conversion refinery disposed at a second geographic location,  Wherein the first energy conversion refinery is configured to produce the energy-carrying at least one compound from the at least one energy-consuming compound using energy obtained from a non-fossil energy source,  Wherein the second energy conversion refinery is configured to produce electricity,  electricity and/or thermal energy,  by reacting at least one energy conversion compound,  To form at least one energy conversion compound,  Wherein the energy system further comprises a delivery system configured to deliver the at least one energy-converting compound produced in the first energy-converting refinery to the at least one energy-converting compound produced in the second energy-converting refinery to the first energy-converting refinery. The invention is characterized in that,  The energy system forms a closed loop by correlating energy-carrying and energy-consuming compounds produced on the first and second energy conversion refineries,  At least one energy-carrying compound produced at the first refinery is conveyed over the closed loop to the second refinery to form a reactant,  and at least one energy-consuming compound produced at the second refinery is conveyed over the closed loop to the first refinery to form a reactant. Energy conversion refineries can also be organized into the grid by transport of energy and energy consuming compounds,  while forming a Sunner grid cycle.', p.application_date = '2013-06-26 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'IDP000041159B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2013552655'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2013552655', p.title_cn = '燃料处理装置', p.title_en = 'Fuel treatment device', p.abstract_cn = '燃料小的温度，外部环境的影响。 具体地，燃烧段； 从原料气体，硫组分的脱硫段； 脱硫和重整原料气体的水加热，蒸发流路，得到混合气体； 混合气体，主要有氢和含氢气体并产生重整部； 一种含氢气体温度降低一氧化碳的浓度转换部分； 一种降低浓度的含一氧化碳和氢气的气体来进一步降低一氧化碳的浓度在低温度 放热催化剂的燃料处理器，其具有改性部分。 蒸发流路， 和重整段和脱硫段相互连通， 和穿过脱硫的上部设置这种方式中， 温度更改段， 所述低温重整段和连通部和， 在脱硫的上部，设置沿所述蒸发路径。', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention is provided with :  a combustion part;  a desulfurization part in which the sulfur component is removed from a feed gas;  an evaporation channel in which the feed gas and reforming water are heated to obtain a mixed gas;  a reforming part in which a hydrogenous gas is yielded from the mixed gas;  a high-temperature modification part in which the carbon monoxide concentration in the hydrogenous gas is lowered;  and a low-temperature modification part which is equipped with an exothermic-type catalyst whereby the carbon monoxide concentration in the hydrogenous gas is further lowered. The evaporation channel has been disposed so that the desulfurization part and the reforming part communicate with each other and that the channel passes over the desulfurization part. The high-temperature modification part makes the reforming part communicate with the low-temperature modification part and has been disposed over the desulfurization part along the evaporation channel.', p.application_date = '2013-06-24 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JPWO2014002470A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2013554135'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2013554135', p.title_cn = '燃料处理装置', p.title_en = 'Fuel treatment device', p.abstract_cn = '本发明， 在降低尺寸的燃料处理器， 氢气和氢气的重整气体混合物以冷却混合气体通过。 本发明，用于汽化重整的蒸发部； 同样， 所述待处理气体通过催化剂， 和蒸发段通过设置分隔板，相邻的第一部分1； 气体供给至第一蒸发器从部件到部件1和散热器和设置在 附近的气体流路。 所述气体流路， 和第一蒸发部和改性部(1)具有相对置的部分的一部分气体通 具有中间流道， 和第一中间通道的下游端1和连接到上游端改性 部分。', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention is provided with :  an evaporation unit which evaporates water for reforming;  a first shift-conversion unit which is disposed adjacent to the evaporation unit via a partition,  and in which a gas to be processed passes through a catalyst;  and a gas passage which feeds the gas from a reforming unit to the first shift-conversion unit,  and which is disposed in the vicinity of the evaporation unit such that heat can be released to the evaporation unit. The gas passage has an intermediate passage which is provided to a location where the first shift-conversion unit and the evaporation unit face each other,  and through which the gas passes. A downstream end of the intermediate passage is connected to an upstream end of the first shift-conversion unit.', p.application_date = '2013-06-24 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JPWO2014002471A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2013546120'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2013546120', p.title_cn = '燃料处理装置', p.title_en = 'Fuel treatment device', p.abstract_cn = '本发明， 所述外部环境温度的影响小，燃料可预热后的原料气体。 燃烧段和具有热源， 和除去硫组分从原料气脱硫单元， 原料气脱硫和基本上由氢从含氢气体并产生重整部， 所述含氢气体中的杂质浓度降低的燃料处理器提供热量。 低温部并设置有催化剂。 脱硫单元和重整部， 燃烧段形成为包围， 向外从燃烧段， 重整段，在脱硫部分的顺序同心设置。 燃烧段由原料气预热的热量， 通过保温材料设置在燃烧段的底部， 脱硫和连通流道，再预热。', p.abstract_en = 'Provided is a fuel processing device including :  a combustion unit equipped with a heat source;  a desulfurization unit for extracting a sulfur component from the source gas;  a reforming unit for generating,  from the desulfurized source gas,  a hydrogen-containing gas having hydrogen as a main component thereof;  and a low-temperature conversion unit equipped with an exothermic catalyst for reducing the impurity concentration in the hydrogen-containing gas. The reforming unit and the desulfurization unit are configured so as to surround the combustion unit,  and are disposed concentrically in the given order facing outwards from the combustion unit. The present invention further includes a preheating passage which is connected to the desulfurization unit,  and which is provided to a bottom part of the combustion unit via a heat insulation material,  such that the source gas is preheated by heat from the combustion unit.', p.application_date = '2013-06-24 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JPWO2014002472A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'FR12002495'}) SET p.application_no = 'FR12002495', p.title_cn = '用于生产纯氢的方法从含烃原料的变性包括具有改进的温度控制脱硫的步骤所述PSA的上游', p.title_en = 'METHOD FOR PRODUCTION OF PURE HYDROGEN FROM A HYDROCARBONACEOUS FEEDSTOCK DENATURED INCLUDING A STEP OF DESULFURIZATION WITH IMPROVED TEMPERATURE CONTROL UPSTREAM OF THE PSA', p.abstract_cn = '生产纯氢的，包括将合成气通过上游压的变压吸附(PSA)净化单元(1008)到一个热交换器(1006)，用于完整的冷凝水排出的气体中含有从自热重整反应器(ATR)，其中换热器包括第一部，其进行冷却的合成气使用冷流体的脱硫负荷，和第二部分继续冷却至完全冷凝的合成气中含有的水到15-40[℃]使用冷却水冷却的冷却塔。', p.abstract_en = 'Producing pure hydrogen comprises passing a synthesis gas through an upstream of a presses swing adsorption (PSA) purification unit (1008) into an exchanger (1006) for complete condensation of the water contained in the gas discharged from an autothermal reforming reactor (ATR),  where the exchanger comprises a first portion which performs cooling of the synthesis gas using a cold fluid to the desulfurized load,  and a second portion that continues cooling to total condensation of the water contained in the synthesis gas to 15-40[deg] C using cooling water cooled by a cooling tower.', p.application_date = '2012-09-20 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'FR2995601B1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/56', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'IN8819DELNP2015'}) SET p.application_no = 'IN8819DELNP2015', p.title_cn = '高热值燃气制造工艺', p.title_en = 'HIGH CALORIE GAS MANUFACTURING PROCESS', p.abstract_cn = '本发明的目的是提供一种高热值燃气的制造方法，通过高热量气体可通过热解制造的甘油。本发明公开了一种高热值燃气的制造方法，该方法包括 : 用铁矿石进行甘油裂解；从而获得具有高热值燃气的低热值000大卡/米3以上。', p.abstract_en = 'The purpose of the present invention is to provide a high calorie gas manufacturing process by which a high calorie gas can be manufactured through pyrolysis of glycerol. The present invention is a high calorie gas manufacturing process which comprises :  subjecting glycerol to pyrolysis using iron ore;  and thus obtaining a high calorie gas having a net calorific value of 3 000kcal/m or more.', p.application_date = '2015-09-25 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'IN8819DELNP2015A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'IN959CHENP2013'}) SET p.application_no = 'IN959CHENP2013', p.title_cn = '合成气生产，通过使用膜技术', p.title_en = 'SYNGAS PRODUCTION THROUGH THE USE OF MEMBRANE TECHNOLOGIES', p.abstract_cn = '污染的天然气流(11)可以以产生合成气与二氧化碳(16)。一个有用的来源(1)的含CO2烟道气和天然气流(11)组合传送复合接近相等的甲烷与CO2的混合物的等离子体反应器(15)等将生成合成气。当与费-托合成反应器(40)的整个方法提供了用于生产合成液态烃的方法。', p.abstract_en = 'Streams (11) of natural gas contaminated with carbon dioxide can be to create Syngas (16). An available source (1) of flue gas and a C02 laden natural gas stream (11) are combined to deliver a composite near equal mixture of methane and C02 to a plasma reactor (15) or the like that will generate Syngas. When coupled with a Fischer Tropsch reactor (40) the overall process provides a process for producing synthetic liquid hydrocarbons.', p.application_date = '2013-02-06 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'IN959CHENP2013A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/34', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'NZ625675'}) SET p.application_no = 'NZ625675', p.title_cn = '产生合成气的方法和系统', p.title_en = 'Process and system for generating synthesis gas', p.abstract_cn = '一种用于产生合成气的方法和装置描述了使用烃类和水。在进一步的实施例的方法和装置，合成气具有任何所需的CO/氢比例和/或合成的官能化和/或非官能化烃产生。与该方法，含烃流体可以具有可变转换成合成气的氢含量而不产生显著量的CO2。进一步，氢和不同形式的碳可以获得作为副产物。', p.abstract_en = 'A method and an apparatus for generating synthesis gas using hydrocarbons and water are described. In further embodiments of the method and the apparatus,  synthesis gases having any desired CO/hydrogen ratio and/or synthetic functionalised and/or non-functionalised hydrocarbons are generated. With this method,  a hydrocarbon containing fluid may be transformed into a synthesis gas having variable hydrogen content without generating significant amounts of CO2. Further,  hydrogen and different forms of carbon may be obtained as by-products.', p.application_date = '2012-12-20 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'NZ625675A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/24', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'RU2014138877'}) SET p.application_no = 'RU2014138877', p.title_cn = '生产气体的装置和方法', p.title_en = 'DEVICE AND METHOD OF PRODUCING GAS', p.abstract_cn = '领域 : 化学物质 : 本发明涉及一种化工工程，具体地，以电解水，提供了一种生产气体流的空气流的方法在离子表面，其生产中使用的电力。生产含氨气体流的方法，氢烃，其中潮湿的空气流与面层接触的固体催化剂和离子形成的水表面金属电极的作用下，激活电流；在通过半透性屏障，其中所述流与含钛铁矿在障壁内表面的相互作用，在温度范围从12到80°C和环境压力或真空中得到的气体流量。生产装置气体流包括圆柱形管(1)，水平放置，与两个相对孔(2)和(3)的直径小，阳极导线(4)连接到供电电源的正极通过连接线；阴极(5)，由绕组围绕阳极连接到电源的负极，阳极和阴极浸入电解液，位于下部管和覆盖电极；多孔陶瓷阻挡层(6)附近的孔(2)。效果 : 本发明能够获得氢气直接在现场，提高了工艺，降低了有害效果在environment.16Cl，1的DWG，10EX', p.abstract_en = 'FIELD :  chemistry. SUBSTANCE :  invention relates to chemical engineering,  particularly,  to electrolysis of water,  and provides a method of producing gas flow by air flow on ionic surface,  which is used in production of electric power. Method of producing gas flow containing ammonia,  hydrogen and hydrocarbon,  where humid air flow is brought into contact with surface layer of a solid catalyst and ion water surface formed under effect of metal electrodes,  activated by electric current;  after passing through semipermeable barrier,  where said flow interacts with ilmenite contained on surface of barrier,  at temperature in range from 12 to 80 °C and ambient pressure or in vacuum to obtain gas flow. Device for producing gas flow comprises cylindrical tube (1),  horizontally located,  with two opposite holes (2) and (3) of smaller diameter;  anode of wire (4) connected to positive pole of power supply source by means of connecting wires;  cathode (5) consisting of winding around anode connected to negative pole of power supply,  anode and cathode are submerged into electrolyte,  located in lower part of tube and covering electrodes;  and porous ceramic barrier (6) near hole (2). EFFECT :  invention enables to obtain hydrogen gas directly on site,  and improves technology and reduces harmful effects on environment. 16 cl,  1 dwg,  10 ex', p.application_date = '2012-04-05 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'RU2585015C1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2015022832'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2015022832', p.title_cn = '氢生成装置及燃料电池系统和操作其的方法', p.title_en = 'HYDROGEN GENERATOR AND METHOD FOR OPERATING THE SAME,  AND FUEL CELL SYSTEM', p.abstract_cn = '要解决的问题 : 自启动，即使不存在停电用于操作氢气发生装置。方法 :  氢产生装置100，原料含有烃组分进行改性，以产生含氢气体和重整装置1，和至少一个所述原料含氢气体的重整器1的燃烧热和燃烧器4，重整装置1，用于供应原料和原料供给装置(2)，外部故障预测基于所述信息从故障发生时，停电时的启动时间在预定定时启动过程开始之前，控制器30，设置，启动之前故障产生的氢气产生装置100，即可加工完成，即使没有提供自启动电源，氢气从氢气产生装置100从故障开始的时间可供给。选择的绘图 : 图。1', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To provide a hydrogen generator capable of operating without using an independent start-up power source at the time of power failure. SOLUTION :  A hydrogen generator 100 includes :  a reformer 1 for reforming a raw material containing a hydrocarbon component to produce hydrogen-containing gas;  a combustor 4 for combusting at least one of the raw material and the hydrogen-containing gas to heat the reformer 1;  a raw material supplier 2 for supplying the raw material to the reformer 1;  and a controller 30 for starting a start-up step at a predetermined timing before a starting time of the occurrence of power failure based on power failure occurrence information which predicts the occurrence of the power failure and is input from the outside. Thereby,  it is possible to end the start-up step of the hydrogen generator 100 before the occurrence of the power failure,  and accordingly hydrogen can be supplied from the hydrogen generator 100 from the start point of the power failure without using an independent start-up power source. SELECTED DRAWING :  Figure 1 COPYRIGHT :  (C)2016, JPO&INPIT', p.application_date = '2015-02-09 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP2016094328A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2014521258'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2014521258', p.title_cn = '氢气发生器', p.title_en = 'The hydrogen generator', p.abstract_cn = '提供一种氢生成装置，其中允许控制要生成的氢的量。该装置包括：氢产生容器1，其设置有容纳镁基氢化物的镁基氢化物容纳部；储存水或水溶液的反应水槽3；与反应水槽3和氢生成容器1连接的配管4a、4b；泵5，其从反应水槽3吸入水或水溶液后，通过配管4a、4b向氢生成容器1排出；测定氢产生容器1内的压力的压力计18；以及控制单元9，基于压力计18的压力值，控制由泵5流过管道的水量。', p.abstract_en = 'A hydrogen generation apparatus is provided in which the amount of hydrogen to be generated is allowed to be controlled. The apparatus includes :  a hydrogen generation container 1 provided with a magnesium-based hydride accommodation part accommodating magnesium-based hydride;  a reaction water tank 3 storing water or the aqueous solution;  the pipes 4a and 4b connected to the reaction water tank 3 and the hydrogen generation container 1;  a pump 5 operating such as to suction water or the aqueous solution from the reaction water tank 3 and then exhaust it through the pipes 4a and 4b to the hydrogen generation container 1;  a pressure gauge 18 measuring the pressure in the inside of the hydrogen generation container 1;  and a control unit 9,  on the basis of the pressure value of the pressure gauge 18,  controlling the amount of water caused to flow through the pipes by the pump 5.', p.application_date = '2013-05-29 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JPWO2013190966A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/06', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14938315'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14938315', p.title_cn = '将反应气体引入反应室的方法和装置', p.title_en = 'METHOD AND DEVICE FOR INTRODUCING REACTIVE GASSES INTO A REACTION CHAMBER', p.abstract_cn = '一种用于将燃料气体和氧化剂分别引入管状反应器的反应室中的方法和装置，以便在该反应室中进行混合并随着热量的释放而反应。该方法包括 : 将燃料气体和氧化剂分别引入管状反应器的反应室中；将燃料气体和氧化剂分别引入管状反应器的反应室中，以便将燃料气体和氧化剂混合并随着热量的释放而反应。 在每种情况下，不仅燃料气体而且氧化剂都以多于三个的气体射流被引入反应室，其中在进入反应室时，燃料气体射流和尽可能靠近燃料气体射流的氧化剂射流之间的间隙在2至500mm之间，优选在5至50mm之间。', p.abstract_en = 'A method and a device for the separate introduction of a fuel gas and also of an oxidizing agent into the reaction chamber of a tubular reactor,  in order there to be mixed and reacted with the release of heat. Not only the fuel gas but also the oxidizing agent are introduced into the reaction chamber in each case in more than three gas jets,  wherein the margin between a fuel gas jet and an oxidizing agent jet as adjacent as possible thereto,  on entry into the reaction chamber,  is between 2 and 500 mm,  preferably between 5 and 50 mm.', p.application_date = '2015-11-11 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US20160145099A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/36', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WOEP15025077'}) SET p.application_no = 'WOEP15025077', p.title_cn = '植物用于生产氢气和用于操作该植物的方法', p.title_en = 'PLANT FOR PRODUCTION OF HYDROGEN AND METHOD FOR OPERATING THIS PLANT', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种植物用于生产氢，以及一种操作该植物的方法，包括蒸汽重整反应器具有炉(20)，在该反应器内的水和至少一种含碳的能量载体反应以形成含氢的粗合成气体，和至少一个清洁装置(40)用于纯化粗合成气，其粗合成气从蒸汽重整通过至少一个给料管线(27)。根据本发明，上游的一个的至少一个清洁装置的至少一个回线(46)分支从馈线(27)，通过粗合成气体至少部分再循环到炉的蒸汽重整反应器。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a plant for production of hydrogen,  and to a method for operating this plant,  comprising a steam reforming reactor having a furnace (20),  in which reactor water and at least one carbonaceous energy carrier are reacted to form a hydrogen-containing crude synthesis gas,  and at least one cleaning device (40) for purifying the crude synthesis gas,  to which the crude synthesis gas is fed from the steam reforming via at least one feed line (27). According to the invention,  upstream of one of the at least one cleaning devices at least one return line (46) branches off from the feed line (27),  through which the crude synthesis gas is at least in part recirculated into the furnace of the steam reforming reactor.', p.application_date = '2015-11-09 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016078775A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WOEP15076030'}) SET p.application_no = 'WOEP15076030', p.title_cn = '生成和储存氢气的方法和装置', p.title_en = 'METHOD AND INSTALLATION FOR GENERATING AND STORING HYDROGEN', p.abstract_cn = '用于生成和储存氢气的方法包括如下步骤 : 制作可用中间具有增加的气体混合物氢含量和使所述中间体的气体混合物与氢气载介质以氢化氢载体介质。', p.abstract_en = 'A method for generating and storing hydrogen comprises the steps of making available an intermediate gas mixture having an increased hydrogen content and of contacting the intermediate gas mixture with a hydrogen carrier medium in order to hydrogenate the hydrogen carrier medium.', p.application_date = '2015-11-09 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016078948A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/26', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WOEP15076031'}) SET p.application_no = 'WOEP15076031', p.title_cn = '装载/卸载单元，用于氢，安装包括所述装载/卸载部和用于存储和释放能量的方法', p.title_en = 'LOADING/UNLOADING UNIT FOR HYDROGEN,  INSTALLATION COMPRISING SAID LOADING/UNLOADING UNIT AND METHOD FOR STORING AND RELEASING ENERGY', p.abstract_cn = '安装用于存储能量的包括加载/卸载单元(8)用于氢具有反应容器(7)中，载体介质加载，与氢气，氢气卸载，加载的载体介质。', p.abstract_en = 'An installation for storing energy comprises a loading/unloading unit (8) for hydrogen which has a reaction container (7) in which a carrier medium is loaded with hydrogen and the hydrogen is unloaded from the loaded carrier medium.', p.application_date = '2015-11-09 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016078949A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'ARP140104179'}) SET p.application_no = 'ARP140104179', p.title_cn = '生产氢气的方法和所述制氢催化剂', p.title_en = 'PROCESS FOR PRODUCTION OF HYDROGEN AND A CATALYST FOR SAID HYDROGEN PRODUCTION', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种氢的生产方法通过催化分解的氨水溶液中。本发明的目的是实现氨的净化流和使用该流作为纯化在蒸汽重整过程。该纯化步骤去除杂质例如硫，卤素，烯属烃和金属的含氨气体流的单元中产生的酸性水。净化流进行蒸汽重整的重整器炉的方法，所述转化入氨。氢，其纯化，用常规工艺在现有蒸汽重整单元。另外合成催化剂具有特性，能够使其用于净化氨的电流', p.abstract_en = 'The present application discloses a method for producing hydrogen by catalytic decomposition of ammonia from acid water units. In a first step,  the ammonia stream is purified in contact with various catalytic beds,  removing chlorides and sulfur,  and more specifically,  ammonia is partially transformed into hydrogen in the bed formed by a catalyst based on alkalis and alkaline earths,  supported on zinc oxide,  alumina,  silica-alumina and mixtures thereof,  with nickel oxide as the active phase. In the second step,  the purified ammonia stream is fed to the steam reforming reactor to generate hydrogen which is then purified. The application also relates to the catalyst used in the method.', p.application_date = '2014-11-06 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'AR098331A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201310549063.8'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201310549063.8', p.title_cn = '太阳能-常压直流辉光等离子体光解水制氢方法和装置', p.title_en = 'Solar-atmospheric DC glow discharge plasma method and apparatus for hydrogen production from water by photodecomposition', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种太阳能-常压直流辉光等离子体光解水制氢方法和装置。其方法是利用聚光器把太阳光密集化，使其光斑(13)中波长λ≤500mn光子密度达到阈值Φ0以上，然后让光斑(13)稳定地笼罩常压直流水蒸气辉光等离子体空间(23)，水就会光解为H2、和O2。其装置由太阳能聚光器、反应器、直流辉光等离子体电源、冷凝集气系统、供水系统和H2/O2分离设备等6部分组成，聚光器的光斑(13)略大于反应器内的等离子体空间(23)，各部分设备由相关管路、支架顺序连接牢固，在工作时，光斑(13)始终笼罩等离子体空间(23)，就得到氢气和氧气。用本方法和装置制氢，以水为原料，不产生污染，制氢成本低，所用场地极小。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention discloses a solar energy-normal pressure direct current glow plasma water photolysis hydrogen production method and device. The method comprises the following steps of concentrating sunlight by utilizing a light concentrator to enable the density of photons with the wavelength of not more than 500mn in light spots (13) to be above a threshold phi 0,  and then enabling the light spots (13) to stably shroud a normal pressure direct current water steam glow plasma space (23),  thereby obtaining H2 and O2 from water by photolysis. The device comprises six parts,  namely a solar light concentrator,  a reactor,  a direct current glow plasma power supply,  a condensation and gas collection system,  a water supply system and an H2/O2 separation device,  wherein the light spots (13) of the light concentrator are slightly larger than the plasma space (23) in the reactor,  all the parts of the devices are sequentially connected firmly through related pipelines and a support,  and when the device works,  the light spots (13) always shroud the plasma space (23),  and then hydrogen and oxygen can be obtained. By using the method and device for producing hydrogen,  as the water is taken as a raw material,  no pollution is produced,  the hydrogen production cost is low,  and a used space is very small.', p.application_date = '2013-10-31 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN103601148B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201410386675.4'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201410386675.4', p.title_cn = '一种生产合成气的耐硫变换工艺', p.title_en = 'A sulfur-resistant for the production of synthesis gas conversion process', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种生产羰基合成气、费托合成气、甲烷合成气的耐硫变换工艺，提供了将粉煤气化所产生的高CO浓度的所有粗煤气原料气全部经过变换催化剂床层，防止了原料气中的羰基硫、焦油、氰化物等有毒杂质进入下游腐蚀设备；避免了发生甲烷化副反应的危险；有效防止变换反应器床层温度过高；不仅不消耗蒸汽，还可以外供大量中压蒸汽和低压蒸汽的高CO新型耐硫变换工艺。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a sulfur-resisting conversion process for producing a carbonyl synthesis gas,  a fischer-tropsch synthesis gas and a methane synthesis gas and provides a high-CO novel sulfur-resisting conversion process. According to the high-CO novel sulfur-resisting conversion process,  all high-Co crude coal raw material gas generated during powdered coal gasification passes through a shift catalyst bed layer,  toxic impurities such as carbonyl sulfide,  tar and cyanides in the raw material gas are prevented from entering the downstream and corroding equipment,  the danger of methanation side reaction is avoided;  over-high temperature of a shift-converter bed layer is effectively prevented;  no steam is consumed and a great deal of medium-pressure steam and low-pressure steam can be provided.', p.application_date = '2014-08-08 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN104176705B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/16', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201410617084.3'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201410617084.3', p.title_cn = '一种制氢方法', p.title_en = 'Hydrogen production method', p.abstract_cn = '本发明提供了一种制氢方法。在金属有机物化学气相沉积(MOCVD)生产氮化镓发光二极管(GaN-LED)的过程中，一方面MOCVD设备需要大量的高纯氢气作为载气，另一方面MOCVD又会排放大量氨气(混有氢气、氮气以及杂质气体)。本发明所提供了一种制氢方法，就是将MOCVD设备排放的尾气先在500℃～1000℃下将氨气分解、过滤粉尘、加压，然后用变压吸附或者中空纤维膜分离技术将氢气分离出来，最后将氢气用分子筛技术、吸气剂技术等将气体纯化得到高纯氢气，为MOCVD设备使用。上述的制氢方法，既解决了MOCVD尾气排放造成环境污染问题，又解决了MOCVD设备所需要原料氢气问题，物质循环利用。该方法制作简单，设备成熟，制作成本低廉，宜于大规模生产。', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention provides a hydrogen production method. In a gallium nitride light-emitting diode (GaN-LED) production process through metal organic chemical vapor deposition (MOCVD),  the MOCVD equipment requires a lot of high-purity hydrogen gas as a carrier gas,  and the MOCVD can emit a large amount of ammonia gas (mixed with hydrogen gas,  nitrogen gas and impurity gases). According to the hydrogen production method,  the exhaust gas discharged by the MOCVD equipment is subjected to ammonia gas decomposition,  dust filtration and pressurization at a temperature of 500-1000 DEG C,  then the hydrogen gas is separated out by using a pressure varying adsorption or hollow fiber membrane separation technology,  and finally the gas is purified by using a molecular sieve technology,  a gas absorption agent technology and the like to obtain the high-purity hydrogen gas so as to be used for the MOCVD equipment. With the hydrogen production method of the present invention,  the environmental pollution caused by the MOCVD exhaust gas emission is solved,  the raw material hydrogen gas required by the MOCVD equipment is solved,  and the material is recycled;  and the method has characteristics of simple production,  mature equipment and low production cost,  and is suitable for mass production.', p.application_date = '2014-11-06 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105600746A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201511016692.X'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201511016692.X', p.title_cn = '潜水式铝镓合金制氢装置工作方法', p.title_en = 'Working method of submersible type aluminum-gallium alloy hydrogen manufacturing unit', p.abstract_cn = '潜水式铝镓合金制氢装置工作方法属于新能源、减少温室气体排放及军事领域，减少古生物能源的使用，减缓南极、北极及全球永久冰盖消溶的速度，减小厄尼诺现象对人类危害，可以将潜水式铝镓合金制氢装置工作方法制氢所得到的新能源来满足全人类在经济发展中对能源的依赖，在军事领域可以用氢氧燃料电站为军用设备服务，此项制氢及氢使用过程都不会有温室气体排放，从而达到减少温室气体排放、减缓南极、北极和全球永久性冰盖消溶及海平面上升速度，氢是非常清洁的能源，美国最新发明了铝镓合金制氢技术，使用80％的铝加上20％的镓(无需高纯度)的合金，就能使铝在常温下极快与水发生化学反应，因此开辟了制氢新路径。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention discloses a working method of a submersible type aluminum-gallium alloy hydrogen manufacturing unit,  and belongs to the fields of new energy,  greenhouse gas emission reduction and military. In order to reduce the use of fossil energy,  slow down the melting speed of antarctic,  arctic and global permanent ice covers,  reduce the hazards of El Nino phenomenon on human,  the new energy obtained through manufacturing hydrogen by the working method of the submersibletype aluminum-gallium alloy hydrogen manufacturing unit can be used for satisfying the dependence of all human beings on energy during the economic development process;  in the military field,  a hydrogen fuel power plant can be used for serving military equipment;  greenhouse gas is not emitted during the hydrogen manufacturing and using process,  so that the greenhouse gas emission is reduced,  the melting speed of the antarctic,  arctic and global permanent ice covers and the rising speed of sea level are slowed down;  hydrogen is quite clean energy;  a aluminum-gallium alloy hydrogen manufacturing technology is newly invited in America;  the alloy with 80 percent of aluminum and 20 percent of gallium (high purity is not needed) is used,  the aluminum can be chemically reacted with water extremely rapidly at a room temperature,  so that a new path to manufacture hydrogen is developed.', p.application_date = '2015-12-29 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105600748A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/08', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201510671028.2'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201510671028.2', p.title_cn = '一种合成氢燃料的方法', p.title_en = 'Method for synthesizing hydrogen fuel', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种合成氢燃料的方法，采用乙醇或甲醇与水混合作为主体原料，甲醇或乙醇方便储存和运输，在潮湿条件下性质稳定，不发生副反应；所述主体原料是可再生能源、来源丰富，乙醇来源于植物、农业废弃物提取的可再生的生物质能源及制药厂使用后的废弃乙醇；甲醇来源于工业副产品和生物甲醇；原料成本低，且不受限制；反应过程无污染物产生，氢燃料可与汽油在汽车中交替使用，可有效节省能源，降低成本，且氢燃料燃烧后的产物无污染，绿色环保零排放。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention discloses a method for synthesizing a hydrogen fuel. Ethanol or methanol and water are mixed as a main body raw material,  and methanol or ethanol is convenient to store and transport,  and is stable without side reactions under wet conditions;  the main body raw material is renewable energy,  and has abundant sources,  and ethanol is from renewable biomass energy extracted from plants and agricultural wastes and waste ethanol used in the pharmaceutical factory;  and methanol is from industrial byproducts and biological methanol. The method has the advantages of low cost and no restriction of the raw material,  no generation of pollutants in the reaction process,  realization of effective energy saving and cost reduction due to alternate use of the hydrogen fuel and gasoline in automobiles,  no pollution of products obtained after combustion of the hydrogen fuel,  environmental protection and zero discharge.', p.application_date = '2015-10-16 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105600749A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/22', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201510789617.0'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201510789617.0', p.title_cn = '用于生产氢的设备和用于操作该设备的方法', p.title_en = 'Plant for production of hydrogen and method for operating this plant', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及用于生产氢的设备和用于操作该设备的方法，设备包括：具有炉的蒸汽重整反应器，在该反应器中，水和至少一种碳能量载体反应以形成含氢的粗合成气体；和至少一个清洁装置，用于净化粗合成气体，粗合成气体从蒸汽重整反应器经由至少一个供给管路供给到所述至少一个清洁装置。根据本发明，在所述至少一个清洁装置中的一个清洁装置的上游，至少一个返回管路从供给管路分支，粗合成气体通过所述至少一个返回管路被至少部分地再循环到蒸汽重整反应器的炉中。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a plant for production of hydrogen,  and to a method for operating this plant,  comprising a steam reforming reactor having a furnace (20),  in which reactor water and at least one carbonaceous energy carrier are reacted to form a hydrogen-containing crude synthesis gas,  and at least one cleaning device (40) for purifying the crude synthesis gas,  to which the crude synthesis gas is fed from the steam reforming via at least one feed line (27). According to the invention,  upstream of one of the at least one cleaning devices at least one return line (46) branches off from the feed line (27),  through which the crude synthesis gas is at least in part recirculated into the furnace of the steam reforming reactor.', p.application_date = '2015-11-17 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105600750A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/36', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201520854140.5'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201520854140.5', p.title_cn = '烧碱生产中的氢气处理装置', p.title_en = 'Hydrogen processing apparatus among caustic soda production', p.abstract_cn = '本专利属于烧碱生产辅助设备领域，具体公开了烧碱生产中的氢气处理装置，包括依次布置的密封水箱、干燥箱、压缩机和分配器，所述密封水箱的底部安装有进气管，密封水箱与干燥箱通过软管连接，干燥箱与压缩机通过无缝管连接，压缩机与分配器通过管道连接；所述软管上安装有第一电控阀，无缝管上安装有湿度传感器和第二电控阀，干燥箱上安装有控制器，湿度传感器、第一电控阀和第二电控阀均与控制器电连接。本装置能降低烧碱生产中氢气的湿度。', p.abstract_en = 'This patent belongs to the caustic soda production auxiliary assembly field,  specifically discloses hydrogen processing apparatus among caustic soda production,  including sealed water tank,  drying cabinet,  compressor and the distributor of arranging in proper order,  the intake pipe is installed to sealed water tank\'s bottom,  and sealed water tank passes through the hose connection with the drying cabinet,  and the drying cabinet passes through the seamless pipe with the compressor to be connected,  and the compressor passes through the pipe connection with the distributor,  installing first automatically controlled valve on the hose,  installing the automatically controlled valve of humidity transducer and second on the seamless pipe,  install the controller on the drying cabinet,  humidity transducer,  first automatically controlled valve and the automatically controlled valve of second all are connected with the controller electricity. This device can reduce the humidity of hydrogen among the caustic soda production.', p.application_date = '2015-10-31 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN205257995U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/52', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'EP13839381'}) SET p.application_no = 'EP13839381', p.title_cn = '大容量高分子聚合物储氢材料及其制备方法', p.title_en = 'HIGH-CAPACITY MACROMOLECULAR POLYMER HYDROGEN STORAGE MATERIAL AND PREPARATION METHOD THEREOF', p.abstract_cn = '提供一种高容量高分子聚合物储氢材料，包括线性高分子聚合物为主链，和硼烷氨衍生物接枝在侧链和/或后端线性高分子聚合物侧链基和/或端基的线性高分子聚合物胺的多胺化合物与硼氢化反应。还提供一种制备方法，该高容量高分子聚合物储氢材料。', p.abstract_en = 'Provided is a high-capacity macromolecular polymer hydrogen storage material,  comprising a linear macromolecular polymer as a main chain,  and a borane ammonia derivative grafted on the side chain and/or end of the linear macromolecular polymer after a side-chain group and/or end group of the linear macromolecular polymer is aminated by a polyamine compound and reacts with a borohydride. Also provided is a preparation method for the high-capacity macromolecular polymer hydrogen storage material.', p.application_date = '2013-09-12 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'EP2899156A4', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'EP13847306'}) SET p.application_no = 'EP13847306', p.title_cn = '合成气体分离和重整方法', p.title_en = 'SYNTHESIS GAS SEPARATION AND REFORMING PROCESS', p.abstract_cn = '获得纯化的方法的氢气和纯净的一氧化碳从粗合成气。第一粗合成气体流通过通过第一分离 分离区的氢气流从流的包含一氧化碳和甲烷。所述一氧化碳和甲烷进行热重整以产生第二的粗合成气，它是通过第二分离区分离一氧化碳从第二粗合成气体流。', p.abstract_en = 'A method of obtaining purified hydrogen and purified carbon monoxide from crude synthesis gas. A first crude synthesis gas stream is passed through a first separation zone to separate a hydrogen stream from a stream comprising carbon monoxide and methane. The carbon monoxide and methane are subjected to thermal reforming to produce a second crude synthesis gas,  which is passed through a second separation zone to separate carbon monoxide from the second crude synthesis gas stream.', p.application_date = '2013-09-19 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'EP2900591A4', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/34', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'EP15162906'}) SET p.application_no = 'EP15162906', p.title_cn = '生产合成气的方法', p.title_en = 'PROCESS FOR PRODUCING A SYNTHESIS GAS', p.abstract_cn = '方法用于制造含氢合成气从天然气原料，包括转换所述天然气为原料的产物气体和纯化所述产物气体，该过程具有热输入提供的燃料的燃烧；所述方法包括含碳原料的转化的步骤，和至少一部分所述燃料为气态燃料的所述步骤得到的转化所述碳质原料。', p.abstract_en = 'Process for manufacturing a hydrogen-containing synthesis gas from a natural gas feedstock,  comprising the conversion of said natural gas into a raw product gas and purification of said product gas,  the process having a heat input provided by combustion of a fuel;  said process comprises a step of conversion of a carbonaceous feedstock,  and at least a portion of said fuel is a gaseous fuel obtained by said step of conversion of said carbonaceous feedstock.', p.application_date = '2015-04-09 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'EP3023388A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2012236672'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2012236672', p.title_cn = '饱和器和天然气具有其的重整系统', p.title_en = 'Saturator and natural gas reforming system having the same', p.abstract_cn = '本发明提供一种饱和器，天然气重整系统，使得可以更有效地回收利用热量从热源到的量最大化水蒸汽加入到一种流体. 饱和器(20)包括 : 其内部流路第一的流体流动. 第第一换热单元(22)，其使第一流体和第第二流体之间的热交换. 第第二换热单元(23)，其使第三流体与第第一流体之间换热后第一具有通过第第一换热单元(22)。. 加湿单元(26)，加水第一上游的流体从第一换热单元(22)和第第二换热单元(23)。. 和第三输送路径输送流体换热后从第二换热单元(23)的上游侧的第第一换热单元(22)。和使所述第三流体流入流动通道第一流体. 第一流体被加热并加湿的第一换热单元(22)。. 第二的流体排出至外部冷却系统. 第一流体进行加热，在第二换热单元(23)和加湿饱和蒸汽压力排放到外部环境之前的系统. 和第三的流体冷却.', p.abstract_en = 'Provided are a saturator and a natural gas reforming system that make it possible to more efficiently recover and use heat from a heat source and to maximize the amount of water vapor added to a fluid. The saturator (20) comprises :  a flow path inside of which a first fluid flows;  a first heat exchange unit (22) that causes heat exchange between the first fluid and a second fluid;  a second heat exchange unit (23) that causes heat exchange between a third fluid and the first fluid after the first fluid has passed through the first heat exchange unit (22);  a humidifying unit (26) that adds water to the first fluid upstream from the first heat exchange unit (22) and the second heat exchange unit (23);  and a conveyance path that conveys the third fluid after heat exchange from the second heat exchange unit (23) to the upstream side of the first heat exchange unit (22) and causes said third fluid to flow into the flow path as the first fluid. The first fluid is heated and humidified at the first heat exchange unit (22),  the second fluid is cooled and discharged to outside of the system,  the first fluid is heated at the second heat exchange unit (23) and humidified to saturation vapor pressure before being discharged to outside of the system,  and the third fluid is cooled.', p.application_date = '2012-10-26 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP5925105B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2012038483'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2012038483', p.title_cn = '用于使用产生氢气的方法', p.title_en = 'A method for generating hydrogen for use', p.abstract_cn = '所要解决的问题 : 提供一种用于产生氢气的氧化物的生产方法，用于氢产生的氧化物是结构简单，制造容易，用于产生氢气和氧化物的生产方法生产的解决手段如下 : 金属氧化膜和反应剂装入反应容器内。被保持在无氧状态下，所述反应容器加热，水被供给润滑剂。', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To provide a production method of an oxide for hydrogen generation,  by which an oxide for hydrogen generation is easily produced with a simple constitution,  and an oxide for hydrogen generation produced by the production method.SOLUTION :  A metal having an oxide film and a reaction agent are enclosed in a reaction vessel of which the inside is kept in an oxygen-free state,  the reaction vessel is heated,  and water is supplied thereto.', p.application_date = '2012-02-24 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP5925521B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/08', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'UAU201510789'}) SET p.application_no = 'UAU201510789', p.title_cn = '强化从碱性溶液中电催化释放氢的反应的方法', p.title_en = 'METHOD OF INTENSIFICATION OF THE REACTION OF ELECTROCATALYTIC RELEASE OF HYDROGEN FROM ALKALINE SOLUTIONS', p.abstract_cn = '强化从碱性溶液中电催化释放氢的反应的方法，包括在电极上由非晶态合金发生的反应。作为电极材料，使用非晶态合金FeNbGdB，其另外被热处理。', p.abstract_en = 'Method of intensification of the reaction of electrocatalytic release of hydrogen from alkaline solutions,  including a reaction that occurs on an electrode from an amorphous alloy. As an electrode material,  the amorphous alloy FeNbGdB is used,  which is additionally heat-processed.', p.application_date = '2015-11-05 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'UA107116U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/50', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'BRPI0418977'}) SET p.application_no = 'BRPI0418977', p.title_cn = '将含碳材料转化为能量气体的方法和系统产生气体的合成', p.title_en = 'process to convert carboniferous material into energy gases and system to produce a gas synthetic', p.abstract_cn = '一种生产合成气的方法和装置用于使用作为气态燃料或作为饲料成费-托反应器中，以产生液态燃料在基本自支持过程。在一个实施例中，含碳材料在水中的浆料，和氢气从内源的，送入加氢气化反应器中以产生富含甲烷的气体送入蒸汽热解重整器以便产生包括氢气和一氧化碳的合成气。使用氢的一部分作为内的氢源。剩余的合成气作为燃料以产生电和/或工艺热，或送入费-托反应器生产液体燃料。在本发明的另一实施例，碳质材料可同时加热在氢和蒸汽存在下经历蒸汽热解和加氢气化在单一的步骤。', p.abstract_en = 'A process and apparatus for producing a synthesis gas for use as a gaseous fuel or as feed into a Fischer-Tropsch reactor to produce a liquid fuel in a substantially self-sustaining process. In one embodiment,  a slurry of carbonaceous material in water,  and hydrogen from an internal source,  are fed into a hydro-gasification reactor to generate methane rich producer gases which are fed into a steam pyrolytic reformer to generate synthesis gas comprising hydrogen and carbon monoxide. A portion of the hydrogen is used as the internal hydrogen source. The remaining synthesis gas is either used as fuel to produce electricity and/or process heat or is fed into a Fischer-Tropsch reactor to produce liquid fuel. In another embodiment of the invention,  carbonaceous material can be heated simultaneously in the presence of both hydrogen and steam to undergo steam pyrolysis and hydro-gasification in a single step.', p.application_date = '2004-08-04 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'BRPI0418977B8', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'BR112012021913'}) SET p.application_no = 'BR112012021913', p.title_cn = '合成气生产方法', p.title_en = 'METHOD FOR SYNTHESIS GAS PRODUCTION', p.abstract_cn = '避免了来自浇注料的硫化合物混入生产的合成气中， 将混合硫化合物与二氧化碳分离收集，收集的二氧化碳作为原料气循环使用，然后将硫化合物直接供给重整器，从而使重整器中的重整催化剂发生硫中毒而降解。 在二氧化碳除去步骤中分离和收集的二氧化碳在再循环到重整器以除去硫化合物之前被引入到脱硫步骤的脱硫装置或硫化合物吸附装置中。', p.abstract_en = 'It is avoided that the sulfur compounds originating from the castable is mixed into produced synthesis gas,  the mixed sulfur compounds are separated and collected with carbon dioxide,  the collected carbon dioxide is recycled as raw material gas and then the sulfur compounds is directly supplied to the reformer to consequently degrade the reforming catalyst in the reformer by sulfur poisoning. The carbon dioxide separated and collected in the carbon dioxide removal step is introduced into the desulfurization apparatus of the desulfurization step or the sulfur compounds adsorption apparatus before being recycled to the reformer to remove the sulfur compounds.', p.application_date = '2011-02-21 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'BRPI1221913A2', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'BR112013001061'}) SET p.application_no = 'BR112013001061', p.title_cn = '用于热解生物质的方法和装置', p.title_en = 'METHOD AND DEVICE FOR PYROLYSIS OF A BIOMASS', p.abstract_cn = '一种利用来自固体热载体或催化剂的快速传热有效热解生物质的方法和装置。 特别地，本发明的各种实施方案提供了方法和装置，其包括逐步的温度骤冷和热载体材料与反应产物的快速分离。', p.abstract_en = 'A method and apparatus for effective pyrolysis of a biomass utilizing rapid heat transfer from a solid heat carrier or catalyst. Particularly,  various embodiments of the present invention provide methods and apparatuses which incorporate progressive temperature quenching and rapid disengagement of the heat carrier material and reaction product.', p.application_date = '2011-06-30 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'BRPI1301061A2', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'DE602006050698'}) SET p.application_no = 'DE602006050698', p.title_cn = '氢制造装置，和使用其的燃料电池发电装置，电动车辆，潜水艇及氢供给系统', p.title_en = 'HYDROGEN PRODUCTION APPARATUS,  AND MAKING USE OF THE SAME,  FUEL CELL POWER GENERATOR,  ELECTRIC VEHICLE,  SUBMERSIBLE SHIP AND HYDROGEN SUPPLY SYSTEM', p.abstract_cn = '氢生成装置，能够生成含氢气体在较低温度，以及燃料电池发电装置，电动汽车，可潜浮船和氢气供应系统的氢气发生装置被提供。氢产生装置(10)用于产生含氢气体的方法，该燃料含有有机复合，包括 : 隔离膜(11)；燃料电极(12)，其设置在隔离膜的一个表面(11)；一种含有有机化合物和水的燃料供给装置的燃料电极(12)；氧化电极(14)的另一面上设有分隔膜(11)；一种氧化电极的氧化剂供给手段(14)；以及一装置，用于产生和收集的含氢气体从燃料极，和氧化剂供给不足的区域设置于氧化电极侧，以使(c)的反应6h+6E-3H-5月2日发生在燃料极侧和(d)CH3OH[2]O的反应？“6H Ce++-+5月2日出现CO氧化电极侧上。所述氧化剂供给不足的区域可以通过执行掩模(14M)的一部分上设置气体扩散所述氧化剂电极层(14)。此外，通过将氢气发生装置(10)连接到燃料电池的燃料电池发电装置供应产生的含氢气体的氢生成装置(10)的燃料电池，电动汽车和潜水船加入燃料电池发电装置，所述氢产生装置(10)，储氢装置，供氢系统可经配置以将产生的含氢气体的氢生成装置(10)所述氢存储装置。', p.abstract_en = 'A hydrogen generating device capable of generating a gas containing hydrogen at a low temperature,  as well as a fuel cell power generating device,  an electric automobile,  a submergible ship and a hydrogen supply system using the hydrogen generating device are provided. A hydrogen generating device (10) for generating a gas containing hydrogen by decomposing a fuel containing an organic compound,  includes :  a partition membrane (11);  a fuel electrode (12) provided on one surface of the partition membrane (11);  a means for supplying a fuel containing organic compound and water to the fuel electrode (12);  an oxidizing electrode (14) provided on the other surface of the partition membrane (11);  a means for supplying an oxidizing agent to the oxidizing electrode (14) ;  and a means for generating and collecting the gas containing hydrogen from the fuel electrode,  and a region of insufficient oxidizing agent supply is provided on the oxidizing electrode side so that a reaction (C) 6H + + 6e - -3H 2 may occur on the fuel electrode side and a reaction (D) CH 3 OH + H 2 O †’ 6H + + Ce - + CO 2 may occur on the oxidizing electrode side. The region of insufficient oxidizing agent supply can be provided by performing masking (14M) on part of the gas diffusion layer of the oxidizing electrode (14). Moreover,  by connecting the hydrogen generating device (10) to a fuel cell and connecting a fuel cell power generating device for supplying a gas containing hydrogen generated by the hydrogen generating device (10) to the fuel cell,  an electric automobile and a submergible ship incorporating the fuel cell power generating device,  and the hydrogen generating device (10) to a hydrogen storage means,  a hydrogen supply system can be configured for supplying a gas containing hydrogen generated by the hydrogen generating device (10) to the hydrogen storage means.', p.application_date = '2006-06-02 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'DE602006050698T2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/32', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2012048845'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2012048845', p.title_cn = '模制', p.title_en = 'Molding', p.abstract_cn = '本发明的目的在于提供一种能够稳定地提供含有分子氢的组合物的成型品。 在该成型品中，与水或该成型品的水性组合物接触的部分的全部或一部分包含通过与水接触产生分子氢的组分。', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To provide a molding capable of providing stably a composition containing molecular hydrogen.SOLUTION :  A molding used by being brought into contact with water or an aqueous composition is provided. In the molding,  the whole or a part of a portion to be brought into contact with water or the aqueous composition of the molding comprises a component generating molecular hydrogen by being brought into contact with water.', p.application_date = '2012-03-06 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP5921917B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/06', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'DE602015030812'}) SET p.application_no = 'DE602015030812', p.title_cn = '一种含氢生物应用液的生产方法及装置', p.title_en = 'METHOD AND DEVICE FOR PRODUCING HYDROGEN-CONTAINING BIOLOGICAL APPLICATION SOLUTION', p.abstract_cn = '一种用于生产含氢流体的装置(1)，包括 : 容器(12)，其存储能够用于生物体并具有水蒸汽渗透性的流体(11)； 利用湿气产生氢气的氢气产生系统(13)； 以及包围容器(12)和氢生成系统(13)并具有低氢分子渗透性的包裹构件(14)， 其中包装构件(14)包围容器(12)和位于容器外部的氢气发生系统(13)，并且进行在容器(12)的外表面和包装构件(14)的内表面之间的空间(15)中增加湿度的处理。', p.abstract_en = 'A device (1) for producing a hydrogen containing fluid,  comprising :  a container (12) that stores fluid (11) which able to be used for a living organism and has water vapor permeability;  a hydrogen generating system (13) that generates hydrogen by using moisture;  and a wrapping member (14) that encloses the container (12) and the hydrogen generating system (13) and has low hydrogen molecule permeability,  wherein the wrapping member (14) encloses the container (12) and the hydrogen generating system (13) located outside the container,  and a treatment to increase humidity in a space (15) between an outer surface of the container (12) and an inner surface of the wrapping member (14) is performed.', p.application_date = '2015-03-13 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'DE602015030812T2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/06', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'TR201501016'}) SET p.application_no = 'TR201501016', p.title_cn = '转化为金属。 从非铸造或铸造的土壤、炉渣和赤泥中产生氢气的装置。', p.title_en = 'Conversion to metal. Plant that produces hydrogen gas from non-cast or cast soil,  slags and red sludge.', p.abstract_cn = '满足； 它涉及从铝土矿矿石生产铝到氧化铝的设施，以及在再生铝生产中利用铸土、炉渣和赤泥分离水来生产氢气(H2)的设施。', p.abstract_en = 'Meet;  It is related to the facilities that produce aluminum from bauxite ore to alumina,  and the facility that produces hydrogen gas (H2) by separating the water using casting soil,  slags and red sludge in secondary aluminum production.', p.application_date = '2015-01-29 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'TR201501016A2', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'RU2015150557'}) SET p.application_no = 'RU2015150557', p.title_cn = '用于生产水ksidov铝和氢气', p.title_en = 'INSTALLATION FOR PRODUCING HYDRO KSIDOV ALUMINIUM AND HYDROGEN', p.abstract_cn = '安装用于生产水ksidov铝和氢气，含反应器与连接到其的碱性水供应管线和用于传输反应器中获得的氢排放的预期其中悬浊液的收集能力和中间端分离的粉末形式的水ksida产品通过洗铝，其特征在于 : 在反应器中制成形态的N个烧瓶，至少，两个，安装在敞口罐运行中的行水，工作灯泡的体积自来水的下永久层，用于接收口瓶作为起始原料，与抽头上设有胶塞，在柔性塑料软管的形式，其中一些连接到管道供气的碱性水和配有内置在每个灯泡截止阀，和其它连接到该管道排气的氢并设置有红外传感器的监测端每个所述烧瓶中反应，灯泡安装在罐体内通过机械手工艺的复杂位移，提供变速器悬置复杂的水从工作容积灯泡ksida铝在所述储水箱用于收集。', p.abstract_en = 'Proposed installation is designed for realization of the method of preparing hydro ksidov aluminum with the use of waste of aluminium and/or its alloys in the form of chips and small pieces of different shape in as initial raw material. Plant reactor has a number of flasks (2),  installed bases in tank (3) with running tap water. Working volume of lower conical part of bulb is designed for receiving initial raw material,  charged through neck (8),  and carrying out exothermic reaction. Of the neck (8) flasks are closed by removable rubber plugs (10) with the built-in in them taps (11 and 12) in the form of sagging flexible plastic hoses. Through branches (11),  connected to pipeline (4),  into the flask is supplied alkaline solution. Operation of built in taps (11) at each of the flasks cutoff valves (13) is provided selective character solution feeding into a specific bulb (2). Obtained in a result of exothermic reaction of hydrogen is discharged through flexible hoses (12),  connected to pipeline (5) at actuation of infrared sensors (14),  each of which that no hydrogen outlet from certain flask (2). Complex technological displacement flasks (2),  required for transfer obtained in a result of exothermic reaction suspension of complex hydro ksida of aluminum in vessel for its collection and cycle,  is carried out with (16),  representing installed near with tank (3) movable in three flat Facility mechanical arm with grip (15). As a result of use of optimum for diffusion condensate safety of the process exothermic reaction working volume (up to 1500 ml),  provision of effective cooling zones of reaction and Your savings of a share of the manual labor considerably is increased operational safety of installation.', p.application_date = '2015-11-26 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'RU162034U1', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/08', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'RU2014143180'}) SET p.application_no = 'RU2014143180', p.title_cn = '方法和装置用于并行生产不同的合成-气体', p.title_en = 'METHOD AND DEVICE FOR PARALLEL PRODUCTION OF DIFFERENT SYNTHESIS OF - GASES', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种方法和一种装置，用于至少两个并行生产合成气体(10，11)具有不同组合物从含烃原料(1)上，混合后的蒸汽(2)和/或二氧化碳(3)，送入蒸汽重整装置(R)和在那里转变成蒸汽转化合成气的至少两个催化剂管(K1，K2，K3)并联运行。本发明的特征是，至少两个的混合物(6，9)具有不同组合物的形成从含烃原料(1)由分加入蒸汽(2)和/或二氧化碳(3)，其中每个所述不同混合物(6，9)供给作为单独的进料催化剂的催化剂管或基团管(K1，K2，K3)的蒸汽重整器(R)和转化成合成气体(10，11)。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a process and an apparatus for the parallel production of at least two synthesis gases (10,  11) having different compositions from a hydrocarbon-containing starting material (1) which is,  after mixing with steam (2) and/or carbon dioxide (3),  fed to a steam reformer (R) and there converted into synthesis gas by steam reforming in at least two catalyst tubes (K1,  K2,  K3) operated in parallel. It is characteristic of the invention that at least two mixtures (6,  9) having different compositions are formed from the hydrocarbon-containing starting material (1) by division and addition of steam (2) and/or carbon dioxide (3),  where each of the different mixtures (6,  9) is fed as exclusive feed to a catalyst tube or a group of catalyst tubes (K1,  K2,  K3) of the steam reformer (R) and converted into synthesis gas (10,  11).', p.application_date = '2014-10-27 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'RU2014143180A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'AU2013292873'}) SET p.application_no = 'AU2013292873', p.title_cn = '综合利用方法低碳排放的费-托合成尾气', p.title_en = 'Process for comprehensively utilizing low carbon emission Fischer-Tropsch synthesis tail gas', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种综合利用工艺低碳排放的费托合成尾气。 过程中， 非循环后产生的尾气费-托合成反应蒸汽重整和转换成富氢 合成气，然后高纯度的氢气分离和提取从富氢合成气使用。 该方法包括以下步骤 : 1)进行水蒸气转化反应，获得变换气； 2)进行费-托合成反应得到的烃燃料； 3)预重整反应后，将含有两个或更多个碳原子的烃类化合物成沼气； 4)进行重整反应将甲烷和蒸汽的成氢气和一氧化碳； 5)分离氢气和一氧化碳的气体； 和6)重整反应器提供热量。 本发明有效利用费托合成尾气， 特别是尾气含有大量惰性组分， 和将尾气进入氢气使用。 此外， 本发明有效利用其剩余重整气体中的可燃成分分离出氢气后， 从而提高能量的利用效率。', p.abstract_en = 'Disclosed is a process for comprehensively utilizing low carbon emission Fischer-Tropsch synthesis tail gas. In the process,  a non-cycling tail gas generated after a Fischer-Tropsch synthesis reaction is steam reformed and converted into a hydrogen-rich synthesis gas,  and then highly purified hydrogen is separated and extracted from the hydrogen-rich synthesis gas for use. The process comprises the following steps :  1) conducting a steam conversion reaction to obtain converted gas;  2) conducting a Fischer-Tropsch synthesis reaction to obtain a hydrocarbon fuel;  3) after a pre-reforming reaction,  converting a hydrocarbon compound containing two or more carbon atoms into methane;  4) conducting a reforming reaction to convert the methane and steam into hydrogen and carbon monoxide;  5) separating the hydrogen and carbon monoxide from the gas;  and 6) providing heat for a reforming reactor. The present invention effectively utilizes the Fischer-Tropsch synthesis tail gas,  especially a tail gas containing a large amount of inert constituents,  and converts the tail gas into the hydrogen for use. Furthermore,  the present invention effectively utilizes the residual combustible constituents in the reformed gas after the hydrogen is separated,  thus improving energy utilization efficiency.', p.application_date = '2013-07-11 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'AU2013292873B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'DE102014116871'}) SET p.application_no = 'DE102014116871', p.title_cn = '氢产生装置及其操作方法', p.title_en = 'Apparatus for the generation of hydrogen and process for operating same', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种安装用于生产氢的方法包括蒸汽重整反应器(20) 炉， 在水和一种含氢的粗合成气反应，至少一个含碳能源 和至少一个清洁装置(30，33，35，40)用于纯化的粗合成气。 所述至少一个清洁装置供给来自蒸汽重整所述的粗合成气体(20)通过至少 一个供应管线(27，32，34，37)。 前一个的至少一个清洗装置(30， 33， 35， 40)， 分支至少一个回线(46，47)从至少一个供给管线(27， 32， 34， 37)AB， 通过粗合成气体至少部分地在所述炉的蒸汽重整反应器(20)返回。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a plant for production of hydrogen,  and to a method for operating this plant,  comprising a steam reforming reactor having a furnace,  in which reactor water and at least one carbonaceous energy carrier are reacted to form a hydrogen-containing crude synthesis gas,  and at least one cleaning device for purifying the crude synthesis gas,  to which the crude synthesis gas is fed from the steam reforming via at least one feed line. According to the invention,  upstream of one of the at least one cleaning devices at least one return line branches off from the feed line,  through which the crude synthesis gas is at least in part recirculated into the furnace of the steam reforming reactor.', p.application_date = '2014-11-18 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'DE102014116871A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/50', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'DE102014223426'}) SET p.application_no = 'DE102014223426', p.title_cn = '装载/卸载单元，用于氢，植物与这种装载/卸载组件和用于存储和释放能量的方法', p.title_en = 'Loading/unloading unit for hydrogen,  plant with such a loading/unloading assembly and method for storing and releasing energy', p.abstract_cn = '植物用于存储能量的加载/卸载单元面(8)上的氢， 包括反应容器(7)， 在加载支撑介质与氢气和出料的氢发生在从加载 载体介质。', p.abstract_en = 'An installation for storing energy comprises a loading/unloading unit (8) for hydrogen which has a reaction container (7) in which a carrier medium is loaded with hydrogen and the hydrogen is unloaded from the loaded carrier medium.', p.application_date = '2014-11-17 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'DE102014223426A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'DE102014223427'}) SET p.application_no = 'DE102014223427', p.title_cn = '生成和储存氢气的方法和装置', p.title_en = 'Method and apparatus for generating and storing hydrogen', p.abstract_cn = '一种产生和储存氢气的方法包括提供至少一种烃化合物包括原料气体混合物 一种， 前处理双离合器具有增加的混合物氢组分的原料气体混合物接触的制造 双离合器混合物与氢加氢的载体介质的氢载体介质。', p.abstract_en = 'A process for producing and storing hydrogen includes providing an intermediate gas mixture having an increased proportion of hydrogen and contacting of the intermediate gas mixture with a hydrogen carrier medium in order to hydrogenate the hydrogen carrier medium.', p.application_date = '2014-11-17 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'DE102014223427A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/24', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'DE602010032036'}) SET p.application_no = 'DE602010032036', p.title_cn = '工艺用于制造含氢产物气体', p.title_en = 'PROCESS FOR PRODUCING A HYDROGEN-CONTAINING PRODUCT GAS', p.abstract_cn = '用于制造含氢产物气体的方法通过催化蒸汽-烃重整的总蒸汽-碳用于该方法的摩尔比为1.5 : 2.4。工艺流反应，反应之前在至少两个预转化炉中的含催化剂的管中在顶烧转化炉。绝热预重整器第一中的过程物流反应，本发明的方法之前被引入物流被加热预重整器第二和/或第二加热预重整器。该方法避免了碳沉积在所述催化剂中的含催化剂的管中的主重整器。', p.abstract_en = 'A process for producing a hydrogen-containing product gas by catalytic steam-hydrocarbon reforming with an overall steam-to-carbon molar ratio between 1.5 and 2.4 for the process. The process stream is reacted in at least two prereformers prior to reaction in catalyst-containing tubes in a top-fired reformer furnace. The process stream is reacted adiabatically in the first prereformer,  while the process stream is heated prior to being introduced into the second prereformer and/or the second prereformer is heated. The process avoids carbon formation on the catalyst in the catalyst-containing tubes in the primary reformer.', p.application_date = '2010-04-15 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'DE602010032036T2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2014217191'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2014217191', p.title_cn = '氢纯化方法.', p.title_en = 'METHOD FOR PURIFYING HYDROGEN', p.abstract_cn = '所要解决的问题 : 钯合金管的一端与支撑管的开口端管板与电池内部的一次侧空间空间分隔成二次侧. 所述含氢杂质从一次侧空间. 用纯氢气钯合金管将取自二次侧空间构成的纯化氢气通过氢气纯化方法. 一种含有杂质的不透过钯合金管的气体量减少. 纯氢，可取出二次侧空间以提供用于净化氢气的方法. 溶液 : 1000或更少为原料用氢气中的氢的杂质浓度. 一种含有杂质的不透过钯合金毛细管. 所述原料的流量的流量通过引入氢气从一次侧空间2-10%. 选择附图中 : 图. 1.', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To provide a method for purifying hydrogen,  in which a hydrogen purification device is used,  which device is constituted so that the inside of a cell is partitioned into primary side space and secondary side space by one end-sealed palladium alloy small tubes and a tube plate for supporting open ends of the palladium alloy small tubes,  impurity-containing hydrogen is introduced from the primary side space and is permeated through the palladium alloy small tubes and pure hydrogen is withdrawn from the secondary side space,  and in which method the amount of the gas to be withdrawn is reduced,  which gas contains impurities unpassed through the palladium alloy small tubes,  and the pure hydrogen can efficiently be withdrawn from the secondary side space. SOLUTION :  In the method for purifying hydrogen,  hydrogen containing impurities of the concentration equal to or lower than 1, 000 ppm is used as raw material hydrogen. The gas containing impurities unpassed through the palladium alloy small tubes is withdrawn from the primary side space by a flow rate of 2-10% of the flow rate of the raw material hydrogen to be introduced. SELECTED DRAWING :  Figure 1 COPYRIGHT :  (C)2016, JPO&INPIT', p.application_date = '2014-10-24 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP2016084252A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/56', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14896883'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14896883', p.title_cn = '烃类气体部分氧化反应器', p.title_en = 'REACTOR FOR PARTIAL OXIDATION OF HYDROCARBON GASES', p.abstract_cn = '本公开涉及用于烃原料的部分氧化的反应器。 反应器包括具有反应产物出口装置的外壳，所述反应产物出口装置具有至少一个用于将原料或原料组分进口到催化剂套筒中的装置，所述催化剂套筒设置在反应器内，在外壳之间具有填充有催化剂的间隙，并且所述反应器包括从其下部出口产物的装置。 该催化剂套筒设置有与催化剂套筒的圆柱形壁的至少一部分接触的护套，该护套在与护套接触的点处具有开口端孔，并且反应器配备有冷却剂进入冷却催化剂套筒的护套的装置。 本发明的技术效果是将催化剂套管壁温降至1000℃以下，减少催化剂套管材料的腐蚀。', p.abstract_en = 'This disclosure is related to reactor for partial oxidation of hydrocarbonaceous feedstock. The reactor comprises outer shell with reaction products outlet device with at least one device for inlet of feedstock or feedstock components into the catalyst sleeve placed within the reactor with a gap between the outer shell filled with a catalyst and comprising means of product outlet from its lower part. This catalyst sleeve is furnished with a jacket in contact with at least a part of the cylindrical wall of the catalyst sleeve having open-end holes in the point of contact with jacket,  and the reactor is equipped with a means of inlet of a cooling agent into the jacket that cools the catalyst sleeve. Technical result of claimed invention is reduction of catalyst sleeve wall temperature to 1000° C. or lower and reduction of catalyst sleeve material corrosion.', p.application_date = '2014-02-28 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US20160136604A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14898998'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14898998', p.title_cn = '高效利用过剩电能的装置和方法', p.title_en = 'PLANT AND PROCESS FOR THE EFFICIENT UTILIZATION OF EXCESS ELECTRIC ENERGY', p.abstract_cn = '在包括用于氢的电化学或电热生产的第一设备的设备中，所述第一设备产生第一氢气物流； 第二装置，用于通过蒸汽重整、部分氧化或脱氢从烃生产氢气，其产生第二氢气物流； 氢导管或氢消耗器，所述第一氢气物流和所述第二氢气物流都进料到所述氢导管或氢消耗器； 以及控制装置，其以第一氢气流和第二氢气流的总量对应于预定值的方式匹配第一设备和第二设备中的氢气的产生，通过操作具有过量电能的用于电化学或电热产生氢气的设备，可以有效地利用过量电能。', p.abstract_en = 'In a plant comprising a first apparatus for the electrochemical or electrothermal production of hydrogen,  which produces a first hydrogen stream;  a second apparatus for producing hydrogen from a hydrocarbon by steam reforming,  partial oxidation or dehydrogenation,  which produces a second hydrogen stream;  a hydrogen conduit or a hydrogen consumer to which both the first hydrogen stream and the second hydrogen stream are fed;  and a control device which matches the production of hydrogen in the first apparatus and in the second apparatus in such a way that the total amount of first hydrogen stream and second hydrogen stream corresponds to a predetermined value,  excess electric energy can be efficiently utilized by operating the apparatus for the electrochemical or electrothermal production of hydrogen with excess electric energy.', p.application_date = '2014-05-20 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US20160136608A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/24', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WOCN14001024'}) SET p.application_no = 'WOCN14001024', p.title_cn = '一种控温式硫化氢连续分解制取氢气的装置', p.title_en = 'TEMPERATURE-CONTROLLED APPARATUS FOR HYDROGEN PRODUCTION BY CONTINUOUS DECOMPOSITION OF HYDROGEN SULFIDE', p.abstract_cn = '提供一种控温式硫化氢连续分解制取氢气的装置，是一种介质阻挡放电可控温式等离子体发生装置，反应器为同轴套管式结构，反应器筒体采用绝缘介质制成，中心电极为金属，接地极为温度可控的循环液体，通过温度控制，使分解产生的硫分离出来。', p.abstract_en = 'Provided is a temperature-controlled apparatus for hydrogen production by continuous decomposition of hydrogen sulfide,  the apparatus is a temperature-controlled dielectric barrier discharge plasma generating apparatus. A reactor is of a coaxial sleeve structure. The cylinder body of the reactor is made of an insulating medium. A central electrode is formed by metal,  and a grounding electrode is formed by a temperature-controllable circulating liquid. The sulfur produced by decomposition is separated by controlling temperature.', p.application_date = '2014-11-15 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016074111A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WOEP15075498'}) SET p.application_no = 'WOEP15075498', p.title_cn = '用于制备合成气的方法', p.title_en = 'PROCESS FOR THE PREPARATION OF SYNGAS', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及的方法用于制备合成气包括氢气和一氧化碳的从 含甲烷的气体， 该方法包括步骤 :  (a)使含甲烷的气体与氧化气体在自热重整器得到的热的粗合成气 包含一氧化碳和氢； (b)冷却该热来自步骤(a)得到的粗合成气的合成气， 所述步骤(B)包括冷却热的粗合成气通过间接换热对含甲烷的气体用于 步骤(A)，并且其中加入硫，上游的冷却步骤(b)。 本发明还涉及一种制备烃产品的方法，其中进料制备的合成气 在如上所述，然后通过第二级经一脱硫过程处理和随后合成气转化为烃的脱硫 产品在费-托法。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention is directed to a process for the preparation of a syngas comprising hydrogen and carbon monoxide from a methane comprising gas,  which process comprises the steps of :  (a) reacting the methane comprising gas with an oxidising gas in an autothermal reformer to obtain a hot raw syngas comprising carbon monoxide and hydrogen;  (b) cooling the hot raw syngas resulting from step (a) to obtain the syngas,  wherein step (b) comprises cooling the hot raw syngas by indirect heat exchange against the methane comprising gas used in step (a) and wherein sulphur is added upstream of cooling step (b). The invention also relates to a process for the preparation of hydrocarbon products in which a feed syngas is prepared in the process as described above followed by a desulphurisation treatment and the desulphurised syngas is subsequently converted into hydrocarbon products in a Fischer-Tropsch process.', p.application_date = '2015-11-03 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016074976A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201180033416.8'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201180033416.8', p.title_cn = '用于生产氨合成气的工艺', p.title_en = 'For the production of ammonia synthesis gas', p.abstract_cn = '一种用于从含烃的原料生产氨合成气的方法，包括如下步骤：初级重整，用氧化剂流次级重整，以及进一步处理所述合成气，包括转化、除去二氧化碳和甲烷化，其中使由次级重整输送的合成气在200-350℃的温度经历中温变换(MTS)，并且初级重整以低于2的水蒸气-碳比率运行。公开了相应的用于改造合成氨设备的方法，其中现有的HTS反应器被改变以在中温下运行，或者被新的MTS反应器代替，并且在所述初级重整器中的水蒸气-碳比率被降低为1.5-2范围内的值，这样就降低了通过前端装置的流速中的惰性流。', p.abstract_en = 'A process for producing ammonia synthesis gas from a hydrocarbon-containing feedstock,  with steps of primary reforming,  secondary reforming with an oxidant stream,  and further treatment of the synthesis gas including shift,  removal of carbon dioxide and methanation,  wherein the synthesis gas delivered by secondary reforming is subject to a medium-temperature shift (MTS) at a temperature between 200 and 350 °C,  and primary reforming is operated with a steam-to-carbon ratio lower than 2. A corresponding method for revamping an ammonia plant is disclosed,  where an existing HTS reactor is modified to operate at medium temperature,  or replaced with a new MTS reactor,  and the steam-to-carbon ratio in the primary reformer is lowered to a value in the range 1-5 €• 2,  thus reducing inert steam in the flow rate trough the equipments of the front-end.', p.application_date = '2011-05-12 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN102971251B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201210150383.1'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201210150383.1', p.title_cn = '异丁烷脱氢反应气的氢气分离方法', p.title_en = 'Isobutane dehydrogenation reaction of the hydrogen gas separation method', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种异丁烷脱氢反应气的氢气分离方法，主要解决现有技术中循环氢气纯度低造成异丁烷脱氢反应异丁烯选择性低、催化剂再生周期短，同时设备投资和能耗高的问题。本发明采用将异丁烷脱氢反应气体在压力为0.5～1.5MPa，温度为0～45℃条件下进行气液分离，分离后的气相含有氢气和异丁烷、异丁烯等烃类，该气相经采用至少一种吸附剂的变压吸附装置，在高压下吸附烃类、在低压下解吸再生而实现对混合气体中氢气组分的分离和提纯，分离得到高纯度氢气，部分返回反应系统，其他氢气送至界外的技术方案，较好地解决了该问题，可用于异丁烷脱氢制异丁烯的工业生产。', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention relates to a hydrogen gas separation method for isobutane dehydrogenation reaction gas,  wherein problems of low isobutene selectivity and short catalyst regeneration period in a isobutane dehydrogenation reaction due to low circulation hydrogen gas purity,  high equipment investment and high energy consumption in the prior art are mainly solved with the present invention. The technical scheme comprises that :  isobutane dehydrogenation reaction gas is subjected to gas-liquid separation at a temperature of 0-45 DEG C under a pressure of 0.5-1.5 MPa,  the separated gas phase contains hydrogen gas,  isobutane,  isobutene and other hydrocarbons,  the hydrocarbons in the gas phase are absorbed under a high pressure through a variable pressure absorption device adopting at least an absorption agent,  separation and purification on the hydrogen gas component in the mixing gas are achieved through absorbing the hydrocarbons under the high pressure and carrying out desorption regeneration under the low pressure,  the high purity hydrogen gas is obtained through separation,  the partial hydrogen gas returns to the reaction system,  and the other hydrogen gas is conveyed to the outside. With the technical scheme,  the problems in the prior art are well solved,  and the hydrogen gas separation method can be used for industrial production of isobutene preparation through isobutane dehydrogenation.', p.application_date = '2012-05-16 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN103420338B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/56', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201410823022.8'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201410823022.8', p.title_cn = '带余热回收功能的自热型重整制氢微反应器', p.title_en = 'With heat recovery function system hydrogen microself-heating reforming reactor', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种带余热回收功能的自热型重整制氢微反应器。上至下依次包括绝热腔盖板、重整制氢微反应模块和绝热外壳，重整制氢微反应模块安装在绝热外壳中，重整制氢微反应模块从上至下依次由上盖板组件，蒸发单元，预热单元，催化燃烧组件，重整反应制氢组件，温差发电组件和下盖板组件组成。本发明集成了温差发电模块，具有对反应器出口气体的余热回收发电功能。重整制氢反应与催化燃烧反应的高温产物气体将热量传递至温差发电器热端，与暴露在空气中的冷端形成较大温差，从而将温度差转发为电能。该电能采用蓄电池收集储存，可用于制氢反应器的控制系统或其它功能模块的供电，整体能量利用率高，在保证制氢效率的同时又实现节能环保。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention discloses an auto-thermal hydrogen-production-by-reforming micro-reactor with a waste heat recovery function. The micro-reactor comprises a heat insulation cavity cover plate,  a hydrogen-production-by-reforming micro-reaction module and a heat insulation housing from top to bottom sequentially,  wherein the hydrogen-production-by-reforming micro-reaction module is mounted in the heat insulation housing and comprises an upper cover plate assembly,  a steaming unit,  a preheating unit,  a catalytic combustion assembly,  a hydrogen-production-by-reforming assembly,  a temperature difference power generation assembly and a lower cover plate assembly from top to bottom sequentially. The micro-reactor integrates the temperature difference power generation module and has the functions of recovering waste heat of outlet gas of the reactor and generating power. High-temperature product gas in hydrogen-production-by-reforming reaction and catalytic combustion reaction transfers heat to a heat end of a temperature difference power generator,  and the temperature of the heat end and the temperature of a cold end exposed in air form a relatively large temperature difference,  so that the temperature difference is converted into electric energy. The electric energy is collected and stored by a storage battery and can be used for supplying power to a control system or other function modules of the hydrogen production reactor,  the overall energy utilization rate is high,  and energy conservation and environmental protection are achieved while the hydrogen production efficiency is guaranteed.', p.application_date = '2014-12-25 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN104555920B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/32', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201480054831.5'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201480054831.5', p.title_cn = '在绝热金属反应器中氢化CO2的方法', p.title_en = 'Method for hydrogenation of co2 in adiabatic metal reactors', p.abstract_cn = '在一个实施方式中：在金属反应器中制造合成气的方法可以包括在催化剂存在下将二氧化碳和氢引入至所述金属反应器以形成合成气，其中，所述金属反应器包含镍，并且其中，所述二氧化碳和氢与所述金属反应器的壁物理接触；并且用含硫的化合物钝化所述镍。', p.abstract_en = 'In an embodiment :  a method of making syngas in a metal reactor can comprise introducing carbon dioxide and hydrogen to the metal reactor in the presence of a catalyst to form the syngas,  wherein the metal reactor comprises nickel and wherein the carbon dioxide and the hydrogen are in physical contact with a wall of the metal reactor;  and passivating the nickel with a sulfur containing compound.', p.application_date = '2014-11-06 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105593160A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/16', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201520997582.5'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201520997582.5', p.title_cn = '一种制氢装置', p.title_en = 'Hydrogen production device', p.abstract_cn = '本实用新型属于氢能源技术领域，具体涉及一种等离子体分解水的制氢装置，包括高频高压发生装置及导电容器，导电容器与高频高压发生装置的负极电连接作为阴极装置，导电容器内设置有阳极装置，导电容器内设置有介质隔离装置，在介质隔离装置与导电容器内壁之间形成电离空间，所述导电容器电连接有接地装置。可实现大地中的电子通过接地装置的传递能够进入电离空间中被氢离子吸收，以实现能量向高品位转移，即将氢离子转化为氢气，作为能源使用，而大地中的电子是取之不尽用之不竭，充分提升了自然资源的利用率。', p.abstract_en = 'The utility model belongs to the technical field of the hydrogen energy source,  the hydrogen production device of a concretely relates to plasma decomposition water,  including high frequency and high voltage generating device and electrically conductive container,  electrically conductive container is connected as the negative pole device with high frequency and high voltage generating device\'s negative electricity,  is provided with anode device in the electrically conductive container,  is provided with medium isolating device in the electrically conductive container,  forms the ionization space between medium isolating device and electrically conductive container inner wall,  electrically conductive container electricity is connected with earthing device. Can realize transmission that electron in the earth passes through earthing device is absorbed by the hydrogen ion in can getting into the ionization space to realize that the energy shifts to the high -grade,  be about to the hydrogen ion and turn into hydrogen that as energy use,  and the electron in the earth inexhaustible,  has fully promoted natural resources\'s utilization ratio.', p.application_date = '2015-12-03 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN205241231U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201521033625.4'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201521033625.4', p.title_cn = '一种氢氧分离产生能源系统', p.title_en = 'Oxyhydrogen separation produces energy system', p.abstract_cn = '本实用新型涉及新型能源领域，尤其涉及一种氢氧分离产生能源系统，其包括补水槽；所述补水槽连接多个反应器；多个反应器顶部连通集气筒，底部连通沉淀槽；所述集气筒依次连通过滤槽，缓冲罐以及暂存罐；其中每一所述反应器内设有反应棒，所述反应棒上设有金属触媒反应物，所述金属触媒反应物是由多种不同金属触媒制备而成。本系统中的金属触媒反应物可以在反应器中诱发水和氢氧分离反应产生所需的清洁能源，可以减少对传统化石能源的依赖，并让能源使用对环境的危害与污染大幅降低，故对能源产业和环境生态的和谐发展具有重要的意义，该系统占地面积较小、原料易得、操作安全、成本低，适合大规模推广利用。', p.abstract_en = 'The utility model relates to a novel energy field especially relates to an oxyhydrogen separation produces energy system,  and it includes the moisturizing groove,  a plurality of reactors are connected in the moisturizing groove,  a plurality of reactor tops connected set inflator,  bottom intercommunication precipitation tank,  the gas cylinder communicates filter -tank,  the buffer tank and the jar of keeping in in proper order,  wherein each reactor is equipped with the reaction stick,  be equipped with metal catalyst reaction thing on the reaction stick,  metal catalyst reaction thing is prepared from multiple different metal catalyst. Metal catalyst reaction thing in this system can bring out water and the required clean energy of oxyhydrogen cracking reaction production in the reactor,  can reduce the reliance to traditional fossil energy to letting the energy use and reducing with polluting the harm of environment by a wide margin,  the event has important meaning to energy industry and environment ecology\'s harmonious development,  and the area of this system is less,  the raw materials is easy,  it is safe,  with low costs to operate,  suitable extensive extend use.', p.application_date = '2015-12-11 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN205241232U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/08', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'EP13807413'}) SET p.application_no = 'EP13807413', p.title_cn = '氢发生装置', p.title_en = 'HYDROGEN GENERATING DEVICE', p.abstract_cn = '一种氢气发生装置设置在待生成氢的量允许控制。 该装置包括 :  氢生成容器(1)设有镁基氢化物容纳部分，容纳镁基氢化物； 反应水箱3储存水或水溶液； 所述管4a和4b连接到反应水箱3和氢气发生容器1； 泵5的操作，以便吸水或水溶液从反应水箱3和 排出通过管道4a和4b到氢气发生容器1； 压力表18测量的内部中的压力的氢气发生容器1； 和控制单元9， 在基于压力值的压力表18， 控制量的引起流动的水通过管道由泵5。', p.abstract_en = 'A hydrogen generation apparatus is provided in which the amount of hydrogen to be generated is allowed to be controlled. The apparatus includes :  a hydrogen generation container 1 provided with a magnesium-based hydride accommodation part accommodating magnesium-based hydride;  a reaction water tank 3 storing water or the aqueous solution;  the pipes 4a and 4b connected to the reaction water tank 3 and the hydrogen generation container 1;  a pump 5 operating such as to suction water or the aqueous solution from the reaction water tank 3 and then exhaust it through the pipes 4a and 4b to the hydrogen generation container 1;  a pressure gauge 18 measuring the pressure in the inside of the hydrogen generation container 1;  and a control unit 9,  on the basis of the pressure value of the pressure gauge 18,  controlling the amount of water caused to flow through the pipes by the pump 5.', p.application_date = '2013-05-29 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'EP2862838A4', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/06', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2014547762'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2014547762', p.title_cn = '方法和装置用于转化一氧化碳为二氧化碳', p.title_en = 'Method and device for conversion of carbon monoxide to carbon dioxide', p.abstract_cn = '用于产生合成气的方法和装置描述了使用烃类和水。在另外的实施例中的方法和装置，具有任何所需的CO合成气/氢比例和/或合成的官能化和/或非官能化烃产生。用这种方法，含烃流体可具有可变转换为合成气的氢含量而不产生显著量的CO2。此外，氢气和不同形式的碳可以获得作为副产物。', p.abstract_en = 'A process and an apparatus for converting carbon dioxide CO2 into carbon monoxide CO using hydrocarbons are described. In further embodiments,  processes and apparatuses for generating synthesis gas and processes and apparatuses for converting synthesis gas into synthetic functionalised and/or non-functionalised hydrocarbons using CO2 and hydrocarbons are described. The processes and apparatuses are adapted to convert CO2 emitted by industrial processes,  and thus the amount of carbon dioxide emitted into the atmosphere may be reduced.', p.application_date = '2012-12-20 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP5919393B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/26', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2012073980'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2012073980', p.title_cn = '生产氢气的方法', p.title_en = 'The method of producing hydrogen', p.abstract_cn = '本发明的一个目的是提供一种制备氢气的方法，该方法能够简单地制备氢气，该氢气是清洁能源，而不使用背景技术中使用的氨，并且安全性非常高。 本发明的氢气制备方法的特征在于，通过将镁橄榄石(Ca12Al14O33)和氢氧化钙[Ca(OH)2]引入水中并使它们与水反应来产生氢气。 这里，优选水的温度为50-100℃，镁橄榄石与氢氧化钙的摩尔比为1/9。', p.abstract_en = 'One object of the present invention is to provide a method for preparing hydrogen which is able to simply produce hydrogen which is clean energy without using ammonia as used in the background art and which is very high in safety. The method for preparing hydrogen of the present invention is characterized in that hydrogen is generated by introducing mayenite (Ca 12 Al 14 O 33 ) and calcium hydroxide [Ca(OH) 2 ] into water and allowing them to react with water. Here,  it is preferable that a temperature of water is from 50 to 100°C,  and a molar ratio of mayenite to calcium hydroxide is 1/9.', p.application_date = '2012-03-28 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP5920822B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/06', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2012073988'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2012073988', p.title_cn = '氢气的连续生产', p.title_en = 'Continued production of hydrogen', p.abstract_cn = '本发明提供一种氢的连续制造方法，其不使用背景技术中所述的氨，能够简单且连续地制造作为清洁能源的氢，并且具有非常高的安全性。 本发明涉及一种连续制氢方法，包括将镁橄榄石(Ca[12]Al[14]O[3])和氢氧化钙(Ca(OH)[2])引入水中并与水反应的制氢步骤， 从而产生氢气，并形成锂皂石[Ca[3]Al[2](OH)[12]； 再生步骤，包括焙烧所形成的钾长石以再生镁长石和氢氧化钙； 以及循环步骤，包括将再生的镁橄榄石和氢氧化钙返回到氢气生产步骤中。 优选在制氢步骤中的水温为50-100℃，镁橄榄石与氢氧化钙的摩尔比为1/9。 另外，优选的是，在再生步骤中，锂蒙脱石的焙烧温度为300-500℃。', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention provides a continuous production method of hydrogen which is able to produce hydrogen,  which is clean energy,  simply and continuously without using ammonia as stated in BACKGROUND ART and which has a very high level of safety. The invention of the continuous production method of hydrogen includes a hydrogen production step comprising introducing mayenite (Ca 12 Al 14 O 33 ) and calcium hydroxide [Ca(OH) 2 ] into water and allowing them to react with water,  thereby generating hydrogen and also forming katoite [Ca 3 Al 2  (OH) 12 ];  a regeneration step comprising baking the formed katoite to regenerate mayenite and calcium hydroxide;  and a circulation step comprising returning the regenerated mayenite and calcium hydroxide into the hydrogen production step. It is preferable that a temperature of water in the hydrogen production step is from 50 to 100°C,  and a molar ratio of mayenite to calcium hydroxide is 1/9. In addition,  it is preferable that a baking temperature of katoite in the regeneration step is from 300 to 500°C.', p.application_date = '2012-03-28 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP5920823B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'BRPI112012019778'}) SET p.application_no = 'BRPI112012019778', p.title_cn = '制氢装置及制氢方法', p.title_en = 'hydrogen producing device and method for producing hydrogen', p.abstract_cn = '本发明提供一种光利用效率高，不降低氢生成速度，能够高效地生成氢的氢生成装置。 根据本发明的制氢装置包括：具有光接收表面和背面的光电转换部分； 设置在背面上的第一气体发生部和第二气体发生部， 其中第一气体产生部分和第二气体产生部分之一是氢产生部分，用于从电解液中产生氢气， 另一个是由电解液生成O2的氧生成部， 第一气体发生部和第二气体发生部中的至少一个为多个， 光电转换部分电连接到第一气体发生部分和第二气体发生部分，使得由光电转换部分的光接收产生的电动势被提供给第一气体发生部分和第二气体发生部分。', p.abstract_en = 'There is provided a hydrogen production device which is high in the light use efficiency and can produce hydrogen with high efficiency without decreasing the hydrogen generation rate. The hydrogen production device according to the present invention comprises :  a photoelectric conversion part having a light acceptance surface and a back surface;  a first gas generation part and a second gas generation part provided on the back surface,  wherein one of the first gas generation part and the second gas generation part is a hydrogen generation part to generate H 2 from an electrolytic solution,  and the other thereof is an oxygen generation part to generate O 2 from the electrolytic solution,  and at least one of the first gas generation part and the second gas generation part is plural,  and the photoelectric conversion part is electrically connected to the first gas generation part and the second gas generation part so that an electromotive force generated by a light acceptance of the photoelectric conversion part is supplied to the first gas generation part and the second gas generation part.', p.application_date = '2010-12-20 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'BR112012019778A2', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'BRPI112012023041'}) SET p.application_no = 'BRPI112012023041', p.title_cn = '生产氢的方法', p.title_en = 'process for producing hydrogen', p.abstract_cn = '描述了一种制备氢气的方法，包括制备包含5wt%～15wt%的含水进料流。 乙醇通过生物质发酵过程； 从原料流中分离至少一部分水，使得所得重整器原料流中乙醇的浓度在15%-35%重量的范围内； 和使重整器进料流与重整器中的催化剂在重整条件下接触，以生产包含氢气的重整器产物流，其中重整器中的压力在100psi至600psi的范围内。', p.abstract_en = 'A process is described for producing hydrogen comprising producing an aqueous feed stream comprising 5% to 15% wt. ethanol by a biomass fermentation process;  separating at least a portion of the water from the feed stream so that the concentration of ethanol in the resulting reformer feed stream is in the range of from 15% to 35% wt.;  and contacting the reformer feed stream with a catalyst in a reformer under reforming conditions to produce a reformer product stream comprising hydrogen wherein the pressure in the reformer is in a range of from 100 psi to 600 psi.', p.application_date = '2011-03-14 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'BR112012023041A2', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/32', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'BRPI112012023048'}) SET p.application_no = 'BRPI112012023048', p.title_cn = '生产氢的方法', p.title_en = 'process for producing hydrogen', p.abstract_cn = '描述了一种制备氢气的方法，包括制备包含5wt%～15wt%的含水进料流。 乙醇通过生物质发酵过程； 和使重整器进料流与烃流和催化剂在重整器中在重整条件下接触，以生产包含氢的重整器产物流。', p.abstract_en = 'A process is described for producing hydrogen comprising producing an aqueous feed stream comprising 5% to 15% wt. ethanol by a biomass fermentation process;  and contacting the reformer feed stream with a hydrocarbon stream and a catalyst in a reformer under reforming conditions to produce a reformer product stream comprising hydrogen.', p.application_date = '2011-03-14 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'BR112012023048A2', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/32', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'BRPI112012023251'}) SET p.application_no = 'BRPI112012023251', p.title_cn = '产生电动势(MBS)和热能的电化学能量系统', p.title_en = 'electrochemical energy system that generates electromotive force (MBS) and thermal energy', p.abstract_cn = '产生电动势(MBS)和热能的电化学能量系统提供一种电化学能量系统， 它从氢的催化反应产生电动势(MBS)到低功率状态(hidino)，提供从反应hidino释放的能量直接转换成电，该系统包括至少两种选自催化剂或催化剂源的组分； 原子氢或氢原子源； 形成催化剂或原子氢源或原子氢源的试剂，和引发原子氢催化的一种或多种试剂。 形成hidinos和电的电化学能量系统还可以包括包含阴极壳体的阴极，包含阳极的壳体阳极，任选的掩埋盐，在具有电子流分离和质量离子迁移的电池运行期间构成hidino试剂的试剂，以及hidrgenio源。 由于半反应电池氧化-还原，反应混合物构成为产生电子通过外电路的Hidrino迁移和面团通过诸如电解质的单独路径的离子迁移，以完成电路。 一种电源和进一步提供的氢化物反应器，其供给能量系统，所述能量系统包括(ii)用于催化原子氢形成氢离子的反应池，(iii)包含至少两种选自以下的组分的化学燃料混合物：催化剂源或催化剂； 氢源或氢原子源，形成催化剂源或催化剂的反应物是原子氢源或氢原子； 一种或多种引发原子氢催化的试剂； 和使催化，(v)热系统和反向交换反应从反应产物中热再生燃料的载体，(ir)接受产生能量(伏特)的热的散热器和功率转换系统。', p.abstract_en = 'electrochemical energy system that generates electromotive force (MBS) and thermal energy a electrochemical energy system is provided,  which generates electromotive force (MBS) from the catalytic reaction of hydrogen to lower power status (hidrino) providing the direct conversion of the energy released from the reaction hidrino into electricity,  the system comprising at least two components chosen from :  a catalyst or a catalyst source;  atomic hydrogen or a source of hydrogen atomic;  reagents to form the catalyst or the source and atomic hydrogen or source of atomic hydrogen,  and one or more reagents to initiate catalysis of atomic hydrogen. the electrochemical energy system to form hidrinos and electricity may further comprise a cathode comprising a cathode housing,  a housing anode comprising an anode,  a buried salt optionally,  reagents constituting hidrino reagents during cell run with electron flow separate and ionic transport of mass,  and a source of hidrôgenio. due to half-reactions cell oxidation-reduction,  the reaction mixture is constituted with producing hidrino migration of electrons through an external circuit and ionic transport of dough through a separate route,  such as the electrolyte,  to complete an electrical circuit. a power supply and is further provided hydride reactor,  that feeds a energy system comprising (II) a reaction cell for the catalysis of atomic hydrogen to form hidrinos,  (III) a mixture of chemical fuel comprising at least two components chosen from :  a source of catalyst or catalyst;  a source of hydrogen or hydrogen atomic atomic,  reactants to form the source of catalyst or the catalyst is an atomic hydrogen source or hydrogen atomic;  one or more reagents to initiate catalysis of atomic hydrogen;  and a support to allow catalysis,  (V) thermal systems and reverse exchange reaction to regenerate the fuel thermally from the reaction products,  (IR) a heat sink that accepts the heat of making nergia,  (volts) and a powe', p.application_date = '2011-03-17 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'BR112012023251A2', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'BRPI112013000704'}) SET p.application_no = 'BRPI112013000704', p.title_cn = '包括剧烈塑性变形操作的储氢材料的制备方法', p.title_en = 'process for preparing a hydrogen storage material comprising a severe plastic deformation operation', p.abstract_cn = '一种用于储存氢气的材料，其通过包括选自冷轧的极端塑性变形操作的方法制备， 对选自金属和包含所述金属的合金的金属材料进行快速锻造和挤压弯曲， 或一种包含选自金属和包含所述金属的合金的金属材料的化合物，所述金属的氢化物或所述合金的氢化物已被加入到所述化合物中。 当对金属材料进行极端塑性变形操作时，随后向金属材料中添加所述金属的氢化物或所述合金的氢化物的操作，以及分散操作。', p.abstract_en = 'A material for storing hydrogen is prepared by a method including an extreme plastic deformation operation selected from cold-rolling,  quick-forging and extrusion-bending performed on a metallic material selected from among a metal and an alloy containing said metal,  or on a compound containing a metal material selected from among a metal and an alloy containing said metal and to which a hydride of said metal or a hydride of said alloy has been added. When the extreme plastic deformation operation is carried out on the metallic material,  it is followed by an operation of adding,  to the metal material,  a hydride of said metal or a hydride of said alloy,  as well as by a dispersing operation.', p.application_date = '2011-07-11 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'BR112013000704A2', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'BRPI112013001141'}) SET p.application_no = 'BRPI112013001141', p.title_cn = '光催化分水器', p.title_en = 'dividing photocatalytic water', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种用于光催化水裂解的方法和一种用于实施所述方法的装置。 本发明的方法包括：用光照射析氧光催化剂氧化水，在析氧光催化剂的导带中产生电子，在析氧光催化剂的价带中产生空穴； 通过用光照射用析氢光催化剂还原水，导致在析氢光催化剂的导带中产生电子和在析氢光催化剂的价带中产生空穴； 其中所述析氧光催化剂与导电隔板层的第一面接触，所述析氢光催化剂与所述导电隔板层的第二面接触， 并且其中来自光激发的析氧光催化剂的导带的电子通过电荷转移穿过导电隔离层与来自光激发的析氢光催化剂的价带的空穴重组。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention is directed to a method for photocatalytic water splitting,  and to an apparatus for carrying out said method. The method of the invention comprises - oxidising water with an oxygen evolution photocatalyst by irradiation with light,  causing an electron to be generated in the conduction band of the oxygen evolution photocatalyst and a hole to be generated in the valence band of the oxygen evolution photocatalyst;  - reducing water with a hydrogen evolution photocatalyst by irradiation with light,  causing an electron to be generated in the conduction band of the hydrogen evolution photocatalyst and a hole to be generated in the valence band of the hydrogen evolution photocatalyst;  wherein said oxygen evolution photocatalyst is in contact with a first side of an electrically conductive separator layer and said hydrogen evolution photocatalyst is in contact with a second side of said electrically conductive separator layer,  and wherein the electron from the conduction band of the photo-excited oxygen evolution photocatalyst recombines with the hole from the valence band of the photo-excited hydrogen evolution photocatalyst via charge transfer through the electrically conductive separator layer.', p.application_date = '2011-07-15 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'BR112013001141A2', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'BR112012021858'}) SET p.application_no = 'BR112012021858', p.title_cn = '以储存和运输为目的的制氢方法', p.title_en = 'METHOD FOR THE HYDROGEN PRODUCTION AIMING AT STORAGE AND TRANSPORT', p.abstract_cn = '本发明提供一种以贮运为目的的氢气的制造方法，通过该方法，能够以低成本高效地工业化地制造顺利进行有机化学氢化物法所必需的贮运用氢气。 该方法是一种以有机化学氢化物法储存和运输为目的的制氢方法， 其中：芳香族化合物的加氢方法使用通过重整反应产生的反应气体作为芳香族化合物反应的氢源，并通过转移反应将氢浓度调节为30-70体积%； 从氢化过程中得到的反应混合物中分离氢化芳族化合物，然后纯化。', p.abstract_en = 'Provided is a method for producing hydrogen aimed at storage and transportation,  by which hydrogen for storage and transportation that is necessary for smoothly performing an organic chemical hydride method can be industrially produced efficiently at low cost. The method is a method for producing hydrogen aimed at storage and transportation in an organic chemical hydride method,  in which :  the hydrogenation process of an aromatic compound uses,  as a hydrogen source for the reaction of the aromatic compound,  a reaction gas is produced by a reforming reaction and adjusted a hydrogen concentration from 30 to 70 vol % by a shift reaction;  and a hydrogenated aromatic compound is separated from a reaction mixture obtained in the hydrogenation process,  which is followed by purification.', p.application_date = '2011-03-24 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'BRPI1221858A2', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'BR112012023048'}) SET p.application_no = 'BR112012023048', p.title_cn = '生产氢的方法', p.title_en = 'PROCESS TO PRODUCE HYDROGEN', p.abstract_cn = '描述了一种制备氢气的方法，包括制备包含5wt%～15wt%的含水进料流。 乙醇通过生物质发酵过程； 和使重整器进料流与烃流和催化剂在重整器中在重整条件下接触，以生产包含氢的重整器产物流。', p.abstract_en = 'A process is described for producing hydrogen comprising producing an aqueous feed stream comprising 5% to 15% wt. ethanol by a biomass fermentation process;  and contacting the reformer feed stream with a hydrocarbon stream and a catalyst in a reformer under reforming conditions to produce a reformer product stream comprising hydrogen.', p.application_date = '2011-03-14 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'BRPI1223048A2', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/32', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'BR112013000704'}) SET p.application_no = 'BR112013000704', p.title_cn = '理解严重塑性变形操作的储氢材料的制备方法', p.title_en = 'PROCESS OF PREPARATION OF A MATERIAL OF HYDROGEN STOCKAGE THAT UNDERSTANDS AN OPERATION OF SEVERE PLASTIC DEFORMATION', p.abstract_cn = '一种用于储存氢气的材料，其通过包括选自冷轧的极端塑性变形操作的方法制备， 对选自金属和包含所述金属的合金的金属材料进行快速锻造和挤压弯曲， 或一种包含选自金属和包含所述金属的合金的金属材料的化合物，所述金属的氢化物或所述合金的氢化物已被加入到所述化合物中。 当对金属材料进行极端塑性变形操作时，随后向金属材料中添加所述金属的氢化物或所述合金的氢化物的操作，以及分散操作。', p.abstract_en = 'A material for storing hydrogen is prepared by a method including an extreme plastic deformation operation selected from cold-rolling,  quick-forging and extrusion-bending performed on a metallic material selected from among a metal and an alloy containing said metal,  or on a compound containing a metal material selected from among a metal and an alloy containing said metal and to which a hydride of said metal or a hydride of said alloy has been added. When the extreme plastic deformation operation is carried out on the metallic material,  it is followed by an operation of adding,  to the metal material,  a hydride of said metal or a hydride of said alloy,  as well as by a dispersing operation.', p.application_date = '2011-07-11 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'BRPI1300704A2', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'BR112013001141'}) SET p.application_no = 'BR112013001141', p.title_cn = '分水脚板', p.title_en = 'WATER DIVISION FOTOCATALÍTICA', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种用于光催化水裂解的方法和一种用于实施所述方法的装置。 本发明的方法包括：用光照射析氧光催化剂氧化水，在析氧光催化剂的导带中产生电子，在析氧光催化剂的价带中产生空穴； 通过用光照射用析氢光催化剂还原水，导致在析氢光催化剂的导带中产生电子和在析氢光催化剂的价带中产生空穴； 其中所述析氧光催化剂与导电隔板层的第一面接触，所述析氢光催化剂与所述导电隔板层的第二面接触， 并且其中来自光激发的析氧光催化剂的导带的电子通过电荷转移穿过导电隔离层与来自光激发的析氢光催化剂的价带的空穴重组。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention is directed to a method for photocatalytic water splitting,  and to an apparatus for carrying out said method. The method of the invention comprises - oxidising water with an oxygen evolution photocatalyst by irradiation with light,  causing an electron to be generated in the conduction band of the oxygen evolution photocatalyst and a hole to be generated in the valence band of the oxygen evolution photocatalyst;  - reducing water with a hydrogen evolution photocatalyst by irradiation with light,  causing an electron to be generated in the conduction band of the hydrogen evolution photocatalyst and a hole to be generated in the valence band of the hydrogen evolution photocatalyst;  wherein said oxygen evolution photocatalyst is in contact with a first side of an electrically conductive separator layer and said hydrogen evolution photocatalyst is in contact with a second side of said electrically conductive separator layer,  and wherein the electron from the conduction band of the photo-excited oxygen evolution photocatalyst recombines with the hole from the valence band of the photo-excited hydrogen evolution photocatalyst via charge transfer through the electrically conductive separator layer.', p.application_date = '2011-07-15 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'BRPI1301141A2', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CA2753619'}) SET p.application_no = 'CA2753619', p.title_cn = '制备超高温氢分子的方法和使用该方法选择性地断裂在衬底表面上或衬底表面上的分子的C-H和/或SI-H键', p.title_en = 'METHOD FOR PRODUCING HYPERTHERMAL HYDROGEN MOLECULES AND USING SAME FOR SELECTIVELY BREAKING C-H AND/OR SI-H BONDS OF MOLECULES AT OR ON SUBSTRATE SURFACES', p.abstract_cn = '一种生产超高温分子氢的方法及其用于选择性地破坏C-H或Si-H键而不破坏其它键的用途。维持氢等离子体，并用电场提取质子，以将它们加速到适当的动能。质子进入漂移区与气相中的分子氢碰撞。碰撞级联产生高通量的超高温分子氢，其通量比从氢等离子体中提取的质子通量大许多倍。当这种产生高通量的超高温分子氢的方法被用于轰击基底上具有所需化学官能度的有机前体分子(或硅酮或硅烷分子)时，由于从超高温氢射弹到前体分子中的氢原子的能量沉积的运动学选择性，C-H或Si-H键因此优先裂解。', p.abstract_en = 'A method for producing hyperthermal molecular hydrogen and use of same for selectively breaking C-H or Si-H bonds without breaking other bonds. A hydrogen plasma is maintained and protons are extracted with an electric field to accelerate them to an appropriate kinetic energy. The protons enter into a drift zone to collide with molecular hydrogen in gas phase. The cascades of collisions produce a high flux of hyperthermal molecular hydrogen with a flux many times larger than the flux of protons extracted from the hydrogen plasma. When this method of generating a high flux of hyperthermal molecular hydrogen is applied to bombard organic precursor molecules (or silicone,  or silane molecules) with desirablechemical functionality/functionalities on a substrate,  the C-H or Si-H bonds are thus cleaved preferentially due to the kinematic selectivity of energy deposition from the hyperthermal hydrogen projectiles to the hydrogen atoms in the precursor molecules.', p.application_date = '2010-03-03 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CA2753619C', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14124365'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14124365', p.title_cn = '富甲烷气体二氧化碳重整制氢耐硫催化剂', p.title_en = 'Sulfur tolerant catalysts for hydrogen production by carbon dioxide reforming of methane-rich gas', p.abstract_cn = '本申请描述了一种适用于抗硫中毒的富甲烷气体如沼气的CO2重整的催化剂。 所述催化剂包含约5wt%至约20wt%的Ni和0wt%至约10wt%的Co，所述Co负载在具有下式的载体上 : (a)Al2O3； (b)M1AOB-Al2O3； (c)M1AOB-ZrO2-Al2O3，其中M1AOB为CaO或MgO。', p.abstract_en = 'The present application describes a catalyst that is suitable for the CO2 reforming of methane-rich gases,  such as biogas,  that is resistant to poisoning by sulfur. The catalyst comprises from about 5 wt % to about 20 wt % Ni and 0 wt % to about 10 wt % Co supported on a support having a formula selected from :  (a) Al2O3;  (b) M1aOb—Al2O3;  and (c) M1aOb—ZrO2—Al2O3,  where M1aOb is either CaO or MgO.', p.application_date = '2012-05-29 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9339797B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/26', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 2, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14552084'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14552084', p.title_cn = '燃料电池供氢系统原料再生方法', p.title_en = 'Regeneration method of raw materials for hydrogen supply system of fuel cell', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种燃料电池供氢系统的原料再生方法及相关系统。 该方法包括在燃料电池的供氢系统中使铝和金属氢氧化物反应以产生氢； 以及回收在反应中与氢同时产生的铝化合物。 从铝化合物中获得氢氧化铝。 对氢氧化铝进行热处理，得到氧化铝。 将氧化铝还原成铝。 将得到的铝作为生产氢的原料再供给。', p.abstract_en = 'Disclosed is a method and related system of regenerating a raw material for a hydrogen supply system of a fuel cell. The method includes reacting aluminum and a metal hydroxide to produce hydrogen in the hydrogen supply system of a fuel cell;  and recovering an aluminum compound produced simultaneously with the hydrogen in the reaction. An aluminum hydroxide is obtained from the aluminum compound. The aluminum hydroxide is heat-treated to obtain an aluminum oxide. The aluminum oxide is reduced to obtain aluminum. The obtained aluminum is re-supplied as a raw material for producing the hydrogen.', p.application_date = '2014-11-24 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9340419B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'ATE792240'}) SET p.application_no = 'ATE792240', p.title_cn = '氢生成系统及热水生产系统', p.title_en = 'HYDROGEN GENERATION SYSTEM AND HOT WATER PRODUCTION SYSTEM', p.abstract_cn = '氢气产生系统(2A)包括氢产生部(201)保持第第一液含有水和 : 允许部分的第一液中含有的水分解成氢气和氧气，和至少第一的一部分待加热液体，通过照射太阳光，一种第一热交换器(207)进行冷却的第一液氢中加热生成单元(201)和加热第二之间通过热交换液第一液和第二液，和机构(例如，一种循环管路(204)和泵(205))，其将第一液体第一中冷却热交换器(207)入的氢气产生单元(201)。', p.abstract_en = 'A hydrogen generation system (2A) includes a hydrogen generation unit (201) that holds a first liquid containing water and that allows a part of the water contained in the first liquid to be decomposed into hydrogen and oxygen,  and at least a part of the first liquid to be heated,  by being irradiated with sunlight,  a first heat exchanger (207) that cools the first liquid heated in the hydrogen generation unit (201) and heats the second liquid by heat exchange between the first liquid and the second liquid,  and a mechanism (for example,  a circulation line (204) and a pump (205)) that introduces the first liquid cooled in the first heat exchanger (207) into the hydrogen generation unit (201).', p.application_date = '2010-05-21 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'ATE792240T1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'ATE796743'}) SET p.application_no = 'ATE796743', p.title_cn = '合成气的生产方法和氢气从试剂包含液体烃， 气态烃类和/或含氧化合物，也衍生自生物质，通过非集成膜反应器', p.title_en = 'PROCESS FOR THE PRODUCTION OF SYNGAS AND HYDROGEN STARTING FROM REAGENTS COMPRISING LIQUID HYDROCARBONS,  GASEOUS HYDROCARBONS,  AND/OR OXYGENATED COMPOUNDS,  ALSO DERIVING FROM BIOMASSES,  BY MEANS OF A NON-INTEGRATED MEMBRANE REACTOR', p.abstract_cn = '合成气的生产方法和氢气从液体烃，气态烃和/或含氧化合物，还由衍生自生物质，及其混合物，设想即架构中所使用膜反应器连续反应和分离阶段。该方法包括在一段预加热的试剂，若干段短接触时间的催化部分氧化制造合成气和氢气的数量产生的氢气通过膜阶段以及后续的分离，热回收段，产生的二氧化碳除去部分和部分进行冷却和清除冷凝液。任选地，该方法包括一段获得的氢气通过变压吸附(PSA)净化，并产生净化气体介质热值。此外，所述的试剂和方法包括加氢脱硫段可以包括CO2转化段通过倒水生成氢气和(rwgs)水煤气变换反应。', p.abstract_en = 'A process for the production of syngas and hydrogen starting from liquid hydrocarbons,  gaseous hydrocarbons and/or oxygenated compounds,  also deriving from biomasses,  and mixtures thereof,  envisages recourse to a membrane reactor in an architecture that uses a succession of reaction and separation stages. The process includes a section for pre-heating the reagents,  a number of sections for short-contact-time catalytic partial oxidation for producing syngas and hydrogen in a number of stages followed by separation of hydrogen produced via membranes,  a thermal-recovery section,  a section for removing produced carbon dioxide,  and a section for cooling and removing condensate. Optionally,  the process includes a section for purifying obtained hydrogen via pressure-swing adsorption (PSA) and generating purge gas with medium calorific value. Furthermore,  the process includes a section for hydrodesulphuration of the reagents and could include a section for conversion of the CO2 and H2 produced by a reverse-water-gas-shift (RWGS) reaction.', p.application_date = '2010-11-04 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'ATE796743T1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'IDW00201100615'}) SET p.application_no = 'IDW00201100615', p.title_cn = '制氢系统和发电系统', p.title_en = 'Hydrogen production system and power generation system', p.abstract_cn = '从外部设备供应的高温蒸煮量减少。提供一种制氢系统(1)，其包括反应器(3)，该反应器允许从加湿器(2)中逸出的潮湿过程流体在催化剂存在下发生反应，将过程流体中的一氧化碳转化为二氧化碳；在反应器(3)中发生反应的高温过程流体流经的第二通道(B)，通过的循环通道(C)，加湿器(2)中的多余水在其中循环；以及第一热交换器(7)，设置在循环通道(C)和第二通道(B)的汇合点，用于在反应器(3)内发生反应的高温过程流体与通过循环通道(C)循环的流体之间的热交换。', p.abstract_en = 'The amount of high temperature cook supplied from external equipment is reduced. There is provided a hydrogen production system (1) comprising a reactor (3) which allows wet process fluid escaping from a humidifier (2) to react in the presence of a catalyst to convert carbon monoxide in the process fluid to carbon dioxide;  A second passage (B) through which the high-temperature process fluid reacted in the reactor (3) flows,  a circulation passage (C) through which excess water in the humidifier (2) circulates;  And a first heat exchanger (7) disposed at the confluence of the circulation passage (C) and the second passage (B) for heat exchange between the high-temperature process fluid reacted in the reactor (3) and the fluid circulated through the circulation passage (C).', p.application_date = '2011-02-17 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'IDP000041291B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/14', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'IN1731DELNP2014'}) SET p.application_no = 'IN1731DELNP2014', p.title_cn = '碳质原料的加氢甲烷化', p.title_en = 'HYDROMETHANATION OF A CARBONACEOUS FEEDSTOCK', p.abstract_cn = '本发明一般涉及进行加氢甲烷化碳质原料的加氢甲烷化反应器，甲烷产物蒸汽中和焦化副产物，更具体地涉及去除所述炭产物从加氢甲烷化反应器中。', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention relates generally to processes for hydromethanating a carbonaceous feedstock in a hydromethanation reactor to methane product steam and a char by product and more specifically to removal of the char by product from the hydromethanation reactor.', p.application_date = '2014-03-07 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'IN1731DELNP2014A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'AU2012235888'}) SET p.application_no = 'AU2012235888', p.title_cn = '高压气体处理成液体的方法', p.title_en = 'High pressure gas to liquid process', p.abstract_cn = '本文描述了一种高压气体向GTL(Gas-To-Liquid)工艺。 更具体地， 本发明描述了通过高压力GTL工艺的一次利用多孔催化膜反应器可连接 一种新型的结构化固定床反应器结合强制流动通过的多孔催化结构化催化剂结合 高水平的热转移，其中没有压缩合成气的重整和费-托合成步骤之间。', p.abstract_en = 'There is herein described a high pressure gas to liquid (GTL) process. More particularly,  there is described a once through high pressure GTL process utilising a porous catalytic membrane reactor capable of being connected to a novel structured fixed bed reactor that incorporates forced flow through the porous catalytic structured catalyst in combination with high levels of heat transfer where there is no compression of syngas between reforming and Fischer-Tropsch steps.', p.application_date = '2012-03-30 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'AU2012235888B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/36', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'AU2012342258'}) SET p.application_no = 'AU2012342258', p.title_cn = '油井产物处理', p.title_en = 'Oil well product treatment', p.abstract_cn = '一种植物(10)用于处理流体的产品(12)从油井(14)， 生产烃类产品(42)， 包括一系列的分离器(20， 30，40)在逐渐降低的压力，所述流体制品提供连续。 一种高压力下的气相(21)从分离器中得到的(20)和供给的限流器(54) 从而通过焦耳-汤姆逊效应经历冷却， 然后传递到NGL分离器(55)，以产生天然气液流(56)和气态自然 气体流(58)。 天然气流(58)然后化学处理， 使用合成气生产单元(60)， 和费-托合成单元(66)以产生合成原油(72)。 合成原油(72)供给一个隔板(20)， 和天然气液流(56)提供给另一个的隔板(30)； 压力在一个分离器(20)中的压力大于另一个分离器(30)。', p.abstract_en = 'A plant (10) for treating fluid products (12) obtained from an oil well (14),  to produce a hydrocarbon product (42),  comprises a series of separators (20,  30,  40) at progressively lower pressures,  to which the fluid products are supplied in succession. A high pressure gas phase (21) is obtained from the separator (20) and is supplied to a flow restrictor (54) so as to undergo cooling through the Joule Thomson effect,  and then passed to a NGL separator (55) to produce a natural gas liquid stream (56) and a gaseous natural gas stream (58). The natural gas stream (58) is then processed chemically,  using a synthesis gas production unit (60),  and a Fischer-Tropsch synthesis unit (66) to produce a synthetic crude oil (72). The synthetic crude oil (72) is supplied to one of the separators (20),  and the natural gas liquid stream (56) is supplied to another of the separators (30);  the pressure in the one separator (20) is greater than the pressure in the other separator (30).', p.application_date = '2012-11-15 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'AU2012342258B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/40', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'AU2014346711'}) SET p.application_no = 'AU2014346711', p.title_cn = '液态燃料重整器包括汽化器和燃料重整液体的可再成形的方法', p.title_en = 'Liquid fuel reformer including a vaporizer and method of reforming liquid reformable fuel', p.abstract_cn = '液态燃料重整器(400)包括燃料汽化器(415)，它利用热量的热量从上游源， 具体地， 电加热器(406)， 启动模式中可操作的重整器(400)， 因此独立的重整器的重整反应区，汽化燃料的下游的汽化区域中。', p.abstract_en = 'A liquid fuel reformer (400) includes a fuel vaporizer (415) which utilizes heat from an upstream source of heat,  specifically,  an electric heater (406),  operable in the start-up mode of the reformer (400),  and therefore independent of the reforming reaction zone of the reformer,  to vaporize fuel in a downstream vaporization zone.', p.application_date = '2014-11-06 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'AU2014346711A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/32', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'AU2014346844'}) SET p.application_no = 'AU2014346844', p.title_cn = '化学反应器具有排污歧管的气态反应介质的流量的管理其上', p.title_en = 'Chemical reactor with manifold for management of a flow of gaseous reaction medium thereto', p.abstract_cn = '化学反应器(例如 重整反应器)系统包括歧管(126)，用于管理流的气态反应介质。 歧管(126)包括歧管壳体(128)限定歧管腔室(129)和具有至少一个附加成分，选自 :  气体分布器(127)； 加热器； 和腔内或相邻的具有密封到其上。', p.abstract_en = 'A chemical reactor (e.g. reformer reactor) system includes a manifold (126) for management of a flow of gaseous reaction medium thereto. Manifold (126) includes manifold housing (128) defining manifold chamber (129) and having at least one additional component selected from :  a gas distributor (127);  a heater;  and a cavity having a seal within or adjacent to it.', p.application_date = '2014-11-05 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'AU2014346844A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/32', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'DE102014016703'}) SET p.application_no = 'DE102014016703', p.title_cn = '提供合成气的方法和装置集罗马帘', p.title_en = 'Method and apparatus for providing a synthesis gas collecting Rome', p.abstract_cn = '一种方法，用于提供在第一压力水平(I)的合成气体收集罗马提出， 所述第一富甲烷进料流(b)(a)得到第一的流出物在第一压力水平， 一种部分氧化和/或自热重整(1)和第二富甲烷进料物流中(E)(D)，得到第二 流出物在第二的压力水平低于第一压力等级蒸汽重整，(2)进行， 其中(b)在第一的压力水平从流体第一流出物(C)由第一的合成 气体物流中(E)和第二流出流体压缩第二第一处的压力水平的压力水平， 一种第二形成的合成气物流(hr)(C)和其中的流体第一的合成气物流(R)和 第二合成气料流(I)的组合合成气收集罗马。 它提供了第一进料流(D)(a)和第二进料流从含有含硫化合物的流体 有， 富含甲烷的输出电流(K)形成， 形成第一进料流(a)在第一压力水平和(D)而形成第二进料流 给第二压力水平先前或随后加热后带来的脱硫和(3)进行 ， 其中(b)用于加热流体的余热第一的流出物用于(E)和/或第二流出物。 对应的安装(100，200，300)也是本发明的主题。', p.abstract_en = 'A method for providing on a first pressure level (i) synthesis gas collecting Rome is proposed,  wherein a first methane rich feed stream (b) (a) to obtain a first effluent on the first pressure level to a partial oxidation and/or autothermal reforming (1) and a second methane rich feed stream (e) (d) to obtain a second effluent on a second pressure level below the first pressure level a steam reforming (2) is subjected to,  wherein (b) on the first pressure level from fluid of the first effluent (c) is formed from a first synthesis gas stream (e) and the second effluent fluid is compressed by the second pressure level at the first pressure level,  a second synthesis gas stream (hr) (c) is formed and wherein fluid of the first synthesis gas stream (hr) and of the second synthesis gas stream (i) is combined to the synthesis gas collecting Rome. It is provided that the first feed stream (d) (a) and the second feed stream from fluid containing sulphur compounds with a,  methane-rich output current (k) are formed,  to form the first feed stream (a) on the first pressure level and (d) to form the second feed stream is brought to the second pressure level previously or subsequently after heating a desulfurization is brought and (3) is subjected to,  wherein (b) for heating waste heat of the fluid of the first effluent is used (e) and/or the second effluent. A corresponding installation (100,  200,  300) is also the subject of the invention.', p.application_date = '2014-11-12 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'DE102014016703A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/34', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'DE602009037203'}) SET p.application_no = 'DE602009037203', p.title_cn = '盒体用于从重整产物中除去硫化氢的吸附器系统', p.title_en = 'Cartridge adsorber system for removing hydrogen sulfide from reformate', p.abstract_cn = '除系统的H2S从含硫的重整产品包括永磁筒组件，其具有配件 通过重整产品流和一个可更换的药筒组件含有H2S吸附器元件与配件方便， 简单，可靠的配合和密封，与永久滤罐组件。 盒组件包括壳体可任选的全圆柱体或半圆柱体。所述钉仓组件 可以很容易地重新加载离线重新使用的墨盒部件与新鲜的吸附器元件。 优选地，所述吸附器元件离线的可再生用于重新使用。', p.abstract_en = 'A system for removal of H 2 S from sulfur-containing reformate comprising a permanent canister assembly having fittings for flow of reformate therethrough and a replaceable cartridge assembly containing an H 2 S adsorber element and fittings for convenient,  simple,  and reliable mating and sealing with the permanent canister assembly. The cartridge assembly comprises a housing that may be optionally a full cylinder or a semi-cylinder. The cartridge assembly may be easily reloaded off-line for re-use of the cartridge components with a fresh adsorber element. Preferably,  the adsorber element is also renewable off-line for re-use.', p.application_date = '2009-04-09 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'DE602009037203T2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/50', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14933535'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14933535', p.title_cn = '制备一种或多种反应产物方法和设备', p.title_en = 'PROCESS AND PLANT FOR PREPARATION OF ONE OR MORE REACTION PRODUCTS', p.abstract_cn = '一种制备一种或多种反应产物的方法， 其中第一富甲烷进料流经受部分氧化过程和/或自热重整过程，第二富甲烷进料流经受蒸汽重整过程， 其中由第一富含甲烷的进料物流形成第一含合成气的输出物流，由第二富含甲烷的进料物流形成第二含合成气的输出物流，这些合成气物流用于形成集合合成气物流，来自集合合成气物流的流体在合成进料物流中进行分子量增加反应，以获得包含二氧化碳和反应产物的合成输出物流。 至少一种富含二氧化碳的第一循环物流由来自合成输出物流的流体形成，并且来自第一循环物流的流体经受蒸汽重整过程。', p.abstract_en = 'A process for preparing one or more reaction products,  in which a first methane-rich feed stream is subjected to a partial oxidation process and/or an autothermal reforming process and a second methane-rich feed stream is subjected to a steam reforming process,  in which a first synthesis gas-containing output stream is formed from the first methane-rich feed stream and a second synthesis gas-containing output stream is formed from the second methane-rich feed stream and these synthesis gas streams are used to form a collective synthesis gas stream and fluid from the collective synthesis gas stream is subjected to a molecular weight-increasing reaction in a synthesis feed stream to obtain a synthesis output stream comprising carbon dioxide and the reaction product(s). At least one carbon dioxide-rich first recycle stream is formed from fluid from the synthesis output stream and fluid from the first recycle stream is subjected to the steam reforming process.', p.application_date = '2015-11-05 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US20160130204A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/36', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WOCN15077344'}) SET p.application_no = 'WOCN15077344', p.title_cn = '甲醇水制氢系统的重整器、甲醇水制氢系统及制氢方法', p.title_en = 'REFORMER FOR HYDROGEN PRODUCTION SYSTEM UTILIZING METHANOL AND WATER,  HYDROGEN PRODUCTION SYSTEM UTILIZING METHANOL AND WATER AND HYDROGEN PRODUCTION METHOD', p.abstract_cn = '一种甲醇水制氢系统的重整器(1)、甲醇水制氢系统及制氢方法。其中，甲醇水制氢系统的重整器(1)一端安装有启动装置(2)，该启动装置(2)包括杯座(21)，杯座(21)上安装有原料输入管道(22)、加热气化管道(23)、点火装置(24)及温度探测装置(25)；原料输入管道(22)与加热气化管道(23)相连通，原料经原料输入管道(22)进入加热气化管道(23)后，从加热气化管道(23)的末端输出；点火装置(24)的位置与加热气化管道(23)的末端相对应，用于对加热气化管道(23)中输出的原料进行点火，原料经点火装置(24)点火后燃烧，可对加热气化管道(23)进行加热，使加热气化管道(23)中的原料气化而迅速加大燃烧强度，进而为重整器(1)加热；温度探测装置(25)用于探测加热气化管道(23)旁的温度。该甲醇水制氢系统的重整器(1)启动时间短、加热效率高、安全可靠，且无需电加热装置加热。', p.abstract_en = 'A reformer (1) for a hydrogen production system utilizing methanol and water,  a hydrogen production system utilizing methanol and water and a hydrogen production method. A starting device (2) is installed at one end of the reformer (1) for the hydrogen production system utilizing methanol and water,  the starting device (2) comprises a cup base (21),  and a raw material input pipeline (22),  a heating gasification pipeline (23),  an ignition device (24) and a temperature detection device (25) are installed on the cup base (21). The raw material input pipeline (22) is communicated with the heating gasification pipeline (23),  and raw materials enter the heating gasification pipeline (23) through the raw material input pipeline (22) and then are output from the tail end of the heating gasification pipeline (23). The position of the ignition device (24) corresponds to the tail end of the heating gasification pipeline (23),  the ignition device (24) is used for igniting the raw materials output from the heating gasification pipeline (23),  the raw materials are ignited by the ignition device (24) and then are burned,  and the heating gasification pipeline (23) can be heated,  so that the raw materials in the heating gasification pipeline (23) are gasified and burning intensity is rapidly increased,  and further the reformer (1) is heated. The temperature detection device (25) is used for detecting temperature beside the heating gasification pipeline (23). The reformer (1) for the hydrogen production system utilizing methanol and water has short starting time,  high heating efficiency,  safety and reliability and does not need an electrical heating device for heating.', p.application_date = '2015-04-24 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016070588A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/32', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WOEP15002206'}) SET p.application_no = 'WOEP15002206', p.title_cn = '用于生产合成气的方法', p.title_en = 'PROCESS FOR PRODUCING SYNTHESIS GAS', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种合成气的生产方法， 其中， 在第一工艺步骤， 一种高温气化反应器中进行， 在热释放能量， 所释放的热能用于附加生产的合成气在第二工艺步骤， 进行所述反应器的内部或外部。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a process for the production of synthesis gas,  wherein,  in a first process step,  a high-temperature gasification is carried out in a reactor,  in which thermal energy is released,  the released thermal energy being used for the additional production of synthesis gas in a second process step which is carried out inside or outside of the reactor.', p.application_date = '2015-11-04 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016070989A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WOEP15072992'}) SET p.application_no = 'WOEP15072992', p.title_cn = '一种合成气的生产方法', p.title_en = 'PROCESS FOR PRODUCING A SYNTHESIS GAS', p.abstract_cn = '方法用于制造含氢合成气从天然气原料， 包括转换所述天然气为原料的产物气体和纯化所述产物气体， 该过程具有热输入提供的燃料的燃烧； 所述方法包括含碳原料的转化的步骤， 和至少一部分所述燃料为气态燃料的所述步骤得到的转化所述 碳质原料。', p.abstract_en = 'Process for manufacturing a hydrogen-containing synthesis gas from a natural gas feedstock,  comprising the conversion of said natural gas into a raw product gas and purification of said product gas,  the process having a heat input provided by combustion of a fuel;  said process comprises a step of conversion of a carbonaceous feedstock,  and at least a portion of said fuel is a gaseous fuel obtained by said step of conversion of said carbonaceous feedstock.', p.application_date = '2015-10-06 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016071061A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WOUS15058859'}) SET p.application_no = 'WOUS15058859', p.title_cn = '可再生能源储存及零排放动力系统', p.title_en = 'RENEWABLE ENERGY STORAGE AND ZERO EMISSION POWER SYSTEM', p.abstract_cn = '本发明提供一种能量系统，包括燃料处理器，用于接收烃燃料和用于催化转化 烃燃料，重整产物， 电加热装置耦合到所述燃料处理器，用于提供热能到燃料处理器， 能量源耦合到向其提供功率的电加热装置， 和催化重整处理的反应器和用于将重整生成油通入液体燃料。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention provides an energy system comprising a fuel processor for receiving a hydrocarbon fuel and for catalytically converting the hydrocarbon fuel into a reformate,  an electric heating apparatus coupled to the fuel processor for providing thermal energy to the fuel processor,  an energy source coupled to the electric heating apparatus for providing power thereto,  and a catalytic reactor for processing the reformate and for converting the reformate into a liquid fuel.', p.application_date = '2015-11-03 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016073500A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201080039011.0'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201080039011.0', p.title_cn = '制备稀释氢气体混合物的方法', p.title_en = 'Method of preparing dilution hydrogen gas mixture', p.abstract_cn = '一种由含氢和一氧化碳的气体混合物开始通过以下步骤制备稀释氢气体混合物的方法：(i)通过催化水煤气变换反应将所述气体混合物中的部分一氧化碳转化为氢和二氧化碳，以得到变换后气体，和(ii)通过膜从所述变换后气体中分离出氢，从而在膜的渗透侧获得含氢气体和在膜的渗余侧获得含二氧化碳气体，其中在膜的渗透侧提供吹扫气；(iii)冷却所述含二氧化碳气体，从而获得液态二氧化碳和不凝气的气体混合物，和(iv)将液态二氧化碳与不凝气分离；其中所述不凝气进料至所述含氢气体中。', p.abstract_en = 'Process to prepare a diluted hydrogen gas mixture starting from a gas mixture comprising hydrogen and carbon monoxide by (i) converting part of the carbon monoxide in said gas mixture to hydrogen and carbon dioxide by means of a catalysed water gas shift reaction to obtain a shifted gas and (ii) separating hydrogen from said shifted gas by means of a membrane to obtain the hydrogen comprising gas at the permeate side of the membrane and a carbon dioxide comprising gas at the retentate side of the membrane,  wherein at the permeate side of the membrane a sweep gas is provided;  (iii) cooling the carbon dioxide comprising gas to obtain liquid carbon dioxide and a gas mixture of non-condensable gasses and (iv) separating the liquid carbon dioxide from the non-condensable gasses;  wherein the non-condensable gasses are fed into the hydrogen comprising gas.', p.application_date = '2010-09-03 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN102482079B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/12', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201210171426.4'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201210171426.4', p.title_cn = '一种合成氨/甲醇装置的放空尾气处理系统及处理方法', p.title_en = 'A synthetic ammonia/methanol device to the evacuation of the exhaust gas treatment system and its treatment method', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种合成氨/甲醇装置的放空尾气处理系统及处理方法。所述系统包括：换热器、加热器和转换炉；换热器和加热器的出口分别连接转换炉顶部，转换炉底部连接换热器；换热器进口连接放空尾气管线；所述加热器进口连接氧气管线；过热蒸汽管线分成两支，分别连接放空尾气管线和氧气管线。所述方法包括：放空尾气和氧气分别先与过热蒸汽混合、经加热后进入转换炉发生反应，转化炉底部得到转化气经换热器后，送入氨或甲醇合成系统。本发明为合成氨(甲醇)生产放空气放空尾气综合利用的重大革新，既能不影响生产，又实现节能减排，还能带来经济效益。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention discloses an emptying tailing gas processing system of a synthesis ammonia or methanol device and a processing method thereof. The system comprises a heat exchanger,  a heater,  and a conversion furnace,  the outlets of the heat exchanger and the heater are connected to the top part of the conversion furnace,  the bottom of the conversion furnace is connected to the heat exchanger,  the inlet of the heat exchanger is connected to a tailing gas emptying pipeline,  the inlet of the heater is connected to an oxygen pipeline,  an over-heated steam pipeline is divided into two branches,  which are individually connected to the tailing gas emptying pipeline and the oxygen pipeline. The processing method comprises the following steps :  mixing emptying tailing gas and oxygen with over-heated steam,  then introducing the heated mixed gas into the conversion finance to carry out reactions,  introducing the conversion gas,  which is obtained in the bottom of the furnace,  into the heat exchanger,  and finally introducing the gas into the ammonia or methanol synthesis system. The processing system and method are an important innovation of comprehensive utilization of emptying tailing gas generated during the production process of synthesis ammonia (methanol),  and have the advantages that production is not affected,  the goals of energy saving and discharge reduction are achieved,  and economic benefit is generated.', p.application_date = '2012-05-30 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN103449367B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/36', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201310628811.1'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201310628811.1', p.title_cn = '富氢机及其制备富氢的方法', p.title_en = 'And its rich hydrogen machine method of preparation of a hydrogen-rich', p.abstract_cn = '本发明揭示了一种富氢机及其制备富氢的方法，富氢机包括原料输送通道、热量回收装置、重整室、燃烧室；原料输送通道的一部分设置于热量回收装置中，热量回收装置输出从重整室排出的高温余气、富氢气体，利用排出的高温余气、富氢气体为原料加热；所述重整室的外壁设有第一气化管路，经过热量回收装置加热的甲醇水混合液在第一气化管路中被加热气化，进入重整室重整；重整室还设有分流机构，用以将一部分制得的富氢气体输出，同时将一部分制得的富氢气体输送至燃烧室；所述燃烧室设置于重整室的外部，燃烧室内通过燃烧气化的甲醇或/和富氢气体或/和尾气放热，为重整室加热。本发明可提高富氢的制备效率，节约能源。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention discloses a hydrogen-rich gas preparing machine and a method for preparing hydrogen-rich gas. The hydrogen-rich gas preparing machine comprises a raw material conveying channel,  a heat recovery apparatus,  a reforming chamber and a combustion chamber;  one part of the raw material conveying channel is arranged in the heat recovery apparatus which is used to output high-temperature residual gas and hydrogen-rich gas from the reforming chamber and utilize the high-temperature residual gas and the hydrogen-rich gas to heat raw materials;  the outer wall of the reforming chamber is provided with a first gasification pipe,  a methanol-water mixed solution heated by the heat recovery apparatus is heated and gasified in the first gasification pip and then enters the reforming chamber for reforming;  the reforming chamber also is provided with a shunting mechanism used to output a part of prepared hydrogen-rich gas and convey the other part of prepared hydrogen-rich gas to the combustion chamber at the same time;  and the combustion chamber is arranged at the outside of the reforming chamber,  the combustion chamber discharges heat via combusting gasified methanol or/and hydrogen-rich gas or/and tail gas and heats the reforming chamber. According to the technical scheme,  the preparation efficiency of hydrogen-rich gas is improved and energy is saved.', p.application_date = '2013-11-29 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN103738919B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 2, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201280046901.3'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201280046901.3', p.title_cn = '具有改进的流体分布的氢气发生器', p.title_en = 'The fluid distribution with improved hydrogen generator', p.abstract_cn = '本发明是一种氢气发生器，其包括外壳、反应区、贮液器、反应区内的包含第一反应物的球粒、贮液器内的包含第二反应物的流体、贮液器和反应区之间的流体流动路径、和氢气出口。所述流体流动路径包括偏向球粒的从动件组件，所述从动件组件包括活节接头和从动件，并且第二反应物可以与第一反应物在反应区内反应以产生氢气和副产物。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention is a hydrogen generator including a housing,  a reaction area,  a fluid reservoir,  a pellet comprising a first reactant within the reaction area,  a fluid comprising a second reactant within the fluid reservoir,  a fluid flow path between the fluid reservoir and the reaction area,  and a hydrogen outlet. The fluid flow path comprises a follower assembly biased toward the pellet,  the follower assembly includes an articulated joint and a follower,  and the second reactant can react with the first reactant in the reaction area to produce hydrogen gas and byproducts.', p.application_date = '2012-05-01 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN103998371B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/06', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201410789085.6'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201410789085.6', p.title_cn = '一种自催化释氢体系及其使用方法', p.title_en = 'A self-catalytic hydrogen-evolution system and method of use thereof', p.abstract_cn = '本发明属于新材料及能源开发的技术领域，具体涉及一种高效释氢体系及其使用方法。释氢体系由固体组分和液体组分按摩尔比1：1～1：6构成，在0℃至70℃条件下，将固体组分与液体组分混合，即可实现氢气的自发、连续、可控释放。本发明首次使用三聚氰胺/硼烷体系，具有原料廉价、无需加催化剂、反应温度低、工艺简单、操作方便等优点。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention belongs to the technical field of development of advanced materials and energy,  and specifically relates to an efficient self-catalyzed hydrogen releasing system and an application method thereof. The hydrogen releasing system comprises a solid component and a liquid component in molar ratio of 1 :  1 to 1 :  6;  the solid component and the liquid component are mixed under the temperature of 0 to 70 DEG C to achieve the spontaneous,  continuous and controllable release of hydrogen. According to the efficient self-catalyzed hydrogen releasing system,  the melamine/ borane system is put into use for the first time;  the efficient self-catalyzed hydrogen releasing system has the advantages that the raw materials are low in cost,  catalysts are saved,  the reaction is performed at a low temperature,  the process is simple,  and the operation is convenient.', p.application_date = '2014-12-17 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN104477842B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201410807641.8'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201410807641.8', p.title_cn = '一种利用焦炉荒煤气制取氢气的装置及方法', p.title_en = 'Using coke-oven gas,  a device and method for producing hydrogen', p.abstract_cn = '本发明属于焦炉荒煤气净化和余热回收技术领域，具体涉及一种利用焦炉荒煤气制取氢气的装置及方法。本发明装置包括重整制氢反应器、吸附剂再生器、气固分离器、料仓、蒸汽再热器、给料装置、余热锅炉、储气柜和变压吸附装置；在重整制氢反应器中，高温焦炉荒煤气在催化剂作用下与水蒸汽发生重整制氢反应，CO2吸附剂与重整反应产生的CO2发生吸附反应，然后进入气固分离器进行气固分离，固体吸附剂进入吸附剂再生器再生，同时获得CO2，富氢煤气依次通过余热锅炉、干燥塔最终储存在H2储气柜。本发明充分利用了荒煤气自身显热，实现荒煤气中焦油和低碳化合物等废气的资源化利用，实现氢气产量、浓度的最优化和连续高效制取，同时可获取高纯CO2等副产物。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention belongs to the technical field of coke oven crude gas purification and waste heat recovery and in particular relates to a device and a method for producing hydrogen by utilizing coke oven crude gas. The device disclosed by the invention comprises a reforming hydrogen production reactor,  an adsorbent reproducer,  a gas-solid separator,  a stock bin,  a steam reheater,  a feeding device,  a waste heat boiler,  a gas storage tank and a pressure swing adsorption device. The method comprises the following steps :  in the reforming hydrogen production reactor,  carrying out a reforming hydrogen production reaction between the high-temperature coke oven crude gas and water vapor in the presence of a catalyst;  carrying out an adsorption reaction between a CO2 adsorbent and CO2 produced by the reforming reaction,  performing gas-solid separation in a gas-solid separator,  allowing the solid adsorbent to enter the adsorbent reproducer for reproducing,  and obtaining CO2;  and allowing the hydrogen-rich gas to sequentially pass through the waste heat boiler and a drying tower,  and finally storing the gas in an H2 gas storage tank. The sensible heat of the crude gas is fully utilized,  resource utilization of tar and low-carbon compounds in the crude gas and other waste gases is realized,  the optimization of hydrogen yield and concentration and continuous and high-efficiency production are realized,  and high-purity CO2 and other side products can be obtained.', p.application_date = '2014-12-23 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN104495749B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/34', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201510991738.3'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201510991738.3', p.title_cn = '一种金属氢化物的聚合物原位聚合包覆改性方法', p.title_en = 'Metal hydride polymer in-situ polymerization coating modification method', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种金属氢化物的聚合物原位聚合包覆改性方法，以双环戊二烯(DCPD)等为聚合物反应单体，通过原位聚合反应，在金属氢化物表面形成聚双环戊二烯(pDCPD)的均聚物或共聚物的包覆层，实现对金属氢化物的隔离保护。该方法具有反应迅速、包覆层稳定的特点，既能起到良好的隔离保护作用，又可使改性金属氢化物保持优异的能量特性，可为金属氢化物在多领域的应用提供性能优良稳定的产品。', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention relates to a metal hydride polymer in-situ polymerization coating modification method,  dicyclopentadiene (DCPD) and the like are used as polymer reactive monomers for formation of a poly dicyclopentadiene(DCPD) homopolymer or copolymer coating layer on metal hydride surface by in-situ polymerization,  and metal hydride isolation protection can be achieved. The method has the characteristics of rapid response and coating layer stability,  good role in isolation and protection can be played,  a modified metal hydride can maintain excellent energy characteristics,  and a good and stable performance product is provided for metal hydride application of in many fields.', p.application_date = '2015-12-23 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105565267A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201610087491.7'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201610087491.7', p.title_cn = '一种合成氨驰放气中氢气的回收装置及回收工艺', p.title_en = 'Device and process for recovering hydrogen in synthetic ammonia purge gas', p.abstract_cn = '本发明属于一种合成氨驰放气中氢气的回收装置及回收工艺；包括合成系统驰放气管道、合成系统高压氮氢压缩机一段入口、LNG生产装置，合成系统驰放气管道通过氨回收装置和加热器的壳程与膜分离单元的首端膜分离装置的中部进口相连，所述膜分离单元的顶部的氢气出口通过管道与合成系统高压氮氢压缩机一段入口相连，膜分离单元末端膜分离装置的底部尾气出口通过管道与LNG生产装置相连；具有设备简单、操作方便、运行可靠、在节能降耗同时能够实现产品的有效利用、且可减少环境污染的优点。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention belongs to a device and process for recovering hydrogen in synthetic ammonia purge gas. The device comprises a synthetic system purge gas pipeline,  a synthetic system high-pressure nitrogen and hydrogen compressor first-section inlet and an LNG production device,  wherein the synthetic system purge gas pipeline is connected with a middle inlet of a head-end membrane separation device of a membrane separation unit through an ammonia recovery device and a shell pass of a heater,  a hydrogen outlet formed in the top of the membrane separation unit is connected with the synthetic system high-pressure nitrogen and hydrogen compressor first-section inlet through a pipe,  and a bottom tail gas outlet of a tail-end membrane separation device of the membrane separation unit is connected with the LNG production device through a pipe. The device has the advantages of being simple,  convenient to operate,  reliable in operation and capable of achieving effective product utilization and reducing environmental pollution while saving energy and reducing consumption.', p.application_date = '2016-02-04 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105565270A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/50', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201610040298.8'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201610040298.8', p.title_cn = '一种室温稳定的半笼形水合物在氢气分离提纯中的应用', p.title_en = 'Application of semi-cage-shaped aquo-complex stable at room temperature to hydrogen separation and purification', p.abstract_cn = '本发明属于能源环保材料技术领域，公开了一种室温稳定的半笼形水合物在氢气分离提纯中的应用。所述应用包括以下步骤：将室温稳定的半笼形水合物置于高压反应釜内，向高压反应釜中通入高压混合气体进行反应，得到固态半笼形水合物和氢气；所述混合气体由氢气和杂质气体组成。所述半笼形水合物由水与四异戊基季铵盐混合得到。本发明采用四异戊基季铵盐作为稳定剂和促进剂来促进杂质气体水合物的形成，具有形成压力低，室温稳定性好的特点，将水合物用于氢气分离提纯，氢气分离效率高，操作条件简单和节能，为氢气分离技术的工业化应用提供了技术支撑。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention belongs to the technical field of energy environmental-protection materials and discloses application of a semi-cage-shaped aquo-complex stable at room temperature to hydrogen separation and purification. The application comprises the following steps that the semi-cage-shaped aquo-complex stable at the room temperature is placed into a high-pressure reaction kettle,  and high-pressure mixed gas is introduced into the high-pressure reaction kettle,  so that the solid semi-cage-shaped aquo-complex and hydrogen are obtained;  the mixed gas is composed of hydrogen and impurity gas. The semi-cage-shaped aquo-complex is obtained by mixing water with a tetraisoamyl quaternary ammonium salt. The tetraisoamyl quaternary ammonium salt serves as a stabilizer and an accelerant to promote formation of impurity gas hydrate,  the aquo-complex has the advantages of being low in formation pressure and high in room temperature stability,  the aquo-complex is used for hydrogen separation and purification,  hydrogen separation efficiency is high,  operation conditions are simple and save energy,  and the technical support is provided for industrialized application of the hydrogen separation technology.', p.application_date = '2016-01-21 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105565271A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/52', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201520675721.2'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201520675721.2', p.title_cn = '一种零碳排放的甲醇水重整制氢系统及其燃料电池汽车', p.title_en = 'Methanol -water reformation hydrogen production system that zero carbon discharged and fuel cell car thereof', p.abstract_cn = '本实用新型公开了一种零碳排放的甲醇水重整制氢系统及其燃料电池汽车，包括甲醇水储存容器、输送泵、第一换热器、重整器及二氧化碳回收装置，其中：重整器，设有重整室、电磁加热器及氢气纯化装置，电磁加热器为重整室提供热能；重整室用于甲醇和水发生重整制氢反应，制得二氧化碳和氢气，其与水汽混合成高温混合气体输向氢气纯化装置，纯化分离后输出氢气，同时输出二氧化碳和未反应的水汽混合气体，其经第一换热器后输向二氧化碳回收装置；二氧化碳回收装置为可更换的模块化二氧化碳回收装置，用于回收二氧化碳及部分水汽。本实用新型能够回收CO2，不影响环境，对制氢系统自身无伤害，有利于燃料电池汽车等新能源领域的推广和应用。', p.abstract_en = 'The utility model discloses a methanol -water reformation hydrogen production system that zero carbon discharged and fuel cell car thereof,  including methanol -water reservoir,  delivery pump,  first heat exchanger,  reformer and carbon dioxide recovery unit,  wherein :  the reformer is equipped with reformation room,  electromagnetic heater and hydrogen purification device,  and electromagnetic heater provides heat energy for the reformation room,  the reformation room is used for methyl alcohol and water emergence reformation hydrogen generation,  makes carbon dioxide and hydrogen,  and it becomes the high temperature mist with water vapor mixing fails to hydrogen purification device,  purification after -separating output hydrogen,  and it is gaseous to export carbon dioxide and unreacted water vapor mixing simultaneously,  and it is defeated to carbon dioxide recovery unit behind first heat exchanger,  carbon dioxide recovery unit is removable modularization carbon dioxide recovery unit for retrieve carbon dioxide and partial steam. The utility model discloses can retrieve CO2,  not influence the environment,  not have hydrogen production system self and hurt,  be favorable to the popularization and the application in new forms of energy fields such as fuel cell car.', p.application_date = '2015-09-02 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN205222680U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/32', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 1, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201520885354.9'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201520885354.9', p.title_cn = '一种甲醇水重整制氢机', p.title_en = 'Methanol -water reformation hydrogen manufacturing machine', p.abstract_cn = '本实用新型公开了一种甲醇水重整制氢机，包括甲醇水储存容器、输送泵、变频器、换热器及重整器，其中：变频器，用于将低频电压或直流电压转换为电磁加热器之电磁线圈所需要的高频电压，所述变频器设置有液冷散热器，所述甲醇水原料在输送泵的泵送过程中，流经该液冷散热器，使变频器产生的热量被甲醇水原料带走；重整器，设有重整室、电磁加热器及氢气纯化装置，所述电磁加热器包括电磁线圈及金属受磁体，所述电磁线圈输入高频电压后能产生高频磁场，使金属受磁体受磁场感应而发热，为重整室提供热能。本实用新型的变频器噪音低、散热效果好、耗能低，并且本实用新型能够有效地利用变频器所产生的热量。', p.abstract_en = 'The utility model discloses a methanol -water reformation hydrogen manufacturing machine,  including methanol -water reservoir,  delivery pump,  converter,  heat exchanger and reformer,  wherein :  the converter for the required high -frequency voltage of solenoid who is low -frequency voltage or direct current voltage conversion electromagnetic heater,  the converter is provided with the liquid cooling radiator,  the methanol -water raw materials is in the pumping process of delivery pump,  and this liquid cooling radiator of flowing through makes the heat of converter production taken away by the methanol -water raw materials,  the reformer is equipped with reformation room,  electromagnetic heater and hydrogen purification device,  electromagnetic heater includes that solenoid and metal receive the magnet,  can produce the high frequency magnetic field behind the solenoid input high -frequency voltage,  make the metal receive the magnet to receive the magnetic field response and generate heat,  provide heat energy for the reformation room. The utility model discloses a converter noise is low,  the radiating effect is good,  the power consumption is low,  and the utility model discloses can effectively utilize the produced heat of converter.', p.application_date = '2015-11-09 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN205222681U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/32', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 1, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201521035845.0'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201521035845.0', p.title_cn = '一种可燃气体发生装置', p.title_en = 'Combustible gas generating device', p.abstract_cn = '一种可燃气体发生装置，包括原料罐，原料罐通过原料输入管道经原料泵与一级热交换器的原料入口相连，一级热交换器的原料出口通过原料输入管道与二级热交换器的原料入口相连，二级热交换器的原料出口通过原料输入管道与重整器的原料入口相连，重整器的原料出口通过原料输入管道与甲醇反应器的原料入口相连，甲醇反应器的可燃气体出口通过可燃气体输送管道与二级热交换器的底部相连，二级热交换器的顶部通过可燃气体输送管道与一级热交换器的底部相连。它结构简单，制造成本低，自身运行耗能低，可将含水50％-85％、甲醇15％-50％的混合液加热产生氢气(含量75％以上)、氧气、一氧化碳、甲烷等混合可燃气体，可替代现有的天然气，节约大量能源，大大降低使用成本。', p.abstract_en = 'The utility model provides a combustible gas generating device,  including the head tank,  it is continuous with one -level heat exchanger\'s feed inlet that the head tank passes through raw materials input tube taoist scriptures feedstock pump,  the feed inlet that one -level heat exchanger\'s silo outlet passes through raw materials input pipeline and second grade heat exchanger links to each other,  the feed inlet that second grade heat exchanger\'s silo outlet passes through raw materials input pipeline and reformer links to each other,  the feed inlet that the silo outlet of reformer passes through raw materials input pipeline and methyl alcohol reactor links to each other,  the combustible gas export of methyl alcohol reactor links to each other with second grade heat exchanger\'s bottom through combustible gas pipeline,  the bottom that combustible gas pipeline and one -level heat exchanger are passed through to second grade heat exchanger\'s top links to each other. Its simple structure,  low in manufacturing cost,  self operation power consumption is low,  can add moisture 50 percent -85 percent,  methyl alcohol 15 percent -50 percent\'s mixed liquid thermogenesis hydrogen (content is more than 75 percent),  oxygen,  carbon monoxide,  methane etc. And mix combustible gas,  and a large amount of energy are practiced thrift,  greatly reduced use cost to the natural gas that the fungible had now.', p.application_date = '2015-12-10 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN205222682U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/32', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201521003631.5'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201521003631.5', p.title_cn = '一种加装脱氧装置提纯氢气结构', p.title_en = 'Install deoxidation device purification hydrogen structure additional', p.abstract_cn = '本实用新型公开了一种加装脱氧装置提纯氢气结构，包括氮气瓶、氢气发生器和低噪音空气泵，所述氮气瓶、氢气发生器和低噪音空气泵均与多路气体净化仪连通，在氢气发生器与多路气体净化仪之间设有一级脱氧管和二级脱氧管。本实用新型氢气发生器后加装脱氧装置，它适用于油色谱分析工作，降低了氢气发生器带来的误差，解决了氢气发生器氢气浓度达不到国标要求(氢气≥99.99％)的问题，同时，本实用新型有效解决了生产作业中存在的实际问题，具有良好的安全效益与经济效益。', p.abstract_en = 'The utility model discloses an install deoxidation device purification hydrogen structure additional,  including nitrogen cylinder,  hydrogen generator and low noise air pump,  nitrogen cylinder,  hydrogen generator and low noise air pump all communicate with multichannel gas purification appearance,  are equipped with one -level deoxidation pipe and second grade deoxidation pipe between hydrogen generator and multichannel gas purification appearance. The utility model discloses install the deoxidation device behind the hydrogen generator additional,  it is applicable to oily chromatography work,  has reduced the error that hydrogen generator brought,  and solve hydrogen generator hydrogen concentration and do not reached the problem that the national standard required (hydrogen >= 99.99 percent),  simultaneously,  the utility model discloses effectively solve the practical problem that exists in the production operation,  had good safe benefit and economic benefits.', p.application_date = '2015-12-08 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN205222683U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/56', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'EP14192002'}) SET p.application_no = 'EP14192002', p.title_cn = '一种合成气的生产方法', p.title_en = 'Process for producing a synthesis gas', p.abstract_cn = '方法用于制造含氢合成气从天然气原料， 包括转换所述天然气为原料的产物气体和纯化所述产物气体， 该过程具有热输入提供的燃料的燃烧； 所述方法包括含碳原料的气化的步骤， 和至少一部分所述燃料为气态燃料的所述步骤得到的气化。', p.abstract_en = 'Process for manufacturing a hydrogen-containing synthesis gas from a natural gas feedstock,  comprising the conversion of said natural gas into a raw product gas and purification of said product gas,  the process having a heat input provided by combustion of a fuel;  said process comprises a step of gasification of a carbonaceous feedstock,  and at least a portion of said fuel is a gaseous fuel obtained by said step of gasification.', p.application_date = '2014-11-06 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'EP3018094A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2013506384'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2013506384', p.title_cn = '操作方法，一种燃料电池系统，氢气发生器，氢气发生器', p.title_en = 'Operation method,  and a fuel cell system,  a hydrogen generator,  a hydrogen generator', p.abstract_cn = '本发明包括氢气发生器相关联的加氢脱硫器(1)，被配置为从原料中除去硫化合物. 重整器(2)被配置成生成含氢气体与原料已经通过使用加氢脱硫器(1). 原料供给装置(3)配置原料供给至所述重整器(2). 循环流道(4)，配置成供给含氢气体的一部分. 所述重整器(2)排出. 所述前的原料的原料进入加氢脱硫器(1). 一种通断阀(5)，设置在所述循环流道(4)。. 压力检测器(6)位于上游位置的通断阀(5)中的再循环流动通道(4). 和配置成检测异常的异常检测部(7)中的堵塞物的再循环流动通道(4)基于检测到的压力的压力检测器(6). 在一种状态中的原料供给装置(3)的原料供给至所述重整器. (2)与通断阀(5)关闭.', p.abstract_en = 'A hydrogen generator associated with the invention comprises a hydro-desulfurizer (1) configured to remove sulfur compounds from a raw material;  a reformer (2) configured to generate hydrogen-containing gas with use of the raw material that has passed through the hydro-desulfurizer (1);  a raw material supply device (3) configured to supply the raw material to the reformer (2);  a recycle flow passage (4) configured to supply a portion of the hydrogen-containing gas,  discharged from the reformer (2),  to the raw material before the raw material flows into the hydro-desulfurizer (1);  an on-off valve (5) provided in the recycle flow passage (4);  a pressure detector (6) located at a position upstream of the on-off valve (5) in the recycle flow passage (4);  and an abnormality detector (7) configured to detect an abnormal clogging in the recycle flow passage (4) based on a pressure detected by the pressure detector (6),  in a state in which the raw material supply device (3) is supplying the raw material to the reformer,  (2) with the on-off valve (5) closed.', p.application_date = '2012-10-03 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP5914863B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2013234272'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2013234272', p.title_cn = '生产氢气的方法和氢气的制造装置', p.title_en = 'A method of producing hydrogen gas and a hydrogen gas manufacturing device', p.abstract_cn = '本发明提供一种通过硅粒子与碱性水溶液的反应来制造氢气的方法，通过适度地抑制硅粒子与碱性水溶液的反应来连续地获得氢气。 [解决方案]用于氢气生产的硅材料A包括硅颗粒和油。 含油量为硅颗粒重量的0.1-10%。 本发明的氢气制造用硅材料A的制造方法包括 : 准备含有硅粒子，油和水的硅废弃物(108)的工序； 离心或过滤硅废料(108)以产生包括硅颗粒，油和少量水的固体(A112)的步骤； 干燥固体(A112)以产生包括硅颗粒和油的固体(B112)的步骤； 和将水(116)混合到固体(B112)中以获得淤泥(A117)的步骤。', p.abstract_en = '[Problem] In a method for producing a hydrogen gas by the reaction of silicon particles and an alkaline aqueous solution,  to continuously obtain the hydrogen gas by moderately inhibiting the reaction of the silicon particles and the alkaline aqueous solution. [Solution] This silicon material A for hydrogen gas production comprises silicon particles and oil. The oil content is 0.1 to 10 weight% of the silicon particles. This method for producing the silicon material A for hydrogen gas production comprises :  a step of preparing silicon waste (108) which includes the silicon particles,  oil and water;  a step of centrifuging or filtrating the silicon waste (108) to produce a solid (A112) which includes the silicon particles,  oil and a small amount of water;  a step of drying the solid (A112) to produce a solid (B112) which includes the silicon particles and oil;  and a step of mixing water (116) into the solid (B112) to obtain sludge (A117).', p.application_date = '2013-11-12 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP5916686B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/06', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'BR112013004679'}) SET p.application_no = 'BR112013004679', p.title_cn = '氨生产在集成过程强化', p.title_en = 'AMMONIA PRODUCTION IN INTEGRATED PROCESSES INTENSIFIED', p.abstract_cn = '公开了一种氨的生产方法。 该方法使用生物质废物等的气化来生产合成气，该合成气使用包括使用富氮空气和多孔涂覆催化剂的集成系统，在等离子体反应器中生产氨。 最后使用磺化聚HIPE聚合物回收氨，磺化聚HIPE聚合物在中和后可用作肥料。', p.abstract_en = 'An ammonia production process is disclosed. The process uses gasification of biomass waste and the like to produce syngas which,  using an integrated system including using nitrogen enriched air and a porous coated catalyst,  produces ammonia in a plasma reactor. The ammonia is finally recovered using sulphonated PolyHIPE Polymer which can be used as a fertilizer after neutralization.', p.application_date = '2011-08-30 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'BRPI1304679A2', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'UAA201408121'}) SET p.application_no = 'UAA201408121', p.title_cn = '产生合成气的方法和系统', p.title_en = 'PROCESS AND A SYSTEM FOR GENERATING SYNTHESIS GAS', p.abstract_cn = '一种方法和一种系统，用于生成合成气的烃和水被描述。在进一步的细节的方法和系统，合成气体产生的任何期望比例的CO氢和/或合成的官能化和/或非官能化的烃。通过该方法，含烃流体可具有可变转换为合成气的氢含量而不产生显著量CO。另外，各种形式的氢和碳可获得作为副产物。', p.abstract_en = 'A process and a system for generating synthesis gas from hydrocarbons and water are described. In further details of the process and the system,  synthesis gases are generated in any desired ratios of CO to hydrogen and/or synthetic functionalized and/or non-functionalized hydrocarbons. By means of this process,  a hydrocarbon-containing fluid can be converted into a synthesis gas having a variable hydrogen content without generating significant amounts of CO. Furthermore,  hydrogen and carbon in various forms can be obtained as byproducts.', p.application_date = '2012-12-20 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'UA111519C2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/24', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14357161'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14357161', p.title_cn = '储氢方法', p.title_en = 'Hydrogen storage method', p.abstract_cn = '本发明提供了一种储氢方法，该方法使得储氢合金能够存储超过通常已知理论值的最大储氢量的氢。 在氢化步骤中，预先获得作为氢和储氢合金之间的原子量比计算出的储氢比作为理论值，将储氢合金存储至理论值的压力设置为第一压力值，将比第一压力值大十倍或更多倍的压力值设置为第二压力值，并且将压力增加至第二压力值。在氢化步骤中，预先获得作为氢和储氢合金之间的原子量比计算出的储氢比作为理论值，将储氢合金存储至理论值的压力设置为第一压力值，将比第一压力值大十倍或更多倍的压力值设置为第二压力值，并且将压力增加至第二压力值。 在脱氢步骤中，压力从第二压力值降低到或低于第一压力值。 重复执行氢化步骤和脱氢步骤。', p.abstract_en = 'A hydrogen storage method is provided which enables a hydrogen storage alloy to store hydrogen up to a maximum hydrogen storage amount thereof in excess of a generally known theoretical value. In a hydrogenation step,  a hydrogen storage ratio calculated as an atomic weight ratio between hydrogen and the hydrogen storage alloy is obtained beforehand as a theoretical value,  a pressure at which the hydrogen storage alloy stores hydrogen up to the theoretical value is set as a first pressure value,  a pressure value ten or more times greater than the first pressure value is set as a second pressure value,  and pressure is increased up to the second pressure value. In a dehydrogenation step,  the pressure is decreased from the second pressure value to or below the first pressure value. The hydrogenation step and the dehydrogenation step are repeatedly executed.', p.application_date = '2012-10-25 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9334163B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/08', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US13264128'}) SET p.application_no = 'US13264128', p.title_cn = '氢发生器和燃料电池系统', p.title_en = 'Hydrogen generator and fuel cell system', p.abstract_cn = '一种氢发生器(100)，包括 : 氢生成单元(1)，被配置为通过使用原料气体生成含氢气体； 加氢脱硫器(7)，其被配置为除去供应到氢气发生单元(1)的原料气体中的硫化合物； 第一气体通道(5)，通过该第一气体通道(5)，通过加氢脱硫器(7)供应到氢气发生单元(1)的原料气体流过该第一气体通道(5)； 再循环通道(10)，通过该再循环通道(10)将来自氢气发生单元(1)的含氢气体供应到位于加氢脱硫器(7)上游的第一气体通道(5)中的原料气体； 原料气体供给单元(6)，其设置在加氢脱硫器(7)与第一气体通道(5)和再循环通道(10)相遇的相遇点之间； 以及第一开关阀(8)，设置在原料气体供给单元(6)和加氢脱硫器(7)之间，当氢气发生器(100)停止时关闭。', p.abstract_en = 'A hydrogen generator (100) includes :  a hydrogen generating unit (1) configured to generate a hydrogen-containing gas by using a raw material gas;  a hydro-desulfurizer (7) configured to remove a sulfur compound in the raw material gas supplied to the hydrogen generating unit (1);  a first gas channel (5) through which the raw material gas supplied through the hydro-desulfurizer (7) to the hydrogen generating unit (1) flows;  a recycle channel (10) through which the hydrogen-containing gas from the hydrogen generating unit (1) is supplied to the raw material gas in the first gas channel (5) located upstream of the hydro-desulfurizer (7);  a raw material gas supply unit (6) disposed between the hydro-desulfurizer (7) and a meeting point where the first gas channel (5) and the recycle channel (10) meet;  and a first on-off valve (8) disposed between the raw material gas supply unit (6) and the hydro-desulfurizer (7) to close when the hydrogen generator (100) stops.', p.application_date = '2010-12-24 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9334164B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 3, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'NO20043021'}) SET p.application_no = 'NO20043021', p.title_cn = '烃类重整的步骤', p.title_en = 'Procedure for reforming hydrocarbons', p.abstract_cn = '一种降低一氧化碳之间的相互作用的方法存在于换热介质和金属壳体侧换热式转化装置，用于烃类的重整处理所述壳体侧的所述设备与至少一个钝化有效量的化合物，该化合物含有至少一个选自磷，锡，锑，砷，铅，铋，铜，锗，银或金进行了描述。其中挥发性化合物形成的钝化化合物，该方法还包括化合物的回收，防止污染和去激活的后续工艺步骤。该方法减少了副反应的发生，提供了改进的重整器管的寿命和待处理允许管原位，而不需要用于过程停机。', p.abstract_en = 'A method for reducing the interaction between carbon monoxide present in a heat exchange medium and metals on the shell side of heat exchange reformer apparatus used for reforming of hydrocarbons by treatment of the shell-side of said apparatus with an effective amount of at least one passivation compound containing at least one element selected from phosphorus,  tin,  antimony,  arsenic,  lead,  bismuth,  copper,  germanium,  silver or gold is described. Where volatile compounds are formed by the passivation compound,  the method further comprises compound recovery to prevent contamination and deactivation of subsequent process steps. The method reduces side reactions,  provides improved reformer tube lifetime and allows tubes to be treated in-situ without the need for process shutdown.', p.application_date = '2004-07-15 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'NO337602B1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'SA515360235'}) SET p.application_no = 'SA515360235', p.title_cn = '重整器中或用于重整器的管监视器和过程测量和控制', p.title_en = 'Tube monitor and process measurement and control in or for a reformer', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及高温管式重整器(例如用于生产甲醇的蒸汽重整器)的监测和控制。本发明的构思允许间接测量重整器内的高温，其然后可用于进行实时调整、监测长期性能和监测/预测重整器的寿命等。图1', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to the monitoring,  and control of a high temperature tube reformer (such as used in a steam reformer for the production of methanol). The inventive concept allows indirect measurement of the high temperatures within the reformer,  which can then be used to make real time adjustments,  monitor long term performance,  and monitor/predict lifespan of the reformer etc. Fig. 1', p.application_date = '2013-10-11 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'SA515360235A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/26', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CA2966243'}) SET p.application_no = 'CA2966243', p.title_cn = '用于生产合成气的方法和设备', p.title_en = 'METHOD AND PLANT FOR THE PRODUCTION OF SYNTHESIS GAS', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种用于生产合成气的方法和设备(3)从烃进料(1)。在所述方法中，在第第一工序，烃为分体式结构，使用等离子体气体在高温下，成氢气(6)和活性炭(5)。该产品与蒸汽混合，(8)和二氧化碳(9)，所述碳层(5)几乎完全转化为氢和一氧化碳在温度范围从800℃。1700℃的热源(10)供给的转化最大化。产品然后淬灭(13)。合成气(3)可部分(3)，反馈作为等离子气体。在进一步的步骤中，例如费-托合成，合成气(3)进一步转化，然后将其分离成不同的部分。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a method and plant for producing synthesis gas (3) from hydrocarbons (1). In the method,  in a first step,  hydrocarbons are split,  using a plasma gas at high temperatures,  into hydrogen (6) and carbon (5). Said product is mixed with steam (8) and carbon dioxide (9),  and the carbon (5) is almost entirely converted to hydrogen and carbon monoxide in a temperature range from 800° C to 1700° C. Heat (10) is supplied to maximize the conversion. The product is then quenched (13). Synthesis gas (3) can be partially (3a) fed back and used as plasma gas. In further steps,  such as Fischer-Tropsch synthesis,  the synthesis gas (3) is further converted and then separated into various fractions.', p.application_date = '2015-10-28 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CA2966243A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/24', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'FR12002496'}) SET p.application_no = 'FR12002496', p.title_cn = '方法用于降低二氧化碳成一氧化碳通过钒氧化物', p.title_en = 'METHOD FOR REDUCING THE CARBON DIOXIDE INTO CARBON MONOXIDE BY VANADIUM OXIDES', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种方法用于处理气体流包括二氧化碳(542， 642， 742)， 其中减少了CO2的氧化钒氧化物以生产气体流出物包含CO(543， 643，743)。 钒氧化物有利地再生在接触还原化合物(532， 632，732)选自有机燃料的化石源，来自生物质，或从合成，最好是甲烷。 本发明还涉及一种生产合成气的方法(533， 633， 733)，其中钒氧化物的还原通过至少一种还原性化合物(532， 632，732)如上所述。根据本发明，这些方法可用于生产二氢。 钒氧化物之间的反应和还原化合物或CO2进行高温， 优选地使用太阳能反应器。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a process for treating a gas stream comprising CO2 (542,  642,  742),  in which the CO2 is reduced by oxidation of vanadium oxides to produce a gas effluent comprising CO (543,  643,  743). The vanadium oxides are advantageously regenerated on contact with a reducing compound (532,  632,  732) chosen from organic fuels of fossil origin,  originating from biomass,  or from synthesis,  preferably methane. The invention also relates to a process for producing syngas (533,  633,  733) in which vanadium oxides are reduced by means of at least one reducing compound (532,  632,  732) as described above. According to the invention,  these processes can be used for producing dihydrogen. The reactions between the vanadium oxides and the reducing compound or the CO2 are carried out at high temperature,  preferably using a solar reactor.', p.application_date = '2012-09-20 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'FR2995600B1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/40', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WOEP15074712'}) SET p.application_no = 'WOEP15074712', p.title_cn = '液态氢的制造方法', p.title_en = 'PROCESS FOR PRODUCING LIQUID HYDROGEN', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种用于连续生产的液氢的集成方法， 包括(a)制备气态氢的电解； 和(b)中的所述气态氢的液化氢液化单元， 液化单元基本上由可再生来源的能量驱动； 和， (c)需要额外的功率时， 使用过程中产生的电能在电能和氢气集成电解产生的共 方法包括 :  (d)电解金属盐或金属盐和水的混合物成相应的金属或金属， 酸或酸， 和氧气(蓄电相)， 和(e)中制备气态氢和回收电再生反应的金属(S)和酸(S) 步骤(d)(再生相)； 其中产生的气态氢的至少一部分在步骤(e)中用于步骤(b)的方法。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to an integrated process for continuous production of liquid hydrogen,  comprising (a) producing gaseous hydrogen by electrolysis;  and (b) liquefying said gaseous hydrogen in a hydrogen liquefaction unit,  which liquefaction unit is powered by energy essentially from renewable sources;  and,  (c) when additional power is needed,  using electrical energy generated in a process in which electrical energy and hydrogen are co-generated by an integrated electrolysis process comprising :  (d) electrolysing a metal salt or mixture of metal salts and water into the corresponding metal or metals,  acid or acids,  and oxygen (electricity storage phase),  and (e) producing gaseous hydrogen and recovering electricity in a regeneration reaction of the metal (s) and acid(s) of step (d) (regeneration phase);  wherein at least part of the gaseous hydrogen generated in step (e) is used in step (b) of the process.', p.application_date = '2015-10-26 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016066571A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/08', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WOUS15057053'}) SET p.application_no = 'WOUS15057053', p.title_cn = '甲烷转化合成气，乙烷和乙烯', p.title_en = 'CONVERSION OF METHANE AND ETHANE TO SYNGAS AND ETHYLENE', p.abstract_cn = '甲烷转化的方法和乙烷转化为合成气和乙烯。 示例性方法可包括提供甲烷的反应混合物， 乙烷， 氧，二氧化碳和使所述反应混合物与催化剂，其包括至少一种金属氧化物。 所述方法可以组合工艺，在该氧化干重整甲烷和乙烷脱氢成乙烯与 二氧化碳和氧的同时发生。', p.abstract_en = 'Processes for conversion of methane and ethane into syngas and ethylene are provided. An exemplary process can include providing a reaction mixture of methane,  ethane,  oxygen,  and carbon dioxide and contacting the reaction mixture with a catalyst that includes at least one metal oxide. The processes can be combined processes in which oxidative dry reforming of methane and dehydrogenation of ethane to ethylene with carbon dioxide and oxygen occur concurrently.', p.application_date = '2015-10-23 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016069389A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'AU2012275131'}) SET p.application_no = 'AU2012275131', p.title_cn = '独立的烟气再循环风机', p.title_en = 'Stand-alone flue gas recirculation fan', p.abstract_cn = '形成的烃重整器中污染物降低使用烟气再循环。 在典型的系统和方法， 一种烃重整器具有进风从进风风机，其中所述烃重整器产生烟道气的排放。 烟气的一部分废气反馈到引风机， 所述烟气再循环(“fgr”)扇机将烟气排气的一部分位于下游的诱导 引风机。 烟气的部分被拉向进气导管进气风机的下游， 减少烃重整器内的火焰温度，减少NOx的形成。', p.abstract_en = 'The formation of pollutants in a hydrocarbon reformer is reduced by use of flue gas recirculation. In typical systems and methods,  a hydrocarbon reformer has air intake from an air intake fan where the hydrocarbon reformer produces flue gas exhaust. A portion of the flue gas exhaust is fed into an induced draft fan,  wherein a flue gas recirculation ("FGR") fan draws a portion of the flue gas exhaust located downstream of the induced draft fan. The portion of the flue gas is drawn towards an air intake conduit downstream of the air intake fan,  which reduces a flame temperature within the hydrocarbon reformer and reduces the formation of NOX.', p.application_date = '2012-06-29 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'AU2012275131B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/24', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14757761'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14757761', p.title_cn = '同时制氢的零排放硫磺回收工艺', p.title_en = 'Zero emissions sulphur recovery process with concurrent hydrogen production', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种从含H2S的气体物流中同时生产氢和硫的方法，该方法具有零排放。 该方法包括H2S热氧化裂解形成H2和S2。 优选地，使用富氧空气，优选纯氧进行氧化。 原料中H2S/O2的比例高于2 : 1，优选在3 : 1-5 : 1的范围内。', p.abstract_en = 'Disclosed is a process for the concurrent production of hydrogen and sulphur from a H2S-containing gas stream,  with zero emissions. The method comprises the thermal oxidative cracking of H2S so as to form H2 and S2. Preferably,  the oxidation is conducted using oxygen-enriched air,  preferably pure oxygen. The ratio H2S/O2 in the feedstock is higher than 2 : 1,  preferably in the range of 3 : 1-5 : 1.', p.application_date = '2015-12-23 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US20160122184A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/06', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201410300016.4'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201410300016.4', p.title_cn = '一种带有自搅拌笼的制氢装置', p.title_en = 'A kind of self- stirs the cage hydrogen producing device', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种带有自搅拌笼的制氢装置，包括密封反应腔，氢气排出管道，气动旋转叶片，搅拌笼，搅拌笼轴，燃料储料仓，进料系统和真空系统；所述密封反应腔内包括反应液体仓，所述氢气排出管道截面为方形，在该管道的路径上设置气动旋转叶片，该气动旋转叶片的旋转轴可传动的连接到搅拌笼轴，带动搅拌笼轴旋转，该搅拌笼至少部分地浸入到反应液体仓的液面以下，该搅拌笼至少一端的轴为中空轴，连通搅拌笼和密封反应腔的燃料进料口，所述燃料储料仓为可密封结构，进料系统包括液相进料系统和燃料进料系统，真空系统用来给密封腔抽真空。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a hydrogen production device with a self-stirring cage. The device comprises a sealed reaction cavity,  a hydrogen outlet pipeline,  pneumatic rotating vanes,  a stirring cage,  a stirring cage shaft,  a fuel storage bin,  a feeding system and a vacuum system,  wherein the sealed reaction cavity comprises a reacting liquid bin;  the hydrogen outlet pipeline has a square section,  and the pneumatic rotating vanes are arranged on the path of the pipeline;  the rotating shaft of the pneumatic rotating vanes is connected to the stirring cage shaft in a transmission manner,  and is capable of driving the stirring cage shaft to rotate;  at least part of the stirring cage is immersed below the liquid surface of the reacting liquid bin;  the shaft of at least one end of the stirring cage is hollow,  and is communicated with the stirring cage and the fuel feeding port of the sealed reaction cavity;  the fuel storage bin is of a sealable structure;  the feeding system comprises a liquid-phase feeding system and a fuel feeding system;  and the vacuum system is used for vacuumizing the sealed cavity.', p.application_date = '2014-06-27 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN104192797B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/08', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201380028592.1'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201380028592.1', p.title_cn = '具有浮动催化剂的燃料处理器', p.title_en = 'With a floating catalyst of the fuel processor', p.abstract_cn = '具有浮动催化剂的燃料处理器具有由分隔壁分隔开的反应气体通道和产物气体通道，所述壁是在一端固定且在另一端自由的，以允许差异化热膨胀。催化剂靠近所述自由端收纳在所述分隔壁内部。外壁至少部分地围绕所述分隔壁并且所述分隔壁的所述固定端可以接合到所述外壁。所述燃料处理器可以包括多个同心管，并且可以包含位于所述分离器壁内部的第三管。所述气体通道设置有气体可渗透支撑结构，例如，相对于所述外壁支撑所述分隔壁的湍流增强器或翅片，但是所述支撑结构仅结合到一个管以便允许所述壁的差异化热膨胀。', p.abstract_en = 'A fuel processor with a floating catalyst has a reactant gas passage and a product gas passage separated by a separating wall which is fixed at one end and free at the other end,  to permit differential thermal expansion. The catalyst is received inside the separating wall proximate to the free end. An outer wall at least partially surrounds the separating wall and the fixed end of the separating wall may be joined to the outer wall. The fuel processor may comprise a plurality of concentric tubes,  and may include a third tube located inside the separator wall. The gas passages are provided with gas permeable support structures such as turbulizers or fins which support the separating wall relative to the outer wall,  but the support structures are bonded to only one tube in order to permit differential thermal expansion of the walls.', p.application_date = '2013-05-29 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN104350006B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/32', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201510998227.4'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201510998227.4', p.title_cn = '核能激光二氧化钛制氢氧方法', p.title_en = 'Method for preparing hydrogen and oxygen by nuclear energy,  laser and titanium dioxide', p.abstract_cn = '核能激光二氧化钛制氢方法是新能源及减少温室气体排放环境保护及军事领域，将核能转换更加便于实用的氢氧能源，将核电站发出的电能，用激光发生装置转换成激光，用光缆将激光导入水下在二氧化钛的催化作用下生产出的氢气与氧气，为了安全起见，在制氢氧过程中，每个激光制氢装置的直径，只能象蜂巢的直径大小，只能用1根光纤，避免高热产生，产生的氢氧在水的作用下会迅速降温及上浮，上部有锥顶桶体将其收集并马上分离，锥顶桶体中总保持最少的氢氧状并远离人员和其它设备，整个制氢氧过程都是在水下进行的，制氢氧设备的阀门是气动阀，仪控用的是不易产生火花的低压电，可自行下潜，驱动制氢氧设备上浮是压缩空气，因此是安全的。', p.abstract_en = 'A method for preparing hydrogen and oxygen by nuclear energy,  laser and titanium dioxide belongs to the fields of novel energy and greenhouse gas emission reduction environment protection as well as military,  wherein the nuclear energy is converted into more practical hydrogen and oxygen energy,  power energy generated by a nuclear power plant is converted into laser by using a laser generation device,  the laser is conducted into water by using an optical cable and generates hydrogen and oxygen under the catalytic action of titanium dioxide,  for safety,  in the process of preparing the hydrogen and oxygen,  the diameter of each hydrogen preparation laser device can only be the size like that of a honeycomb,  only one piece of optical cable can be used,  high heat is prevented from occurring,  the generated hydrogen and oxygen are quickly cooled and float under the action of water,  an tapered-top barrel at the upper part can collect the hydrogen and oxygen and quickly separate the hydrogen and oxygen,  the inner part of the tapered-top barrel is always kept in a state with least hydrogen and oxygen,  and is kept away from personnel and other devices,  the whole hydrogen and oxygen preparation process is performed in the water,  a valve of a hydrogen and oxygen preparation device is a pneumatic valve,  low voltage not liable to generate sparks is used for instrument control,  automatic diving is realized,  and compressed air is used for driving the hydrogen and oxygen preparation device to float,  so that the method is safe.', p.application_date = '2015-12-26 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105540540A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201510683405.4'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201510683405.4', p.title_cn = '氢精制方法', p.title_en = 'Method for refining hydrogen', p.abstract_cn = '本发明提供一种氢精制方法，其为基于氢精制装置而进行的氢精制方法，所述氢精制方法可减少包含未透过钯合金细管的杂质的气体的取出量，可从二次侧空间高效地取出纯氢，所述氢精制装置的结构如下，利用一端被封闭的钯合金细管与支撑该细管的开口端的管板，将单元的内部隔开为一次侧空间和二次侧空间，将包含杂质的氢从一次侧空间导入，透过钯合金细管从二次侧空间取出纯氢。使用杂质的浓度为1000ppm以下的氢作为原料氢，将包含未透过钯合金细管的杂质的气体以原料氢的导入流量的10％以下的流量从一次侧空间取出。或者，将包含未透过钯合金细管的杂质的气体按照与原料氢中所含杂质的含有率对应的流量从一次侧空间取出。', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention is to provide a method for refining hydrogen with a hydrogen refining device in which the inside of a cell is divided into a primary side space and a secondary side space by palladium alloy capillaries each having one end being closed and a tube sheet supporting the open end of the palladium alloy capillaries,  in which impurity-containing hydrogen is introduced from the primary side space to allow hydrogen to permeate the palladium alloy capillaries so as to collect pure hydrogen from the secondary side space. The method for refining hydrogen has a capability of decreasing the removed amount of gas containing impurities and efficiently collecting pure hydrogen from the secondary side space. From hydrogen with 1000 ppm or less of impurities as raw material hydrogen,  gas containing impurities that does not penetrate the palladium alloy capillaries is removed from the primary side space at the flow rate of 10% or less of the introduction flow rate of the raw material hydrogen. Furthermore,  gas containing impurities that does not penetrate the palladium alloy capillaries is removed from the primary side space at a flow rate based on the content of impurities contained in raw material hydrogen.', p.application_date = '2015-10-20 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105540541A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/56', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201510886019.5'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201510886019.5', p.title_cn = 'Mn-Cu/Al-PILM脱氧剂的制备工艺', p.title_en = 'Preparation process of Mn-Cu/Al-PILM deoxidizing agent', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种Mn-Cu/Al-PILM脱氧剂的制备工艺，本发明制备的Al-柱撑蒙脱土颗粒比较均匀, 峰强增加最大，Al2O3进入到蒙脱土层间, 不会破坏蒙脱土原有的结构。并以所制备的Al-PILM为载体, Mn和Cu过渡金属元素为组分, 用浸渍法制备出Mn-Cu/Al-PILM脱氧剂, 脱氧容量和脱氧深度、一在同类产品中有较大提高, 可以满足工业需求。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention discloses a preparation process of a Mn-Cu/Al-PILM deoxidizing agent. The Al-pillared montmorillonite particles prepared by the process provided by the invention are uniform,  the peak intensity increases maximumly,  and Al2O3 enters the interlayer of montmorillonite without damaging the original structure of montmorillonite. Also,  the prepared Al-PILM is adopted as the carrier,  Mn and Cu are taken as the transition metal elements to prepare the Mn-Cu/Al-PILM deoxidizing agent by impregnation method,  the deoxidation capacity and deoxidation depth of the deoxidizing agent are greatly improved among similar products,  thus being able to meet the industrial demand.', p.application_date = '2015-12-07 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105540542A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/56', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201520980335.4'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201520980335.4', p.title_cn = '一种利用碳化物的装置', p.title_en = 'Utilize device of carbide', p.abstract_cn = '本实用新型涉及一种利用碳化物的装置，包括反应炉，原料仓，固体成品仓，催化剂或氧化剂，其中原料仓通过进料装置连接于反应炉，成品仓通过出料装置连接反应炉，反应炉为高温炉。本实用新型利用碳化物的装置通过设置高温反应炉，在原料仓中加入不同的原料，再用催化剂或氧化剂反应得到固体物、气体，使碳化物能联合生产不同的物质，节省了资源，节约了成本，有效利用反应后的物质，提高了经济效益。', p.abstract_en = 'The utility model relates to an utilize device of carbide (b),  (b) be including the reacting furnace,  former feed bin,  and solid finished product storehouse,  catalyst or oxidant,  wherein former feed bin passes through feed arrangement and connects in the reacting furnace,  and discharging device ligation stove is passed through in the finished product storehouse,  and the reacting furnace is the high temperature furnace. The utility model discloses utilize device of carbide is through setting up the pyroreaction stove,  and different raw materialss is gone into by china and canada at former feed bin,  and reuse catalyst or oxidant reaction obtain solids,  gas,  make the different material of carbide ability joint production,  have saved the resource,  have practiced thrift the cost,  effectively utilize the reacted material,  have improved economic benefits.', p.application_date = '2015-12-02 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN205204814U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/06', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201490000542.2'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201490000542.2', p.title_cn = '生产合成气的设备', p.title_en = 'Equipment of production synthetic gas', p.abstract_cn = '为了由含有烃类的原料气体生产包含氢气和一氧化碳的合成气，本实用新型公开了一种生产合成气的设备，其具有将原料气体分流为第一部分料流(T1)和第二部分料流(T2)的分流器，其中将第一部分料流(T1)供给至蒸汽重整器(13)，在所述蒸汽重整器(13)中其与蒸汽一起被催化转化从而获得包含氢气和碳氧化物的气体料流，在蒸汽重整器的下游第一部分料流(T1)又与第二部分料流(T2)合并，其中将合并的气体料流供给至自热重整器(32)，在自热重整器(32)中将合并的气体料流与含氧气体自热重整为合成气。将第一部分料流(T1)直接引入蒸汽重整器(13)中，并且第二部分料流(T2)在通过自热重整器(32)之前被引导通过预重整器(23)。', p.abstract_en = 'The synthetic gas that contains hydrogen and carbon monoxide for the production of the unstripped gas by containing the hydro carbons,  the utility model discloses an equipment of production synthetic gas,  it has the shunt for first portion material stream (T1) and second portion material stream (T2) with raw materials gas diffluence,  and wherein flow (T1) with the first portion material and supply with to steam reformer (13) it is flowed by the gaseous material that catalytic conversion obtained to contain hydrogen and oxides of carbon with steam together in thereby for steam reformer (13),  flows (T1) at the low reaches of steam reformer first portion material and flows (T2) with the second portion material again and merge,  and the gaseous material that wherein will merge flows to be supplied with to self -heating reformer (32),  and the gaseous material that will merge in self -heating reformer (32) flows and is the synthetic gas with oxygen containing gas from the thermal reforming. In first portion material stream (T1) direct entry steam reformer (13) to the second portion material flows (T2) and is being passed through reformer (23) in advance by the guide before through self -heating reformer (32).', p.application_date = '2014-02-11 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN205204815U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'DE602011024320'}) SET p.application_no = 'DE602011024320', p.title_cn = '合成气生产，通过使用膜技术', p.title_en = 'SYNGAS PRODUCTION THROUGH THE USE OF MEMBRANE TECHNOLOGIES', p.abstract_cn = '污染的天然气流(11)的具有显著量的二氧化碳可以有效和更经济地处理，以创建合成气(16)。可用的源(1)的烟气，否则分散到大气中结合有这种含CO2天然气流(11)使得该方法更经济，高效的通过多个进料流的创建(14，27，34)结合，以将复合接近相等的甲烷和二氧化碳的混合物到等离子体反应器(15)或将产生合成气等。当与费-托合成反应器(40)，全过程提供了一种特别高效和经济的方法，用于生产合成液态烃。', p.abstract_en = 'Streams (11) of natural gas contaminated with significant amounts of carbon dioxide can be efficiently and economically processed to create Syngas (16). An available source (1) of flue gas that might otherwise be dispersed into the atmosphere in conjunction with such a CO2-laden natural gas stream (11) renders the process even more economical and efficient through the creation of multiple feedstreams (14,  27,  34) that are combined to deliver a composite near equal mixture of methane and CO2 to a plasma reactor (15) or the like that will generate Syngas. When coupled with a Fischer-Tropsch reactor (40),  the overall process provides a particularly efficient and economical process for producing synthetic liquid hydrocarbons.', p.application_date = '2011-06-29 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'DE602011024320T2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/34', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'EP10790685'}) SET p.application_no = 'EP10790685', p.title_cn = '合成气的生产方法和氢气从试剂包含液体烃， 气态烃类和/或含氧化合物，也衍生自生物质，通过非集成膜反应器', p.title_en = 'PROCESS FOR THE PRODUCTION OF SYNGAS AND HYDROGEN STARTING FROM REAGENTS COMPRISING LIQUID HYDROCARBONS,  GASEOUS HYDROCARBONS,  AND/OR OXYGENATED COMPOUNDS,  ALSO DERIVING FROM BIOMASSES,  BY MEANS OF A NON-INTEGRATED MEMBRANE REACTOR', p.abstract_cn = '合成气的生产方法和氢气从液体烃，气态烃和/或含氧化合物，还由衍生自生物质，及其混合物，设想即架构中所使用膜反应器连续反应和分离阶段。该方法包括在一段预加热的试剂，若干段短接触时间的催化部分氧化制造合成气和氢气的数量产生的氢气通过膜阶段以及后续的分离，热回收段，产生的二氧化碳除去部分和部分进行冷却和清除冷凝液。任选地，该方法包括一段获得的氢气通过变压吸附(PSA)净化，并产生净化气体介质热值。此外，所述的试剂和方法包括加氢脱硫段可以包括CO2转化段通过倒水生成氢气和(rwgs)水煤气变换反应。', p.abstract_en = 'A process for the production of syngas and hydrogen starting from liquid hydrocarbons,  gaseous hydrocarbons and/or oxygenated compounds,  also deriving from biomasses,  and mixtures thereof,  envisages recourse to a membrane reactor in an architecture that uses a succession of reaction and separation stages. The process includes a section for pre-heating the reagents,  a number of sections for short-contact-time catalytic partial oxidation for producing syngas and hydrogen in a number of stages followed by separation of hydrogen produced via membranes,  a thermal-recovery section,  a section for removing produced carbon dioxide,  and a section for cooling and removing condensate. Optionally,  the process includes a section for purifying obtained hydrogen via pressure-swing adsorption (PSA) and generating purge gas with medium calorific value. Furthermore,  the process includes a section for hydrodesulphuration of the reagents and could include a section for conversion of the CO2 and H2 produced by a reverse-water-gas-shift (RWGS) reaction.', p.application_date = '2010-11-04 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'EP2566810B1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'EP14739896'}) SET p.application_no = 'EP14739896', p.title_cn = '电化学净化装置和氢组成的，具有多个级的压缩', p.title_en = 'DEVICE FOR THE ELECTROCHEMICAL PURIFICATION AND COMPRESSION OF HYDROGEN HAVING A PLURALITY OF STAGES', p.abstract_cn = '本装置具有多个级的电化学压缩机，可加压的氢气流通过所述装置。它包括 : 氢气入口和出口；至少两个(ame)膜电极组件，每个膜电极组件形成一个电化学电池；所述的过滤嘴并且按照Ames被设置以将穿过氢气流，并且在电气上彼此串联连接；每个所述的过滤嘴并且按照Ames包括有源表面设计成允许氢气发生还原反应；所述的过滤嘴并且按照Ames具有活性表面彼此分离，降低中的氢气流动方向。', p.abstract_en = 'This device forms an electrochemical compressor having a plurality of stages,  capable of pressurising hydrogen flowing through said device. It comprises :  a hydrogen inlet and outlet;  at least two membrane-electrode assemblies (AME),  each membrane-electrode assembly forming an electrochemical cell;  said AMEs being arranged so as to be traversed by a hydrogen stream,  and being electrically connected to each other in series;  each of the AMEs comprising an active surface designed to allow hydrogen redox reactions to take place;  The AMEs have active surfaces separate from each other,  and decreasing in the direction of flow of the hydrogen.', p.application_date = '2014-06-26 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'EP3013738A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'EP14191287'}) SET p.application_no = 'EP14191287', p.title_cn = '催化剂包含氟化金属氧化物，制造工艺和加氢方法', p.title_en = 'Catalyst comprising fluorinated metal oxide,  manufacture process and hydrogenation process', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种催化剂的制造方法，包括氟化金属氧化物， 催化剂包括氟化的金属氧化物，和催化加氢工艺。', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention concerns a process for the manufacture of a catalyst comprising a fluorinated metal oxide,  a catalyst comprising a fluorinated metal oxide,  and a catalytic hydrogenation process.', p.application_date = '2014-10-31 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'EP3015423A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'KR1020107023070'}) SET p.application_no = 'KR1020107023070', p.title_cn = '固体化合物， 自维持燃烧含硼氮烷和/或polyaminoborane的氢气发生器和至少一个无机氧化剂，和用于产生氢气的方法', p.title_en = 'SOLID COMPOUNDS,  SELF-SUSTAINING COMBUSTION HYDROGEN GENERATORS CONTAINING BORAZANE AND/OR POLYAMINOBORANE AND AT LEAST ONE INORGANIC OXIDANT,  AND METHOD FOR GENERATING HYDROGEN', p.abstract_cn = '本发明的主题为固体的化合物可通过自维持燃烧反应产生氢. 其组合物包括硼氮烷和/或polyaminoborane和至少一种无机氧化剂. 有利地选自硝酸铵. 碱式金属硝酸盐. 碱性碱土金属硝酸盐. 金属硝酸盐. 金属氧化物. dinitramines家族以及它们的混合物的氧化剂. 本发明还涉及产生氢气的自维持燃烧至少一种该类化合物.', p.abstract_en = 'The main subject of the present invention are solid compounds capable of generating hydrogen by a self-sustaining combustion reaction. Their composition comprises borazane and/or polyaminoborane and at least one inorganic oxidant,  advantageously chosen from ammonium nitrate,  alkali metal nitrates,  alkaline-earth metal nitrates,  metal nitrates,  metal oxides,  oxidants of the family of dinitramines and mixtures thereof. It also relates to the generation of hydrogen by self-sustaining combustion of at least one such compound.', p.application_date = '2009-04-16 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'KR101620424B1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'KR1020140141738'}) SET p.application_no = 'KR1020140141738', p.title_cn = '用于收集氢气的方法产生的气体从湿法冶金方法和从矿石回收有价值金属的方法', p.title_en = 'METHOD FOR COLLECTING HYDROGEN GAS PRODUCED FROM HYDROMETALLURGICAL PROCESS AND METHOD FOR COLLECTING VALUABLE METAL FROM ORE', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种含有作为有效金属的有效酸浸出金属的浸出工艺中的酸和有效产生金属氢气的反应气体中去除氢回收的方法. 所述放电商品，通过投入金属的有效酸，所述酸原料进行浸出反应，. 所述氢气被顶出，浸出反应步骤的流量测量. 根据流经所述流量测量的氢气产物与酸的六条曲线通过速度控制输入. 以预定流量的氢气所述预定的充电端流量范围的步骤包括控制油门转变成. 具有控制流量和产生氢气的回收方法，包括 : .', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention relates to a method to collect a hydrogen gas produced by a reaction between an acid and a valuable metal in a leaching process to leach the valuable metal using the acid from a raw material containing the valuable metal. The method to collect the hydrogen gas comprises :  a step of performing a leaching reaction between the acid and the valuable metal by inputting the acid into the raw material;  a step of measuring an amount of the hydrogen gas discharged by the leaching reaction;  a step of controlling the amount of the hydrogen gas to be within a predetermined target amount range by controlling a speed of inputting the acid inputted into a reaction bath in accordance with the amount of the measured hydrogen gas;  and a step of collecting the hydrogen gas of which the produced amount is controlled. The purpose of the present invention is to provide the method to collect a constant amount of hydrogen gas in order to reuse the hydrogen gas produced in the leaching process for various processes.', p.application_date = '2014-10-20 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'KR101620724B1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'BR112012020279'}) SET p.application_no = 'BR112012020279', p.title_cn = '系统化学反应器，处理组合物的方法和处理烃的方法', p.title_en = 'SYSTEM CHEMICAL REACTOR,  METHOD TO PROCESS A COMPOSITION hidrogenoHIDROGENO AND METHOD TO PROCESS A HYDRO-CARBON', p.abstract_cn = '用于生产氢基燃料和结构元件的具有压力和传热特征的反应器容器，以及相关的系统和方法。 根据特定实施例的代表性反应器系统包括第一反应区和定位成将热导入第一反应区的热路径，连接到第一反应区的反应物源，以及连接成循环加压第一反应区的第一致动器。 该系统还可包括与第一反应区流体连通的第二反应区， 连接在第一和第二反应区之间以控制其间的流速的阀，以及与第二反应区流体连通以循环加压第二反应区的第二致动器。 第一热交换器定位成将热量从离开第一反应区的第一产物引导到进入第一反应区的反应物， 以及第二热交换器，其定位成将热量从离开第二反应区的第二产物引导至进入第一反应区的反应物。 控制器耦合到第一和第二致动器，并且用指令编程，所述指令在被执行时至少部分地基于来自第二反应区的第二产物的流速以协调的方式控制第一和第二致动器。', p.abstract_en = 'Reactor vessels with pressure and heat transfer features for producing hydrogen-based fuels and structural elements,  and associated systems and methods. A representative reactor system in accordance with a particular embodiment includes a first reaction zone and a heat path positioned to direct heat into the first reaction zone,  a reactant source coupled to the first reaction zone,  and a first actuator coupled to cyclically pressurize the first reaction zone. The system can further include a second reaction zone in fluid communication with the first,  a valve coupled between the first and second reaction zones to control a flow rate therebetween,  and a second actuator coupled in fluid communication with the second reaction zone to cyclically pressurize the second reaction zone. A first heat exchanger is positioned to direct heat from a first product leaving the first reaction zone to a reactant entering the first reaction zone,  and a second heat exchanger is positioned to direct heat from a second product leaving the second reaction zone to the reactant entering the first reaction zone. A controller is coupled to the first and second actuators and is programmed with instructions that,  when executed,  control the first and second actuators in a coordinated manner based at least in part on a flow rate of the second product from the second reaction zone.', p.application_date = '2011-02-14 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'BRPI1220279A2', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'BR112012020286'}) SET p.application_no = 'BR112012020286', p.title_cn = '用于燃料生产的具有可透射表面的反应器花瓶，结构氢基和元件，以及系统关联件和方法', p.title_en = 'VASES OF REACTORS WITH TRANSMISSIBLE SURFACES FOR THE FUEL PRODUCTION THE STRUCTURAL HYDROGEN BASE AND ELEMENTS,  AND SYSTEMS ASSOCIATES AND METHODS', p.abstract_cn = '用于生产氢基燃料和结构元件的具有透射表面的反应器容器，以及相关的系统和方法。 根据特定实施例的化学反应器包括具有反应区的反应器容器，与反应区流体连通地连接的氢供体源，以及与反应区流体连通地连接的蒸汽源。 该反应器还包括在反应区的透射表面，该透射表面对进入反应区的反应物和/或进入反应区的辐射能是透射的。', p.abstract_en = 'Reactor vessels with transmissive surfaces for producing hydrogen-based fuels and structural elements,  and associated systems and methods. A chemical reactor in accordance with a particular embodiment includes a reactor vessel having a reaction zone,  a hydrogen donor source coupled in fluid communication with the reaction zone,  and a steam source coupled in fluid communication with the reaction zone. The reactor further includes a transmissive surface at the reaction zone,  with the transmissive surface being transmissive to a reactant entering the reaction zone and/or radiant energy entering the reaction zone.', p.application_date = '2011-02-14 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'BRPI1220286A2', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/36', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'BR112012020288'}) SET p.application_no = 'BR112012020288', p.title_cn = '有效生产氢燃料和结构材料的化学方法和反应器以及相关的系统和方法', p.title_en = 'CHEMICAL PROCESSES AND REACTORS TO PRODUCE HYDROGEN FUELS AND STRUCTURAL MATERIALS EFFICIENT,  AND SYSTEMS AND METHODS ASSOCIATES', p.abstract_cn = '本公开涉及提供各种类型燃料的有效喷射，点火和完全燃烧的集成喷射器/点火器。 这种喷射器/点火器的一个例子可以包括具有与喷嘴部分相对的基部的主体。 基部将燃料接收到主体中，并且喷嘴部可定位成邻近燃烧室。 喷射器还包括由喷嘴部分承载的阀，该阀可在关闭位置和打开位置之间移动以将燃料喷射到燃烧室中。 致动器联接到阀并且朝向基部纵向延伸穿过主体，并且驱动器由主体承载并且可在第一位置和第二位置之间移动。 捕获由燃烧和相关燃烧事件产生的废热的热化学再生，并将其投入到吸热反应中以提高燃烧事件的效率。 以氢为特征的燃料可以用作散热器。', p.abstract_en = 'The present disclosure is directed to integrated injector/igniters providing efficient injection,  ignition,  and complete combustion of various types of fuels. One example of such an injectors/igniter can include a body having a base portion opposite a nozzle portion. The base portion receives the fuel into the body and the nozzle portion can be positioned adjacent to the combustion chamber. The injector further includes a valve carried by the nozzle portion that is movable between a closed position and an open position to inject the fuel into the combustion chamber. An actuator is coupled the valve and extends longitudinally through the body towards the base portion,  and a driver is carried by the body and is movable between a first position and a second position. Thermochemical regeneration of waste heat produced by combustion and associated combustion events is captured and invested in endothermic reactions to improve efficiency of the combustion event. Hydrogen characterized fuel may be used as a heat sink.', p.application_date = '2011-02-14 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'BRPI1220288A2', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/36', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CA2790287'}) SET p.application_no = 'CA2790287', p.title_cn = '用于生产氢的方法针对存储和运输', p.title_en = 'METHOD FOR PRODUCING HYDROGEN AIMED AT STORAGE AND TRANSPORTATION', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种用于储存和运输氢的生产方法，通过该氢用于储存和运输顺利促进必需的有机化学氢化物可以高效地生产方法在工业规模上以成本低。具体公开的是一种用于储存和运输氢的制造方法通过有机化学氢化物的方法，其特征在于 : 反应气体，它是通过调节合成气的氢浓度通过重整反应合成30-70体积%通过变换反应，作为反应氢源在氢化芳族化合物的步骤；和氢化芳族化合物从反应混合物中分离纯化得到在加氢步骤。', p.abstract_en = 'Disclosed is a method for producing hydrogen for storage and transportation,  by which hydrogen for storage and transportation necessary for smoothly promoting an organic chemical hydride method can be efficiently produced on a commercial scale at low cost. Specifically disclosed is a method for producing hydrogen for storage and transportation by an organic chemical hydride method,  which is characterized in that :  a reaction gas,  which is obtained by adjusting the hydrogen concentration of a synthesis gas synthesized by a reforming reaction to 30-70 vol% by a shift reaction,  is used as a hydrogen source for a reaction in a hydrogenation step of an aromatic compound;  and that a hydrogenated aromatic compound is separated and purified from the reaction mixture that is obtained in the hydrogenation step.', p.application_date = '2011-03-24 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CA2790287C', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CA2829868'}) SET p.application_no = 'CA2829868', p.title_cn = '非发射的CO2用于合成气体的制造方法', p.title_en = 'NON-CO2 EMITTING MANUFACTURING METHOD FOR SYNTHESIS GAS', p.abstract_cn = '提供一种非发射的CO2合成气的制造方法。本方法是一种制造合成气的方法通过重整烃类气体，包括 : 提供一种轻烃燃气加入蒸汽和/或二氧化碳的催化剂的填充管的侧一种壳和管热交换器型的重整器；使重整反应在壳体侧通过循环加热介质，如熔盐，具有太阳热或原子能核热作为热源；提取从产生的二氧化碳气体排出管侧和回收相同的上游所述管侧。', p.abstract_en = 'Provided is a non-CO2 emitting manufacturing method for synthesis gas. This method is a method for manufacturing synthesis gas by reforming hydrocarbon gas,  and includes :  supplying a light hydrocarbon gas added with steam and/or carbon dioxide to the side of a catalyst filled tube of a shell & tube heat exchanger type reformer;  causing a reforming reaction at the shell side by circulating a heating medium,  such as a molten salt,  having solar heat or nuclear heat of atomic energy as a heat source;  and extracting carbon dioxide from the produced gas exhausted from the tube side and recycling the same to the upstream of the tube side.', p.application_date = '2012-03-21 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CA2829868C', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14376840'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14376840', p.title_cn = '用于处理液体和/或糊状烃材料的方法、系统和装置', p.title_en = 'Process,  system and installation for treating liquid and/or pasty hydrocarbon materials', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种处理液体和/或糊状烃材料，更具体地是燃料油，更具体地是重油的方法，其中烃材料首先被带到自燃温度，然后与受控量的氧混合，以获得第一气态物流和非气态物流，更具体地是包括固体烃分子的固体物流，然后固体烃分子被CO2的气态物流氧化，以获得第二气态物流。 然后混合第一和第二气态物流，以获得包含具有高能量值的一氧化碳的第三气态物流。 本发明还涉及实现根据本发明的方法的系统和实现这种系统的装置。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a process for treating liquid and/or pasty hydrocarbon materials,  more particularly fuel oil,  more particularly still heavy fuel oil,  in which the hydrocarbon materials are firstly brought to the autoignition temperature,  then mixed with a controlled amount of oxygen in order to obtain a first gaseous stream and a non-gaseous mass,  more particularly a solid mass,  comprising solid hydrocarbon molecules which are then oxidized by a gaseous stream of CO2 in order to obtain a second gaseous stream. The first and second gaseous streams are then mixed in order to obtain a third gaseous stream comprising carbon monoxide having a high energy value. The invention also relates to a system implementing the process according to the invention and an installation implementing such a system.', p.application_date = '2013-02-05 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9327971B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US12544099'}) SET p.application_no = 'US12544099', p.title_cn = '生产超高纯高压氢的系统和方法', p.title_en = 'Systems and processes for producing ultrapure,  high pressure hydrogen', p.abstract_cn = '在各种实施方案中，使包括甲烷的进料物流反应以产生合成气。 合成气可进一步加工以产生超纯高压氢气物流。', p.abstract_en = 'In various implementations,  feed streams that include methane are reacted to produce synthesis gas. The synthesis gas may be further processed to produce ultrapure,  high-pressure hydrogen streams.', p.application_date = '2009-08-19 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9327972B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 3, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'DE602007048139'}) SET p.application_no = 'DE602007048139', p.title_cn = '减少氨的产生在镍催化剂的重整器', p.title_en = 'REDUCED GENERATION OF AMMONIA IN NICKEL CATALYST OF REFORMER', p.abstract_cn = '重整天然气在不产生过量的氨，即使天然气包括多达14%的氮，重整器中实现，包括管(75)，其具有外腔(78)与其中的催化剂，一种第一级(80)具有大约10%和大约25%之间的镍催化剂，一种第二级(81)的催化剂具有小于约10%的镍，和一个末级(82)具有2%或更低的低浓度铑催化剂。', p.abstract_en = 'Reformation of natural gas without excessive production of ammonia,  even if the natural gas includes as much as 14% nitrogen,  is achieved in reformers including tubes (75) having outer chambers (78) with catalysts therein,  a first stage (80) of catalyst having between about 10% and about 25% nickel,  a second stage (81) of catalyst having less than 10% nickel,  and a final stage (82) having 2% or less rhodium catalyst of a low concentration.', p.application_date = '2007-10-25 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'DE602007048139T2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'KR1020147003283'}) SET p.application_no = 'KR1020147003283', p.title_cn = '生产氢气的方法通过多步铜氯的热化学循环', p.title_en = 'HYDROGEN PRODUCTION METHOD BY MULTI-STEP COPPER-CHLORINE THERMOCHEMICAL CYCLE', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种从氢气和氧气的热化学生产方法通过低温水. 多步. 封闭. 环状铜-铜-氯(Cl)方法，它涉及铜与氯气反应的化合物. 用于生产氢的方法，采用Cu-Cl热化学循环由四个热反应和电化学反应，将一个单元操作. 所述周期包括六个步骤 : (1)氢生产步骤. (2)将铜生产步骤. (3)干燥步骤. (4)生产氯化氢的步骤. (5)分解步骤. (6)生产步骤中氧气. 该顺序进程号的净反应是水分解成氢气和氧气，. 氧化铜的生产方法，该方法包括使过热蒸汽，生产的氧氯化铜颗粒包括作为铜的氧化物，氯化氢的反应热化学制氢部分铜-铜-氯(Cl)循环. 本流过式石英反应器中进行反应为固定床式高温和大气压力.', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention discloses a method for thermochemical production of hydrogen and oxygen from water by a low temperature,  multi-step,  closed,  cyclic copper-chlorine (Cu—Cl) process involving the reactions of copper and chlorine compounds. A method for production of hydrogen via Cu—Cl thermochemical cycle consists of four thermal reactions and one electrochemical reaction and one unit operation. The cycle involves six steps :  (1) hydrogen production step;  (2) copper production step;  (3) drying step;  (4) hydrogen chloride production step;  (5) decomposition step;  (6) oxygen production step. The net reaction of the sequential process is the decomposition of water into hydrogen and oxygen. The methods for production of copper oxide which comprises contacting copper chloride particles with superheated steam and production of oxygen comprises reaction of copper oxide with dry chlorine as a part of hydrogen production by thermochemical Copper-Chlorine (Cu—Cl) cycle. The reactions are performed in a flow through type quartz reactor as fixed bed type at high temperature and atmospheric pressure.', p.application_date = '2012-07-09 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'KR101619677B1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/08', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'GC201015703'}) SET p.application_no = 'GC201015703', p.title_cn = '制备含氢气和一氧化碳的气体的方法', p.title_en = 'PROCESS FOR THE PREPARATION OF HYDROGEN AND CARBON MONOXIDE CONTAINING GAS', p.abstract_cn = '由气态碳质原料制备含氢气和一氧化碳的气体的方法，包括以下步骤：(a)气态原料的自热重整，从而获得氢气和一氧化碳的第一气态混合物，(b)气态碳质原料的催化蒸汽重整，从而获得氢气和一氧化碳的第二气态混合物，这是通过将蒸汽和气态碳质原料通过具有蒸汽重整催化剂的第一组多个微通道，并将氢气和一氧化碳的第一气态混合物通过第二组多个微通道来实现的，其中第一组和第二组微通道被定向成使得第一组微通道中蒸汽重整反应所需的热量由来自第二组微通道的对流热交换提供，从而获得含有氢气和一氧化碳的气体作为第二组微通道的流出物。', p.abstract_en = 'Process for the preparation of hydrogen and carbon monoxide containing gas from a gaseous carbonaceous feedstock by performing the following steps : (a) auto-thermal reforming of a gaseous feedstock thereby obtaining a first gaseous mixture of hydrogen and carbon monoxide, (b) catalytic steam reforming of the gaseous carbonaceous feedstock to obtain a second gaseous mixture of hydrogen and carbon monoxide by feeding steam and the gaseous carbonaceous feedstock through a first set of numerous microchannels provided with a steam reforming catalyst and feeding the first gaseous mixture of hydrogen and carbon monoxide through a second set of numerous microchannels,  wherein the first and second set of microchannels are oriented such that the required heat for the steam reforming reaction in the first set of microchannels is provided by convective heat exchange from the second set of microchannels,  thereby obtaining the hydrogen and carbon monoxide containing gas as the effluent of the second set of microchannels.', p.application_date = '2010-04-20 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'GC0004089A', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'GC201015712'}) SET p.application_no = 'GC201015712', p.title_cn = '费-托法', p.title_en = 'FISCHER-TROPSCH PROCESS', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种用于由包含甲烷的原料生产烃产物的方法，其包括以下步骤：-在合成气制造工艺中制备包含具有氢气/一氧化碳摩尔进料比的氢气和一氧化碳的进料合成气，和-使用存在于一个或多个合成气转化反应器中的一个或多个固定床催化剂床在费-托法中使用所述进料合成气，从而获得所述烃产物和残余尾气。所述制造方法包括两个并行操作的合成气制造方法，所述合成气制造方法从相同的包含气态甲烷的原料开始。-一种合成气制造工艺是部分氧化(POX)工艺，其制备具有低于摩尔进料比的氢/一氧化碳[H2/CO]摩尔比的合成气，和-第二合成气制造工艺是热交换重整(HER)工艺，其制备具有高于摩尔进料比的氢/一氧化碳[H2/CO]摩尔比的合成气。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention is directed to a process for the production of hydrocarbon products from a methane comprising feedstock comprising of the steps of : - preparing a feed syngas comprising hydrogen and carbon monoxide having a hydrogen/carbon monoxide molar feed ratio in a syngas manufacturing process and - using the feed syngas in a Fischer-Tropsch process using one or more fixed bed catalyst beds as present in one or more syngas conversion reactors thereby obtaining the hydrocarbon product and an residual tail gas.- The manufacturing process comprises of two parallel operated syngas manufacturing processes starting from the same gaseous methane comprising feedstock. - One syngas manufacturing process is a partial oxidation (POX) process which prepares a syngas having a hydrogen/carbon monoxide [H2/CO] molar ratio below the molar feed ratio and - The second syngas manufacturing process is a heat exchange reforming (HER) process,  which prepares a syngas having a hydrogen/carbon monoxide [H2/CO] molar ratio above the molar feed ratio.', p.application_date = '2010-04-21 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'GC0004092A', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/36', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'GCP200413448'}) SET p.application_no = 'GCP200413448', p.title_cn = '制备合成气的方法、利用合成气制备二甲醚的方法以及制备合成气的炉', p.title_en = 'METHOD FOR PREPARING SYNTHESIS GAS,  METHOD FOR PREPARING DIMETHYL ETHER USING SYNTHESIS GAS,  AND FURNACE FOR PREPARING SYNTHESIS GAS', p.abstract_cn = '公开了一种生产不含烃且所生产的合成气中二氧化碳浓度降低的合成气的方法，根据本发明的方法包括：在用于生产合成气的炉中，使用安装在炉内催化剂层上的催化剂对烃部分燃烧所产生的气体进行重整，并生产以氢气和一氧化碳为主要成分的合成气，其特征在于催化剂层出口处的温度为1100-1300℃，所产生的合成气中二氧化碳的浓度不超过10体积%。', p.abstract_en = 'Disclosed is a process for producing a synthesis gas containing no hydrocarbon and reduced concentration of carbon dioxide among the produced synthesis gas.	The process according to the present invention comprises reforming the gas generated by partial combustion of hydrocarbon using a catalyst in a furnace for generating the synthesis gas mounted on a catalyst layer inside the furnace,  and producing the synthesis gas comprising hydrogen and carbon monoxide as main components,  and is characterized in that the temperature at outlet of the catalyst layer ranges from 1100 to 1300?C and the concentration of carbon dioxide in the produced synthesis gas is not more than 10% by volume.', p.application_date = '2004-09-04 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'GC200413448A0', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'GCP20054359'}) SET p.application_no = 'GCP20054359', p.title_cn = '现场气体用于将常规原油预精炼成预精炼的不含沥青质的炼油厂原料Pa和液态渣油炼油厂原料PB的用途', p.title_en = 'Use Of Field Gas For Pre-Refining Conventional Crude Oil Into A Pre-Refined Asphaltenes-Free Oil Refinery Feedstock Pa And A Liquid Residual Oil Refinery Feedstock PB', p.abstract_cn = '', p.abstract_en = '', p.application_date = '2005-03-01 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'GC20054359A0', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/34', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'GCP20079281'}) SET p.application_no = 'GCP20079281', p.title_cn = '制备气态混合物的方法', p.title_en = 'PROCESS TO PREPARE A GASEOUS MIXTURE', p.abstract_cn = '', p.abstract_en = '', p.application_date = '2007-10-20 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'GC20079281A0', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/36', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'GCP200810440'}) SET p.application_no = 'GCP200810440', p.title_cn = '使用多孔烧嘴的新型蒸汽转化炉', p.title_en = 'NOVEL STEAM REFORMING FURNACE USING POROUS BURNERS', p.abstract_cn = '使用多孔烧嘴的新型蒸汽转化炉', p.abstract_en = 'NOVEL STEAM REFORMING FURNACE USING POROUS BURNERS', p.application_date = '2008-03-26 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'GC200810440A0', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'GCP200913483'}) SET p.application_no = 'GCP200913483', p.title_cn = '用于回收被高水平CO2污染的天然气的方法', p.title_en = 'METHOD FOR RECOVERING A NATURAL GAS CONTAMINATED WITH HIGH LEVELS OF CO2', p.abstract_cn = '用于回收被高水平CO2污染的天然气的方法', p.abstract_en = 'METHOD FOR RECOVERING A NATURAL GAS CONTAMINATED WITH HIGH LEVELS OF CO2', p.application_date = '2009-05-13 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'GC200913483A0', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'GCP200914187'}) SET p.application_no = 'GCP200914187', p.title_cn = '具有改进的低温纯化的生产氨合成气的方法', p.title_en = 'Process for the production of ammonia synthesis gas with improved cryogenic purification', p.abstract_cn = '公开了一种用于生产氨合成气的方法和相关设备，其中粗合成气(13)在低温段(CS)中被净化，并且在净化和HN比调节期间从粗合成气流中分离富氮液体流(30)，并且其中所述液体流(30)的压力在涡轮机(60)中被降低以增强低温段的净制冷效果。还公开了其中也由低压或高压合成气膨胀机提供冷却的实施方案。', p.abstract_en = 'A process and related equipment for producing ammonia synthesis gas are disclosed,  wherein a raw syngas (13) is purified in a cryogenic section (CS) and a nitrogen-rich liquid stream (30) is separated from the raw syngas flow during purification and HN ratio adjustment,  and wherein the pressure of said liquid stream (30) is reduced in a turbine (60) to enhance net refrigerative effect for the cryogenic section. Embodiments wherein chilling is also provided by a low-pressure or high-pressure syngas expander are also disclosed.', p.application_date = '2009-08-26 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'GC200914187A0', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'GCP200914639'}) SET p.application_no = 'GCP200914639', p.title_cn = '通过从低温废热回收热量生产工艺气体', p.title_en = 'Production of process gas by heat recovery from low-temperature waste heat', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种在通过蒸汽对含烃原料进行蒸汽重整中的热回收方法，其中蒸汽重整器产生包含第一热量的工艺气体和包含第二热量的烟道气，所述蒸汽重整器包括至少六个热交换器、水处理单元、冷却段、高温转化单元、至少两个增压单元、至少一个消耗器和至少一个用于对所得工艺气体进行后续处理的单元。所产生的含有第一热量的工艺气体首先通过高温转化单元，在高温转化单元中，其大部分被转化为二氧化碳和氢气，在此之后，所得的含热工艺气体被引导到第一热交换器中以用于随后的热传递，并且随后进入至少两个另外的热交换器，所述热交换器作为锅炉给水预热器、产品冷凝物热交换器或低压蒸发器操作，并且以任何期望的顺序串联连接，由低压蒸发器产生的工艺气体首先被送入另一个锅炉给水预热器，在那里热能被传递到来自水处理单元的锅炉给水的部分流，之后获得的工艺气体通过冷却段，在那里它被进一步冷却，产生冷凝液流，最后被送入至少一个单元，用于对所得工艺气体进行后续处理。此外，将去离子水流送至第二热交换器进行加热。来自第二热交换器的去离子水流被引导到水处理单元中用于脱气，来自水处理单元的锅炉给水流通过增压单元并且被细分，锅炉给水流的第一部分被发送到低压蒸发器，在低压蒸发器中产生低压蒸汽，并且所产生的低压蒸汽被细分，并且第一部分低压流被引导到水处理单元中用于传热，并且第二部分低压流被发送到至少一个消耗器。锅炉给水物流的第二部分通过第二热交换器以进行能量传递，随后通过一个或多个锅炉给水预热器以被包含在工艺气体中的热量加热，并最终被输送到蒸汽发生器。来自冷却段的冷凝物流通过增压单元被传送到产品冷凝物热交换器，以被包含在工艺气体中的热量加热，之后冷凝物流被再次加热。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a heat recovery process in the steam reforming of hydrocarbonaceous feedstocks by means of steam,  in which a steam reformer generates a process gas which contains a first amount of heat and a flue gas which contains a second amount of heat,  comprising at least six heat exchangers,  a water treatment unit,  a cooling section,  a high-temperature conversion unit,  at least two pressure boosting units,  at least one consumer and at least one unit for subsequent processing of the resulting process gas. The generated process gas containing the first amount of heat first passes the high-temperature conversion unit,  where it is,  for the most part,  converted into carbon dioxide and hydrogen,  after which the resulting heat-containing process gas is directed into a first heat exchanger for subsequent heat transfer,  and afterwards into at least two more heat exchangers which are operated as boiler feed water preheaters,  product condensate heat exchangers or low-pressure evaporators,  and are connected in series in any sequence desired,  the process gas resulting from the low-pressure evaporator being first fed into a further boiler feed water preheater,  where heat energy is transferred to a partial stream of the boiler feed water from the water treatment unit,  after which the process gas obtained passes the cooling section,  where it is further cooled generating a condensate flow,  and finally fed into at least one unit for subsequent processing of the resulting process gas. Furthermore,  a deionised water stream is sent to a second heat exchanger for being heated. The deionised water stream from the second heat exchanger is directed for degassing into the water treatment unit,  the boiler feed water stream from the water treatment unit passes a pressure boosting unit and is subdivided,  a first part of the boiler feed water stream being sent to the low-pressure evaporator,  where a low-pressure steam is generated,  and the generated low-pres', p.application_date = '2009-11-04 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'GC200914639A0', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/34', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'GCP200914730'}) SET p.application_no = 'GCP200914730', p.title_cn = '由烃的重整生产含氢和氮的合成气的方法', p.title_en = 'Process for the production of a syngas containing hydrogen and nitrogen from reforming of a hydrocarbon', p.abstract_cn = '一种方法，其中未脱硫的天然气(10)在非催化重整器(11)中部分氧化成含有H2、N2、CO和CO2的合成气; 在变换反应器(15)中处理所述合成气以将至少部分CO转化为CO2和H2; 然后，合成气在分离单元(19)中被纯化，以除去二氧化碳(20)和硫化氢(21)，并且纯化的合成气(22)可以为燃气轮机提供燃料。', p.abstract_en = 'A process where non-desulphurized natural gas (10) is partially oxidated in a non-catalytic reformer (11) to a syngas comprising H2,  N2,  CO and CO2;  said syngas is treated in a shift reactor (15) to convert at least part of the CO into CO2 and H2;  the syngas is then purified in a separation unit (19) removing the carbon dioxide (20) and the hydrogen sulfide (21),  and the purified syngas (22) can fuel a gas turbine.', p.application_date = '2009-11-17 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'GC200914730A0', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/36', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'GC201015158'}) SET p.application_no = 'GC201015158', p.title_cn = '用于由烃生产合成气的方法和燃烧器', p.title_en = 'Process and burner for production of syngas from hydrocarbons', p.abstract_cn = '一种用于烃原料的部分氧化的燃烧器(10)，包括燃烧室和预混合室(E)，以及用于将燃料和氧化剂供应到燃烧室的多个环形通道，所述多个环形通道包括用于燃料的至少第一环形通道和用于氧化剂的至少第二同轴环形通道，产生进入预混合室(E)的分层流。在一个优选实施例中，燃烧器具有一个用于燃料或氧化剂的环形通道(1)，该环形通道分别被两个用于氧化剂或燃料的其它通道(2和3)所包围; 在另一个实施例中，启动燃烧器(20)与主过程燃烧器集成，所述启动燃烧器具有燃烧室(L)、主轮毂(G)和旋流器(H)，并且提供从启动到过程阶段的平滑过渡，该过渡不需要压力容器/燃烧器组件的任何机械干预，并且可以通过自动控制系统执行。', p.abstract_en = 'A burner (10) for the partial oxidation of a hydrocarbon feedstock,  comprising a combustion chamber and a premixing chamber (E),  and a plurality of annular passages for feeding fuel and oxidizer to the combustion chamber,  said plurality of annular passages comprising at least a first annular passage for the fuel,  and at least a second coaxial annular passage for the oxidizer,  producing a layered flow into the premixing chamber (E). In a preferred embodiment the burner has an annular passage (1) for fuel or oxidizer surrounded by two other passages (2 and 3) for the oxidizer or fuel,  respectively;  in a further embodiment a start-up burner (20) is integrated with the main process burner,  said start-up burner having a combustion chamber (L),  a main hub (G) and a swirler (H),  and providing a smooth transition from the start-up to the process phase that does not require any mechanical intervention of the pressure vessel/burner assembly and can be performed through automatic control systems.', p.application_date = '2010-01-24 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'GC201015158A0', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/36', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'GC201016138'}) SET p.application_no = 'GC201016138', p.title_cn = '具有高硫化氢含量的天然气的改质方法', p.title_en = 'PROCESS FOR UPGRADING NATURAL GAS WITH A HIGH HYDROGEN SULFIDE CONTENT', p.abstract_cn = '改质硫化氢含量大于或等于60体积%的超酸天然气并产生氢气的方法，该方法包括：根据吸热反应2H2S+CH4=CS2+4H2(1)b用甲烷处理硫化氢(重整)。冷却反应产物，分离二硫化碳(CS2)并回收氢气; c.燃烧二硫化碳; d.将二硫化碳燃烧的热气体的至少一部分供入重整步骤，作为维持吸热反应的热源(1); e.处理冷却的硫化碳燃烧气体。', p.abstract_en = 'Process for upgrading superacid natural gas,  with a content of hydrogen sulfide higher than or equal to 60% by volume,  with the production of hydrogen,  which comprises : a. treating the hydrogen sulfide with methane (reforming) according to the endothermic reaction2 H2S + CH4 = CS2 + 4H2 (1)b. cooling the reaction products,  separating the carbon disulfide (CS2) and recovering the hydrogen; c. burning the carbon disulfide; d. feeding at least a part of the hot gases of the combustion of carbon disulfide to the reforming step,  as heat source for maintaining the endothermic reaction (1); e. disposing of the cooled combustion gases of carbon sulfide.', p.application_date = '2010-06-22 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'GC201016138A0', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/34', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'GC201016417'}) SET p.application_no = 'GC201016417', p.title_cn = '由炼油厂相关气体高剪切生产增值产品', p.title_en = 'HIGH SHEAR PRODUCTION OF VALUE-ADDED PRODUCT FROM REFINERY-RELATED GAS', p.abstract_cn = '一种由炼油厂相关气体生产增值产品的方法，所述方法包括：提供包含至少一种选自C1-C8化合物的炼油厂相关气体; 在高剪切装置中将炼油厂相关气体与液体载体紧密混合以形成气体在液体载体中的分散体，其中分散体中的气泡具有小于或等于约5微米的平均直径; 以及提取包括至少一种选自高级烃、烯烃和醇的组分的增值产品。一种用于从炼油厂相关气体生产增值产品的系统，包括：至少一个高剪切装置，其包括至少一个转子和至少一个互补形状的定子; 用于生产包含一种或多种C1-C8化合物的炼油厂相关气体的设备; 以及栗，所述栗被配置用于将包含所述液体载体的液体流输送至所述高剪切装置。', p.abstract_en = 'A method of producing value-added product from refinery-related gas,  the method comprising :  providing a refinery-related gas comprising at least one selected from C1-C8 compounds;  intimately mixing the refinery-related gas with a liquid carrier in a high shear device to form a dispersion of gas in the liquid carrier,  wherein the gas bubbles in the dispersion have a mean diameter of less than or equal to about 5?m;  and extracting value-added product comprising at least one component selected from higher hydrocarbons,  olefins and alcohols. A system for producing value-added product from refinery-related gas comprising :  at least one high shear device comprising at least one rotor and at least one complementarily-shaped stator;  apparatus for the production of a refinery-related gas comprising one or more of C1-C8 compounds;  and a pump configured for delivering a liquid stream comprising the liquid carrier to the high shear device.', p.application_date = '2010-07-28 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'GC201016417A0', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/24', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'IN7239DELNP2013'}) SET p.application_no = 'IN7239DELNP2013', p.title_cn = '方法用于生产甲醇或烃从碳材料包括重整步骤的操作条件，选择性地调整', p.title_en = 'METHOD FOR PRODUCING METHANOL OR HYDROCARBONS FROM A CARBON MATERIAL INCLUDING A REFORMING STEP THE OPERATING CONDITIONS OF WHICH ARE SELECTIVELY ADJUSTED', p.abstract_cn = '本发明的生产方法包括以下步骤 : 根据由所述碳材料生产合成气的方法，包括至少一个转化步骤的合成具有含第一个氢/一氧化碳的摩尔比，在第一重整操作的操作条件；从被加氢的原料中产生的氢气流和从所消耗的电力所述氢气物流第一具有第一摩尔流率；对所述第一所消耗的电力；降低生产的氢气流中所消耗的电力的第第二电力低于第一电力和从第一转换到第二的操作状态的不同操作条件下操作的重整为了补偿该降低的氢气流的摩尔流率的合成气在第二操作条件下，含第二个氢/一氧化碳的摩尔比大于第一，氢气/一氧化碳摩尔比。', p.abstract_en = 'The production method of the invention includes the following steps :  producing a synthetic gas from the carbon material according to a method including at least one reforming step the synthetic gas having a first hydrogen/carbon monoxide molar ratio under the first operating conditions for the reforming operation;  producing a stream of hydrogen from a hydrogenated raw material and from a first consumed electrical power the hydrogen stream having a first molar flow rate for said first consumed electrical power;  and lowering the consumed electrical power for producing the hydrogen stream to a second electrical power lower than the first electrical power and transitioning to second operating conditions that are different from the first operating conditions for the reforming operation in order to compensate for the lowering of the molar flow rate of the hydrogen stream the synthetic gas having under the second operating conditions a second hydrogen/carbon monoxide molar ratio that is greater than the first hydrogen/carbon monoxide molar ratio.', p.application_date = '2013-08-14 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'IN7239DELNP2013A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/32', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'IN7898DELNP2015'}) SET p.application_no = 'IN7898DELNP2015', p.title_cn = '集成发电应用熔融碳酸盐燃料电池', p.title_en = 'INTEGRATED POWER GENERATION USING MOLTEN CARBONATE FUEL CELLS', p.abstract_cn = '在各种方面的系统和方法提供了用于集成涡轮机中用于操作熔融碳酸盐燃料电池电源产生。替代于选择的操作条件的燃料电池电效率的提高或最大化燃料电池燃料的可再成形可通入过量的燃料电池以增加阳极的化学燃料电池的能量输出。所述增加的化学能量输出可以用于生成额外的能量，例如通过提供用于氢气燃料涡轮。', p.abstract_en = 'In various aspects systems and methods are provided for integrated operation of molten carbonate fuel cells with turbines for power generation. Instead of selecting the operating conditions of a fuel cell to improve or maximize the electrical efficiency of the fuel cell an excess of reformable fuel can be passed into the anode of the fuel cell to increase the chemical energy output of the fuel cell. The increased chemical energy output can be used for additional power generation such as by providing fuel for a hydrogen turbine.', p.application_date = '2015-09-02 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'IN7898DELNP2015A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/50', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'AU2010362092'}) SET p.application_no = 'AU2010362092', p.title_cn = '方法和装置用于集成植物中甲醇的合成', p.title_en = 'Method and apparatus for the integrated synthesis of methanol in a plant', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种过程(称为comfuel过程)和装置(100)用于热电联产的电能和甲醇。该装置(100)包括 : 燃烧室(10)设计用于基于氧气的燃烧过程。燃烧室(10)具有烟气出口(11)，烃进料(12)，和氧气的气体输入(13)。-一封存设备(20)设计用于从烟道气中二氧化碳的分离。所述封存设备(20)包括二氧化碳出口(21)。一种重整装置(30)具有合成气出口(31)，所述重整装置(30)连接至二氧化碳出口(21)并且被设计用于进行重整过程，产生包含一氧化碳和氢气的合成气。气态烃入口(32)连接到重整装置(30)。-水电解装置(40)供应的电能(E1)。电解水设备(40)设计成产生氢气和氧气。它包括氢气的气体出口(41)和氧气出口(42)。-甲醇反应器(50)，用于合成甲醇，所述甲醇反应器(50)，包括甲醇出口(51)，进料气体入口(52)，用于将所获得的氢气的合成气和从所述水电解装置(40)到甲醇反应器(50)。', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention concerns a process (called ComFuel process) and apparatus (100) for the cogeneration of electric energy and methanol. The apparatus (100) comprises - a combustion chamber (10) designed for an oxygen-based combustion process. The combustion chamber (10) has a flue gas outlet (11),  a hydrocarbon infeed (12),  and an oxygen gas infeed (13). - a sequestration facility (20) designed for the separation of carbon dioxide from flue gas. The sequestration facility (20) comprises a carbon dioxide outlet (21). - a reforming plant (30) having a syngas outlet (31),  the reforming plant (30) being connected to the carbon dioxide outlet (21) and being designed for carrying out a reforming process which produces syngas comprising carbon monoxide and hydrogen gas. A gaseous hydrocarbon inlet (32) is connected to the reforming plant (30). - a water electrolysis facility (40) suppliable by electric energy (E1). The water electrolysis facility (40) is designed to produce hydrogen gas and oxygen gas. It comprising a hydrogen gas outlet (41) and an oxygen gas outlet (42). - a methanol reactor (50) for synthesizing methanol,  the methanol reactor (50) comprising a methanol outlet (51),  a feed gas inlet (52) for feeding the syngas and the hydrogen gas obtained from the water electrolysis facility (40) into the methanol reactor (50).', p.application_date = '2010-11-10 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'AU2010362092B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'AU2014258898'}) SET p.application_no = 'AU2014258898', p.title_cn = '用于产生氢气的方法，所述方法中使用的氢气发生装置', p.title_en = 'Method for generating hydrogen,  and hydrogen generating device used in said method', p.abstract_cn = '本发明的目的是提供一种方法用于产生氢气而不降解底物。该方法用于产生氢气涉及第一制备的氢气发生装置。本发明的氢生成装置具有 : 容器(91)；一种光半导体电极(100)包括基板(101)，光阻第一导体层(102)和第一半导体光催化剂层(103)；对电极(92)；导线(94)电连接第第一导体层(102)的反电极(92)；和液体(93)的内部储存容器(91)。第一导体层(102)夹在基板(101)和第一半导体光催化剂层(103)。至少一部分第一半导体光催化剂层(103)接触液体(93)。至少一部分反电极(92)与液体相接触(93)。液体(93)选自一组由水电解质溶液和水。基板(101)由树脂形成。然后，第一半导体光催化剂层(103)照射光(1000)产生计数器上的氢电极(92)。', p.abstract_en = 'The purpose of the present invention is to provide a method for generating hydrogen without degrading a substrate. This method for generating hydrogen involves first preparing a hydrogen generating device. This hydrogen generating device is provided with :  a container (91);  an optical semiconductor electrode (100) including a substrate (101),  a light-blocking first conductor layer (102) and a first semiconductor optical catalyst layer (103);  a counter electrode (92);  a conducting wire (94) electrically connecting the first conductor layer (102) to the counter electrode (92);  and a liquid (93) stored inside of the container (91). The first conductor layer (102) is sandwiched between the substrate (101) and the first semiconductor optical catalyst layer (103). At least a part of the first semiconductor optical catalyst layer (103) is in contact with the liquid (93). At least a part of the counter electrode (92) is in contact with the liquid (93). The liquid (93) is selected from a group consisting of an aqueous electrolyte solution and water. The substrate (101) is formed from a resin. Then,  the first semiconductor optical catalyst layer (103) is irradiated with light (1000) to generate hydrogen on the counter electrode (92).', p.application_date = '2014-04-17 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'AU2014258898B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CA2964576'}) SET p.application_no = 'CA2964576', p.title_cn = '重整炉，包括重整与翅片管', p.title_en = 'REFORMING FURNACE COMPRISING REFORMING TUBES WITH FINS', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种制氢转化炉，包括多个重整管使烃流和至少一个流体内管，从上至下，具，在至少一部分外表面的上半部，至少一个鳍片具有厚度1和30毫米之间，3毫米和100毫米之间的宽度，和长度为1m，长度等于所述炉的高度。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a reforming furnace for producing hydrogen,  comprising a plurality of reforming tubes that allow a flow of hydrocarbons and at least one fluid inside the tubes,  from top to bottom,  and have,  on at least part of the upper half of the outer surface thereof,  at least one fin that has a thickness of between 1 and 30mm,  a width of between 3mm and 100mm,  and a length of between 1m and a length equivalent to the height of said furnace.', p.application_date = '2015-09-18 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CA2964576A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/34', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'DE602004048857'}) SET p.application_no = 'DE602004048857', p.title_cn = '氢气发生器，氢气发生器的关闭操作的方法，以及燃料电池系统', p.title_en = 'Hydrogen generator,  method of shutting down operation of hydrogen generator,  and fuel cell system', p.abstract_cn = '本发明的氢气发生器包括 : 一种用于产生富氢气体的重整器从进料气体和水的反应使用重整催化剂体和将其发送；从出口端口；物料进料系统，用于进料的进料气体以所述重整器；一种燃烧器，用于提供，所述的重整催化剂体，产生的热量将燃料气体与空气和燃烧；和空气供给系统用于将空气供应到燃烧器；其中，在使用重整器的内部吹扫关闭氢气发生器中的进料气体，供给的空气的量增加了扑灭火焰的燃烧器，和发出吹扫气体从吹扫出口与空气的混合和被稀释在燃烧器和外排。', p.abstract_en = 'A hydrogen generator of the invention includes :  a reformer for generating a hydrogen-rich gas from a feed gas and water by a reaction using a reforming catalyst body and sending it out from an outlet port;  a material feed system for feeding the feed gas to the reformer;  a burner for supplying,  to the reforming catalyst body,  heat generated by mixing a fuel gas with air and burning it;  and an air supply system for supplying air to the burner;  wherein,  when purging an interior of the reformer using the feed gas in shutting down the hydrogen generator,  an amount of the air supplied is increased to put out a flame of the burner,  and a purge gas sent out from the outlet port by the purging is mixed and diluted with the air in the burner and is discharged outside.', p.application_date = '2004-12-02 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'DE602004048857T2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'DE602012024289'}) SET p.application_no = 'DE602012024289', p.title_cn = '从甲醇或烃的碳材料的制造方法，包括 : 转化步骤，所述操作条件可选择性地调整', p.title_en = 'METHOD FOR PRODUCING METHANOL OR HYDROCARBONS FROM A CARBON MATERIAL,  INCLUDING A REFORMING STEP,  THE OPERATING CONDITIONS OF WHICH ARE SELECTIVELY ADJUSTED', p.abstract_cn = '提供了用于生产甲醇或烃的方法。生产方法包括从含碳材料制备合成气，根据一种方法，包括至少一个转化步骤，具有第一个氢/一氧化碳合成气的摩尔比在第一重整操作的操作条件；从被加氢的原料中产生的氢气流和从第第一电力消耗，所述氢气物流具有第一摩尔流率对所述第一消耗的电功率；消耗，降低了电力生产的氢气流，降低到第二第一以下的电力的电力和从第一转换到第二不同的操作条件的操作以补偿该摩尔流率的降低的氢气流量，具有第二个氢/一氧化碳合成气摩尔比大于第一，在第二操作条件。', p.abstract_en = 'A method for producing methanol or hydrocarbons is provided. The production method comprises producing a synthesis gas from carbonaceous material,  according to a method comprising at least one reforming step,  the synthesis gas having a first hydrogen/carbon monoxide molar ratio under the first operating conditions for the reforming operation;  producing a stream of hydrogen from a hydrogenated raw material and from a first consumed electric power,  the hydrogen stream having a first molar flow rate for said first consumed electric power;  and lowering the consumed electric power for producing the hydrogen stream,  down to a second electric power below the first electric power and transitioning to second operating conditions different from the first for the reforming operation in order to compensate for the lowering of the molar flow rate of the hydrogen flow,  the synthesis gas having a second hydrogen/carbon monoxide molar ratio greater than the first under the second operating conditions.', p.application_date = '2012-02-22 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'DE602012024289T2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/34', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'DE602013005492'}) SET p.application_no = 'DE602013005492', p.title_cn = '系统和方法用于生产含H2气体和纯净水', p.title_en = 'System and process for producing a H2-containing gas and purified water', p.abstract_cn = '系统和方法用于生产H2含有产品气体和净化水从组合的H2-制备重整和热水纯化过程。原水，如盐水，通过间接加热传热与重整产物从H2-中生产重整净化原水的方法一种多效蒸馏工艺。', p.abstract_en = 'System and process for producing a H 2 -containing product gas and purified water from an integrated H 2 -producing reforming and thermal water purification process. Raw water,  such as salt water,  is heated by indirect heat transfer with reformate from the H 2 -producing reforming process for purifying raw water in a multiple effect distillation process.', p.application_date = '2013-10-23 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'DE602013005492T2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'HUE10700594'}) SET p.application_no = 'HUE10700594', p.title_cn = '氢气工艺', p.title_en = 'HYDROGEN PROCESS', p.abstract_cn = '用于生产氢的方法，包括 : 使烃进料通过净化吸附剂(一个或多个)，合并蒸汽与所述的纯烷烃或通过床将烃/蒸汽混合物进行绝热蒸汽重整的催化剂，通过预重整气体混合物通过燃烧蒸汽重整产生粗合成气混合物，将粗合成气混合物通过一个或更多的水气变换催化剂床产生的偏移合成气混合物，经过转换的合成气混合物的膜变换反应器装有一层水气变换催化剂CO2选择性膜，富氢气体混合物冷却到低于露点，并分离除去冷凝物，经过脱水的富氢混合气中分离CO2的变压吸附装置，回收吹扫气体流的至少一部分为燃料的燃烧蒸汽重整器或烃类进料或纯化的烃进料流中。', p.abstract_en = 'A process for producing hydrogen includes :  passing a hydrocarbon feed though purification sorbent(s),  combining steam with the purified hydrocarbon and passing the hydrocarbon/steam mixture adiabatically through a bed of steam reforming catalyst,  passing the pre-reformed gas mixture through a fired steam reformer to generate a crude synthesis gas mixture,  passing the crude synthesis gas mixture through one or more beds of water-gas shift catalyst to generate a shifted synthesis gas mixture,  passing the shifted synthesis gas mixture to a membrane shift reactor containing a bed of water-gas shift catalyst and a CO2-selective membrane,  cooling the hydrogen-enriched gas mixture to below the dew point and separating off the condensate,  passing the de-watered hydrogen-enriched gas mixture to CO2 separation in pressure-swing absorption apparatus,  and recycling at least a portion of the purge gas stream as fuel to the fired steam reformer or to the hydrocarbon feed or purified hydrocarbon feed streams.', p.application_date = '2010-01-14 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'HUE025689T2', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2014193122'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2014193122', p.title_cn = '氢输送系统，和产生氢气的氢气站', p.title_en = 'HYDROGEN DELIVERY SYSTEM,  HYDROGEN STATION THEREFOR,  AND HYDROGEN GENERATING FACILITY', p.abstract_cn = '要解决的问题 : 氢在氢站制造，高压力的氢气给氢站，以减少运输的次数。方法 : 从电源座金属，氢站，其装备有氢气产生，铁或粉末金属形成的多孔质密闭金属容器通过加载使用方法，氢气发生使用生产中的铁金属氢，通过一种方法得到的氢，在该氢站B出售给顾客，步骤B反应后含铁的铁氧化物和金属容器，其包括供给基重定向方法在该氢输送系统C，B，过程中，氢产生反应室为在金属容器的同时，施加负载，然后向反应室和热水，蒸汽或过热蒸汽供给到一个或多个产生氢气，氢气输送系统)。选择的绘图 : 图。1', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To decrease a number of times of transporting high-pressure hydrogen to a hydrogen station by simply producing hydrogen at the hydrogen station. SOLUTION :  Provided is a hydrogen delivery system comprising :  a step A of transporting metallic iron by using a container packed airtight with porous or powdery metallic iron from a metallic iron supply station to a hydrogen station having a hydrogen generating facility installed;  a step B of producing hydrogen by the hydrogen generating facility using the metallic iron and selling the hydrogen obtained to a customer at the hydrogen station;  and a step C of transporting back a container containing iron oxide generated after a reaction in the step B to the metallic iron supply station. In the step B,  the container having the metallic iron packed is applied as a reaction chamber at the hydrogen generating facility,  and hydrogen is generated by supplying one or two or more of hot water,  steam,  or superheated steam to the reaction chamber. SELECTED DRAWING :  Figure 1 COPYRIGHT :  (C)2016, JPO&INPIT', p.application_date = '2014-09-22 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP2016064935A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/10', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2014193930'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2014193930', p.title_cn = '脱硫装置和燃料电池发电系统和方法', p.title_en = 'DESULFURIZATION METHOD AND APPARATUS,  AND FUEL CELL POWER GENERATION SYSTEM', p.abstract_cn = '要解决的问题 : 尽管简单的设备配置，水长时间稳定和活化脱硫方法，可利用高硫化附件偏离脱硫装置，从而，燃料气体利用装置如燃料电池发电系统，去除中的硫等成分，燃料气体的稳定供应。方法 : 该燃料含有硫组分P蒸汽添加到气体，燃料气体在蒸汽存在下重整反应，生成的氢气从P进行2b和蒸汽重整催化剂，含硫化合物的水用于从燃料中去除硫化合物的气体依次通过硫化连接偏差从2a和P以除去燃料中硫组分的气体。选择的绘图 : 图。1', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To provide a desulfurization method and apparatus capable of using a hydrodesulfurization agent stably for a long term with high activity in spite of a simple apparatus configuration,  thereby enabling stable supply of a sulfur component-removed fuel gas to a fuel gas utilization apparatus such as a fuel cell power generation system. SOLUTION :  Steam is added to a fuel gas P containing sulfur components,  and then the fuel gas P is passed sequentially through a steam reforming catalyst 2b that performs a reforming reaction in which hydrogen gas is generated from the fuel gas P in the presence of the steam and a hydrodesulfurization agent 2a that removes sulfur compounds from a fuel gas containing sulfur compounds,  thereby removing the sulfur components in the fuel gas P. SELECTED DRAWING :  Figure 1 COPYRIGHT :  (C)2016, JPO&INPIT', p.application_date = '2014-09-24 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP2016064942A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'KR1020150097857'}) SET p.application_no = 'KR1020150097857', p.title_cn = '氢气净化器', p.title_en = 'HYDROGEN PURIFIER', p.abstract_cn = '本发明提供了一种氢气净化装置是指. 1号腔室. 所述的保温层1与腔的内周面之间的网，使用时，所述1号. 2号填充冷却介质. 用于存储液化气的具有与腔体. 所述2号和网络的利用. 下部分上移动，以控制开花爸Hu的外径小的供氢的供氢的氢供应提供给所述降低的同时，旋转流. 外换热，冷却介质可以是分离的杂质和1号旋风室. 旋风所述号码(1)设置在所述腔室的内部中心部分. 其下端靠近下腔室的内部和所述多个旋风1放置在一个下侧，所述1号旋风分离器在所述室流动氢气流中以扩展. 一种氢释放工具上的1数字中配置管. 所述数量的所述数量和2的氢释放工具1被构造成使墨室的内部的氢气进入管. 氢释放工具，所述1号进入管移动的同时接触正仲氢的邻对位线程转换为制氢转化催化剂.', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention relates to a hydrogen purifier which can enhance hydrogen purifying efficiency. The hydrogen purifier comprises :  a main body comprising a first chamber and a second chamber which has an insulation layer formed between the second chamber and the inner circumferential surface of the first chamber,  is installed in the first chamber,  and has an inner part filled with a liquid cooling medium;  a first cyclone chamber installed in the second chamber,  and having a hopper-shaped lower part and a hydrogen supply pipe connected to the upper part of one side to receive hydrogen from the outside,  thereby allowing the received hydrogen to move downwards while rotating in order to allow impurities in the hydrogen to be isolated during heat exchange performed between the hydrogen and the cooling medium;  a first hydrogen discharge pipe which is mounted on the central part in the first cyclone chamber,  has a lower end placed to be adjacent to the inner lower end of the first cyclone chamber to receive the hydrogen which moves downwards in the first cyclone chamber,  and is extended upwards;  and an ortho-para hydrogen conversion catalyst mounted on a path where the hydrogen supplied to the first hydrogen discharge pipe moves in the second chamber,  thereby allowing the hydrogen supplied to the first hydrogen discharge pipe to be converted into ortho-hydrogen and para-hydrogen while moving to touch the catalyst.COPYRIGHT KIPO 2016', p.application_date = '2015-07-09 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'KR101618338B1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14890646'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14890646', p.title_cn = '用于固体有机原料至少部分气化的方法和设备', p.title_en = 'PROCESS AND PLANT FOR AT LEAST PARTIAL GASIFICATION OF SOLID ORGANIC FEED MATERIAL', p.abstract_cn = '一种至少部分气化固体有机原料的方法，其中在低温气化器中通过从原料低温碳化获得含焦油的低温碳化气体，然后在高温气化器中通过部分氧化和随后的部分还原将低温碳化气体转化为合成气。 低温碳化气体与第二气体混合。 一种用于实施该方法的设备，包括用于从原料获得低温碳化气体的低温气化器，用于从低温碳化气体获得合成气的高温气化器，以及用于将低温碳化气体与第二气体混合的装置。', p.abstract_en = 'A process for at least partial gasification of solid organic feed material,  in which a tar-containing low-temperature carbonization gas is obtained by low-temperature carbonization from the feed material in a low-temperature gasifier and the low-temperature carbonization gas is then converted to a synthesis gas in a high-temperature gasifier by partial oxidation and subsequent partial reduction. The low-temperature carbonization gas is admixed with a second gas. A plant equipped for carrying out the process includes a low-temperature gasifier for obtaining the low-temperature carbonization gas from the feed material,  a high-temperature gasifier for obtaining synthesis gas from the low-temperature carbonization gas,  and means for admixing the low-temperature carbonization gas with the second gas.', p.application_date = '2014-04-30 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US20160115020A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/36', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14873380'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14873380', p.title_cn = '氢气精制方法', p.title_en = 'METHOD FOR REFINING HYDROGEN', p.abstract_cn = '本发明提供一种用氢气精制装置精制氢气的方法，其中通过钯合金毛细管将电池的内部分成一次侧空间和二次侧空间，每个毛细管具有封闭的一端和支撑钯合金毛细管的开口端的管板，其中从一次侧空间引入含杂质的氢气以允许氢气渗透钯合金毛细管从而从二次侧空间收集纯氢气。 本发明的氢气精制方法能够减少含杂质气体的去除量，有效地从二次侧空间收集纯氢气。 从以1000ppm以下的杂质作为原料氢的氢中，以原料氢的导入流量的10%以下的流量，从一次侧空间除去含有不透过钯合金毛细管的杂质的气体。 此外，含有不穿透钯合金毛细管的杂质的气体以基于原料氢中所含杂质的含量的流速从一次侧空间移除。', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention is to provide a method for refining hydrogen with a hydrogen refining device in which the inside of a cell is divided into a primary side space and a secondary side space by palladium alloy capillaries each having one end being closed and a tube sheet supporting the open end of the palladium alloy capillaries,  in which impurity-containing hydrogen is introduced from the primary side space to allow hydrogen to permeate the palladium alloy capillaries so as to collect pure hydrogen from the secondary side space. The method for refining hydrogen has a capability of decreasing the removed amount of gas containing impurities and efficiently collecting pure hydrogen from the secondary side space. From hydrogen with 1000 ppm or less of impurities as raw material hydrogen,  gas containing impurities that does not penetrate the palladium alloy capillaries is removed from the primary side space at the flow rate of 10% or less of the introduction flow rate of the raw material hydrogen. Furthermore,  gas containing impurities that does not penetrate the palladium alloy capillaries is removed from the primary side space at a flow rate based on the content of impurities contained in raw material hydrogen.', p.application_date = '2015-10-02 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US20160115022A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/50', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14521251'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14521251', p.title_cn = '从分馏段尾气中回收氢气', p.title_en = 'RECOVERY OF HYDROGEN FROM FRACTIONATION ZONE OFFGAS', p.abstract_cn = '描述了提高从分馏段废气中回收氢的方法和装置。 所述方法包括降低来自高压反应区的液体流出物的压力，并将流出物引入闪蒸鼓中形成低压液体流出物。 将低压流出物引入低压汽提塔，并分离成塔顶蒸汽物流和至少一种附加物流。 汽提塔塔顶蒸气物流在压缩机的一个汽缸中压缩到中间压力，该压缩机具有至少一个附加汽缸。 将压缩塔顶物流引入中压卸料鼓，形成气体物流和液体物流。 将气体物流引入变压吸附区以在中压下产生富氢气体物流。', p.abstract_en = 'Methods and apparatus for increasing the recovery of hydrogen from fractionation section offgas are described. The methods include reducing the pressure of a liquid effluent from a high-pressure reaction zone,  and introducing the effluent into a flash drum forming a low pressure liquid effluent. The low pressure effluent is introduced into a low-pressure stripper column,  and separated into an overhead vapor stream and at least one additional stream. The stripper column overhead vapor stream is compressed in a one cylinder of a compressor,  which has at least one additional cylinder,  to an intermediate pressure. The compressed overhead stream is introduced to an intermediate pressure knockout drum forming a gas stream and a liquid stream. The gas stream is introduced into a pressure swing adsorption zone to produce a hydrogen rich gas stream at an intermediate pressure.', p.application_date = '2014-10-22 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US20160115023A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/52', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14524291'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14524291', p.title_cn = '用于烃的重整的方法和设备，包括使用回收区、吸收区和变压吸附区回收产物', p.title_en = 'METHODS AND APPARATUSES FOR REFORMING OF HYDROCARBONS INCLUDING RECOVERY OF PRODUCTS USING A RECOVERY ZONE,  AN ABSORPTION ZONE AND A PRESSURE SWING ADSORPTION ZONE', p.abstract_cn = '提供了用于烃的重整包括产物回收的装置和方法的实施例。 在一个实施例中，一种方法包括将重整区流出物分离成净气相物流和液相烃物流。 分离净气相物流以形成富含H2的物流和第一中间液相烃物流。 富H2物流与吸附剂接触以形成超富H2物流和PSA尾气物流。 将PSA尾气流和至少一部分液相烃流冷却并彼此接触以形成H2、C2、C3和C4。 含烃气体物流和冷却的第二中间液相烃物流。', p.abstract_en = 'Embodiments of apparatuses and methods for reforming of hydrocarbons including recovery of products are provided. In one example,  a method comprises separating a reforming-zone effluent into a net gas phase stream and a liquid phase hydrocarbon stream. The net gas phase stream is separated for forming an H2-rich stream and a first intermediate liquid phase hydrocarbon stream. The H2-rich stream is contacted with an adsorbent to form an H2-ultra rich stream and a PSA tail gas stream. The PSA tail gas stream and at least a portion of the liquid phase hydrocarbon stream are cooled and contacted with each other to form a H2,  C2− hydrocarbons-containing gas stream and a cooled second intermediate liquid phase hydrocarbon stream.', p.application_date = '2014-10-27 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US20160115024A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/56', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WOIN15000314'}) SET p.application_no = 'WOIN15000314', p.title_cn = '双金属多相催化剂用于在生态环境友好溶剂', p.title_en = 'BIMETALLIC HETEROGENEOUS CATALYST FOR USE IN ECO- FRIENDLY SOLVENTS', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种固体非均相，多功能，双金属铜和氧化锆基催化剂。更具体地，本发明涉及一种异构，双功能催化剂包括铜和氧化锆，涂覆有钯，其结果，它可防止浸出第一和第二中的金属催化剂的反应介质，以及该催化剂的制备方法。发现该催化剂的应用更加经济和可选择性的反应，如羟醛缩合，Knoevenagel缩合，脱水，酯化和氢化，其中水可作为溶剂使整个反应经济和环境友好。', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention relates to a solid heterogeneous,  multi-functional,  bimetallic copper and zirconia based catalyst. More specifically,  the present invention relates to a heterogeneous,  bifunctional catalyst comprising a copper and zirconia,  coated with palladium,  with the result that it prevents the leaching of first and second metal catalyst in reaction medium,  as well as a process for the preparation of this catalyst. The application of this catalyst is found to be more economic and selective in the reactions such as aldol condensation,  Knoevenagel condensation,  dehydration,  esterification and hydrogenation,  wherein the water can be used as a solvent which makes the overall reactions economic and environmental friendly.', p.application_date = '2015-08-05 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016020934A3', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WOFR15052503'}) SET p.application_no = 'WOFR15052503', p.title_cn = '重整炉，包括重整管与翅片', p.title_en = 'REFORMING FURNACE COMPRISING REFORMING TUBES WITH FINS', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种用于生产氢的重整炉，包括多个允许的烃流的重整管和至少一个流体内管，从上至下，具有，在至少部分的外表面的上半部，至少一个翅片具有1和30毫米之间的厚度，3毫米和100毫米之间的宽度，和m及长度之间的长度相当于所述炉的高度。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a reforming furnace for producing hydrogen,  comprising a plurality of reforming tubes that allow a flow of hydrocarbons and at least one fluid inside the tubes,  from top to bottom,  and have,  on at least part of the upper half of the outer surface thereof,  at least one fin that has a thickness of between 1 and 30mm,  a width of between 3mm and 100mm,  and a length of between 1m and a length equivalent to the height of said furnace.', p.application_date = '2015-09-18 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016062932A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WOUS15056322'}) SET p.application_no = 'WOUS15056322', p.title_cn = '从分馏区的氢尾气的回收', p.title_en = 'RECOVERY OF HYDROGEN FROM FRACTIONATION ZONE OFFGAS', p.abstract_cn = '方法和装置用于增加从分馏段回收氢的尾气被描述。所述方法包括降低压力的液体流出物从高压反应区，和将流出物进入闪蒸槽形成低压力液体流出物。低压流出物引入到低压汽提塔，和分离为塔顶蒸汽流和至少一个附加流。所述汽提塔塔顶蒸汽流被压缩在一个气缸的压缩机，具有至少一个附加磁柱，到中间压力。所述压缩的塔顶料流引入到中间压力分离罐形成气体流和液体料流。气体流引入到压力摆动吸附区以产生富氢气体流在中间压力。', p.abstract_en = 'Methods and apparatus for increasing the recovery of hydrogen from fractionation section offgas are described. The methods include reducing the pressure of a liquid effluent from a high-pressure reaction zone,  and introducing the effluent into a flash drum forming a low pressure liquid effluent. The low pressure effluent is introduced into a low-pressure stripper column,  and separated into an overhead vapor stream and at least one additional stream. The stripper column overhead vapor stream is compressed in a one cylinder of a compressor,  which has at least one additional cylinder,  to an intermediate pressure. The compressed overhead stream is introduced to an intermediate pressure knockout drum forming a gas stream and a liquid stream. The gas stream is introduced into a pressure swing adsorption zone to produce a hydrogen rich gas stream at an intermediate pressure.', p.application_date = '2015-10-20 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016064788A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201180071546.0'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201180071546.0', p.title_cn = '使用微通道加热器的烃重整装置', p.title_en = 'Reforming of the heater using the micro-channel device', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种使用微通道加热器的烃重整装置，其中，利用燃料的燃烧热作为烃重整反应所需的能量来源。所述烃重整装置通过层压具有微通道的薄金属板形成多层结构，因此，所述烃重整装置适合用于小型和中型的紧凑型氢气生产装置。特别地，由于在使用分离膜的氢气再生方法中，不被分离膜过滤的含氢气的气体可以作为燃料使用，因此，所述烃重整装置可以被用作高效的氢气生产系统。', p.abstract_en = 'Disclosed is a hydrocarbon reforming device using a micro channel heater capable of utilizing combustion heat of a fuel as an energy source for reforming reaction of hydrocarbon,  which includes metal sheets having micro channels laminated in plural,  thus being suitably used as a middle and small compact type device for hydrogen production. Specifically,  in the case where a hydrogen purification process is applied to a hydrogen production device combined with a separation membrane,  since the hydrogen-containing gas,  which does not penetrate the separation membrane,  can be utilized as a fuel,  the inventive device may be utilized as a hydrogen production system having high efficiency.', p.application_date = '2011-04-15 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN103687803B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201520809033.0'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201520809033.0', p.title_cn = '一种变换饱和热水塔外排水回收装置', p.title_en = 'Alternate outer drainage recovery unit of saturated hot water tower', p.abstract_cn = '本实用新型公开了一种变换饱和热水塔外排水回收装置，所属领域为化工设备设计技术领域，包括热水塔、收集箱、增压泵、造汽汽包夹套，收集箱通过管道与热水塔连接，将热水塔内的水收集至收集箱，收集箱的右端连接有增压泵，从收集箱输送过来的水被增压泵增压，再通过管道输送至与增压泵连接的造汽汽包夹套，经过造汽汽包夹套造汽处理，再输送至热水塔，供其使用，节约了大量的水资源，本实用新型所公开的变换饱和热水塔外排水回收装置，塔内热水气体在变换塔内为其内部反应提供必要的条件，增压泵和造汽汽包夹套处理以后的循环水能够保证热水塔内热水总固体含量小于500ppm，防止了催化剂表面细小孔被堵塞，催化剂活性高，系统阻力小。', p.abstract_en = 'The utility model discloses an alternate outer drainage recovery unit of saturated hot water tower,  affiliated field is design and manufacture of chemical equipment technical field,  including hot water tower,  collecting box,  booster pump,  make the vapour steam pocket and press from both sides the cover,  the collecting box passes through the pipeline to be connected with the hot water tower,  collects the water in the hot water tower to the collecting box,  the right -hand member of collecting box is connected with the booster pump,  carries the water of coming by the booster pump pressure boost from the collecting box,  rethread pipe -line transportation to the vapour steam pocket of being connected with the booster pump of making presss from both sides the cover,  presss from both sides to overlap and makes the vapour processing through making the vapour steam pocket,  carries to the hot water tower again,  supplies its use,  has practiced thrift a large amount of water resources,  the utility model discloses an alternate outer drainage recovery unit of saturated hot water tower,  the tower internal heat aqueous vapor body provide necessary condition for its inside reaction in the transform tower,  the booster pump with make the vapour steam pocket press from both sides the cover handle later circulating water can guarantee the hot water tower in the total solids content of hot water be lighter than 500ppm,  prevented that the tiny hole of catalyst surface from being stopped up,  the catalyst activity is high,  system resistance is little.', p.application_date = '2015-10-14 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN205187844U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/16', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201521016459.7'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201521016459.7', p.title_cn = '煤制汽车用氢气能源供气系统', p.title_en = 'Coal system is hydrogen energy gas supply system for car', p.abstract_cn = '本实用新型公开了一种煤制汽车用氢气能源供气系统，煤炭进料仓与输送系统连接，输送系统与氢气发生器连接，氢气发生器与多余物质收集系统和氢气收集系统连接，氢气收集系统与氢气净化系统连接，氢气净化系统与氢气储存系统连接，氢气储存系统与氢气压缩系统连接，氢气压缩系统与压缩氢气储存系统连接，压缩氢气储存系统与氢气发电系统和压缩氢气售气系统连接，压缩氢气售气系统与氢能源汽车连接。本实用新型用于氢能源汽车的供给，氢气生产量可根据具体要求具体设定，可实现煤制氢气供给加氢站为氢能源汽车提供足够的氢能源。可以解决在无人区、高原、没有电力供应的地区，实现氢能源汽车的优秀性能。', p.abstract_en = 'The utility model discloses a coal system is hydrogen energy gas supply system for car,  coal feeding storehouse is connected with conveying system,  conveying system and hydrogen generator are connected,  hydrogen generator is connected with unnecessary material collecting system and hydrogen collecting system,  the hydrogen collecting system is connected with hydrogen clean system,  hydrogen clean system and hydrogen storage headtotail,  the hydrogen system that stores is connected with hydrogen compression system,  hydrogen compression system stores the headtotail with compression hydrogen,  compression hydrogen system that stores and hydrogen generates electricity system sell the gas headtotail with compression hydrogen,  compression hydrogen is sold the gas system and is connected with hydrogen energy source car. The utility model is used for the supply of hydrogen energy source car,  the hydrogen amount of production can specifically be set for according to the specific requirement,  can realize coal hydrogen manufacturing gas and supply with the hydrogenation station and provide sufficient hydrogen energy source for hydrogen energy source car. Can solve on depopulated zone,  plateau,  not have power supply\'s area,  realize the outstanding performance of hydrogen energy source car.', p.application_date = '2015-12-09 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN205187845U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/50', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'EP14735829'}) SET p.application_no = 'EP14735829', p.title_cn = '烟尘控制在氧化反应', p.title_en = 'SOOT CONTROL IN OXIDATION REACTIONS', p.abstract_cn = '积灰在部分氧化含碳进料是通过控制氧化剂流的动量相对以含碳进料流的动量。', p.abstract_en = 'Soot formation in the partial oxidation of carbonaceous feed is controlled by controlling the momentum of the oxidant stream relative to the momentum of the carbonaceous feed stream.', p.application_date = '2014-06-17 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'EP3010851A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/36', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'EP14725685'}) SET p.application_no = 'EP14725685', p.title_cn = '植物和方法，所述高效利用多余的电能，', p.title_en = 'PLANT AND PROCESS FOR THE EFFICIENT UTILIZATION OF EXCESS ELECTRIC ENERGY', p.abstract_cn = '在植物中包括第一装置，用于电化学或电热生产氢，产生第一氢流；第二装置用于从烃蒸汽重整制氢，部分氧化或脱氢，产生第二氢流；氢导管或氢消费者，与两个第一氢气料流和第二氢气流进给；和控制装置第一中氢的生产相匹配的设备和第二中的装置，这样一种方式是总量第一的氢气料流和第二的氢气流对应于预定值，多余的电能可有效地利用操作该装置用于电化学或电热生产氢多余的电能。', p.abstract_en = 'In a plant comprising a first apparatus for the electrochemical or electrothermal production of hydrogen,  which produces a first hydrogen stream;  a second apparatus for producing hydrogen from a hydrocarbon by steam reforming,  partial oxidation or dehydrogenation,  which produces a second hydrogen stream;  a hydrogen conduit or a hydrogen consumer to which both the first hydrogen stream and the second hydrogen stream are fed;  and a control device which matches the production of hydrogen in the first apparatus and in the second apparatus in such a way that the total amount of first hydrogen stream and second hydrogen stream corresponds to a predetermined value,  excess electric energy can be efficiently utilized by operating the apparatus for the electrochemical or electrothermal production of hydrogen with excess electric energy.', p.application_date = '2014-05-20 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'EP3011076A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/34', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2015013278'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2015013278', p.title_cn = '用于产生氢气的方法产生氢气从水和氢发生器', p.title_en = 'A method for generating hydrogen to generate hydrogen from water and hydrogen generator', p.abstract_cn = '所要解决的问题 : 提供一种氢生成方法，该方法从水产生的氢气的量增加. 溶液 : sus304不锈钢熔盐溶解在氢氧化钠和一组细颗粒分散在表面上的熔盐. 反应液面上的空间自由碰撞而将氧气和蒸汽与一组细颗粒. 当反应空间得到负压力. 自动注入惰性气体如氩气或阀操作的反应空间，保持正压，以保持无反应空间氧气. 反应管，用于将水从微粒子发生管独立安装.', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To provide a hydrogen generating method that increases the amount of hydrogen produced from water.SOLUTION :  Stainless steel SUS304 is dissolved in a molten salt of sodium hydroxide and a group of fine particles are dispersed on the surface of the molten salt. A reaction space on the liquid surface is made free of oxygen and steam is made to collide with the group of fine particles. When the reaction space gets a negative pressure,  an inert gas such as argon is automatically injected or a valve is operated to keep the reaction space at a positive pressure to keep the reaction space free of oxygen. A reaction tube for supplying water is installed independently from a fine particle generating tube.', p.application_date = '2015-01-27 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP5911980B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/10', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'BRPI112012013909'}) SET p.application_no = 'BRPI112012013909', p.title_cn = '二氧化碳与氢气反应的方法', p.title_en = 'process for reacting carbon dioxide with hydrogen', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种使二氧化碳与氢气反应的方法。 在该方法中，使吸附有二氧化碳的催化剂与氢气在高温下接触。 该催化剂可通过使贫化的催化剂与二氧化碳源，例如发电厂的烟道气接触而再生。 在一个优选的实施方案中，二氧化碳通过水的原位水解反应。', p.abstract_en = 'Disclosed is a process for reacting carbon dioxide with hydrogen. In the process a catalyst having carbon dioxide adsorbed thereto is contacted with hydrogen at an elevated temperature. The catalyst can be regenerated by contacting depleted catalyst with a carbon dioxide source,  for example a flue gas of a power plant. In a preferred embodiment carbon dioxide is reacted by in situ hydrolysis of water.', p.application_date = '2010-12-09 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'BR112012013909A2', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/18', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'BR112012013909'}) SET p.application_no = 'BR112012013909', p.title_cn = '二氧化碳与氢气反应的方法', p.title_en = 'process for reacting carbon dioxide with hydrogen', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种使二氧化碳与氢气反应的方法。 在该方法中，使吸附有二氧化碳的催化剂与氢气在高温下接触。 该催化剂可通过使贫化的催化剂与二氧化碳源，例如发电厂的烟道气接触而再生。 在一个优选的实施方案中，二氧化碳通过水的原位水解反应。', p.abstract_en = 'Disclosed is a process for reacting carbon dioxide with hydrogen. In the process a catalyst having carbon dioxide adsorbed thereto is contacted with hydrogen at an elevated temperature. The catalyst can be regenerated by contacting depleted catalyst with a carbon dioxide source,  for example a flue gas of a power plant. In a preferred embodiment carbon dioxide is reacted by in situ hydrolysis of water.', p.application_date = '2010-12-09 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'BRPI1213909A2', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/18', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CA2731306'}) SET p.application_no = 'CA2731306', p.title_cn = '低能量氨或甲醇的生产方法', p.title_en = 'LOW ENERGY PROCESS FOR THE PRODUCTION OF AMMONIA OR METHANOL', p.abstract_cn = '利用合成气的热量的方法用于产生超临界蒸汽在低能量氨或甲醇设备 包括重整或部分氧化阶段(1)， 至少一个超临界蒸汽发生器(3)具有壳侧和管侧， 至少一个过热器(14)， 至少一个背压式汽轮机(17)， 至少一个提取和凝式汽轮机(23)，至少一个锅炉给水泵(7)。 所合成的合成气(2)被发送到壳体侧的超临界蒸汽发生器(3)， 超临界蒸汽发生器(3)供给加压给水(4)， 给水流量调节，以保持蒸汽的温度在超临界蒸汽发生器的出口在 375-500℃的范围(13)， 超临界蒸汽的超临界蒸汽发生器中产生的225-450巴的压力下， 超临界蒸汽(13)的过热器(14)中进一步加热到500-750℃的温度， 和过热器中产生的超临界蒸汽供给到背压式汽轮机(17)。', p.abstract_en = 'Process for utilizing synthesis gas heat for the generation of supercritical steam in a low energy ammonia or methanol plant comprising a reforming or partial oxidation stage (1),  at least one supercritical steam generator (3) having a shell side and a tube side,  at least one superheater (14),  at least one back pressure turbine (17),  at least one extraction and condensing turbine (23),  at least one boiler feedwater pump (7). The synthesized synthesis gas (2) is sent to the shell side of the supercritical steam generator (3),  the supercritical steam generator (3) is fed with pressurized feedwater (4),  the feedwater flow is adjusted to maintain the steam temperature at the exit of the supercritical steam generator in the range of 375-500 C (13),  the supercritical steam is generated in the supercritical steam generator at a pressure of 225 - 450 bar,  the supercritical steam (13) is further heated in a superheater (14) to a temperature of 500 - 750 C,  and the supercritical steam generated in the superheater is fed to a back pressure turbine (17).', p.application_date = '2009-07-03 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CA2731306C', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2013532431'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2013532431', p.title_cn = '生产氢的方法，光制氢发生装置', p.title_en = 'The method of producing hydrogen and light hydrogen generating device', p.abstract_cn = '本发明的半导体材料的半导体材料包括含氧氮化物的至少一种元素选自4族元素和第5族元素. 在该氮氧化合物. 至少一个部分选自氧和氮的取代的碳. 优选为Nb5族元素.', p.abstract_en = 'A semiconductor material of the present invention is a semiconductor material including an oxynitride containing at least one element selected from the Group 4 elements and Group 5 elements. In the oxynitride,  part of at least one selected from oxygen and nitrogen is substituted with carbon. Nb is preferable as the Group 5 element.', p.application_date = '2012-08-31 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP5907973B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2011187137'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2011187137', p.title_cn = '氢气发生器和燃料电池', p.title_en = 'The hydrogen generator and fuel cell', p.abstract_cn = '要解决的问题 : 提供一种氢气产生的量的氢气发生器，其可以容易地控制. 不需要大型机械，并提供燃料电池. 溶液 : 所述氢气发生器包括一个圆柱形的氢发生元件5包括一个流体供应路径15通过该反应液和反应层(16)上设置所述流体供给通道15的外周. 本发明通过引入氢气发生反应时反应流体进入所述流体供给通道15，然后使流体渗入反应层(16). 由此产生氢气. 然后，. 由此产生的氢气排放到反应室(4). A(c)2013. &耕作方法.', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To provide a hydrogen generator that can easily control the amount of hydrogen generated,  without requiring a large mechanism and to provide a fuel cell.SOLUTION :  The hydrogen generator includes a cylindrical hydrogen-generating element 5 consisting of a fluid-supplying path 15 through which a reaction liquid flows and a reaction layer 16 arranged on the outer periphery of the fluid-supplying path 15. The hydrogen generation reaction is made by introducing the reaction fluid into the fluid-supplying path 15 and then making the fluid permeate the reaction layer 16,  whereby the hydrogen is generated. Then,  the hydrogen thus generated is discharged to a reaction chamber 4.', p.application_date = '2011-08-30 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP5909337B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/06', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'KR1020167005866'}) SET p.application_no = 'KR1020167005866', p.title_cn = '一氧化碳优先氧化反应器', p.title_en = 'REACTOR FOR PREFERENTIAL OXIDATION OF CARBON MONOXIDE', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一氧化碳选择性氧化反应器，特别是水上船舶或海上应用在燃料电池的一部分连续地加入乙醇处理系统一种反应器可以包括选择氧化的技术领域。. 用于冷却流的水，其中H[2]浓度高至少3的气体流换热器和至少催化剂层3包括用户操作模块氧化反应. 热交换器(1). 10. 12)单管(15)的总数在筒体外壳(14)，其特征在于 : 掺入. 其中，重整气(2)，圆柱形壳体的歧管用于基带中的一个上，而填料. 收集的重整气中CO选择性氧化反应器流出的锅炉模块(5). 11. 13)分别提供给设置在筒体底部的出口歧管以及多.', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention can be included in the technical field of CO preferential oxidation reactors and,  more specifically,  in preferential oxidation reactors that form part of an ethanol processing system for subsequently feeding a fuel cell used in naval or marine applications,  which comprises at least three heat exchangers for cooling a gas stream with a high H2 concentration by means of a water stream and at least three preferential oxidation reactor modules having a catalyst bed,  characterised in that the total number of tubes (15) of the heat exchangers (1,  10,  12) is integrated in a single cylindrical shell (14) and wherein an inlet manifold for the reformate gas (2) is disposed on one base of the cylindrical shell,  while an oulet manifold that collects the reformate gas that flows out of the tubes and feeds it to each of the CO preferential oxidation modules (5,  11,  13) is disposed on the other base of the cylindrical shell.', p.application_date = '2014-08-04 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'KR1020160045078A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/58', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US13737131'}) SET p.application_no = 'US13737131', p.title_cn = '磷酸三苯酯用作金属酰胺储氢材料的风险缓蚀剂', p.title_en = 'Use of triphenyl phosphate as risk mitigant for metal amide hydrogen storage materials', p.abstract_cn = '通过使用TPP添加剂的球磨工艺对储氢金属酰胺进行改性的过程的产物中的一种方法。 所得产品提供具有涂层的储氢金属酰胺，所述涂层使所述储氢金属酰胺耐空气、环境湿气和液态水，同时改善有用的储氢和释放动力学。', p.abstract_en = 'A process in a resulting product of the process in which a hydrogen storage metal amide is modified by a ball milling process using an additive of TPP. The resulting product provides for a hydrogen storage metal amide having a coating that renders the hydrogen storage metal amide resistant to air,  ambient moisture,  and liquid water while improving useful hydrogen storage and release kinetics.', p.application_date = '2013-01-09 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9321638B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 3, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US13391433'}) SET p.application_no = 'US13391433', p.title_cn = '甲醇与氨联产工艺', p.title_en = 'Process for methanol and ammonia co-production', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种联产甲醇和氨的方法，其中主要由一氧化碳(CO)、二氧化碳(CO2)和氢气(H2)组成的合成气混合物首先在甲醇直流反应器中部分反应，未反应的合成气被分成第一物流和第二物流，第一物流被纯化并进料到氨合成段，第二物流被进料到甲醇合成和纯化段。 利用该工艺，可以在一个集成的单一工艺中以非常高的能力生产甲醇和氨，采用不超过当前实际能力限制的单元操作。 例如，该工艺允许从天然气和空气开始每天生产8000吨甲醇和2000吨氨。 该工艺进一步显示出氨和二氧化碳的平衡生产，从而也允许尿素的联合生产。', p.abstract_en = 'This invention relates to a process for co-producing methanol and ammonia,  wherein a syngas mixture consisting essentially of carbon monoxide (CO),  carbon dioxide (CO2) and hydrogen (H2) is first partially reacted in a methanol once-through reactor,  unreacted syngas is divided into a first and a second stream,  the first stream is purified and fed to an ammonia synthesis section,  and the second stream is fed to a methanol synthesis and purification section. With this process it is possible to produce methanol and ammonia at very high capacities in an integrated single process,  applying unit operations not exceeding current practical capacity limitations. For example,  the process allows production of 8000 mtpd of methanol and 2000 mtpd of ammonia starting from natural gas and air. The process further shows a balanced production of ammonia and carbon dioxide,  thus allowing co-production of urea also to be integrated.', p.application_date = '2010-08-17 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9321639B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14716214'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14716214', p.title_cn = '将天然气转化为液体燃料和化学品的工艺', p.title_en = 'Process to convert natural gas into liquid fuels and chemicals', p.abstract_cn = '将轻烃如天然气转化为液体的过程。 真空变压吸附(VPSA)用于产生相对高纯度的氧气物流。 相对高纯度的氧在部分氧化反应器中与轻烃和水蒸气反应以产生合成气。 然后，合成气通过费托反应或相关反应转化为烃液体。', p.abstract_en = 'A process to convert light hydrocarbons such as natural gas to a liquid or liquids. Vacuum pressure swing adsorption (VPSA) is used to produce a stream of relatively high purity oxygen. The relatively high purity oxygen is reacted with light hydrocarbons and steam in a partial oxidation reactor in order to produce synthesis gas. The synthesis gas is thereafter converted to a hydrocarbon liquid or liquids via a Fischer Tropsch or related reaction.', p.application_date = '2015-05-19 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9321641B1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14096293'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14096293', p.title_cn = '降低SMR管温度的方法', p.title_en = 'Method for decreasing SMR tube temperature', p.abstract_cn = '提供了一种降低蒸汽甲烷重整(SMR)管温度的方法。 该方法可以包括以下步骤 : 在蒸汽存在下，在有效产生氢气和一氧化碳的条件下，将包含烃的进料引入到多个SMR管中，在操作期间监测SMR内的至少多个管的温度，将监测到的温度与第一预定值进行比较，以及当重整器管的监测到的温度在预定值或高于预定值时，将有效量的水引入到重整器管中，使得重整器管的温度降低。', p.abstract_en = 'A method for decreasing steam methane reformer (SMR) tube temperature is provided. The method can include the steps of introducing a hydrocarbon containing feed to be reformed to a plurality of SMR tubes in the presence of steam under conditions effective to produce hydrogen and carbon monoxide,  monitoring the temperature of at least a plurality of the tubes within the SMR during operation,  comparing the monitored temperature against a first predetermined value,  and introducing an effective amount of water to a reformer tube when the monitored temperature of the reformer tube is at or above the predetermined value,  such that the temperature of the reformer tube is reduced.', p.application_date = '2013-12-04 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9321642B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/26', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 2, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14364307'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14364307', p.title_cn = '通过烟气保持能量传递生产合成气的方法', p.title_en = 'Process for producing synthesis gas with preservation of the energy transfer by means of the fumes', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种通过在设有燃烧室和对流室的重整炉中对烃负载进行蒸汽重整来生产合成气的方法； 燃烧室包括填充有催化剂的竖直管，其中烃和蒸汽的混合物从管的顶部到底部循环，回收管的底部的粗合成气，以及成排设置的燃烧器加热管； 对流室排出含有燃烧产生的气体的烟气。 该方法还包括使用包含在烟气中的热量来预热和/或加热与该方法相关或无关的各种流体的步骤。 在烟气质量流减少的情况下，通过向燃烧区域供应补充气流来维持要传递到对流区域中的能量的量。', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention concerns a process for producing synthesis gas by steam reforming a hydrocarbon load in a reforming furnace provided with a combustion chamber and a convection chamber;  the combustion chamber includes vertical tubes filled with catalyst wherein a mixture of hydrocarbons and steam circulates from top to bottom recovering raw synthesis gas at the bottom of the tubes,  and burners disposed in rows heat the tubes;  the convection chamber discharges fumes containing the gases produced by the combustion. The process also comprises steps of using the heat contained in the fumes for preheating and/or heating various fluids related or unrelated to the process. In the event of the reduction of the mass flow of fumes,  the quantity of energy to be transferred into the convection area is maintained by supplying a supplementary gaseous flow to the combustion area.', p.application_date = '2012-12-11 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9321643B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14286633'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14286633', p.title_cn = '可再充装且无腐蚀性的气瓶内的环保型燃料气体', p.title_en = 'Environmentally friendly fuel gas within a refillable and non-corrosive gas cylinder', p.abstract_cn = '提供了一种可用作各种应用的热源的制品。 该物品包括气缸内的环境友好气体燃料混合物，该混合物既无腐蚀性又可再充装。 更具体地说，气体燃料混合物含有氢和甲烷。 还提供了使用该制品作为热源的方法。', p.abstract_en = 'An article is provided that can be used as a heating source for various applications. The article includes an environmentally friendly gaseous fuel mixture within a gas cylinder that is both non-corrosive and refillable. More specifically,  the gaseous fuel mixture contains hydrogen and methane. Methods of using the article as a heating source are also provided.', p.application_date = '2014-05-23 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9322572B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'IN7838DELNP2015'}) SET p.application_no = 'IN7838DELNP2015', p.title_cn = '集成发电和化工生产，利用燃料电池', p.title_en = 'INTEGRATED POWER GENERATION AND CHEMICAL PRODUCTION USING FUEL CELLS', p.abstract_cn = '在各种方面的系统和方法提供了用于操作熔融碳酸盐燃料电池与过量的可再成形燃料进行氧化的量相对于燃料电池的阳极中。替代于选择的操作条件的燃料电池电效率的提高或最大化燃料电池燃料的可再成形可通入过量的燃料电池以增加阳极的化学燃料电池的能量输出。这可以导致总效率提高电效率的基于燃料电池的组合化学燃料电池的效率。', p.abstract_en = 'In various aspects systems and methods are provided for operating a molten carbonate fuel cell with an excess of reformable fuel relative to the amount of oxidation performed in the anode of the fuel cell. Instead of selecting the operating conditions of a fuel cell to improve or maximize the electrical efficiency of the fuel cell an excess of reformable fuel can be passed into the anode of the fuel cell to increase the chemical energy output of the fuel cell. This can lead to an increase in the total efficiency of the fuel cell based on the combined electrical efficiency and chemical efficiency of the fuel cell.', p.application_date = '2015-09-01 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'IN7838DELNP2015A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/50', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'DE60049219'}) SET p.application_no = 'DE60049219', p.title_cn = '氢气发生器', p.title_en = 'Hydrogen generator', p.abstract_cn = '本说明书公开了一种氢气发生器，用于产生氢气， 包括至少一个燃料供给部，用于将烃类燃料， 燃料燃烧部， 供水部分， 一种气体混合部，用于混合燃料和水， 和重整部分填充有重整催化剂， 其中至少一个所述气体混合部分和加热的重整部产生的废气 在燃烧部。 氢气发生器根据本发明的目的是提高热效率， 降低热损失的装置，具有简单的结构和收集余热用于有效使用 。', p.abstract_en = 'The present specification discloses a hydrogen generator for generating a hydrogen gas,  comprising at least a fuel supply part for supplying a hydrocarbon type fuel,  a fuel combustion part,  a water supply part,  a gas mixing part for mixing the fuel and water,  and a reforming part filled with a reforming catalyst,  wherein at least one of the gas mixing part and the reforming part is heated by an exhaust gas generated in the combustion part. The hydrogen generator according to the present invention aims to improve the heat efficiency,  reducing the heat loss from the apparatus with a simple constitution and collecting the waste heat for an effective use thereof.', p.application_date = '2000-05-22 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'DE60049219T2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'DE602013005440'}) SET p.application_no = 'DE602013005440', p.title_cn = '燃料处理装置', p.title_en = 'FUEL PROCESSING DEVICE', p.abstract_cn = '提供一种燃料处理装置，包括 : 一燃烧单元设有热源； 一种脱硫单元提取硫组分从源气体； 重整单元，用于生成， 从脱硫源气体，含氢气体具有氢作为主要成分； 和低温转换单元，其配备有一发热催化剂用于降低在含氢的杂质浓度 气体。 重整单元，脱硫单元被配置为以围绕所述燃烧单元， 并向外同心地设置在给定顺序从所述燃烧单元。 本发明还包括预热通道，连接到脱硫单元， 其提供给所述燃烧单元的底部通过保温材料， 使得源气体进行预热，热量从燃烧器。', p.abstract_en = 'Provided is a fuel processing device including :  a combustion unit equipped with a heat source;  a desulfurization unit for extracting a sulfur component from the source gas;  a reforming unit for generating,  from the desulfurized source gas,  a hydrogen-containing gas having hydrogen as a main component thereof;  and a low-temperature conversion unit equipped with an exothermic catalyst for reducing the impurity concentration in the hydrogen-containing gas. The reforming unit and the desulfurization unit are configured so as to surround the combustion unit,  and are disposed concentrically in the given order facing outwards from the combustion unit. The present invention further includes a preheating passage which is connected to the desulfurization unit,  and which is provided to a bottom part of the combustion unit via a heat insulation material,  such that the source gas is preheated by heat from the combustion unit.', p.application_date = '2013-06-24 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'DE602013005440T2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'KR1020140141610'}) SET p.application_no = 'KR1020140141610', p.title_cn = '甲醇燃料refomer紧凑', p.title_en = 'COMPACT METHANOL FUEL REFOMER', p.abstract_cn = '外壳，该外壳具有结构简单，显著降低内的放大比例甲醇燃料的小型容易的公开. 本发明根据少量的甲醇燃料扭转圆柱形的壳体. 所述圆柱形壳体的中心供暖单元的记录层上的数据. 所述供热单元内芯含有. 原料包括甲醇和水提供多个热催化剂加热所述原料蒸发的蒸气供应单元，效率. 所述内芯包括包括原料供应单元. 气化原料与氢气和甲醇重整器，用于将. 在上侧形成所述重整器. 重整器，用于去除废气中所含的一氧化碳的一氧化碳除去部. 所述重整器和一氧化碳消除单元以将数据广播到所述圆柱形壳体板和棱镜支持件. 所述重整器或一氧化碳去除单元填充部分填充催化剂的催化剂. 其特征在于，包括 : .', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention relates to a compact methanol fuel reformer which can be easily manufactured by simplifying the structure thereof. The compact methanol fuel reformer comprises :  a cylindrical housing;  a heat supplying part formed at the central portion in the cylindrical housing;  a raw material feeding part which supplies raw materials including methanol and water while they are vaporized by the heat supplied from the heat supplying part;  a reforming part formed at the outside of the raw material feeding part and reforming the methanol contained in the vaporized raw materials into hydrogen;  a carbon monoxide removing part formed at the top of the reforming part to remove carbon monoxide contained in the discharge gas of the reforming part;  and a catalyst filling part formed on the lateral surface of the cylindrical housing to be connected to the reforming part and the carbon monoxide removing part so that the reforming part or the carbon monoxide removing part may be filled with a catalyst.(AA) Methanol + H_2O(BB) Combustion exhaust gas(CC) Reforming gasCOPYRIGHT KIPO 2016', p.application_date = '2014-10-20 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'KR101616199B1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'SG11201504154T'}) SET p.application_no = 'SG11201504154T', p.title_cn = '用于生产氢气的方法和组件', p.title_en = 'A METHOD AND ASSEMBLY FOR THE PRODUCTION OF HYDROGEN GAS', p.abstract_cn = '提供了一种在与合成气分开的料流中生产氢气的方法。 还提供了一种用于在与合成气分开的流中生产氢气的组件和一种生产氢气的方法。', p.abstract_en = 'Provided is a process for producing hydrogen gas in a separate stream from syngas. An assembly for producing hydrogen gas in a separate stream from syngas and a method of producing hydrogen are also provided.', p.application_date = '2012-11-27 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'SG11201504154TB', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'TR201505759'}) SET p.application_no = 'TR201505759', p.title_cn = '一种溶液控制的新设计氢气发生器。', p.title_en = 'A solution controlled new design hydrogen generator.', p.abstract_cn = '本发明的目的在于，对于所有消耗汽油、柴油、内燃机中的LPG、天然气、LPG、丙烷丁烷、燃料油、沼气和类似的燃料消耗燃烧系统，除了现有的燃烧燃料系统中产生氢气和氧气之外，还可以将氢气和氧气添加到燃烧反应中，并且通过使用市电水，所产生的气体尽可能多； 天然气丙烷-丁烷，燃料油汽油，柴油，LPG，CNG，LNG是用于燃烧系统的新一代发电机，其根据需要混合沼气燃烧系统，由于燃烧反应的改善，减少了对环境的有害排放。允许仅使用市电水的单元(图1)，两个电解单元设计成在12V、24V或48、110V直流电压下操作(图2)，两个水箱携带溶液和纯水(图3)， 收集容器，其中收集过量溶液以便保持单元池中的电流值恒定(图4)、用于洗涤作为该过程的结果产生的氢气和氧气的一个洗涤室容器(图5)和气体火焰长度调节容器(图6)以及电子控制系统(图7)，所述电子控制系统可以将混合物分离成所需比例的氢气和氧气。', p.abstract_en = 'The aim of the present invention is that for all systems that consume gasoline,  diesel,  LPG in internal combustion engines,  natural gas,  LPG,  Propane butane,  fuel oil,  biogas and similar fuel consuming combustion systems,  hydrogen and oxygen gas can be added to the combustion reaction in addition to the existing burning fuel Generating hydrogen and oxygen in the system and as much as desired by using mains water,  the produced gas;  natural gas Propane-butane,  fuel oil gasoline,  diesel,  LPG,  CNG, LNG is a new generation generator for combustion systems that mixes biogas burning systems as desired,  reduces harmful emissions to the environment as a result of the improvement of the combustion reaction.a unit that allows using only mains water (Figure 1) Two electrolysis units designed to operate at 12 V,  24 V or 48,  110 V DC voltage (Figure 2), Two water tanks carrying solution and pure water (figure 3),  collecting container in which excess solutions are collected in order to keep the current value constant in the cells (figure 4),  one washing chamber container for washing the hydrogen and oxygen gas produced as a result of this process (figure 5) and gas There is a flame length regulation vessel (Figure 6) and an electronic control system (Figure 7) that can separate the mixture into hydrogen and oxygen at the desired ratio.', p.application_date = '2015-05-13 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'TR201505759A2', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14922389'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14922389', p.title_cn = '利用捕获二氧化碳的天然气发电', p.title_en = 'GENERATING POWER FROM A NATURAL GAS WITH CARBON DIOXIDE CAPTURE', p.abstract_cn = '在一些实施方式中，一种或多种方法可包括产生用于燃气轮机的富氢燃料气体，该富氢燃料气体用氮气和蒸汽压载并过热至高于其露点的温度。 燃料气体可以具有最小的或减少的CO2含量或包含碳的燃料组分CO和CH4含量，使得当在合适的燃气轮机中燃烧时，可以具有最小的或减少的CO2向大气的排放。 这些示例性方法可导致捕获作为压缩到管道输送压力的CO2存在于总天然气进料中的大部分碳，以进行螯合。', p.abstract_en = 'In some implementations,  one or more methods can include producing a hydrogen rich fuel gas for a gas turbine ballasted with nitrogen and steam and superheated to a temperature above its dew point. The fuel gas may have a minimal or reduced content of CO2 or fuel components CO and CH4 which contain carbon so that when combusted in a suitable gas turbine there may be minimal or reduced emissions of CO2 to the atmosphere. These example methods may result in a capture of the bulk of the carbon present in the total natural gas feed as CO2 compressed to pipeline delivery pressure for sequestration.', p.application_date = '2015-10-26 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US20160107890A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/34', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 2, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14855493'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14855493', p.title_cn = '气体发生装置', p.title_en = 'Gas Generating Apparatus', p.abstract_cn = '在不使用铂催化剂的情况下，使碳化氢和水反应，生成一氧化碳浓度为0.1%以下的氢。 一种气体发生设备，包括气体瞬时加热机构和催化剂容器，所述气体瞬时加热机构瞬时加热源气体，所述催化剂容器连接到所述气体瞬时加热机构并包含催化剂，由所述气体瞬时加热机构产生的高温加热的源气体束与所述催化剂碰撞以产生气体。 更具体地说，将含有碳化氢和水的原料气体瞬时加热到高温，并使原料气体束与催化剂碰撞。 由于没有驻点层，源气体的热量被传递到催化剂表面，并且非平衡反应在催化剂上有效地进行。 氢可以用钌制成的廉价催化剂提取。', p.abstract_en = 'To generate hydrogen having a carbon monoxide concentration of 0.1% or less by reacting a hydrogen carbide and water with each other without using a platinum catalyst. A gas generating apparatus includes a gas instantaneously-heating mechanism that instantaneously heats a source gas and a catalyst vessel that is connected to the gas instantaneously-heating mechanism and contains a catalyst,  a high-temperature heated source gas beam generated by the gas instantaneously-heating mechanism being caused to collide with the catalyst to generate a gas. More specifically,  a source gas containing a hydrogen carbide and water is instantaneously heated to a high temperature,  and a source gas beam is caused to collide with the catalyst. Heat of the source gas is transmitted to a catalyst surface because of the absence a stagnation layer,  and nonequilibrium reaction efficiently proceeds on the catalyst. Hydrogen can be extracted with a low-price catalyst made of ruthenium.', p.application_date = '2015-09-16 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US20160107891A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201180008085.2'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201180008085.2', p.title_cn = '热化学过程的诱导及相关系统和方法', p.title_en = 'Induction of thermochemical process and related system and method', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及热化学过程的诱导及相关的系统和方法。根据特定实施方案的方法包括在反应器中设置第一和第二基底，各基底具有彼此面对的表面。方法可进一步包括将前体气体导入反应器并激活接近基底的相对表面的感应线圈以解离前体气体。将前体气体的成分沉积在第一和第二表面上，且由每个表面和/或沉积在该表面上的成分辐射的热在另一表面和/或沉积在另一表面上的成分处被接收。', p.abstract_en = 'In one embodiment,  a gas hydrate conversion system is provided comprising a floating factory,  an appendage for harvesting a gas hydrate from an oceanic hydrate deposit,  and one or more storage tanks. The floating factory comprises one or more heat exchange assemblies,  one or more heat pump assemblies and an engine. In another embodiment,  a method for harvesting hydrocarbon hydrate deposits is provided,  the method comprising providing a gas hydrate conversion system;  inducing release of methane from an oceanic hydrate deposit;  capturing the methane from a primary methane capture zone and/or a secondary methane capture zone;  and converting the methane to hydrogen and carbon.', p.application_date = '2011-02-14 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN102844264B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/24', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201310181309.0'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201310181309.0', p.title_cn = '一种制氢储氢为一体的集成供氢装置', p.title_en = 'system hydrogen Chu Qing as a whole an integrated hydrogen supply device', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种制氢储氢为一体的集成供氢装置，由制氢装置、储氢装置、进出气管道系统三部分构成。制氢装置由外壳、蒸笼式内胆、方形密封法兰盖构成。储氢装置由方形外壳、密封法兰盖、内置储氢隔层构成。进出气系统由水蒸气输入系统、氢气输出系统、净化后的氢气输出系统构成。本发明将制氢装置安装在储氢装置内部，可以有效解决储氢装置所需氢源问题。干燥器、储氢隔层安装在所述集成供氢装置内部，为氢气的干燥提纯提供便利条件。本发明还解决了水解装置反应不可控制的难题。将制氢储氢集成为一整体，设计简单，节省空间，便于控制，为不同型号燃料电池提供较纯的氢气燃料，可适用于工业生产。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to an integrated hydrogen supply device integrating hydrogen production with hydrogen storage. The integrated hydrogen supply device is composed of a hydrogen production device,  a hydrogen storage device and a gas inlet and outlet pipeline system,  wherein the hydrogen production device is composed of a shell,  a steaming basket-shaped liner and a square sealing flange cover,  the hydrogen storage device is composed of a square shell,  a sealing flange cover and a built-in hydrogen storage interlayer,  the gas inlet and outlet pipeline system is composed of a water vapor input system,  a hydrogen output system and a purified hydrogen output system. According to the integrated hydrogen supply device provided by the invention,  the hydrogen production device is installed in the hydrogen storage device to effectively solve the necessary hydrogen source problem of the hydrogen storage device. A dryer and the hydrogen storage interlayer are installed in the integrated hydrogen supply device for providing a convenient condition to dry and purify the hydrogen. The integrated hydrogen supply device is used for further solving the difficulty of reaction uncontrollability of the hydrolysisplant. The hydrogen production is integrated with hydrogen storage,  thereby ensuring simple design,  saving space,  facilitating to control,  providing pure hydrogen fuel to fuel cells with different model numbers and being applicable to industrial production.', p.application_date = '2013-05-16 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN103241710B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201410259647.6'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201410259647.6', p.title_cn = '利用双流化床同时制取氢气和二氧化碳的装置及方法', p.title_en = 'By using dual fluidized bed at the same time of producing hydrogen gas and carbon dioxide device and method for', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种利用双流化床同时制取氢气和二氧化碳的装置及方法，可解决氢气纯度不高容易引起爆炸，以及无法同时制取CO2的问题。本发明的优点在于装置通过反应剂的再生使得设备能够循环运行，由此可大规模生产；反应产生的热在冷凝器内传递给空气，再经热空气将热量供给给余热锅炉，使整套设备比较节能。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention discloses a device and method for simultaneously preparing hydrogen and carbon dioxide by using double fluidized beds,  which can solve the problems that explosion is easily caused due to low purity of hydrogen and CO2 cannot be simultaneously prepared. The device and method disclosed by the invention have the advantages that the device can run circularly through regeneration of reactants,  so that large-scale production can be realized;  heat generated by reaction is transferred to air in a condenser and then supplied to a waste heat boiler through hot air,  so that the whole device is relatively energy-saving.', p.application_date = '2014-06-11 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN104030240B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/06', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201410280325.X'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201410280325.X', p.title_cn = '一种气基竖炉系统还原气净化和尾气处理的系统及方法', p.title_en = 'An air-based vertical furnace system reduction is mad the purification and exhaust gas processing system and method', p.abstract_cn = '本发明提供了一种气基竖炉系统还原气净化和尾气处理的系统，包括制粗还原气单元(1)、粗还原气脱硫脱碳单元(2)、脱硫脱碳酸气处理单元(3)、尾气处理及催化剂再生单元(4)、气基竖炉还原炼铁单元(5)；其中，所述制粗还原气单元(1)依次连接所述粗还原气脱硫脱碳单元(2)、所述脱硫脱碳酸气处理单元(3)、所述尾气处理及催化剂再生单元(4)；所述粗还原气脱硫脱碳单元(2)与所述尾气处理及催化剂再生单元(4)、所述气基竖炉还原炼铁单元(5)分别相连；所述气基竖炉还原炼铁单元(5)与所述尾气处理及催化剂再生单元(4)相连。本发明降低了对粗还原气原料的要求，减少了尾气排放及环境污染。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention provides a system for reducing gas purification and tail gas treatment of a gas base shaft furnace system. The system comprises a crude reducing gas preparation unit (1),  a crude reducing gas decarburization and desulfurization unit (2),  a decarburization and desulfurization acid gas treatment unit (3),  a tail gas treatment and catalyst regeneration unit (4) and a gas base shaft furnace reducing iron-making unit (5),  wherein the crude reducing gas preparation unit (1) is sequentially connected with the crude reducing gas decarburization and desulfurization unit (2),  the decarburization and desulfurization acid gas treatment unit (3) and the tail gas treatment and catalyst regeneration unit (4);  the crude reducing gas decarburization and desulfurization unit (2) is respectively connected with the tail gas treatment and catalyst regeneration unit (4) and the gas base shaft furnace reducing iron-making unit (5);  and the gas base shaft furnace reducing iron-making unit (5) is connected with the tail gas treatment and catalyst regeneration unit (4). By adopting the system,  the demands on the crude reducing gas materials are reduced,  and exhaust gas emission and environmental pollution are reduced.', p.application_date = '2014-06-20 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN104030243B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 2, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201410280315.6'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201410280315.6', p.title_cn = '一种天然气催化部分氧化生产直接海绵铁的工艺', p.title_en = 'A kind of natural gas the catalytic partial oxidation process for producing direct sponge iron', p.abstract_cn = '本发明提供了一种天然气催化部分氧化生产直接海绵铁的工艺，将天然气导入预热器预热；预热后的天然气进入精脱硫反应器经加氢催化、高温脱硫后排出；在蓄热式管式加热炉中，精脱硫后的天然气在催化剂晶格氧作用下转化为CO和H2；还原气进入气基竖炉生产海绵铁。本发明的工艺流程简单高效，能耗低，既避免了爆炸的危险，又可低成本地制造出合格的海绵铁还原气，整个工艺体系简单，过程容易控制，易于实现工业化。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention provides a process for directly producing sponge iron by catalytic partial oxidation of natural gas. The process comprises the following steps :  introducing natural gas into a preheater and preheating;  enabling the preheated gas to enter a fine desulfurization reactor,  carrying out catalytic hydrogenation,  desulfurizing at a high temperature and discharging;  in a regenerative tubular heating furnace,  converting the finely desulfurized natural gas into CO and H2 under the action of lattice oxygen used as a catalyst;  enabling the reduced gas to enter a gas-based shaft furnace to produce sponge iron. The process disclosed by the invention is simple and efficient and low in energy consumption,  the risk of explosion is avoided,  qualified sponge iron reducing gas can be manufactured at a low cost,  the entire process system is simple,  the process is easily controlled and the industrialization is easily realized.', p.application_date = '2014-06-20 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN104045057B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 2, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201410606442.0'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201410606442.0', p.title_cn = '富含甲烷气体制备H2/CO比例可调的合成气的装置和方法', p.title_en = 'Preparation rich in methane gas H 2/CO proportion of the synthesis gas of the adjustable device and method', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开一种富含甲烷气体制备H2/CO比例可调的合成气的装置和方法，包括燃料反应器、空气反应器、第一旋风分离器、第二旋风分离器、返料阀一、返料阀二、返料阀三；所述燃料反应器下部为鼓泡流化床，上部为提升管；鼓泡流化床通过返料阀一和空气反应器连接，空气反应器上部和第一旋风分离器连接，第一旋风分离器的下料管通过返料阀二和提升管连接，提升管上部连接第二旋风分离器，第二旋风分离器的下料管通过返料阀三和鼓泡流化床下部连接。通过调节载氧体的循环量和在鼓泡流化床内的停留时间控制鼓泡流化床中载氧体的还原深度，从而调整合成气出口处的H2/CO比例，便于后续合成工艺，同时能即时分离捕获CO2，避免了分离步骤。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention discloses an apparatus for preparing synthetic gas with adjustable H2/CO proportion by methane-rich gas and a method thereof. The apparatus comprises a fuel reactor,  an air reactor,  a first cyclone separator,  a second cyclone separator,  a material returning valve 1,  a material returning valve 2 and a material returning valve 3;  a bubbling fluidized bed is arranged at bottom of the fuel reactor,  a lifting pipe is arranged at upper part of the fuel reactor;  the bubbling fluidized bed is connected to the air reactor through the material returning valve 1,  the upper part of the air reactor is connected to the first cyclone separator,  a blanking tube of the first cyclone separator is connected to the lifting pipe through the material turning valve 2,  the upper part of the lifting pipe is connected to the second cyclone separator,  and the blanking tube of the second cyclone separator is connected to the lower part of the bubbling fluidized bed through the material turning valve 3. By adjusting the circulation volume of oxygen carrier and stay time in the bubbling fluidized bed,  the reduction depth of the oxygen carrier in the bubbling fluidized bed can be controlled,  proportion of H2/CO at a synthetic gas outlet can be adjusted,  subsequent synthesis technology is convenient,  CO2 can be instantly separated and captured,  and separating step can be avoided.', p.application_date = '2014-10-31 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN104401938B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201520797263.X'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201520797263.X', p.title_cn = '一种带有闭环冷却系统的转化炉烧嘴', p.title_en = 'A closed-loop cooling system with the conversion furnace burner', p.abstract_cn = '本实用新型涉及一种带有闭环冷却系统的转化炉烧嘴，包括空气通道，空气通道的侧面设有空气入口，空气通道的一端设有电点火器接口，空气通道的另一端设有孔板构成的圆锥筒状扩散口一；空气通道的外侧套置有原料气通道，原料气通道的侧面设有原料气入口，原料气通道位于扩散口一的一端设有圆锥筒状的扩散口二；在空气通道的左端外侧设置有冷却系统。本实用新型在烧嘴高温处设置有散热盘管，能够实时降温，从而大大提高烧嘴的寿命。', p.abstract_en = 'The utility model relates to a closed-loop cooling system with the conversion furnace burner,  comprising an air passage,  the side of the air channel is provided with an air inlet,  one end of the air channel is provided with an electric igniter interface,  the other end of the air channel is provided with the orifice plate to form a conical tubular diffusion mouth one ;  sleeved on the outer side of the air passage channel with a raw material gas,  the raw material gas channel is provided with a raw material gas inlet side of the,  raw materials located in diffusion of gas passage is arranged on one end of a conical cylindrical diffusion mouth two ;  the outer side of the left end of the air passage is provided with a cooling system. The utility model of the burner at high temperature portion is provided with a radiating disk tube,  the temperature can be real-time,  thereby greatly improving the service life of the burner.', p.application_date = '2015-10-15 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN205170384U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/34', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201520803591.6'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201520803591.6', p.title_cn = '一种制氢转化炉烧嘴', p.title_en = 'A hydrogen-conversion furnace burner', p.abstract_cn = '本实用新型涉及一种制氢转化炉烧嘴，包括空气通道、内管和原料气通道，空气通道上设有空气入口，原料气通道上设有原料气入口，内管的一端设有电点火器接口；空气通道上依次设有第一扩散口、喉管、平滑带和第二扩散口，在第一扩散口和喉管之间设有一富氧空气分布器，空气通道对应富氧空气分布器的位置设有原料气分布环；在原料气通道的外侧设有对接法兰，对接法兰上设有催化剂通道，催化剂通道的端部设有催化剂入口。在所述第二扩散口的出口位置内腔设置有用以支撑内管的网格状呈喇叭状的支撑架，所述支撑架的中心固定设置有用以使内管穿过的支撑管。本实用新型能够使得富氧空气与原料气的混合更加均匀，利于燃烧和反应的进行。', p.abstract_en = 'The utility model relates to a hydrogen-conversion furnace burner,  comprising an air passage,  the inner tube and the raw gas channel,  an air passage is provided with an air inlet,  the raw material gas channel is provided with a raw material gas inlet,  one end of the inner pipe is provided with an electric igniter interface;  sequentially on an air passage is provided with a 1st proliferation mouth,  pipes,  smooth proliferation mouth with and 2nd,  1st diffusion port and pipes in between suitable distributor is provided with a rich,  oxygen-enriched air distributor air channel corresponding to the position of the gas distribution ring is provided with a raw material;  the outside of the raw material gas channel is provided with a butt flange,  the channel abutting the flange is provided with a catalyst,  catalyst the end of the channel is provided with a catalyst inlet. In the 2nd diffusing opening position is arranged in the inner cavity of the outlet of the inner tube is useful in order to support the grid form took the form of a trumpet-shaped supporting frame,  the supporting frame is fixed to the center of the inner tube through the support tube. The utility model can be used for the raw material gas of the oxygen-enriched air can be more evenly mixed,  thereby favoring the combustion and of the reaction.', p.application_date = '2015-10-15 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN205170385U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/34', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 1, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'EP10777592'}) SET p.application_no = 'EP10777592', p.title_cn = '氢生成系统及热水生产系统', p.title_en = 'HYDROGEN GENERATION SYSTEM AND HOT WATER PRODUCTION SYSTEM', p.abstract_cn = '氢气产生系统(2A)包括氢产生部(201)保持第第一液含有水和 : 允许部分的第一液中含有的水分解成氢气和氧气，和至少第一的一部分待加热液体，通过照射太阳光，一种第一热交换器(207)进行冷却的第一液氢中加热生成单元(201)和加热第二之间通过热交换液第一液和第二液，和机构(例如，一种循环管路(204)和泵(205))，其将第一液体第一中冷却热交换器(207)入的氢气产生单元(201)。', p.abstract_en = 'A hydrogen generation system (2A) includes a hydrogen generation unit (201) that holds a first liquid containing water and that allows a part of the water contained in the first liquid to be decomposed into hydrogen and oxygen,  and at least a part of the first liquid to be heated,  by being irradiated with sunlight,  a first heat exchanger (207) that cools the first liquid heated in the hydrogen generation unit (201) and heats the second liquid by heat exchange between the first liquid and the second liquid,  and a mechanism (for example,  a circulation line (204) and a pump (205)) that introduces the first liquid cooled in the first heat exchanger (207) into the hydrogen generation unit (201).', p.application_date = '2010-05-21 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'EP2433903B1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'EP13748505'}) SET p.application_no = 'EP13748505', p.title_cn = '氢气或氘气的生产方法，用于生产氢化或氘代有机化合物的方法，氢化或重氢化有机化合物的方法，脱卤有机化合物的方法具有卤素，和机械化学反应中使用的球', p.title_en = 'METHOD FOR PRODUCING HYDROGEN OR DEUTERIUM,  METHOD FOR PRODUCING HYDROGENATED OR DEUTERATED ORGANIC COMPOUND,  METHOD FOR HYDROGENATING OR DEUTERATING ORGANIC COMPOUND,  METHOD FOR DEHALOGENATING ORGANIC COMPOUND HAVING HALOGEN,  AND BALL FOR USE IN MECHANOCHEMICAL REACTION', p.abstract_cn = '目的是提供的高效氢或重氢的制造方法和用于氢化(protiating，重氢化或tritiating)的有机化合物，和提供设备和使用等优点。一种氢或重氢的制造方法，含有使水或重水到机械化学反应，在催化剂金属的存在下，在能量密度的旋转加速度75克或更高，应用于水或重水中25分钟以上，用于生产氢化重水进行机械化学反应的方法，氘或氚)的有机化合物，用于加氢(protiating的方法，重氢化或tritiating)的有机化合物，脱卤有机化合物的方法具有卤素，和球机械化学反应，备有。', p.abstract_en = 'Objects are to provide efficient methods for producing hydrogen or heavy hydrogens and for hydrogenating (protiating,  deuterating or tritiating) an organic compound,  and to provide an equipment and the like used therefor. A method for producing hydrogen or heavy hydrogens,  containing subjecting water or heavy water to mechanochemical reaction in the presence of a catalyst metal,  in which an energy density of a rotational acceleration of 75 G or more is applied to water or heavy water for 25 minutes or more,  a method for producing a hydrogenated (protiated,  deuterated or tritiated) organic compound,  a method for hydrogenating (protiating,  deuterating or tritiating) an organic compound,  a method for dehalogenating an organic compound having halogen,  and a ball for mechanochemical reaction are provied.', p.application_date = '2013-02-08 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'EP2816008A4', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/08', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2013015095'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2013015095', p.title_cn = '氢氧化催化剂', p.title_en = 'Catalyst hydroxide', p.abstract_cn = '一种非晶态钴进行氧化处理，用水本发明公开了一种钨酸盐. 多个非晶态钴钨酸盐纳米粒子负载在电极上，并能产生氧气与水分子发生催化性相互作用. 所述催化剂可用作电化学或光电化学电池的一部分电能的产生.', p.abstract_en = 'A process for oxidizing water using amorphous cobalt tungstate is disclosed. A plurality of amorphous cobalt tungstate nanoparticles are supported on an electrode and are able to catalytically interact with water molecules generating oxygen. The catalyst can be used as part of a electrochemical or photo-electrochemical cell for the generation of electrical energy.', p.application_date = '2013-01-30 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP5905839B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2014149898'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2014149898', p.title_cn = '余热回收装置及余热的回收方法', p.title_en = 'The waste heat recovery device and method of recovering waste heat', p.abstract_cn = '本发明提供一种废热回收装置，其包括第第一热交换器. 一种重整器和重整器进料预热器依次设置在汽车中的废气排放管从上游到下游. 其中，在废气的上游废气温度高于在下游排气管. 在一个实施方案中. 所述重整器可以具有一种制氢重整器. 和将产生的氢气通入燃烧用的设备. 以这样的方式. 可有效利用余热. 和可固定的燃烧设备内部积碳的问题. 还提供了一种余热回收方法.', p.abstract_en = 'Provided is a waste heat recovery apparatus including a first heat exchanger,  a reformer and a reformer feed pre-heater sequentially disposed on or in the waste gas exhaust pipe from the upstream to the downstream thereof,  wherein the waste gas temperature at the upstream of the waste gas exhaust pipe is higher than that at the downstream. In an embodiment,  the reformer can be a hydrogen-generation reformer,  and the generated hydrogen is introduced into the burning equipment for use. In such manner,  the waste heat can be effectively utilized,  and the carbon deposition issue inside the burning equipment can be fixed. A waste heat recovery method is also provided.', p.application_date = '2014-07-23 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP5905933B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2014509034'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2014509034', p.title_cn = '氢生成装置及燃料电池系统', p.title_en = 'Hydrogen generator and fuel cell system', p.abstract_cn = '一种氢气发生器(1)包括重整器(7). 燃烧器(15). 第第一温度检测器(10). 原料供应单元(11)。. 原料流量测量单元(12)。. 移除单元(8). 9). 反应气体供给单元(13). 14). 以及控制单元(18)。. 所述控制单元被配置为控制量的原料气体从所述原料供应单元，使得检测的第第一检测温度第一的温度达到预定温度探测器. 并控制反应物的量基于反应气体供应单元供应的气体的原料气体流的测量原料流量测量装置. 在原料气体的量控制.', p.abstract_en = 'A hydrogen generator (1) comprises a reformer (7),  a combustor (15),  a first temperature detector (10),  a raw material supply unit (11),  a raw material flow measuring unit (12),  a removing unit (8,  9),  a reactant gas supply unit (13,  14),  and a control unit (18). The control unit is configured to control an amount of the raw material gas supplied from the raw material supply unit such that a first detection temperature detected by the first temperature detector reaches a predetermined temperature,  and to control an amount of the reactant gas supplied from the reactant gas supply unit based on the flow of the raw material gas which is measured by the raw material flow measuring unit,  during control of the amount of the raw material gas.', p.application_date = '2013-03-12 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP5906423B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2014509035'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2014509035', p.title_cn = '氢生成装置及燃料电池系统', p.title_en = 'Hydrogen generator and fuel cell system', p.abstract_cn = '一种氢气发生器(1)包括重整器(7). 燃烧器(15). 第第一温度检测器(10). 原料供应单元(11)。. 原料流量测量单元(12)。. 移除单元(8). 9). 反应气体供给单元(13). 14). 以及控制单元(18)。. 所述控制单元被配置为控制量的原料气体从所述原料供应单元，使得检测的第第一检测温度第一的温度达到预定温度探测器. 并控制反应物的量基于反应气体供应单元供应的气体的原料气体流的测量原料流量测量装置. 在原料气体的量控制.', p.abstract_en = 'A hydrogen generator (1) comprises a reformer (7),  a combustor (15),  a first temperature detector (10),  a raw material supply unit (11),  a raw material flow measuring unit (12),  a removing unit (8,  9),  a reactant gas supply unit (13,  14),  and a control unit (18). The control unit is configured to control an amount of the raw material gas supplied from the raw material supply unit such that a first detection temperature detected by the first temperature detector reaches a predetermined temperature,  and to control an amount of the reactant gas supplied from the reactant gas supply unit based on the flow of the raw material gas which is measured by the raw material flow measuring unit,  during control of the amount of the raw material gas.', p.application_date = '2013-03-12 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP5906424B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CA2831561'}) SET p.application_no = 'CA2831561', p.title_cn = '抑制金属污染的方法合成气生产装置', p.title_en = 'METHOD OF SUPPRESSING METAL CONTAMINATION OF SYNTHESIS GAS PRODUCTION APPARATUS', p.abstract_cn = '合成气生产装置(重整装置)可用于合成气生产的步骤，GTL(气-液)工艺防止金属污染成分。抑制金属污染的方法的合成气制造装置的运转用于GTL工艺包括生产合成气的合成气制造工序通过使天然气与含水蒸气的气体和/或二氧化碳与每个其它用于重整反应在合成气生产装置中，在分离的时间，收集产生的合成气中所含的二氧化碳在合成气生产步骤和回收分离和收集到的二氧化碳作为重整反应源气体在合成气制造工序，回收的二氧化碳中镍的浓度不高于0.0510PPMv。', p.abstract_en = 'A synthesis gas production apparatus (reformer) to be used for a synthesis gas production step in a GTL (gas-to-liquid) process is prevented from beingcontaminated by metal components. A method ofsuppressing metal contamination of a synthesis gas production apparatus operating for a GTL process that includes a synthesis gas production step of producing synthesis gas by causing natural gas and gas containing steam and/or carbon dioxide to react with each other for reforming in a synthesis gas production apparatus in which,  at the time of separating and collecting a carbon dioxide contained in the synthesis gas produced in the synthesis gas production step and recycling the separated and collected carbon dioxide as source gas for the reforming reaction in the synthesis gas production step,  a nickel concentration in the recycled carbon dioxide is not higher than 0.05 ppmv.', p.application_date = '2012-03-22 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CA2831561C', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US13122864'}) SET p.application_no = 'US13122864', p.title_cn = '由气态烃生产合成气的方法和装置', p.title_en = 'Method and device for producing synthesis gas from gaseous hydrocarbons', p.abstract_cn = '一种从气态烃生产合成气的方法，包括使用具有催化剂的变温蒸汽重整。 为了在紧凑的设备中高效地生产合成气而不产生废气，能量至少部分地由电能提供，能量由电加热的接触面提供，并且能量由催化剂颗粒的固定床和/或至少部分地由催化剂颗粒组成的流化床内的接触面提供。', p.abstract_en = 'A method for the production of synthesis gas from gaseous hydrocarbons includes the use of allothermal steam reforming with catalysts. In order to produce the synthesis gas efficiently without exhaust gas in a compact apparatus,  energy is at least partly supplied by electrical energy,  that the energy is supplied by electrically heated contact surfaces and that the energy is supplied by contact surfaces within a fixed bed of catalyst pellets and/or within a fluidized bed at least partly consisting of catalyst particles.', p.application_date = '2009-10-08 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9314761B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/44', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14312105'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14312105', p.title_cn = '镧系氧化物在降低催化剂烧结中的应用', p.title_en = 'Use of lanthanide oxides to reduce sintering of catalysts', p.abstract_cn = '公开了一种镧系氧化物涂覆的催化剂及其使用方法，其包括负载型催化剂，所述负载型催化剂包括载体材料、催化材料和镧系氧化物，其中所述镧系氧化物附着于所述负载型催化剂的表面的至少一部分。', p.abstract_en = 'Disclosed is a lanthanide oxide coated catalyst,  and methods for its use,  that includes a supported catalyst comprising a support material,  a catalytic material,  and a lanthanide oxide,  wherein the lanthanide oxide is attached to at least a portion of the surface of the supported catalyst.', p.application_date = '2014-06-23 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9314771B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 2, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'DE602009046057'}) SET p.application_no = 'DE602009046057', p.title_cn = '组合的合成气体发生器', p.title_en = 'COMBINED SYNTHESIS GAS GENERATOR', p.abstract_cn = '各种系统和方法中，生成合成气可以被组合。一种部分氧化反应器(POX)和气体对流加热蒸汽/碳氢化合物催化重整器(GHR)可进行组合，以产生合成燃气。在一些实施例中，一种部分氧化反应器中，气体对流加热蒸汽/催化重整器和余热锅炉可组合，以产生合成气。', p.abstract_en = 'In various systems and processes,  synthesis gas generation may be combined. A partial oxidation reactor (POX) and a gas convectively heated steam/hydrocarbon catalytic reformer (GHR) may be combined to produce synthesis gas. In some implementations,  a partial oxidation reactor,  a gas convectively heated steam/catalytic reformer,  and a waste hat boiler may be combined to produce synthesis gas.', p.application_date = '2009-09-29 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'DE602009046057T2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'DKPA201400705'}) SET p.application_no = 'DKPA201400705', p.title_cn = '预重整和/或蒸汽重整催化剂', p.title_en = 'A catalyst for prereforming and/or steam reforming', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种预重整和/或蒸汽重整催化剂，包含活性材料负载于陶瓷材料，其中活性材料是镍与陶瓷材料包括Mg的氧化物，Al以及一种或多种镧系元素，其中，镁和铝的原子比为1 : 0.05和1 : 0.25，原子比Mg与Ni的原子比介于1 : 0.10和1 : 0.45之间和mg，一种或多种镧系元素为1 : 0.005和1 : 0.05之间。本发明还涉及一种根据本发明的催化剂前体，根据本发明使用的催化剂和预重整和/或蒸汽重整的方法，所述烃类燃料，本发明中通过在催化剂存在下蒸汽。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a catalyst for prereforming and/or steam reforming,  comprising an active material supported on a ceramic material,  where the active material is Ni and the ceramic material comprises oxides of Mg,  Al as well as of one or more lanthanide elements,  wherein the atomic ratio between Mg and Al is between 1 : 0.05 and 1 : 0.25,  the atomic ratio between Mg and Ni is between 1 : 0.10 and 1 : 0.45 and the atomic ratio between Mg and the one or more lanthanide elements is between 1 : 0.005 and 1 : 0.05. The invention also relates to a precursor for a catalyst according to the invention,  the use of a catalyst according to the invention and a prereforming and/or steam reforming process,  wherein a hydrocarbon fuel is passed over a catalyst of the invention in the presence of steam.', p.application_date = '2014-12-03 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'DK201400705A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/40', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'DK10765566'}) SET p.application_no = 'DK10765566', p.title_cn = '变烟气流动的初级改革', p.title_en = 'Primary reforms with variable smoke stream', p.abstract_cn = '一种方法公开了一种用于催化初级重整烃与蒸汽在升高的压力下通过分体 管反应器和燃烧室。 在分体式管系统，可以使用催化剂材料， 待重整的烃水蒸汽转换合成气。 分体式管系统由多个点火加热设施之间的分体式管包括多个 串联布置燃烧器，燃烧器产生主要的向下指向的火焰。 相关烧制设施提供与燃料和空气，与空气在被从相关送料器。 烟道气体从而演化穿过所述烧制室从上至下进入下部区域中 烧室中的水平设置的陶瓷烟气隧道彼此平行延伸并垂直于 竖直分流管和被分配给一个烧制设施。 烟气进入通过侧壁中的孔的烟气隧道。 烟气在燃烧室的出口通入热回收装置。 在每个烟气隧道的附加气体进入隧道的前侧， 在烟气流动方向， 所述含氧气体和非可燃气体， 使得附加气体经过烟气隧道在整个长度的燃烧室。 体积的附加气体通入到烟气隧道的调节。', p.abstract_en = 'A method is disclosed for catalytic primary reformation of hydrocarbons with steam at elevated pressure by means of a split tube reactor and a firing chamber. In the split tube system which can use a catalyst material,  hydrocarbons to be reformed are converted by water steam to synthesis gas. The split tube system is heated by a plurality of firing facilities between the split tubes which include a plurality of burners arranged in series,  the burners generating mainly downwardly directed flames. The relevant firing facilities are supplied with fuel and air,  with the air being withdrawn from the relevant feeders. The flue gas thus evolving passes through the firing chamber from top to bottom and enters in the lower area of the firing chamber into horizontally arranged ceramic flue gas tunnels extending in parallel to each other and perpendicular to the vertical split tubes and being allocated to one firing facility each. The flue gas enters through apertures in the lateral walls of the flue gas tunnels. The flue gas at the exit of the firing chamber is passed into heat recovery devices. In each flue gas tunnel an additional gas is fed into the tunnel\'s front side,  in flue gas flow direction,  wherein the gas containing oxygen and a non-combustible gas,  so that the additional gas passes the flue gas tunnels over the entire length of the firing chamber. The volume of the additional gas passed into the flue gas tunnels is regulated.', p.application_date = '2010-06-24 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'DK2445830T3', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'SA515360988'}) SET p.application_no = 'SA515360988', p.title_cn = '辐射壁催化反应器和在该反应器中进行化学反应的方法', p.title_en = 'Radiating wall catalytic reactor and process for carrying out a chemical reaction in this reactor', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种辐射壁催化反应器，用于通过辐射16从反应室1的内壁表面8提供热量，以支持在反应室1中发生的整个吸热的气相化学反应，该辐射壁催化反应器包括反应室1，该反应室具有用于以连续方式将气态反应物(s)引入反应室1的入口2和使气态产物(s)能够以连续方式离开反应室1的出口3，其中所述反应室1包括多个催化剂段(A)5，其中气流流过并与催化剂材料4接触，和空隙段(B)6，其中热量从空隙段(B)6的内壁表面8辐射到构成催化剂段(A)5和空隙段(B6)之间界面的催化剂段表面9; 其中，通过穿过内壁表面8的辐射产生的热通量发生在所述一个内壁表面中', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a radiating wall catalytic reactor for providing heat from the inside wall surface 8 of a reaction chamber 1 by radiation 16 to support an overall endothermic gas phase chemical reaction taking place in the reaction chamber 1,  comprising a reaction chamber 1 with an entrance port 2 for the introduction of a gaseous reactant(s) in a continuous manner into the reaction chamber 1 and an exit port 3 to enable the gaseous product(s) to leave the reaction chamber 1 in a continuous manner,  wherein said reaction chamber 1 comprises a plurality of catalyst segments (A) 5,  wherein a gaseous stream flows through and comes into contact with a catalyst material 4,  and of void segments (B) 6,  wherein heat is radiated from the inside wall surface 8 in the void segment (B) 6 to a catalyst segment surface 9 constituting an interface between the catalyst segment (A)5 and the void segment (B6);  wherein a heat flux by radiation through the inside wall surface 8 occurs in the one', p.application_date = '2014-03-04 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'SA515360988A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'ATE781043'}) SET p.application_no = 'ATE781043', p.title_cn = '系统和方法用于生产含H2气体和纯净水', p.title_en = 'System and process for producing a H2-containing gas and purified water', p.abstract_cn = '系统和方法用于生产H2含有产品气体和净化水从组合的H2-制备重整和热水纯化过程。原水，如盐水，通过间接加热传热与重整产物从H2-中生产重整净化原水的方法一种多效蒸馏工艺。', p.abstract_en = 'System and process for producing a H 2 -containing product gas and purified water from an integrated H 2 -producing reforming and thermal water purification process. Raw water,  such as salt water,  is heated by indirect heat transfer with reformate from the H 2 -producing reforming process for purifying raw water in a multiple effect distillation process.', p.application_date = '2013-10-23 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'ATE781043T1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'ATE782946'}) SET p.application_no = 'ATE782946', p.title_cn = '合成气生产，通过使用膜技术', p.title_en = 'SYNGAS PRODUCTION THROUGH THE USE OF MEMBRANE TECHNOLOGIES', p.abstract_cn = '污染的天然气流(11)的具有显著量的二氧化碳可以有效和更经济地处理，以创建合成气(16)。可用的源(1)的烟气，否则分散到大气中结合有这种含CO2天然气流(11)使得该方法更经济，高效的通过多个进料流的创建(14，27，34)结合，以将复合接近相等的甲烷和二氧化碳的混合物到等离子体反应器(15)或将产生合成气等。当与费-托合成反应器(40)，全过程提供了一种特别高效和经济的方法，用于生产合成液态烃。', p.abstract_en = 'Streams (11) of natural gas contaminated with significant amounts of carbon dioxide can be efficiently and economically processed to create Syngas (16). An available source (1) of flue gas that might otherwise be dispersed into the atmosphere in conjunction with such a CO2-laden natural gas stream (11) renders the process even more economical and efficient through the creation of multiple feedstreams (14,  27,  34) that are combined to deliver a composite near equal mixture of methane and CO2 to a plasma reactor (15) or the like that will generate Syngas. When coupled with a Fischer-Tropsch reactor (40),  the overall process provides a particularly efficient and economical process for producing synthetic liquid hydrocarbons.', p.application_date = '2011-06-29 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'ATE782946T1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/34', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'ATE785171'}) SET p.application_no = 'ATE785171', p.title_cn = '盒体用于从重整产物中除去硫化氢的吸附器系统', p.title_en = 'Cartridge adsorber system for removing hydrogen sulfide from reformate', p.abstract_cn = '除系统的H2S从含硫的重整产品包括永磁筒组件，其具有配件 通过重整产品流和一个可更换的药筒组件含有H2S吸附器元件与配件方便， 简单，可靠的配合和密封，与永久滤罐组件。 盒组件包括壳体可任选的全圆柱体或半圆柱体。所述钉仓组件 可以很容易地重新加载离线重新使用的墨盒部件与新鲜的吸附器元件。 优选地，所述吸附器元件离线的可再生用于重新使用。', p.abstract_en = 'A system for removal of H 2 S from sulfur-containing reformate comprising a permanent canister assembly having fittings for flow of reformate therethrough and a replaceable cartridge assembly containing an H 2 S adsorber element and fittings for convenient,  simple,  and reliable mating and sealing with the permanent canister assembly. The cartridge assembly comprises a housing that may be optionally a full cylinder or a semi-cylinder. The cartridge assembly may be easily reloaded off-line for re-use of the cartridge components with a fresh adsorber element. Preferably,  the adsorber element is also renewable off-line for re-use.', p.application_date = '2009-04-09 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'ATE785171T1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/50', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'ATE787607'}) SET p.application_no = 'ATE787607', p.title_cn = '工艺用于制造含氢产物气体', p.title_en = 'PROCESS FOR PRODUCING A HYDROGEN-CONTAINING PRODUCT GAS', p.abstract_cn = '用于制造含氢产物气体的方法通过催化蒸汽-烃重整的总蒸汽-碳用于该方法的摩尔比为1.5 : 2.4。工艺流反应，反应之前在至少两个预转化炉中的含催化剂的管中在顶烧转化炉。绝热预重整器第一中的过程物流反应，本发明的方法之前被引入物流被加热预重整器第二和/或第二加热预重整器。该方法避免了碳沉积在所述催化剂中的含催化剂的管中的主重整器。', p.abstract_en = 'A process for producing a hydrogen-containing product gas by catalytic steam-hydrocarbon reforming with an overall steam-to-carbon molar ratio between 1.5 and 2.4 for the process. The process stream is reacted in at least two prereformers prior to reaction in catalyst-containing tubes in a top-fired reformer furnace. The process stream is reacted adiabatically in the first prereformer,  while the process stream is heated prior to being introduced into the second prereformer and/or the second prereformer is heated. The process avoids carbon formation on the catalyst in the catalyst-containing tubes in the primary reformer.', p.application_date = '2010-04-15 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'ATE787607T1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'IN7960CHENP2012'}) SET p.application_no = 'IN7960CHENP2012', p.title_cn = '重整催化剂', p.title_en = 'REFORMING CATALYST', p.abstract_cn = '烃类蒸汽重整的方法，该方法包括使原料气与催化剂由活性化合物在形成的合金，镍，铱铑和钌之一的氧化铝载体上氧化镁氧化钛或氧化锆及其组合。', p.abstract_en = 'Process for the steam reforming of hydrocarbons comprising contacting a feed gas with a catalyst consisting of an active compound in the form of an alloy of nickel and one of iridium rhodium and ruthenium on a support comprising alumina zirconia magnesia titania or combinations thereof.', p.application_date = '2012-09-14 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'IN7960CHENP2012A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/40', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'AU2012254167'}) SET p.application_no = 'AU2012254167', p.title_cn = '用于生物质转化的合成气的工艺', p.title_en = 'Process for biomass conversion to synthesis gas', p.abstract_cn = '处理生物质，通过生物质分馏系统产生，通过应用选择性温度的上升或下降和压力冲击，一系列用于挥发性组分和BMF炭，所述BMP炭反应sacriflcially与任何一个的甲烷物流，二氧化碳，水蒸汽或氧气以产生高纯合成气与可控范围的组合物。所得到的合成气体可以用于任何希望的方式，包括转换到含氧化合物如甲醇和二甲醚，和烃的方法。', p.abstract_en = 'Biomass is processed through a biomass fractioning system that creates,  through the application of selective temperature ramps and pressure shocks,  a series of useful volatile components and BMF char,  wherein the BMP char is reacted sacriflcially with any one stream of methane,  carbon dioxide,  steam or oxygen to create highly pure synthesis gas with a controllable range of compositions. The resulting synthesis gas may be used in any desired manner,  including conversion to oxygenates such as methanol and dimethyl ether,  and to hydrocarbons.', p.application_date = '2012-02-23 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'AU2012254167B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/32', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'AU2012350999'}) SET p.application_no = 'AU2012350999', p.title_cn = '液态燃料脱硫的方法和系统用于燃料电池中的应用', p.title_en = 'Method and system for liquid fuel desulphurization for fuel cell application', p.abstract_cn = '一种液体化石燃料脱硫的方法，以用于连接燃料电池进行在一种系统，包括蒸发器单元(1)，其中所述液体蒸发的燃料的第一，固定床反应器(2)中形成的气相加氢脱硫剂，其中燃料在大气压力下用氢气处理过的高活性加氢裂化(haht)催化剂，其中硫物质转化为H2S，吸附器(3)，其中产生的硫化氢可吸附在催化床，和燃料重整器(4)，其中燃料产品转化为合成气，待馈送到固体氧化物燃料电池(SOFC)系统(6)。蒸发器单元(1)包括喷液装置，优选在形成的压电喷头。', p.abstract_en = 'A method for desulphurization of a liquid fossil fuel to be used in connection with a fuel cell is performed in a system comprising an evaporator unit (1),  wherein the liquid fuel is first evaporated,  a fixed bed reactor (2) in the form of a gas-phase hydro-desulphurizer,  where the fuel is treated with hydrogen at atmospheric pressure over a highly active hydro-cracking (HAHT) catalyst,  whereby sulphur species are converted to H2S,  an adsorber (3),  where the produced hydrogen sulphide can be adsorbed on a catalytic bed,  and a fuel reformer (4),  in which the fuel product is converted to syngas to be fed to an SOFC system (6). The evaporator unit (1) comprises a liquid spraying device,  preferably in the form of a piezoelectric spray nozzle.', p.application_date = '2012-11-21 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'AU2012350999B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/34', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'AU2013221020'}) SET p.application_no = 'AU2013221020', p.title_cn = '水煤气变换工艺', p.title_en = 'Water gas shift process', p.abstract_cn = '高压蒸汽供应氢生产工艺更加高效利用水煤气变换过程包括，在交替顺序 : (a)反应阶段，其中进料气体含有CO和H', p.abstract_en = 'High-pressure steam supply in hydrogen production process is made more efficient by water gas shift process which comprises,  in alternating sequence :  (a) a reaction stage wherein a feed gas comprising CO and H', p.application_date = '2013-02-15 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'AU2013221020B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/12', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14879813'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14879813', p.title_cn = '一种捕集和螯合碳的方法和装置', p.title_en = 'METHOD AND APPARATUS FOR CAPTURING AND SEQUESTERING CARBON', p.abstract_cn = '一种将二氧化碳(CO2)转化为有用的含碳化合物的方法，包括以下步骤 : 从CO2排放源回收CO2，使回收的CO2通过CO2汽提器，并使用通过CO2汽提器的CO2作为生成有用的含碳化合物的反应的原料。 该方法通过制备用作原料以驱动其它有益反应的CO2来进一步减少CO2排放。', p.abstract_en = 'A method for converting carbon dioxide (CO2) into useful carbonaceous compounds includes the steps of recovering CO2 from a CO2 emitting source,  passing the recovered CO2 through a CO2 stripper,  and using CO2 passed through the CO2 stripper as feedstock for reactions that generate useful carbonaceous compounds. The method further reduces CO2 emissions by preparing CO2 to be used as feedstock to drive other beneficial reactions.', p.application_date = '2015-10-09 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US20160101977A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/44', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201180013871.1'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201180013871.1', p.title_cn = '制氢方法', p.title_en = 'Method for hydrogen production', p.abstract_cn = '描述了一种制氢方法，其包括：通过生物质发酵过程产生含5-15wt%乙醇的含水原料物流；从所述原料物流中分离至少一部分水从而使所得重整器原料物流中乙醇的浓度为15-35wt%；和在重整器中在重整条件下使重整器原料物流与催化剂接触，以产生包含氢的重整器产物物流，其中重整器中的压力为100-600psi。', p.abstract_en = 'A process is described for producing hydrogen comprising producing an aqueous feed stream comprising 5% to 15% wt. ethanol by a biomass fermentation process;  separating at least a portion of the water from the feed stream so that the concentration of ethanol in the resulting reformer feed stream is in the range of from 15% to 35% wt.;  and contacting the reformer feed stream with a catalyst in a reformer under reforming conditions to produce a reformer product stream comprising hydrogen wherein the pressure in the reformer is in a range of from 100 psi to 600 psi.', p.application_date = '2011-03-14 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN102791619B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/32', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201410230493.8'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201410230493.8', p.title_cn = '低排放发电和烃采收系统及方法', p.title_en = 'Low emission power generation and hydrocarbon recovery system and method', p.abstract_cn = '提供用于烃采收方法中低排放发电的方法和系统。一个系统包括以低排放发电的集成的压力保持和混相驱动系统。该系统也可包括集成变压重整装置(PSR)、吹气式自热重整单元(ATR)或吹氧式ATR与燃气发电轮机系统，优选地为组合循环燃气发电轮机系统。这样的系统可被用来捕获和利用温室气体(GHG)并产生用于烃采收操作中的电力。', p.abstract_en = 'Methods and systems for low emission power generation in hydrocarbon recovery processes are provided. One system includes integrated pressure maintenance and miscible flood systems with low emission power generation. The system may also include integration of a pressure swing reformer (PSR),  air-blown auto-thermal reformer (ATR),  or oxygen-blown ATR with a gas power turbine system,  preferably a combined cycle gas power turbine system. Such systems may be employed to capture and utilize greenhouse gases (GHG) and generate power for use in hydrocarbon recovery operations.', p.application_date = '2009-03-27 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN104098070B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201410366341.0'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201410366341.0', p.title_cn = '一种费托合成尾气转化为费托合成原料气的方法', p.title_en = 'A Fischer-Tropsch synthesis gas into Fischer-Tropsch synthesis method of the raw material gas', p.abstract_cn = '一种费托合成尾气转化为费托合成原料气的方法是费托合成尾气通过在装有加氢催化剂的加氢反应器中进行催化加氢反应转化为饱和烃，再在一段转化炉和二段转化炉进行水蒸气重整及部分氧化，中变炉内进行水汽变换反应，最后进行气液分离，气相为满足费托合成所要求的氢碳配比的原料气。本发明具有工艺简单、操作方便的优点。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a method for converting a Fischer-Tropsch synthesis tail gas into a Fischer-Tropsch synthesis feed gas. The method comprises the following steps that :  carrying out catalytic hydrogenation reaction on the Fischer-Tropsch synthesis tail gas in a hydrogenation reactor filled with a hydrogenation catalyst,  so as to convert the Fischer-Tropsch synthesis tail gas into saturated hydrocarbon;  then carrying out steam reforming and partial oxidation in a primary converter and a secondary converter,  carrying out water gas shift reaction in an intermediate converter and finally carrying out gas-liquid separation,  wherein a gas phase is the feed gas which meets the requirement for hydrogen carbon ratio required by Fischer-Tropsch synthesis. The method disclosed by the invention has the advantages of simple process and convenience for operation.', p.application_date = '2014-07-29 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN104150441B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201510929563.3'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201510929563.3', p.title_cn = 'Mn-Cu-Co/蒙脱土脱氧剂的制备工艺', p.title_en = 'Mn-Cu-Co/montmorillonite deoxidant preparing process', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种Mn-Cu-Co/蒙脱土脱氧剂的制备工艺，本工艺采用Mn、Cu和Co过渡金属元素为活性组分, 并选用了合适的载体蒙脱土和填加剂磁铁矿及分散剂聚乙二醇, 用共沉淀法制备得到活性高、强度好、长期使用不粉化流失及活性组分分布均匀的Mn-Cu-Co/蒙脱土高效过渡金属氧化物脱氧剂。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention discloses a Mn-Cu-Co/montmorillonite deoxidant preparing process. According to the process,  the Mn,  Cu and Co transition metal elements are taken as active components,  the proper carrier montmorillonite,  the proper additive magnetite and the proper dispersant polyethylene glycol are adopted,  and a Mn-Cu-Co/montmorillonite efficient transition metallic oxide deoxidant which is high in activity and strength,  not prone to pulverization after long-term use and uniform in active component distribution is prepared with the coprecipitation method.', p.application_date = '2015-12-15 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105480943A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/56', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201480047131.3'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201480047131.3', p.title_cn = '炉顶气在直接还原工艺中的使用', p.title_en = 'Use of top gas in direct reduction processes', p.abstract_cn = '一方面，本发明涉及用于产生直接还原铁的系统，其中将来自用于通过直接还原工艺还原氧化铁的第一模块的炉顶气的一部分在用于通过直接还原工艺还原氧化铁的第二模块的热设备中用作燃料，其中所述第二模块包括工艺气体加热单元。在各个方面，所述第二模块的所述热设备是还原气体加热器和/或蒸汽锅炉。另一方面，可以将来自所述第一模块的多个情形的炉顶气在所述第二模块的所述热设备中共同用作燃料。本摘要旨在作为用于对特定技术进行检索的扫描工具并且并不旨在限制本发明。', p.abstract_en = 'In one aspect,  the invention relates to a system for producing direct reduced iron wherein a portion of the top gas from a first module for reducing iron oxide by a direct reduction process is utilized as fuel in the thermal equipment of a second module for reducing iron oxide by a direct reduction process,  wherein the second module comprises a process gas heating unit. In various aspects,  the thermal equipment of the second module is a reducing gas heater and/or a steam boiler. In a further aspect,  the top gas from multiple instances of the first module can be utilized collectively as fuel in the thermal equipment of the second module. This abstract is intended as a scanning tool for purposes of searching in the particular art and is not intended to be limiting of the present invention.', p.application_date = '2014-07-22 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105492376A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/34', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201480016085.0'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201480016085.0', p.title_cn = '用于烃重整的催化剂', p.title_en = 'Catalysts for hydrocarbon reforming', p.abstract_cn = '在一些实施例中, 提供一种用于处理重整催化剂的方法, 所述方法包括在还原气体混合物环境中加热用于重整烃的催化剂金属。还原气体混合物包括氢和至少一种含硫的化合物。所述至少一种含硫的化合物包括下述的一种或多种：硫化氢、硫化羰、二硫化羰，以及有机含硫的化合物例如噻吩、四氢噻吩、硫醚(RSH)、二硫化物(RS2Rˊ)、三硫化物(RS3Rˊ)和硫醇(RSRˊ)。', p.abstract_en = 'In some embodiments,  a method for treating a reforming catalyst is provided that includes heating a catalyst metal used to reform a hydrocarbon in an environment of a reducing gas mixture. The reducing gas mixture includes hydrogen and at least one sulfur-containing compound The at least one sulfur-containing compound includes one or more of the following :  hydrogen sulfide,  carbonyl sulfide,  carbonyl disulfide,  and organic sulfur-containing compounds such as thiophene,  tetrahydrothiophene,  thioether (RSH),  disulfide Sulfide (RS2R \'),  trisulfide (RS3R\') and thiol (RSR \').', p.application_date = '2014-03-07 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105492377A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201520941352.7'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201520941352.7', p.title_cn = '一种贮氢罐简易活化制作装置', p.title_en = 'Simple and easy activation making devices of hydrogen storage tank', p.abstract_cn = '本实用新型公开了一种贮氢罐简易活化制作装置，包括一个带有中部压力表装置的活化罐，所述活化罐左端焊接有中抽气管，所述活化罐右端设置有充氢管和排氢管，所述充氢管上设置有充氢阀，所述排氢管上设置有排氢阀，所述活化罐的上端焊接有中间阀，所述中间阀的上端焊接有进料室，所述进料室左端焊接有上抽气管，且上抽气管上设置有上抽气阀，所述进料室的右端设置有上压力表装置，所述进料室的上端通过第一法兰连接有装料阀，所述装置通过在原有活化装置的顶部和底部添加抽气管和抽气阀，能够在储氢金属活化过程中有效的过滤掉装置内的空气，防止储氢金属在装填和激活的过程中被氧化。', p.abstract_en = 'The utility model discloses a simple and easy activation making devices of hydrogen storage tank,  including an activation tank who has middle part manometer device,  the welding of activation tank left end has well exhaust tube,  the activation tank right -hand member is provided with the hydrogen charging pipe and arranges the hydrogen pipe,  be provided with the hydrogen charging valve on the hydrogen charging pipe,  arrange hydrogen and manage the row\'s of being provided with hydrogen valve,  activation tank\'s upper end welding has middle valve,  the upper end welding of middle valve has the feed space,  the welding of feed space left end has last exhaust tube,  and is provided with the bleeder valve on the last exhaust tube,  the right -hand member of feed space is provided with upward pressure table device,  the upper end of feed space is through the flange joint valve of feeding,  exhaust tube and bleeder valve are added to the top of device through at original activation device and bottom,  and air in can the device is fallen in effectual filtration in storage hydrogen metal activation process prevents to store up the hydrogen metal at the in -process that loads and activate by the oxidation.', p.application_date = '2015-11-23 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN205151759U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201520936804.2'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201520936804.2', p.title_cn = '一种小型的天然气制氢装置', p.title_en = 'Miniature natural gas hydrogen plant', p.abstract_cn = '本实用新型公开了一种小型的天然气制氢装置，包括天然气瓶，所述天然气瓶通过软管与压缩机连接，所述压缩机通过脱硫装置与混合罐连接，所述催化装置的内腔中部设有床层，所述催化装置的上端左右两侧分别设有回气口和出气口，所述出气口通过软管连接有冷却器，所述冷却器通过软管连接有氢气提纯器，所述氢气提纯器通过软管连接有氢气收集器，该小型的天然气制氢装置采用对天然气进行压缩，然后再用脱硫装置，最后利用催化装置制造出氢气，其次采用氢气提纯器对制造出来的氢气进一步优化，使制造出来的氢气更优良，且本装置是一种小型的制氢装置，节省了大量的空间，以致其他的地方也能利用起来。', p.abstract_en = 'The utility model discloses a miniature natural gas hydrogen plant,  including natural gas cylinder,  natural gas cylinder passes through the hose and is connected with the compressor,  the compressor passes through desulphurization unit and is connected with the blending tank,  catalytic unit\'s inner chamber middle part is equipped with the bed,  catalytic unit\'s the upper end left and right sides is equipped with return -air mouth and gas outlet respectively,  there is the cooler gas outlet through the hose connection,  the cooler has the hydrogen purifier through the hose connection,  the hydrogen purifier has a hydrogen collector through the hose connection,  and this miniature natural gas hydrogen plant adopts natural gas compress,  and then use desulphurization unit,  utilizes catalytic unit to produce hydrogen at last,  and next adopts the hydrogen purifier further to optimize making the hydrogen that comes out,  and the hydrogen that the messenger made out is better,  and this device is a miniature hydrogen plant,  has saved a large amount of spaces to the place of sending other also can utilize.', p.application_date = '2015-11-23 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN205151760U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/26', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201520868048.4'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201520868048.4', p.title_cn = '一种水氢智能家居系统', p.title_en = 'Water hydrogen smart home systems', p.abstract_cn = '本实用新型揭示了一种水氢智能家居系统，包括智能家居控制系统、甲醇制氢系统、氢气发电系统，甲醇制氢系统、氢气发电系统、智能家居控制系统依次连接；所述智能家居控制系统包括主控中心、环境参数调节系统；所述环境参数调节系统包括窗户打开角度调节装置、窗帘控制装置、湿度调节装置、温度调节装置、亮度调节装置、氧气释放装置、空气净化装置；所述甲醇制氢系统利用甲醇水蒸气重整制备氢气，氢气通过镀有钯银合金的膜分离装置获得高纯度的氢气，获取的氢气通过氢气发电系统发电，发出的电能供智能家居控制系统工作。本实用新型提出的水氢智能家居系统，可利用甲醇制得氢气发电作为智能家居系统的能源，将智能家居系统用于没有交流电的场所。', p.abstract_en = 'The utility model discloses a water hydrogen smart home systems,  including intelligent house control system,  methyl alcohol hydrogen production system,  hydrogen generates electricity system,  methyl alcohol hydrogen production system,  hydrogen generates electricity system,  intelligent house control system connect gradually,  intelligent house control system includes master control center,  environmental parameter governing system,  environmental parameter governing system includes that the window opens angle adjusting device,  curtain control device,  humidity adjusting device,  temperature adjusting device,  luminance adjusting device,  oxygen release,  air purification device,  methyl alcohol hydrogen production system utilizes methanol steam reforming preparation hydrogen,  and hydrogen obtains the hydrogen of high -purity through the membrane separation device who plates palladium -silver,  and the hydrogen that acquires passes through the electricity generation of hydrogen generates electricity system,  and the electric energy that sends supplies intelligent house control system work. The utility model provides a water hydrogen smart home systems,  usable methyl alcohol make hydrogen generates electricity as smart home systems\'s the energy,  are used for smart home systems not have the place of alternating current.', p.application_date = '2015-11-03 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN205151761U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/32', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 2, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201520843948.3'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201520843948.3', p.title_cn = '一种天然气重整制氢系统', p.title_en = 'Natural gas reformation hydrogen production system', p.abstract_cn = '本实用新型涉及一种天然气重整制氢系统，包括通过管路顺序连通的加氢反应器、脱硫罐、转化炉、高温变换器及变压吸附装置，所述的加氢反应器入口与天然气原料管线连通，所述的变压吸附装置出口为可直接供应的天然气重整氢气产品管线，本系统还包括HYCO合成气分离净化装置，该HYCO合成气分离净化装置入口与HYCO合成气原料管线连通，出口分别与合成气分离净化氢气产品管线与CO产品管线连通，所述的天然气重整氢气产品管线上设有与天然气原料管线连通的加氢管线，所述的合成气分离净化氢气产品管线上设有与加氢管线连通的引氢管线。与现有技术相比，本实用新型本系统一次性投资即可，安全可靠，操作方便。', p.abstract_en = 'The utility model relates to a natural gas reformation hydrogen production system,  include hydrogenation ware,  digester,  reborner,  high temperature converter and pressure swing adsorption unit through pipeline order intercommunication,  hydrogenation ware entry and natural gas raw tube line intercommunication,  the pressure swing adsorption unit export natural gas reformation hydrogen product pipeline for can directly supplying,  this system still includes HYCO synthetic gas separation purifier,  this HYCO synthetic gas separation purifier entry and HYCO synthetic gas raw tube line intercommunication,  the export purifies hydrogen product pipeline and CO product pipeline intercommunication with the synthetic gas separation respectively,  natural gas reformation hydrogen product pipeline on be equipped with with the hydrogenation pipeline of natural gas raw tube line intercommunication,  synthetic gas separation purify be equipped with on the hydrogen product pipeline with hydrogenation pipeline intercommunication draw the hydrogen pipeline. Compared with the prior art,  the utility model discloses the disposable investment of this system can,  safe and reliable,  convenient operation.', p.application_date = '2015-10-28 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN205151762U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/34', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201520864825.8'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201520864825.8', p.title_cn = '一种精确控制蒸汽流量的天然气水蒸汽制氢系统', p.title_en = 'Accurate control steam flow\'s natural gas steam hydrogen production system', p.abstract_cn = '本实用新型涉及一种精确控制蒸汽流量的天然气水蒸汽制氢系统，包括依次连接的预转化炉、转化炉、高变反应器、变压吸附制氢装置，天然气进料管与预转化炉的入口相连，天然气进料管上设置有天然气分析仪。与现有技术相比，本实用新型利用天然气在线分析仪得出天然气各个组分的组成，在根据各组成需要的水蒸汽量来控制总的蒸汽用量，即有效的节约燃料用量，做到了节能减排，又保证了反应的需要，保护炉管和催化剂。', p.abstract_en = 'The utility model relates to an accurate control steam flow\'s natural gas steam hydrogen production system,  including the reborner in advance,  reborner,  hypermutation reactor,  the pressure swing adsorption hydrogen plant that connect gradually,  natural gas inlet pipe and in advance the entry of reborner link to each other,  be provided with natural gas analysis appearance on the natural gas inlet pipe. Compared with the prior art,  the utility model discloses total steam quantity is controlled in the steam volume according to each constitution needs to the constitution that utilizes natural gas on line analyzer to reach each component of the natural gas,  and energy saving and emission reduction has been accomplished to effectual fuel economy quantity promptly,  has guaranteed the needs of reaction again,  protection boiler tube and catalyst.', p.application_date = '2015-11-02 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN205151763U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/48', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2011283649'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2011283649', p.title_cn = '一种燃料重整方法', p.title_en = 'A fuel reforming method', p.abstract_cn = '所要解决的问题是 :  本发明提供一种在起动等瞬态运转模式等各种条件下能够有效发挥重整催化剂的功能的车载燃料的重整方法， 加速和减速。解决方案 :  当通过使用燃料重整催化剂和废气的热量从含有水和二氧化碳的废气或从废气和燃料产生含有氢的重整气体时， 一种燃料喷射器， 在排气循环装置的系统中设置燃料蒸发单元和包含该燃料重整催化剂的燃料重整催化剂反应器， 检测燃料重整催化剂的温度， 根据温度， 调节供给燃料重整催化剂反应器的废气中的氧量，废气量和燃料量，从而控制燃料重整催化剂入口处燃料中氧与碳的摩尔比(O/C)。', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To provide a method for reforming onboard fuel in which the function of a reforming catalyst can be effectively exhibited under various conditions including a transient operation mode such as starting,  acceleration and deceleration.SOLUTION :  When a reformed gas containing hydrogen is generated from exhaust gas containing water and carbon dioxide or from the exhaust gas and fuel by using a fuel reforming catalyst and the heat of the exhaust gas,  a fuel sprayer,  a fuel evaporation unit and a fuel reforming catalyst reactor containing the fuel reforming catalyst are arranged in the system of an exhaust circulation apparatus,  the temperature of the fuel reforming catalyst is detected,  and according to the temperature,  the amount of oxygen in exhaust gas to be supplied to the fuel reforming catalyst reactor,  the amount of the exhaust gas and the amount of fuel are adjusted to thereby control the molar ratio (O/C) of oxygen to carbon in the fuel at the fuel reforming catalyst inlet.', p.application_date = '2011-12-26 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP5904399B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'BRPI112012017633'}) SET p.application_no = 'BRPI112012017633', p.title_cn = '由烃进料生产合成气的方法', p.title_en = 'process for producing syngas from a charge hydrocarbon feed', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种由烃原料生产合成气的方法， 其中整个烃进料通过辐射炉， 热交换器重整器和串联布置的自热重整器，其中来自自热重整器的排出气体用作在热交换器重整器中发生的重整反应的热源，并且其中冷却介质被加入到热交换器重整器中。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a process for the production of synthesis gas from a hydrocarbon feedstock,  wherein the entire hydrocarbon feed is passed through a radiant furnace,  heat exchanger reformer and autothermal reformer in a series arrangement,  in which effluent gas from the autothermal reformer is used as heat source for the reforming reactions occurring in the heat exchange reformer and wherein a cooling medium is added to the heat exchange reformer.', p.application_date = '2011-01-18 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'BR112012017633A2', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'BR112012016777'}) SET p.application_no = 'BR112012016777', p.title_cn = '用于氧化反应气体的装置，以及在用于氧化反应气体的用过的装置的整个反应区中废弃和/或移除热量的方法', p.title_en = 'DEVICE FOR THE OXIDATION OF REACTING GASES,  AND,  METHOD TO WASTE AND/OR TO REMOVE HEAT THROUGHOUT A ZONE OF REACTION OF A USED DEVICE FOR THE OXIDATION OF REACTING GASES', p.abstract_cn = '本文描述了用于烃的部分氧化的方法和设备。 更具体地，描述了用于甲烷部分氧化的方法和等温反应器装置，其包括传热表面、多孔催化膜，并且其中热量通过传热表面耗散和/或移除。', p.abstract_en = 'There is herein described a process and apparatus for partial oxidation of hydrocarbons. More particularly,  there is described a process and an isothermal reactor apparatus for the partial oxidation of methane which comprises a heat transfer surface,  a porous catalytic membrane and wherein heat is dissipated and/or removed through the heat transfer surface.', p.application_date = '2011-01-07 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'BRPI1216777A2', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'BR112012017633'}) SET p.application_no = 'BR112012017633', p.title_cn = '由烃进料负荷生产合成气的方法', p.title_en = 'PROCESS FOR THE GAS PRODUCTION OF SYNTHESIS FROM A LOAD OF FEEDING OF HYDRO-CARBONS', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种由烃原料生产合成气的方法， 其中整个烃进料通过辐射炉， 热交换器重整器和串联布置的自热重整器，其中来自自热重整器的排出气体用作在热交换器重整器中发生的重整反应的热源，并且其中冷却介质被加入到热交换器重整器中。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a process for the production of synthesis gas from a hydrocarbon feedstock,  wherein the entire hydrocarbon feed is passed through a radiant furnace,  heat exchanger reformer and autothermal reformer in a series arrangement,  in which effluent gas from the autothermal reformer is used as heat source for the reforming reactions occurring in the heat exchange reformer and wherein a cooling medium is added to the heat exchange reformer.', p.application_date = '2011-01-18 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'BRPI1217633A2', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14314000'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14314000', p.title_cn = '生物质合成气的正压净化方法', p.title_en = 'Method of purification of biomass syngas under positive pressure', p.abstract_cn = '一种在正压下净化生物质合成气的方法。 该方法包括 : 1)使用氧化风机对热解气化炉进行充气； 2)将热解气化炉产生的合成气通过水冷烟道引入水冷急冷塔； 3)将合成气从水冷急冷塔引入水管式余热锅炉和热管式余热锅炉；4)在没有填料的情况下，将合成气从热管式余热锅炉引入文丘里洗涤器，以洗涤合成气并除尘；5)将合成气从文丘里洗涤器引入湿式电除尘器，以进一步除尘；6)将合格的合成气输送到湿气罐中储存或输送到下游工艺中使用。', p.abstract_en = 'A method for purifying biomass syngas under a positive pressure. The method includes :  1) aerating a pyrolysis gasifier by using an oxidation fan;  2) introducing syngas produced in the pyrolysis gasifier through a water-cooling flue to a water-cooling quench tower;  3) introducing the syngas from the water-cooling quench tower to a waste heat boiler of a water-tube type and a waste heat boiler of a heat-tube type;  4) introducing the syngas from the waste heat boiler of the heat-tube type to a Venturi scrubber in the absence of a filler to wash the syngas and remove dust;  5) introducing the syngas from the Venturi scrubber to a wet electrical dust precipitator for further removing the dust;  and 6) transporting qualified syngas to a wet gas tank for storage or to a downstream process for use.', p.application_date = '2014-06-24 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9309115B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14129134'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14129134', p.title_cn = '用于产生合成气方法和系统', p.title_en = 'Process and system for generating synthesis gas', p.abstract_cn = '描述了一种使用烃和水产生合成气的方法和设备。 在该方法和设备的其它实施方案中，产生具有任何期望的CO/氢比和/或合成官能化和/或非官能化烃的合成气体。 利用该方法，可将含烃流体转化为具有可变氢含量的合成气，而不产生显著量的CO2。 此外，可以获得氢和不同形式的碳作为副产物。', p.abstract_en = 'A method and an apparatus for generating synthesis gas using hydrocarbons and water are described. In further embodiments of the method and the apparatus,  synthesis gases having any desired CO/hydrogen ratio and/or synthetic functionalized and/or non-functionalized hydrocarbons are generated. With this method,  a hydrocarbon containing fluid may be transformed into a synthesis gas having variable hydrogen content without generating significant amounts of CO2. Further,  hydrogen and different forms of carbon may be obtained as by-products.', p.application_date = '2012-12-20 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9309125B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/24', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14061428'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14061428', p.title_cn = '氢气和水的综合生产工艺', p.title_en = 'Integrated process for the production of hydrogen and water', p.abstract_cn = '使用催化蒸汽-烃重整生产含氢产物和一种或多种液态水产物的方法。 在该方法中，在将补充水引入除氧器之前，一部分补充水被重整物加热，另一部分补充水被燃烧产物气体加热。 燃烧产物气体中的水被冷凝形成液态水产物。 该工艺可与热水淡化工艺集成。', p.abstract_en = 'Process for producing a hydrogen-containing product and one or more liquid water products using catalytic steam-hydrocarbon reforming. In the process,  a portion of the make-up water is heated by the reformate and another portion of the make-up water is heated by the combustion product gas prior to introducing the make-up water to a deaerator. Water in the combustion product gas is condensed to form a liquid water product. The process may be integrated with a thermal water desalination process.', p.application_date = '2013-10-23 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9309130B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/26', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2014176494'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2014176494', p.title_cn = '脱氢系统', p.title_en = 'Dehydrogenation system', p.abstract_cn = '要解决的问题 : 同时抑制结焦，可提高转化率的脱氢系统。方法 : 脱氢系统3，30和脱氢反应器，脱氢反应器30和热供给到所述加热机构22。所述脱氢反应器30，MCH原料含有反应容器31a，31b，在其中循环，和，位于反应容器通过氢和脱氢反应MCH脱氢的脱氢催化剂，用于将氢化物和32a，32b设置。所述脱氢反应器1中部分30a具有第一30，第二，热源141a在预定加热温度的加热介质供给到第一热热交换器1加热42a，1部分30a比第二的流动方向下游侧第一部分230b，第一热源241b第二，热源141a中高于加热的温度加热介质加热到温度第一的热交换器2提供42b。选择的绘图 : 图。2', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To provide a dehydrogenation system capable of improving the conversion ratio while suppressing caulking. SOLUTION :  There is provide a dehydrogenation system 3 which comprises a dehydrogenation reactor 30 and a heating mechanism 22 for supplying heat to the dehydrogenation reactor 30. The dehydrogenation reactor 30 has reaction vessels 31A and 31B in which a raw material containing MCH is circulated and dehydrogenation catalysts 32A and 32B which are located in the reaction vessels and convert MCH into hydrogen and a dehydrogenated product by dehydrogenation reaction. A first part 30A in the dehydrogenation reactor 30 is heated by supplying a heat medium heated to a predetermined heating temperature by supplying a first heat source 41A to a first heat exchanger 42A and a second part 30B on the downstream side in the circulation direction of a raw material from the first part 30A is heated by supplying a heat medium heated to a heating temperature higher than that of the first heat source 41A to a second heat exchanger 42B by a second heat source 41B. SELECTED DRAWING :  Figure 2 COPYRIGHT :  (C)2016, JPO&INPIT', p.application_date = '2014-08-29 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP2016050143A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/26', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2014176495'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2014176495', p.title_cn = '脱氢反应器，脱氢系统', p.title_en = 'DEHYDROGENATION REACTOR AND DEHYDROGENATION SYSTEM', p.abstract_cn = '要解决的问题 : 脱氢的催化剂可高效利用，脱氢反应器中的脱氢系统。方法 : 在反应容器31，32和脱氢催化剂用于混合和颗粒状传热构件33由混合段50。颗粒状传热构件33，脱氢催化剂32由于高导热性，在混合部分50，和加热机构(35)的反应容器(31)从外部供给的热量，通过颗粒状传热部件33在反应容器31的容易传递到内反应管31a。例如，反应容器31的加热机构(35)从外部供给的热量，通过反应管的管壁(31a)传输到内部，所述颗粒的热量传递到内部的传热部件33通过整个内部的反应管31a。因此，例如，大距离的管壁在中心轴线(CL1)的附近以脱氢催化剂32，传输热量充足。选择的绘图 : 图。2', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To provide a dehydrogenation reactor and a dehydrogenation system capable of utilizing a dehydrogenation catalyst in an efficient manner. SOLUTION :  A dehydrogenation reactor 31 comprises a mixing part 50 constituted by mixing a dehydrogenation catalyst 32 with a particulate heat transfer member 33. Since the particulate heat transfer member 33 has a higher thermal conductivity than the dehydrogenation catalyst 32,  in a mixing part 50 heat supplied by a heating mechanism 35 from outside of the reactor 31 is easily transferred through the particulate heat transfer member 33 into a reaction tube 31a in the reactor 31. For example,  the heat supplied by a heating mechanism 35 from outside of the reactor 31 is transferred through a pipe wall of the reaction tube 31a into the reactor and the heat transferred into the reactor is transferred through the particulate heat transfer member 33 in the whole inside of 31a. Therefore,  for example,  heat is also fully transferred from a pipe wall to the dehydrogenation catalyst 32 which is in the vicinity of the center-axis line CL1 and is far from the pipe wall. SELECTED DRAWING :  Figure 2 COPYRIGHT :  (C)2016, JPO&INPIT', p.application_date = '2014-08-29 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP2016050144A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/26', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2014176498'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2014176498', p.title_cn = '脱氢系统', p.title_en = 'Dehydrogenation system', p.abstract_cn = '要解决的问题 : 同时抑制结焦，可提高转化率的脱氢系统。方法 : 脱氢系统3，30和脱氢反应，和减压阀23。所述脱氢反应器30，MCH原料含有反应容器31a，31b，在其中循环，和，位于反应容器通过氢和脱氢反应MCH脱氢的脱氢催化剂，用于将氢化物和32a，32b设置，减压阀23，在脱氢反应器1中部分30a30比下游侧在流动方向第一部分230b位于反应容器的内部压力31b，位于第一反应室31a的1部分30a调整到低于内部压力。选择的绘图 : 图。2', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To provide a dehydrogenation system capable of improving the conversion ratio while suppressing caulking. SOLUTION :  There is provide a dehydrogenation system 3 which comprises a dehydrogenation reactor 30 and a pressure reducing valve 23. The dehydrogenation reactor 30 has reaction vessels 31A and 31B in which a raw material containing MCH is circulated and dehydrogenation catalysts 32A and 32B which are located in the reaction vessels and convert MCH into hydrogen and a dehydrogenated product by dehydrogenation reaction. The pressure reducing valve 23 adjusts the internal pressure in the reaction vessel 31B located on a second part 30B on the downstream side in the circulation direction of a raw material from a first part 30A in the dehydrogenation reactor 30 so as to be lower than the internal pressure in the reaction vessel 31A located on the first part 30A. SELECTED DRAWING :  Figure 2 COPYRIGHT :  (C)2016, JPO&INPIT', p.application_date = '2014-08-29 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP2016050145A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/26', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'TW103134184'}) SET p.application_no = 'TW103134184', p.title_cn = '氢气产生组件及氢气纯化装置', p.title_en = 'HYDROGEN GENERATION ASSEMBLIES AND HYDROGEN PURIFICATION DEVICES', p.abstract_cn = '本发明揭示氢气产生组件、氢气纯化装置及其构件，及制造彼等组件、装置及构件之方法在一些具体实例中，该等组件可包括具有填充材料之蒸发区，该材料经组态以使热量自热排出流转移至含液体进料流，及/或隔热基座，其相邻於燃烧区且经组态以降低外壳之外部温度在一些具体实例中，该等组件可包括经组态以维持点火器组件与进料流管道热连通之冷却块、包括催化涂层之点火器组件、及/或燃料流分布组件在一些具体实例中，该等组件可包括经组态以使热量自外部加热器传导至外壳部分的导热组件在一些具体实例中，该等装置可包括具有膜支撑结构之框架及/或可包括经组态以防止金属间扩散的微孔筛网结构', p.abstract_en = 'Hydrogen generation assemblies,  hydrogen purification devices,  and their components,  and methods of manufacturing those assemblies,  devices,  and components are disclosed. In some embodiments,  the assemblies may include a vaporization region with packing material configured to transfer heat from a heated exhaust stream to a liquid-containing feed stream,  and/or an insulation base adjacent a combustion region and configured to reduce external temperature of an enclosure. In some embodiments,  the assemblies may include a cooling block configured to maintain an igniter assembly in thermal communication with a feed stream conduit,  an igniter assembly including a catalytic coating,  and/or a fuel stream distribution assembly. In some embodiments,  the assemblies may include a heat conducting assembly configured to conduct heat from external heaters to an enclosure portion. In some embodiments,  the devices may include frames with membrane support structures and/or may include a microscreen structure configured to prevent intermetallic diffusion.', p.application_date = '2012-07-05 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'TWI529124B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/50', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'UAA201400418'}) SET p.application_no = 'UAA201400418', p.title_cn = '改性含甲烷气流的方法', p.title_en = 'METHOD FOR MODIFYING METHANE-CONTAINING GAS STREAM', p.abstract_cn = '一种改性含甲烷气流的方法， 包括以下步骤 :  i)从含甲烷的气流中抽出至少一个支流， ii)用电产生的等离子体处理子流， 生成甲烷比所用含甲烷物流的甲烷分数低的改性气体组合物，和iii)将改性气体组合物返回到含甲烷气流中，允许在天然气管网中储存过量的流。', p.abstract_en = 'A method for modifying a methane-containing gas stream,  comprising the steps :  i) withdrawal of at least one substream from a methane-containing gas stream,  ii) treatment of the substream with an electrically generated plasma,  generating a modified gas composition that has a lower fraction of methane than the methane-containing stream used,  and iii) return of the modified gas composition into the methane-containing gas stream,  permits the storage of excess flow in a natural gas pipe grid.', p.application_date = '2012-05-24 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'UA111209C2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/24', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'UAA201408122'}) SET p.application_no = 'UAA201408122', p.title_cn = '工商企业的发展动态。', p.title_en = 'METHOD AND DEVICE FOR CONVERTING CARBON DIOXIDE INTO CARBON MONOXIDE', p.abstract_cn = '用于将二氧化碳(CO2)的方法和装置以一氧化碳CO，描述了使用烃类。在进一步的细节，描述了用于产生合成气的方法和装置描述了用于将合成气的方法和装置合成的官能化和/或非官能化烃，然后用CO2和烃。通过所述方法和装置，从工业工艺可以转换发射和二氧化碳的量释放到大气中的二氧化碳降低。', p.abstract_en = 'A process and a device for converting carbon dioxide CO2 to carbon monoxide CO,  using hydrocarbons are described. In further details,  processes and devices are described for generating synthesis gases and processes and devices are described for converting synthesis gases to synthetic functionalized and/or non-functionalized hydrocarbons,  using CO2 and hydrocarbons. By means of the processes and the devices,  carbon dioxide emitted from industrial process can be converted and the amount of carbon dioxide released into the atmosphere can be decreased.', p.application_date = '2012-12-20 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'UA111259C2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/24', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'RU2014104491'}) SET p.application_no = 'RU2014104491', p.title_cn = '膜系统的氧运输和方法的热输送到催化/工艺反应器', p.title_en = 'MEMBRANE SYSTEM OF OXYGEN TRANSPORTATION AND METHOD OF HEAT TRANSPORTATION INTO CATALYTIC/TECHNOLOGICAL REACTORS', p.abstract_cn = '领域 :  化学物质 :  膜模块含有多个管状膜元件用于运输氧气， 接触侧的滞留物的膜元件。 氧， 穿在渗透侧， 通过合成燃烧气体流， 含有氢，接触侧管状膜元件的渗透物，生成反应产物流和辐射热。 催化反应器含有催化剂加速反应的蒸汽重整和包围多个管状膜元件 氧运输。 系数的能见度， 表示部的各能源， 表面离开的能量， 到达其他表面， 等于或大于0.5。效果 :  本发明使得可以产生热量， 必要的用于支撑的吸热加热要求的蒸汽甲烷重整reactions.24Cl，13的DWG', p.abstract_en = 'FIELD :  chemistry.SUBSTANCE :  membrane module contains multitude of tubular membrane elements for transportation of oxygen,  which contacts with side of retentate of membrane elements. Oxygen,  which penetrates on permeate side,  is burnt by means of synthesis-gas stream,  containing hydrogen,  which contacts side of permeate of tubular membrane elements,  generating stream of reaction product and radiant heat. Catalytic reactor contains catalyst for acceleration of reaction of steam reforming and is surrounded by multitude of tubular membrane elements for oxygen transportation. Coefficient of visibility,  representing part of all energy,  surface-leaving energy,  which reaches other surface,  is equal or larger than 0.5.EFFECT :  invention makes it possible to generate heat,  necessary for supporting requirements of endothermic heating of steam methane reforming reactions.24 cl,  13 dwg', p.application_date = '2012-07-05 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'RU2579584C2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'IN536MUMNP2015'}) SET p.application_no = 'IN536MUMNP2015', p.title_cn = '高容量高分子聚合物储氢材料及其制备方法', p.title_en = 'HIGH CAPACITY MACROMOLECULAR POLYMER HYDROGEN STORAGE MATERIAL AND PREPARATION METHOD THEREOF', p.abstract_cn = '本发明提供一种高容量高分子聚合物储氢材料，其包含线性高分子聚合物作为主链，一种硼烷氨衍生物侧链上接枝和/或后端线性高分子聚合物的侧链基团和/或线性高分子聚合物的端基化多胺化合物与硼氢化反应。还提供了一种制备高分子聚合物高容量储氢材料的方法。', p.abstract_en = 'Provided is a high capacity macromolecular polymer hydrogen storage material comprising a linear macromolecular polymer as a main chain and a borane ammonia derivative grafted on the side chain and/or end of the linear macromolecular polymer after a side chain group and/or end group of the linear macromolecular polymer is aminated by a polyamine compound and reacts with a borohydride. Also provided is a preparation method for the high capacity macromolecular polymer hydrogen storage material.', p.application_date = '2015-03-13 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'IN536MUMNP2015A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'IN7837DELNP2015'}) SET p.application_no = 'IN7837DELNP2015', p.title_cn = '集成发电和化工生产，利用燃料电池', p.title_en = 'INTEGRATED POWER GENERATION AND CHEMICAL PRODUCTION USING FUEL CELLS', p.abstract_cn = '在各种方面的系统和方法提供了用于操作熔融碳酸盐燃料电池减少或最小化损失由于热能损耗。一种基于即可操作熔融碳酸盐燃料电池中放热反应产生的热量所需比值，燃料电池相对于所消耗的热量进行吸热反应中的吸热反应和任何可选的集成式燃料电池阶段。', p.abstract_en = 'In various aspects systems and methods are provided for operating a molten carbonate fuel cell to reduce or minimize losses due to loss of heat energy. A molten carbonate fuel cell can be operated based on a desired ratio of heat generated by exothermic reactions in the fuel cell relative to heat consumed by endothermic reactions in the fuel cell and any optional integrated endothermic reaction stages.', p.application_date = '2015-09-01 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'IN7837DELNP2015A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/50', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CA2963010'}) SET p.application_no = 'CA2963010', p.title_cn = '非平衡等离子体精制合成气的系统和方法', p.title_en = 'A NON-EQUILIBRIUM PLASMA SYSTEM AND METHOD OF REFINING SYNGAS', p.abstract_cn = '本发明的一个目的是提供一种非平衡等离子体(nep)精制合成气的系统和方法。根据本发明的一个方面，本发明提供一种非平衡等离子体合成气的精制系统，所述系统包括反应器具有空腔，具有一个或多个入口歧管被配置为促使沿轴向对称和涡流的形式，将合成气和一种或多种气化剂在反应器中引入其内用于加工，高压电极；和接地电极，所述系统被配置以产生非平衡等离子体产生的电弧在高电压的应用在引弧高压电极和接地电极之间的间隙及所述系统配置成使得合成气，所述一个或多个气化剂(一个或多个)和等离子体产生的电弧反应器中同时结合在一起。在本发明的一个实施例中，非平衡等离子体系统由两个偏心圆柱歧管构造成用以形成单进气管，所述的两个偏心圆柱歧管包括第一偏心气化剂输入端和第二偏心圆筒形的总管用于合成气输入圆筒形的总管。本发明还包括合成气的精制方法，其中所述非平衡等离子体本发明结合系统合成气，产气和等离子体电弧在同一区域，将共存在同一位置。', p.abstract_en = 'An object of the present invention is to provide a non-equilibrium plasma (NEP) system and method of refining syngas. In accordance with an aspect of the present invention,  there is provided a non-equilibrium plasma system for refining syngas,  the system comprising a reactor with a hollow chamber,  having one or more inlet manifolds configured to promote an axially symmetric and swirling flow pattern,  into which syngas and one or more gasifying agents are introduced for processing within the reactor,  a high voltage electrode;  and a ground electrode,  wherein the system is configured to create a non-equilibrium plasma producing electric arc upon application of a high voltage potential across an arc initiating gap between the high voltage electrode and the ground electrode and wherein the system is configured such that the syngas,  the one or more gasifying agent(s) and plasma producing electric arc come together concurrently in the reactor. In one embodiment of the invention,  the non-equilibrium plasma system comprises two eccentric cylindrical manifolds configured to form a single inlet manifold,  wherein the two eccentric cylindrical manifolds comprise a first eccentric cylindrical manifold for gasifying agent input and a second eccentric cylindrical manifold for syngas input. The invention also comprises a method for refining syngas wherein the non-equilibrium plasma system of the present invention combines the syngas,  the air and the plasma-producing electric arc in the same region,  which will co-exist in the same location.', p.application_date = '2015-09-30 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CA2963010A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'DE602014000948'}) SET p.application_no = 'DE602014000948', p.title_cn = '使用方法自由热量从氢制造设备向供电区与绿色热加热网络', p.title_en = 'Method using the free heat from a hydrogen production facility to supply district heating networks with green heat', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种使用余热的方法从通过蒸汽重整制氢工艺以有助于加热的水的集中供热网络。通常，合成气低于温度Tg，它不超过160℃，后合成气转化为蒸汽，将热量传递给工艺流体，产生的油烟低于温度Tf为不超过170℃；所述方法还产生了未使用输出蒸汽温度TV的下方高于200℃，热交换与合成气和烟气进行供应的外蒸汽系统利用软化水。根据本发明的方法，可获得的热量从流体加热水，其位于附近的集中热水系统由传热流体的装置，其通常为水，循环在闭合的回路中在可变温度；回路中的水通过间接热交换加热与合成气体和油烟，和从输出蒸汽提供额外的热量需要。本发明还涉及一种设备，用于implemting的方法。', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention relates to a method for using the waste heat from a hydrogen production process by steam reforming to contribute to the heating of the water of a district heating network. Generally,  a synthesis gas is below a temperature TG,  which is no more than 160 DEG C,  after the synthesis gas is converted into steam and transmits heat to a process fluid;  generated fume is below a temperature TF which is no more than 170 DEG C;  and the method also produces unused output steam below a temperature TV higher than 200 DEG C,  so heat exchange with the synthesis gas and the fume is performed to supply an extermal steam system by utilizing demineralized water. According to the method of the invention,  heat which can be obtained from the fluid heats water which locates in a nearby centralized water heating system by means of a heat transfer fluid,  which generally is water,  cycled in a closed loop at a variable temperature;  water in the loop is heated through indirect heat exchange with the synthesis gas and the fume;  and additional heat is supplied from output steam as needed. The invention further relates to equipment for implemting the method.', p.application_date = '2014-05-15 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'DE602014000948T2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/36', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'DE602014027923'}) SET p.application_no = 'DE602014027923', p.title_cn = '高热量气体的制造方法', p.title_en = 'HIGH-CALORIE GAS MANUFACTURING PROCESS', p.abstract_cn = '本发明的目的在于提供一种能够通过甘油的热解制造高热量气体的高热量气体制造方法。本发明是一种制造高热量气体的方法，该方法包括：用铁矿石使甘油热解；从而获得净热值为3000kcal/m3或更高的高热量气体。', p.abstract_en = 'The purpose of the present invention is to provide a high-calorie gas manufacturing process by which a high-calorie gas can be manufactured through pyrolysis of glycerol. The present invention is a high-calorie gas manufacturing process which comprises :  subjecting glycerol to pyrolysis using iron ore;  and thus obtaining a high-calorie gas having a net calorific value of 3, 000 kcal/m 3 or more.', p.application_date = '2014-03-27 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'DE602014027923T2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/22', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2014173591'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2014173591', p.title_cn = '所述制氢的方法', p.title_en = 'METHOD FOR PRODUCING HYDROGEN', p.abstract_cn = '要解决的问题 : 通过机械化学反应，廉价和简单的方式，能够产生氢生产氢和提供。方法 : 研磨介质具有容器与行星球磨机，和无机材料与溶剂混合，通过机械化学反应产生氢气。选择的绘图 :', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To provide a method for producing hydrogen that makes it possible to inexpensively and simply produce hydrogen by a mechanochemical reaction. SOLUTION :  A planetary ball mill having a container storing a crushed medium is used to mix inorganic substance and solvent,  and the mechanochemical reaction produces hydrogen. SELECTED DRAWING :  None COPYRIGHT :  (C)2016, JPO&INPIT', p.application_date = '2014-08-28 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP2016047789A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/06', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14863056'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14863056', p.title_cn = '生产液体运输燃料的方法和系统', p.title_en = 'PROCESSES AND SYSTEMS FOR PRODUCING LIQUID TRANSPORTATION FUELS', p.abstract_cn = '本申请公开了使用含碳原料生产液体燃料产品的系统和方法。 还公开了可用于系统和方法中的催化剂以及制备催化剂的方法。', p.abstract_en = 'Disclosed in the application include systems and processes for producing a liquid transportation fuel product using a carbon-containing feedstock. Also disclosed include catalysts that can be used in the systems and the processes,  and processes of making the catalysts.', p.application_date = '2015-09-23 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US20160096998A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/34', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WOCA15050980'}) SET p.application_no = 'WOCA15050980', p.title_cn = '非平衡等离子体系统和合成气的精制方法', p.title_en = 'A NON-EQUILIBRIUM PLASMA SYSTEM AND METHOD OF REFINING SYNGAS', p.abstract_cn = '本发明的目的是提供非平衡等离子体(nep)的系统和方法精制的合成气。根据本发明的一个方面，本发明提供一种非平衡等离子体合成气的精制系统，所述系统包括反应器与中空的腔室，具有一个或多个进气歧管被构造成促进轴向对称和涡流的形式，其中合成气和一种或多种气化剂引入其内用于加工反应器内，高电压电极；和接地电极，其中，该系统被配置为产生非平衡等离子体的产生电弧在高电压的应用两端的电势的弧高之间的间隙高压电极和接地电极和所述的系统配置为使得合成气，所述一个或多个气化剂(S)和等离子体产生电弧来在一起同时在反应器。在本发明的一个实施例中，非平衡等离子体系统包括两个偏心圆柱歧管被配置为形成单进气歧管，所述的两个偏心圆柱歧管包括第一偏心圆柱歧管为气化剂输入和第二偏心圆柱形歧管用于合成气输入。本发明还包括合成气的精制方法，其中所述非平衡等离子体本发明结合系统合成气，空气和等离子体产生的电弧在同一区域，将相同的位置中共同存在。', p.abstract_en = 'An object of the present invention is to provide a non-equilibrium plasma (NEP) system and method of refining syngas. In accordance with an aspect of the present invention,  there is provided a non-equilibrium plasma system for refining syngas,  the system comprising a reactor with a hollow chamber,  having one or more inlet manifolds configured to promote an axially symmetric and swirling flow pattern,  into which syngas and one or more gasifying agents are introduced for processing within the reactor,  a high voltage electrode;  and a ground electrode,  wherein the system is configured to create a non-equilibrium plasma producing electric arc upon application of a high voltage potential across an arc initiating gap between the high voltage electrode and the ground electrode and wherein the system is configured such that the syngas,  the one or more gasifying agent(s) and plasma producing electric arc come together concurrently in the reactor. In one embodiment of the invention,  the non-equilibrium plasma system comprises two eccentric cylindrical manifolds configured to form a single inlet manifold,  wherein the two eccentric cylindrical manifolds comprise a first eccentric cylindrical manifold for gasifying agent input and a second eccentric cylindrical manifold for syngas input. The invention also comprises a method for refining syngas wherein the non-equilibrium plasma system of the present invention combines the syngas,  the air and the plasma-producing electric arc in the same region,  which will co-exist in the same location.', p.application_date = '2015-09-30 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016049762A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WOEP15071043'}) SET p.application_no = 'WOEP15071043', p.title_cn = '膜电极装置，反应器，包括膜电极用于氢分离的装置和方法', p.title_en = 'MEMBRANE ELECTRODE ARRANGEMENT,  REACTOR COMPRISING THE MEMBRANE ELECTRODE ARRANGEMENT AND METHOD FOR HYDROGEN SEPARATION', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种膜电极装置(1)包括 : 气密的，选择性质子传导膜(3)，具有一滞留侧(5)包括阳极(7)，和一个渗透侧(9)与阴极(11)，-电压源(13)之间产生电位差的阳极(7)和阴极(11)，-阳极催化剂(15)，具有催化活性材料，在滞留侧(5)和阴极催化剂(17)，具有催化活性材料，在渗透侧(9)，其中阴极催化剂(17)具有较少催化活性材料较阳极催化剂(15)。此外，本发明涉及一种反应器，包括膜电极装置(1)和分离氢的方法通过使用该膜电极装置(1)。', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention relates to a membrane electrode arrangement (1) comprising - a gas-tight,  selectively proton-conducting membrane (3),  which has a retentate side (5) comprising an anode (7),  and a permeate side (9) with a cathode (11),  - a voltage source (13) for generating a potential difference between the anode (7) and the cathode (11),  - an anode catalyst (15),  which has a catalytically active material,  on the retentate side (5) and - a cathode catalyst (17),  which has a catalytically active material,  on the permeate side (9),  wherein the cathode catalyst (17) has less catalytically active material than the anode catalyst (15). Furthermore,  the present invention relates to a reactor comprising the membrane electrode arrangement (1) and to a method for separating hydrogen by using the membrane electrode arrangement (1).', p.application_date = '2015-09-15 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016050500A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/22', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201110294308.8'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201110294308.8', p.title_cn = '一种催化重整制氢方法与催化装置', p.title_en = 'A catalytic reforming hydrogen production method and the catalytic device', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种催化重整制氢方法，包括：以长径比≥20的金属催化管为催化装置，将第一气体原料与水蒸气的混合气体通入所述金属催化管内，反应后得到氢气。与现有技术相比，由于本发明以长径比≥20的金属催化管为催化装置，因此，第一气体原料与水蒸气在该催化装置内形成层流，避免了在制氢过程中由于紊流带来的积碳现象的发生，提高了催化剂的寿命和催化重整制氢的转化效率。另外，本发明还提供一种用于催化重整制氢的催化装置，该装置以长径比≥20的金属催化管为主要结构，在该装置的工作过程中，气体流场在金属催化管内主要为层流方式，避免了由于紊流产生的堆积炭黑，不会堵塞催化剂的气体通道，保证了催化装置的寿命。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention discloses a method for producing hydrogen by catalytic reforming. The method comprises the following steps of :  on the basis of taking a metal catalytic tube with the length-diameter ratio larger than or equal to 20 as a catalytic device,  introducing mixed gas of a first gas material and water vapor into the metal catalytic tube,  and obtaining hydrogen after reaction. Compared with the prior art,  the method has the advantages that as the metal catalytic tube with the length-diameter ratio larger than or equal to 20 is taken as the catalytic device,  the first gas material and water vapor form laminar flow in the catalytic device,  the phenomenon of carbon deposition caused by turbulent flow during the hydrogen producing process is avoided,  the service life of a catalyst is increased,  and the conversion rate of producing hydrogen by catalytic reforming is improved. In addition,  the invention also provides a catalytic device for producing hydrogen by catalytic reforming. The device takes the metal catalytic tube with the length-diameter ratio larger than or equal to 20 as a main structure;  the flow field of gas mainly adopts a laminar flow mode in the metal catalytic tube during the operation of the device;  carbon black deposition caused by turbulent flow is avoided;  a gas channel for catalytic can not be clogged;  and the service life of the catalytic device is guaranteed.', p.application_date = '2011-09-27 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN103011077B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/40', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201310048980.8'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201310048980.8', p.title_cn = '采用金属镁连续生产氢气和氢氧化镁的工艺', p.title_en = 'The metal magnesium continuous hydrogen production process and magnesium hydroxide', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种采用金属镁连续生产氢气和氢氧化镁的工艺，包括首先将储电池两个轮出电极与供电系统供电连接，供电系统经电压检测报警电路，电压检测合格后给智能控制单元及各泵、阀、传感器供电，电压检测不合格禁止供电；实现本工艺的专用设备包括反应器、水箱、金属镁原料箱、氢燃料电池、尾料箱、氢气收集箱、散热器、料泵、给水泵、抽气泵、冷却水循环泵、排气电磁阀、电动球型阀、抽气阀、电磁阀、水气分离排水阀、第一压力传感器、第二压力传感器、上液位传感器、下液位传感器、第一液位传感器、第二液位传感器。本发明适用于金属水解制氢发电，具有设计科学、结构合理、控作方便、安全环保节能的特点，可以实现制氢、发电、供热的连续进行。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a technology using magnesium metal for continuous hydrogen and magnesium hydroxide production,  and the technology is as follows :  first,  two output electrodes of a storage battery are in power supply connection with a power supply system,  after voltage detection of the power supply system by a voltage detection and alarm circuit,  if the voltage detection of the power supply system is qualified,  the power supply system provides power to an intelligent control unit,  each pump,  each valve and each sensor,  and if the voltage detection of the power supply system is unqualified,  the power supply is forbidden;  special equipment for implementation of the technology comprises a reactor,  a water box,  a metal magnesium raw material tank,  a hydrogen fuel cell,  a tail material box,  a hydrogen collecting box,  a heat sink,  a material pump,  a water supply pump,  a hydrogen circulation pump,  an electromagnetic valve,  an electric ball valve and an electromagnetic valve;  a high-liquid-level-surface liquid level sensor and a low-liquid-level-surface liquid level sensor are arranged in the reactor,  and the top of the reactor passes through a pipeline. The technology is applicable to metal hydrolysis for hydrogen production for power generation,  has the advantages of scientific design,  reasonable structure,  convenient control,  safety,  environmental friendliness and energy saving,  and can achieve continuous hydrogen production,  power generation and heat supply.', p.application_date = '2013-02-07 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN103979488B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/08', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201310049017.1'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201310049017.1', p.title_cn = '采用金属镁或铝连续制氢的热电联供工艺', p.title_en = 'The metal magnesium or aluminum for the thermoelectricity is joint process for continuous production of hydrogen', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种采用金属镁或铝连续制氢的热电联供工艺，包括首先将储电池两个轮出电极与供电系统供电连接，供电系统经电压检测报警电路，电压检测合格后给智能控制单元及各泵、阀、传感器供电，电压检测不合格禁止供电；实现本工艺的专用设备包括反应器、碱液箱、金属镁或铝原料箱、氢燃料电池、尾料箱、热水系统、蠕动泵、给水泵、氢气循环泵、排气电磁阀、电动球型阀、第一电磁阀、抽气阀、第二电磁阀、水气分离排水阀、第一压力传感器、第二压力传感器、上液位传感器。本发明适用于金属水解制氢发电，具有设计科学、结构合理、控作方便、安全环保节能的特点，可以实现制氢、发电、供热的连续进行。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a combined heat and power technology using magnesium metal or aluminum for continuous hydrogen production,  and the combined heat and power technology is as follows :  first,  two output electrodes of a storage battery are in power supply connection with a power supply system,  after voltage detection of the power supply system by a voltage detection and alarm circuit,  if the voltage detection of the power supply system is qualified,  the power supply system provides power to an intelligent control unit,  a pump,  a valve and a sensor,  and if the voltage detection of the power supply system is unqualified,  the power supply is forbidden;  special equipment for implementation of the combined heat and power technology comprises a reactor,  a lye box,  a metal magnesium or aluminum raw material tank,  a hydrogen fuel cell,  a tail material box,  a hot water system,  a peristaltic pump,  a water supply pump,  a hydrogen circulation pump,  an exhaust electromagnetic valve,  a pressure sensor,  an upper liquid level sensor,  a lower liquid level sensor,  a tail material box liquid level sensor,  a lye box liquid level sensor and a raw material tank liquid level sensor. The combined heat and power technology is applicable to metal hydrolysis for hydrogen production for power generation,  has the advantages of scientific design,  reasonable structure,  convenient control,  safety,  environmental friendliness and energy saving,  and can achieve continuous hydrogen production,  power generation and heat supply.', p.application_date = '2013-02-07 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN103979489B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/08', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201410230333.3'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201410230333.3', p.title_cn = '一种高容量轻质金属复合储氢材料及制备方法', p.title_en = 'A high capacity light metal composite hydrogen storage material and its preparation method', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种高容量轻质金属复合储氢材料及制备方法，所述储氢材料主要含有碱金属硼氢化物或碱土金属硼氢化物，所述碱金属硼氢化物或碱土金属硼氢化物至少还键合了一个尿素分子基团。所述方法包括：将碱金属硼氢化物或碱土金属硼氢化物与尿素按摩尔比10 : 1～1 : 10的比例混合，并于惰性气氛中球磨反应，球磨反应的时间为1-10小时。本发明公开的是一种新型复合储氢材料，能够在100-250℃下释放高纯氢气。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention discloses a high-capacity light metal composite hydrogen storage material and a preparation method thereof. The hydrogen storage material mainly comprises alkali metal boron hydride or alkali earth metal boron hydride bonded with at least one urea molecule group. The method comprises the following steps :  mixing alkali metal boron hydride or alkali earth metal boron hydride with urea at a molar ratio of (10 : 1)-(1 : 10),  and performing ball-milling reaction in an inert atmosphere for 1-10 hours. According to the novel composite hydrogen storage material disclosed by the invention,  high-purity hydrogen can be released at 100-250 DEG C.', p.application_date = '2014-05-28 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN104030239B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201410612052.4'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201410612052.4', p.title_cn = '一种氢氦混合气体分离与回收装置', p.title_en = 'A hydrogen helium the separation of the mixed gas and the recovering device', p.abstract_cn = '本发明提供了一种氢氦混合气体分离与回收装置，其特点是：所述装置中的高浓度氢氦混合气体与膜分离器连接，膜分离器分别与低温吸附床、氢气储罐连接；中等浓度氢氦混合气体与低温吸附床连接，低温吸附床分别与膜分离器、催化氧化床、氦气储罐连接，催化氧化床分别与氦气储罐和水储罐连接；低浓度氢氦混合气体与催化氧化床连接，催化氧化床分别与氦气储罐和水储罐连接。采用本发明的装置，能够实现不同体积浓度的氢氦混合气体的分离与回收。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention provides a hydrogen and helium gas mixture separation and recovery device. The device characterized in that a high-concentration hydrogen and helium gas mixture in the device is connected with a membrane separator,  and the membrane separator is connected with a low-temperature adsorption bed and a hydrogen gas storage tank respectively;  a medium-concentration hydrogen and helium gas mixture is connected with the low-temperature adsorption bed,  the low-temperature adsorption bed is connected with the membrane separator,  a catalytic oxidation bed and a helium gas storage tank respectively,  and the catalytic oxidation bed is connected with the helium gas storage tank and a water storage tank respectively;  a low-concentration hydrogen and helium gas mixture is connected with the catalytic oxidation bed,  and the catalytic oxidation bed is connected with the helium gas storage tank and the water storage tank respectively. By adopting the device provided by the invention,  the separation and recovery of the hydrogen and helium gas mixtures of different volumetric concentrations can be realized.', p.application_date = '2014-11-05 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN104340959B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/50', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201410432569.5'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201410432569.5', p.title_cn = '一种甲醇制合成气燃料的生产工艺', p.title_en = 'Production process for preparing synthetic gas fuel from methanol', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种甲醇制合成气燃料的生产工艺，该工艺通过选取甲醇作为原料，甲醇被加热汽化至120±10℃时通过热交换器换热提高到200±10℃，再通过过热器进一步加热至310±10℃，再将加热完成的气态的甲醇传送至反应器内，甲醇在反应器催化剂的作用下发生裂解反应，生成一氧化碳和氢气，产生的热气流的热能量通过热交换器被甲醇蒸汽所吸收，增加了甲醇汽化温度，降低了热气流的温度，反应过程中的反应热也得到了充分利用，热气流通过冷却器被冷水冷却至常温后进入气柜，常温气体被减压至适当的压力后作为燃料被燃烧；本发明的有益效果是：甲醇的发热量由原20083KJ/kg被提高到28372KJ/kg，热值被提高了41%，达到了降低燃料成本和节省能源的目的。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention discloses a production process for preparing a synthetic gas fuel from methanol. According to the process,  methanol is used as a raw material and heated and vaporized to 120 DEG C +/- 10 DEG C;  then the methanol undergoes heat exchange via a heat exchanger so as to increase the temperature of the methanol to 200 DEG C +/- 10 DEG C;  then the methanol is further heated to 310 +/- 10 DEG C by a superheater;  the gaseous methanol obtained after completion of heating is conveyed to a reactor and undergoes a cracking reaction under the action of a catalyst in the reactor to produce carbon monoxide and hydrogen;  heat energy of produced thermal current is absorbed by methanol steam through the heat exchanger,  so methanol vaporization temperature is increased,  the temperature of the thermal current is decreased,  and reaction heat produced in the process of reaction is fully utilized;  the thermal current passes through a cooler and is cooled normal temperature by cold water,  and then the cooled current enters a gasometer;  and the pressure of normal-temperature gas is properly reduced,  and then the gas is used as a fuel and combusted. The invention has the following beneficial effects :  the caloric power of methanol is increased to 28372 KJ/kg from original 20083 KJ/kg,  and a calorific value is increased by 41%,  so the purposes of reducing fuel cost and saving energy are achieved.', p.application_date = '2014-08-28 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105460889A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/26', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201480046737.5'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201480046737.5', p.title_cn = '通过基于费-托的合成产生烯烃的方法', p.title_en = 'A process for the production of olefins through fischer-tropsch based synthesis', p.abstract_cn = '本公开和发明涉及一种方法，所述方法包括：a)引入天然气；b)重整所述天然气；其中所述重整步骤包括使所述天然气与蒸汽接触以产生合成气；c)将所述合成气转化成包含至少一种烯烃的产物混合物和包含链烷烃和汽油的副产物；其中所述转化步骤包括使所述合成气与Co/Mn催化剂接触；以及d)将所述副产物转化成合成气。', p.abstract_en = 'The present disclosures and inventions relate to a method comprising :  a) introducing a natural gas;  b) reforming the natural gas;  wherein the reforming step comprises contacting the natural gas with steam to produce a syngas;  c) converting the syngas to a product mixture comprising at least one olefin and a byproduct comprising a paraffin and a gasoline;  wherein the converting step comprises contacting the syngas with a Co/Mn catalyst;  and d) converting the byproduct to syngas.', p.application_date = '2014-07-28 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105473495A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/34', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201380079136.X'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201380079136.X', p.title_cn = '利用电化学电池生产和提供净化的气体的方法', p.title_en = 'Methods of producing and providing purified gas using an electrochemical cell', p.abstract_cn = '根据一个实施例，一种生产满足预定的纯度阈值的氢气的方法，可以包括通过电化学氢泵传输一定数量的氢气混合物，其中电化学氢泵包括阳极、阴极及位于阳极和阴极之间的电解质膜；通过将氢气从阳极经电解质膜传输到阴极，从氢气混合物中分离一定数量的氢气；从阴极收集氢气，其中收集的氢气至少满足预定的纯度阈值；以及生成证书：收集的氢气具有至少基本上等于预定的纯度阈值的纯度。', p.abstract_en = 'In accordance with one embodiment,  a method of producing hydrogen gas meeting a predetermined threshold of purity may include transferring a quantity of a hydrogen gas mixture through an electrochemical hydrogen pump,  wherein the electrochemical hydrogen pump includes an anode,  a cathode,  and an electrolyte membrane located between the anode and the cathode;  separating a quantity of hydrogen gas from the hydrogen gas mixture by transferring the hydrogen gas from the anode,  through the electrolyte membrane,  to the cathode;  collecting the hydrogen gas from the cathode,  wherein the collected hydrogen gas at least meets the predetermined threshold of purity;  and producing a certificate that the collected hydrogen gas has a purity that is at least substantially equal to the predetermined threshold of purity.', p.application_date = '2013-09-30 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105473497A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/50', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'EP10719140'}) SET p.application_no = 'EP10719140', p.title_cn = '工艺用于制造含氢产物气体', p.title_en = 'PROCESS FOR PRODUCING A HYDROGEN-CONTAINING PRODUCT GAS', p.abstract_cn = '用于制造含氢产物气体的方法通过催化蒸汽-烃重整的总蒸汽-碳用于该方法的摩尔比为1.5 : 2.4。工艺流反应，反应之前在至少两个预转化炉中的含催化剂的管中在顶烧转化炉。绝热预重整器第一中的过程物流反应，本发明的方法之前被引入物流被加热预重整器第二和/或第二加热预重整器。该方法避免了碳沉积在所述催化剂中的含催化剂的管中的主重整器。', p.abstract_en = 'A process for producing a hydrogen-containing product gas by catalytic steam-hydrocarbon reforming with an overall steam-to-carbon molar ratio between 1.5 and 2.4 for the process. The process stream is reacted in at least two prereformers prior to reaction in catalyst-containing tubes in a top-fired reformer furnace. The process stream is reacted adiabatically in the first prereformer,  while the process stream is heated prior to being introduced into the second prereformer and/or the second prereformer is heated. The process avoids carbon formation on the catalyst in the catalyst-containing tubes in the primary reformer.', p.application_date = '2010-04-15 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'EP2419375B1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'EP13822971'}) SET p.application_no = 'EP13822971', p.title_cn = '氢能系统', p.title_en = 'HYDROGEN ENERGY SYSTEMS', p.abstract_cn = '氢能系统获取氢气的气体从固态储存媒体使用控制的激光器，本发明还公开了系统充电/再充电镁与氢反应得到氢化镁。其它相对安全系统辅助存储，运输和使用(如车辆)公开了这种固态存储介质。', p.abstract_en = 'Hydrogen energy systems for obtaining hydrogen gas from a solid storage medium using controlled lasers. Also disclosed are systems for charging/recharging magnesium with hydrogen to obtain magnesium hydride. Other relatively safe systems assisting storage,  transport and use (as in vehicles) of such solid storage mediums are disclosed.', p.application_date = '2013-07-24 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'EP2877773A4', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2012221545'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2012221545', p.title_cn = '所述保持构件和所述制氢装置', p.title_en = 'The holding member and the hydrogen producing device', p.abstract_cn = '要解决的问题 : 在所述反应器，和一种粒状催化剂氢分离器和容纳时，氢分离器是几乎不损坏(用于保持粒状催化剂)，以提供一种装置用于生产氢和所述保持件。溶液 : 该颗粒状催化剂(3)，(5)是一种状态中保持通过所述保持件容纳在所述反应器(13)。因此，该保持件(5)是保持在所述反应器(3)和(9)和一种氢分离器的粒状催化剂(13)。是存储在所述的制氢装置(1)，和一种低温度状态，使得该状态的一种高温度，通过施加热循环，和所述的膨胀和收缩所述反应器(13)被重复，一种氢分离器(9)是不易受到损坏，。在详细描述，该保持件(5)和(9)一种氢气分离器(3)之间是保持该颗粒状催化剂在该情况下，该反应器的温度(13)通过收缩率，(3)的颗粒催化剂在所述反应器(13)是不向内推的，(3)一种粒状催化剂是压制到所述的破损的问题所述氢分离器(9)几乎不发生。选自拉拔 : 图5', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To provide a holding member (holding a granular catalyst) with which a hydrogen separation body is hardly broken when the granular catalyst and the hydrogen separation body are accommodated in a reactor,  and to provide a hydrogen production apparatus. SOLUTION :  A granular catalyst (3) is accommodated in a reactor (13) in a state held by a holding member (5). Accordingly,  in a hydrogen production apparatus (1) in which the granular catalyst (3) held by the holding member (5) and a hydrogen separation body (9) are accommodated in the reactor (13),  the hydrogen separation body (9) is hardly broken even if expansion and contraction of the reactor (13) are repeated when a heat cycle of a high temperature state and a low temperature state is applied. In more detail,  in the case when the granular catalyst (3) is held between the holding member (5) and the hydrogen separation body (9),  the hydrogen separation body (9) is not broken by being pressed with the granular catalyst (3) because the granular catalyst (3) is not pressed to the inside by the reactor (13) even if the reactor (13) becomes a low temperature and contracts. COPYRIGHT :  (C)2014, JPO&INPIT', p.application_date = '2012-10-03 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP5898037B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2013540300'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2013540300', p.title_cn = '产生电，液氢的方法', p.title_en = 'Method of generating electricity and liquid hydrogen', p.abstract_cn = '本发明提供了一种利用生产氢气和电的方法适用于生产氢和/或电液系统. 该系统包括气体重整单元，用于接收转化天然气以生产含氢气体. 发电单元，用以接收并将氢气从气体转化发电装置. 和一种氢液化单元，用于接收从气体液化氢重整装置. 氢气液化单元产生的电力的至少一部分由通过该发电单元. 在第一时间段的操作. 天然气气体提供给重整装置和操作液氢系统. 以及在第二时间段的操作. 天然气气体提供给重整装置和被操作以输出电力的系统.', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention provides a method for producing hydrogen and electricity utilizing a system suitable for producing liquid hydrogen and/or electricity. The system includes a gas reforming unit for receiving and reforming a natural gas feed to produce a hydrogen-comprising gas;  an electricity generation unit for receiving and converting hydrogen from the gas reforming unit to generate electricity;  and a hydrogen liquefaction unit for receiving and liquefying hydrogen from the gas reforming unit. The hydrogen liquefaction unit is powered by at least part of the electricity produced by the electricity generation unit. During a first period of operation,  natural gas is provided to the gas reforming unit and the system is operated to export liquid hydrogen,  and during a second period of operation,  natural gas is provided to the gas reforming unit and the system is operated to export electricity.', p.application_date = '2011-11-16 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP5899231B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/34', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2014253971'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2014253971', p.title_cn = '氢气生成方法和装置', p.title_en = 'The hydrogen gas generation method and device', p.abstract_cn = '要解决的问题 : 提供一种方法，其中氢气体高效率地获得比常规方法更容易. 热反应生产的产品可有效回收利用. 溶液 : 金属M和金属氢化物M‘H>(M和M’是相同或不同的氢吸收性金属. 且A为相同的金属M的化合价‘)与蒸汽接触以生成氧化物MB“柱”pos=pos=“后”OCM“pos=Sb>B”柱“pos=”后“OC(其中. B×(金属M的价态或M‘)=2℃)，并产生氢气. 其回收. M和M‘是优选的为镁. 铝或铁. 反应中产生的热量可以用于由水产生蒸汽. 所述蒸汽循环回反应. 一包含所述金属M和第二层第一层包括金属氢化物M‘H>一种铺设在容器中的蒸汽被供给以通通过第一层和第二层中排出之前，. 生产MB“柱”pos=pos=“后”OCM“pos=Sb>B”柱“pos=”后“OC可以降低回收作为原料. A(c)2013. &耕作方法.', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To provide a method in which hydrogen gas is efficiently obtained more easily than in conventional methods,  and heat and products produced in reaction can be effectively recycled.SOLUTION :  A metal M and a metal hydride M\'H(M and M\' are the same or a different hydrogen absorbing metal;  and a is the same as the valence of the metal M\') are brought into contact with steam to produce oxides MOand M\'O(wherein,  b×(valence of the metal M or M\')=2c) and to generate hydrogen gas,  which is recovered. M and M\' are preferably Mg,  Al or Fe. The heat generated in the reaction may be used for producing steam from water,  the steam being recycled to the reaction. A first layer including the metal M and a second layer including the metal hydride M\'Hare laid in a vessel and the steam is supplied so as to pass through the first layer and then the second layer before being discharged. The produced MOand M\'Omay be reduced and recycled as raw materials.', p.application_date = '2014-12-16 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP5900992B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/06', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'KR1020140130481'}) SET p.application_no = 'KR1020140130481', p.title_cn = '双流化床反应器和从沼气生产合成气的方法', p.title_en = 'DUAL FLUIDIZED BED REACTOR AND METHOD FOR PRODUCING SYNGAS FROM BIOGAS', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及用于生产生物气(沼气)，从双流式反应器与合成气产生合成气体的制造方法，涉及一种. 甲烷. 二氧化碳和水分的气体包括生物合成制备成含一氧化碳和氢的气态区域中，其中流化床反应器. 2不同流速流化床，包括流化床反应器. 所述生物气和作用在其上的催化剂. (1)称为原料的2CH4共2±5h2H2O→3，Co(1)与间苯二酚反应合成数字1，所述流化床反应器. 竖炉中的碳和1，以提供其上沉积有催化流化床反应器. 供应氧. 氧和碳的碳氧反应催化剂的再生是在所述催化剂中Co2已经转化为2的数，包括流化床反应器. 所述再生催化剂和2离开反应器的CO反应中循环使用1号2号中提供了一种双流化床反应器.', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention relates to a dual fluidized-bed reactor for producing synthetic gas from biogas and a method for producing synthetic gas. More particularly,  the present invention relates to a dual fluidized-bed reactor for producing synthetic gas containing carbon monoxide and hydrogen from biogas containing methane,  carbon dioxide and water. The dual fluidized-bed reactor comprises two fluidized-bed reactors having different flow rates. More particularly,  the dual fluidized-bed reactor comprises :  a first fluidized-bed reactor to which the biogas and a catalyst are supplied and which produces synthesis gas through the reaction of the formula (1) represented by 2CH_4 + CO_2 + H_2O &rarr;  3CO + 5H_2;  and a second fluidized-bed reactor to which the catalyst having the catalyst deposited thereon from the first fluidized-bed reactor is supplied together with oxygen and which regenerates the catalyst by converting the carbon deposited on the catalyst into CO_2 through the reaction of oxygen with carbon,  wherein the regenerated catalyst and CO_2 are circulated from the second reactor to the first reactor.COPYRIGHT KIPO 2016', p.application_date = '2014-09-29 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'KR1020160037633A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/44', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'SA515370284'}) SET p.application_no = 'SA515370284', p.title_cn = '有效利用多余电能的设备和方法', p.title_en = 'A plant and process for efficient use of excess electrical energy', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种设备，其包括用于电化学或电热制氢的第一装置，产生第一氢气流; 用于通过蒸汽重整、部分氧化或脱氢由烃生产氢气的第二装置。 5 脱氢，其产生第二氢气; 供入第一氢气流和第二氢气流的氢气导管或氢气消耗器; 以及控制装置，其以第一氢气流和第二氢气流的总量匹配预定值的方式适应第一装置中和第二装置中的氢气生产的产生。通过操作该装置，可以有效地利用多余的电能。 10 用于利用过量电能电化学或电解生产氢气', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention relates to a plant comprising a first device for the electrochemical or electrothermal production of hydrogen,  producing a first hydrogen stream;  A second device for producing hydrogen from a hydrocarbon by steam reformation,  partial oxidation,  or dehydrogenation.  5 dehydrogenation,  which produces a second hydrogen stream;  A hydrogen conduit or hydrogen consumer to both of which the first hydrogen stream and the second hydrogen stream are fed;  And a control device that accommodates the production of hydrogen production in the first device and in the second device in such a way that the total amount of the first hydrogen stream and the second hydrogen stream matches a predetermined value. The excess electrical energy can be used effectively by operating the device.  10 For the electrochemical or electrolytic production of hydrogen with excess electrical energy.', p.application_date = '2015-12-16 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'SA515370284A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/36', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2014168163'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2014168163', p.title_cn = '氢气发生装置', p.title_en = 'HYDROGEN GENERATOR', p.abstract_cn = '要解决的问题 :  空气的混合物与含氢气体分散和装配性能不被降解， 一种均匀混合气供应到氢气发生器。 溶液 :  空气混合通道12是含氢气体供给， 送风管13插入第一流路1，18和， 空气的混合物从第一流路1的18含氢气体供给至第一 流道含有2和19， 第一环形空间，在流动路径118， 送风管的顶端13， 第一流路1中的空气18形成，从而在两个方向上流动， 第一入口16进入流道2， 以空气供应管13的端部， 第一隔壁(1)5设置在相对的位置， 送风管13装配通过变化，即使安装在对角线上， 同样在两个方向上的空气分为流动通道1， 混合均匀的气体可供给。 选择的绘图 : 图。 3', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To provide a hydrogen generator in which mixing performance between air and hydrogen-containing gas is not reduced by assembling variation,  and feeding uniform mixed gas. SOLUTION :  An air mixing flow passage 12 includes :  a first flow passage 18 fed with hydrogen-containing gas and inserted with an air feed tube 13;  and a second flow passage 19 fed with the hydrogen-containing gas mixed with the air from the first flow passage 18. The first flow passage 18 being an annular space,  the tip of the air feed tube 13 is formed in such a manner that the air is separated to both the directions orbiting the inside of the first flow passage 18,  and an inlet 16 to the second flow passage is arranged at a position confronted with the first barrier 5 held to the position of the tip of the air feed tube 13,  thus,  even in the case that the air feed tube 13 is diagonally fitted by assembling variation,  the air is uniformly separated to both the directions of the first flow passage,  and uniform mixed gas can be fed. SELECTED DRAWING :  Figure 3 COPYRIGHT :  (C)2016, JPO&INPIT', p.application_date = '2014-08-21 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP2016044085A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2014169744'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2014169744', p.title_cn = '氢气发生器，氢气生成方法和制造方法', p.title_en = 'HYDROGEN GENERATING AGENT AND METHOD FOR PRODUCING THE SAME,  AND HYDROGEN GENERATING METHOD', p.abstract_cn = '要解决的问题 : 该树脂所含的小金属中氢的量即使，反应，足够高以产生实际的氢气的量，氢气发生器能保持形状的成型体，或堵塞过滤器或类似物能够抑制灰尘如氢气发生器，其制造方法，和用于产生氢气的方法。方法 : 热固性树脂，亲水聚合物，和粒状含氢氢发电机，其制造方法，和用于产生氢气的方法。选择绘制 : 图。1', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To provide a hydrogen generating agent which can generate a practical amount of hydrogen gas having sufficiently high reactivity,  can maintain a shape of a hydrogen generating agent molding,  and can suppress clogging of a filter and the like,  powdery dust and the like,  even when a content of a metal hydride in a resin is low;  a method for producing the same;  and a hydrogen generating method. SOLUTION :  There are provided a hydrogen generating agent containing a thermosetting resin,  a hydrophilic polymer,  and a granular metal hydride,  a method for producing the same,  and a hydrogen generating method. SELECTED DRAWING :  Figure 1 COPYRIGHT :  (C)2016, JPO&INPIT', p.application_date = '2014-08-22 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP2016044104A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/06', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2014170528'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2014170528', p.title_cn = '氢制造系统，氢和氨制造方法的制造方法及其使用', p.title_en = 'HYDROGEN PRODUCTION SYSTEM,  HYDROGEN PRODUCTION METHOD AND AMMONIA PRODUCTION METHOD USING THE SAME', p.abstract_cn = '要解决的问题 : 热分解硫酸或碘化氢和作为热量集中，石油，煤等不依赖于化石燃料通过提供热源，共2可以有助于氢气还原生产系统，使用其的氨和氢的生产方法。方法 : 通过热分解产生的硫酸二氧化硫气体的混合物通过水吸收，碘化，通过热分解得到的碘化氢在氢生产系统，第一热介质1，使用硫酸热分解装置和热分解硫酸，12比第一低温热介质的热介质通过第一和第二热介质热交换器1，2使用第二热介质加热产生蒸汽和蒸汽发生装置。选择的绘图 : 图。1', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To provide a hydrogen production system capable of contributing to the reduction of CO2 by providing a heat source not depending on fossil fuels such as petroleum and coal as heat energy used for the thermal decomposition and concentration of hydrogen iodide and sulfuric acid,  a hydrogen production method,  and an ammonia production method using the same. SOLUTION :  Provided is a system where a sulfur dioxide gas produced by thermally decomposing sulfuric acid is absorbed into a mixture of water and iodine,  and the obtained hydrogen iodide is thermally decomposed to produce hydrogen,  comprising a sulfuric acid thermal decomposition means of thermally decomposing sulfuric acid using a first heat medium and a waver vapor generating means of thermally exchanging the second heat medium at a temperature lower than that of the first heat medium and using the second heat medium whose temperature is raised to generate water vapor. SELECTED DRAWING :  Figure 1 COPYRIGHT :  (C)2016, JPO&INPIT', p.application_date = '2014-08-25 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP2016044107A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'IDP00201405658'}) SET p.application_no = 'IDP00201405658', p.title_cn = '制氨合成气工艺及氨炼厂前端', p.title_en = 'Process for preparing ammonia synthesis gas and front end of ammonia refinery', p.abstract_cn = '一种从碳氢化合物源制备氨合成气的工艺，包括：在用氧(12)或富氧空气(28)燃烧的ATR或POX反应器(11)中将碳氢化合物源转化为粗合成气(14)；一种原料合成气(14)的水气变换过程，包括在200-300℃温度下的中温变换(15)，从而得到变换合成气(16)；一种移位合成气净化(16)，它包括至少一个变压吸附阶段(17)，以除去合成气中的二氧化碳和残余甲烷，从而获得纯合成气(18)，并且作为选择，在纯合成气(18)中加入氮气(19)，从而获得具有预期氢氮比的氨合成气', p.abstract_en = 'A process for the production of ammonia synthesis gas from a hydrocarbon source comprises :  converting the hydrocarbon source to raw synthesis gas (14) in an ATR or POX reactor (11) combusting with oxygen (12) or oxygen-enriched air (28);  A process for the water gas shift of a raw synthesis gas (14) comprises a moderate temperature shift (15) at a temperature of 200 to 300 DEG C to obtain a shifted synthesis gas (16);  A shift synthesis gas purification (16) comprising at least one pressure swing adsorption stage (17) to remove carbon dioxide and residual methane from the synthesis gas to obtain a pure synthesis gas (18) and,  optionally,  to add nitrogen (19) to the pure synthesis gas (18) to obtain an ammonia synthesis gas having a desired hydrogen to nitrogen ratio', p.application_date = '2014-09-22 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'IDP00201405658A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'AU2012364340'}) SET p.application_no = 'AU2012364340', p.title_cn = '共同生产甲醇和尿素的', p.title_en = 'Co-production of methanol and urea', p.abstract_cn = '用于由甲醇和尿素联产的烃进料在不需排气大量的二氧化碳到大气中。', p.abstract_en = 'Process for the co-production of methanol and urea from a hydrocarbon feed without venting large amounts of carbon dioxide to the atmosphere.', p.application_date = '2012-12-21 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'AU2012364340B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'DE60348583'}) SET p.application_no = 'DE60348583', p.title_cn = '自氧化内部加热型蒸汽重整系统', p.title_en = 'AUTOOXIDATION INTERNAL HEATING TYPE STEAM REFORMING SYSTEM', p.abstract_cn = '所述系统是自氧化内部加热蒸汽重整系统进行自原料气体的氧化氧的存在下进行蒸汽重整以产生富氢的重整气体。该系统包括蒸汽发生器(2)包括燃烧部分2a，用于燃烧空气-燃料混合物得到的混合助燃空气与燃料，从而加热水使用燃烧中产生的气体的燃烧部分2a至产生氢气；一种第一吸混合器(4)吸附的原料气体为来自蒸汽发生器的蒸汽流2，得到原料-蒸汽混合物；和氧化重整器1的原料气在原料-蒸汽混合物通过含氧从外部供给的气体，从而进行蒸汽重整的原料气体使用了该反应的热氧化以产生富氢重整气体。', p.abstract_en = 'The system is a self-oxidation internal heating steam reforming system for conducting self-oxidation of a raw material gas under the presence of oxygen and conducting steam reforming to generate a hydrogen-rich reformed gas. The system includes a steam generator 2 including a combustion section 2a for combusting an air-fuel mixture obtained by mixing a combustion air with a fuel,  thereby heating water using a combustion gas generated in the combustion section 2a to generate hydrogen;  a first sucking-mixer 4 for sucking the raw material gas into a steam stream coming from the steam generator 2 to obtain a raw material-steam mixture;  and a reformer 1 for oxidizing the raw material gas in the raw material-steam mixture by an oxygen-containing gas supplied from outside,  thereby conducting steam reforming of the raw material gas using the reaction heat of the oxidation to generate a hydrogen-rich reformed gas.', p.application_date = '2003-10-17 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'DE60348583T2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'EA201592137'}) SET p.application_no = 'EA201592137', p.title_cn = '在线吹扫用于在植物中生产氨和氢气', p.title_en = 'LINE BLOWING FOR USE IN PLANTS PRODUCTION OF AMMONIA AND HYDROGEN', p.abstract_cn = '在氨或氢气的设备，该设备包括进料段，重整段和偏移部，该换档部分包括低温变换炉和中温变换炉，一个通风线路的下游设置低温换档转换器以中温变换炉以允许所述换档来重新加热过程气体在低压(通常是3-7巴)。这样避免了工艺气体中的水蒸气冷凝。通过将该排放管道可以节省相当多的时间，更具体讲$time，用于临时关闭后重启的生产方法，由于LTS/手动切换开关的转换器加热的氮气循环的现象。', p.abstract_en = 'In an ammonia or hydrogen plant comprising a desulfurisation section,  a reforming section and a shift section,  where the shift section comprises a low temperature shift converter and a medium temperature shift converter,  a vent line is arranged downstream from the low temperature shift converter and the medium temperature shift converter in order to allow the shift converters to be re-heated with process gas at a low pressure (typically 3-7 bar). This way condensation of water vapour in the process gas is avoided. By applying this vent line it becomes possible to save significant time,  more specifically 8-24 hours,  for restarting the production after temporary shut-down thereof,  because a heat-up of the LTS/MTS converter in circulating nitrogen is avoided.', p.application_date = '2014-04-16 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'EA201592137A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'GCP200913124'}) SET p.application_no = 'GCP200913124', p.title_cn = 'GTL装置中合成气重整器的操作方法', p.title_en = 'OPERATION METHOD OF SYNTHESIS GAS REFORMER IN GTL PLANT', p.abstract_cn = '一种GTL(气体到液体)设备的合成气重整器的操作方法，包括：设置合成气重整器的操作条件；确定所述轻烃气体、所述蒸汽和所述CO2的流量以及所述合成气重整器所需的热量的控制目标值；控制合成气重整器的操作负荷；设定所述合成气重整器的炉效率；计算合成气重整器的燃烧器的燃烧负荷；基于所述燃烧器的所述燃料气体的组成测量值来计算所述燃料气体的较低热值；确定所述燃料气体的压力的控制目标值；计算燃料气体的压力的控制目标值与燃料气体的压力的测量值之间的偏差；以及通过控制设置在燃烧器入口处的压力控制阀来控制合成气重整器出口处的合成气的温度，以补偿偏差。', p.abstract_en = 'An operation method of a synthesis gas reformer of a GTL (gas to liquids) plant is provided with :  setting an operation condition of the synthesis gas reformer;  determining control target values of a flow rate of the light hydrocarbon gas,  the steam,  and the CO2,  and an amount of heat needed for the synthesis gas reformer;  controlling operation load of the synthesis gas reformer;  setting a furnace efficiency of the synthesis gas reformer;  calculating a combustion load of a burner of the synthesis gas reformer;  calculating a lower heating value of the fuel gas based on a composition measurement of the fuel gas of the burner;  determining a control target value of the pressure of the fuel gas;  calculating a deviation between the control target value of the pressure of the fuel gas and a measured value of the pressure of the fuel gas;  and controlling the temperature of the synthesis gas at the outlet of the synthesis gas reformer by controlling a pressure control valve provided at an inlet of the burner to compensate for the deviation.', p.application_date = '2009-03-25 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'GC0003682A', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'GC201120146'}) SET p.application_no = 'GC201120146', p.title_cn = '制氢工艺', p.title_en = 'HYDROGEN PRODUCTION PROCESS', p.abstract_cn = '提供了一种以高能量效率从水生产氢气的方法。本发明的氢气生产方法包括将水分解成氢气和氧气，其中本发明的方法包括通过使用太阳热能通过由下式(X1)10表示的反应将硫酸分解成水、二氧化硫和氧气，其中使用热太阳能进行下式(X1-1)的基本反应的至少一部分，并且使用除太阳热能之外的附加热能进行下式(X1-2)的基本反应的至少一部分，并且其中通过附加热能的加热温度比通过太阳热能的加热温度高10℃或更多，并且至少一部分附加热能是在反应容器中产生的20：(X1)H2S04~H20+S02+11202，(X1-1)H2S04~H20+so3，和(X1-2)so3~so2+1/202', p.abstract_en = 'A method for producing hydrogen from water with goodenergy efficiency is provided.5 The hydrogen production process of the presentinvention comprises splitting water into hydrogen andoxygen,  wherein the process of the present inventioncomprises decomposing sulfuric acid into water,  sulfurdioxide and oxygen through a reaction represented by the10 following formula (X1) by using solar thermal energy, wherein at least a part of the elementary reaction of thefollowing formula (X1-1) is performed using thermal solarenergy,  and at least a part of the elementary reaction ofthe following formula (X1-2) is performed using15 additional thermal energy other than solar thermalenergy,  and wherein the heating temperature by theadditional thermal energy is higher by 10°C or more thanthe heating temperature by the solar thermal energy,  andat least a part of the additional thermal energy is20 generated in a reaction vessel :  (X1) H2S04 ~ H20 + S02 +11202,  (X1-1) H2S04 ~ H20 + so3,  and (X1-2) so3 ~ so2 +1/202', p.application_date = '2011-12-27 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'GC0003880A', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/06', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2015555762'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2015555762', p.title_cn = '一种方法用于产生氢气的反应的铝', p.title_en = 'A method for generating hydrogen by the reaction of aluminum', p.abstract_cn = '本发明，一种方法用于产生氢气的反应的铝相对于，以醇溶液为溶剂的溶液中含有氢氧化铝加入到水中，基于反应。醇，低密度，和蒸汽温度高和具有低反应性，优选异丙醇，生物乙醇或乙醇。反应器，第一填充有铝，然后，随后，microreacter完全充满，使加入醇。铝，从而只覆盖该相同，然后去除酒精的一部分，和剩余的空间是空的。此外，溶液中的氢氧化物，根据要求调整氢。所产生的氢和酒精蒸汽，在热交换器。蒸馏得到microreacter再循环到醇，氢气过滤。选择的绘图 : 图。1', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a method for generating hydrogen by means of a reaction with aluminium,  based on reacting aluminium with water in a hydroxide solution,  comprising the addition of alcohol as a solvent to the solution. The alcohol is of the type having a lower density,  higher vaporisation temperature and lower reactivity,  preferably isopropanol,  ethanol or bioethanol. The reactor is first filled with aluminium and,  subsequently,  the alcohol is added so that the the reactor is completely full. Part of the alcohol is then emptied such that it only covers the aluminium,  with the rest of the space being emptied,  The hydroxide solution is then metered according to the hydrogen demand. The hydrogen and the alcohol vapour generated are distilled in an exchanger. The distilled alcohol is returned to the reactor and the hydrogen is filtered and stored.', p.application_date = '2013-02-01 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP2016509570A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/08', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WOUS15029023'}) SET p.application_no = 'WOUS15029023', p.title_cn = '组合物和方法产生一种水基氢等离子体燃料氢气能量', p.title_en = 'COMPOSITION AND METHOD TO GENERATE A WATER-BASED HYDROGEN PLASMA FUEL HYDROGEN ENERGY', p.abstract_cn = '本发明提供了一种富集水中与氢的组合物和方法提供一种氢能的燃料源。该组合物由与方法使用硅和二氧化硅作为催化剂以形成富氢水基燃料。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention provides a composition and method to enrich water with hydrogen to provide a fuel source for hydrogen energy. The composition is made with a method using silicon and silicon dioxide as a catalyst to form the hydrogen enriched water based fuel.', p.application_date = '2015-05-04 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016022186A9', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201310492030.4'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201310492030.4', p.title_cn = '利用LNG冷能的焦炉煤气低温制氢工艺', p.title_en = 'Use of LNG cold energy of the low-temperature process for preparing hydrogen from coke oven gas', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种利用LNG冷能的焦炉煤气低温制氢工艺，焦炉煤气经加压、处理后，除去H2O、CO2和NH3等物质，在换热系统与LNG换热，LNG升温至常温后进入蒸汽动力锅炉燃烧，而焦炉煤气温度降低；降温后的焦炉煤气输入第一分离器中，重烃类物质从第一分离器底部分离，剩余的焦炉煤气从分离器顶部输出后，经过换热系统再次降温后进入第二个分离器中，除去CH4，剩余的焦炉煤气从第二分离器顶部输出后经过换热系统再次降温进入制冷系统，经过制冷系统降温进入第三分离器，除去O2、CO和N2等物质后加压得到氢气。该法综合利用LNG冷能，解决了焦炉煤气低温制氢需要单纯通过加压膨胀来获取低温而大量消耗电能的问题。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a process for low-temperature production of hydrogen from coke oven gas by utilizing LNG cold energy. The coke oven gas is pressurized and treated to remove H2O,  CO2,  NH3 and other substances and is subjected to heat exchanger with LNG in a heat exchanging system,  LNG is heated to the room temperature and then enters a steam power boiler for combustion,  and the coke oven gas temperature is reduced;  the cooled coke oven gas is inputted into a first separator,  and heavy hydrocarbon matters are separated from the bottom of the first separator;  the remaining coke oven gas is outputted from the top of the separator,  then is cooled through the heat exchanging system again,  and goes into a second separator to remove CH4;  the remaining coke oven gas is outputted from the top of the second separator,  then is cooled again through the heat exchanging system,  followed by,  goes into a refrigerating system,  is cooled by the refrigerating system,  next goes into a third separator to remove O2,  CO,  N2 and other substances,  and finally is pressurized to obtain hydrogen. With comprehensive utilization of the LNG cold energy,  the method solves the problem that in the coke oven gas low-temperature hydrogen production,  the low temperature is obtained simply through pressurizing expansion resulting in consumption of a large amount of electric energy.', p.application_date = '2013-10-21 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN103738920B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/50', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201310717737.0'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201310717737.0', p.title_cn = '一种掺杂过渡金属氟化物的氢化铝储氢材料及其制备方法', p.title_en = 'A hydrogenation of doped with transition metal fluoride aluminum Chu Qing material and its preparation method', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种可以在较低温度下放氢的掺杂过渡金属氟化物的氢化铝储氢材料，由以下摩尔百分含量的90%～99.9%AlH3和0.1%～10%MFx组分制成。该储氢材料甚至能够在室温(10–30℃)下较快地放出氢气，且放氢量可达6.5wt%。本发明还公开了一种掺杂过渡金属氟化物的氢化铝储氢材料的制备方法，制备简单，易于控制，可控性好。本发明制备的掺杂过渡金属氟化物的氢化铝储氢材料的放氢温度和储氢容量均符合氢燃料电池汽车储氢系统的操作温度(&lt; 85℃)和储氢容量(&gt; 5.5wt%)要求，为车载储氢系统提供了一个极好的选择。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention discloses an aluminum hydride hydrogen storage material doped with a transition metal fluoride and capable of releasing hydrogen at low temperature. The aluminum hydride hydrogen storage material is prepared from AlH3 with the mol percent content of 90%-99.9% and MFx with the mol percent content of 0.1%-10%. The hydrogen storage material even can rapidly release hydrogen at room temperature (10-30 DEG C) and the hydrogen releasing amount can reach 6.5wt%. The invention further discloses a preparation method of the aluminum hydride hydrogen storage material doped with the transition metal fluoride. The preparation is simple and is easy to control,  and the controllability is good. The hydrogen releasing temperature and the hydrogen storage capacity of the prepared aluminum hydride hydrogen storage material doped with the transition metal fluoride meet the requirements of the operation temperature (less than 85 DEG C) and the hydrogen storage capacity (more than 5.5wt%) of a hydrogen cell car hydrogen storage system,  so as to provide an optimal choice to a vehicle-mounted hydrogen storage system.', p.application_date = '2013-12-23 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN103771337B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201410467867.8'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201410467867.8', p.title_cn = '一种基于铝合金与水反应的可控制氢装置', p.title_en = 'A kind of the aluminum alloy to react with the water based on controllable hydrogen production device', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种基于铝合金与水反应的可控制氢装置，水仓(1)和合金仓(2)分别通过管道和阀门连接反应仓(4)，中间水仓(3)通过管道连接到所述的反应仓(4)的底部，所述的反应仓(4)内装备有水平放置的反应网(401)，所述的反应网(401)的空隙间距小于合金小球的直径，所述的反应仓(4)底部通过管道和阀门连接废液仓(5)，所述的反应仓(4)的顶部通过管道和减压阀(41)连接有耗氢装置(6)。合金仓内有合金小球，可与水反应产生氢气。反应仓装配有反应网，能够与中间水仓一起调节产氢速率。本发明装置结构简单，利用自身压力来进行氢气发生和产氢速率的调节，无需消耗额外能源，且无需配备氢气储存装置。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention discloses a controllable hydrogen device based on aluminum alloy-water reaction. A water bin (1) and an alloy bin (2) are connected with a reaction bin respectively through pipelines and valves;  an intermediate water bin (3) is connected to the bottom of the reaction bin (4) through a pipeline;  reaction meshes (401),  which are horizontally arranged,  are arranged in the reaction bin (4);  the interval between every two reaction meshes (401) is less than the diameter of the alloy balls;  the bottom of the reaction bin (4) is connected with a waste liquid bin (5) through a pipeline and a valve;  and the top of the reaction bin (4) is connected with a hydrogen consumption device (6) through a pipeline and a pressure relief valve (41). The alloy balls are filled in the alloy bin and can react with water to generate hydrogen. The reaction meshes are assembled to the reaction bin and can regulate the hydrogen production rate together with the intermediate water bin. The controllable hydrogen device is simple in structure,  and can implement hydrogen production and hydrogen production rate regulation by using the self pressure without consuming additional energy or using any hydrogen storage device.', p.application_date = '2014-09-15 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN104276541B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/08', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201610052416.7'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201610052416.7', p.title_cn = '一种用于部分氧化系统的氮气无循环升温装置', p.title_en = 'Nitrogen non-circulating heating device for partial oxidation system', p.abstract_cn = '一种用于部分氧化系统的氮气无循环升温装置。本发明涉及一种升温装置，具体涉及一种用于部分氧化系统的氮气无循环升温装置。本发明为解决现有甲醇生产装置在部分氧化工序升温过程中由于停车造成的能源浪费及产量减少的问题。一种用于部分氧化系统的氮气无循环升温装置中的氮气输送管道通过第一连接管道由前至后依次穿过原料气预热器、混合气预热器、加热炉和转化炉，转化炉的排气端连接有废热锅炉，废热锅炉的排气端连接有第二连接管道，第二连接管道由前至后依次穿过混合气预热器、锅炉给水预热器、原料气预热器、除盐水预热器和水冷器，水冷器的排气端与分离器连接，分离器的排气端上设有放空阀。本发明用于氮气升温。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a heating device,  in particular to a nitrogen non-circulating heating device for a partial oxidation system. The problem that due to parking,  in the partial oxidation procedure of an existing methanol production device,  energy waste and yield decrease are caused is solved. A nitrogen conveying pipeline in the nitrogen non-circulating heating device sequentially penetrates through a raw material gas preheater,  a mixed gas preheater,  a heating furnace and a reformer from front to back through a first connecting pipeline. The exhaust end of the reformer is connected with a waste heat boiler. The exhaust end of the waste heat boiler is connected with a second connecting pipeline. The second connecting pipeline sequentially penetrates through the mixed gas preheater,  a boiler water supply preheater,  the raw material gas preheater,  a demineralized water preheater and a water cooler from front to back. The exhaust end of the water cooler is connected with a separator. The exhaust end of the separator is provided with an emptying valve. The heating device is used for nitrogen heating.', p.application_date = '2016-01-26 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105439086A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/36', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201410398121.6'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201410398121.6', p.title_cn = '一种生产电子级氢气的方法和装置', p.title_en = 'Method and apparatus for production of electronic grade hydrogen gas', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种生产电子级氢气的方法和装置，该方法包括以下步骤：(1)将多晶硅生产中的尾气经过处理后得到的纯度为99.808～99.945％的氢气通过活性炭吸附剂进行吸附；(2)使用含有氢氧化钠和高锰酸钾的水溶液进行淋洗，得到电子级氢气。本发明中得到了纯度为99.9999％以上的电子级氢气，完全除掉了多晶硅生产中的尾气经过处理后得到的纯度为99.808～99.945％的氢气中的氯化氢、氯化硼、氯化磷、磷烷、CH3BCl2、(CH3)2PH等杂质，氢气净化效率高，将多晶硅生产中无法生产高纯多晶硅的废氢气净化后，变废为宝转化成高价值的电子级氢气。', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention discloses a method and an apparatus for the production of electronic grade hydrogen gas,  and the method comprises the following steps :  (1) tail gas of the production of polysilicon is treated to obtain hydrogen gas with a purity of 99.808-99.945%,  and the hydrogen gas with the purity of 99.808-99.945% is adsorbed by an activated carbon adsorption agent;  and (2) an aqueous solution containing sodium hydroxide and potassium permanganate is used for rinsing to obtain the electronic grade hydrogen gas. The electronic grade hydrogen gas with a purity of 99.9999% can be obtained,  hydrogen chloride,  boron trichloride,  phosphoric chloride,  phosphorane,  CH3BCl2,  (CH3) 2PH other impurities in the hydrogen gas with the purity of 99.808-99.945% obtained by treatment of the tail gas of the production of polysilicon can be completely removed,  hydrogen purification efficiency is high,  and waste hydrogen gas,  in the production of polysilicon,  which cannot produce high-purity polysilicon is purified for turning the waste into the high-value electronic grade hydrogen gas.', p.application_date = '2014-08-13 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105439087A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/56', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201520880921.1'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201520880921.1', p.title_cn = '一种甲烷化学链重整制合成反应装置', p.title_en = 'Synthetic reaction unit of methane chemistry chain system of reforming', p.abstract_cn = '本实用新型公开了一种甲烷化学链重整制合成反应装置，包括反应器筒体，反应器筒体内设置有蜂窝状氧载体和若干个贯穿反应器筒体的蜂窝状氧载体孔道，反应器筒体一端设置有气体存储区，气体存储区设置有反应器气体入口，另一端设置有气体收集区，气体收集区设置有尾气出口。本实用新型的优点是：甲烷化学链重整反应装置与传统的水蒸汽或CO2重整相比，省去了水蒸气和纯氧制备环节，成本显著降低；易于实现反应的等温操作，而且避免了甲烷与气相氧直接接触可能发生爆炸的危险；不需要驱动催化剂颗粒在反应器中循环，能量损耗低，设备使用寿命长；蜂窝状氧载体在反应中具有蓄热功能，帮助反应器维持反应温度，有利于反应的稳定进行。', p.abstract_en = 'The utility model discloses a methane chemical chain reforming synthesis reaction device Comprises a reactor barrel,  wherein a honeycomb oxygen carrier and a plurality of honeycomb oxygen carrier pore passages penetrating through the reactor barrel are arranged in the reactor barrel; a gas storage area is arranged at one end of the reactor barrel; a reactor gas inlet is formed in the gas storage area; a gas collection area is arranged at the other end of the reactor barrel; and a tail gas outlet is formed in the gas collection area The utility model has the advantages that compared with the traditional water vapor or CO2 reforming,  the methane chemical chain reforming reaction device saves the preparation link of water vapor and pure oxygen,  and the cost is significantly reduced; it is easy to realize isothermal operation of reaction,  and avoids the danger of explosion caused by direct contact between methane and gas phase oxygen; the catalyst particles do not need to be driven to circulate in the reactor,  the energy loss is low,  and the service life of the equipment is long The honeycomb oxygen carrier has a heat storage function during the reaction,  which helps the reactor maintain the reaction temperature and is conducive to the stable progress of the reaction.', p.application_date = '2015-11-05 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN205115038U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201520852265.4'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201520852265.4', p.title_cn = '回收充装LNG杜瓦瓶时产生的BOG为制氢燃料的装置', p.title_en = 'BOG that recovery produced when filling dress LNG dewar bottle is device of hydrogen manufacturing fuel', p.abstract_cn = '本实用新型公开了一种回收充装LNG杜瓦瓶时产生的BOG为制氢燃料的装置，其中LNG槽车的液相出口通过调节阀连接杜瓦瓶的液相充装口，所述的LNG槽车的气相管口及杜瓦瓶的BOG气相管口并联后通过调节阀与缓冲罐的入口连接，所述的缓冲罐的出口通过调节阀与流量计的进口连接，所述的流量计的出口通过单向阀与裂解制氢转化炉的进口连接。通过使用本实用新型的装置能使充装LNG过程中放空的BOG气体得到有效的利用，创造了一定的经济效益。', p.abstract_en = 'The utility model discloses a BOG that recovery produced when filling dress LNG dewar bottle is device of hydrogen manufacturing fuel,  wherein the liquid phase export of LNG tank wagon connect the liquid phase filling hole of dewar bottle through the governing valve,  the parallelly connected back of the BOG gaseous phase mouth of pipe of the gaseous phase mouth of pipe and dewar bottle of LNG tank wagon through the entry linkage of governing valve with the buffer tank,  the export of buffer tank pass through the access connection of governing valve and flowmeter,  the export of flowmeter pass through the access connection of check valve and schizolysis hydrogen manufacturing reborner. Through using the utility model discloses a device enables to fill the BOG gas of adorning the unloading of LNG in -process and obtains effectual utilization,  has created certain economic benefits.', p.application_date = '2015-10-30 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN205115039U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/24', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'EP09157741'}) SET p.application_no = 'EP09157741', p.title_cn = '盒体用于从重整产物中除去硫化氢的吸附器系统', p.title_en = 'Cartridge adsorber system for removing hydrogen sulfide from reformate', p.abstract_cn = '除系统的H2S从含硫的重整产品包括永磁筒组件，其具有配件 通过重整产品流和一个可更换的药筒组件含有H2S吸附器元件与配件方便， 简单，可靠的配合和密封，与永久滤罐组件。 盒组件包括壳体可任选的全圆柱体或半圆柱体。所述钉仓组件 可以很容易地重新加载离线重新使用的墨盒部件与新鲜的吸附器元件。 优选地，所述吸附器元件离线的可再生用于重新使用。', p.abstract_en = 'A system for removal of H 2 S from sulfur-containing reformate comprising a permanent canister assembly having fittings for flow of reformate therethrough and a replaceable cartridge assembly containing an H 2 S adsorber element and fittings for convenient,  simple,  and reliable mating and sealing with the permanent canister assembly. The cartridge assembly comprises a housing that may be optionally a full cylinder or a semi-cylinder. The cartridge assembly may be easily reloaded off-line for re-use of the cartridge components with a fresh adsorber element. Preferably,  the adsorber element is also renewable off-line for re-use.', p.application_date = '2009-04-09 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'EP2110361B1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/50', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2013517827'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2013517827', p.title_cn = '氢生成装置及燃料电池系统', p.title_en = 'Hydrogen generator and fuel cell system', p.abstract_cn = '一种氢气发生器(1)包括 :  管式重整装置(2)，被配置为生成含氢气体的重整反应使用一种材料气体； 共减速机(4)被构造成减少所含的一氧化碳在含氢重整器中产生的气体； 管状加氢脱硫器(3)设置在重整器的外周和配置成去除硫化合物 材料中所含的气体； 和原料气体供给通道(331)，通过材料气体供应到加氢脱硫剂流。 所述原料气体供给通道被配置为与所述协处理器的减速机进行热交换， 和材料气体入口(341)的加氢脱硫装置中设有在端面更靠近 共减速机。', p.abstract_en = 'A hydrogen generator (1) includes :  a tubular reformer (2) configured to generate a hydrogen-containing gas by a reforming reaction using a material gas;  a CO reducer (4) configured to reduce carbon monoxide contained in the hydrogen-containing gas generated in the reformer;  a tubular hydro-desulfurizer (3) provided at an outer periphery of the reformer and configured to remove a sulfur compound contained in the material gas;  and a material gas supply passage(331) through which the material gas to be supplied to the hydro-desulfurizer flows. The material gas supply passage is configured to perform heat exchange with the CO reducer,  and a material gas inlet port (341) of the hydro-desulfurizer is provided at an end surface closer to the CO reducer.', p.application_date = '2012-04-20 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP5895241B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/32', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2012019159'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2012019159', p.title_cn = '制氢装置', p.title_en = 'Hydrogen production device', p.abstract_cn = '要解决的问题：使基板小型化； 高效地生产氢气； 以小且可选的排列形式连接多个数字； 以及在具有各种面积和各种形状的每个空间上，通过设置导电板，所述导电板与所述光催化剂侧的表面接触。解决方案：一种氢生产装置，其具有阴极部件和包括光催化剂的阳极部件，所述氢生产装置通过由所述光催化剂接收光来电解水，从而产生氢和氧，所述氢生产装置包括框架，所述框架保持所述阴极部件和所述阳极部件，并且在内部形成电解质存储空间，以及与所述阳极部件导电的电连接部分， 其中，所述阳极部件包括在一个表面上附着有所述光催化剂的基板和在一个表面上形成的导电膜，并且所述电连接部连接到导电板，所述导电板在所述基板的周边上与在一个表面上形成的所述导电膜接触。', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To miniaturize a substrate;  to produce hydrogen highly efficiently;  to connect a plurality of numbers in a small and optional arrangement form;  and to dispose on each space having various areas and various shapes,  by disposing a conductive plate having a contact with a surface on the photocatalyst side of the substrate.SOLUTION :  A hydrogen production apparatus having a cathode member,  and an anode member including a photocatalyst,  for electrolyzing water by receiving light by the photocatalyst to thereby generate hydrogen and oxygen,  includes a frame holding the cathode member and the anode member and forming an electrolyte storing space inside,  and an electric connection part conducting to the anode member,  wherein the anode member includes a substrate having the photocatalyst attached to one surface and a conductive film formed on one surface,  and the electric connection part is connected to a conductive plate having a contact with the conductive film formed on one surface on the periphery of the substrate.', p.application_date = '2012-01-31 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP5895562B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2011074882'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2011074882', p.title_cn = '混合型氢气生产·发电系统', p.title_en = 'The hybrid-type hydrogen production · power generation system', p.abstract_cn = '要解决的问题 : 本发明提供一种混合式制氢发电系统能够有效地收集从高温余热发电装置，有效的利用所收集通过高温热发电式发电装置，同时产生氢气将从存储/输送的有机氢化芳族化合物的化学氢化物中的方法氢气高温苛刻的地方设有式发电装置产生电能，通过消耗氢. 方案 : 在所述混合式制氢发电系统. 多管换热式固定床反应器上使用的均匀高分散型铂-氧化铝催化剂作为脱氢催化剂作为脱氢反应器. 所述脱氢反应器进行脱氢反应制氢的脱氢催化剂存在下氢化芳族化合物. 所得到的氢被引入的高温型发电装置进行发电. 采集的热能收集高温废气从高温型发电装置引入所述脱氢反应器盖的部分或全部脱氢反应所需的热量. A(c)2013. &耕作方法.', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To provide a hybrid type hydrogen production and power generation system capable of efficiently collecting exhaust heat from a high-temperature type power generation apparatus and effectively utilizing the collected heat by generating electric power by the high-temperature type power generation apparatus while producing hydrogen from a hydrogenerated aromatic compound stored/conveyed by an organic chemical hydride method in a hydrogen demanding place equipped with the high-temperature type power generation apparatus for generating electric power by consuming hydrogen.SOLUTION :  In the hybrid type hydrogen production and the power generation system,  a multitubular heat exchange type reactor using a fixed bed of a uniform high-dispersion type platinum-alumina catalyst as a dehydrogenation catalyst is used as a dehydrogenation reactor,  the dehydrogenation reactor produces hydrogen by performing a dehydrogenation reaction of a hydrogenerated aromatic compound in the presence of the dehydrogenation catalyst,  the obtained hydrogen is introduced into the high-temperature type power generation apparatus to perform power generation,  and collected heat collected from high-temperature exhaust gas from the high-temperature type power generation apparatus is introduced into the dehydrogenation reactor to cover a part or all of heat required for the dehydrogenation reaction.', p.application_date = '2011-03-30 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP5897811B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/26', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'BRPI102014018297'}) SET p.application_no = 'BRPI102014018297', p.title_cn = '一种适用于电解制氢操作台的反应器', p.title_en = 'reactor is applicable in command panel for producing hydrogen by electrolysis', p.abstract_cn = '摘要：“适用于电解制氢的反应器和面板指令”， 一种反应器(2)，其由无纺织物铁或其它具有相同特性的材料构成， 其中在生产反应器(2)中加入用于通过电解生产氢的A， 铁是承受比PVC大得多的压力的原料， 目前用于生产用于该应用的反应器的材料， 所述反应器(2)的尺寸可以增大，使得可以认识到它可以提高更大的性能和功率效率，增加气体的产量，由于所述物品是这种类型的反应器的材料，现在的方法是不可能的； 另外， 面板(8)命令设想使用至少一个电容器(9)， 从而也提高了能量(1)的值和循环效率， 所述面板(8)命令提供桥式整流二极管并产生不完整的波06， 当在所述面板(8)中连接振荡器和命令时，利用电容器(9)进入命令(8)，能量容量被改善，至少在电容器(9)的存在下振荡，提供更高的能量利用和有效的1/1。', p.abstract_en = 'abstract "reactor and panel command applicable in for producing hydrogen by electrolysis",  a reactor (2) nonwoven iron or other material with equivalent features,  wherein in to produce a reactor (2) to incorporate a for producing hydrogen by electrolysis,  iron is a feedstock which supports a pressure substantially larger than the PVC,  the material currently used in producing reactors for this application,  said reactor (2) and can be augmented in their dimensions such that it is recognizable promote a greater performance and power efficiency,  increasing the production of gas,  today\'s procedure is not possible due to the material from which the articles are reactors of this type;  in addition,  the panel (8) command envisions the utilization of at least a capacitor (9),  such that the value of the energy (1) to be elevated and cycling efficiency also,  said panel (8) command provides a bridge rectifier diodes and produces a wave 06 incomplete,  fact easily seen when connecting an oscillator in said panel (8) and command,  utilizing capacitors (9) into the command (8),  energy capacity is improved,  at least oscillate in the presence of capacitors (9),  providing higher energy exploitation and effective 1/1.', p.application_date = '2014-07-24 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'BR102014018297A2', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'BRPI1011532'}) SET p.application_no = 'BRPI1011532', p.title_cn = '过程产生链G的合成purificadapurificadaá克á将合成气链， 和，合成气更purificado的使用', p.title_en = 'PROCESS TO PRODUCE A CHAIN OF gáGÁ OF SYNTHESIS purificadaPURIFICADA OF A GAS CHAIN OF FEEDING SYNTHESIS,  AND,  USE OF THE SYNTHESIS GAS MORE PURIFICADO', p.abstract_cn = '一种生产纯化的合成气物流的方法从进料合成气物流除主成分 一氧化碳和氢气也硫化氢， HCN和/或COS， 该方法包括步骤 :  (a)使一个部分的进料合成气物流与水煤气变换催化剂的变换反应器 在水/蒸汽的存在下反应至少部分碳水/蒸汽的一氧化碳与水， 以得到一种经移位的合成气体流，其富含氢气和二氧化碳； (b)使另一部分进料气体流与水解催化剂在水存在下除去 HCN和/或COS，得到水解的合成气物流中HCN和/或COS； (c)除去H2S从转化的合成气物流和从水解的合成气物流接触， 这些气体流在H2S脱除区与含水碱性洗涤液，得到H 2S的合成气物流和硫化物包括含水物流； (d)使所述硫化物包括含水物流与硫化物-氧化细菌在生物反应器中氧的存在下 获得硫淤浆和再生的含水碱性洗涤液； (e)除去二氧化碳从贫H2S的合成气物流，得到纯化的合成气物流。', p.abstract_en = 'A process for producing a purified synthesis gas stream from a feed synthesis gas stream comprising besides the main constituents carbon monoxide and hydrogen also hydrogen sulphide,  HCN and/or COS,  the process comprising the steps of :  (a) contacting one part of the feed synthesis gas stream with a water gas shift catalyst in a shift reactor in the presence of water/steam to react at least part of the carbon water/steam monoxide with water,  to obtain a shifted synthesis gas stream enriched in hydrogen and in carbon dioxide;  (b) contacting another part of the feed gas stream with a hydrolysis catalyst in the presence of water to remove HCN and/or COS to obtain a hydrolysed synthesis gas stream depleted in HCN and/or COS;  (c) removing H 2 S from the shifted synthesis gas stream and from the hydrolysed synthesis gas stream by contacting these gas streams in a H 2 S-removal zone with an aqueous alkaline washing liquid to obtain a H 2 S-depleted synthesis gas stream and a sulphide-comprising aqueous stream;  (d) contacting the sulphide-comprising aqueous stream with sulphide-oxidizing bacteria in the presence of oxygen in a bioreactor to obtain a sulphur slurry and a regenerated aqueous alkaline washing liquid;  (e) removing carbon dioxide from the H 2 S-depleted synthesis gas stream,  to obtain the purified synthesis gas stream.', p.application_date = '2010-03-30 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'BRPI1011532A2', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/16', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'BR112012017482'}) SET p.application_no = 'BR112012017482', p.title_cn = '用于制造合成气的方法和燃烧器', p.title_en = 'PROCESS AND BURNER FOR THE SYNTHESIS GAS MANUFACTURE', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及通过液体或气体的部分氧化生产合成气， 在含氧氧化剂存在下的含碳燃料，其中燃料，氧化剂和调节剂分别供给燃烧器，并且其中燃料和调节剂在与氧化剂接触之前在燃烧器的混合室中混合。 为了降低燃烧器的负荷，特别是在具有瞬态条件的操作期间， 氧化剂通过燃烧器的出口中心引入燃烧室，燃料和缓和剂的混合物通过出口同心地围绕氧化剂引入燃烧室。', p.abstract_en = 'This invention relates to the production of synthesis gas by partial oxidation of liquid or gaseous,  carbonaceous fuel in the presence of an oxygen-containing oxidant,  wherein the fuel,  the oxidant and a moderator are separately supplied to a burner and wherein the fuel and the moderator are mixed in a mixing chamber of the burner,  before they are brought in contact with the oxidant. To reduce the load of the burner in particular during operation with transient conditions,  the oxidant is centrally introduced through an outlet opening of the burner into a combustion chamber and the mixture of fuel and moderator is introduced through the outlet opening into the combustion chamber concentrically around the oxidant.', p.application_date = '2010-11-12 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'BRPI1217482A2', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/36', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'ES10765566'}) SET p.application_no = 'ES10765566', p.title_cn = '改造原烟气流与可变', p.title_en = 'Reform primary flue gas stream with variable', p.abstract_cn = '一种方法公开了一种用于催化初级重整烃与蒸汽在升高的压力下通过分体 管反应器和燃烧室。 在分体式管系统，可以使用催化剂材料， 待重整的烃水蒸汽转换合成气。 分体式管系统由多个点火加热设施之间的分体式管包括多个 串联布置燃烧器，燃烧器产生主要的向下指向的火焰。 相关烧制设施提供与燃料和空气，与空气在被从相关送料器。 烟道气体从而演化穿过所述烧制室从上至下进入下部区域中 烧室中的水平设置的陶瓷烟气隧道彼此平行延伸并垂直于 竖直分流管和被分配给一个烧制设施。 烟气进入通过侧壁中的孔的烟气隧道。 烟气在燃烧室的出口通入热回收装置。 在每个烟气隧道的附加气体进入隧道的前侧， 在烟气流动方向， 所述含氧气体和非可燃气体， 使得附加气体经过烟气隧道在整个长度的燃烧室。 体积的附加气体通入到烟气隧道的调节。', p.abstract_en = 'A method is disclosed for catalytic primary reformation of hydrocarbons with steam at elevated pressure by means of a split tube reactor and a firing chamber. In the split tube system which can use a catalyst material,  hydrocarbons to be reformed are converted by water steam to synthesis gas. The split tube system is heated by a plurality of firing facilities between the split tubes which include a plurality of burners arranged in series,  the burners generating mainly downwardly directed flames. The relevant firing facilities are supplied with fuel and air,  with the air being withdrawn from the relevant feeders. The flue gas thus evolving passes through the firing chamber from top to bottom and enters in the lower area of the firing chamber into horizontally arranged ceramic flue gas tunnels extending in parallel to each other and perpendicular to the vertical split tubes and being allocated to one firing facility each. The flue gas enters through apertures in the lateral walls of the flue gas tunnels. The flue gas at the exit of the firing chamber is passed into heat recovery devices. In each flue gas tunnel an additional gas is fed into the tunnel\'s front side,  in flue gas flow direction,  wherein the gas containing oxygen and a non-combustible gas,  so that the additional gas passes the flue gas tunnels over the entire length of the firing chamber. The volume of the additional gas passed into the flue gas tunnels is regulated.', p.application_date = '2010-06-24 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'ES2564655T3', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'IN9961DELNP2015'}) SET p.application_no = 'IN9961DELNP2015', p.title_cn = '用于生产高纯度氢气气体的方法', p.title_en = 'METHOD FOR PRODUCING HIGH -PURITY HYDROGEN GAS', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种氢气制造方法包括以下步骤 : 将钢渣与H2O温度为150°C至500°C，降温步骤(a)的反应产物中分离氢气体的水蒸气和氢气收集部件。', p.abstract_en = 'The disclosure relates to a method for producing hydrogen gas comprising the steps of reacting steel slags with H20 at a temperature ranging from 150°C to 500°C,  cooling down the reaction product of step (a) to separate hydrogen gas from water steam and collecting hydrogen gas.', p.application_date = '2015-10-23 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'IN9961DELNP2015A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/08', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'DE202012013304'}) SET p.application_no = 'DE202012013304', p.title_cn = '用于生产氢的装置', p.title_en = 'Apparatus for production of hydrogen', p.abstract_cn = '用于生产高纯度氢气的原料气体与压力容器(1)和进料和出料线(4，5，6)用于粗煤气或贫氢的粗煤气，一个在内部空间(2)的压力容器(1)的内部区域(3)，完全暴露于内部空间(2)的压力容器(1)完成，该内区(3)至少部分地与半透水材料内部压力容器(2)的限定，其中所述半透材料是可渗透氢，用于沉积高纯度氢气从原料气，以及控制和调节单元，用于控制所述电源施加到半透膜，其特征在于 : 所述半透材料，至少在段，可加热该能量以控制由自动控制单元。', p.abstract_en = 'A method for obtaining highly pure hydrogen from a raw gas begins with heating and/or treating a semipermeable material made of metal or a metal alloy,  preferably,  conducting an electric current through the semipermeable material at the beginning of the method in order to increase the quantity of hydrogen passing through the material. A device for obtaining highly pure hydrogen from the raw gas includes a semipermeable material which forms a boundary between the interior of a pressure vessel and the outer region of the pressure vessel and which is permeable to hydrogen. The device is designed such that is can be heatable or treatable at least in sections,  in particular,  by means of electric energy.', p.application_date = '2012-09-27 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'DE202012013304U1', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/50', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'DE502010011088'}) SET p.application_no = 'DE502010011088', p.title_cn = '用于生产合成气的方法及燃烧器', p.title_en = 'METHOD AND BURNER FOR PRODUCING SYNTHESIS GAS', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及生产合成气的部分氧化液态或气态的，含碳燃料在存在含氧的氧化剂，其中所述燃料，氧化剂和调节剂分别供给到燃烧器，其中所述燃料和调节剂混合在燃烧器的混合室，在它们被带入与氧化剂接触。减少负载的燃烧器，特别在操作过程中与瞬态情况下，所述氧化剂为集中引入通过出口开口的燃烧器，燃烧室和混合物燃料和减速剂通过出口开口引入到燃烧室同心地围绕氧化剂。', p.abstract_en = 'This invention relates to the production of synthesis gas by partial oxidation of liquid or gaseous,  carbonaceous fuel in the presence of an oxygen-containing oxidant,  wherein the fuel,  the oxidant and a moderator are separately supplied to a burner and wherein the fuel and the moderator are mixed in a mixing chamber of the burner,  before they are brought in contact with the oxidant. To reduce the load of the burner in particular during operation with transient conditions,  the oxidant is centrally introduced through an outlet opening of the burner into a combustion chamber and the mixture of fuel and moderator is introduced through the outlet opening into the combustion chamber concentrically around the oxidant.', p.application_date = '2010-11-12 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'DE502010011088T2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/36', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'IDW00201100072'}) SET p.application_no = 'IDW00201100072', p.title_cn = '生物质生产低焦油合成气的方法及装置', p.title_en = 'The invention relates to a method and a device for producing low-tar synthetic gas from biomass', p.abstract_cn = '说明和描述了一种从生物质中生产低焦油合成气的方法和装置。生物质中生产合成气的方法暴露了高焦油含量或要求温度，使灰烧结成玻璃状的质量，从而不能用作矿物肥料。本发明的目的是为了避免这些缺点，并且高效率地生产高质量的合成气，通过根据本发明的方法，在合成气(15a)中的焦油含量在生物质(1)中被分为热解焦和热解气的流化床反应器(3)中，两者都被送入至少一个以上的流化床反应器(11)中，其中在较高的温度下对大部分无焦油的热解焦中的tar-焦油进行无灰熔点的催化分割。根据本发明的方法允许生产基本上不含焦油的合成气', p.abstract_en = 'A method and apparatus for producing low tar syngas from biomass is illustrated and described. Processes for the production of synthesis gas from biomass are exposed to high tar content or required temperatures,  causing the ash to sinter to glassy quality and thus not be useful as a mineral fertilizer. The object of the invention is to avoid these disadvantages,  And high-quality synthesis gas can be efficiently produced,  By the method according to the invention,  the tar content in the synthesis gas (15a) is separated in the biomass (1) into pyrolysis coke and pyrolysis gas in a fluidized bed reactor (3),  both of which are fed into at least one fluidized bed reactor (11),  wherein the tar-tar content in the majority of the tar-free pyrolysis coke is catalytically separated at an ash-free melting point at a higher temperature. The process according to the present invention allows for the production of a substantially tar-free synthesis gas', p.application_date = '2011-01-07 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'IDP000041501B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2014164904'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2014164904', p.title_cn = '脱氢的脱氢系统和操作该系统的方法', p.title_en = 'DEHYDROGENATION SYSTEM,  AND OPERATING METHOD OF DEHYDROGENATION SYSTEM', p.abstract_cn = '要解决的问题 : Org。通过控制或hydlide一种结构简单，能够管理的转化率脱氢的脱氢系统和提供一种操作气化系统的方法。方法 : 所述控制部(23)，其检测的检测部(25)基于所述出口的脱氢反应温度，供给到脱氢反应器30中供给量，供给到脱氢反应器30中供给热量，和，在脱氢反应器30中的至少一个的脱氢反应的反应压力。脱氢反应产物和转化率的有机氢化物的出口温度，由于是强的相关性，控制部分23，其检测的检测部(25)基于出口温度，转化率的状态可以轻松掌握。基于此，控制部分23，供给到所述脱氢反应器30，例如通过控制原料的供给量，可调节的转化率。选择的绘图 : 图。2', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To provide a dehydrogenation system and an operating method of the dehydrogenation system which are capable of controlling conversion ratio of an organic hydride by simpler configuration or control. SOLUTION :  A control part 23 controls at least one of a supply amount of materials to be supplied to a dehydrogenation reactor 30,  a supply amount of heat to be supplied to the dehydrogenation reactor 30,  and reaction pressure of dehydrogenation reaction in the dehydrogenation reactor 30 on the basis of the outlet temperature of a dehydrogenation reactant detected by a detection part 25. Because the outlet temperature of the dehydrogenation reactant and the conversion ratio of an organic hydride have strong correlation,  the control part 23 can easily grasp the state of the conversion ratio on the basis of the outlet temperature detected by the detection part 25. The control part 23 can consequently adjust the conversion ratio by controlling the supply amount or the like of materials to be supplied to the dehydrogenation reactor 30. SELECTED DRAWING :  Figure 2 COPYRIGHT :  (C)2016, JPO&INPIT', p.application_date = '2014-08-13 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP2016040217A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/26', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2014164905'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2014164905', p.title_cn = '脱氢系统，操作脱氢的系统和方法', p.title_en = 'DEHYDROGENATION SYSTEM AND OPERATION METHOD OF DEHYDROGENATION SYSTEM', p.abstract_cn = '要解决的问题 : 脱氢的脱氢催化剂劣化可以抑制系统。方法 : 控制部分23，原料供应部分(21)通过脱氢反应器3停止供给的材料，在氢气供应部分(22)的反应容器31由含氢气体和大气。在该状态下，控制部分23，脱氢反应条件下的反应器为3，脱氢反应氢化反应速率的速度变得大于夹持状态。因此，在反应容器31，和含氢气体中的氢气，剩余之间的脱氢产物氢进行反应。以这种方式，剩余的氢副产物，脱氢催化剂劣化，能够抑制。选择的绘图 : 图。2', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To provide a dehydrogenation system capable of suppressing deterioration of a dehydrogenation catalyst. SOLUTION :  A control unit 23 places the inside of a reaction vessel 31 into an atmosphere of hydrogen-containing gas through a hydrogen supply unit 22 when supply of raw materials to a dehydrogenation reactor 3 by a raw material supply unit 21 is stopped. In this state,  the control unit 23 maintains a condition of a hydrogenation reaction rate being larger than a dehydrogenation reaction rate as a reaction condition for the dehydrogenation reactor 3. Consequently,  hydrogenation reaction progresses between hydrogen in the hydrogen-containing gas and remaining dehydrogenated products in the reaction vessel 31. By hydrogenating the remaining dehydrogenated products in this manner,  deterioration of a dehydrogenation catalyst can be suppressed. SELECTED DRAWING :  Figure 2 COPYRIGHT :  (C)2016, JPO&INPIT', p.application_date = '2014-08-13 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP2016040218A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/26', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2015542815'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2015542815', p.title_cn = '4冲程柴油发动机制动机构回收从驱动的车辆的动能和/或潜在的能量，用于生成燃料含氢气体的方法，用于执行这样的方法和系统', p.title_en = '4 stroke diesel engine brake mechanism is recovered from a vehicle driven by kinetic and/or potential energy,  for generating a fuel gas containing hydrogen method,  useful for the execution of such a method and system', p.abstract_cn = '在减速阶段4冲程柴油发动机制动回收Jacobs设置从驱动车辆的动能和/或用于产生氢气的势能从燃料。这种方法，以下步骤，即a)将预热的蒸汽流动阶段，B)预热的碳和氢作为供应源的至少一种化学物质1，使气体流量从阶段，c)级)的碳和氢从供应源的至少一种化学物质作为一种气体流量，大约1，步骤b)和蒸气流从混合物中。选择的绘图 : 图。1', p.abstract_en = 'A method for producing a hydrogen gaseous fuel from kinetic and/or potential energy recovered from a vehicle powered by a four stroke Diesel engine fitted with a Jacobs engine brake during a deceleration stage. Such a method comprises the following steps :  a) providing a preheated steam flow;  b) providing a gas flow from at least one chemical species used as preheated carbon and hydrogen source;  c) mixing the gas flow from at least one chemical species used as carbon and hydrogen source from step a) with the steam flow from step b);  d) reacting the mixture from step c) in the catalytic bed of a reforming reactor,  heated by high temperature air from the compression stage of the Diesel engine acting as engine brake upon deceleration,  producing an outlet synthesis gas flow which contains hydrogen;  e) causing water to condense in the outlet synthesis gas flow which contains hydrogen,  producing a water-free synthesis gas flow,  and f) storing the synthesis gas flow obtained at step e) in a reservoir for its subsequent use during an acceleration stage of the vehicle. A system useful to implement the method for recovering kinetic and/or potential energy from a vehicle powered by a four stroke Diesel engine fitted with a Jacobs engine brake during a deceleration stage.', p.application_date = '2013-11-15 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP2016508938A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2015556505'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2015556505', p.title_cn = '燃料供给站中的氢的质量识别', p.title_en = 'The quality of hydrogen in fuel supply station identification', p.abstract_cn = '本发明，燃料供给站上分布氢气体在该方法中，分配器之前，至少一个第一划分的流的氢料流2包括，在这种情况下，至少一个所述流1，氢纯化步骤中被净化，该方法。在进一步的形式中，本发明，系统分配气态氢。选择绘制 : 图。2', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention provides a process for dispensing gaseous hydrogen at a refueling station comprising before dispensing dividing an initial hydrogen stream into at least two streams,  wherein at least one of the streams is purified in a hydrogen purification step. In a further aspect the invention provides a system for dispensing gaseous hydrogen.', p.application_date = '2014-02-07 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP2016508949A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'MN1020130005140'}) SET p.application_no = 'MN1020130005140', p.title_cn = '合成天然气的制造方法。', p.title_en = 'Method for manufacturing synthetic natural gas.', p.abstract_cn = '简要信息本发明适用于合成天然气(SNG)的生产，具体取决于化工部门。具体地，合成气体(SNG)的合成涉及引入燃料和除尘器产生的合成气体的第一甲烷合成；气体的唯一部分是与水煤气反应，跳过剩余部分；以及通过丙酮气体从流体中释放出的丙酮气体的合成，结合向第二甲烷合成反应中通入合成气体，可以控制甲烷合成反应的热量，延长催化剂的利用时间。', p.abstract_en = 'Brief information This invention applies to the production of synthetic natural gas (SNG) depending on the chemical sector. Specifically,  synthesis of synthetic gas (SNG) involves the introduction of first methane synthesis of synthetic gas generated by fuel and dust collectors;  The only part of the gas is to react with water gas reaction and skip the remaining part;  and the synthesis of acetone gas released from the fluid through the acetone gas,  combined with the introduction of synthetic gas into the second methane synthesis reaction,  and the heat of the methane synthesis reaction can be controlled and prolonged the catalyst utilization time.', p.application_date = '2011-12-27 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'MN100004399B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/32', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14785088'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14785088', p.title_cn = '从能源、CO2和H2O生产液态烃的方法', p.title_en = 'METHODS FOR PRODUCTION OF LIQUID HYDROCARBONS FROM ENERGY,  CO2 AND H2O', p.abstract_cn = '能量上传方法，将能量转移到液态烃中，包括步骤a)从二氧化碳、H2O和能量制备氢气和一氧化碳的混合物，b)使所述混合物反应形成液态烃，c)将热能从形成的液态烃转移到二氧化碳和/或H2O。', p.abstract_en = 'Energy uploading method transferring energy into liquid hydrocarbon comprising the steps a) preparing a mixture of hydrogen and carbon monoxide from carbon dioxide,  H2O and energy,  b) reacting said mixture to form liquid hydrocarbon,  c) transferring heat energy from the formed liquid hydrocarbon to the carbon dioxide and or the H2O.', p.application_date = '2014-04-10 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US20160083658A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/12', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WOEP15067143'}) SET p.application_no = 'WOEP15067143', p.title_cn = '氢气合成方法', p.title_en = 'PROCESS FOR HYDROGEN SYNTHESIS', p.abstract_cn = '本文提供了用于合成氢气(H2)温和的水热条件下的反应器中，在120a°C之间的温度和240a°C，压力低于70巴。该方法包括接触金属铁(fe0)或Fe(L1)含有化合物与含水组合物包含碳酸根离子；并让金属铁或Fe(L1)的化合物与水反应，从而获得磁铁矿和氢气。', p.abstract_en = 'Provided herein are processes for the synthesis of hydrogen gas (H2) in a reactor under mild hydrothermal conditions,  at a temperature between 120° C and 240° C and a pressure below 70 bar. The processes comprise contacting metallic iron (Fe0) or a Fe(ll) containing compound with an aqueous composition comprising carbonate ions;  and letting the metallic iron or Fe(ll) containing compound react with water,  thereby obtaining magnetite and hydrogen gas.', p.application_date = '2015-07-27 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016041672A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/08', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201511016950.4'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201511016950.4', p.title_cn = '潜水式镁镓合金制氢装置工作方法', p.title_en = 'Underwater-type magnesium-gallium-alloy hydrogen production device working method', p.abstract_cn = '潜水式镁镓合金制氢装置工作方法属于新能源、减少温室气体排放及军事领域，减少古生物能源的使用，减缓南极、北极及全球永久冰盖消溶的速度，减小厄尼诺现象对人类危害，可以将潜水式镁镓合金制氢装置工作方法制氢所得到的新能源来满足全人类在经济发展中对能源的依赖，在军事领域可以用氢氧燃料电站为军用设备服务，此项制氢及氢使用过程都不会有温室气体排放，从而达到减少温室气体排放、减缓南极、北极和全球永久性冰盖消溶及海平面上升速度，氢是非常清洁的能源，美国最新发明了铝镓合金制氢技术，使用80％的镁加上20％的镓(无需高纯度)的合金，就能使镁在常温下极快与水发生化学反应，因此开辟了制氢新路径。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention provides an underwater-type magnesium-gallium-alloy hydrogen production device working method and belongs to the new energy,  greenhouse gas emission reduction and military fields. Usage of palaeontological energy is reduced,  the melting speed of the Antarctic Pole,  the Arctic Pole and global permanent ice covers is alleviated,  damage of El Nino phenomena to human body is reduced,  new energy obtained through hydrogen production through the provided working method can meet energy dependence of human body in the economic development,  and an oxy-hydrogen fuel power station can be employed to provide service for military devices in the military field. There is no greenhouse gas emission during the hydrogen production and hydrogen usage processes,  and therefore greenhouse gas emission reduction and alleviation of the Antarctic Pole,  the Arctic Pole and global permanent ice covers melting and sea level rise speeds are achieved. Hydrogen is very clean energy,  the magnesium-gallium-alloy hydrogen production technology is invented by America lately,  alloy of 80% of magnesium and 20% of gallium (high purity is not needed) is employed,  magnesium can be subjected to a chemical reaction with water rapidly at a room temperature,  and therefor a new hydrogen production path is developed.', p.application_date = '2015-12-29 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105417495A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/08', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201520876691.1'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201520876691.1', p.title_cn = '一种高效节能氨分解设备', p.title_en = 'Energy -efficient ammonia decomposition equipment', p.abstract_cn = '本实用新型公开了一种高效节能氨分解设备，包括设备主体，所述设备主体上设有进口阀门、汽化器、换热器、炉膛和出口阀门，所述炉膛内设有柱状的炉胆，炉胆内装镍触媒，所述炉胆的顶端和底端都为椭圆封头，炉胆顶端或底端还设有进出口管，所述进出口管的管径小于炉胆的外径，所述炉胆外侧还设有螺旋状的电热丝，所述电热丝以所述炉胆的轴心为中心均匀环绕于所述炉胆外侧并与所述炉胆的外壁保持一定的间隙，本实用新型可高效节能地分解液氨。', p.abstract_en = 'The utility model discloses an energy -efficient ammonia decomposition equipment,  comprises an equipment body,  last imported valve,  vaporizer,  heat exchanger,  furnace and the outlet valve of being equipped with of equipment principal,  be equipped with cylindrical stove courage in the furnace,  the stove courage installs the nickel catalyst inside,  the top of stove courage and bottom all are the elipse head,  and stove courage top or bottom still are equipped with the business turn over oral siphon,  the pipe diameter of business turn over oral siphon is lighter than the external diameter of stove courage,  the stove courage outside still is equipped with spiral helicine heating wire,  the heating wire with the axle center of stove courage be the center even encircle in the stove courage outside and with the outer wall of stove courage keeps certain clearance,  the utility model discloses can decompose liquid ammonia energy -efficiently.', p.application_date = '2015-11-06 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN205099348U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201520769663.X'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201520769663.X', p.title_cn = '氢气发生溶氢装置', p.title_en = 'Hydrogen device takes place to dissolve for hydrogen', p.abstract_cn = '本实用新型涉及氢气发生溶氢装置，包括以下部分：a.氢气发生部，为一端部具有开口的柱形腔体，在该柱形腔体内，沿内壁密封设置有环形框架，环形框架表面覆盖有纳米透气薄膜，该柱形腔体内未开口一端与纳米透气薄膜形成闭合空间；b.容器部，为一端部具有开口的柱形腔体，容器部的柱形腔体截面形状与氢气发生部的柱形腔体截面形状相同。容器部的开口与发生部的开口配合对接密封，连接成一个密封柱形空间，环形框架固定在所述的氢气发生部中或沿该密封柱形空间的内壁滑动。本实用新型使用范围广、装置可大可小，使用灵活；溶氢浓度高，现做现用、携带方便。', p.abstract_en = 'The utility model relates to a hydrogen device takes place to dissolve for hydrogen,  including following part :  A. Hydrogen emergence portion,  for a tip has open -ended cylindricality cavity,  in this cylindricality cavity,  along the sealed ring frame frame that is provided with of inner wall,  ring frame frame surface covering has the nanometer film of breathe freely,  opening one end and the nanometer thin film formation closed space of breathing freely not in this cylindricality cavity,  B. Container portion,  for a tip has an open -ended cylindricality cavity,  the cylindricality cavity cross sectional shape of container portion is the same with the cylindricality cavity cross sectional shape of hydrogen emergence portion. The opening of container portion is sealed with the opening of emergence portion cooperation butt joint,  connects into a sealed cylindrical space,  and the ring frame frame is fixed hydrogen emergence portion in or slide along this sealed cylindrical space\'s inner wall. The utility model discloses application range is wide,  the device is changeable,  uses in a flexible way,  dissolve the hydrogen concentration height,  be existing usefulness,  convenient to carry at present.', p.application_date = '2015-09-30 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN205099349U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/06', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201520883826.7'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201520883826.7', p.title_cn = '合成氨装置二段炉和换热式转化炉余热回收利用系统', p.title_en = 'Synthetic ammonia installation two -stage process stove and heat transfer formula reborner waste heat recovery utilize system', p.abstract_cn = '本实用新型公开了一种合成氨装置二段炉和换热式转化炉余热回收利用系统，所述二段炉和换热式转化炉的夹套出水口通过管道与换热器的夹套水进口相连，所述换热器的冷空气进口与空气压缩机的富氧空气出口相连，所述换热器的热空气出口与空气加热器相连，所述空气加热器与加热炉的进口相连，所述加热炉的出口与二段炉进气口相连；所述换热器的夹套水出口与夹套水冷却器的热水进口相连，所述夹套水冷却器的夹套水出口与夹套水槽相连，所述夹套水冷却器的冷侧进口与循环水管相连。经过本实用新型改进后，将夹套水的余热用于预热富氧空气，大大降低了生产过程中的低压蒸汽和天然气的消耗，降低成本。', p.abstract_en = 'The utility model discloses a synthetic ammonia installation two -stage process stove and heat transfer formula reborner waste heat recovery utilize system,  the clamp cover delivery port of two -stage process stove and heat transfer formula reborner passes through the pipeline and imports continuously with the jacket water (J. W. ) of heat exchanger,  the cold air intlet of heat exchanger links to each other with the export of air compressor\'s oxygen -enriched air,  the hot -air export of heat exchanger links to each other with air heater,  air heater links to each other with the import of heating furnace,  the export of heating furnace links to each other with two -stage process stove air inlet,  the jacket water (J. W. ) export of heat exchanger links to each other with the hot water import who presss from both sides cover water chiller,  the jacket water (J. W. ) export of pressing from both sides cover water chiller links to each other with the jacket water (J. W. ) groove,  the cold side import of pressing from both sides cover water chiller links to each other with circulating pipe. The process the utility model discloses improve the back,  be used for preheating the oxygen -enriched air with the waste heat of jacket water (J. W. ),  greatly reduced low pressure steam and the consumption of the natural gas in the production process,  reduce cost.', p.application_date = '2015-11-09 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN205099350U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/34', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201520805075.7'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201520805075.7', p.title_cn = '一种叠片式重整制氢器', p.title_en = 'Lamination formula reformation hydrogen manufacturing ware', p.abstract_cn = '本实用新型公开了一种叠片式重整制氢器，包括上盖板(10)、垫片(30)、催化板(20)、隔板(40)、下盖板(50)，催化板表面涂覆有催化剂层并且对角两个顶点上分别设置有通孔，催化板与垫片间隔层叠安装，垫片上有曲折镂空的流道，从而在催化板表面形成固定间隙，催化剂层相互之间不接触，完全避免互相挤压产生粉尘，解决了现有技术重整制氢设备所产氢气携带粉尘的问题，主要应用于重整制氢设备，特别是与燃料电池结合使用的现场重整制氢设备。', p.abstract_en = 'The utility model discloses a lamination formula reformation hydrogen manufacturing ware,  including upper cover plate (10),  gasket (30),  catalysis board (20),  baffle (40),  lap down (50),  catalysis board surface coating has the catalyst layer and be provided with the through -hole on two summits at the diagonal angle respectively,  catalysis board and the range upon range of installation in gasket interval,  the runner that has tortuous fretwork on the gasket,  thereby at catalysis board surface formation fixed interval,  the catalyst layer is the contactless each other,  avoid extrudeing mutually no powder completely,  the problem of the prior art reformation hydrogen that hydrogen preparation equipment is produced carry the dust is solved,  mainly be applied to reformation hydrogen preparation equipment,  the on -the -spot reformation hydrogen preparation equipment who especially uses coordinately with fuel cell.', p.application_date = '2015-10-17 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN205099351U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'EP04028601'}) SET p.application_no = 'EP04028601', p.title_cn = '氢气发生器，氢气发生器的关闭操作的方法，以及燃料电池系统', p.title_en = 'Hydrogen generator,  method of shutting down operation of hydrogen generator,  and fuel cell system', p.abstract_cn = '本发明的氢气发生器包括 : 一种用于产生富氢气体的重整器从进料气体和水的反应使用重整催化剂体和将其发送；从出口端口；物料进料系统，用于进料的进料气体以所述重整器；一种燃烧器，用于提供，所述的重整催化剂体，产生的热量将燃料气体与空气和燃烧；和空气供给系统用于将空气供应到燃烧器；其中，在使用重整器的内部吹扫关闭氢气发生器中的进料气体，供给的空气的量增加了扑灭火焰的燃烧器，和发出吹扫气体从吹扫出口与空气的混合和被稀释在燃烧器和外排。', p.abstract_en = 'A hydrogen generator of the invention includes :  a reformer for generating a hydrogen-rich gas from a feed gas and water by a reaction using a reforming catalyst body and sending it out from an outlet port;  a material feed system for feeding the feed gas to the reformer;  a burner for supplying,  to the reforming catalyst body,  heat generated by mixing a fuel gas with air and burning it;  and an air supply system for supplying air to the burner;  wherein,  when purging an interior of the reformer using the feed gas in shutting down the hydrogen generator,  an amount of the air supplied is increased to put out a flame of the burner,  and a purge gas sent out from the outlet port by the purging is mixed and diluted with the air in the burner and is discharged outside.', p.application_date = '2004-12-02 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'EP1538126B1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 2, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'EP11734202'}) SET p.application_no = 'EP11734202', p.title_cn = '合成气生产，通过使用膜技术', p.title_en = 'SYNGAS PRODUCTION THROUGH THE USE OF MEMBRANE TECHNOLOGIES', p.abstract_cn = '污染的天然气流(11)的具有显著量的二氧化碳可以有效和更经济地处理，以创建合成气(16)。可用的源(1)的烟气，否则分散到大气中结合有这种含CO2天然气流(11)使得该方法更经济，高效的通过多个进料流的创建(14，27，34)结合，以将复合接近相等的甲烷和二氧化碳的混合物到等离子体反应器(15)或将产生合成气等。当与费-托合成反应器(40)，全过程提供了一种特别高效和经济的方法，用于生产合成液态烃。', p.abstract_en = 'Streams (11) of natural gas contaminated with significant amounts of carbon dioxide can be efficiently and economically processed to create Syngas (16). An available source (1) of flue gas that might otherwise be dispersed into the atmosphere in conjunction with such a CO2-laden natural gas stream (11) renders the process even more economical and efficient through the creation of multiple feedstreams (14,  27,  34) that are combined to deliver a composite near equal mixture of methane and CO2 to a plasma reactor (15) or the like that will generate Syngas. When coupled with a Fischer-Tropsch reactor (40),  the overall process provides a particularly efficient and economical process for producing synthetic liquid hydrocarbons.', p.application_date = '2011-06-29 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'EP2590894B1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/34', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'BRPI1004550'}) SET p.application_no = 'BRPI1004550', p.title_cn = '组合物，方法和系统用于产生氢气的生产方法', p.title_en = 'COMPOSITION,  METHODS AND SYSTEMS FOR HYDROGEN GENERATION AND METHOD TO PRODUCE', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及制氢的组合物和方法涉及从水中的金属颗粒与水反应有效量的活化剂存在下。尤其，本发明涉及组合物和方法中反应而产生氢的金属颗粒选自自铝(Al)，镁(Mg)，硼(B)，硅(Si)，铁(Fe)，用水和锌(Zn)，在有效量的活化剂催化剂的存在下，其中活化剂选自所组成的组 : 碱金属，碱土金属，碱金属氢化物，碱土金属氢化物，碱金属氢氧化物和碱土金属氢氧化物。', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention relates to compositions and methods for producing hydrogen from water involving reacting metal particles with water in the presence of an effective amount of activator. In particular the invention pertains to compositions and methods for producing hydrogen upon reaction of metal particles selected from the group consisting of aluminum (Al),  magnesium (Mg),  boron (B),  silicon (Si),  iron (Fe),  and zinc (Zn) with water,  in the presence of an effective amount of an activator catalyst,  wherein the activator is selected from the group consisting of :  alkali metals,  earth alkali metals,  hydrides of alkali metals,  hydrides of earth alkali metals,  hydroxides of alkali metals,  and hydroxides of earth alkali metals.', p.application_date = '2010-01-05 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'BRPI1004550A2', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/08', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CA2629078'}) SET p.application_no = 'CA2629078', p.title_cn = 'Pt，Re的工艺条件，双金属水煤气转换催化剂', p.title_en = 'PROCESS CONDITIONS FOR PT-RE BIMETALLIC WATER GAS SHIFT CATALYSTS', p.abstract_cn = '操作条件用于产生氢的水-气变换反应已经发现减少老化Pt，Re双金属水-气转换催化剂的应用。所述水煤气转换反应操作在温度约150A°到450a°C，进料气体含有至多大约20体积%CO，蒸汽和气体空速的饲料气体约4500至50～-1h-1，降低催化剂的老化通过控制温度，体积%CO，气体空速以满足式 : ΔT(50)20h=(5.51+4.40×10-5×[空速X Pt(克/升)/7.4]-0.015×T±0.049X%Co)2-1.65，其中T是温度为摄氏度，[%Co]CO含量的干法工艺，无水蒸汽，在体积%，空速是，气时空速为每升含7.4克Pt催化剂的催化剂。ΔT(50)～H为差在50%一氧化碳转化率随温度的公式T(50)老化20小时-T(50)新鲜，ΔT(50)20h小于7，', p.abstract_en = 'Operating conditions for generating hydrogen by the water-gas shift reaction have been found which reduce the aging of Pt-Re bimetallic water-gas shift catalysts. The water gas shift reaction is operated at a temperature of about 150.degree. to 450.degree.C,  a feed gas comprising up to about 20 vol% CO and steam and a gas space velocity of the feed gas of about 4500 to 50, 000h-1 and reducing catalyst aging by controlling temperature,  vol% CO,  gas space velocity so as to meet the formula :  .DELTA.T(50)20h = (5.51 +4.40 x 10 -5 x [VHSV x Pt(g/l)/7.4] - 0.015 x T + 0.049 x % CO)2 - 1.65,  wherein T is temperature in degrees C,  [%CO] is the CO content of the dry process,  without steam,  in volume percent,  VHSV is the gas hourly space velocity for a catalyst containing 7.4 g Pt per liter of catalyst and .DELTA.T(50)20h is the difference of the temperatures at 50% CO conversion following the equation T(50) aged 20 hours-T (50) fresh,  and .DELTA.T(50)20h is less than 7.0.', p.application_date = '2006-12-04 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CA2629078C', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/16', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14597240'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14597240', p.title_cn = '费托合成废气的回收方法', p.title_en = 'Method for recycling exhaust gases from Fischer-Tropsch synthesis', p.abstract_cn = '一种费托合成废气回收方法。 该方法包括 : 1)向变换反应器中通入原料气进行水煤气变换反应，收集变换气； 2)将变换气导入费托合成装置，得到烃类燃料和废气，部分废气作为循环气体返回； 3)将废气的另一部分引入甲烷化反应器，允许废气的该部分与水蒸气之间发生甲烷化反应；4)将甲烷化反应产生的混合气体产物引入甲烷重整反应器；5)将甲烷重整反应产生的氢气和一氧化碳输送到气体分离器，分离氢气并获得包括二氧化碳的混合气体；以及6)将包括二氧化碳的混合气体返回到甲烷重整反应器。', p.abstract_en = 'A method for recycling exhaust gas from Fischer-Tropsch synthesis. The method includes :  1) introducing raw gas to a shift reactor to conduct a water-gas shift reaction,  and collecting shift gas;  2) introducing the shift gas to a Fischer-Tropsch synthesis device to yield a hydrocarbon fuel and exhaust gas,  returning part of the exhaust gas as recycle gas;  3) introducing another part of the exhaust gas to a methanation reactor,  allowing a methanation reaction to happen between the part of the exhaust gas and water vapor;  4) introducing a mixed gas product from the methanation reaction to a methane reforming reactor;  5) transporting the hydrogen and carbon monoxide resulting from the methane reforming reaction to a gas separator,  separating the hydrogen and obtaining a mixed gas including carbon dioxide;  and 6) returning the mixed gas including carbon dioxide to the methane reforming reactor.', p.application_date = '2015-01-15 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9290383B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/16', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US13902175'}) SET p.application_no = 'US13902175', p.title_cn = '乙炔和合成气的制备方法', p.title_en = 'Process for preparing acetylene and synthesis gas', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种用氧气部分氧化烃制备乙炔和合成气的方法。 该方法包括分别预热然后混合含烃的第一输入流和含氧的第二输入流， 经由燃烧器块将所述第一输入流和所述第二输入流供应到点火空间， 淬火获得的裂解气以产生工艺水物流和产品气物流，通过与冷却水直接热交换在冷却塔中冷却产品气物流，在静电过滤器中耗尽碳烟，合并所有工艺水物流并通过碳烟通道，在一级闪蒸容器中通过部分汽化对合并的工艺水物流进行清洁操作以获得清洁的工艺水物流，并将清洁的工艺水物流再循环到工艺中。', p.abstract_en = 'A process for preparing acetylene and synthesis gas by partial oxidation of hydrocarbons with oxygen,  is disclosed. The process consists of separately preheating and then mixing a first input stream containing a hydrocarbon and a second input stream containing oxygen,  supplying the first input stream and the second input stream via a burner block to a firing space,  quenching a cracking gas obtained to produce a process water stream and a product gas stream,  cooling the product gas stream in a cooling column by direct heat exchange with cooling water,  depleting soot in an electrostatic filter,  combining all process water streams and passing through soot channels,  subjecting the combined process water stream to a cleaning operation by partial vaporization in a one-stage flash vessel to obtain a cleaned process water stream,  and recycling the cleaned process water stream into the process.', p.application_date = '2013-05-24 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9290384B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14200809'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14200809', p.title_cn = '硫化氢转化制氢', p.title_en = 'Hydrogen sulfide conversion to hydrogen', p.abstract_cn = '一种用于从气体和由此产生的气体中基本上消除污染物的方法和系统。', p.abstract_en = 'A process and system for substantially eliminating contaminants from a gas and a gas produced therefrom.', p.application_date = '2014-03-07 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9290386B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 8, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US13745858'}) SET p.application_no = 'US13745858', p.title_cn = '生物质气化的方法和系统', p.title_en = 'Method and system for gasification of biomass', p.abstract_cn = '一种生物质气化方法。 a)粉碎生物质，将生物质送入气化炉，同时向气化炉中喷射过热水蒸气，控制气化炉工作温度在1200～1600°C，生物质与过热水蒸气接触，干燥，分离挥发性物质，热解，气化生物质产生粗合成气和灰； b)将粗合成气送入喷雾塔，通过喷水将粗合成气急冷至650-800°C，从粗合成气中冷凝炉渣和焦油，溶解并除去碱金属氧化物和部分酸性气体，得到初级合成气；c)冷却、除尘、脱酸、干燥初级合成气，将初级合成气转化为清洁合成气。', p.abstract_en = 'A method for gasifying biomass. The method includes :  a) grinding the biomass,  feeding the biomass into a gasifier while spraying superheated water vapor into the gasifier,  controlling the gasifier at an operating temperature of 1200-1600° C.,  contacting the biomass with the superheated water vapor,  desiccating,  separating volatile matters,  pyrolyzing,  and gasifying the biomass to produce crude synthetic gas and ash;  b) transporting the crude synthetic gas into a spray tower,  quenching the crude synthetic gas by spraying water to cool down the crude synthetic gas to a temperature of 650-800° C.,  condensing a slag and a tar from the crude synthetic gas,  dissolving and removing alkali metal oxides and part of acid gas to obtain primary synthetic gas;  and c) cooling,  dust removing,  deacidifying,  and desiccating the primary synthetic gas to transform the primary synthetic gas into clean synthetic gas.', p.application_date = '2013-01-20 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9290707B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/36', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'IDW00201102706'}) SET p.application_no = 'IDW00201102706', p.title_cn = '用储罐燃料供应流式运行气化反应器的方法', p.title_en = 'A method of operating a gasification reactor using a storage tank fuel supply flow', p.abstract_cn = '本发明的目的是提供一种用于以经济上有效的方式向加压气化系统供应燃料的方法，该方法确保完全减少或防止来自煤的转移和运输的污染物的排放。在含有至少10个bpj卷的气体的情况下，可以实现这一目标。CO用于转移和/或运输，其中含氧气体被混合到这些气体中，并且这些气体混合物被加热到一定温度，直到至少氧化气体中所含污染物的10%。', p.abstract_en = 'It is an object of the present invention to provide a method for supplying fuel to a pressurized gasification system in an economically effective manner which ensures that the emission of pollutants from the transfer and transportation of coal is completely reduced or prevented. This is achieved in the case of a gas containing at least 10 bpj rolls. CO is used for transfer and/or transport in which an oxygen-containing gas is mixed with the gases and the gas mixture is heated to a temperature until at least 10% of the pollutants contained in the oxidizing gas are oxidized.', p.application_date = '2011-07-27 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'IDP000040658B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'TR201410070'}) SET p.application_no = 'TR201410070', p.title_cn = '一种从水中瞬间产生氢气和氧气的辅助燃料组件。', p.title_en = 'An auxiliary fuel assembly that instantly produces hydrogen and oxygen from water.', p.abstract_cn = '本发明的目的在于，对于具有以汽油、柴油、LPG和天然气(CNG)运行的内燃机的发电机，除了现有的燃烧燃料之外，还可以将氢气添加到燃烧反应中，从而在系统中产生氢气，并且根据需要将所产生的氢气生产在汽油、柴油中。 能够利用LPG和天然气(CNG)进行燃烧，以开发一种辅助燃料系统，该辅助燃料系统即时测量由于燃烧反应的改善而扩散到环境中的有害排放物，并减少现有燃料的消耗，发电机的燃料消耗向发动机提供额外的电力并将其作为数据发送给用户。一种电解池(图1)，其使用诸如氢氧化钠、氢氧化钾或碳酸氢钠的物质的浓缩溶液(图2、3、4)在12V DC或24V DC电压下以低电流执行电解过程。 )催化剂溶液容器(图5、6)备用水容器，(30)控制溶液转移的泵和阀(2 5、27、28、29、21、26)，将反应结束时形成的气体混合物送至发生器的气体切割器(19、20)和控制整个系统的传感器(图9)，它由具有软件的电子卡(图9)和放置系统的箱式外壳(图7和图8)组成，在软件中评估数据并协调电解过程。', p.abstract_en = 'The aim of the present invention is that for generators with internal combustion engines operating with gasoline,  diesel,  LPG and Natural Gas (CNG),  hydrogen gas can be added to the combustion reaction in addition to the existing burning fuel,  generating hydrogen in the system and as much as desired,  producing the produced hydrogen in gasoline,  diesel. Enables combustion with LPG and Natural Gas (CNG), To develop an auxiliary fuel system that instantly measures the harmful emissions spreading to the environment as a result of the improvement of the combustion reaction and reduces the consumption of existing fuel,  the fuel consumption of generators that provide additional power to the engine and sends it to the user as data.An electrolysis cell (figure 1) that performs electrolysis process under 12V DC or 24 V DC voltage with a low current using concentrated solutions of substances such as Sodium Hydroxide,  Potassium Hydroxide or Sodium Bicarbonate (Figure 2, 3, 4). ) Catalyst Solution container feeding the cell (Figure 5, 6) spare water container, (30) Pumps and valves controlling the solution transfer (2 5, 27, 28, 29, 21, 26),  gas cutters that send the gas mixture formed at the end of the reaction to the generator (19, 20) and sensors that control the whole system (Figure 9) It consists of an electronic card (Figure 9) with software where the data is evaluated and the electrolysis process coordinated,  and the box enclosure in which the system is placed (figures 7 and 8).', p.application_date = '2014-08-28 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'TR201410070U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'RU2014133930'}) SET p.application_no = 'RU2014133930', p.title_cn = '使用方法易熔断水响应的合金的碱金属(钠， 钾)为燃料的氢响应燃料功率和发动机植物和发电厂', p.title_en = 'METHOD OF USE OF EASILY FUSE HYDRO RESPONSIVE ALLOYS OF ALKALI METALS (SODIUM,  POTASSIUM) AS FUEL HYDRO RESPONSIVE FUELS POWER AND ENGINE PLANTS AND POWER PLANTS', p.abstract_cn = '1。使用易熔断水响应的方法合金的碱金属(钠， 钾)为燃料的氢响应燃料功率和发动机通过进料容易的植物，电厂水反应合金 钠和钾的消费者(例如， 反应器)的温度， 当今熔点温度合金， 与水一起在调整后的比率， 其特征在于 : 熔化温度容易加氢反应的合金小于纯钠的熔化温度， 钾。 2。根据权利要求1的方法， 其特征在于容易地加氢反应的合金含量Na和K中的加氢反应，燃料不会少 80%。3。根据权利要求1的方法， 其特征在于 : 易熔的氢响应合金Na和K中含有，重量。 % :', p.abstract_en = '1 .The method of using easily fuse hydro responsive alloys of alkali metals (sodium,  potassium) as fuel hydro responsive fuels power and engine plants and power plants by feeding easily of hydro reacting alloy of sodium and potassium in consumer (for example,  reactor) at temperature,  Nowadays melting temperature alloy,  together with water in regulated ratio,  characterized in that melting temperature easily of hydro reacting alloy is less than the melting temperature of pure sodium and potassium. 2. Method according to Claim 1,  characterized in that content of easily of hydro reacting alloy Na and K in hydro reacting fuel is not less than 80% .3. Method according to Claim 1,  characterized in that easily fusible hydro responding alloy Na and K contains,  wt. % :', p.application_date = '2014-08-18 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'RU2014133930A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/08', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'RU2012136151'}) SET p.application_no = 'RU2012136151', p.title_cn = '质子导电膜', p.title_en = 'PROTON-CONDUCTING MEMBRANE', p.abstract_cn = '领域 : 化学物质 : 本发明涉及一种质子导电膜，含有脱水催化剂和式(II)的混合的金属氧化物，laawb-cmoco12-Y(Ⅱ)，其中摩尔比A : B构成4.8至6，优选地从5.3到6，C为间隔从0到0。5b和Y是不带电的数量是式(II)，例如为≤Y≤1a。8。本发明还涉及质子导电膜在基板上，反应器，包括所述质子导电膜，这种反应器中物质脱水的方法，应用质子导电膜，以及以质子导电膜的形成方法。效果 : 所述质子导电膜在二氧化碳存在下稳定和酸性气体，使其可以应用于在air.13Cl存在下，8的DWG，6EX', p.abstract_en = 'FIELD :  chemistry. SUBSTANCE :  invention relates to proton-conducting membrane,  which contains dehydration catalyst and mixed oxide of metals of formula (II) LaaWb-cMocO12-y (II),  where molar ratio a : b constitutes from 4.8 to 6,  preferably from 5.3 to 6,  c is in the interval from 0 to 0.5b and y is such number that formula (II) is not charged,  for instance 0≤y≤1.8. Invention also relates to proton-conducting membrane on substrate,  reactor,  including said proton-conducting membrane,  method for substance dehydration in such reactor,  application of proton-conducting membrane,  as well as to method for formation of proton-conducting membrane. EFFECT :  claimed proton-conducting membrane is stable in presence of carbon dioxide and acidic gases,  which makes it possible to apply it in presence of air. 13 cl,  8 dwg,  6 ex', p.application_date = '2011-02-10 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'RU2577852C2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/50', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'IN9849DELNP2015'}) SET p.application_no = 'IN9849DELNP2015', p.title_cn = '方法用于共生产氨的尿素和甲醇', p.title_en = 'A PROCESS FOR CO- PRODUCTION OF AMMONIA UREA AND METHANOL', p.abstract_cn = '用于联合生产氨的方法，从天然气中尿素和甲醇，包括以下步骤 : (a)生产合成气的同时投加涉及一种天然气自热重整器(ATR)和蒸汽甲烷重整装置(SMR)，两个重整器并联运行，(b)将空气供应给空气分离单元(ASU)其中空气被分成氧，该信号被馈送到ATR，和氮气，(c)使所述合成气从SMR一种水煤气转换，(d)除去二氧化碳从合成气从步骤c)中和将其引导到尿素合成尿素合成单元，e)将从步骤(d)的富氢气体与氮气从步骤(b)，从气体中去除催化剂毒物和使ammoma氨合成单元中合成气体混合物，(f)任选的二氧化碳去除部分从所述合成气从在步骤(a)中，使其自动复位响应一种尿素合成中的尿素合成单元从步骤(f)和(g)使合成气与甲醇的合成单元，其中来自步骤(a)的合成气可以被导入来自SMR ATR出口的出口的上游在变速档或其它方式。', p.abstract_en = 'A process for co-production of ammonia,  urea and methanol from natural gas,  comprising the steps of (a) producing a synthesis gas by simultaneous feeding naturalgas to an autothermal reformer (ATR) and to a steam methane reformer (SMR),  the two reformers running in parallel,  (b) feeding air to an air separation unit (ASU),  where the air is split into oxygen,  which is fed to the ATR,  and nitrogen,  (c) subjecting the synthesis gas from the SMR to a water gas shift,  (d) removing the carbon dioxide from the synthesis gas from step (c) and leading it to urea synthesis in a urea synthesis unit,  (e) combining the hydrogen-rich gas from step (d) with the nitrogen from step (b),  removing catalyst poisons from the gases and leading the gas mixture to ammoma synthesis in an ammonia synthesis unit,  (f) optionally removing part of the carbon dioxide from the syngas from the ATR in step (a) and leading it to urea synthesis in a urea synthesis unit and (g) leading the syngas from step (f) to the methanol synthesis unit,  wherein synthesis gas from step (a) may be led either from the ATR outlet to the SMR outlet upstream from the shift stage or the other way.', p.application_date = '2015-10-20 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'IN9849DELNP2015A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2014158316'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2014158316', p.title_cn = '氢生成装置及燃料电池系统和操作其的方法', p.title_en = 'HYDROGEN GENERATOR AND METHOD FOR OPERATING THE SAME,  AND FUEL CELL SYSTEM', p.abstract_cn = '要解决的问题是 : 仅使用自启动电源，以减少启动时的功率消耗。方法 : 该氢生成装置100，17hydrogenetion hydrogenetion脱硫单元19和加热器，用于加热脱硫剂，重整器1份含氢的气体排出的脱硫剂hydrogenetion17)，用于提供所述前的原料流入回收流动通道16提供，使用自启动电源32启动时，当使用所述系统电源在比的定时更早启动，循环流的通道16设置于第第四密封单元(15)从关闭状态和打开状态。选择的绘图 : 图。1', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To reduce power consumption at the time of starting up using only a power source for self-sustained startup. SOLUTION :  A hydrogen generator 100 includes :  a heater 19 for heating a hydrogenation desulfurizer for heating a hydrogenation desulfurizer 17;  and a recycling flow channel 16 for supplying a part of hydrogen-containing gas discharged by a reformer 1 to a raw material before flowing into the hydrogenation desulfurizer 17. When starting up using a power source 32 for self-sustained startup,  a fourth sealer 15 provided on the recycling flow channel 16 is switched to an opened state from a closed state at a timing earlier than the case of starting up using a system power source. SELECTED DRAWING :  Figure 1 COPYRIGHT :  (C)2016, JPO&INPIT', p.application_date = '2014-08-04 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP2016034881A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2015548776'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2015548776', p.title_cn = '该储氢材料', p.title_en = 'The hydrogen storage material', p.abstract_cn = '该储氢材料，和聚(环氧乙烷)pyridineborane中含有的氨，所述聚(环氧乙烷)，多个MDA9a MDA具有的重均分子量小于T选择的绘图 : 图。1', p.abstract_en = 'A hydrogen-storage-material comprising ammonia borane and poly(ethylene oxide).', p.application_date = '2013-12-20 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP2016508111A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201310121121.7'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201310121121.7', p.title_cn = '一种半水煤气处理方法', p.title_en = 'A semi-water gas processing method', p.abstract_cn = '本发明提供了一种半水煤气处理方法，压缩三段来气进入半水煤气处理装置，先经油分离器进行油水分离，然后分两路，一路进入中变做为冷线用来调节中变入口温度，一路进入饱和热水塔饱和段，在塔内经与循环热水充分接触，使湿气温度达到150℃以上并配入水蒸汽一同进入汽水分离器，分离掉水后进入热交换器管内，换热后与冷线汇合，温度调节在310℃～350℃进入中变上段，出来进入中变增湿器，调节下段入口温度在350℃左右进入中变下段，下段出来进入热交换器管间，经换热后进入一调温水加热器进行换热。通过采用本发明的半水煤气处理方法，能够在尽可能的节约蒸汽的情况下，制备出合格的交换气体。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention provides a semi-water gas treatment method. The method is characterized in that compressed three-section coming gas enters a semi-water gas treatment device and then is subjected to oil-water separation in an oil separator;  then the compressed three-section coming gas is divided into two paths,  wherein one path of the gas enters into an intermediate converter to be used as a cold line to regulate the inlet temperature of the intermediate converter,  the other path enters a saturated section of a saturated hot water tower to come into full contact with circulating hot water in the tower so that temperature of the wet gas is above 150 DEG C,  water vapor is blended and then the wet gas and the water vapor enter a gas-water separator together,  then enter a heat exchange tube after water is separated out;  the gas joins in the cold line after heat exchange;  after the temperature is regulated to be 310-350 DEG C,  then the gas enters the upper section of the intermediate converter and then comes out to enters into an intermediate converter humidifier,  the inlet temperature of the lower section is regulated to be about 350 DEG C,  the gas enters the lower section of the intermediate converter and comes out of the lower section to enter a heat exchange tube for heat exchange,  and then enters a warm water regulation heater for heat exchange. By adopting the semi-water gas treatment method,  qualified exchange gas can be prepared under the condition that vapor is saved as much as possible.', p.application_date = '2013-04-09 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN103241712B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/16', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201410338472.8'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201410338472.8', p.title_cn = '一种干气分离氢气方法及系统', p.title_en = 'A dry method and system for hydrogen separation', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种干气分离氢气方法及系统，所述方法包括原料气压缩工艺、膜分离工艺和产品氢气压缩工艺，所述系统包括第一压缩机和在其之后连接的除雾器，在所述第一压缩机之前设置有原料气缓冲罐和第一过滤器，在所述除雾器之后顺序连接有第二过虑器、原料气加热器、膜分离器，所述膜离器有两路输出口：一路为成品-含氢气尾气输出口，一路为非成品-其它废气输出口。本发明提高了含氢干气中氢气的回收效率，其膜分离器是普利森膜分离器，安装投产快，所采用的加温后的分离氢气的工艺，使原料气远离露点，不至因氢气渗透后滞留气烃类含量升高冷凝形成液膜而影响分离性能，提高膜分离器的使用效率。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention discloses a method for using dry gas to separate hydrogen as well as a system. The method comprises feed-gas-compressing process,  membrane-separating process and product-hydrogen-compressing process;  the system comprises a first compressor,  and a demister connected at rear of the first compressor;  a feed gas buffer tank and a first filter are arranged in front of the first compressor;  a second filter,  a feed gas heater and a membrane separator are connected at rear of the demister in sequence;  the membrane separator has two output openings;  one output opening is a finished product-tail gas containing hydrogen output opening,  and the other output opening is a non-finished product-other exhaust gas output opening. According to the method and the system,  the hydrogen recovery efficiency of the dry gas containing the hydrogen is improved;  as the membrane separator is a PRISM membrane separator,  the membrane separator is mounted and went into operation rapidly;  the process of separating the hydrogen after rising temperature is adopted to make raw materials far away from dew point;  the phenomenon that the content of retention gas hydrocarbon rises and condenses to form a liquid membrane due to the permeation of the hydrogen and effects the separation performance can be avoided;  the using efficiency of the membrane can be improved.', p.application_date = '2014-07-16 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN104071749B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/56', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201410479628.4'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201410479628.4', p.title_cn = '一种多功能甲醇裂解制氢设备', p.title_en = 'A multifunctional methanol cracking hydrogen production apparatus', p.abstract_cn = '本发明是一种甲醇裂解制氢设备，由(1)甲醇泵、(2)柴油泵、(3)电磁阀、(4)喷嘴、(5)操作台、(6)鼓风机、(7)进风口、(8)甲醇裂解器、(9)空气加热器、(10)温度传感器、(11)氢气冷却器、(12)防爆安全罐、(13)离心泵、(14)冷却水罐、(15)气体取样器等组成。本发明的设备模拟工业烟道与炉窑，利用工厂余热废热将甲醇裂解成氢气燃烧，提高了燃料的燃烧热值，降低了废气排放。还可根据实际烟道的温度高低状况选择安装不同裂解管，可用于改造大小工业炉窑，实现了设备应用的普遍性。另外本发明的设备操作简单，安全性高，能调节设备实现不同温度下的甲醇裂解，可用于甲醇裂解制氢数据采集和学术研究。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention provides a methanol splitting decomposition hydrogen production device,  which comprises a methanol pump (1),  a diesel pump (2),  a solenoid valve (3),  a nozzle (4),  an operating table (5),  an air blower (6),  an air inlet (7),  a methanol cracking device(8),  an air heater (9),  a temperature sensor (10),  a hydrogen cooler (11),  an explosion-proof safety tank (12),  a centrifugal pump (13),  a cooling water tank (14) and a gas sampler (15). The device provided by the invention simulate industrial flue and kiln,  uses waste heat of factory to carry out methanol splitting decomposition to produce hydrogen for combustion,  improves combustion heat value of fuel,  and reduces exhaust emissions. In addition,  the device provided by the invention has simple operation and high security,  can be adjusted to realize methanol splitting decomposition under different temperatures and can be used to data acquisition and science research of methanol splitting decomposition hydrogen production.', p.application_date = '2014-09-19 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN104310308B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/22', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 2, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201520885689.0'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201520885689.0', p.title_cn = '小型一体化水光解制氢系统', p.title_en = 'Small -size integrated water photodissociation hydrogen production system', p.abstract_cn = '本实用新型涉及一种小型一体化水光解制氢系统，包括光解制氢单元和气体吸收单元，太阳光线透过所述光解制氢单元的集光孔处的透明玻璃片进入所述光解池内，入射的太阳光一部分使次氯酸分解产生氯化氢和氧气，另一部分被单晶硅光电池吸收产生电能，由石墨电极电解电解液，在正极氯离子失电子反应生成氯气，而氯气又与水反应产生氯化氢和次氯酸，产生的次氯酸补充了次氯酸的光照分解，在负极氢离子得电子反应产生氢气，因此可实现水光解制氢。所述的小型一体化水光解制氢系统，太阳能利用率高达36％到50％，整套装置配套设备少，结构简单，拆装方便，占用空间小，成本较低，能够实现自动化，操作和维护方便。', p.abstract_en = 'The utility model relates to a small -size integrated water photodissociation hydrogen production system,  including photodissociation hydrogen manufacturing unit gentleness bulk absorption unit,  the Sun\'s rays sees through the transparent glass plate of the light harvesting hole department of photodissociation hydrogen manufacturing unit gets into in the photodissociation pond,  the sunlight of incident some make the hypochlorous acid decomposition produce hydrogen chloride and oxygen,  and another part is absorbed the production electric energy by single crystal silicon photocell,  and by graphite electrode electrolysis electrolyte,  at anodal chlorion betatopic reaction formation chlorine,  and chlorine and water reaction produce hydrogen chloride and hypochlorous acid,  and the hypochlorous acid of production has replenished the illumination decomposition of hypochlorous acid,  gets the electron reaction at the negative pole hydrogen ion to produce hydrogen,  so can realize water photodissociation hydrogen manufacturing. Small -size integrated water photodissociation hydrogen production system,  the solar energy utilization ratio is few to 50%,  complete equipment corollary equipment up to 36%,  simple structure,  easy dismounting,  occupation space is little,  the cost is lower,  can realize automaticly,  operations and maintenance is convenient.', p.application_date = '2015-11-09 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN205087914U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'EP13189958'}) SET p.application_no = 'EP13189958', p.title_cn = '系统和方法用于生产含H2气体和纯净水', p.title_en = 'System and process for producing a H2-containing gas and purified water', p.abstract_cn = '系统和方法用于生产H2含有产品气体和净化水从组合的H2-制备重整和热水纯化过程。原水，如盐水，通过间接加热传热与重整产物从H2-中生产重整净化原水的方法一种多效蒸馏工艺。', p.abstract_en = 'System and process for producing a H 2 -containing product gas and purified water from an integrated H 2 -producing reforming and thermal water purification process. Raw water,  such as salt water,  is heated by indirect heat transfer with reformate from the H 2 -producing reforming process for purifying raw water in a multiple effect distillation process.', p.application_date = '2013-10-23 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'EP2865641B1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'EP13819821'}) SET p.application_no = 'EP13819821', p.title_cn = '综合利用方法低碳排放的费-托合成尾气', p.title_en = 'PROCESS FOR COMPREHENSIVELY UTILIZING LOW CARBON EMISSION FISCHER-TROPSCH SYNTHESIS TAIL GAS', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种综合利用工艺低碳排放的费托合成尾气。过程中，非循环后产生的尾气费-托合成反应蒸汽重整和转换成富氢合成气，然后高纯度的氢气是分离和从富氢合成气使用。该方法包括以下步骤 : 1)进行水蒸气转化反应，获得变换气；2)进行费-托合成反应得到的烃燃料；3)预重整反应后，将含有两个或更多个碳原子的烃类化合物成沼气；4)进行重整反应将甲烷和蒸汽的成氢气和一氧化碳；5)分离氢气和一氧化碳的气体；和6)重整反应器提供热量。本发明有效利用费托合成尾气，特别是尾气含有大量惰性组分，和将尾气进入氢气使用。此外，本发明有效利用其剩余重整气体中的可燃成分氢气分离后，从而提高能量的利用效率。', p.abstract_en = 'Disclosed is a process for comprehensively utilizing low carbon emission Fischer-Tropsch synthesis tail gas. In the process,  a non-cycling tail gas generated after a Fischer-Tropsch synthesis reaction is steam reformed and converted into a hydrogen-rich synthesis gas,  and then highly purified hydrogen is separated and extracted from the hydrogen-rich synthesis gas for use. The process comprises the following steps :  1) conducting a steam conversion reaction to obtain converted gas;  2) conducting a Fischer-Tropsch synthesis reaction to obtain a hydrocarbon fuel;  3) after a pre-reforming reaction,  converting a hydrocarbon compound containing two or more carbon atoms into methane;  4) conducting a reforming reaction to convert the methane and steam into hydrogen and carbon monoxide;  5) separating the hydrogen and carbon monoxide from the gas;  and 6) providing heat for a reforming reactor. The present invention effectively utilizes the Fischer-Tropsch synthesis tail gas,  especially a tail gas containing a large amount of inert constituents,  and converts the tail gas into the hydrogen for use. Furthermore,  the present invention effectively utilizes the residual combustible constituents in the reformed gas after the hydrogen is separated,  thus improving energy utilization efficiency.', p.application_date = '2013-07-11 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'EP2876080A4', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'EP14718083'}) SET p.application_no = 'EP14718083', p.title_cn = '氨和氢中使用的排出管线植物', p.title_en = 'VENT LINE FOR USE IN AMMONIA AND HYDROGEN PLANTS', p.abstract_cn = 'Iin氨或氢装置，包括脱硫段，重整段和换档段，该换档段包括低温变换转换器和中温变换炉，一个通风线路下游设置有从低温度变换转换器和介质温度位移转换器为以允许所述换档转换器被重新加热，具有促-池气体在低压(通常是3-7巴)。这样冷凝水蒸汽的过程中避免了煤气。通过将该通风管路成为可能节约了大量时间，更具体讲$time，用于临时关闭后重启的生产，由于加热循环中的LTS/手动切换开关的转换器避免了氮气。', p.abstract_en = 'In an ammonia or hydrogen plant comprising a desulfurisation section,  a reforming section and a shift section,  where the shift section comprises a low temperature shift converter and a medium temperature shift converter,  a vent line is arranged downstream from the low temperature shift converter and the medium temperature shift converter in order to allow the shift converters to be re-heated with process gas at a low pressure (typically 3-7 bar). This way condensation of water vapour in the process gas is avoided. By applying this vent line it becomes possible to save significant time,  more specifically 8-24 hours,  for restarting the production after temporary shut-down thereof,  because a heat-up of the LTS/MTS converter in circulating nitrogen is avoided.', p.application_date = '2014-04-16 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'EP2994414A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'EP14727065'}) SET p.application_no = 'EP14727065', p.title_cn = '重整气为燃料用于启动期间的一次转化装置', p.title_en = 'REFORMED GAS AS FUEL FOR PRIMARY REFORMER DURING STARTUP', p.abstract_cn = '本发明提供了一种方法和装置用于回收的甲醇工厂中产生的重整气启动期间。在一个方面，该方法用于回收的甲醇工厂中产生的重整气在启动期间，包括 : a)的温度降低甲醇厂的重整气体包括(1)中的水的量不大于2.5重量%，基于重整气体的总重量，(2)中甲烷的量为1重量%至8重量%，基于重整气体的总重量，(3)氢，(4)氮，(5)二氧化碳，和(6)一氧化碳，以除去至少一些水从重整气；和b)使用的水中除去重整气为燃料的蒸汽重整器。', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention provides a method and apparatus for recovery of reformed gas produced in a methanol plant during startup. In one aspect,  the method for recovery of a reformed gas produced in a methanol plant during startup comprising :  a) decreasing the temperature of the methanol plant reformed gas comprising (1) water in an amount no greater than 2.5 wt %,  based on the total weight of the reformed gas,  (2) methane in an amount that ranges from 1 wt % to 8 wt %,  based on the total weight of the reformed gas,  (3) hydrogen,  (4) nitrogen,  (5) carbon dioxide,  and (6) carbon monoxide,  to remove at least some of the water from the reformed gas;  and b) using the water removed reformed gas as fuel in a steam reformer.', p.application_date = '2014-05-05 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'EP2994416A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/32', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'EP14734549'}) SET p.application_no = 'EP14734549', p.title_cn = '回收气体热加氢脱硫段', p.title_en = 'RECYCLING GAS TO HEAT THE HYDRODESULPHURIZATION SECTION', p.abstract_cn = '在一个方面，本发明提供了一种回收天然气的方法在甲醇重整器启动时植物。该方法包括从之前的点的回收天然气进入天然气饱和器，其中天然气循环使用至天然气达到期望的温度。', p.abstract_en = 'In one aspect,  the present invention provides a method for recycling natural gas during a reformer startup in a methanol plant. The method comprises recycling natural gas from a point before entry into the natural gas saturator where the natural gas is recycled until the natural gas reaches a desired temperature.', p.application_date = '2014-05-06 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'EP2994417A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/34', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2014547763'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2014547763', p.title_cn = '方法和装置用于生产合成气', p.title_en = 'Method and device for the production of synthesis gas', p.abstract_cn = '用于产生合成气的方法和装置从烃和水。详细的方法和装置，氢气和一氧化碳和/或具有官能团和/或合成烃具有无官能基在期望的比率产生合成气体。用这种方法，含烃流体，相当量的CO2具有不产生可变合成气的氢含量。还有，各种形式的碳，氢和副产物可获得的。', p.abstract_en = 'Method and device for generating a synthesis gas from a hydrocarbon and water. The method and device in detail,  hydrogen and CO and/or having a functional group and/or a synthetic hydrocarbon having no functional group in a desired ratio to produce synthesis gas. By this process,  the hydrocarbon-containing fluid,  a considerable amount of CO 2 variable without generating a synthesis gas having a hydrogen content. Also,  various forms of carbon and hydrogen and by-product can be obtained.', p.application_date = '2012-12-20 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP5886443B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/24', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2012110790'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2012110790', p.title_cn = '重整系统', p.title_en = 'Reforming system', p.abstract_cn = '要解决的问题 : 本发明的冷启动催化剂可有效地拉伸的和因此，所述的温度该重整催化剂可以被改性以达到一种重整系统的进一步缩短时间。溶液 : 将重整系统本发明的，一种重整器，一氢基燃料，氢是通过重整催化剂生产的，当该催化剂是在还原状态，在该普通自热的产生通过所述反应的氧和conchospore正常启动催化剂设置使得，该重整器的正常操作期间的开始-停止周期在还原状态的催化剂载体具有一种保持装置用于保持还原气氛，和该保持装置气氛的免疫测定，改性装置，以控制该流入的空气进入第一控制阀1和，所述的重整气体从重整器和控制该第二控制的释放阀2，该控制阀1和第二之间的上游侧通道的重整器该氢的系统具有一个燃料喷射装置，用于供给燃料和，在停止该操作的时间所述的重整器，挤出的剩余气体在一种78a078a0氢基燃料在所述的I选自拉拔 : 图。1。', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To provide a reforming system capable of bringing out the effect of a normal temperature starting catalyst effectively,  and enabling the further shortening of an arrival time of a reforming catalyst to a reformable temperature. SOLUTION :  A reforming system includes a reducing atmosphere holding means that maintains a carrier of a normal temperature starting catalyst in a reduced state over an operation shutdown period of a reformer,  the normal temperature starting catalyst being disposed in the reformer,  being a catalyst that reforms a hydrogen-based fuel to generate hydrogen,  and self-heating by the reaction of oxygen and the carrier at normal temperature when the carrier of the catalyst is in the reduced state. The reducing atmosphere holding means has a first control valve that controls inflow of air into the reformer,  a second control valve that controls emission of a reformed gas from the reformer,  and a fuel injection system that supplies the hydrogen-based fuel to an upstream side passage between the first control valve and the reformer. The system controls so that a remaining gas in the reformer is extruded to fill the reformer with the hydrogen-based fuel upon the shutdown of the reformer. COPYRIGHT :  (C)2014, JPO&INPIT', p.application_date = '2012-05-14 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP5886497B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2011237047'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2011237047', p.title_cn = '优化蒸汽发电，蒸汽重整油生产氢气的方法', p.title_en = 'Optimized steam generating,  steam-reforming oil cut hydrogen production method', p.abstract_cn = '该方法包括中冷却合成气体的一系列热交换器(13)， 冷却的烟气在另一系列的换热器用于产生蒸汽的水， 将蒸汽与烃原料(1)在蒸汽重整反应器， 控制蒸汽的流量，以调节比的蒸汽在烃进料的值 1.5-2， 压缩吹扫气体以形成燃烧气体送入燃烧室， 和将合成气转化为一单元筛分离用于生产氢的具有纯度大于 99.9wt。%。该方法包括中冷却合成气体的一系列热交换器(13)， 冷却的烟气在另一系列的换热器用于产生蒸汽的水， 将蒸汽与烃原料(1)在蒸汽重整反应器， 控制蒸汽的流量，以调节比的蒸汽在烃进料的值 1.5-2， 压缩吹扫气体以形成燃烧气体送入燃烧室， 和将合成气转化为一单元筛分离用于生产氢的具有纯度大于 99.9wt。%。所述的热烟气进入压力通过压缩机(32)， 其中热从热烟气提供给交换反应器在烃的蒸汽重整反应 饲料与蒸汽进行混合和反应流出物。 所产生的蒸汽供应到蒸汽涡轮与压缩机相关联。 一种气流送料压缩机控制通过阀(36)的下游的放置在电路 该换热器使压缩机的工作压力3-5绝对巴之间的配合保持在 所述压缩机特性曲线。 蒸汽重整反应器进料为石油馏分具有1-。', p.abstract_en = 'The process comprises cooling synthesis gas in a series of heat exchangers (13),  cooling fumes in another series of heat exchangers for generating steam from water,  sending the steam mixed with hydrocarbon feedstock (1) in the steam reforming reactor,  controlling a flow rate of steam to adjust a ratio of the steam on the hydrocarbon feed to a value of 1.5-2,  compressing a purge gas to form a combustion gas that is fed to a combustion chamber,  and introducing the synthesis gas into a unit of sieve separation for producing hydrogen having a purity of greater than 99.9 wt.%. The process comprises cooling synthesis gas in a series of heat exchangers (13),  cooling fumes in another series of heat exchangers for generating steam from water,  sending the steam mixed with hydrocarbon feedstock (1) in the steam reforming reactor,  controlling a flow rate of steam to adjust a ratio of the steam on the hydrocarbon feed to a value of 1.5-2,  compressing a purge gas to form a combustion gas that is fed to a combustion chamber,  and introducing the synthesis gas into a unit of sieve separation for producing hydrogen having a purity of greater than 99.9 wt.%. The hot fumes are brought into pressure by a compressor (32),  where a heat from the hot fumes is supplied to an exchange reactor within which steam reforming reactions of hydrocarbon feed is carried out by mixing with the steam and reaction effluent. The generated steam is supplied to a steam turbine associated with the compressor. An air flow feeding the compressor is controlled through a valve (36) placed on a circuit of a downstream of the exchangers so that an operating pressure of the compressor fits between 3-5 bars absolute to stay on a characteristic curve of the compressor. The steam-reforming reactor feed is a petroleum fraction having 1-5C.', p.application_date = '2011-10-28 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP5887103B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2012008599'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2012008599', p.title_cn = '方法用于产生氢气和产生氢的装置', p.title_en = 'A method for generating hydrogen and hydrogen-generating device', p.abstract_cn = '要解决的问题 : 通过更简单的结构和能够产生的氢，通过该氢发生器产生的氢可以可以高效地收集。溶液 : 该中空反应细胞和一种金属的材料制成的，一种加热装置用于加热该反应细胞和，在该反应细胞和所述的空气和去除装置，用于去除空气是提供。选自拉拔 : 图。4。', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To provide a hydrogen generation apparatus capable of generating hydrogen by a simpler structure,  and efficiently collecting generated hydrogen.SOLUTION :  A hydrogen generation apparatus has a hollow reaction cell composed of a metallic material,  a heating apparatus to heat the reaction cell,  and an air removing apparatus to remove air in the reaction cell.', p.application_date = '2012-01-19 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP5887148B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/06', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2012133574'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2012133574', p.title_cn = '燃料产生装置和燃料电池系统，具有相同', p.title_en = 'Fuel generating device and a fuel cell system having the same', p.abstract_cn = '所要解决的问题 : 提供一种高安全性的燃料中生成单元，用于生成燃料进料燃料电池单元。溶液 : 燃料发电机组，包括 : 多孔燃料产生剂，该自由产生燃料进行氧化反应，一种多孔容积膨胀剂的膨胀体积的氧化反应，和所述容器内含有燃料发生剂的体积膨胀剂。氧化前的体积膨胀剂的填充率高于前的燃气发生剂氧化。体积膨胀剂位于燃气发生剂容器的内壁。', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To provide a high-security fuel generating unit for generating a fuel to feed in a fuel cell unit.SOLUTION :  A fuel generating unit includes a porous fuel generating agent which generates a fuel by oxidation reaction,  a porous volume expanding agent which expands its volume by oxidation reaction,  and a vessel containing the fuel generating agent and the volume expanding agent. The filling rate of the volume expanding agent before oxidation is higher than that of the fuel generating agent before oxidation. The volume expanding agent is located between the fuel generating agent and the inner wall of the vessel.', p.application_date = '2012-06-13 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP5888136B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2012173970'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2012173970', p.title_cn = '用于产生氢气的方法', p.title_en = 'A method for generating hydrogen gas', p.abstract_cn = '要解决的问题 : 提供一种简单和廉价的方法产生氢气。方法 :  产生的氢气通过施加处理包括加热至温度范围内，优选为100-～°C 将-FeOOH加入到Fe≤Sb pos=“柱”#-[2]/Sb>OO由FeOOH 将Fe≤Sb pos=“柱”#-[2]/Sb>O氧化铁。加热的原料进行优选在非氧化性气氛， 更优选在容器中。 作为非氧化性气氛，惰性气氛，如纯氩气，引用。 作为原料的含有FeOOH的一个铁锈， 铁基材料如各种钢铁材料能够形成红锈是优选的， 进一步， Fe基合金， 含Fe的合金，低品质铁矿，铁屑等被包括。版权 : (C)2013，补正', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To provide a simple and inexpensive method for generating hydrogen gas.SOLUTION :  Hydrogen gas is generated by applying a treatment comprising heating to a temperature within the range of preferably 100-400°C to convert FeOOH into FeOto a raw material containing FeOOH. Further,  it is possible to repeatedly generate hydrogen gas by applying a rust treatment to FeOformed from FeOOH to convert FeOinto FeOOH. Heating of the raw material is carried out preferably in a non-oxidizing atmosphere,  more preferably in a container. As the non-oxidizing atmosphere,  an inert atmosphere such as pure argon is cited. As the raw material containing FeOOH being one of iron rust,  iron-based materials such as various iron and steel materials capable of forming red rust are preferable,  and further,  Fe-based alloys,  alloys containing Fe,  low quality iron ore,  iron scrap or the like are included.', p.application_date = '2012-08-06 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP5888174B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'MX2015017856'}) SET p.application_no = 'MX2015017856', p.title_cn = '一种纯化方法合成的含氢气体和杂质。', p.title_en = 'A PROCESS FOR PURIFICATION OF A SYNTHESIS GAS CONTAINING HYDROGEN AND IMPURITIES.', p.abstract_cn = '方法用于净化的含氢合成气(100)的电流，特别是在氨厂的前端，其中所述气体含有氢气和少量的一氧化碳，二氧化碳，水和杂质，所述方法包括甲烷化的步骤(13)的所述电流(100)，转化剩余量的一氧化碳和二氧化碳，甲烷和水，脱水(14)的气体，从而除去水，然后低温纯化(15)如液氮洗，除去甲烷和氩气，一种相应的设备和方法，本发明还公开了氨厂的改造。', p.abstract_en = 'A process for purification of a current of hydrogen synthesis gas (100),  particularly in the front-end of an ammonia plant,  wherein said gas contains hydrogen and minor amounts of carbon monoxide,  carbon dioxide,  water and impurities,  said process including steps of methanation (13) of said current (100),  converting residual amounts of carbon monoxide and carbon dioxide to methane and water,  dehydration (14) of the gas to remove water,  and then a cryogenic purification (15) such as liquid nitrogen wash,  to remove methane and Argon;  a corresponding plant and method for revamping an ammonia plant are also disclosed.', p.application_date = '2014-06-25 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'MX2015017856A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'TW104126272'}) SET p.application_no = 'TW104126272', p.title_cn = '制造合成气之方法', p.title_en = 'PROCESS FOR PRODUCING SYNTHESIS GAS', p.abstract_cn = '本发明系关於一种制造合成气(5)之方法，其中烃(2)在第一反应区(Z1)中热分解成氢气及碳，且所形成之氢气自该第一反应区(Z1)传递至第二反应区(Z2)中，以便在其中与二氧化碳(4)反应得到水及一氧化碳此处之特徵性特点为该烃之热分解所需的能量自该第二反应区(Z2)供应至该第一反应区(Z1)', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a process for producing synthesis gas (5) in which hydrocarbon (2) is decomposed thermally in a first reaction zone (Z1) to hydrogen and carbon,  and hydrogen formed is passed from the first reaction zone (Z1) into a second reaction zone (Z2) in order to be reacted therein with carbon dioxide (4) to give water and carbon monoxide. The characteristic feature here is that energy required for the thermal decomposition of the hydrocarbon is supplied to the first reaction zone (Z1) from the second reaction zone (Z2).', p.application_date = '2015-08-12 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'TW201609526A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/30', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'ATE775545'}) SET p.application_no = 'ATE775545', p.title_cn = '用于生产合成气的方法及燃烧器', p.title_en = 'METHOD AND BURNER FOR PRODUCING SYNTHESIS GAS', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及生产合成气的部分氧化液态或气态的，含碳燃料在存在含氧的氧化剂，其中所述燃料，氧化剂和调节剂分别供给到燃烧器，其中所述燃料和调节剂混合在燃烧器的混合室，在它们被带入与氧化剂接触。减少负载的燃烧器，特别在操作过程中与瞬态情况下，所述氧化剂为集中引入通过出口开口的燃烧器，燃烧室和混合物燃料和减速剂通过出口开口引入到燃烧室同心地围绕氧化剂。', p.abstract_en = 'This invention relates to the production of synthesis gas by partial oxidation of liquid or gaseous,  carbonaceous fuel in the presence of an oxygen-containing oxidant,  wherein the fuel,  the oxidant and a moderator are separately supplied to a burner and wherein the fuel and the moderator are mixed in a mixing chamber of the burner,  before they are brought in contact with the oxidant. To reduce the load of the burner in particular during operation with transient conditions,  the oxidant is centrally introduced through an outlet opening of the burner into a combustion chamber and the mixture of fuel and moderator is introduced through the outlet opening into the combustion chamber concentrically around the oxidant.', p.application_date = '2010-11-12 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'ATE775545T1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/36', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'ATE776596'}) SET p.application_no = 'ATE776596', p.title_cn = '使用方法自由热量从氢制造设备向供电区与绿色热加热网络', p.title_en = 'Method using the free heat from a hydrogen production facility to supply district heating networks with green heat', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种使用余热的方法从通过蒸汽重整制氢工艺以有助于加热的水的集中供热网络。通常，合成气低于温度Tg，它不超过160℃，后合成气转化为蒸汽，将热量传递给工艺流体，产生的油烟低于温度Tf为不超过170℃；所述方法还产生了未使用输出蒸汽温度TV的下方高于200℃，热交换与合成气和烟气进行供应的外蒸汽系统利用软化水。根据本发明的方法，可获得的热量从流体加热水，其位于附近的集中热水系统由传热流体的装置，其通常为水，循环在闭合的回路中在可变温度；回路中的水通过间接热交换加热与合成气体和油烟，和从输出蒸汽提供额外的热量需要。本发明还涉及一种设备，用于implemting的方法。', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention relates to a method for using the waste heat from a hydrogen production process by steam reforming to contribute to the heating of the water of a district heating network. Generally,  a synthesis gas is below a temperature TG,  which is no more than 160 DEG C,  after the synthesis gas is converted into steam and transmits heat to a process fluid;  generated fume is below a temperature TF which is no more than 170 DEG C;  and the method also produces unused output steam below a temperature TV higher than 200 DEG C,  so heat exchange with the synthesis gas and the fume is performed to supply an extermal steam system by utilizing demineralized water. According to the method of the invention,  heat which can be obtained from the fluid heats water which locates in a nearby centralized water heating system by means of a heat transfer fluid,  which generally is water,  cycled in a closed loop at a variable temperature;  water in the loop is heated through indirect heat exchange with the synthesis gas and the fume;  and additional heat is supplied from output steam as needed. The invention further relates to equipment for implemting the method.', p.application_date = '2014-05-15 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'ATE776596T1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/36', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'ATE779332'}) SET p.application_no = 'ATE779332', p.title_cn = '燃料处理装置', p.title_en = 'FUEL PROCESSING DEVICE', p.abstract_cn = '提供一种燃料处理装置，包括 : 一燃烧单元设有热源； 一种脱硫单元提取硫组分从源气体； 重整单元，用于生成， 从脱硫源气体，含氢气体具有氢作为主要成分； 和低温转换单元，其配备有一发热催化剂用于降低在含氢的杂质浓度 气体。 重整单元，脱硫单元被配置为以围绕所述燃烧单元， 并向外同心地设置在给定顺序从所述燃烧单元。 本发明还包括预热通道，连接到脱硫单元， 其提供给所述燃烧单元的底部通过保温材料， 使得源气体进行预热，热量从燃烧器。', p.abstract_en = 'Provided is a fuel processing device including :  a combustion unit equipped with a heat source;  a desulfurization unit for extracting a sulfur component from the source gas;  a reforming unit for generating,  from the desulfurized source gas,  a hydrogen-containing gas having hydrogen as a main component thereof;  and a low-temperature conversion unit equipped with an exothermic catalyst for reducing the impurity concentration in the hydrogen-containing gas. The reforming unit and the desulfurization unit are configured so as to surround the combustion unit,  and are disposed concentrically in the given order facing outwards from the combustion unit. The present invention further includes a preheating passage which is connected to the desulfurization unit,  and which is provided to a bottom part of the combustion unit via a heat insulation material,  such that the source gas is preheated by heat from the combustion unit.', p.application_date = '2013-06-24 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'ATE779332T1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'BRPI112012004752'}) SET p.application_no = 'BRPI112012004752', p.title_cn = '化工厂和工艺中的热回收，特别是用于合成氨', p.title_en = 'recovery of heat in a chemical plant and process,  particularly for the synthesis of ammonia', p.abstract_cn = '一种用于在合成化学产品，特别是氨的过程中回收废热的方法，其中所述产品用作热力学循环的工作流体； 废热用于增加所述产品(11)的高压液流的焓含量， 由合成段(10)输送，从而获得蒸汽或超临界产物流(20)，并且通过使所述蒸汽或超临界物流在至少一个合适的膨胀器(13)上膨胀来回收能量； 该方法特别适合于回收低温变换后的合成气流出物的热含量。', p.abstract_en = 'A method for recovering waste heat in a process for the synthesis of a chemical product,  particularly ammonia,  where the product is used as the working fluid of a thermodynamic cycle;  the waste heat is used to increase the enthalpy content of a high-pressure liquid stream of said product (11),  delivered by a synthesis section (10),  thus obtaining a vapour or supercritical product stream (20),  and energy is recovered by expanding said vapour or supercritical stream across at least one suitable expander (13);  the method is particularly suited to recover the heat content of the syngas effluent after low-temperature shift.', p.application_date = '2010-05-17 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'BR112012004752A2', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'BRPI1010624'}) SET p.application_no = 'BRPI1010624', p.title_cn = '用于合成气制造的方法', p.title_en = 'METHOD FOR THE SYNTHESIS GAS MANUFACTURE', p.abstract_cn = 'H2-和含有CO的合成气通过分离来自焦炉工艺焦炉气为氢气和一种包含烃类和残余气体物流得到富含CO的合成气从顶部气体流高炉。所述从焦炉气中分离出来的氢气通入富含CO的合成气物流得到的高炉煤气，使合成气的方法，残余气体物流和含烃作为原料送入高炉。', p.abstract_en = 'An H2- and CO-containing synthesis gas is made by separating coke-oven gas from a coke-oven process into hydrogen and a residual gas stream containing hydrocarbons and obtaining a CO-rich synthesis-gas stream from a top gas of a blast furnace. The hydrogen separated from the coke-oven gas is fed into the CO-rich synthesis gas stream obtained from the top gas of a blast furnace to make the synthesis gas,  and the hydrocarbon-containing residual gas stream is fed into the blast furnace as feedstock.', p.application_date = '2010-05-06 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'BRPI1010624A2', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/50', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'BR112012004752'}) SET p.application_no = 'BR112012004752', p.title_cn = '特别用于合成氨的方法和设备化学中的热回收', p.title_en = 'RECOVERY OF HEAT IN A PROCESS AND PLANTS CHEMISTRY,  PARTICULARLY FOR THE SYNTHESIS OF AMMONIA', p.abstract_cn = '一种用于在合成化学产品，特别是氨的过程中回收废热的方法，其中所述产品用作热力学循环的工作流体； 废热用于增加所述产品(11)的高压液流的焓含量， 由合成段(10)输送，从而获得蒸汽或超临界产物流(20)，并且通过使所述蒸汽或超临界物流在至少一个合适的膨胀器(13)上膨胀来回收能量； 该方法特别适合于回收低温变换后的合成气流出物的热含量。', p.abstract_en = 'A method for recovering waste heat in a process for the synthesis of a chemical product,  particularly ammonia,  where the product is used as the working fluid of a thermodynamic cycle;  the waste heat is used to increase the enthalpy content of a high-pressure liquid stream of said product (11),  delivered by a synthesis section (10),  thus obtaining a vapour or supercritical product stream (20),  and energy is recovered by expanding said vapour or supercritical stream across at least one suitable expander (13);  the method is particularly suited to recover the heat content of the syngas effluent after low-temperature shift.', p.application_date = '2010-05-17 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'BRPI1204752A2', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CA2714694'}) SET p.application_no = 'CA2714694', p.title_cn = '掺杂储氢材料', p.title_en = 'DOPED HYDROGEN STORAGE MATERIAL', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种掺杂储氢材料根据通式 : Mg。Mz/Mw大于HN其中 : (i)比X/Y为从0.15至1.5的范围内；(II)时，Z在从0.005至0.35的范围内；(Ⅲ)x[y]z等于1；(iv)m=是一个或多个选自所述金属的组中选择的Sc，Ti，V，Cr，Mn，Fe，Co，Ni，Cu和Zn；(v)n为不大于4Y；并且其中X/Y不等于0.5和至少部分掺杂的储氢材料为非晶态。本发明进一步涉及使用掺杂的储氢材料根据本发明的用于储存氢和方法能够可逆解吸和/或吸收氢。', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention relates to a doped hydrogen storage material according to the general formula :  Mg. By Mz Hn wherein  :  (i) the ratio of x/y is in the range of from 0.15 to 1.5;  (ii) z is in the range of from 0.005 to 0.35;  (iii) x+y+z equals 1;  (iv) M= is one or more metals selected from the group of selected Sc,  Ti,  V,  Cr,  Mn,  Fe,  Co,  Ni,  Cu and Zn;  (v) n is no more than 4y;  and wherein x/y does not equal 0.5 and at least part of the doped hydrogen storage material is amorphous. The present invention further relates to the use of doped hydrogen storage materials according to the invention for storing hydrogen and a method for reversibly desorbing and/or absorbing hydrogen.', p.application_date = '2009-02-09 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CA2714694C', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'IDW00201304993'}) SET p.application_no = 'IDW00201304993', p.title_cn = '重烃排除法', p.title_en = 'Heavy hydrocarbon removal process', p.abstract_cn = '通过使FT烟气与吸收油接触、将FT烟气引入蒸馏塔、冷却FT烟气或将FT烟气推送至吸附剂，去除GTL工艺FT烟气中所含的重烃。用于加热重塑管的燃烧器端部，使用FT废气作为燃料，防止由于FT废气中含有的重烃的沉积而阻塞。', p.abstract_en = 'The heavy hydrocarbons contained in the FT flue gas of the GTL process are removed by contacting the FT flue gas with an absorbent oil,  introducing the FT flue gas into a distillation column,  cooling the FT flue gas or pushing the FT flue gas to an adsorbent. A burner end for heating a reshaping tube uses FT exhaust gas as fuel to prevent clogging due to deposition of heavy hydrocarbons contained in the FT exhaust gas.', p.application_date = '2012-03-22 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'IDP000041789B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'KR1020140029869'}) SET p.application_no = 'KR1020140029869', p.title_cn = '金属-碳纳米纤维的制造方法', p.title_en = 'Methods of fabricating metal-carbon nanofiber', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及通过选择性地蚀刻所述衬底形成氧化保护的双用铜制造碳纳米纤维的制造方法. 金属前驱体及有机物质包括金属-有机前体形成纳米纤维的制造. 所述碳被氧化和有机. 同时. 从而进行选择性还原金属前体的所述金属前体的金属-有机纳米纤维的制造选择性氧化的热处理. 制造金属-碳纳米纤维制成的步骤. 包括 : . 所述的展示和低反应性碳金属氧化物. 所述多个选择性氧化与选择性毒蕈碱型乙酰胆碱受体以外的热处理的热处理步骤中在热处理步骤中执行功率. 所述选择性氧化热处理的氧分压，并通过根据不同结构尺寸与金属的碳纳米纤维可以形成. 铜-碳纳米纤维及其制造方法.', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention provides a method for fabricating metal-carbon nanofibers,  which can realize an oxidation resistance characteristic and process simplification,  the method comprising the steps of :  forming metal precursor-organic material nanofibers containing a metal precursor and an organic material;  and forming metal-carbon nanofibers by performing selective oxidative thermal treatment for the metal precursor-organic material nanofibers to oxidize the carbon of the organic material and simultaneously deoxidize the metal precursor into metal,  wherein the metal has lower oxidation reactivity than the carbon;  the selective oxidative thermal treatment is preformed according to one thermal treatment step,  not multiple thermal treatment steps;  and the metal-carbon nanofibers may be formed to have different structures according to the size of oxygen partial pressure at which the selective oxidation thermal treatment is performed.', p.application_date = '2014-03-13 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'KR101605155B1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14288765'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14288765', p.title_cn = '利用超高纯高压氢气生产甲醇', p.title_en = 'Generating methanol using ultrapure,  high pressure hydrogen', p.abstract_cn = '在各种实施方案中，使用含(CO+H2)的合成气来生产甲醇，所述合成气是在用于甲醇合成的正确化学计量组成下，在70巴至100巴的压力下，由组合POX加EHTR或组合ATR加EHTR产生的，从而不需要原料气体压缩机来将原料送入甲醇合成反应器回路。', p.abstract_en = 'In various implementations,  methanol is produced using a (CO+H2) containing synthesis gas produced from a combined POX plus EHTR or a combined ATR plus EHTR at a pressure of 70 bar to 100 bar at the correct stoichiometric composition for methanol synthesis so that no feed gas compressor is required for the feed to the methanol synthesis reactor loop.', p.application_date = '2014-05-28 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9283536B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/36', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 3, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14400905'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14400905', p.title_cn = '废物处理', p.title_en = 'Waste processing', p.abstract_cn = '本发明提供了一种用于热解和/或气化材料的系统和方法，所述材料例如有机涂层废物和有机材料，所述有机材料包括生物质、工业废物、城市固体废物和污泥。 在第一操作模式中，该方法/系统通过使热气体通过处理室(10)来加热处理室(10)中的材料。 这使其有机含量热解和/或气化以产生合成气，并且总是产生烟灰。 在第二操作模式中，该方法/系统增加热气体的氧含量，使得热气体内的氧与加热的烟灰反应形成一氧化碳。', p.abstract_en = 'This invention provides a system and method for pyrolyzing and/or gasifying material such as organically coated waste and organic materials including biomass,  industrial waste,  municipal solid waste and sludge. In a first mode of operation the method/system heats the material in a processing chamber (10) by passing hot gas therethrough. This pyrolyzes and/or gasifies the organic content it to produce syngas and,  invariably,  soot. In a second mode of operation the method/system increases the oxygen content of the hot gas such that the oxygen within the hot gas reacts with the heated soot to form carbon monoxide.', p.application_date = '2013-05-08 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9284504B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 2, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US13576640'}) SET p.application_no = 'US13576640', p.title_cn = '从含碳原料通过CO2转化生产热能源的方法和系统', p.title_en = 'Method and system for producing a source of thermodynamic energy by CO2 conversion from carbon-containing raw materials', p.abstract_cn = '本发明构成了一种通过含碳原料上的CO2转化来发电的方法和系统。 它包括通过基本上含有CO2的气流使含碳原料气化的步骤，其中在气化后获得的气流被氧保持器氧化和获得的失活氧保持器的氧化。 该过程允许对通过这些步骤的集合所产生的全球能量进行赋值，以供给发电系统，例如涡轮发电机。 本发明还对应于执行这样的处理的系统。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention constitutes a process and system to generate electricity from the conversion of CO2 over carbon-containing raw material. It comprises steps of gasification of the raw material containing carbon by means of a gaseous flow essentially containing CO2,  wherein the oxidation of the gaseous flow obtained after the gasification by oxygen holders and the oxidation of deactivated oxygen holders as obtained. The process allows to give value to the global energy as generated by the set of these steps to feed an electricity generating system,  such as a turboalternator. The invention also corresponds to a system to perform such a process.', p.application_date = '2010-08-08 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9284854B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/36', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'TW100141836'}) SET p.application_no = 'TW100141836', p.title_cn = '改良之多层复合吸气剂', p.title_en = 'Improved multi-layer composite getter', p.abstract_cn = '本发明揭示一种改良之多层复合吸气剂，以及其制造方法及使用该多层复合吸气剂之储存能源用的电化学装置', p.abstract_en = 'An improved multi-layer composite getter is disclosed,  as well as a method for its manufacturing and electrochemical devices for energy storage that employ said multi-layer getter composites.', p.application_date = '2011-11-16 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'TWI525036B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'AU2012338628'}) SET p.application_no = 'AU2012338628', p.title_cn = '增加合成气的氢含量的方法', p.title_en = 'Process for increasing hydrogen content of synthesis gas', p.abstract_cn = '方法描述了一种用于提高氢气含量的合成气(110)，其含有一种或多种硫化合物， 所述的合成气包含氢气，碳氧化物和蒸汽，并具有比，R，定义为R=(H', p.abstract_en = 'A process is described for increasing the hydrogen content of a synthesis gas (110) containing one or more sulphur compounds,  said synthesis gas comprising hydrogen,  carbon oxides and steam,  and having a ratio,  R,  defined as R = (H', p.application_date = '2012-10-10 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'AU2012338628B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/16', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'AU2012338629'}) SET p.application_no = 'AU2012338629', p.title_cn = '增加合成气的氢含量的方法', p.title_en = 'Process for increasing hydrogen content of synthesis gas', p.abstract_cn = '方法描述了一种用于提高合成气的氢含量含有一种或多种硫化合物， 所述的合成气包含氢气，碳氧化物和蒸汽，并具有比，R，定义为R=(H', p.abstract_en = 'A process is described for increasing the hydrogen content of a synthesis gas containing one or more sulphur compounds,  said synthesis gas comprising hydrogen,  carbon oxides and steam,  and having a ratio,  R,  defined as R = (H', p.application_date = '2012-10-10 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'AU2012338629B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/16', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CA2959873'}) SET p.application_no = 'CA2959873', p.title_cn = '液体-有机氢载波系统中基于催化肽的形成和氢化', p.title_en = 'LIQUID-ORGANIC HYDROGEN CARRIER SYSTEMS BASED ON CATALYTIC PEPTIDE FORMATION AND HYDROGENATION', p.abstract_cn = '本发明提供了一种系统和方法，存储氢气(H2)和按需释放，包括利用氨基链烷和醇，或(lohc)氨基醇作为液体载体的有机氢系统。(AE)或其N-甲基2-氨基乙醇衍生物2-(甲基氨基)乙醇反应，催化脱氢，形成环二肽(甘氨酸酸酐Ga)或其N，N-二甲基衍生物(N，N-二甲基镓)与氯化氢进行释放。类似地，(EO)和乙醇乙二胺进行催化脱氢，形成N，N‘-diacetylethylenediamine(dae)与氯化氢进行释放。甘氨酸的酸酐(ga)或N，N-二甲基镓可被氢化后(AE)或2-氨基2-(甲基氨基)乙醇，分别作为氢存储系统的功能。N，N‘-diacetylethylenediamine(dae)可被氢化后对ED和乙醇，其用作储氢系统。这些反应可以在多种化合物或络合物催化，包括钌络合物如本文所述。', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention provides a system and method of storing hydrogen (H2) and releasing it on demand,  comprising and making use of diaminoalkanes and alcohols,  or aminoalcohols as liquid-organic hydrogen carrier systems (LOHC). 2-aminoethanol (AE) or its N-methyl derivative 2-(methylamino)ethanol undergo catalytic dehydrogenation to form a cyclic dipeptide (glycine anhydride - GA) or its N, N-dimethyl derivative (N, N-dimethyl GA) with release of hydrogen. Similarly,  ethylenediamine (ED) and ethanol undergo catalytic dehydrogenation to form N, N\'-diacetylethylenediamine (DAE) with release of hydrogen. Glycine anhydride (GA) or N, N-dimethyl-GA may be hydrogenated back to 2-aminoethanol (AE) or 2-(methylamino)ethanol,  respectively,  each of which functions as a hydrogen storage system. N, N\'-diacetylethylenediamine (DAE) may be hydrogenated back to ED and ethanol,  which functions as a hydrogen storage system. These reactions may be catalyzed by a variety of compounds or complexes,  including Ruthenium complexes as described herein.', p.application_date = '2015-09-03 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CA2959873A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'DE102007006990'}) SET p.application_no = 'DE102007006990', p.title_cn = '方法和系统用于转化的原料气在气态和液态烃的部分氧化', p.title_en = 'Method and system for the conversion of raw gases in the partial oxidation of gaseous and liquid hydrocarbons', p.abstract_cn = '原料气(1)转换包括喷淬水在流动方向向下。 原料气冷却，将冷却后的原料从淬火装置除去气体。 加热原料气中的水通过喷嘴中喷出在被加热的原料气体的流量 从部分氧化在第一区的淬转换室， 使得原料气的控制，分步冷却产生在温度从800-900[℃]C 或通过类似的水蒸气分压力的增加。', p.abstract_en = 'Raw gas (1) conversion involves spraying quenched water in the flow directed downwards. The raw gas is cooled and the cooled raw gas is removed from a quenching device. The water in heated raw gas is sprayed in through the nozzles in the flow of the heated raw gas extracted from the partial oxidation in a first zone of the quenching conversion chamber,  such that a controlled and stepwise cooling of the raw gas is produced at a temperature from 800-900[deg] C or by similar increasing of the water vapor partial pressure.', p.application_date = '2007-02-07 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'DE102007006990B4', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/12', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'DE502010011001'}) SET p.application_no = 'DE502010011001', p.title_cn = '初级重整器具有可变的烟气流量', p.title_en = 'PRIMARY REFORMER HAVING VARIABLE SMOKE GAS FLOW', p.abstract_cn = '一种方法，公开了一种用于催化初级重整烃与蒸汽在升高的压力下通过分体管反应器和燃烧室。在分体式管系统，可以使用催化剂材料，待重整的烃水蒸汽转换合成气。分体式管系统由多个点火加热设施之间的分体式管包括多个串联布置燃烧器，燃烧器产生主要的向下指向的火焰。相关烧制设施提供与燃料和空气，与空气在被从相关送料器。烟道气体从而演化穿过所述烧制室从上至下进入下部区域中烧室中的水平设置的陶瓷烟气隧道彼此平行延伸并垂直于竖直分流管和被分配给一个烧制设施。烟气进入通过侧壁中的孔的烟气隧道。烟气在燃烧室的出口通入热回收装置。在每个烟气隧道的附加气体进入隧道的前侧，在烟气流动方向，所述含氧气体和非可燃气体，使得附加气体经过烟气隧道在整个长度的燃烧室。体积的附加气体通入到烟气隧道的调节。', p.abstract_en = 'A method is disclosed for catalytic primary reformation of hydrocarbons with steam at elevated pressure by means of a split tube reactor and a firing chamber. In the split tube system which can use a catalyst material,  hydrocarbons to be reformed are converted by water steam to synthesis gas. The split tube system is heated by a plurality of firing facilities between the split tubes which include a plurality of burners arranged in series,  the burners generating mainly downwardly directed flames. The relevant firing facilities are supplied with fuel and air,  with the air being withdrawn from the relevant feeders. The flue gas thus evolving passes through the firing chamber from top to bottom and enters in the lower area of the firing chamber into horizontally arranged ceramic flue gas tunnels extending in parallel to each other and perpendicular to the vertical split tubes and being allocated to one firing facility each. The flue gas enters through apertures in the lateral walls of the flue gas tunnels. The flue gas at the exit of the firing chamber is passed into heat recovery devices. In each flue gas tunnel an additional gas is fed into the tunnel\'s front side,  in flue gas flow direction,  wherein the gas containing oxygen and a non-combustible gas,  so that the additional gas passes the flue gas tunnels over the entire length of the firing chamber. The volume of the additional gas passed into the flue gas tunnels is regulated.', p.application_date = '2010-06-24 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'DE502010011001T2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'DE602009036098'}) SET p.application_no = 'DE602009036098', p.title_cn = '操作氢气发生器的方法', p.title_en = 'Method of operating a hydrogen generator', p.abstract_cn = '氢发生器包括 : 重整器(102)，被配置为生成含氢气体的重整反应中使用原料；燃烧器(104)被配置为加热重整器；空气供给装置(106)，配置成供给燃烧空气的燃烧器；第第一热交换器(108)配置成从烟道排出的气体中回收热量从燃烧器；第第一热介质通道(110)通过第第一热介质流过，第一热介质接收从烟气中回收的热量第一热交换器；第第一泵(112)配置成使第一第一热介质通道中的热介质流动；蓄热体(140)被配置成存储由第一回收的热量的热介质；和控制器(114)配置成使第一泵上的冷却步骤中的操作步骤降温至少重整器供给空气从空气供应装置连接，以在燃烧器状态下，不进行燃烧的燃烧器停止期间处理', p.abstract_en = 'A hydrogen generator includes :  a reformer (102) configured to generate a hydrogen-containing gas by a reforming reaction using a raw material;  a combustor (104) configured to heat the reformer;  an air supplying device (106) configured to supply combustion air to the combustor;  a first heat exchanger (108) configured to recover heat from a flue gas discharged from the combustor;  a first heat medium passage (110) through which a first heat medium flows,  the first heat medium receiving the heat recovered from the flue gas in the first heat exchanger;  a first pump (112) configured to cause the first heat medium in the first heat medium passage to flow;  a heat accumulator (140) configured to store the heat recovered by the first heat medium;  and a controller (114) configured to cause the first pump to operate in a cooling step that is a step of cooling down at least the reformer by supplying the air from the air supplying device to the combustor in a state where the combustor is not carrying out combustion during a stop processing', p.application_date = '2009-11-20 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'DE602009036098T2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'MX2012000871'}) SET p.application_no = 'MX2012000871', p.title_cn = '热引发的产氢的燃料电池系统。', p.title_en = 'THERMALLY PRIMED HYDROGEN-PRODUCING FUEL CELL SYSTEM.', p.abstract_cn = '产热引发的燃料处理装置和氢燃料电池系统，该系统包括相同。所述可热引发的制氢燃料加工组件包括至少一个的区域容纳在内部隔间加热封闭结构。在一些实施例中，将加热后的封隔结构的烤箱。在一些实施例中，该隔室也包含一净化区和/或加热组件。在一些实施例中，封隔结构适于加热并保持在等于或高于阈值温度的内部隔间，它可对应于生产温度适宜的氢气。在一些实施例中，封隔结构适于将该温度保持的时间段内不产生燃料电池系统功率和/或不产生功率来满足施加的载荷的系统。在一些实施例中，燃料电池系统适于提供备用电源的动力源，该密封结构可调整以提供电功率。', p.abstract_en = 'Thermally primed fuel processing assemblies and hydrogen-producing fuel cell systems that include the same. The thermally primed fuel processing assemblies include at least one hydrogen-producing region housed within an internal compartment of a heated containment structure. In some embodiments,  the heated containment structure is an oven. In some embodiments,  the compartment also contains a purification region and/or heating assembly. In some embodiments,  the containment structure is adapted to heat and maintain the internal compartment at or above a threshold temperature,  which may correspond to a suitable hydrogen-producing temperature. In some embodiments,  the containment structure is adapted to maintain this temperature during periods in which the fuel cell system is not producing power and/or not producing power to satisfy an applied load to the system. In some embodiments,  the fuel cell system is adapted to provide backup power to a power source,  which may be adapted to power t he containment structure.', p.application_date = '2008-03-14 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'MX337542B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'UAU201214186'}) SET p.application_no = 'UAU201214186', p.title_cn = '本发明涉及一种水制备氢气和氧气的混合物', p.title_en = 'PROCESS FOR THE PREPARATION OF HYDROGEN AND OXYGEN MIXTURE OF WATER', p.abstract_cn = '一种从水中制备氢和氧混合物的方法，包括通过加热并通过电场使其通过，从水中制备蒸汽雾混合物。 蒸汽雾混合物是通过水通过置于径向相对于旋转轴的锥状喷嘴而获得的，其中氢气和氧气是从锥状喷嘴出口处的蒸汽雾混合物通过脉冲直流电场而获得的。', p.abstract_en = 'The method of obtaining a mixture of hydrogen and oxygen from water involves obtaining a vaporous mixture from water by heating and passing it through an electric field. The vapor-fog mixture is obtained by passing water through cone-shaped nozzles,  which are placed radially relative to the axis of rotation,  while hydrogen and oxygen are obtained from the vapor-fog mixture at the outlet of the cone-shaped nozzles,  passing it through a pulsed electric field of direct current.', p.application_date = '2012-12-13 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'UA105053U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'UAU201507369'}) SET p.application_no = 'UAU201507369', p.title_cn = '用于水制备氢气和氧气的混合物', p.title_en = 'DEVICE FOR THE PREPARATION OF HYDROGEN AND OXYGEN MIXTURE OF WATER', p.abstract_cn = '一种从水中制备氢和氧混合物的装置，包括与放置电极的水分室相连的壳体。 在具有壳体和盖的圆柱形壳体中，在电动机轴上安装圆盘形转子，转子一侧设置有供水室，转子具有径向通道，其中安装锥状喷嘴(拉瓦喷嘴)的旋涡组合流体加速器，其螺柱端固定在细面上。 另一方面，转子具有直径的点，它与圆柱形的水分室体形成，其中，在壳体上以同心环的形式放置在高压电极的多极板的绝缘体上。 沿外围，轴向，水分室具有设置在密封圆柱壳中的氢气和氧气的输出巡逻，在密封圆柱壳的盖中设置有入口巡逻。', p.abstract_en = 'The device for obtaining a mixture of hydrogen and oxygen from water contains a housing that is connected to the water splitting chamber in which the electrodes are placed. In the cylindrical housing,  which has a housing and a cover,  a rotor in the form of a disk is installed on the shaft of the electric motor,  on one side of the rotor there is a water supply chamber,  from which the rotor has radial channels in which vortex combined liquid accelerators are installed in the form of cone-shaped nozzles (Laval nozzles) interconnected,  at the ends of which direct-flow,  spiral,  vortex,  centrifugal and fog-forming nozzles are fixed. On the other hand,  the rotor has a diametrical turn,  which forms a water splitting chamber with a cylindrical body,  in which multipolar plates of high-voltage electrodes in the form of concentric rings are placed on the insulators. Along the periphery,  in the axial direction,  the water splitting chamber has outlet pipes for hydrogen and oxygen,  which are placed in an airtight cylindrical housing,  and an inlet pipe is placed in the lid of the sealed cylindrical housing.', p.application_date = '2015-07-22 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'UA105122U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WOIL15050888'}) SET p.application_no = 'WOIL15050888', p.title_cn = '液体有机氢载体系统基于催化肽的形成和氢化', p.title_en = 'LIQUID-ORGANIC HYDROGEN CARRIER SYSTEMS BASED ON CATALYTIC PEPTIDE FORMATION AND HYDROGENATION', p.abstract_cn = '本发明提供了一种储氢的系统和方法(H2)和释放点播， 包括，利用二氨基烷烃和醇，或氨基醇作为液体有机氢载体系统(lohc)。 2-氨基乙醇(AE)或其N-甲基衍生物2-(甲氨基)乙醇进行催化脱氢形成的环状二肽(甘氨酸 酸酐Ga)或其N，N-二甲基衍生物(N，N-二甲基镓)与释放氢。 类似地，乙二胺(ED)和乙醇进行催化脱氢，形成N，N‘-diacetylethylenediamine(dae)与释放氢。 甘氨酸的酸酐(ga)或N，N-二甲基镓可被氢化后，以2-氨基乙醇(AE)或2-(甲氨基)乙醇， 分别，其中每个功能作为氢存储系统。 N，N‘-diacetylethylenediamine(dae)可被氢化后对ED进行和乙醇，其功能是作为储氢系统。 这些反应可以催化多种的化合物或配合物包括钌配合物如本文所述。', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention provides a system and method of storing hydrogen (H2) and releasing it on demand,  comprising and making use of diaminoalkanes and alcohols,  or aminoalcohols as liquid-organic hydrogen carrier systems (LOHC). 2-aminoethanol (AE) or its N-methyl derivative 2-(methylamino)ethanol undergo catalytic dehydrogenation to form a cyclic dipeptide (glycine anhydride - GA) or its N, N-dimethyl derivative (N, N-dimethyl GA) with release of hydrogen. Similarly,  ethylenediamine (ED) and ethanol undergo catalytic dehydrogenation to form N, N\'-diacetylethylenediamine (DAE) with release of hydrogen. Glycine anhydride (GA) or N, N-dimethyl-GA may be hydrogenated back to 2-aminoethanol (AE) or 2-(methylamino)ethanol,  respectively,  each of which functions as a hydrogen storage system. N, N\'-diacetylethylenediamine (DAE) may be hydrogenated back to ED and ethanol,  which functions as a hydrogen storage system. These reactions may be catalyzed by a variety of compounds or complexes,  including Ruthenium complexes as described herein.', p.application_date = '2015-09-03 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016035081A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201510742603.3'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201510742603.3', p.title_cn = '一种合成氨联产含碳化学品的工艺', p.title_en = 'Ammonia-synthesis and carbon-containing-chemical combinative production technology', p.abstract_cn = '一种合成氨联产含碳化学品的工艺是将含碳气源，先经甲烷重整单元，再经净化单元；或含碳气源直接经净化单元，使气体中H2/CO摩尔比满足合成油或低碳醇或低碳烯烃的要求，进入反应器进行合成油反应或低碳醇反应或低碳烯烃反应；产物经过分离装置分离，剩余尾气送入CO变换装置，然后经过脱碳装置脱掉CO2，或剩余尾气直接经过脱碳装置脱掉CO2，再经过PSA提氢装置得到高纯度的氢气，送入合成氨工段，同时通过空分装置将合适比例的氮气送入合成氨工段。本发明具有碳的利用高，效率经济效益好的优点。', p.abstract_en = 'A process for synthesizing ammonia and co-producing carbon-containing chemical includes such steps as reforming the carbon-containing gas source in methane reforming unit,  purifying Or the carbon-containing gas source directly passes through the purification unit to make the H2/CO molar ratio in the gas meet the requirements of synthetic oil or low-carbon alcohol or low-carbon olefin,  and then enters the reactor for synthetic oil reaction,  low-carbon alcohol reaction or low-carbon olefin reaction; the product is separated by separation device,  the residual tail gas is fed into CO conversion device,  and then CO2 is removed by decarbonization device,  or the residual tail gas is directly removed by decarbonization device,  and CO2 is removed by PSA hydrogen extraction device to obtain high-purity hydrogen gas,  which is fed into synthetic ammonia section,  and at the same time,  a proper proportion of nitrogen gas is fed into synthetic ammonia section by air separation device The present invention has the advantages of high carbon utilization,  high efficiency and high economic benefit', p.application_date = '2015-11-04 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105384147A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/34', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201520607536.X'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201520607536.X', p.title_cn = '一种低压多功能氢气机', p.title_en = 'Multi -functional hydrogen of low pressure machine', p.abstract_cn = '一种低压多功能氢气机，其形状、构造主要特征是；加碱桶通过上控制阀连通稳压瓶并延伸到隔离板以下的位置，下控制阀装在反应桶的隔离板以下的位置，冷却桶由一次冷却室置于二次冷却室的内部，通过导气管1与反应桶连通，通过双S型排水、加压和过压保护装置与外部连通，通过L型连通管、导气管2与二次冷却室连通，两个S型排水、加压和过压保护装置分别装在一次冷却室和二次冷却室的中部位置，二次冷却室通过转换阀与外部连通，变径充球口装在二次冷却室的上部位置，变径进水口装在二次冷却室的下部位置。', p.abstract_en = 'The utility model provides a multi -functional hydrogen of low pressure machine which shape,  structure leading features are,  it communicates the steady voltage bottle and extends to the position below the division board through last control valve to add the alkali bucket,  the position below the division board of reaction bucket is adorned to the control valve down,  the cooling tank is arranged in the inside of secondary cooling room by the primary cooling room,  through air duct 1 and reaction bucket intercommunication,  through the drainage of two S type,  pressurization and overvoltage protector and outside intercommunication,  through L type communicating pipe,  air duct 2 and secondary cooling room intercommunication,  the drainage of two S types,  pressurization and overvoltage protector adorn the middle part position in primary cooling room and secondary cooling room respectively,  secondary cooling passes through the room change -over valve and outside intercommunication,  the reducing fills the upper portion position of ball mouth dress in the secondary cooling room,  reducing water inlet dress is in the lower part position of secondary cooling room.', p.application_date = '2015-08-07 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN205076797U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/08', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201520669459.0'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201520669459.0', p.title_cn = '一种汽车发动机等离子体自动制氢环保节能设备', p.title_en = 'Automatic hydrogen manufacturing environmental protection and energy saving equipment of automobile engine plasma', p.abstract_cn = '一种汽车发动机等离子体自动制氢环保节能设备：是由水箱、水泵、电磁阀、发动机排气管、水分蒸发器、金属催化器、电加热器、温度传感器、智能控制器、等离子体电源、等离子体催化器、阻火器、发动机进气管、氢气喷管、转速传感器和氧传感器构成，其特征是电加热器的出气管连接水分蒸发器的进水管，水分蒸发器和金属催化器制成一体安装在排气管上，金属催化器的出气管连接等离子体催化器，等离体子催化器的出气管连接阻火器，阻火器连接氢气喷管，氢气喷管安装在发动机进气管上，智能控制器和等离子体电源制成一体，智能控制器和电加热器、温度传感器、氧传感器、发动机转速传感器、电磁阀、水泵电连接，等离子体电源和等离子体催化器电连接。', p.abstract_en = 'The utility model provides an automatic hydrogen manufacturing environmental protection and energy saving equipment of automobile engine plasma :  by the water tank,  a water pump,  the solenoid valve,  engine exhaust pipe,  the evaporation of water ware,  the metal catalyst converter,  electric heater,  a weighing sensor and a temperature sensor,  the intelligent control ware,  the plasma power,  the plasma catalyst converter,  the spark arrester,  engine intake manifold,  the hydrogen spray tube,  speed sensor and oxygen sensor constitute,  the inlet tube of evaporation of water ware is connected to characterized by electric heater\'s outlet duct,  evaporation of water ware and metal catalyst converter are made an organic whole and are installed on the blast pipe,  the plasma catalyst converter is connected to the outlet duct of metal catalyst converter,  the spark arrester is connected to the outlet duct of plasmon catalyst converter,  the hydrogen spray tube is connected to the spark arrester,  the hydrogen spray tube is installed on engine intake manifold,  an organic whole is made to intelligent control ware and plasma power,  intelligent control ware and electric heater,  a weighing sensor and a temperature sensor,  oxygen sensor,  engine speed sensor,  the solenoid valve,  the water pump electricity is connected,  plasma power and plasma catalyst converter electricity are connected.', p.application_date = '2015-08-25 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN205076798U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/32', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201520753026.3'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201520753026.3', p.title_cn = '一种带超声辅助汽化的重整制氢微反应器', p.title_en = 'Take reformation hydrogen manufacturing micro -reactor of supplementary vaporization of supersound', p.abstract_cn = '本实用新型公开了一种带超声辅助汽化的重整制氢微反应器。从下至上依次包括下盖板、蒸发单元、预热单元、重整制氢反应单元和上盖板；从下至上依次组成雾化蒸发腔、预热腔、重整制氢反应腔和产物气体缓冲腔。本实用新型反应物液体通过进料孔进入雾化腔后在超声换能器的作用下雾化成飘逸气雾，使反应物分散均匀，雾化液滴接触蒸发单元后迅速吸热蒸发成气体，提高工质液体的蒸发效率；反应物液体雾化蒸发压强迅速增大，能减小反应器所需入口压力；调节超声换能器的功率达到调节重整反应腔入口气体流量；通过超声波换能器的雾化作用，反应物液化蒸发过程连续，能显著减小重整制氢反应单元入口气体的流量脉动，提高反应腔内流速分布均匀度和反应效率。', p.abstract_en = 'The utility model discloses a take reformation hydrogen manufacturing micro -reactor of supplementary vaporization of supersound. From down supremely lap,  evaporate the unit under including in proper order,  preheat the unit,  reformation hydrogen generation unit and upper cover plate,  from down supremely constituteing atomizing evaporation chamber in proper order,  preheating the gaseous cushion chamber of chamber,  reformation hydrogen generation chamber and result. The utility model discloses reactant fluid passage feed port atomizes into elegant aerial fog after getting into spray chamber under ultrasonic transducer\'s effect,  it is even to make the reactant disperse,  and gas is evaporated in rapid heat absorption behind the atomized liquid contact evaporation unit,  improves the evaporation efficiency of working medium liquid,  reactant liquid atomization evaporation pressure increases rapidly,  can reduce the required inlet pressure of reactor,  the power of adjusting ultrasonic transducer reaches adjusts reforming reaction chamber entry gas flow,  through ultrasonic transducer\'s atomizing,  reactant liquefaction evaporation process is continuous,  can show the flow pulsation that reduces to reform hydrogen generation unit inlet gas,  improves the interior velocity of flow distribution degree of consistency of reaction chamber and reaction efficiency.', p.application_date = '2015-09-25 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN205076799U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/32', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'EP00304298'}) SET p.application_no = 'EP00304298', p.title_cn = '氢气发生器', p.title_en = 'Hydrogen generator', p.abstract_cn = '本说明书公开了一种氢气发生器，用于产生氢气， 包括至少一个燃料供给部，用于将烃类燃料， 燃料燃烧部， 供水部分， 一种气体混合部，用于混合燃料和水， 和重整部分填充有重整催化剂， 其中至少一个所述气体混合部分和加热的重整部产生的废气 在燃烧部。 氢气发生器根据本发明的目的是提高热效率， 降低热损失的装置，具有简单的结构和收集余热用于有效使用 。', p.abstract_en = 'The present specification discloses a hydrogen generator for generating a hydrogen gas,  comprising at least a fuel supply part for supplying a hydrocarbon type fuel,  a fuel combustion part,  a water supply part,  a gas mixing part for mixing the fuel and water,  and a reforming part filled with a reforming catalyst,  wherein at least one of the gas mixing part and the reforming part is heated by an exhaust gas generated in the combustion part. The hydrogen generator according to the present invention aims to improve the heat efficiency,  reducing the heat loss from the apparatus with a simple constitution and collecting the waste heat for an effective use thereof.', p.application_date = '2000-05-22 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'EP1055638B1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'EP13810310'}) SET p.application_no = 'EP13810310', p.title_cn = '燃料处理装置', p.title_en = 'FUEL PROCESSING DEVICE', p.abstract_cn = '提供一种燃料处理装置，包括 : 一燃烧单元设有热源； 一种脱硫单元提取硫组分从源气体； 重整单元，用于生成， 从脱硫源气体，含氢气体具有氢作为主要成分； 和低温转换单元，其配备有一发热催化剂用于降低在含氢的杂质浓度 气体。 重整单元，脱硫单元被配置为以围绕所述燃烧单元， 并向外同心地设置在给定顺序从所述燃烧单元。 本发明还包括预热通道，连接到脱硫单元， 其提供给所述燃烧单元的底部通过保温材料， 使得源气体进行预热，热量从燃烧器。', p.abstract_en = 'Provided is a fuel processing device including :  a combustion unit equipped with a heat source;  a desulfurization unit for extracting a sulfur component from the source gas;  a reforming unit for generating,  from the desulfurized source gas,  a hydrogen-containing gas having hydrogen as a main component thereof;  and a low-temperature conversion unit equipped with an exothermic catalyst for reducing the impurity concentration in the hydrogen-containing gas. The reforming unit and the desulfurization unit are configured so as to surround the combustion unit,  and are disposed concentrically in the given order facing outwards from the combustion unit. The present invention further includes a preheating passage which is connected to the desulfurization unit,  and which is provided to a bottom part of the combustion unit via a heat insulation material,  such that the source gas is preheated by heat from the combustion unit.', p.application_date = '2013-06-24 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'EP2735541B1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2011140108'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2011140108', p.title_cn = '制氢方法', p.title_en = 'Hydrogen production method', p.abstract_cn = '所要解决的问题：提供一种能够在室温下高效地产生大量氢气的氢气产生剂，以及提供一种氢气的制造方法。方案：该氢产生剂以Al金属和氢氧化钙为主要成分，Al金属与碱土化合物的重量比为80/20~98/2。所述氢气发生剂中，所述碱土化合物为氢氧化钙，所述Al金属与所述氢氧化钙的粒径比为10/1~200/1。在该制备方法中，通过将添加氢产生剂之后的水的pH保持在7或更高，可以在没有外部过热的情况下制备氢，并且可以通过形成卡托特石来有效地制备氢。版权所有：(C)2013，JPO&INPIT', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To provide a hydrogen generating agent capable of generating a large amount of hydrogen efficiently at room temperature,  and to provide a method for producing hydrogen gas. SOLUTION :  This hydrogen generating agent is constituted of an Al metal and calcium hydroxide as main components,  and the weight ratio between the Al metal and an alkaline earth compound is 80/20-98/2. In the hydrogen generating agent,  the alkaline earth compound is calcium hydroxide,  and the particle size ratio between the Al metal and the calcium hydroxide is 10/1-200/1. In the production method,  hydrogen can be produced without external overheating by keeping pH of water after addition of the hydrogen generating agent at 7 or higher,  and hydrogen can be formed efficiently by forming Katoite. COPYRIGHT :  (C)2013, JPO&INPIT', p.application_date = '2011-06-24 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP5883240B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/08', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'KR1020167002755'}) SET p.application_no = 'KR1020167002755', p.title_cn = '便携式氢水生成罐', p.title_en = 'PORTABLE HYDROGEN WATER GENERATING POT', p.abstract_cn = '提供一种便携式氢水生成罐，该便携式氢水生成罐不仅使用饮用水，而且使用水或以水为主要成分的液体如咖啡作为原水，可以随时随地在短时间内生成高浓度的可饮用氢水，其中该便携式氢水生成罐包括：由透明圆柱形构件1a等制成的容器主体1；设置在位于容器主体下部的下部上层块1b中的定量供水装置2，该定量供水装置2将容器主体1中容纳的一定量的水供应到形成在下部的下盖1c中的化学容器6中；配备有止回阀3的气体通道4，其也设置在下部的上层块1b中，气体通道4允许在化学罐6中产生的氢气移动到容器主体1；配置在形成容器主体1的下部的下层的下盖1c内的、收容氢产生剂5的药剂箱6；上部块体，其形成位于容器主体1的上部的排出口部7；以及盖9，安装有减压阀8，可装卸地外装于排出口部7。', p.abstract_en = 'To provide a portable hydrogen-water generating pot that can generate highly concentrated drinkable hydrogen water anytime and anywhere in a short amount of time by using not only drinking water but also water or liquids,  such as coffee,  that have water as their major ingredient as raw water,  wherein the portable hydrogen-water generating pot comprises a vessel\'s main body 1 made of a transparent cylindrical member 1a etc.;  a fixed-quantity water supply means 2 provided in the lower part\'s upper layer block 1b located in the lower part of the vessel\'s main body,  the fixed-quantity water supply means 2 supplying a certain quantity of water contained in the vessel\'s main body 1 to a chemical tank 6 created in the lower lid 1c of the lower part;  a gas passage 4,  equipped with a check valve 3,  also provided in the lower part\'s upper layer block 1b,  the gas passage 4 allowing hydrogen gas generated in the chemical tank 6 to move to the vessel\'s main body 1;  a chemical tank 6,  for containing a hydrogen-generating agent 5,  arranged in the lower lid 1c that forms the lower layer of the lower part of the vessel\'s main body 1;  an upper part block that forms the discharge port part 7 located in the upper part of the vessel\'s main body 1;  and a lid 9,  equipped with a pressure reducing valve 8,  detachably and externally attached to the discharge port part 7.', p.application_date = '2013-08-26 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'KR1020160027145A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/08', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'MX2015014818'}) SET p.application_no = 'MX2015014818', p.title_cn = '使用在氨和氢的排出管线。', p.title_en = 'VENT LINE FOR USE IN AMMONIA AND HYDROGEN PLANTS.', p.abstract_cn = 'Iin氨或氢装置，包括脱硫段，一种重整段和换档段，该换档段包括低温变换转换器和中温变换炉，一个通风线路下游设置有从低温度变换转换器和介质温度位移转换器为以允许所述换档转换器被重新加热，具有促-池气体在低压(通常是3-7巴)。这样水蒸汽冷凝过程中避免了煤气，通过应用该通气口线成为可能节约了大量时间，更具体讲$time，用于临时关闭后重启的生产，由于加热循环中的LTS/手动切换开关的转换器避免了氮气。', p.abstract_en = 'IIn an ammonia or hydrogen plant comprising a desulfurisation section,  a reforming section and a shift section,  where the shift section comprises a low temperature shift converter and a medium temperature shift converter,  a vent line is arranged downstream from the low temperature shift converter and the medium temperature shift converter in order to allow the shift converters to be re-heated with pro- cess gas at a low pressure (typically 3-7 bar). This way condensation of water vapour in the process gas is avoided. By applying this vent line it becomes possible to save significant time,  more specifically 8-24 hours,  for restarting the production after temporary shut-down thereof,  because a heat-up of the LTS/MTS converter in circulating nitrogen is avoided.', p.application_date = '2014-04-16 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'MX2015014818A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'BRPI0604607'}) SET p.application_no = 'BRPI0604607', p.title_cn = '可逆储氢的方法基于离子液体， 方法用于获得分子氢储存器，和，分子氢储存器', p.title_en = 'process of reversible hydrogen storage based on ionic liquids,  process for the attainment of molecular hydrogen reservoir,  and,  molecular hydrogen reservoir', p.abstract_cn = '可逆储氢的方法在基于离子液体中的分子水库本发明描述了氢的可逆过程 存储在离子液体中。 在一优选的方面， 所述离子液体的合力结CátioncáTiON imidazóLiCo1-x-y-zMnxNiyAlzO2，与循环hexano的环， 提供分子结构能够存储大量的氢， 其回收，取用简单加热hidrogenadoshidrogenados的衍生物在催化剂的存在下。 本发明的方法安全， 干净卫生，经济， 超过满足所需要的无价值的压力的蒸汽，密度高，不存在易燃性高的热稳定性。', p.abstract_en = 'process of reversible hydrogen storage in molecular reservoirs based in ionic liquids the present invention describes reversible processes of hydrogen storage in ionic liquids. in a preferential aspect,  the ionic liquid are resultant of the junction of cátioncátion imidazólico with the ring of the cycle-hexano,  providing molecular structures capable to storage significant amounts of hydrogen,  being its recovery gotten for simple heating of the derivatives hidrogenadoshidrogenados in presence of catalysers. the process of the invention is safe,  clean and economic,  beyond satisfying the requisite ones of pressure of worthless vapor,  high density,  absence of inflammability and high thermal stability.', p.application_date = '2006-10-17 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'BRPI0604607B1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/26', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14356608'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14356608', p.title_cn = '内换热转化管', p.title_en = 'Reformer tube with internal heat exchange', p.abstract_cn = '一种用于通过含烃进料气体(优选天然气)的蒸汽重整生产合成气的重整器管，包括一个或多个螺旋盘管，所述螺旋盘管布置在重整催化剂的催化剂床内，并且在位于催化剂床内的它们的长度的一部分上螺旋盘管，否则是直的，其中换热器管的直比例和/或螺旋盘管部分的螺旋节距在催化剂床内改变，并且与压降、热交换性能和耐腐蚀性的要求相匹配。', p.abstract_en = 'A reformer tube for producing synthesis gas by steam reforming of hydrocarbon-containing feed gases,  preferably natural gas,  includes one or more helically coiled heat exchanger tubes which are arranged within a catalyst bed of a reforming catalyst and are helically coiled over part of their length located within the catalyst bed and are otherwise straight are present,  where the straight proportion of the heat exchanger tubes and/or the helix pitch of the helically coiled part alters within the catalyst bed and matching to requirements of the pressure drop,  the heat exchange properties,  and the corrosion resistance.', p.application_date = '2012-11-07 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9278328B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 2, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US13111922'}) SET p.application_no = 'US13111922', p.title_cn = '可见光二氧化钛光催化剂及其制备方法和使用方法', p.title_en = 'Visible light titania photocatalyst,  method for making same,  and processes for use thereof', p.abstract_cn = '具有高可见光光催化活性的二氧化钛的制备方法为 : (a)将二氧化钛与碳粉混合； (b)在惰性或弱反应性气氛中将二氧化钛/碳粉末混合物加热至至少约1000°C； 和(c)此后在氧化气氛中将所得粉末混合物加热到约350至约1000°C的温度范围。 所得二氧化钛可用于气体的解毒或消毒液体，用于从水介质中产生氢，以及用于防晒剂和太阳镜中。', p.abstract_en = 'Titania having high visible light photocatalytic activity is prepared by (a) mixing titania with carbon powder;  (b) heating the titania/carbon powder mixture to at least about 1000° C. in an inert or weakly reactive atmosphere;  and (c) thereafter heating the resultant powder mixture to a temperature in the range of about 350 to about 1000° C. in an oxidizing atmosphere. The resultant titania may be used for detoxifying or disinfecting liquids for gases,  for generating hydrogen from aqueous media and in sunscreens and sunglasses.', p.application_date = '2011-05-19 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9278337B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14115095'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14115095', p.title_cn = '混合金属氧化物循环水分解', p.title_en = 'Hybrid metal oxide cycle water splitting', p.abstract_cn = '本发明提供一种混合热化学分水循环，其中热还原的金属氧化物颗粒用于置换分水电解槽中的一些但不是全部电需求。 在这些混合循环中，与仅需要热能从水产生氢的两步金属氧化物热化学循环相比，热还原温度显著降低。 另外，与必须在降低的氧气压力下进行还原步骤的常规高温循环不同，所提出的混合循环中的还原步骤可以在空气中进行，从而允许通过具有无窗空腔接收器的太阳能动力塔进行热输入。', p.abstract_en = 'Hybrid thermochemical water splitting cycles are provided in which thermally reduced metal oxides particles are used to displace some but not all of the electrical requirements in a water splitting electrolytic cell. In these hybrid cycles,  the thermal reduction temperature is significantly reduced compared to two-step metal-oxide thermochemical cycles in which only thermal energy is required to produce hydrogen from water. Also,  unlike the conventional higher temperature cycles where the reduction step must be carried out under reduced oxygen pressure,  the reduction step in the proposed hybrid cycles can be carried out in air,  allowing for thermal input by a solar power tower with a windowless,  cavity receiver.', p.application_date = '2011-07-29 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9279188B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/06', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 4, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'MX2015008003'}) SET p.application_no = 'MX2015008003', p.title_cn = '一种储氢材料。', p.title_en = 'A HYDROGEN-STORAGE-MATERIAL.', p.abstract_cn = '一种储氢材料包括氨硼烷和聚(环氧乙烷)，其中所述聚(环氧乙烷)具有的重均分子量大于或等于MDA和的小于或等于MDA。', p.abstract_en = 'A hydrogen-storage-material comprising ammonia borane and poly(ethylene oxide),  wherein the poly(ethylene oxide) has a weight average molecular weight of greater than or equal to 1MDa and of less than or equal to 9MDa.', p.application_date = '2013-12-20 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'MX2015008003A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'TH1301005750'}) SET p.application_no = 'TH1301005750', p.title_cn = '合成气用炭质原料气化的装置和工艺', p.title_en = 'The invention relates to a device and a process for gasifying synthetic gas by using a carbonaceous raw material', p.abstract_cn = '提供了一种处理方法和一套机器，用于气化碳基物质。该方法产生未经净化的合成气体，可在焦油去除区进行进一步熏蒸，以获得热焦油气体。所述方法包括使所述碳基材料与气体接触，所述气体在气体化区域中具有氧分子，以使所述碳基材料的一部分气化，以及用于第一气体产品。将碳基材料的其余部分与燃烧区域中含有氧分子的气体接触，以使碳基材料的附加体积气化并产生第一气体。将碳基材料的其余部分与燃烧区域中含有氧分子的气体接触，以使碳基材料的附加体积部分气化，并产生第二种气体产品。如果将固体、第一类气体产品和第二类气体产品混合在一起，以产生包括一氧化碳(CO)、二氧化碳(CO2)和焦油在内的未净化气体。将未经净化的合成气与焦油去除区中含有氧分子的气体接触，产生这样的热合成气。', p.abstract_en = 'A process and a set of machines are provided for gasifying carbon-based materials. The process produces an unpurified synthesis gas which can be further fumigated in a tar removal zone to obtain a hot tar gas. The method includes contacting the carbon-based material with a gas having oxygen molecules in a gasification region to vaporize a portion of the carbon-based material,  and for a first gas product. The remainder of the carbon-based material is contacted with a gas containing oxygen molecules in the combustion zone to vaporize an additional volume of the carbon-based material and produce a first gas. The remainder of the carbon-based material is contacted with a gas containing oxygen molecules in the combustion zone to vaporize an additional volume portion of the carbon-based material and produce a second gas product. If the solids,  the first gaseous product and the second gaseous product are mixed together to produce an unpurified gas including carbon monoxide (CO),  carbon dioxide (CO2) and tar. The unpurified synthesis gas is contacted with a gas containing oxygen molecules in the tar removal zone to produce such a thermal synthesis gas.', p.application_date = '2013-10-04 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'TH146014A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'TH1401003464'}) SET p.application_no = 'TH1401003464', p.title_cn = '合成气的制造方法和装置，以及液体燃料的合成方法和装置。', p.title_en = 'Method and apparatus for producing synthesis gas,  and method and apparatus for synthesizing liquid fuel.', p.abstract_cn = 'DC60(18/06/14)一种合成气的生产方法，其能够获得具有良好组成的合成气，该合成气实际上没有煤烟(煤烟)，在方便的设备下可以很好地有效。通过使用生物燃料作为原料，并使生产高质量液体燃料如甲醇、苯、 各种轻油可以依靠此供应蒸汽到液体生物燃料，这是由生物质的热分解引起的气化到管道内的自由空间制成的。反应管中不充满催化剂的反应。并通过吸热反应在液体生物燃料和蒸汽之间与蒸汽发生反应重整，通过反应管壁从外部加热到800°C~1200°C。对纵横比进行设置 供给的水蒸气与液体生物燃料中所含的碳之间的摩尔([H2O]/[C])为0.3或更大，并且以H2、CO为主要成分的良好组成的合成气体。几乎没有原油，煤烟(煤烟)包括精选图图', p.abstract_en = 'DC60 (18/06/14) A production method of synthetic gas capable of obtaining a synthetic gas with good composition,  which Virtually no soot (soot) can be effective well with convenient equipment. By using biofuels as raw materials and making it possible to produce high quality liquid fuels such as methanol,  benzene,  Various light oils Can by relying on this Supply steam to liquid biofuels,  which is caused by The thermal decomposition of biomass to the gasification free space within the pipeline is made. Reaction that does not fill the catalist inside the reaction tube. And cause reaction Reforming with steam between liquid biofuels and steam by endothermic reaction,  heated to 800 ° C ~ 1200 ° C from outside through the reaction pipe wall. Make a setting for the aspect ratio The mole between the supplied water vapor and the carbon contained in liquid biofuels ([H2O] / [C]) is 0.3 or more and a well-composed synthetic gas with H2,  CO is the main component. With almost no crude oil,  soot (soot) included Selected Figure Figure 2', p.application_date = '2014-06-18 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'TH146609A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/22', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'TH1401003563'}) SET p.application_no = 'TH1401003563', p.title_cn = '合成气生产的工艺和系统', p.title_en = 'A process and system for the production of synthesis gas', p.abstract_cn = 'DC60(20/06/57)描述了使用烃将CO2转化为一氧化碳CO的方法和设备。在另外的特征中， 用于合成合成气的方法和设备以及用于将合成气转化为合成烃的方法和仪器。无效和/或非无效函数。使用CO2和碳氢化合物的无效函数被描述为调整过程和仪器以改变工业过程排放的CO2，因此可以减少大气中排放的二氧化碳', p.abstract_en = 'DC60 (20/06/57) The process and equipment for the conversion of CO2 to carbon monoxide CO using hydrocarbons are described. In additional features,  Processes and equipment for the synthesis of synthetic gases and processes and instruments for the conversion of synthetic gases to synthetic hydrocarbons. Nullised and / or non-nonlised functions. Nullised functions using CO2 and hydrocarbons are described as processes and instruments are adjusted to alter the CO2 emitted by Industrial processes,  and therefore the amount of carbon dioxide emitted In the atmosphere may be reduced', p.application_date = '2014-06-20 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'TH147206A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/24', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'AU2012367935'}) SET p.application_no = 'AU2012367935', p.title_cn = '离子液体用于储氢的使用', p.title_en = 'Use of an ionic liquid for storing hydrogen', p.abstract_cn = '储氢的方法形成第一离子液体的诱导硼氢化物在第二离子液体，其包括阳离子和阴离子包括硼酸盐，和形成第二离子液体通过释放氢从第一离子液体以水和/或催化剂，该方法的特征在于，第一和第二离子液体均与水混溶的和第二离子液体分离，特别是盐析，从水中的溶液加入分离诱导剂；某些离子液体用于存储和释放氢的包括硼氢化物或用于制备离子液体用于存储和释放氢的包括硼酸盐；和制备方法的离子液体用于存储和释放氢的包括硼氢化物。', p.abstract_en = 'Method of storing hydrogen by forming a first ionic liquid by inducing a borohydride in a second ionic liquid comprising a cation and an anion comprising borate,  and forming the second ionic liquid by releasing the hydrogen out of the first ionic liquid by using water and/or a catalyst,  which method is characterized in that the first and the second ionic liquid are both water miscible and the second ionic liquid is separated,  particularly is salted out,  from solution in water by adding a separation inducer;  certain ionic liquids for storing and releasing hydrogen comprising a borohydride or for preparing a ionic liquid for storing and releasing hydrogen comprising a borate;  and a process for preparing ionic liquids for storing and releasing hydrogen comprising a borohydride.', p.application_date = '2012-12-20 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'AU2012367935B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/06', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'ES12704389'}) SET p.application_no = 'ES12704389', p.title_cn = '装置的分解化学化合物及相应的方法', p.title_en = 'Device decomposition of a chemical compound and corresponding method', p.abstract_cn = '分切装置的化学化合物(3)， 包括温度控制装置(4)， 两独立气室(6， 7)， 和元件(8)包括热释电材料，具有至少两个表面(10， 11)具有不同的电荷的极性，并至少部分地接触所述化学化合物的被 分体式。 至少两个表面(10， 11)每面一个所述分开的气室(6， 7)， 和气体(12， 13)在表面(10，11)分别到达气室与各自的相关表面(10，11)。', p.abstract_en = 'Device for splitting a chemical compound (3),  comprising a temperature control device (4),  two separate gas chambers (6,  7),  and an element (8) which comprises a pyroelectric material and has at least two surfaces (10,  11) that have charges of different polarity and are at least partially in contact with the chemical compound to be split. At least two of the surfaces (10,  11) each face one of the separate gas chambers (6,  7),  and the gases (12,  13) produced on the surfaces (10,  11) separately reach the gas chamber associated with the respective surface (10,  11).', p.application_date = '2012-02-07 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'ES2562331T3', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2015540209'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2015540209', p.title_cn = '再生废的氢化物燃料', p.title_en = 'Regeneration of spent hydride fuel', p.abstract_cn = '用于再生失效的氢化物燃料的方法包括步骤 : (1)生成的肼的等离子体；例如液氨中产生肼溶液的使用中产生的等离子体的辉光放电单元，(2)使该废氢化物燃料与所述肼和(3)然后分离再生的氢化物燃料。可广泛用于再生失效的过程氢化物运输燃料，用于向例如燃料细胞或内燃发动机。它特别可用于再生废氨硼烷的燃料，例如那些从脱氢氨硼烷/聚合物复合燃料。', p.abstract_en = 'A process for regenerating spent hydride fuel comprises the steps of (1) generating hydrazine from a plasma;  for example generating a solution of hydrazine in liquid ammonia using a plasma generated in a glow discharge cell,  (2) contacting the spent hydride fuel with said hydrazine and (3) thereafter separating a regenerated hydride fuel therefrom. The process is widely applicable in regenerating spent hydride transportation fuels which are used to power for example a fuel cell or an internal combustion engine. It is especially useful in regenerating spent ammonia borane fuels such as those arising from the dehydrogenation of ammonia borane/polymer composite fuels.', p.application_date = '2013-10-31 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP2016506347A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2015549493'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2015549493', p.title_cn = '用于收集氢气的方法和装置中[…]', p.title_en = 'Apparatus and method for hydrogen recovery in the Andrusov process', p.abstract_cn = '一种方法和系统用于回收氢的方法，本文描述了用于制造氰化氢。在该方法中，从气态的氢气的回收废物流的安氏法制得。该方法包括以下步骤 : (a)调节反应混合物包含甲烷，氨和氧，以提供反应混合物中有充足的氧气，以产生废气流，具有除氨后的至少40%氢和回收氢的氰化物；和(b)去除部件从废气流，以产生回收的氢气。', p.abstract_en = 'A method and a system for recovering hydrogen from a process for making hydrogen cyanide are described herein. In the method,  hydrogen is recovered from a gaseous waste stream of an Andrussow process. The method comprises the following steps :  (a) adjusting a reaction mixture comprising methane,  ammonia and oxygen to provide the reaction mixture with sufficient oxygen to generate a gaseous waste stream that has at least 40% hydrogen after removal of ammonia and recovery of hydrogen cyanide;  and (b) removing components from the gaseous waste stream to generate recovered hydrogen.', p.application_date = '2013-12-12 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP2016506356A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/56', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WOJP15073721'}) SET p.application_no = 'WOJP15073721', p.title_cn = '制氢系统，和用于生产氢的方法和使用其的生产氨的方法', p.title_en = 'SYSTEM FOR PRODUCING HYDROGEN,  AND METHOD FOR PRODUCING HYDROGEN AND METHOD FOR PRODUCING AMMONIA USING SAME', p.abstract_cn = '提供了一种系统用于生产氢气的方法，和氢的制造方法和使用其的生产氨的方法，由此，能够有助于降低CO2的提供热源是 : 不依赖对化石燃料，例如油，煤热能用于热解或碘化氢的浓度，硫酸。用于生产氢的系统，包括使二氧化硫气体的热解产生的硫酸吸收水的混合物，碘，热解所得的碘化氢，所述系统具有一种硫酸热解装置进行热解，硫酸使用第一加热介质，和水的蒸气发生装置用于换热的第第二加热介质具有温度低于第一加热介质与第一加热介质并产生水蒸汽使用温度提高第二的加热介质。', p.abstract_en = 'Provided are a system for producing hydrogen,  and a method for producing hydrogen and a method for producing ammonia using the same,  whereby it is possible to contribute to a decrease in CO2 by providing a heat source that does not depend on fossil fuels such as oil and coal for heat energy used for pyrolysis or concentration of hydrogen iodide and sulfuric acid. A system for producing hydrogen,  comprising causing sulfur dioxide gas produced by pyrolysis of sulfuric acid to be absorbed by a mixture of water and iodine,  and pyrolyzing the resultant hydrogen iodide,  wherein the system has a sulfuric acid pyrolysis means for pyrolyzing sulfuric acid using a first heating medium,  and a water vapor generating means for heat-exchanging a second heating medium having a lower temperature than the first heating medium with the first heating medium and generating water vapor using the temperature-increased second heating medium.', p.application_date = '2015-08-24 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016031771A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201010607790.1'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201010607790.1', p.title_cn = '氨氧化合成气除氨的环保工艺方法', p.title_en = 'Ammonia the gas eliminates ammoxidizing of environmental protection process of synthesizing method', p.abstract_cn = '本发明是提供一种氨氧化合成气除氨的环保工艺方法，其特征是采用一种联合除氨的工艺技术方法，是由磷酸或磷酸二氢铵初级除氨与硫酸或硫酸氢铵精细除氨组成；氨氧化合成气的初级除氨，采用磷酸或磷酸二氢铵作为载体，在初级除氨塔中吸收合成气中的游离氨，磷酸或磷酸二氢铵转化为磷酸氢二铵，磷酸氢二铵在解析塔中解析出游离氨，又转化为磷酸二氢铵，这样反复循环实现了合成气的初级除氨与氨的回收；氨氧化合成气通过初级除氨后再进入精细除氨塔，精细除氨是采用硫酸或硫酸氢铵作为吸收剂，在精细除氨塔中吸收初级除氨后的合成气中的残余氨，硫酸或硫酸氢铵转换为硫酸铵副产品，实现氨氧化合成气的精细除氨。氨氧化合成气联合除氨，实现了氨氧化合成气中游离氨的回收利用，即节约了资源又实现了除氨工艺的真正的环保性，有非常好的经济效益和社会效益。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention provides an environmental-protection process method for removing ammonia from ammoxidation synthesis gas. The method is characterized in that a combined ammonia removal technological method composed of a primary ammonia removal process using phosphoric acid or ammonium dihydrogen phosphate and a fine ammonia removal process using sulfuric acid or ammonium bisulfate. In the primary ammonia removal process of ammoxidation synthesis gas,  primary ammonia removal and ammonia recovery of the synthesis gas can be achieved through the repeated cycle of the following steps :  phosphoric acid or ammonium dihydrogen phosphate absorbs free ammonia in the synthesis gas as a carrier in a primary ammonia removal tower,  and is transformed to diammonium hydrogen phosphate;  and diammonium hydrogen phosphate produces free ammonia in a desorption tower,  and is transformed to ammonium dihydrogen phosphate. The ammoxidation synthesis gas enters a fine ammonia removal tower after the primary ammonia removal process,  and fine ammonia removal process is achieved by using sulfuric acid or ammonium bisulfate as an absorber to absorb remaining ammonia in the synthesis gas after the primary ammonia removal process in a fine ammonia removal tower,  wherein sulfuric acid or ammonium bisulfate is transformed to ammonium sulfate byproducts. The combined ammonia removal method can recover free ammonia in the ammoxidation synthesis gas to save resources and achieve real environmental protection property of the ammonia removal process,  and has good economic and social benefits.', p.application_date = '2010-12-28 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN102530868B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/52', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201210434505.X'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201210434505.X', p.title_cn = '具有集成式蒸汽产生管束的产氢换热器反应器', p.title_en = 'With integrated steam generating tube bundle reactor produces the hydrogen heat interchanger', p.abstract_cn = '本发明描述用于进行吸热反应例如油馏分或醇类的蒸汽重整的换热器-反应器，其集成了蒸汽产生管束，从而提高了热效率。公布了图1。', p.abstract_en = 'The exchanger-reactor comprises bayonet tubes (4) that are suspended on an upper dome (2) of the reactor and extend to a bottom (3) of the reactor,  and a steam generation bundle. The bayonet tubes are adapted to carry out endothermic chemical reactions,  and are enclosed in a shell (1) comprising an inlet pipe (E) for hot flue gas supplying heat to the bayonet tubes and an outlet pipe (S) for evacuating a cold flue gas. The steam generation bundle comprises vertical tubes that are suspended on upper dome and are contained in a peripheral space between an internal baffle and a vertical wall. The exchanger-reactor comprises bayonet tubes (4) that are suspended on an upper dome (2) of the reactor and extend to a bottom (3) of the reactor,  and a steam generation bundle. The bayonet tubes are adapted to carry out endothermic chemical reactions,  and are enclosed in a shell (1) comprising an inlet pipe (E) for hot flue gas supplying heat to the bayonet tubes and an outlet pipe (S) for evacuating a cold flue gas. The steam generation bundle comprises vertical tubes that are suspended on the upper dome and are contained in a peripheral space between an internal baffle and a vertical wall,  is surrounded by a tube with the vertical wall,  and is coaxial with the tube for the generation flue gas around the steam generation tube. The internal baffle is parallel to the vertical wall of the shell,  and baffle has an opening for transferring the flue gas from a core of the reactor to the peripheral space. The vertical tubes are supplied with water via a lower feeder head located in the lower portion of the peripheral space. A liquid-steam mixture coming from the vertical tubes is collected in an upper collector located above the upper dome of the reactor exchanger. A lower line connects a liquid phase of a separator drum to the upper collector. An upper line connects the upper collector to a vapor phase of the separator drum. A deflector system is fixed to walls of the peripher', p.application_date = '2012-08-24 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN102992265B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/32', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201210455151.7'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201210455151.7', p.title_cn = '中低温太阳能与化石燃料热化学互补的发电系统与方法', p.title_en = 'Low and medium temperature solar energy with fossil fuel thermochemical complementary power generation system and method', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种中低温太阳能与化石燃料热化学互补的发电系统与方法，系统包括：原料供应装置，用于贮存化石燃料；原料混合装置，用于混合原料和未反应物；原料计量装置，用于控制单位时间内原料进入预热器的量；预热器，用于对原料进行预热；太阳能吸收反应器，利用吸收的太阳能热量驱动化石燃料进行分解或重整反应，将太阳能转换为富氢的燃料化学能，产生太阳能燃料；太阳能集热器，将低能流密度的太阳能聚集成高能流密度的中低温热能，向分解或重整反应提供热量；冷凝器，用于冷却反应产物；气液分离器，用于对混合物进行气液分离；燃料分流装置，调节用于蓄能或发电的太阳能燃料的比例；储气罐，蓄存太阳能燃料；动力发电设备，燃烧太阳能燃料对外输出电功。本发明实现了太阳能的高效发电利用。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention discloses a mid-and-low temperature solar and fossil fuel thermo-chemical complementary power generation system and method. The system comprises a raw material supply device for storing a fossil fuel,  a raw material mixing device for mixing a raw material and non-reacted materials,  a raw material metering device for controlling the quantity of the raw material entering a pre-heater within unit time,  the pre-heater for pre-heating the raw material,  a solar absorption reactor for driving the fossil fuel by using absorbed solar heat to perform decomposition or reforming reaction so as to convert solar energy into hydrogen-rich fuel chemical energy and produce a solar fuel,  a solar heat collector for gathering solar energy with low energy flow density into mid-and-low temperature heat energy with high energy flow density and supplying heat to the decomposition or reforming reaction,  a condenser for cooling a reaction product,  a gas-liquid separator for gas-liquid separation of a mixture,  a fuel diversion device for adjusting the proportion of the solar fuel for energy storage or power generation,  a gasholder for storing the solar fuel,  and power generation equipment for burning the solar fuel and outputting power to the outside. The system and the method realize efficient power generation utilization of the solar energy.', p.application_date = '2012-11-13 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN103803491B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/32', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201510918714.5'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201510918714.5', p.title_cn = '一种便携式自动控制铝水反应制氢设备', p.title_en = 'Portable hydrogen production equipment by automatic control of aluminum-water reaction', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种便携式自动控制铝水反应制氢设备，卡箍将反应基座和反应釜溢流装置固定在反应釜内部，储液室将反应釜包围住；储氢罐置于储液室内，之间的输水管上装气动阀；储氢罐上装限压阀、抽真空口、输氢管、温度计、气压表；输氢管上装输氢阀、外接快速接口；储液室装泄压阀、反应控制开关、进水阀、出水阀；反应釜内有反应釜溢流装置，之间的连管道装有气动阀；装在储液室下部的进水、出水管道上。本发明的反应釜与储氢罐均处于储液室水环境中，能快速冷却；铝水反应可通过气动阀和反应釜溢流装置进行控制，内部气压稳定；反应釜易于拆卸，反应产物易于回收再利用。本发明结构简单，造价低廉、易于携带与拆卸、安全性高。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to portable hydrogen production equipment by automatic control of aluminum-water reaction. A reaction pedestal and a reaction kettle overflow device are fixed inside a reaction kettle through clamps. A fluid reservoir encircles the reaction kettle. A hydrogen storage tank is arranged inside the fluid reservoir,  and a water delivery pipe between the hydrogen storage tank and the fluid reservoir is provided with a pneumatic valve. The hydrogen storage tank is equipped with a pressure-limiting valve,  a vacuum orifice,  a hydrogen delivery pipe,  a thermometer and a barometer. The hydrogen delivery pipe is provided with a hydrogen delivery valve and an external fast interface. The fluid reservoir is equipped with a decompression valve,  a reaction control switch,  an inlet valve and an outlet valve. The reaction kettle overflow device is arranged inside the reaction kettle,  and a pipeline between the reaction kettle and the reaction kettle overflow device is provided with a pneumatic valve. The inlet valve and the outlet valve are arranged on an inlet conduit and an outlet conduit at the lower part of the fluid reservoir. The reaction kettle and the hydrogen storage tank are both in a water environment of the fluid reservoir and can be rapidly cooled. The aluminum-water reaction can be controlled through the pneumatic valve and the reaction kettle overflow device,  and internal pressure is stable. The reaction kettle is easy to disassemble,  and a reaction product is easy to recycle and reuse. The portable hydrogen production equipment of the invention has a simple structure,  is low-cost,  is easy to carry and disassemble and has high safety.', p.application_date = '2015-12-10 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105366639A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/08', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201480035848.6'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201480035848.6', p.title_cn = '在基于氧气输送膜的转化系统内生产合成气的方法和系统', p.title_en = 'Method and system for producing a synthesis gas in an oxygen transport membrane based reforming system', p.abstract_cn = '用于在基于氧气输送膜的转化系统内生产合成气的方法和系统，其使用具有在约1.6和3.0之间的汽碳比并且具有在约500℃和750℃之间的温度的合并的进料流(200)，其中所述基于氧输送膜的转化系统和相关的合成生产工艺设备大体上没有碳形成和金属尘化腐蚀。所述合并的进料流包括预转化的烃类进料(195)、过热蒸汽(180)和反应产物流(198)，所述反应产物流(198)通过与位于氧输送膜元件(120)的渗透侧的渗透氧反应的含氢气流(163)的反应产生。', p.abstract_en = 'A method and system for producing a synthesis gas in an oxygen transport membrane based reforming system that utilizes a combined feed stream (200) having a steam to carbon ratio between about 1.6 and 3.0 and a temperature between about 500 DEG C and 750 DEG C wherein the oxygen transport membrane based reforming system and associated synthesis production process equipment are substantially free of carbon formation and metal dusting corrosion. The combined feed stream is comprised a pre-reformed hydrocarbon feed (195),  superheated steam (180),  and a reaction product stream (198) created by the reaction of a hydrogen containing stream (163) reacted with the permeated oxygen at the permeate side of the oxygen transport membrane elements (120).', p.application_date = '2014-04-07 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105377750A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201520783752.X'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201520783752.X', p.title_cn = '一种丁辛醇生产中的循环氢冷却器', p.title_en = 'Circulation hydrogen cooler among butyl octanol production', p.abstract_cn = '本实用新型涉及丁辛醇生产的循环氢技术领域，具体涉及一种丁辛醇生产中的循环氢冷却器，它包括壳体，所述壳体内设置有氢腔，所述氢腔内设置有冷却管，所述氢腔下端设置有进氢管，上端设置有出氢管，所述冷却管上端连接有冷却管进口，下端设置有冷却管出口，所述进氢管和出氢管与氢腔之间设置有滤片，所述进氢管和出氢管采用旋钮固定在壳体上。本实用新型它采用冷却器壳体内设置有冷却管，通过冷却管对氢气的直接冷却打到降温的目的，有利于氢气的回收循环使用；且它具有使用方便，操作简单，实用性强，成本低廉等特点。', p.abstract_en = 'The utility model relates to a butyl octanol production\'s recycle hydrogen technical field,  concretely relates to circulation hydrogen cooler among butyl octanol production,  it includes the casing,  be provided with the hydrogen chamber in the casing,  the hydrogen intracavity is provided with the cooling tube,  hydrogen chamber lower extreme is provided with into hydrogen pipe,  and the upper end is provided with out the hydrogen pipe,  the cooling tube upper end is connected with the cooling tube import,  and the lower extreme is provided with the cooling tube and exports,  it is provided with the filter element to advance the hydrogen pipe and go out between hydrogen pipe and the hydrogen chamber,  it adopts the knob to fix on the casing to advance the hydrogen pipe and go out the hydrogen pipe. The utility model discloses it is provided with the cooling tube in adopting the cooler casing,  and the purpose of cooling is got to to the direct cooling of hydrogen to the by freezing pipe,  is favorable to the recycle of hydrogen,  and it has convenient to use,  easy operation,  and the practicality is strong,  characteristics such as low cost.', p.application_date = '2015-10-12 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN205061553U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201520796878.0'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201520796878.0', p.title_cn = '一种氨裂解装置', p.title_en = 'Ammonia cracker', p.abstract_cn = '本实用新型公开了一种氨裂解装置，属于化工装置技术领域。壳体总成的内部设置有炉衬及加热系统，壳体总成的中部设置有加热管，加热管的一端与换热器连接，加热管的另一端与卡套弯头连接，且加热管的前后两端外侧设置有盘根，加热管上涂覆有镍触媒介质，壳体总成的外侧通过内六角螺栓安装有把手，且炉衬及加热系统内部设置有热电偶，热电偶外侧套接有热电偶卡套。它的结构设计合理新颖，体积小，结构紧凑，不占用空间，能直接与氮气炉集成在一体，可以放置在氮气炉的顶部使用，裂解生成的氮气和氢气，可以直接额作为新的工艺气体，导入到氮气炉中使用，此装置降低了设备的投入成本使用更加方便。', p.abstract_en = 'The utility model discloses an one (b) plants ammonia cracker,  belongs to chemical industry technical field. The inside of casing assembly is provided with furnace wall and heating system,  and the middle part of casing assembly is provided with the heating pipe,  and the one end and the heat exchanger of heating pipe are connected,  the other end and the cutting ferrule corner joint of heating pipe,  and be provided with the packing outside the front and back both ends of heating pipe,  and the coating has nickel catalyst medium on the heating pipe,  and the handle is installed through hexagon socket head cap screw in the outside of casing assembly,  and furnace wall and the inside thermocouple that is provided with of heating system,  and the thermocouple cutting ferrule has been cup jointed in the thermocouple outside. Its the reasonable novelty of structural design,  small,  compact structure,  occupation space not,  can be direct with the integration of nitrogen gas stove in an organic whole,  can place and use at the top of nitrogen gas stove,  nitrogen gas and hydrogen that the schizolysis generated,  can direct volume as new process gas,  leading -inly use to the nitrogen gas stove in,  it is more convenient that this device has reduced the input cost use of equipment.', p.application_date = '2015-10-16 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN205061554U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201520729461.2'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201520729461.2', p.title_cn = '一种应用流化床的天然气水蒸汽重整制氢的装置', p.title_en = 'Use device of natural gas steam reformation hydrogen manufacturing of fluidized bed', p.abstract_cn = '本实用新型公开了一种应用流化床的天然气水蒸汽重整制氢的装置，包括燃烧室本体、置于燃烧室本体下方的燃烧器、装有催化剂的反应管、分别呈螺旋状缠绕在燃烧室本体外壁的天然气换热管和水换热管、呈螺旋状缠绕在燃烧室本体内壁的内换热盘管；通入天然气换热管的天然气以及通入水换热管的水，分别自下而上进入混合阀内混合，混合后再进入进料管，然后自上而下螺旋式经过内换热盘管，最后流入反应管内。本制氢工艺及装置的换热系数高，温度均匀，无局部热点，催化剂催化效率提高，床层压力降减少，可适用于低压天然气，而且含氢合成气中CO含量低，消耗小，安装和拆卸方便易行，体积小，占地面积少，可置于阳台，屋檐下等闲置的空间。', p.abstract_en = 'The utility model discloses an use device of natural gas steam reformation hydrogen manufacturing of fluidized bed,  including the combustion chamber body,  arrange in combustion chamber body below the combustor,  be equipped with the catalyst the reaction tube,  respectively be spirally wound at the natural gas heat exchange tube and the water heat exchange tube of combustion chamber body outer wall,  be the interior heat exchange coil of spirally wound at combustion chamber body inner wall,  let in the natural gas of natural gas heat exchange tube and let in the water of water heat exchange tube,  mix in getting into the mixing valve respectively from bottom to top,  mix the reentrant inlet pipe in back,  then heat exchange coil in the spiral process of top -down,  flow in in the reaction tube at last. The heat exchange coefficient of this hydrogen manufacturing technology and device is high,  and the temperature is even,  does not have local focus,  and catalyst catalysis efficiency improves,  and the bed differential pressure reduces,  and applicable in the low pressure natural gas,  CO content is low in the hydrogeneous synthetic gas moreover,  consumes little,  the installation with dismantle convenient easy line,  small,  area is few,  can arrange the balcony in,  the inferior idle space of eave.', p.application_date = '2015-09-18 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN205061555U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/34', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2013059683'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2013059683', p.title_cn = '蒸发器，制造方法和燃料电池系统，氢气发生器', p.title_en = 'Evaporator,  manufacturing method thereof,  and fuel cell system,  a hydrogen generator', p.abstract_cn = '要解决的问题 : 提供一种蒸发器，其中密封形成螺旋流道，分区； 制造该蒸发器的方法； 和氢气发生器和燃料电池系统每个都具有蒸发器，溶液 :  内缸20和外缸21同轴定位， 和金属粉末22填充到所述间隙的内筒20和外筒21。 接着， 所述外筒的外周面21照射高能射线B如激光束， 电子束，等离子，等从散热器24。 金属粉末22在站点之间的外筒(21)，照射的所述高能射线B 和至少内筒的外周面20相对前者然后，将其熔化。 一种螺旋体25形成通过动员的高能射线照射部位沿螺旋方向。', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To provide an evaporator wherein spiral flow channels are hermetically formed and zoned;  a method for manufacturing the evaporator;  and a hydrogen generator and a fuel cell system each possessing the evaporator.SOLUTION :  An inner cylinder 20 and an outer cylinder 21 are coaxially positioned,  and a metal powder 22 is filled into the gap of the inner cylinder 20 and outer cylinder 21. Next,  the outer circumferential surface of the outer cylinder 21 is irradiated with high-energy rays b such as laser beams,  electron beams,  plasmas,  etc. from an irradiator 24. The metal powder 22 in-between the site of the outer cylinder 21 irradiated with the high-energy rays b and at least the outer circumferential surface of the inner cylinder 20 opposing the former is then melted. A spiral body 25 is formed by mobilizing the high-energy ray-irradiated site along a spiral direction.', p.application_date = '2013-03-22 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP5874667B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2013066675'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2013066675', p.title_cn = '用于操作方法的氢生成装置，', p.title_en = 'Method for operating a hydrogen generation device', p.abstract_cn = '要解决的问题 :  提供一种氢气发生器的操作方法，可以减少量的CO产生的氨，通过重整 反应。方法 :  在氢气发生器的操作方法将烃类气体和蒸汽重整反应中使用Ru基 重整催化剂，然后降低一氧化碳的转化催化剂和选择性氧化催化剂，从而产生含氢 气体， 当氢气发生器在额定负载状态， 蒸汽与碳的比例(S/C)调节至3.5-5， 重整催化剂和出口的温度调整到500-～°C， 当氢气发生器中的30%的低负荷状态或更少的额定负荷， S/调整C4.5-5.5，重整催化剂的出口温度调整到480～80A°C。', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To provide a hydrogen generator operation method which can reduce the amounts of CO and ammonia generated by a reforming reaction.SOLUTION :  In a hydrogen generator operation method of subjecting a hydrocarbon gas and steam to a reforming reaction using a Ru-based reforming catalyst and then reducing carbon monoxide by a transforming catalyst and a selective oxidation catalyst to generate a hydrogen-containing gas,  when a hydrogen generator is in a rated load state,  a ratio of steam to carbon (S/C) is adjusted to 3.5-5,  and the outlet temperature of the reforming catalyst is adjusted to 500-600°C,  and when the hydrogen generator is in a state of low load of 30% or less of rated load,  S/C is adjusted to 4.5-5.5,  and the outlet temperature of the reforming catalyst is adjusted to 480-580°C.', p.application_date = '2013-03-27 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP5874669B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2011282482'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2011282482', p.title_cn = '氢气发生器', p.title_en = 'The hydrogen generator', p.abstract_cn = '所要解决的问题是： 本发明提供一种能够抑制单位时间的氢气产生量的变动而稳定地产生氢气的氢气发生装置。 本发明的氢生成装置包括进行氢氧化镁的水解反应的反应容器，向该反应容器内供给水或酸性溶液而生成氢。 反应容器1包括底部11， 以及第一至第三圆柱形部分31， 32， 还包括滴落部，用于从最高的第一圆筒部的上方将水或酸性溶液滴落到填充在第一圆筒部中的氢氧化镁中。 第一至第三圆柱形部分31，32，33例如是圆柱形的，并且同心地布置，使得每个高度从中心部分向外按适当的顺序变低。', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To provide a hydrogen generator capable of generating hydrogen stably by suppressing fluctuation of the hydrogen generation amount per unit time.SOLUTION :  This hydrogen generator includes a reaction vessel 1 wherein a hydrolysis reaction of magnesium hydride is carried out,  and generates hydrogen by supplying water or an acidic solution into the reaction vessel 1. The reaction vessel 1 includes a bottom part 11,  and first to third cylindrical parts 31,  32,  33 having each different height and erected on the bottom part 11 for filling magnesium hydride therein,  and further includes a dropping part 23 for dropping water or an acidic solution into magnesium hydride filled in the first cylindrical part 31 from above the highest first cylindrical part 31. The first to third cylindrical parts 31,  32,  33 are,  for example cylindrical,  and are arranged concentrically so that each height becomes lower in due order from the center part toward the outside.', p.application_date = '2011-12-23 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP5874969B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/06', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'MOJ001912'}) SET p.application_no = 'MOJ001912', p.title_cn = '使用离子液体储氢的方法。', p.title_en = 'A method of storing hydrogen using ionic liquids.', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种储氢方法，其中所述方法包括通过将硼氢化物导入包括阳离子和阴离子的第二离子液体来形成第一离子液体，所述阴离子包括硼酸根，尤其是偏硼酸根；以及通过使用水和/或催化剂将氢从所述第一离子液体中释放而形成所述第二离子液体。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a method for storing hydrogen,  wherein said method comprises forming a first ionic liquid by introducing a borohydride compound into a second ionic liquid comprising a cation and an anion,  said anion comprising a borate,  in particular metaborate;  And forming the second ionic liquid by releasing hydrogen from the first ionic liquid using water and/or a catalyst.', p.application_date = '2015-10-22 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'MOJ001912B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'BRPI112012013374'}) SET p.application_no = 'BRPI112012013374', p.title_cn = '制氢装置及制氢方法', p.title_en = 'hydrogen producing device and method for producing hydrogen', p.abstract_cn = '本发明提供一种光利用效率高，能够高效地制造氢的氢制造装置。 根据本发明的制氢装置包括具有光接收表面和背面的光电转换部分， 设置在背面上的第一气体发生部； 以及设置在背面上的第二气体发生部， 其中第一气体产生部分和第二气体产生部分中的一个是氢产生部分，用于从电解液中产生氢气， 其中的另一个是氧产生部分，用于从电解液产生O2，第一气体产生部分电连接到背面，第二气体产生部分通过第一导电部分电连接到光接收表面。', p.abstract_en = 'There is provided a hydrogen production device high in light use efficiency and capable of producing hydrogen with high efficiency. The hydrogen production device according to the present invention includes a photoelectric conversion part having a light acceptance surface and a back surface,  a first gas generation part provided on the back surface,  and a second gas generation part provided on the back surface,  in which one of the first gas generation part and the second gas generation part is a hydrogen generation part to generate H 2 from an electrolytic solution,  another one thereof is an oxygen generation part to generate O 2 from the electrolytic solution,  the first gas generation part is electrically connected to the back surface,  and the second gas generation part is electrically connected to the light acceptance surface via a first conductive part.', p.application_date = '2010-06-25 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'BR112012013374A2', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'BR112012013313'}) SET p.application_no = 'BR112012013313', p.title_cn = '催化反应器，包括蜂窝催化结构和至少一个结构元件', p.title_en = 'CATALYTIC REACTOR INCLUDING A CELLULAR CATALYTIC STRUCTURE AND AT LEAST A STRUCTURAL ELEMENT', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种催化反应器，其包括至少两个催化蜂窝结构和至少一个结构元件， 插入两个催化蜂窝结构之间，其中整个外周边与反应器的内壁接触，蜂窝结构和结构元件同轴设置。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a catalytic reactor including at least two catalytic cellular architectures and at least one structural element,  inserted between the two catalytic cellular architectures,  in which the entire outer perimeter is in contact with the inner wall of the reactor,  the cellular architecture and the structural element being arranged coaxially.', p.application_date = '2010-11-24 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'BRPI1213313A2', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/48', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'BR112012013374'}) SET p.application_no = 'BR112012013374', p.title_cn = '制氢装置及制氢方法', p.title_en = 'DEVICE OF HYDROGEN PRODUCTION AND METHOD TO PRODUCE HYDROGEN', p.abstract_cn = '本发明提供一种光利用效率高，能够高效地制造氢的氢制造装置。 根据本发明的制氢装置包括具有光接收表面和背面的光电转换部分， 设置在背面上的第一气体发生部； 以及设置在背面上的第二气体发生部， 其中第一气体产生部分和第二气体产生部分中的一个是氢产生部分，用于从电解液中产生氢气， 其中的另一个是氧产生部分，用于从电解液产生O2，第一气体产生部分电连接到背面，第二气体产生部分通过第一导电部分电连接到光接收表面。', p.abstract_en = 'There is provided a hydrogen production device high in light use efficiency and capable of producing hydrogen with high efficiency. The hydrogen production device according to the present invention includes a photoelectric conversion part having a light acceptance surface and a back surface,  a first gas generation part provided on the back surface,  and a second gas generation part provided on the back surface,  in which one of the first gas generation part and the second gas generation part is a hydrogen generation part to generate H 2 from an electrolytic solution,  another one thereof is an oxygen generation part to generate O 2 from the electrolytic solution,  the first gas generation part is electrically connected to the back surface,  and the second gas generation part is electrically connected to the light acceptance surface via a first conductive part.', p.application_date = '2010-06-25 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'BRPI1213374A2', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2012014483'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2012014483', p.title_cn = '重整装置', p.title_en = 'The reforming device', p.abstract_cn = '要解决的问题 : 汽化室和水被供应到重整反应室是防止从流动，从而本发明的氧化重整催化剂，重整装置能够抑制粉末。溶液 : 水蒸发器用于蒸发室68和该气体被重整以一种重整反应的反应室70具有一种改性的壳体62，到汽化室68用于将水供应到该水供给管76为连接，以重整气体的反应室70用于蒸汽重整催化剂用于重整84是填充与所述重整装置。在汽化室68，水供应管76供给到所述汽化室68从该重整水是防止从流动到该反应室70用于防止该构件78的流动是提供。该流动阻挡件78，例如，该壳体62在该底壁82的改性该反应室70，它被设置在相邻的部分至所述板状构件80。选自拉拔 : 图。2。', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To provide a reforming apparatus which can prevent reforming water supplied to a vaporization chamber from flowing to a reaction chamber,  and thereby can suppress oxidation and pulverization of a reforming catalyst.SOLUTION :  A reforming apparatus includes a reforming housing 62 which defines a vaporization chamber 68 for vaporizing water and a reaction chamber 70 for performing a reforming reaction of a gas to be reformed,  and in the reforming apparatus,  a water supply pipe 76 for supplying a reforming water is connected to the vaporization chamber 68,  and a reforming catalyst 84 for steam reforming the gas to be reformed is filled in the reaction chamber 70. In the vaporization chamber 68,  a flow preventing member 78 for preventing the reforming water,  supplied to the vaporization chamber 68 from the water supply pipe 76,  from flowing to the reaction chamber 70 is provided. The flow preventing member 78 is constituted of,  for example,  a plate-like member 80 which is provided at a part adjacent to the reaction chamber 70,  on a bottom wall 82 of the reforming housing 62.', p.application_date = '2012-01-26 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP5871637B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'PH12013501363'}) SET p.application_no = 'PH12013501363', p.title_cn = '叔胺制备工艺', p.title_en = 'TERTIARY AMINE PREPARATION PROCESS', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种制备叔胺的方法，其包括以下步骤(1)和(2)。 步骤(1)：将具有1-36个碳原子的醇和由以下通式(I)表示的粗胺引入第一反应器中，在催化剂和氢的存在下彼此反应，然后继续反应，同时将反应中产生的水和含氢气体排出第一反应器中的反应体系：(I)R1R2NH，其中R1和R2各自独立地为氢原子或具有1-36个碳原子的烃基; 以及步骤(2)：将从第一反应容器排出的含氢气体引入第二反应容器中以减少含氢气体中所含的一氧化碳的量，然后将部分或全部含氢气体引入第一反应容器中。', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention relates to a process for producing a tertiary amine including the following steps (1) and (2). Step (1) :  introducing an alcohol having 1-36 carbon atoms and a raw amine represented by the following general formula (I) into a first reaction vessel to react with each other in the presence of a catalyst and hydrogen,  and then continuing the reaction while discharging water produced in the reaction and a hydrogen-containing gas out of a reaction system in the first reaction vessel :  (I) R1R2NH wherein R1 and R2 are each independently a hydrogen atom or a hydrocarbon group having 1-36 carbon atoms;  and Step (2) :  introducing the hydrogen-containing gas discharged from the first reaction vessel into a second reaction vessel to reduce the amount of carbon monoxide contained in the hydrogen-containing gas,  and then introducing a part or whole of the hydrogen-containing gas into the first reaction vessel.', p.application_date = '2013-06-24 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'PH12013501363B1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/58', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14255102'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14255102', p.title_cn = '生产合成气方法和燃烧器', p.title_en = 'Process and burner for producing synthesis gas', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及在含氧氧化剂存在下通过液态或气态碳质燃料的部分氧化生产合成气，其中燃料、氧化剂和慢化剂分别供给燃烧器，并且其中燃料和慢化剂在与氧化剂接触之前在燃烧器的混合室中混合。 为了减少燃烧器的负荷，特别是在瞬态条件下的操作期间，氧化剂通过燃烧器的出口被中心地引入燃烧室，燃料和慢化剂的混合物通过出口被同心地围绕氧化剂引入燃烧室。', p.abstract_en = 'This invention relates to the production of synthesis gas by partial oxidation of liquid or gaseous,  carbonaceous fuel in the presence of an oxygen-containing oxidant,  wherein the fuel,  the oxidant and a moderator are separately supplied to a burner and wherein the fuel and the moderator are mixed in a mixing chamber of the burner,  before they are brought in contact with the oxidant. To reduce the load of the burner in particular during operation with transient conditions,  the oxidant is centrally introduced through an outlet opening of the burner into a combustion chamber and the mixture of fuel and moderator is introduced through the outlet opening into the combustion chamber concentrically around the oxidant.', p.application_date = '2014-04-17 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9272904B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/36', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14191649'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14191649', p.title_cn = '下烧式重整炉的优化方法', p.title_en = 'Method for optimizing down fired reforming furnaces', p.abstract_cn = '多室下燃炉中甲烷蒸汽重整的优化方法 该方法包括以下步骤 : 将碳氢化合物和蒸汽引入到多个充满催化剂的工艺管中；以V m/s的燃烧器排出速度和1kg/s的质量流率通过多个中心单元下燃燃烧器燃烧气体；以1.5V2V m/s的燃烧器排出速度和0.5-0.65kg/s的质量流率通过外单元下燃燃烧器燃烧气体；最后以基本均匀的动量从外单元下燃燃烧器和中心单元下燃燃烧器排出燃烧产物。', p.abstract_en = 'A method of optimizing steam methane reforming in a multiple cell,  down-fired furnace. The method includes the steps of introducing hydrocarbons and steam to a plurality of catalyst filled process tubes,  combusting gases through a plurality of center cell down-fired burners at a burner discharge velocity of V m/s,  and a mass flow rate of 1 kg/s,  combusting gases through outer cell down-fired burners at a burner discharge velocity of 1.5V-2V m/s and a mass flow rate of 0.5-0.65 kg/s,  and finally discharging combustion products from the outer cell down-fired burners and the center cell down-fired burners at a substantially uniform momentum.', p.application_date = '2014-02-27 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9272905B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 2, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14561677'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14561677', p.title_cn = '氨、氮和氢的混合物或氮、氢和氨的纯化方法', p.title_en = 'Method for purification of ammonia,  mixtures of nitrogen and hydrogen,  or nitrogen,  hydrogen and ammonia', p.abstract_cn = '用于净化氨或氮和氢的混合物的方法， 或氮， 氢和氨， 其中在0.1－25MPa压力下的氨或气体混合物通过填充有具有大比表面积的氧化铝的塔， 然后，氨或气体混合物在20至70°C和0.1至25MPa的压力下分别或以混合物形式通过填充有CaO、NaOH、KOH或NaOH/KOH熔体的柱，氨或气体混合物通过填充有比表面积为100至3000m2/g的活性炭的柱，其中钠、钾、铯、镁、钙、锶、硝酸钡或硝酸铈(Ⅴ)或硝酸铈(Ⅲ)分别或以混合物形式沉积在其表面。', p.abstract_en = 'Method for purification of ammonia or mixtures of nitrogen and hydrogen,  or nitrogen,  hydrogen and ammonia,  where ammonia or a mixture of gases under pressure of from 0.1 to 25 MPa is passed through a column packed with aluminum oxide with a large specific surface area,  the ammonia or mixture of gases is then passed through a column packed with CaO,  NaOH,  KOH or an NaOH/KOH melt,  separately or in a mixture,  at 20 to 70° C. and under pressure of from 0.1 to 25 MPa,  and the ammonia or mixture of gases is passed through a column packed with activated carbon having a specific area of 100-3000 m2/g with sodium,  potassium,  caesium,  magnesium,  calcium,  strontium,  barium or cerium nitrates(V) or nitrates(III) deposited on its surface,  separately or in a mixture.', p.application_date = '2014-12-05 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9272906B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'NO20060457'}) SET p.application_no = 'NO20060457', p.title_cn = '从含甲烷气体，特别是天然气中提取氢气的方法，以及用于执行该方法的设施', p.title_en = 'Procedure for extracting hydrogen from a methane-containing gas,  especially a natural gas,  and facilities for carrying out the procedure', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种提取氢的方法从含甲烷的气体，特别是天然气。所述气体中含有的烃类催化裂解重整器(4)中通过蒸汽以形成氢，一氧化碳和二氧化碳。所得到的催化转化一氧化碳与蒸汽发生在下游转化步骤以形成碳一氧化碳和水。二氧化碳从转化的气体流(8)通过气体洗涤步骤(7)，并将清洗后的富氢气体流(10)随后被分割在压力摆动吸附系统(11)成产物气体流(12)由氢和废气流(13)。废气流(13)通入氢气(14)，其分离气体流(10)洗气后，到重整器(4)基本上是无碳可燃气体，在那里燃烧。本发明还涉及一种用于进行该方法的系统。', p.abstract_en = 'A system for extracting hydrogen from a gas containing methane,  especially natural gas. Hydrocarbons contained in the gas are catalytically broken down in a reformer by steam in order to form hydrogen,  carbon monoxide and carbon dioxide. Catalytic conversion of the obtained carbon monoxide with steam occurs in a downstream conversion step in order to form carbon monoxide and water. Carbon dioxide is removed from the converted gas flow by gas washing,  and the washed hydrogen-rich gas flow is subsequently divided in a pressure-swing adsorption system into a product gas flow made of hydrogen and a waste gas flow. The waste gas flow is introduced with hydrogen,  which is separated from the gas flow after gas washing,  into a reformer which is essentially a carbon-free combustible gas,  and is combusted there.', p.application_date = '2006-01-27 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'NO337257B1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'RSP20150654'}) SET p.application_no = 'RSP20150654', p.title_cn = '二氧化碳转化为一氧化碳的方法和系统', p.title_en = 'PROCESS AND SYSTEM FOR CONVERSION OF CARBON DIOXIDE TO CARBON MONOXIDE', p.abstract_cn = '描述了一种使用烃将二氧化碳CO2转化为一氧化碳CO的方法和装置。 在进一步的实施方式中，描述了用于产生合成气的工艺和设备以及用于使用CO2和烃将合成气转化成合成官能化和/或非官能化烃的工艺和设备。 所述方法和装置适于转化由工业过程排放的CO2，并且因此可以减少排放到大气中的二氧化碳的量。', p.abstract_en = 'A process and an apparatus for converting carbon dioxide CO2 into carbon monoxide CO using hydrocarbons are described. In further embodiments,  processes and apparatuses for generating synthesis gas and processes and apparatuses for converting synthesis gas into synthetic functionalised and/or non-functionalised hydrocarbons using CO2 and hydrocarbons are described. The processes and apparatuses are adapted to convert CO2 emitted by industrial processes,  and thus the amount of carbon dioxide emitted into the atmosphere may be reduced.', p.application_date = '2012-12-20 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'RS54285B1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/24', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'BYa20121019'}) SET p.application_no = 'BYa20121019', p.title_cn = '用于运输动力设备的氢气发生器', p.title_en = 'Hydrogen generator for a transport power plant', p.abstract_cn = '', p.abstract_en = '', p.application_date = '2012-07-09 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'BY19761C1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/08', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'RU2013146371'}) SET p.application_no = 'RU2013146371', p.title_cn = '节能，环保的方法提取轻质油和/或燃料从天然沥青从油页岩中和/或油承载砂', p.title_en = 'METHOD OF ENERGY-SAVING AND ENVIRONMENTALLY FRIENDLY EXTRACTION OF LIGHT OIL AND/OR FUEL OUT OF NATURAL BITUMEN FROM OIL SHALE AND/OR OIL-BERATING SAND', p.abstract_cn = '领域 : 油和天然气工业。内容 : 本发明称为光的提取的油和/或燃料从天然沥青从油页岩和/或油的承载砂。根据所述方法，天然沥青从油页岩中提取水分离和/或油形成承载砂固体残渣，挥发性烃蒸馏从天然沥青，在不溶油焦保持与含有最多10%的硫，气态烃，通过蒸馏分割分级冷凝成轻质油，原料油和不同燃料。本实用新型的方法，其特征是由水的固体残渣中分离和/或油焦使用热，在它们转换成亚化学计量的含氧的氧化气体(26)在counteflow气化器(19)分别与活动层的松散材料(21)，在添加碱性物质在温度<800A°C与低硫气态裂解产物含量这些分体式产品再经亚化学计量的氧化的显热，其用于产生被加热的水介质用于含油的物理研磨砂和/或油页岩(a)和/或从岩体中分离天然沥青和/或作为过程热量用于热破天然沥青，通过添加碱性物质在还原条件下气态含硫生产的产品在逆流气化器(19)处转化400A以上的温度°C的成分的碳和含硫渣与碱性物质的化学反应的固体含硫化合物，这些固体含硫化合物处理至少部分地由反应的气态产物和除去气相通过分离细颗粒的物料在温度高于300A°C。效果 : 改进的能量平衡，防止威胁environment.13Cl，2的DWG', p.abstract_en = 'FIELD :  oil and gas industry. SUBSTANCE :  invention is referred to extraction of light oil and/or fuel out of natural bitumen from oil shale and/or oil-berating sand. According to the method natural bitumen is extracted by water separation from oil shale and/or oil-berating sand with formation of solid residue,  volatile hydrocarbons are distilled from natural bitumen,  at that insoluble oil coke remains with inclusion of up to 10% of sulphur,  gaseous hydrocarbons upon distillation are divided by fractional condensation into light oil,  raw oil and different fuels. The method is featured by the fact that solid residue of water separation and/or oil coke are used thermally,  at that they are converted by substochiometric oxidation by oxygen-containing gas (26) in counteflow gasifier (19) interacting with movable layer of loose material (21),  at addition of alkali substances at temperature <1800°C to gaseous split products with low sulphur content these split products are further converted by substochiometric oxidation to sensible heat,  which is used for generation of heated water medium for physical grinding of oil-bearing sand and/or oil shale (A) and/or for separating natural bitumen from rock mass and/or as process heat for thermal breaking of natural bitumen,  and by adding alkali substances at reductive conditions gaseous sulphur-containing products produced in counterflow gasifer (19) are converted at temperature of more than 400°C from ingredients of carbon- and sulphur-containing residues by chemical reaction with alkali substances to solid sulphur-containing compounds,  and these solid sulphur-containing compounds are treated at least partially by gaseous products of the reaction and removed from gaseous phase by separating fine-grain materials at temperature higher than 300°C. EFFECT :  improved energy balance,  prevented threat to environment. 13 cl,  2 dwg', p.application_date = '2012-03-16 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'RU2576250C2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'IN2353DEL2014'}) SET p.application_no = 'IN2353DEL2014', p.title_cn = '纳米掺铂纳米孔活性碳和其制备方法', p.title_en = 'NANO PLATINUM DOPED NANOPOROUS ACTIVATED CARBON AND A PROCESS FOR THE PREPARATION THEREOF', p.abstract_cn = '掺杂纳米铂纳米多孔活性炭(npac)开发的预处理后的纳米多孔活性炭为前体。掺杂NPAC纳米铂催化剂存在下具有高容量，产生羟基自由基氧的破坏。cyanotoxins在中性(pH)条件下水溶液中。这种新的技术可用于治疗毒素污染的水/污水不消耗化学品/紫外灯臭氧在环境条件下。新工艺不产生破坏cyanotoxin从水/废水时污泥。', p.abstract_en = 'Nano platinum doped nano porous activated carbon (NPAC) is developed using pretreated nano porous activated carbon as the precursor. Nano Platinum doped NPAC catalyst has high capacity to generate hydroxyl radical in presence of oxygen for the destruction of cyanotoxins in aqueous solution at neutral (pH) conditions. This new technique can be applied for the treatment of toxin contaminated water/wastewater without consumption of chemicals /ultra violet light / ozone at ambient conditions. The new process does not generate sludge during the destruction of cyanotoxin from water/wastewater.', p.application_date = '2014-08-20 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'IN2353DEL2014A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'AU2014317223'}) SET p.application_no = 'AU2014317223', p.title_cn = '用于生产氨的方法和设备补充气体，包括生产氢气体的蒸汽重整', p.title_en = 'Process and plant for the production of ammonia make-up gas including production of a hydrogen gas by steam reforming', p.abstract_cn = '化妆的方法和用于生产合成气体(20)用于氨的合成，包括 : 重整的烃原料(10)在蒸汽重整装置(SMR)，纯化所述气体产物获得含氢合成气，加入合适量的氮(19)对所述氢气的合成气，其中所述纯化包括分离主分离单元中的氢(S1)，产生氢的电流(14)和尾气(15)，并且其中进一步的氢气的回收从所述尾气(15)中的附加分离单元(S2)；一些实施例提供了使一定量的气体产品(24)同样也被供给到所述附加分离单元；相应的方法用于修补的前端本发明还公开了氨厂的。', p.abstract_en = 'A process and plant for producing a makeup synthesis gas (20) for the synthesis of ammonia,  comprising :  reforming of a hydrocarbon feedstock (10) in a steam reformer (SMR),  purification of said gas product obtaining a hydrogen synthesis gas,  addition of a suitable amount of nitrogen (19) to said hydrogen synthesis gas,  wherein said purification includes separation of hydrogen in a main separation unit (S1),  which produces a hydrogen current (14) and a tail gas (15),  and wherein further hydrogen is recovered from the said tail gas (15) in an additional separation unit (S2);  some embodiments provides that an amount of gas product (24) is also fed to said additional separation unit;  a corresponding method for the revamping of a front-end of an ammonia plant is also disclosed.', p.application_date = '2014-09-02 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'AU2014317223A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CA2958101'}) SET p.application_no = 'CA2958101', p.title_cn = '生产合成气的方法', p.title_en = 'PROCESS FOR PRODUCING SYNTHESIS GAS', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种用于产生合成气的方法(5)。烃类(2)中热分解成氢和碳第一反应区(Z1)，和进行过程中产生的氢气从第一反应区(Z1)至第二反应区(Z2)以氢气与一氧化碳反应第二反应区(4)中，以生成水和一氧化碳。本发明的特征在于 : 所述的烃类热分解所需的能量在第一反应区(Z1)提供从第二反应区(Z2)。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a method for generating syngas (5). Hydrocarbon (2) is thermally decomposed into hydrogen and carbon in a first reaction zone (Z1),  and hydrogen produced in the process is conducted from the first reaction zone (Z1) to a second reaction zone (Z2) in order to react the hydrogen with carbon monoxide (4) in the second reaction zone so as to produce water and carbon monoxide. The invention is characterized in that the energy required for the thermal hydrocarbon decomposition in the first reaction zone (Z1) is supplied from the second reaction zone (Z2).', p.application_date = '2015-08-13 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CA2958101A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/24', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'DE602008041822'}) SET p.application_no = 'DE602008041822', p.title_cn = '氢生成装置，燃料电池系统和氢气形成装置的控制方法', p.title_en = 'HYDROGEN FORMING APPARATUS,  FUEL CELL SYSTEM AND METHOD OF CONTROLLING HYDROGEN FORMING APPARATUS', p.abstract_cn = '氢气产生装置能够稳定地供给的重整水，稳定产生氢气和防止降解的重整器。所述氢气产生装置包括重整器1进行重整反应中使用材料和蒸汽生成含氢气体；水蒸发器1a产生的蒸汽供给到重整器1；一种第一水通路5，通过该重整水供给到水蒸发器1a流动；泵6，其提供的重整水到水蒸发器1a；一种第二水通路7分支从第一水通路在泵6的下游侧；第一水箱(2)，其通过第二水流动的水通路7的流动；一种第一流量控制器8设置在第二水通路7；和控制器9，其可以操作泵6和控制器第一，流量控制器8使水流经第二水通路7。', p.abstract_en = 'A hydrogen generating apparatus is capable of stably supplying reforming water,  stably generating hydrogen and preventing degradation of the reformer thereof. The hydrogen generating apparatus comprises a reformer 1 which performs a reforming reaction using a material and steam to generate hydrogen-containing gas;  a water evaporator 1a which generates the steam supplied to the reformer 1;  a first water pathway 5 through which reforming water to be supplied to the water evaporator 1a flows;  a pump 6 which supplies the reforming water to the water evaporator 1a;  a second water pathway 7 branching from the first water pathway on the downstream side of the pump 6;  a first water tank 2 to which the water flowing through the second water pathway 7 flows;  a first flow rate controller 8 provided on the second water pathway 7;  and a controller 9 which operates the pump 6 and controls the first flow rate controller 8 so that water flows through the second water pathway 7.', p.application_date = '2008-04-07 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'DE602008041822T2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'KR1020147020286'}) SET p.application_no = 'KR1020147020286', p.title_cn = '方法和系统用于转换二氧化碳一氧化碳', p.title_en = 'PROCESS AND SYSTEM FOR CONVERSION CARBON DIOXIDE TO CARBON MONOXIDE', p.abstract_cn = '一种方法和一种装置，用于产生描述了合成气使用烃类和水。在进一步的实施例的方法和装置，合成气具有任何所需的CO/氢比例和/或合成的官能化和/或非官能化烃产生。与该方法，含烃流体可以被变换成具有可变的合成气的氢含量而不产生显著量的CO2。进一步，氢和不同形式的碳可以获得作为副产物。', p.abstract_en = 'A process and an apparatus for converting carbon dioxide CO2 into carbon monoxide CO using hydrocarbons are described. In further embodiments,  processes and apparatuses for generating synthesis gas and processes and apparatuses for converting synthesis gas into synthetic functionalised and/or non-functionalised hydrocarbons using CO2 and hydrocarbons are described. The processes and apparatuses are adapted to convert CO2 emitted by industrial processes,  and thus the amount of carbon dioxide emitted into the atmosphere may be reduced.', p.application_date = '2012-12-20 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'KR101599374B1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/24', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'TH1601001043'}) SET p.application_no = 'TH1601001043', p.title_cn = 'None', p.title_en = 'None', p.abstract_cn = '', p.abstract_en = '', p.application_date = '2016-02-25 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'TH1601001043A0', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'UAA201401061'}) SET p.application_no = 'UAA201401061', p.title_cn = '用于生产合成气的方法', p.title_en = 'PROCESS FOR THE PRODUCTION OF SYNTHESIS GAS', p.abstract_cn = '生产合成气的方法(3)，在甲烷和二氧化碳(2)引入反应空间(R)和存在下反应在升高的温度下固体(w)来产生氢气和一氧化碳。甲烷和二氧化碳通过含碳颗粒状材料(W)和高温区中反应(H)。', p.abstract_en = 'Process for the production of synthesis gas (3),  in which methane and carbon dioxide (2) are introduced into a reaction space (R) and reacted in the presence of a solid (W) at elevated temperatures to give hydrogen and carbon monoxide. Methane and carbon dioxide are passed through a carbon-containing granular material (W) and reacted in a hightemperature zone (II).', p.application_date = '2012-07-05 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'UA110840C2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/34', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'VN1201503892'}) SET p.application_no = 'VN1201503892', p.title_cn = '合成烃类化合物的方法', p.title_en = 'METHOD FOR SYNTHESIZING HYDROCARBONACEOUS COMPOUNDS', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种合成烃类化合物的方法。在各个方面，提供了用于将熔融碳酸盐燃料电池与费-托合成工艺集成的系统和方法。熔融碳酸盐燃料电池可以以各种方式与费-托合成方法集成，包括提供用于生产烃的合成气。此外，熔融碳酸盐燃料电池与费-托合成工艺的集成可有助于进一步处理在合成工艺期间产生的排出流或次级产物流。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a method for synthesizing hydrocarbonaceous compounds. In various aspects,  systems and methods are provided for integration of molten carbonate fuel cells with a Fischer-Tropsch synthesis process. The molten carbonate fuel cells can be integrated with a Fischer-Tropsch synthesis process in various manners,  including providing synthesis gas for use in producing hydrocarbonaceous carbons. Additionally,  integration of molten carbonate fuel cells with a Fischer-Tropsch synthesis process can facilitate further processing of vent streams or secondary product streams generated during the synthesis process.', p.application_date = '2015-10-14 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'VN45905A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'VN1201503893'}) SET p.application_no = 'VN1201503893', p.title_cn = '合成烃类化合物的方法', p.title_en = 'METHOD FOR SYNTHESIZING HYDROCARBONACEOUS COMPOUNDS', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种合成烃类化合物的方法。在各个方面，提供了用于将熔融碳酸盐燃料电池与费-托合成工艺集成的系统和方法。熔融碳酸盐燃料电池可以以各种方式与费-托合成方法集成，包括提供用于生产烃的合成气。此外，熔融碳酸盐燃料电池与费-托合成工艺的集成可有助于进一步处理在合成工艺期间产生的排出流或次级产物流。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a method for synthesizing hydrocarbonaceous compounds. In various aspects,  systems and methods are provided for integration of molten carbonate fuel cells with a Fischer-Tropsch synthesis process. The molten carbonate fuel cells can be integrated with a Fischer-Tropsch synthesis process in various manners,  including providing synthesis gas for use in producing hydrocarbonaceous carbons. Additionally,  integration of molten carbonate fuel cells with a Fischer-Tropsch synthesis process can facilitate further processing of vent streams or secondary product streams generated during the synthesis process.', p.application_date = '2015-10-14 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'VN45906A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'VN1201503895'}) SET p.application_no = 'VN1201503895', p.title_cn = '合成烃类化合物的方法', p.title_en = 'METHOD FOR SYNTHESIZING HYDROCARBONACEOUS COMPOUNDS', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种合成烃类化合物的方法。在各个方面，提供了用于将熔融碳酸盐燃料电池与甲醇合成工艺集成的系统和方法。熔融碳酸盐燃料电池可以以各种方式与甲醇合成工艺集成，包括提供用于生产甲醇的合成气。此外，熔融碳酸盐燃料电池与甲醇合成工艺的集成可促进甲醇合成期间产生的排出流或次级产物流的进一步处理。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a method for synthesizing hydrocarbonaceous compounds. In various aspects,  systems and methods are provided for integration of molten carbonate fuel cells with a methanol synthesis process. The molten carbonate fuel cells can be integrated with a methanol synthesis process in various manners,  including providing synthesis gas for use in producing methanol. Additionally,  integration of molten carbonate fuel cells with a methanol synthesis process can facilitate further processing of vent streams or secondary product streams generated during methanol synthesis.', p.application_date = '2015-10-14 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'VN45907A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'VN1201503896'}) SET p.application_no = 'VN1201503896', p.title_cn = '合成烃类化合物的方法', p.title_en = 'METHOD FOR SYNTHESIZING HYDROCARBONACEOUS COMPOUNDS', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种合成烃类化合物的方法。在各个方面，提供了用于将熔融碳酸盐燃料电池与费-托合成工艺集成的系统和方法。熔融碳酸盐燃料电池可以以各种方式与费-托合成方法集成，包括提供用于生产烃的合成气。此外，熔融碳酸盐燃料电池与费-托合成工艺的集成可有助于进一步处理在合成工艺期间产生的排出流或次级产物流。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a method for synthesizing hydrocarbonaceous compounds. In various aspects,  systems and methods are provided for integration of molten carbonate fuel cells with a Fischer-Tropsch synthesis process. The molten carbonate fuel cells can be integrated with a Fischer-Tropsch synthesis process in various manners,  including providing synthesis gas for use in producing hydrocarbonaceous carbons. Additionally,  integration of molten carbonate fuel cells with a Fischer- Tropsch synthesis process can facilitate further processing of vent streams or secondary product streams generated during the synthesis process.', p.application_date = '2015-10-14 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'VN45908A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/50', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'VN1201504618'}) SET p.application_no = 'VN1201504618', p.title_cn = '制氢方法', p.title_en = 'Hydrogen production method', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种通过促进甲醇部分氧化反应和甲醇分解反应制氢的方法，在该方法中催化剂寿命可以提拉，并且可以长期稳定地生产氢气。 该制氢方法包括制备作为原料的气体的步骤(S1)和制氢步骤(S2)。 在制备作为原料的气体的步骤(S1)中，制备至少含有甲醇，水和氧的作为原料的气体，其温度调节到预定的反应温度。 在制氢步骤(S2)中，通过使作为调温原料的气体在反应器(2a)中流动，使作为调温原料的气体与催化剂接触，并由此导致部分氧化反应和甲醇分解反应而生成氢气。 在制氢步骤(S2)中，通过控制作为原料的气体在反应器(2a)中流动的流量，控制作为原料的气体与其接触的催化剂表面的最大温度，使其小于或等于300oC。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a method for producing hydrogen by promoting a partial oxidation reaction of methanol and a decomposition reaction of methanol,  in which the life of a catalyst can be lifted and hydrogen can be stably produced for a long time. The hydrogen production method includes a step of preparing a gas as a raw material (S1) and a hydrogen production step (S2). In the step of preparing a gas as a raw material (S1),  a gas as a raw material containing at least methanol,  water and oxygen is prepared,  and the temperature of the gas is adjusted to a predetermined reaction temperature. In the hydrogen production step (S2),  the gas as the temperature-regulating raw material is brought into contact with the catalyst by flowing the gas as the temperature-regulating raw material in the reactor (2a),  thereby causing a partial oxidation reaction and a methanol decomposition reaction to generate hydrogen gas. In the hydrogen production step (S2),  by controlling the flow rate of the gas as the raw material flowing through the reactor (2a),  the maximum temperature of the catalyst surface with which the gas as the raw material comes into contact is controlled to be less than or equal to 300oC.', p.application_date = '2015-12-02 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'VN46059A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/32', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WOEP15001675'}) SET p.application_no = 'WOEP15001675', p.title_cn = '用于产生合成气的方法', p.title_en = 'METHOD FOR GENERATING SYNGAS', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种用于产生合成气的方法(5)。烃类(2)热分解成氢和碳在第一反应区(Z1)，和进行过程中产生的氢气从第一反应区(Z1)至第二反应区(Z2)为了使氢与一氧化碳(4)在第二反应区，从而生成水和一氧化碳。本发明其特征是 : 所述烃类热分解所需的能量在第一反应区(Z1)提供从第二反应区(Z2)。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a method for generating syngas (5). Hydrocarbon (2) is thermally decomposed into hydrogen and carbon in a first reaction zone (Z1),  and hydrogen produced in the process is conducted from the first reaction zone (Z1) to a second reaction zone (Z2) in order to react the hydrogen with carbon monoxide (4) in the second reaction zone so as to produce water and carbon monoxide. The invention is characterized in that the energy required for the thermal hydrocarbon decomposition in the first reaction zone (Z1) is supplied from the second reaction zone (Z2).', p.application_date = '2015-08-13 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016026562A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/24', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WOIB15056136'}) SET p.application_no = 'WOIB15056136', p.title_cn = '氢生产', p.title_en = 'HYDROGEN PRODUCTION', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种制氢单元，包括多材料管由不锈钢管和钨杆或管。不锈钢管为船用级不锈钢和钨杆或管由实心或管状的纯钨。所述制氢单元的尺寸和适合于以复制所述车辆电池的尺寸。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention discloses a hydrogen production unit,  which includes a multi-material tube made of stainless steel pipe and a tungsten rod or tube. The stainless steel pipe is made of marine grade stainless steel and the tungsten rod or tube is made of solid or tubular pure tungsten. The hydrogen production unit is dimensioned and adapted so as to replicate the size of a vehicle battery.', p.application_date = '2015-08-12 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016027201A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WOJP15004117'}) SET p.application_no = 'WOJP15004117', p.title_cn = '氢气发生器，及其操作方法和燃料电池系统', p.title_en = 'HYDROGEN GENERATOR,  METHOD FOR OPERATING SAME AND FUEL CELL SYSTEM', p.abstract_cn = '氢气发生器(200)，其具有 : 重整器(31)；起始原料气体供给装置(34)供给的原料气体的重整器(31)；和用于加热重整器的燃烧器(31)。氢气发生器(200)还设置有 : 燃烧空气供应装置(36)，用于供应燃烧用的空气到燃烧器；燃烧状态检测器，用于检测燃烧器的燃烧状态；和控制器(39)控制的基础上控制参数。控制器(39)被配置成设置控制参数的值的基础上检测到的燃烧状态检测器时比燃烧用空气的供给量到燃烧器的燃烧送风装置(36)相对于供给量的原料气体的原料气体供应装置(34)的状态下改变所述重整器(31)加热的燃烧器。', p.abstract_en = 'A hydrogen generator (200) which is provided with :  a reformer (31);  a starting material gas supply device (34) for supplying a starting material gas to the reformer (31);  and a combustor for heating the reformer (31). The hydrogen generator (200) is also provided with :  a combustion air supply device (36) for supplying an air for combustion to the combustor;  a combustion state detector for detecting the combustion state of the combustor;  and a controller (39) for controlling on the basis of a control parameter. The controller (39) is configured to set a control parameter on the basis of the value detected by the combustion state detector when the ratio of the supply amount of the air for combustion to the combustor by the combustion air supply device (36) relative to the supply amount of the starting material gas by the starting material gas supply device (34) is changed in a state where the reformer (31) is heated by the combustor.', p.application_date = '2015-08-19 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016027459A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN200880125540.5'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN200880125540.5', p.title_cn = '氨加工效率的提高', p.title_en = 'The improvement of the efficiency of ammonia processing', p.abstract_cn = '用于生产氨的系统和方法。该系统可以包括其中布置有两个或多个不连续的催化剂床的第一壳体，布置在该第一壳体周围的第二壳体，布置在第一壳体外面并且与之流体联通的第一热交换器，布置在第二壳体外面并且与之流体联通的第二热交换器，和布置在第一壳体内的流路。第一部分原料气可以在催化剂的存在下反应来提供氨流出物。来自该氨流出物的反应热可以在第一热交换器和第二热交换器中进行交换。加热的第二部分原料气可以引入到第一壳体中，并且可以在催化剂的存在下进行反应。', p.abstract_en = 'Systems and methods for producing ammonia. The system can include a first shell having two or more discrete catalyst beds disposed therein,  a second shell disposed about the first shell,  a first heat exchanger disposed external to the first shell and in fluid communication therewith,  a second heat exchanger disposed external to the second shell and in fluid communication therewith,  and a flow path disposed within the first shell. A first portion can be reacted in the presence of the catalyst to provide an ammonia effluent. The heat of reaction from the ammonia effluent can be exchanged within the first heat exchanger and the second heat exchanger. The heated second portion of the feed gas can be introduced to the first shell and can be reacted in the presence of the catalyst.', p.application_date = '2008-09-08 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN101925531B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201180058369.2'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201180058369.2', p.title_cn = '制备乙炔和合成气的方法和装置', p.title_en = 'The preparation of acetylene and synthesis gas method and apparatus for', p.abstract_cn = '本发明提供了一种通过用氧气部分氧化烃而制备乙炔和合成气的方法，该方法包括首先分别预热包括含烃料流和含氧料流的起始气体，然后将其在混合区中混合，且在其流经燃烧器区段后，使其在燃烧空间中反应，然后快速冷却产物，所述方法的特征在于：所述燃烧器区段的燃烧空间侧上的表面被清洁气流所覆盖，并将该清洁气流借助多个孔引导通过所述燃烧器区段，其中所述燃烧器区段的有效表面区域与该燃烧器区段中用于清洁气流的这些孔的数目的平均比值为5-100cm2。', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention provides a process for preparing acetylene and synthesis gas by partial oxidation of hydrocarbons with oxygen,  by first separately preheating the starting gases comprising a hydrocarbon-containing stream and an oxygen-containing stream and then mixing them in a mixing zone and,  after they have flowed through the burner block,  reacting them in the firing space and then cooling the products rapidly,  wherein the surface on the firing space side of the burner block is covered with a purge gas stream and this purge gas stream is introduced through the burner block by means of several bores,  where the averaged ratio of effective surface area of the burner block to number of these bores in the burner block for the purge gas stream is within a range from 5 to 100 cm2.', p.application_date = '2011-10-27 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN103249669B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/36', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201510904338.4'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201510904338.4', p.title_cn = '煤制汽车用氢气能源供气系统', p.title_en = 'Coal-consuming hydrogen energy supplying system for automobile', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种煤制汽车用氢气能源供气系统，煤炭进料仓与输送系统连接，输送系统与氢气发生器连接，氢气发生器与多余物质收集系统和氢气收集系统连接，氢气收集系统与氢气净化系统连接，氢气净化系统与氢气储存系统连接，氢气储存系统与氢气压缩系统连接，氢气压缩系统与压缩氢气储存系统连接，压缩氢气储存系统与氢气发电系统和压缩氢气售气系统连接，压缩氢气售气系统与氢能源汽车连接。本发明用于氢能源汽车的供给，氢气生产量可根据具体要求具体设定，可实现煤制氢气供给加氢站为氢能源汽车提供足够的氢能源。可以解决在无人区、高原、没有电力供应的地区，实现氢能源汽车的优秀性能。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention discloses a coal-consuming hydrogen energy supplying system for an automobile. A coal feed bin is connected with a conveying system,  the conveying system is connected with a hydrogen generator,  the hydrogen generator is connected with an excessive substance collection system and a hydrogen collection system,  the hydrogen collection system is connected with a hydrogen purification system,  the hydrogen purification system is connected with a hydrogen storage system,  the hydrogen storage system is connected with a hydrogen compression system,  the hydrogen compression system is connected with a compressed hydrogen storage system,  the compressed hydrogen storage system is connected with a hydrogen power generation system and a compressed hydrogen selling system,  and the compressed hydrogen selling system is connected with the hydrogen energy automobile. The coal-consuming hydrogen energy supplying system is used for supplying energy to the hydrogen energy automobile,  the hydrogen production output can be set according to the specific requirement,  and sufficient hydrogen energy can be provided for the hydrogen energy automobile by a coal-consuming hydrogen supplying and refueling station. By means of the system,  the purpose that in a depopulated zone,  a plateau or an area where no electric power is supplied,  excellent performance of the hydrogen energy automobile is achieved can be achieved.', p.application_date = '2015-12-09 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105347303A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/50', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201510949727.9'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201510949727.9', p.title_cn = '一种双高带压解吸PSA提氢方法', p.title_en = 'Double-high PSA (pressure swing adsorption) hydrogen purification method adopting pressure desorption', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开一种双高带压解吸PSA提氢方法，涉及制氢和变压吸附气体分离技术领域，包括一段变压吸附阶段和二段变压吸附阶段，所述一段变压吸附阶段为氢气浓缩阶段，在一段变压吸附单元中进行，解吸时采用带压解吸；所述二段变压吸附阶段为氢气提纯阶段，在二段变压吸附单元中进行，解吸时采用常压解吸；带压解吸时，使得解吸尾气本身带压，不用压缩直接去管网作为燃烧气，克服了传统变压吸附工艺解吸尾气需增压以回收利用而带来的能耗高的缺点，取消了解吸尾气压缩机，增加了装置可靠性的同时大大降低了装置的投资和能耗；采用两段变压吸附单元吸附，在保证产品纯度99.9%以上的同时，也提高收率至90%以上，实现了“双高”即高纯度、高收率的提氢目标。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention discloses a double-high PSA (pressure swing adsorption) hydrogen purification method adopting pressure desorption and relates to the technical field of hydrogen production and PSA gas separation. The method includes a first PSA stage and a second PSA stage,  wherein the first PSA stage is a hydrogen concentration stage and is performed in a first-stage PSA unit,  and pressure desorption is adopted during desorption;  the second PSA stage is a hydrogen purification stage and is performed in a second-stage PSA unit,  and normal-pressure desorption is adopted during desorption;  during pressure desorption,  desorption tail-gas has pressure and can enter a pipe network directly to be used as combustion gas without compression,  the defect of high energy consumption due to the fact that the desorption tail-gas is required to be pressurized for recycling in a traditional PSA technology is overcome,  a desorption tail-gas compressor is omitted,  the reliability of a device is improved,  and meanwhile,  the investment and energy consumption of the device are greatly reduced;  two stages of PSA units are adopted for adsorption,  the product purity is higher than 99.9%,  meanwhile,  the yield is increased to be higher than 90%,  and the double-high (high-purity and high-yield) hydrogen purification goal is achieved.', p.application_date = '2015-12-18 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105347304A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/56', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201480036311.1'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201480036311.1', p.title_cn = '一种净化包含氢气和杂质的合成气的方法', p.title_en = 'A process for purification of a synthesis gas containing hydrogen and impurities', p.abstract_cn = '一种氢合成气流(100)的净化方法，特别是在氨设备的前端，其中所述气体包含氢气和少量的一氧化碳、二氧化碳、水和杂质，所述方法包括步骤：将所述气流(100)甲烷化(13)、将残余量的一氧化碳和二氧化碳转化为甲烷和水、将气体脱水(14)以除去水，然后深冷净化(15)如液氮洗以除去甲烷和氩气；也公开了用于改造氨设备的相应的设备和方法。', p.abstract_en = 'A process for purification of a current of hydrogen synthesis gas (100),  particularly in the front-end of an ammonia plant,  wherein said gas contains hydrogen and minor amounts of carbon monoxide,  carbon dioxide,  water and impurities,  said process including steps of methanation (13) of said current (100),  converting residual amounts of carbon monoxide and carbon dioxide to methane and water,  dehydration (14) of the gas to remove water,  and then a cryogenic purification (15) such as liquid nitrogen wash,  to remove methane and Argon;  a corresponding plant and method for revamping an ammonia plant are also disclosed.', p.application_date = '2014-06-25 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105358476A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201520696326.2'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201520696326.2', p.title_cn = '一种氢气发生器', p.title_en = 'A hydrogen generator', p.abstract_cn = '一种氢气发生器，包括筒体，所述筒体上设有人孔、催化剂填装口以及气体出口，所述筒体底部盖有椭圆封头，所述椭圆封头外周设有若干催化剂出口，所述椭圆封头内侧设有用于催化剂导流的锥体，所述锥体的底部圆周正对所述催化剂出口。与现有技术相比，本实用新型的氢气发生器，在筒体的椭圆封头设置用于催化剂导流的锥体，锥体就占据了原先滞留催化剂的空间，而催化剂便会依附锥体的外周分布，从而增大了催化剂与反应物的接触面积，提升了反应速率，另外锥体的底部圆周正对所述催化剂出口，当反应完成后需要清理发生器，只要打开催化剂出口，催化剂便会顺着锥体外周下滑至催化剂出口，然后排出。', p.abstract_en = 'A hydrogen generator,  comprises a cylinder body,  the cylinder is provided with a manhole,  and filling mouth gas outlet of the catalyst,  are at the bottom of the cylinder head cover,  the periphery of the elliptical head is provided with a plurality of catalyst exit,  is arranged at the inner side of the elliptical head for catalyst flow guiding cone,  said cone to circular at the bottom of the outlet of the catalyst structure. Compared with the prior art,  the utility model the hydrogen generator,  the elliptical end of the tube body is used for catalyst flow guiding cone,  cone occupies the original space of the detention of the catalyst,  but the catalyst would be distributed on the periphery of the cone,  so as to increase the contact area of the catalyst and the reactants,  the reaction rate,  in addition to circular at the bottom of the cone of the outlet of the catalyst structure,  the generator needs to be cleaned after the completion of reaction,  as long as the outlet of the catalyst,  the catalyst will be along the periphery of the cone down to the catalyst outlet,  and then discharged.', p.application_date = '2015-09-09 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN205045819U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'EP03756665'}) SET p.application_no = 'EP03756665', p.title_cn = '自氧化内部加热型蒸汽重整系统', p.title_en = 'AUTOOXIDATION INTERNAL HEATING TYPE STEAM REFORMING SYSTEM', p.abstract_cn = '所述系统是自氧化内部加热蒸汽重整系统进行自原料气体的氧化氧的存在下进行蒸汽重整以产生富氢的重整气体。该系统包括蒸汽发生器(2)包括燃烧部分2a，用于燃烧空气-燃料混合物得到的混合助燃空气与燃料，从而加热水使用燃烧中产生的气体的燃烧部分2a至产生氢气；一种第一吸混合器(4)吸附的原料气体为来自蒸汽发生器的蒸汽流2，得到原料-蒸汽混合物；和氧化重整器1的原料气在原料-蒸汽混合物通过含氧从外部供给的气体，从而进行蒸汽重整的原料气体使用了该反应的热氧化以产生富氢重整气体。', p.abstract_en = 'The system is a self-oxidation internal heating steam reforming system for conducting self-oxidation of a raw material gas under the presence of oxygen and conducting steam reforming to generate a hydrogen-rich reformed gas. The system includes a steam generator 2 including a combustion section 2a for combusting an air-fuel mixture obtained by mixing a combustion air with a fuel,  thereby heating water using a combustion gas generated in the combustion section 2a to generate hydrogen;  a first sucking-mixer 4 for sucking the raw material gas into a steam stream coming from the steam generator 2 to obtain a raw material-steam mixture;  and a reformer 1 for oxidizing the raw material gas in the raw material-steam mixture by an oxygen-containing gas supplied from outside,  thereby conducting steam reforming of the raw material gas using the reaction heat of the oxidation to generate a hydrogen-rich reformed gas.', p.application_date = '2003-10-17 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'EP1559679B1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 2, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'EP14168469'}) SET p.application_no = 'EP14168469', p.title_cn = '使用方法自由热量从氢制造设备向供电区与绿色热加热网络', p.title_en = 'Method using the free heat from a hydrogen production facility to supply district heating networks with green heat', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种使用余热的方法从通过蒸汽重整制氢工艺以有助于加热的水的集中供热网络。通常，合成气低于温度Tg，它不超过160℃，后合成气转化为蒸汽，将热量传递给工艺流体，产生的油烟低于温度Tf为不超过170℃；所述方法还产生了未使用输出蒸汽温度TV的下方高于200℃，热交换与合成气和烟气进行供应的外蒸汽系统利用软化水。根据本发明的方法，可获得的热量从流体加热水，其位于附近的集中热水系统由传热流体的装置，其通常为水，循环在闭合的回路中在可变温度；回路中的水通过间接热交换加热与合成气体和油烟，和从输出蒸汽提供额外的热量需要。本发明还涉及一种设备，用于implemting的方法。', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention relates to a method for using the waste heat from a hydrogen production process by steam reforming to contribute to the heating of the water of a district heating network. Generally,  a synthesis gas is below a temperature TG,  which is no more than 160 DEG C,  after the synthesis gas is converted into steam and transmits heat to a process fluid;  generated fume is below a temperature TF which is no more than 170 DEG C;  and the method also produces unused output steam below a temperature TV higher than 200 DEG C,  so heat exchange with the synthesis gas and the fume is performed to supply an extermal steam system by utilizing demineralized water. According to the method of the invention,  heat which can be obtained from the fluid heats water which locates in a nearby centralized water heating system by means of a heat transfer fluid,  which generally is water,  cycled in a closed loop at a variable temperature;  water in the loop is heated through indirect heat exchange with the synthesis gas and the fume;  and additional heat is supplied from output steam as needed. The invention further relates to equipment for implemting the method.', p.application_date = '2014-05-15 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'EP2816009B1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/36', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2014230768'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2014230768', p.title_cn = '一种燃料重整装置和及其操作方法', p.title_en = 'A fuel reforming device and method of operating the same', p.abstract_cn = '要解决的问题 :  提供一种燃料重整器可包括在原料燃料的充分的除氧气体，既在 燃料重整器的操作而且运转停止时相， 在正在进行的启动相， 和进行中的堵的相位相同。方法 :  燃料重整器中的R包括 :  脱硫剂2填充有脱硫催化剂(2a)用于从烃中去除硫化合物的基于原燃料气体； 重整器3，用于生成含有氢的重整气体作为主成分的蒸汽重整原料燃料 气体脱硫的脱硫剂2； 和氢气添加装置，用于加入部分原料的重整气体的燃料气体流分成 脱硫剂2， 一种氧化还原反应器1中填充有氧化-还原试剂1a用于可逆地和重复诱导氧化-还原反应 氧化和还原状态之间之间设有加法单元8，用于将重整气体的一部分 以原燃料气体和脱硫剂2。', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To provide a fuel reformer capable of sufficiently removing oxygen included within a raw fuel gas not only during the operation of the fuel reformer but also during the operation stoppage phase,  start-in-progress phase,  and stoppage-in-progress phase of the same.SOLUTION :  In a fuel reformer R including :  a desulfurizer 2 filled with a desulfurizing catalyst 2a for removing sulfur compounds from a hydrocarbon-based raw fuel gas;  a reformer 3 for generating a reformed gas including hydrogen as a main component by steam-reforming the raw fuel gas desulfurized by the desulfurizer 2;  and a hydrogen addition means for adding a portion of the reformed gas to the raw fuel gas streaming into the desulfurizer 2,  an oxidation-reduction reactor 1 filled with an oxidation-reduction reagent 1a for reversibly and repeatedly inducing oxidation-reduction reactions between oxidized and reduced states is furnished between the addition unit 8 for adding a portion of the reformed gas to the raw fuel gas and the desulfurizer 2.', p.application_date = '2014-11-13 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP5868477B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2012524067'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2012524067', p.title_cn = '使用所述组合物含有硅和镁的氢生成', p.title_en = 'Using the composition containing silicon and magnesium hydrogen generation', p.abstract_cn = '实施例涉及产生氢的方法包括使镁和硅以形成混合物，并使混合物 与水溶液中，足以生成氢气。 所述溶液可包括水和盐。', p.abstract_en = 'Embodiments relate to methods of generating hydrogen including contacting magnesium and silicon to form a mixture and reacting the mixture with an aqueous solution,  sufficient to generate hydrogen. The solution can include water and salt.', p.application_date = '2010-08-12 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP5869479B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/08', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2012527592'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2012527592', p.title_cn = '氢生成装置及燃料电池系统', p.title_en = 'Hydrogen generator and fuel cell system', p.abstract_cn = '本发明的氢生成装置100具备：重整器4，其通过使用原料气体的重整反应生成含氢气体；向重整装置4供给原料气体的原料气体供给装置13；甲烷化器6，用于通过甲烷化反应还原含氢气体中所含的一氧化碳；以及控制器，用于控制原料气体供应器13，以减少供应到重整器4的原料气体的量，从而当甲烷化器6的温度升高时减少含氢气体的产生量。', p.abstract_en = 'A hydrogen generation apparatus 100 of the present invention includes :  a reformer 4 for generating a hydrogen-containing gas through a reforming reaction using a raw material gas;  a raw material gas supplier 13 for supplying the raw material gas to the reformer 4 ;  a methanator 6 for reducing carbon monoxide contained in the hydrogen-containing gas through a methanation reaction;  and a controller for controlling the raw material gas supplier 13 to decrease an amount of the raw material gas supplied to the reformer 4 so as to decrease an amount of generation of the hydrogen-containing gas when a temperature of the methanator 6 increases.', p.application_date = '2011-08-02 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP5870269B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CA2522401'}) SET p.application_no = 'CA2522401', p.title_cn = '系统和高压氢的制造方法', p.title_en = 'SYSTEM AND PROCESS FOR PRODUCING HIGH-PRESSURE HYDROGEN', p.abstract_cn = '一种方法和设备用于生产高压氢气从天然气，甲醇，乙醇，或其它化石燃料衍生的和可再生的烃资源。该方法可产生氢在压力为从2000至12, 000磅/平方英寸(psi))使用氢原料(16，18)高压水(12，18)，和合适的催化剂。如下制备和加热预热器(14)，催化剂与氢气反应的原料(16，18)和高压水(12，18)在催化重整器(20)保持在期望的温度和压力条件。重整器的重整产品出口(200)流入冷凝器(22)，在水和二氧化碳产品的一部分冷凝。', p.abstract_en = 'A method and apparatus for use in producing high-pressure hydrogen from natural gas,  methanol,  ethanol,  or other fossil fuel-derived and renewable hydrocarbon resources. The process can produce hydrogen at pressure ranging from 2000 to 12, 000 pounds per square inch (psi) using a hydrogen feedstock (16,  18) high pressure water (12,  18),  and an appropriate catalyst. Following making and heating in preheater (14),  the catalyst reacts with the hydrogen feedstock (16,  18) and high pressure water (12,  18) in a catalytic reformer (20) maintained under desired temperature and pressure conditions. Reformate products exit reformer (200) and flow into condenser (22),  in which water and a portion of the carbon dioxide product are condensed.', p.application_date = '2004-04-15 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CA2522401C', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CA2829539'}) SET p.application_no = 'CA2829539', p.title_cn = '氢产生方法和装置及其控制系统', p.title_en = 'HYDROGEN GENERATION PROCESSES AND APPARATUS AND CONTROL SYSTEM', p.abstract_cn = '用于产生氢气的氢气发生器和方法从燃料部分氧化/蒸气重整的燃料提供可以实现希望的纯氢气的效率范围上的燃料和氢气产品的生产速率和纯度。方法包括将含氧流和至少一个含有燃料和蒸汽流，提供一种重整器进料，用于产生包含氢的重整产物在部分氧化和蒸汽重整条件。重整产物进行间接换热，进一步产生冷却器从其氢重整产品回收。', p.abstract_en = 'Hydrogen generators and processes for generating hydrogen from a fuel using partial oxidation/steam reforming of fuel are provided that can achieve desirable Net Hydrogen Efficiencies over a range of fuels and hydrogen product production rates and purities. Processes include combining oxygen-containing streams and at least one stream containing fuel and steam,  to provide a reformer feed which is used to generate a reformate comprising hydrogen under partial oxydation and steam reforming conditions. The reformate is then subjected to indirect heat exchange to further produce a cooler reformate from which a hydrogen product is recovered.', p.application_date = '2007-07-06 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CA2829539C', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/32', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US13978832'}) SET p.application_no = 'US13978832', p.title_cn = '燃料处理机', p.title_en = 'Fuel processor', p.abstract_cn = '本发明的目的是提供一种燃料处理器，其能够减少由结构的热变形引起的重整催化剂劣化。 燃料处理器包括重整器8，重整器8被供给燃料气体70以通过重整催化剂7的反应精制富氢重整气体73。 在内筒18和外筒19之间的填充有重整催化剂7的空间中设置有用于分割重整催化剂7的多个隔板20。 所有的隔板20都从外部圆柱体悬臂，防止隔板20在温度变化中彼此接触。 这可以减少由重整催化剂7的压缩应力引起的劣化，例如破碎或粉末化。', p.abstract_en = 'An object of the present invention is to provide a fuel processor that can reduce reforming catalyst deterioration caused by thermal deformation of a structure. The fuel processor includes a reformer 8 that is fed with fuel gas 70 to refine hydrogen-rich reformed gas 73 by a reaction of a reforming catalyst 7. A plurality of partition plates 20 for dividing the reforming catalyst 7 are provided in a space filled with the reforming catalyst 7 between an internal cylinder 18 and an external cylinder 19. All the partition plates 20 are cantilevered from the external cylinder,  preventing the partition plates 20 from coming into contact with each other in temperature variations. This can reduce deterioration such as crushing or powdering that is caused by a compressive stress of the reforming catalyst 7.', p.application_date = '2012-08-29 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9266729B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/32', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 3, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US13801538'}) SET p.application_no = 'US13801538', p.title_cn = '重油沥青部分改质工艺', p.title_en = 'Partial upgrading process for heavy oil and bitumen', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种用于烃合成的沥青和重油改质方法和系统，其示例是合成原油(SCO)。 该工艺将费托合成技术与气化和富氢气流床相结合。 富氢气体的产生可以使用氢源、来自加氢处理和费托法的富氢蒸汽、蒸汽甲烷重整器(SMR)和自热重整器(ATR)或SMR/ATR的组合单独或组合来方便地实现。 将用于升级的原料蒸馏并将塔底馏分在费-托反应器中气化和转化。 然后将得到的贫氢合成气暴露于富氢气流中以优化例如合成原油的形成。 还详细说明了部分升级和相应的好处。 本说明书还描述了一种用于实现所述过程的系统。', p.abstract_en = 'A bitumen and heavy oil upgrading process and system is disclosed for the synthesis of hydrocarbons,  an example of which is synthetic crude oil (SCO). The process integrates Fischer-Tropsch technology with gasification and hydrogen rich gas stream generation. The hydrogen rich gas generation is conveniently effected using singly or in combination a hydrogen source,  a hydrogen rich vapor from hydroprocessing and the Fischer-Tropsch process,  a steam methane reformer (SMR) and autothermal reformer (ATR) or a combination of SMR/ATR. The feedstock for upgrading is distilled and the bottoms fraction is gasified and converted in a Fischer-Tropsch reactor. A resultant hydrogen lean syngas is then exposed to the hydrogen rich gas stream to optimize the formation of,  for example,  the synthetic crude oil. Partial upgrading and the commensurate benefits is detailed as well. A system for effecting the processes is also characterized in the specification.', p.application_date = '2013-03-13 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9266730B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/34', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 2, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14130942'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14130942', p.title_cn = '合成气生产方法', p.title_en = 'Process for production of synthesis gas', p.abstract_cn = '一种生产合成气(3)的方法，其中甲烷和二氧化碳(2)被引入反应空间(R)中，并在固体(W)存在下在高温下反应，得到氢气和一氧化碳。 甲烷和二氧化碳通过含碳粒状材料(W)并在高温区(H)中反应。', p.abstract_en = 'Process for the production of synthesis gas (3),  in which methane and carbon dioxide (2) are introduced into a reaction space (R) and reacted in the presence of a solid (W) at elevated temperatures to give hydrogen and carbon monoxide. Methane and carbon dioxide are passed through a carbon-containing granular material (W) and reacted in a high-temperature zone (H).', p.application_date = '2012-07-05 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9266731B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'IN9517DELNP2015'}) SET p.application_no = 'IN9517DELNP2015', p.title_cn = '用于使用氨中和制氢设备', p.title_en = 'VENT LINE FOR USE IN AMMONIA AND HYDROGEN PLANTS', p.abstract_cn = '在氨或氢气的设备，该设备包括进料段，重整段和偏移部，该换档部分包括低温变换炉和中温变换炉，通风管路的下游设置低温变换炉和中温变换炉中，以便允许所述换档来再次加热，工艺气体在低压下(通常是3-7巴)。这样避免了工艺气体中的水蒸汽冷凝。通过将该排放管道可以节省相当多的时间，更具体讲$time，临时关闭后重启的生产方法，由于LTS/手动切换开关的转换器加热的氮气循环的现象。', p.abstract_en = 'In an ammonia or hydrogen plant comprising a desulfurisation section,  a reforming section and a shift section,  where the shift section comprises a low temperature shift converter and a medium temperature shift converter,  a vent line is arranged down stream from the low temperature shift converter and the medium temperature shift converter in order to allow the shift converters to be re-heated with process gas at a low pressure (typically 3-7 bar). This way condensation of water vapour in the process gas is avoided. By applying this vent line it becomes possible to save significant time,  more specifically 8-24 hours,  for restarting the production after temporary shut-down thereof,  because a heat-up of the LTS/MTS converter in circulating nitrogen is avoided.', p.application_date = '2015-10-12 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'IN9517DELNP2015A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'ES08102939'}) SET p.application_no = 'ES08102939', p.title_cn = '催化转化的蒸汽与回收', p.title_en = 'Catalytic Reformed steam with recycling', p.abstract_cn = '方法用于产生氢气的生产设备中具有催化蒸汽重整器，锅炉下游的催化蒸汽重整器，任选地具有预重整器，并且任选地具有转移反应器，其中形成重整器进料气体混合物使用含蒸汽再循环气体混合物是从锅炉流出物。所述锅炉产生的蒸汽可用于形成重整器进料气体混合物，用于生产设施中的其它地方，和/或用于输出蒸汽。', p.abstract_en = 'A method for generating hydrogen in a production facility having a catalytic steam reformer,  a boiler downstream of the catalytic steam reformer,  optionally having a prereformer,  and optionally having a shift reactor,  wherein the reformer feed gas mixture is formed using a steam-containing recycle gas mixture which was formed from boiler effluent. The boiler generates steam which may be used to form the reformer feed gas mixture,  used elsewhere in the production facility,  and/or used for export steam.', p.application_date = '2008-03-26 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'ES2560250T3', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2015503415'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2015503415', p.title_cn = '所有的粗气体在气化炉壁和用于发电的集成方法', p.title_en = 'All of the crude gas in a gasification furnace walls and integrated process for power generation', p.abstract_cn = '成本低，通过混合细碎的材料用于产生灰所有的部分氧化粗煤气中的反应挖掘集成方法，水-气变换反应气化，气化，任选地含有大量氢产物流的产生。从通过气化回收显热热量值，工艺蒸汽和产生电力。', p.abstract_en = 'An integrated process for the partial oxidation of whole crude oil mixed with a low cost finely divided solid ash-producing material in a membrane wall gasification reactor produces a syngas and,  optionally,  a more hydrogen-rich product stream by subjecting the syngas to a water-gas shift reaction. Process steam and electricity are produced by recovering the sensible heat values from the hot syngas.', p.application_date = '2013-03-22 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP2015514665A5', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/36', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14457211'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14457211', p.title_cn = '在水裂解反应中机械地和化学地转化元素硅的系统、设备和方法', p.title_en = 'SYSTEM,  APPARATUS,  AND METHOD TO MECHANICALLY AND CHEMICALLY CONVERT THE ELEMENT SILICON IN A WATER SPLIT REACTION', p.abstract_cn = '一种使用硅作为能量载体作为碳氢化合物燃料替代物的系统和方法。 所述方法可包括使用能量来纯化和精炼硅，并将其转化为有用的原料以进料到反应器系统中。 反应器系统提供了一种环境，其中硅可以被研磨或化学处理，然后可以与水反应形成氢气。 然后可以直接使用或储存该氢气，并且可以根据需要对反应中使用的硅进行再循环。', p.abstract_en = 'A system and method for using silicon as an energy carrier as an alternative to hydrocarbon fuel. The method may include using energy to purify and refine silicon,  and converting it into useful feedstock to be fed into a reactor system. The reactor system provides an environment in which silicon may be abraded or chemically treated and may then be reacted with water to form hydrogen gas. This hydrogen gas may then be directly used or stored,  and the silicon used in the reaction may be recycled as desired.', p.application_date = '2014-08-12 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US20160046486A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/06', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14872663'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14872663', p.title_cn = '在水裂解反应中机械地和化学地转化元素硅的系统、设备和方法', p.title_en = 'SYSTEM,  APPARATUS,  AND METHOD TO MECHANICALLY AND CHEMICALLY CONVERT THE ELEMENT SILICON IN A WATER SPLIT REACTION', p.abstract_cn = '一种使用硅作为能量载体作为碳氢化合物燃料替代物的系统和方法。 所述方法可包括使用能量来纯化和精炼硅，并将其转化为有用的原料以进料到反应器系统中。 反应器系统提供了一种环境，其中硅可以被研磨或化学处理，然后可以与水反应形成氢气。 然后可以直接使用或储存该氢气，并且可以根据需要对反应中使用的硅进行再循环。', p.abstract_en = 'A system and method for using silicon as an energy carrier as an alternative to hydrocarbon fuel. The method may include using energy to purify and refine silicon,  and converting it into useful feedstock to be fed into a reactor system. The reactor system provides an environment in which silicon may be abraded or chemically treated and may then be reacted with water to form hydrogen gas. This hydrogen gas may then be directly used or stored,  and the silicon used in the reaction may be recycled as desired.', p.application_date = '2015-10-01 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US20160046487A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/06', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14832701'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14832701', p.title_cn = '烃类重整工艺', p.title_en = 'PROCESS FOR REFORMING HYDROCARBONS', p.abstract_cn = '一种利用自热重整生产合成气的方法，其中来自下游费托合成的尾气被氢化，然后加入到自热重整阶段。', p.abstract_en = 'A process for the production of synthesis gas by the use of autothermal reforming in which tail gas from downstream Fischer-Tropsh synthesis is hydrogenated and then added to the autothermal reforming stage.', p.application_date = '2015-08-21 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US20160046488A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WOJP15070225'}) SET p.application_no = 'WOJP15070225', p.title_cn = '氢气净化方法和净化用于该方法的装置', p.title_en = 'HYDROGEN GAS PURIFICATION METHOD AND PURIFICATION DEVICE FOR SAME', p.abstract_cn = '提供 : 氢气净化方法，通过该杂质可以从氢气中除去提取用有机化学氢化物或等，可净化氢气具有高回收率，和用于所述方法的净化装置。氢气净化方法，其中两个吸附塔(10a)，10b填充有吸附剂用于纯化含有杂质气体的粗氢，所述方法包括吸附循环包括至少一个吸附步骤，其中吸附杂质的吸附剂在吸附柱(10a)，10b，从而分离从原料氢气的杂质，和热再生步骤，在加热的吹扫气体提供给吸附柱吸附步骤后，从而剥离杂质从吸附剂，所述周期进行反复在每个吸附柱10a，(10B)的吸附步骤进行的同时在一个吸附柱，吸附步骤以外的步骤中进行另一吸附塔。在热再生步骤，吹扫气体循环的同时被加热。', p.abstract_en = 'Provided are :  a hydrogen gas purification method by which impurities can be removed from hydrogen gas extracted using organic chemical hydrides or the like,  and which can purify the hydrogen gas with a high recovery rate;  and a purification device for said method. A hydrogen gas purification method in which two adsorption columns 10A,  10B filled with an adsorbent are used to purify raw hydrogen gas containing impurities,  said method comprising an adsorption cycle including at least an adsorption step,  in which the impurities are absorbed by the adsorbent in the adsorption columns 10A,  10B,  thereby separating the impurities from the raw hydrogen gas,  and a thermal regeneration step,  in which a heated purge gas is provided to the adsorption columns after the adsorption step,  thereby stripping the impurities from the adsorbent,  said cycle being carried out repeatedly in each of the adsorption columns 10A,  10B. While the adsorption step is being carried out in one adsorption column,  a step other than the adsorption step is being carried out in the other adsorption column. In the thermal regeneration step,  the purge gas is circulated while being heated.', p.application_date = '2015-07-15 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016024456A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/56', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WOJP15072867'}) SET p.application_no = 'WOJP15072867', p.title_cn = '氢气和烯烃净化系统', p.title_en = 'HYDROGEN AND OLEFIN PURIFICATION SYSTEM', p.abstract_cn = '提供一种氢气和烯烃净化系统净化氢气和烯烃作为有用气体从混合气体至少含有氢和烯烃，和能净化氢气和/或烯烃在较高的回收率。烯烃分离膜组件10a设置在现有级氢分离膜组件20a，和使烯烃分离从混合气体在现有级到氢气分离膜模块20A换句话说，净化系统1可以具有更高的氢气回收率由于氢气通过氢气分离 分离膜21中氢的浓度增加后第一的非透过气体。作为结果，该净化系统1净化氢气和烯烃作为有用气体从混合气体至少含有氢和烯烃，和可以纯化氢气在较高的回收率。', p.abstract_en = 'Provided is a hydrogen and olefin purification system that purifies hydrogen and an olefin as useful gases from a mixed gas containing at least hydrogen and an olefin,  and that can purify the hydrogen and/or the olefin at a higher recovery rate. An olefin separation membrane module 10A is disposed at a prior stage to a hydrogen separation membrane module 20A,  and so an olefin is separated from a mixed gas at a prior stage to the hydrogen separation membrane module 20A. In other words,  the purification system 1 can have a higher recovery rate of hydrogen because hydrogen is separated by a hydrogen separation membrane 21 after increasing the hydrogen concentration in a first non-permeated gas. As a result,  the purification system 1 purifies hydrogen and an olefin as useful gases from a mixed gas containing at least hydrogen and an olefin,  and can purify hydrogen at a higher recovery rate.', p.application_date = '2015-08-12 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016024619A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/56', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201080022074.5'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201080022074.5', p.title_cn = '氢产生材料及其制造方法、氢的制造方法以及氢制造装置', p.title_en = 'Hydrogen generation material and its manufacturing method,  and manufacturing method of hydrogen-producing apparatus for producing hydrogen', p.abstract_cn = '本发明提供一种即使在大气中也稳定的氢产生材料等。一种氢产生材料，其含有表面被缓慢氧化处理的Mg纳米粒子，该经缓慢氧化处理的Mg纳米粒子与水反应产生氢。该Mg纳米粒子的比表面积低于70m2/g高于3m2/g。上述氢产生材料进一步含有标准电极电位在正方向上比Mg大的金属的粉末。一种所述的氢产生材料的制造方法，至少具备以下的步骤(a)以及(b)：(a)将Mg金属块在氢、氮、Ar或它们的混合气体气氛中进行电弧熔化得到Mg纳米粒子的步骤，(b)将所述Mg纳米粒子的表面进行缓慢氧化处理的步骤。', p.abstract_en = '', p.application_date = '2010-05-24 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN102438939B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/08', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201410381658.1'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201410381658.1', p.title_cn = '一种能延长催化剂使用寿命的CO变换工艺', p.title_en = 'One can prolong the service life of the catalyst of the conversion process CO', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及到一种能延长催化剂使用寿命的CO变换工艺，其特征在于包括下述步骤：粗合成气分为两股，初始时第一股与第二股的流量比为3 : 7；第一股粗煤气送入第一变换炉中进行变换反应，控制水气比为1.7-1.8，温度为250～270℃；第二股与一变混合气混合，送入第二变换炉；当第一变换炉出口一变混合气中干基CO浓度≥6v％时，改变第一股粗煤气和第二股粗煤气的分配比例为1 : 1，向第一股粗煤气中补入的蒸汽量不变，进入第一变换炉的水气比变为1.45-1.55；当第一变换炉出口一变混合气中干基CO浓度≥7.5v％时，改变第一股粗煤气和第二股粗煤气的分配比例为7 : 3，向第一股粗煤气中补入的蒸汽量不变，进入第一变换炉的粗合成气的水气比变为1.15-1.25。本发明能有效控制反应超温从而延长催化剂使用寿命。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a CO conversion process capable of prolonging the service life of catalysts. The CO conversion process capable of prolonging the service life of catalysts is characterized by comprising the following steps :  crude synthesis gas is divided into two strands;  initially,  the flow ratio of a first stand of the crude synthesis gas and a second strand of the crude synthesis gas is 3 : 7;  a first raw gas is blown into a first conversion furnace for conversion reaction;  the water-air ratio is controlled to be 1.7-1.8;  the temperature is 250-270 DEC G;  the second strand of the raw gas is mixed with a variable gas mixture and blown into a second conversion furnace;  when the dry basis CO concentration in a variable gas mixture at the exit of the first conversion furnace is equal to or larger than 6v %,  the distribution ratio of the first strand of raw gas and the second strand of raw gas is changed into 1 : 1;  the vapor quantity supplemented to the first strand of raw gas is not changed;  the water-air ratio entering the first conversion furnace is changed into 1.45-1.65;  when the dry basis CO concentration in a variable gas mixture at the exit of the first conversion furnace is equal to or larger than 7.5 v %,  the distribution ratio of the first strand of raw gas and the second strand of raw gas is changed into 7 : 3;  the vapor quantity supplemented to the first strand of raw gas is not changed;  the water-air ratio of the crude synthesis gas entering the first conversion furnace is changed into 1.15-1.25. The CO conversion process provided by the invention can effectively control reaction over temperature,  therefore,  the service life of the catalysts is prolonged.', p.application_date = '2014-08-06 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN104152187B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/16', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201510849968.6'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201510849968.6', p.title_cn = '一种纳米掺杂剂改性的LiBH4储氢材料及其制备方法', p.title_en = 'Nano doping agent modified LiBH4 hydrogen storage material and preparation method thereof', p.abstract_cn = '本发明提供一种纳米掺杂剂改性的LiBH4储氢材料及其制备方法，所述储氢材料由纳米铁氧体掺杂剂与配位氢化物LiBH4组成，其中掺杂剂的摩尔比为3-11％，所述制备方法包括采用PV内衬的球磨罐和氧化锆材质磨球的球磨1000～1500rpm转速下球磨20-100min。本发明的纳米掺杂剂改性的LiBH4储氢材料，其初始分解温度降幅可达226℃，最终放氢量提升5倍以上，在300℃下的动力学性能得到显著提高，制备方法简单易行。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention provides a nano doping agent modified LiBH4 hydrogen storage material and a preparation method thereof. The hydrogen storage material is composed of a nano ferrite doping agent and a ligand hydride LiBH4,  wherein the mol ratio of the doping agent is 3% to 11%. The preparation method comprises the following step of carrying out ball milling for 20 to 100 minutes at the rotary speed of 1000rpm to 1500rpm by adopting a ball milling pot with a PV lining and a zirconium oxide material milling ball. According to the nano doping agent modified LiBH4 hydrogen storage material,  the decreasing range of an initial decomposition temperature can be up to 226 DEG C and the final hydrogen releasing amount is improved by more than 5 times;  the dynamic performance at 300 DEG C can be remarkably improved and the preparation method is simple and feasible.', p.application_date = '2015-11-27 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105329852A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201510756645.2'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201510756645.2', p.title_cn = '基于甲醇水制氢的便携式移动制氢机', p.title_en = 'Portable mobile hydrogen making machine based on principle of making hydrogen through methyl alcohol water', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了基于甲醇水制氢的便携式移动制氢机，包括汽化室和重整室，还包括一个机壳，所述汽化室和重整室设置在机壳内，所述机壳上设有甲醇水原料入口、氢气出口；所述制氢机内还设有氢气纯化模块、燃烧器和主控制面板，所述甲醇水原料入口、汽化室、重整室、氢气纯化模块的氢气输出端和氢气出口依次相继连接；本发明不需要外接交流电或采用大型的变压装置，体积小、便携且容易移动，实现了自给供热，只需要提供甲醇水原料即可维持制氢机的运行，解决了氢气运输和储存成本高的问题，降低使用氢能的成本，对于氢能的开发、氢能源进入市场生产具有很大的促进作用，实现能源使用的可持续发展，大大提高了经济效益和社会效益。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention discloses a portable mobile hydrogen making machine based on the principle of making hydrogen through methyl alcohol water. The portable mobile hydrogen making machine based on the principle of making hydrogen through methyl alcohol water comprises a vaporizer and a reforming chamber and further comprises a machine case. The vaporizer and the reforming chamber are arranged in the machine case. The machine case is provided with a methyl alcohol water raw material inlet and a hydrogen outlet;  a hydrogen purifying module,  a combustor and a master control panel are further arranged in the hydrogen making machine. The methyl alcohol water raw material inlet,  the vaporizer,  the reforming chamber,  the hydrogen output end of the hydrogen purifying module and the hydrogen outlet are sequentially connected. External alternating current or a large potential device are not needed,  the size is small,  the portable mobile hydrogen making machine is portable and easy to move,  heat self-supply is achieved,  running of the hydrogen making machine can be maintained just by providing a methyl alcohol water raw material,  the problem that hydrogen transportation and storage cost is high is solved,  the hydrogen energy using cost is reduced,  the portable mobile hydrogen making machine has a large promoting effect on hydrogen energy development and the situation that hydrogen energy enters the market for production,  sustainable development of energy use is achieved,  and economic benefits and social benefits are greatly improved.', p.application_date = '2015-11-06 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105329853A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/32', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201510688612.9'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201510688612.9', p.title_cn = '用于提高氨合成效率的系统和方法', p.title_en = 'Systems and methods for improving ammonia synthesis efficiency', p.abstract_cn = '提供了一种生产合成气的系统和方法。在至少一种具体实施方案中，烃可以在水蒸气和一种或多种第一催化剂存在下，在第一反应区中重整来提供处于第一温度的流出物，该流出物含有一部分的烃、一氧化碳、二氧化碳和氢气。该第一反应区可以包括一种或多种包含催化剂的管。该流出物可以从第一温度间接加热到第二温度。处于第二温度的流出物可以在一种或多种氧化剂和一种或多种第二催化剂存在下，在足够的条件下重整来提供合成气，该合成气包含氢气，一氧化碳，二氧化碳，和小于大约5mol%干基的甲烷。该合成气可以用于将流出物从第一温度间接加热到第二温度。', p.abstract_en = 'Systems and methods for producing syngas are provided. In at least one specific embodiment,  a hydrocarbon can be reformed in the presence of steam and one or more first catalysts in a first reaction zone to provide an effluent containing a portion of the hydrocarbon,  carbon monoxide,  carbon dioxide,  and hydrogen at a first temperature. The first reaction zone can include one or more catalyst-containing tubes. The effluent can be indirectly heated from the first temperature to a second temperature. The effluent at the second temperature can be reformed in the presence of one or more oxidants and one or more second catalysts at conditions sufficient to provide a syngas comprising hydrogen,  carbon monoxide,  carbon dioxide,  and less than about 5% mol,  dry basis,  methane. The syngas can be used to indirectly heat the effluent from the first temperature to the second temperature.', p.application_date = '2009-10-19 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105329854A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'EP10784260'}) SET p.application_no = 'EP10784260', p.title_cn = '用于生产合成气的方法及燃烧器', p.title_en = 'METHOD AND BURNER FOR PRODUCING SYNTHESIS GAS', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及生产合成气的部分氧化液态或气态的，含碳燃料在存在含氧的氧化剂，其中所述燃料，氧化剂和调节剂分别供给到燃烧器，其中所述燃料和调节剂混合在燃烧器的混合室，在它们被带入与氧化剂接触。减少负载的燃烧器，特别在操作过程中与瞬态情况下，所述氧化剂为集中引入通过出口开口的燃烧器，燃烧室和混合物燃料和减速剂通过出口开口引入到燃烧室同心地围绕氧化剂。', p.abstract_en = 'This invention relates to the production of synthesis gas by partial oxidation of liquid or gaseous,  carbonaceous fuel in the presence of an oxygen-containing oxidant,  wherein the fuel,  the oxidant and a moderator are separately supplied to a burner and wherein the fuel and the moderator are mixed in a mixing chamber of the burner,  before they are brought in contact with the oxidant. To reduce the load of the burner in particular during operation with transient conditions,  the oxidant is centrally introduced through an outlet opening of the burner into a combustion chamber and the mixture of fuel and moderator is introduced through the outlet opening into the combustion chamber concentrically around the oxidant.', p.application_date = '2010-11-12 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'EP2523899B1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/36', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2012221375'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2012221375', p.title_cn = '一种供氢系统', p.title_en = 'A hydrogen supply system', p.abstract_cn = '氢供应系统用于将氢气包括反应单元，用于产生含氢气体通过脱氢 反应的起始原料， 供热单元，用于提供热量给反应单元， 一种去除单元去除通过膜分离含氢的脱氢产物从反应产生的气体 单元， 和第一脱气线，用于提供部分或全部的废气从所述去除单元 至反应单元。', p.abstract_en = 'A hydrogen supply system for supplying hydrogen comprises a reaction unit for producing a hydrogen-containing gas by a dehydrogenation reaction of a starting material,  a heat supply unit for supplying heat to the reaction unit,  a removal unit for removing through membrane separation a dehydrogenation product from the hydrogen-containing gas produced by the reaction unit,  and a first off-gas line for supplying a part or whole of an off-gas from the removal unit to the reaction unit.', p.application_date = '2012-10-03 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP5864393B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/26', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2013126557'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2013126557', p.title_cn = '改进的多层复合材料的吸气剂', p.title_en = 'Improved multilayer composite material getter', p.abstract_cn = '描述了多层复合吸气剂。还描述了一种方法，用于制造的多层复合吸气剂和储能的电化学装置是应用多层复合吸气剂。', p.abstract_en = 'A multi-layer composite getter is described. Also described is a method for the manufacturing of the multi-layer composite getter and electrochemical devices for energy storage that employ the multi-layer composite getter.', p.application_date = '2013-06-17 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP5865869B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/56', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'BRPI1007232'}) SET p.application_no = 'BRPI1007232', p.title_cn = '“系统的气体生产合成质量高，和用于连续干燥的改造，和方法，产生气体，Síntasesíntase，用于深dessulfurizaodessulfuriza°的合成气，用于连续干燥的改造“', p.title_en = '“SYSTEMS FOR GAS PRODUCTION OF SYNTHESIS OF HIGH QUALITY,  AND FOR THE CONTINUOUS REFORMATION THE DRY ONE,  AND,  METHODS TO PRODUCE síntaseSÍNTASE GAS,  FOR DEEP dessulfurizaçãoDESSULFURIZAÇÃO OF SYNTHESIS GAS,  AND FOR THE CONTINUOUS REFORMATION THE DRY ONE”', p.abstract_cn = '合成气深度脱硫的方法，包括将含碳材料和任选的蒸汽进入气化器包括热传递介质，提取第一传热流包括传热介质和任选地未转化含碳材料从气化炉，和将至少一部分第一传热流至燃烧器，通入氧化剂，和任选的燃料到燃烧器中，提取第二传热流包括来自燃烧器的热传递介质，和将至少第二传热流的一部分进入气化器，将化合物可与硫反应生成硫酸盐，硫化物或两个，提取净化流包含灰分，硫酸，卤化物，或其组合从第二传热流，提取烟气从燃烧器，和提取气化器的合成气产品流包括从气化炉出来的小于1000的硫。', p.abstract_en = 'A method for continuous dry reforming,  the method comprising :  introducing a feed comprising carbon dioxide and at least one selected from methane and propane into a fluid bed conditioner operated at a conditioning temperature,  wherein the fluid bed conditioner is one fluid bed of a dual fluidized bed loop and is configured to convert at least a portion of said feed into synthesis gas components;  extracting a first catalytic heat transfer stream comprising a catalytic heat transfer material and having a first temperature from the fluid bed conditioner and introducing at least a portion of the first catalytic heat transfer stream and a flue gas into a fluid bed combustor,  wherein the fluid bed combustor is configured to regenerate the catalyst via combustion;  extracting a second catalytic heat transfer stream comprising catalytic heat transfer material and having a second temperature from the fluid bed combustor and introducing at least a portion of the second catalytic heat transfer stream into the fluid bed conditioner;  and extracting synthesis gas from the fluid bed conditioner.', p.application_date = '2010-01-21 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'BRPI1007232A2', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/44', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CA2720533'}) SET p.application_no = 'CA2720533', p.title_cn = '铝-碱金属氢氧化物可再生氢发生器', p.title_en = 'ALUMINUM-ALKALI HYDROXIDE RECYCLABLE HYDROGEN GENERATOR', p.abstract_cn = '铝-碱金属氢氧化物可再生氢发生器提供使氢气的产生用于消费装置的需要。氢气发生器包括铝源，源的氢氧化物，源水，和反应室，其中，所述至少一个的铝的量，氢氧化钠，和水引入反应室用于限制化学反应量的控制产生氢。', p.abstract_en = 'An aluminum-alkali hydroxide recyclable hydrogen generator is provided that enables generation of hydrogen for a consuming apparatus on demand. The hydrogen generator includes a source of aluminum,  a source of a hydroxide,  a source of water,  and a reaction chamber,  where the amount of at least one of the aluminum,  sodium hydroxide,  and water that is introduced into the reaction chamberis used to limit the chemical reaction to control the amount of hydrogengenerated.', p.application_date = '2009-04-02 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CA2720533C', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/08', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2014126042'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2014126042', p.title_cn = '氢气发生器', p.title_en = 'The hydrogen generator', p.abstract_cn = '要解决的问题 :  获得氢气通过简单的水的分解。方法 :  一种催化剂筒3由SUS304设置相邻的蒸汽腔室2用于把水变为蒸汽， 和产生氢气通过加热的催化剂筒3至约700a°C与热传递加热器4与 无需催化剂，所述催化剂筒3。 加入NaOH进一步作为催化剂，氢产生400a°C。', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To obtain hydrogen by simple decomposition of water.SOLUTION :  A catalyst cylinder 3 composed of SUS304 is arranged adjacent to a steam chamber 2 for changing water into steam,  and hydrogen is generated by heating the catalyst cylinder 3 to about 700°C with a heat transfer heater 4 with no catalyst in the catalyst cylinder 3. By adding NaOH further as a catalyst,  hydrogen is generated at 400°C.', p.application_date = '2014-06-19 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP5860099B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/08', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2011087937'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2011087937', p.title_cn = 'CO2生产合成气不消耗', p.title_en = 'CO2 production of synthesis gas is not exhausted', p.abstract_cn = '提供了一种生产合成气而没有CO2排放的方法。在通过重整烃类气体生产合成气的方法中，重整反应是通过将包含添加到其中的蒸汽和/或二氧化碳的轻质烃类气体供应到管壳式热交换器型重整器的填充有催化剂的管侧，并且在管壳式热交换器型重整器的壳侧中循环由热源如太阳能热或核热加热的加热介质如熔融盐来引起的。从管侧排出的生成气体中除去二氧化碳，向管侧的上游侧供给并再循环。', p.abstract_en = 'There is provided a method for producing synthesis gas without CO 2 emissions. In the method for producing synthesis gas by reforming a hydrocarbon gas,  a reforming reaction is caused by supplying a light hydrocarbon gas containing steam and/or carbon dioxide added thereto to a catalyst-filled tube side of a shell-and-tube heat exchanger-type reformer and circulating a heating medium,  such as a molten salt,  heated by a heat source such as solar heat or nuclear heat in a shell side of the shell-and-tube heat exchanger-type reformer. Carbon dioxide is removed from a produced gas discharged from the tube side and is supplied to the upstream side of the tube side and recycled.', p.application_date = '2011-04-12 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP5860224B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14117211'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14117211', p.title_cn = '整体干燥气化', p.title_en = 'Integrated drying gasification', p.abstract_cn = '一种集成干燥气化系统，包括气化器和气流干燥器，气化器用于气化碳质燃料以产生热的产物气体，气流干燥器接收热的产物气体以在气化之前干燥碳质燃料。 气化器的至少一个入口将来自系统的一种或多种另外的气体，例如再循环的合成气、蒸汽和/或再循环的二氧化碳，输送到气化器，以从气化器产生增加的热产物气体质量流速。 所述系统可包括多个锁料斗系统，所述锁料斗系统联接到夹带流干燥器。 至少一个中间储存容器可设置在气化器的一个或多个进料支腿中，以在一个临时时段内独立于提供给气流干燥器的碳质燃料而保持对气化器的碳质燃料的恒定供应。', p.abstract_en = 'An integrated drying gasification system comprises a gasifier for gasifying carbonaceous fuel to produce hot product gas and an entrained flow dryer which receives the hot product gas to dry the carbonaceous fuel prior to gasification. At least one inlet to the gasifier communicates one or more additional gases from the system,  such as recycled syngas,  steam and/or recycled carbon dioxide,  to the gasifier to generate an increased hot product gas mass flow rate from the gasifier. The system may comprise a plurality of lock hopper systems coupled to the entrained flow dryer. At least one intermediate storage vessel may be provided in one or more feed legs to the gasifier maintain a constant supply of carbonaceous fuel to the gasifier for a temporary period independently of carbonaceous fuel supplied to the entrained flow dryer.', p.application_date = '2012-05-09 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9260301B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14379039'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14379039', p.title_cn = '水煤气变换工艺', p.title_en = 'Water gas shift process', p.abstract_cn = '通过水煤气变换工艺使氢气生产工艺中的高压蒸汽供应更有效，所述水煤气变换工艺交替地包括 : (a)反应阶段，其中将包含CO和H2O的原料气进料到含有能够吸附H2O和CO2的吸附剂材料的水煤气变换反应器中，并且其中收集从反应器中排出的产物气体，(b)再生阶段，其中从反应器中除去CO2，(c)装载阶段，其中将H2O进料到反应器中； 其中所述原料气体混合物具有低于1.2的H2O与CO的摩尔比，并且所述装载阶段在低于所述反应阶段的压力下进行。', p.abstract_en = 'High-pressure steam supply in hydrogen production process is made more efficient by water gas shift process which comprises,  in alternating sequence :  (a) a reaction stage wherein a feed gas comprising CO and H2O is fed into a water gas shift reactor containing a sorbent material capable of adsorbing H2O and CO2 and wherein a product gas issuing from the reactor is collected,  (b) a regeneration stage wherein CO2 is removed from the reactor,  (c) a loading stage,  wherein H2O is fed into the reactor;  wherein said feed gas mixture has a molar ratio of H2O to CO below 1.2,  and the loading stage is performed at a lower pressure than the pressure of the reaction stage.', p.application_date = '2013-02-15 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9260302B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/16', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 2, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14380741'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14380741', p.title_cn = '氨合成气的生产方法和氨工厂的相关前端', p.title_en = 'Process for producing ammonia synthesis gas and a related front-end of an ammonia plant', p.abstract_cn = '一种从烃源生产氨合成气的方法，包括 : 在用氧(12)或富氧空气(28)燃烧的ATR或POX反应器(11)中将烃源转化为粗合成气(14)； 对原料合成气(14)进行水煤气变换处理，包括在200-300°C的温度下进行中温变换(15)，得到变换后的合成气(16)； 所述变换后的合成气(16)的净化包括至少一个变压吸附(17)步骤，以从合成气中除去残余的碳氧化物和甲烷，获得纯化的合成气(18)，以及任选地，向所述纯化的合成气(18)中加入氮(19)，从而获得具有所需氢氮比的氨合成气。', p.abstract_en = 'A process for producing ammonia synthesis gas from a hydrocarbon source,  comprising :  conversion of the hydrocarbon source into a raw synthesis gas (14) in ATR or POX reactor (11) which is fired with oxygen (12) or oxygen-enriched air (28);  a water-gas shift treatment of the raw synthesis gas (14),  which consist of a medium-temperature shift (15) at a temperature of 200-300° C.,  thus obtaining a shifted synthesis gas (16);  purification of said shifted synthesis gas (16) including at least a step of pressure-swing adsorption (17) to remove residual carbon oxides and methane from the synthesis gas,  obtaining a purified synthesis gas (18),  and optionally,  addition of nitrogen (19) to said purified synthesis gas (18),  thus obtaining ammonia synthesis gas with a desired hydrogen to nitrogen ratio.', p.application_date = '2013-01-15 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9260303B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/48', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US13661815'}) SET p.application_no = 'US13661815', p.title_cn = '双流化床气化炉燃烧室的补充燃料', p.title_en = 'Supplemental fuel to combustor of dual fluidized bed gasifier', p.abstract_cn = '一种通过将待气化的进料引入双流化床气化器中进行气化的方法，所述双流化床气化器包括与燃烧器流体连接的热解器，使得包含传热材料的循环流可在所述热解器之间连续循环， 其中所述热解器可操作以将至少一部分所述进料转化为包含氢气和一氧化碳的气化器产物气体，并且其中所述燃烧器可操作以通过与所述循环流和至少一种补充燃料一起引入的炭的燃烧来提高所述循环流的温度。 还提供了一种用于执行该方法的系统。', p.abstract_en = 'A method of gasification by introducing a feed material to be subjected to gasification into a dual fluidized bed gasifier comprising a pyrolyzer fluidly connected with a combustor such that a circulation stream comprising a heat transfer material can be continuously circulated between the pyrolyzer,  in which the temperature of the circulation stream is reduced,  and the combustor,  in which the temperature of the circulation stream is increased,  wherein the pyrolyzer is operable to convert at least a portion of the feed material into a gasifier product gas comprising hydrogen and carbon monoxide,  and wherein the combustor is operable to increase the temperature of the circulation stream via combustion of char introduced thereto with the circulation stream and at least one supplemental fuel. A system for carrying out the method is also provided.', p.application_date = '2012-10-26 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9261274B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/24', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 2, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'AT505262014'}) SET p.application_no = 'AT505262014', p.title_cn = '方法', p.title_en = 'Method', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种装置用于制造压缩氢，包括耐压反应器(1)与反应器腔室具有一含金属的接触物质(2)，所述反应器(1)包括至少一个给料管线(3)用于将流体输送到反应器室，至少一个放电线(4)，用于从反应器排出流体的室，所述至少一个排放管路上设有装置(5a，5b，5C，5d)用于控制或调节流量，优选具有阀，用于调节反应器内的压力室，所述输送单元设置在至少一个含进给管线用于将水介质引入反应器室中，并且其中至少一个排出管道(4)伸入到所述反应室或直接通到所反应器室，通过压缩氢气从反应器排出室，所述反应器室具有至少两个区域被彼此分离和连接在气体导通方式，的至少一个区域包括含金属的接触物质(2)和至少一个附加区域包括至少一个惰性材料(7，13)。', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention relates to a device for producing compressed hydrogen,  comprising a pressure-resistant reactor (1) with a reactor chamber having a metal-containing contact mass (2),  wherein the reactor (1) comprises at least one feed line (3) for feeding fluids into the reactor chamber and at least one discharge line (4) for discharging fluids from the reactor chamber,  wherein the at least one discharge line is provided with a device (5a,  5b,  5c,  5d) for controlling or regulating the flow rate,  preferably having a valve,  for adjusting the pressure within the reactor chamber,  wherein a conveyance means is provided on at least one feed line for introducing a water-containing medium into the reactor chamber and wherein at least one discharge line (4) protrudes into the reactor chamber or opens directly into the reactor chamber,  through which the compressed hydrogen is discharged from the reactor chamber,  wherein the reactor chamber exhibits at least two areas that are separate from each other and connected in a gas-conducting manner,  of which at least one area comprises the metal-containing contacting mass (2) and at least one additional area comprises at least one inert material (7,  13).', p.application_date = '2014-07-25 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'AT516101A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/10', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'ATE772594'}) SET p.application_no = 'ATE772594', p.title_cn = '操作氢气发生器的方法', p.title_en = 'Method of operating a hydrogen generator', p.abstract_cn = '氢发生器包括 : 重整器(102)，被配置为生成含氢气体的重整反应中使用原料；燃烧器(104)被配置为加热重整器；空气供给装置(106)，配置成供给燃烧空气的燃烧器；第第一热交换器(108)配置成从烟道排出的气体中回收热量从燃烧器；第第一热介质通道(110)通过第第一热介质流过，第一热介质接收从烟气中回收的热量第一热交换器；第第一泵(112)配置成使第一第一热介质通道中的热介质流动；蓄热体(140)被配置成存储由第一回收的热量的热介质；和控制器(114)配置成使第一泵上的冷却步骤中的操作步骤降温至少重整器供给空气从空气供应装置连接，以在燃烧器状态下，不进行燃烧的燃烧器停止期间处理', p.abstract_en = 'A hydrogen generator includes :  a reformer (102) configured to generate a hydrogen-containing gas by a reforming reaction using a raw material;  a combustor (104) configured to heat the reformer;  an air supplying device (106) configured to supply combustion air to the combustor;  a first heat exchanger (108) configured to recover heat from a flue gas discharged from the combustor;  a first heat medium passage (110) through which a first heat medium flows,  the first heat medium receiving the heat recovered from the flue gas in the first heat exchanger;  a first pump (112) configured to cause the first heat medium in the first heat medium passage to flow;  a heat accumulator (140) configured to store the heat recovered by the first heat medium;  and a controller (114) configured to cause the first pump to operate in a cooling step that is a step of cooling down at least the reformer by supplying the air from the air supplying device to the combustor in a state where the combustor is not carrying out combustion during a stop processing', p.application_date = '2009-11-20 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'ATE772594T1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'ATE772595'}) SET p.application_no = 'ATE772595', p.title_cn = '初级重整器具有可变的烟气流量', p.title_en = 'PRIMARY REFORMER HAVING VARIABLE SMOKE GAS FLOW', p.abstract_cn = '一种方法，公开了一种用于催化初级重整烃与蒸汽在升高的压力下通过分体管反应器和燃烧室。在分体式管系统，可以使用催化剂材料，待重整的烃水蒸汽转换合成气。分体式管系统由多个点火加热设施之间的分体式管包括多个串联布置燃烧器，燃烧器产生主要的向下指向的火焰。相关烧制设施提供与燃料和空气，与空气在被从相关送料器。烟道气体从而演化穿过所述烧制室从上至下进入下部区域中烧室中的水平设置的陶瓷烟气隧道彼此平行延伸并垂直于竖直分流管和被分配给一个烧制设施。烟气进入通过侧壁中的孔的烟气隧道。烟气在燃烧室的出口通入热回收装置。在每个烟气隧道的附加气体进入隧道的前侧，在烟气流动方向，所述含氧气体和非可燃气体，使得附加气体经过烟气隧道在整个长度的燃烧室。体积的附加气体通入到烟气隧道的调节。', p.abstract_en = 'A method is disclosed for catalytic primary reformation of hydrocarbons with steam at elevated pressure by means of a split tube reactor and a firing chamber. In the split tube system which can use a catalyst material,  hydrocarbons to be reformed are converted by water steam to synthesis gas. The split tube system is heated by a plurality of firing facilities between the split tubes which include a plurality of burners arranged in series,  the burners generating mainly downwardly directed flames. The relevant firing facilities are supplied with fuel and air,  with the air being withdrawn from the relevant feeders. The flue gas thus evolving passes through the firing chamber from top to bottom and enters in the lower area of the firing chamber into horizontally arranged ceramic flue gas tunnels extending in parallel to each other and perpendicular to the vertical split tubes and being allocated to one firing facility each. The flue gas enters through apertures in the lateral walls of the flue gas tunnels. The flue gas at the exit of the firing chamber is passed into heat recovery devices. In each flue gas tunnel an additional gas is fed into the tunnel\'s front side,  in flue gas flow direction,  wherein the gas containing oxygen and a non-combustible gas,  so that the additional gas passes the flue gas tunnels over the entire length of the firing chamber. The volume of the additional gas passed into the flue gas tunnels is regulated.', p.application_date = '2010-06-24 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'ATE772595T1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'IN10503DELNP2015'}) SET p.application_no = 'IN10503DELNP2015', p.title_cn = '烟尘控制在氧化反应', p.title_en = 'SOOT CONTROL IN OXIDATION REACTIONS', p.abstract_cn = '部分氧化含碳进料中的积灰通过控制氧化剂流的动量相对以含碳进料流的动量。', p.abstract_en = 'Soot formation in the partial oxidation of carbonaceous feed is controlled by controlling the momentum of the oxidant stream relative to the momentum of the carbonaceous feed stream.', p.application_date = '2015-11-16 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'IN10503DELNP2015A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/36', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'IN201621000805'}) SET p.application_no = 'IN201621000805', p.title_cn = '用发生炉煤气的装置和方法直接再热部分水蒸汽重整反应和焦油裂解', p.title_en = 'APPARATUS AND METHOD FOR PRODUCER GAS DIRECT REHEATING WITH PARTIALLY STEAM REFORMING AND TAR CRACKING', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及直接加热的方法和装置通过部分水蒸汽重整反应和焦油裂解气体的装置。本发明还涉及利用生产过程中产生的热气体的装置主要包含氢和一氧化碳和甲烷的燃料如煤/生物质从固体/本发明涉及一种上吸式气化工艺的城市固体垃圾等发生炉中产生的气体进入主反应器(9)中的焦油重整系统(13)，其中组合热，水蒸汽与重质烃的部分裂解和改造并将其转换成一氧化碳和氢。所述的发生炉煤气生产中产生的热量用于进一步加热气体的装置和气态形式存在(焦油)中局部开裂的发生。热清洗发生炉煤气向应用直接供电。fig.1', p.abstract_en = 'This invention relates to the method and apparatus of direct reheating of producer gas by partially steam reforming and tar cracking. The present invention also relates to utilization of heat generated during production of Producer gas that mainly contains hydrogen and carbon monoxide and methane from the Solid fuels like coal/Biomass/ MSW etc. Present invention relates to up draft gasification technology in which producer gas generated in the main reactor (9) enters in the tar reforming system (13) where combination of heat,  water vapor and heavy hydrocarbon partially cracked and reform and convert into carbon monoxide and hydrogen. The heat generated during the production of Producer gas is used for further heating of producer gas and partial cracking of tar present (Gaseous form) in the producer gas. Hot and cleaned Producer gas is directly supplied towards the application. Fig.1', p.application_date = '2016-01-08 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'IN201621000805A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/32', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'IN9344DELNP2015'}) SET p.application_no = 'IN9344DELNP2015', p.title_cn = '重整烃类的设备和方法', p.title_en = 'APPARATUSES AND METHODS FOR REFORMING OF HYDROCARBONS', p.abstract_cn = '实施例本文提供了用于烃重整的设备和方法。在一个实施例中，一种方法包括将燃气燃烧形成热烟气和热重整区原料，其含有(CS，CN)以形成经加热的烃的重整区进料流。所述加热进料流的部分重整的重整区，以形成部分而流出物。先进的部分重整流出物通过工艺热回收的线圈配置为从热回收热量烟气加热形成部分转化流出物。所述局部加热重整流出物在重整条件下与重整催化剂接触，在有效形成重整反应区，流出物。重整反应区的流出物包括H2，包括芳烃烃，和烃。', p.abstract_en = 'Embodiments of apparatuses and methods for reforming of hydrocarbons are provided herein. In one example,  a method comprises burning fuel gas to form a hot flue gas and heat a reforming-zone feedstock that contains (Cs -Cn) hydrocarbons to form a heated reforming-zone feed stream. The heated reforming-zone feed stream is partially reformed to form a partially re formed effluent. The partially reformed effluent is advanced through a process heat recovery coil arrangement that is recovering heat from the hot flue gas to form a heated partially reformed effluent. The heated partially reformed effluent is contacted with reforming catalyst at reforming conditions effective to form a reforming reaction-zone effluent. The reforming reaction-zone effluent comprises H2,  C hydrocarbons including aromatics,  and C hydrocarbons.', p.application_date = '2015-10-08 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'IN9344DELNP2015A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/26', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'AU2011294911'}) SET p.application_no = 'AU2011294911', p.title_cn = '生产氨的通过整合强化方法', p.title_en = 'Ammonia production by integrated intensified processes', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种氨生产方法。该方法使用气化的生物质废物等产生合成气，使用集成系统，包括使用富氮空气和多孔涂布催化剂，等离子体反应器中产生氨。最后回收的氨使用磺化PolyHIPE聚合物可用于中和后作为肥料。', p.abstract_en = 'An ammonia production process is disclosed. The process uses gasification of biomass waste and the like to produce syngas which,  using an integrated system including using nitrogen enriched air and a porous coated catalyst,  produces ammonia in a plasma reactor. The ammonia is finally recovered using sulphonated PolyHIPE Polymer which can be used as a fertilizer after neutralisation.', p.application_date = '2011-08-30 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'AU2011294911B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'DE102014011868'}) SET p.application_no = 'DE102014011868', p.title_cn = '用于生产氢的装置和方法通过直接的热离解的水蒸气通过激光', p.title_en = 'Arrangement and method for the production of hydrogen by direct thermal dissociation of water vapor by means of a laser', p.abstract_cn = '氢气发生器，其特征在于 : 所述反应室(23)的氢气发生器(1)与冷却套(8)的供应线(16)通过混合器(22)与定量可变地供给水射流器(15)与上联的光学器件(3)连续波激光器工作在脉冲或注入并贯穿其中(2)具有，其中激光点火点(14)的激光(2)在自由部分的水射流(15)位于交互式在其功率和工作平面可变化，反应空间(23)的电容器(17)，疏水性氢可渗透壁(6)，H2传感器(7)，O2传感器(9)，传感器印刷温度(24)，填充水平传感器(25)，H2-衍生物(4)与泵(5)，O2-衍生物(10)与泵(11)和槽(13)与泵(18)和流体连接(19)与冷凝器(20)和混合器(22)与进水口(21)。', p.abstract_en = 'Hydrogen generator,  characterized in that the reaction chamber (23) of the hydrogen generator (1) with the cooling jacket (8) the supply line (16) with the via the mixer (22) quantitatively variably supplied water jet (15) with the on the linking optics (3) continuous wave laser operated in the pulsed or injected and extending therein (2) has,  wherein the laser ignition point (14) of the laser (2) in a free portion of the water jet (15) lies and interactively in its power and working plane can be varied and that the reaction space (23) the capacitor (17),  the hydrophobic hydrogen permeable wall (6),  the H2-sensor (7),  the O2-sensor (9),  the sensor printing temperature (24),  the filling level sensor (25),  the H2-derivative (4) to the pump (5),  the O2-derivative (10) with the pump (11) and the trough (13) with the pump (18) and the flow connection (19) with the condenser (20) and the mixer (22) with the water inlet (21) has.', p.application_date = '2014-08-11 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'DE102014011868A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14781056'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14781056', p.title_cn = '一种生产高纯氢气的方法', p.title_en = 'Method for Producing High-Purity Hydrogen Gas', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种生产氢气的方法，该方法包括以下步骤 : 使钢渣与H2O在150°C至500°C的温度范围内反应，冷却步骤(a)的反应产物以将氢气从水蒸汽中分离并收集氢气。', p.abstract_en = 'The disclosure relates to a method for producing hydrogen gas comprising the steps of reacting steel slags with H2O at a temperature ranging from 150° C. to 500° C.,  cooling down the reaction product of step (a) to separate hydrogen gas from water steam and collecting hydrogen gas.', p.application_date = '2014-03-31 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US20160039669A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/06', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14780374'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14780374', p.title_cn = '生产合成气方法和设备', p.title_en = 'PROCESS AND PLANT FOR PRODUCING SYNTHESIS GAS', p.abstract_cn = '用于从含烃的起始气体生产含氢和一氧化碳的合成气， 将起始气体分成第一部分物流和第二部分物流，其中将第一部分物流供给蒸汽重整器，在该蒸汽重整器中，将其与蒸汽一起催化转化以获得含氢和碳氧化物的气体物流，其中在蒸汽重整之后，第一部分物流再次与第二部分物流合并，并且其中将合并的气体物流供给自热重整器，在该自热重整器中，合并的气体物流与含氧气体一起自热重整为合成气。 第一部分物流被直接引导到蒸汽重整器中，第二部分物流在通过自热重整器之前被引导通过预重整器。', p.abstract_en = 'For producing a synthesis gas containing hydrogen and carbon monoxide from a starting gas containing hydrocarbons,  the starting gas is split up into a first partial stream and a second partial stream,  wherein the first partial stream is supplied to a steam reformer in which it is catalytically converted together with steam to obtain a gas stream containing hydrogen and carbon oxides,  wherein after the steam reformation the first partial stream is again combined with the second partial stream,  and wherein the combined gas stream is supplied to an autothermal reformer in which the combined gas stream together with an oxygen-containing gas is autothermally reformed to a synthesis gas. The first partial stream is guided directly into the steam reformer and the second partial stream is guided through a pre-reformer before passing through the autothermal reformer.', p.application_date = '2014-02-11 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US20160039670A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WOJP15003912'}) SET p.application_no = 'WOJP15003912', p.title_cn = '氢生成设备，操作方法和燃料电池系统', p.title_en = 'HYDROGEN GENERATION APPARATUS,  OPERATION METHOD THEREOF,  AND FUEL CELL SYSTEM', p.abstract_cn = '该氢生成设备包括一个原料供应器，加氢脱硫剂，原料供给通道，重整器，一种含氢气体流道，循环气体流道，顶针，通断阀，和异常的检测装置。所述异常检测器具有压力检测器和控制单元。控制单元之间的至少一个控制任务执行的控制任务异常判断，氢生成设备的上报状态或异常，或停止操作，，当原料供应器进行的供气操作和由压力检测器所检测的压力值与开关量上开口低于第一阈值或当原料供应器执行供应操作和由压力检测器检测出的压力值在断电后值已经被从打开关闭状态不低于第二阈值设定为低于第一阈值。', p.abstract_en = 'This hydrogen generation apparatus includes a feedstock supplier,  a hydro-desulfurizer,  a feedstock supply channel,  a reformer,  a hydrogen-containing gas flow channel,  a recycle gas flow channel,  an ejector,  an on-off valve,  and an abnormality detector. The abnormality detector has a pressure detector and a control unit. The control unit performs at least one control task among the control tasks of determining an abnormality,  reporting the state of the hydrogen generation apparatus or the abnormality thereof,  or stopping the operation,  when the feedstock supplier is performing a supplying operation and the pressure value detected by the pressure detector with the on-off value open is lower than a first threshold or when the feedstock supplier is performing a supplying operation and the pressure value detected by the pressure detector after the on-off value has been closed from an open state does not fall below a second threshold that is set lower than the first threshold.', p.application_date = '2015-08-04 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016021182A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201180065228.3'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201180065228.3', p.title_cn = '使用低温分离生产氨合成气和纯甲烷的方法和装置', p.title_en = 'Using low-temperature producing ammonia synthesis gas and pure methane method and device', p.abstract_cn = '在一种用于通过低温分离原料气生产氨合成气和纯甲烷的方法中，所述原料气含有至少75%的氢，以及甲烷和氮，原料气在热交换器(7)中被冷却并部分冷凝，部分冷凝的原料被送至相分离器(31)，来自相分离器的气体被送至氮洗涤塔(45)，液氮被送至所述氮洗涤塔的顶部并且氨合成气(57，67，69)从所述氮洗涤塔的顶部被提取出，来自所述相分离器的液体经过膨胀并被送至分离塔(19)，富含氮的气体流(43)从所述分离塔的顶部被提取出，氮含量低而富含甲烷的液体流(39)从所述分离塔的底部被提取出，该氮含量低而富含甲烷的液体流蒸发以产生纯甲烷产品(71，73)。', p.abstract_en = 'A process for the production of ammonia synthesis gas and pure methane by cryogenic separation of a feed gas containing at least 75% hydrogen as well as methane and nitrogen,  the feed gas is cooled in a heat exchanger and partially condensed,  the partially condensed feed is sent to a phase separator,  the gas from the phase separator is sent to a nitrogen wash column,  liquid nitrogen is sent to the top of the nitrogen wash column and ammonia synthesis gas is removed from the top of the nitrogen wash column,  the liquid from the phase separator is expanded and sent to a separation column,  a nitrogen enriched gas stream is removed from the top of the column and a nitrogen depleted liquid stream rich in methane is removed from the bottom of the column and the nitrogen depleted liquid stream rich in methane is vaporized to form a pure methane product.', p.application_date = '2011-01-17 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN103328375B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/50', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201180067188.6'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201180067188.6', p.title_cn = '蒸汽甲烷转化工艺方法', p.title_en = 'Steam methane conversion method', p.abstract_cn = '本发明提供蒸汽甲烷转化工艺方法和系统，其利用具有高压蒸汽回路和低压蒸汽回路两者的整合的蒸汽系统。根据本发明，充分将离开脱气器的全部的处理过的锅炉给水流加压并送至在升高的压力下的锅炉给水加热器。将所得的高压的加热的锅炉给水分流，其中一部分用作制备低压蒸汽的进料，且将其余部分送至高压蒸汽回路。', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention provides a steam methane reforming process and system utilizing an integrated steam system having both high pressure and low pressure steam circuits. According to this invention,  substantially the entire stream of treated boiler feed water leaving the deaerator is pressurized and sent to the boiler feed water heater at elevated pressures. The resulting high pressure heated boiler feed water is split with a portion used as the feed to make low pressure steam and the balance is sent to the high pressure steam circuit.', p.application_date = '2011-11-10 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN103339058B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201310040900.4'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201310040900.4', p.title_cn = '临氢设备耐火炉衬结构及其制备方法', p.title_en = 'Hydro-refining equipment refractory lining structure and method for preparing the same', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种临氢设备耐火炉衬结构及其制备方法，由内向外依次为耐火层、隔热层以及金属壳体，其所述隔热层内的隔热层锚固钉固接金属壳体；耐火层内的耐火层锚固钉固接隔热层，且该耐火层锚固钉延伸穿过隔热层并与金属壳体固接。本发明可以使设备外壁温度均匀、减少耐火浇注料施工难度、保证炉衬均匀一致、整体性强、使用寿命长、不会发生突然性破坏、利于设备安全运行。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a hydroequipment refractory furnace lining structure and a preparation method thereof. The refractory furnace lining structure consists of,  from the inside out in order,  a refractory layer,  a thermal insulating layer and a metal shell,  wherein the thermal insulating layer anchoring nails in the thermal insulating layer are in fixed connection with the metal shell,  the refractory layer anchoring nails in the refractory layer are in fixed connection with the thermal insulating layer,  and the refractory layer anchoring nails extend to penetrate through the thermal insulating layer and are in fixed connection with the metal shell. The hydroequipment refractory furnace lining structure provided by the invention can make the equipment outer wall temperature uniform,  reduce the construction difficulty of refractory castables,  ensures uniform furnace lining,  strong integrity and long service life. Without sudden destruction,  the hydroequipment refractory furnace lining structure is conducive to safe operation of the equipment.', p.application_date = '2013-02-01 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN103964377B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201510744889.9'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201510744889.9', p.title_cn = '一种高效节能氨分解设备', p.title_en = 'Efficient energy-saving ammonia decomposition equipment', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种高效节能氨分解设备，包括设备主体，所述设备主体上设有进口阀门、汽化器、换热器、炉膛和出口阀门，所述炉膛内设有柱状的炉胆，炉胆内装镍触媒，所述炉胆的顶端和底端都为椭圆封头，炉胆顶端或底端还设有进出口管，所述进出口管的管径小于炉胆的外径，所述炉胆外侧还设有螺旋状的电热丝，所述电热丝以所述炉胆的轴心为中心均匀环绕于所述炉胆外侧并与所述炉胆的外壁保持一定的间隙，本发明可高效节能地分解液氨。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention discloses efficient energy-saving ammonia decomposition equipment which comprises an equipment main body,  wherein an inlet valve,  a vaporizer,  a heat exchanger,  a hearth and an outlet valve are arranged on the equipment main body;  a columnar furnace pipe is arranged in the hearth and is filled with a nickel catalyst;  the top end and the bottom end of the furnace pipe take the shape of ellipse heads;  an inlet-outlet pipe is further arranged at the top end or the bottom end of the furnace pipe;  the pipe diameter of the inlet-outlet pipe is smaller than the external diameter of the furnace pipe;  a helical heating wire is further arranged on the outer side of the furnace pipe,  uniformly surrounds the outer side of the furnace pipe by centering on the axis of the furnace pipe,  and keeps a certain clearance with the outer wall of the furnace pipe. The efficient energy-saving ammonia decomposition equipment can decompose liquid ammonia in an efficient and energy-saving manner.', p.application_date = '2015-11-06 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105314594A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201410331283.8'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201410331283.8', p.title_cn = 'CO变换反应炉', p.title_en = 'CO conversion reaction furnace', p.abstract_cn = '本发明属于CO耐硫变换技术领域，具体涉及一种CO变换反应炉。包括炉体，炉体内部设有催化剂床层，离炉体顶部距离占炉体高度的16％～22％处设置第一换热装置，第一换热装置由第一大换热盘管和第一小换热盘管组成，离炉体底部距离占炉体高度的20％～25％处设置第二换热装置，第二换热装置由第二大换热盘管和第二小换热盘管组成，第一大换热盘管和第二大换热盘管直径为炉体直径的75％～55％，第一小换热盘管和第二小换热盘管直径为床层直径的45％～55％。本发明有效的控制床层温度在320℃～380℃，避免甲烷化副反应，并兼顾到反应速度，有效设置一段变换就能变换到CO含量要求，适用于不同水气比、CO含量的工艺。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention belongs to the technical field of CO sulfur resistant conversion,  and specifically relates to a CO conversion reaction furnace. The furnace comprises a furnace body,  a catalyst bed is arranged in the furnace body;  a first heat exchange device is arranged on a position (A),  the distance between the top of the furnace and the position (A) accounts for 16 to 22% of the height of the furnace,  the first heat exchange device is composed of a first large heat exchange coil pipe and a first small heat exchange coil pipe;  a second heat exchange device is arranged on a position (B),  the distance between the bottom of the furnace and the position (B) accounts for 20 to 25% of the height of the furnace,  the second heat exchange device is composed of a second large heat exchange coil pipe and a second small heat exchange coil pipe;  the diameters of the first large heat exchange coil pipe and the second large heat exchange coil pipe is 75 to 55% of the diameter of the furnace body,  and the diameters of the first small heat exchange coil pipe and the second small heat exchange coil pipe is 45 to 55% of the diameter of the catalyst bed. The temperature of the bed is effectively controlled in a range of 320 to 380 DEG C so as to avoid the methanation by-reactions;  at the same time the reaction speed is taken into account,  a section of conversion can be effectively arranged to meet the requirements on CO content,  and the CO conversion reaction furnace is suitable for technology with different water/gas ratios and CO contents.', p.application_date = '2014-07-11 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105314595A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/16', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201510331497.X'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201510331497.X', p.title_cn = '一种甲烷二氧化碳自热重整制备合成气的方法及设备', p.title_en = 'Method and device for preparing synthesis gas through methane and carbon dioxide auto-thermal reforming', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开一种甲烷二氧化碳自热重整制备合成气的方法，其包括步骤：原料气经两次换热后，进入提升管重整反应器；在提升管重整反应器内经催化剂作用进行重整反应生成合成气；反应后的催化剂和合成气经旋风分离器进行气固分离，分离后的合成气经降温后输出；分离后的催化剂经返料器进入流化床再生器进行再生，再生后的催化剂再回到提升管重整反应器。本发明通过提升管重整反应器-流化床再生器构成的反应—再生系统，解决了甲烷二氧化碳重整制备合成气工艺过程中，催化剂易积炭导致活性下降的问题。同时，本发明通过往流化床再生器中补充燃料的方式，为催化剂加热，再通过催化剂维持重整反应所缺热量，解决了重整反应过程能量不足的问题。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention discloses a method and device for preparing synthesis gas through methane and carbon dioxide auto-thermal reforming. The method includes the steps that feed gas enters a lift pipe reforming reactor after being subjected to two times of heat exchange;  a reforming reaction is conducted in the lift pipe reforming reactor through the effect of a catalyst to generate the synthesis gas;  the catalyst and the synthesis gas obtained after the reaction are subjected to gas-solid separation through a cyclone separator,  and the separated-out synthesis gas is output after being cooled;  the separated-out catalyst enters a fluidized bed regenerator through a return feeder for regeneration,  and the regenerated catalyst returns to the lift pipe reforming reactor again. Through a reaction-regeneration system formed by the lift pipe reforming reactor and the fluidized bed regenerator,  the problem of activity decline caused by the fact that the catalyst is prone to carbon deposition in the technological process of preparing the synthesis gas through methane and carbon dioxide reforming is solved. Meanwhile,  the catalyst is heated in the mode that fuel is supplemented into the fluidized bed regenerator,  heat absent in the reforming reaction is maintained through the catalyst,  and the problem that energy is insufficient in the reforming reaction process is solved.', p.application_date = '2015-06-16 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105314596A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/34', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201520745898.5'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201520745898.5', p.title_cn = '合成氨低压膜回收装置一键停车系统', p.title_en = 'Synthetic ammonia low-pressure film recovery device push-to-parking system', p.abstract_cn = '本实用新型公开了一种合成氨低压膜回收装置一键停车系统，包括有DCS系统、电磁阀、洗氨塔液位调节阀、入膜温度调节阀、预处理放空调节阀、入膜压力调节阀和尾气压力调节阀，电磁阀的进口端连接仪表气源，电磁阀的出口端分别与洗氨塔液位调节阀、入膜温度调节阀、入膜压力调节阀和尾气压力调节阀的空气进口端相连接，DCS系统分别与电磁阀和预处理放空调节阀电连接。本实用新型借助DCS系统平台，通过一键停车控制程序，实现了操作人员按下停车键后，自动将低压膜氢回收装置安全停车的功能。', p.abstract_en = 'The utility model discloses a synthetic ammonia low-pressure film recovery device push-to-parking system,  comprises a DCS system,  the solenoid valve,  the column to wash ammonia liquid level regulating valve,  a temperature regulating valve enters the membrane,  pre-emptying regulating valve,  into the film pressure regulating valve and the exhaust gas pressure regulating valve,  solenoid valve is connected to the inlet end of instrument gas source,  solenoid valve are respectively connected with the outlet end of the liquid level regulating valve washes the ammonia tower,  enters the membrane temperature regulating valve,  into the film pressure regulating valve and the exhaust gas pressure regulating valve is connected with the air inlet end,  DCS system is respectively connected with the solenoid valve and is electrically connected to pre-vent regulating valve. The utility model through the DCS system platform,  parking control program through a key,  the operator presses a after parking key,  automatic in the low-pressure hydrogen recovery device security parking function.', p.application_date = '2015-09-23 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN205023843U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/56', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'EP14724738'}) SET p.application_no = 'EP14724738', p.title_cn = '存储结构', p.title_en = 'STORAGE STRUCTURE', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种存储结构包括存储介质和惰性材料，其集成到存储介质或存在作为分离相在存储介质，所述的惰性材料至少部分地包含或包括复式惰性材料。复式惰性材料具有至少一个复式相之间的过渡范围内环境温度和最大工作固体电解质电池的温度。复式相变引起失真的惰性材料的晶格结构，从而使特定体积中的变化和作用在周围粮食的存储媒体。机械耦合触发的应力的由惰性材料的相变使相邻的晶粒存储介质破裂，使得新的反应性区变得可用存储介质中。根据本发明，一种固体电解质电池的再生是这样实现。', p.abstract_en = 'A storage medium and an inert material,  either integrated into the storage medium or existing as a separate phase in the storage medium,  form a storage structure. The inert material at least partially contains or is formed by a polymorphous inert material. The polymorphous inert material has at least one polymorphous phase transition in the range between ambient temperature and maximum operating temperature of the solid electrolyte battery. The polymorphous phase transition induces a distortion of the lattice structure of the inert material,  thus causing a change in the specific volume and acting on the surrounding grains of the storage medium. A mechanical coupling of the stresses triggered by the phase transition of the inert material causes the neighboring grains of the storage medium to break apart,  such that new reactive zones become available in the storage medium,  thereby regenerating the solid electrolyte battery.', p.application_date = '2014-05-16 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'EP2981502A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2013548177'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2013548177', p.title_cn = '具有该燃料产生装置2和二次电池型燃料电池系统', p.title_en = 'With the same fuel generating device 2 and a secondary battery type fuel cell system', p.abstract_cn = '本燃油发电机上设有细颗粒的燃料生成剂(1)，其生成燃料由氧化 反应与氧化气体和可再生的还原反应还原气体， 和多孔部件(3)。 细颗粒的燃料生成剂(1)分散配置在内部的多孔件(3)。', p.abstract_en = 'This fuel generator is equipped with fine particles of a fuel-generating agent (1) that generates fuel by an oxidation reaction with an oxidizing gas and can be regenerated by a reduction reaction with a reducing gas,  and a porous member (3). The fine particles of the fuel-generating agent (1) are dispersed and disposed in the interior of the porous member(3).', p.application_date = '2012-11-26 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP5858049B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/08', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'MX2014007345'}) SET p.application_no = 'MX2014007345', p.title_cn = '过程一氧化碳和二氧化碳的转化系统。', p.title_en = 'PROCESS AND SYSTEM FOR CONVERSION OF CARBON DIOXIDE TO CARBON MONOXIDE.', p.abstract_cn = '用于将二氧化碳(CO2)的方法和装置以一氧化碳CO，描述了使用烃类。在进一步的细节，描述了用于产生合成气的方法和装置描述了用于将合成气的方法和装置合成的官能化和/或非官能化烃，然后用CO2和烃。通过所述方法和装置，从工业工艺可以转换发射和二氧化碳的量释放到大气中的二氧化碳降低。', p.abstract_en = 'A process and a device for converting carbon dioxide CO2 to carbon monoxide CO,  using hydrocarbons are described. In further details,  processes and devices are described for generating synthesis gases and processes and devices are described for converting synthesis gases to synthetic functionalized and/or non-functionalized hydrocarbons,  using CO2 and hydrocarbons. By means of the processes and the devices,  carbon dioxide emitted from industrial process can be converted and the amount of carbon dioxide released into the atmosphere can be decreased.', p.application_date = '2012-12-20 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'MX337017B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/24', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'RU2015108355'}) SET p.application_no = 'RU2015108355', p.title_cn = '合成气的生产装置', p.title_en = 'DEVICE FOR PRODUCTION OF THE SYNTHESIS - GAS', p.abstract_cn = '1。装置生产的合成气从液态或气态烃，由蒸发器的液体燃料和反应器，容置体与双层金属冷却壁，内腔，喷嘴头进给原料和氧，位于上部的壳部分，水蒸汽的蒸汽发生器，其输出连接到外部冷却系统和内腔中的蒸汽输入，混合器燃料与加热水蒸汽，其输出连接到喷嘴头，其特征在于表面的内层双层金属冷却壁上侧的副由翅片螺旋形加强筋的矩形的轮廓。2。根据权利要求1，其特征在于 : 在双层金属壁的外表面装配的电抗器的补偿器温度变形，不同程度的加热中产生的内，外表面的双层壁在装置操作期间。', p.abstract_en = '1. device for production of synthesis - gas from liquid or gaseous hydrocarbons,  consisting of evaporator liquid fuel and reactor,  containing body with double-layer metal cooled walls,  inner cavity,  nozzle head for feeding raw material and oxygen,  located in upper part of case,  water vapour steam generator,  the output of which is connected to external cooling systems and input of steam in inner cavity of,  mixer fuel with reheated water vapor,  output of which is connected to nozzle head,  characterized in that surface of inner layer of double-layer metal cooled wall on the side of the pair is made of finned helical ribs rectangular profile. 2. Device according to Claim 1,  characterized in that on outer surface of double-layer metal walls of the reactor are installed compensators temperature deformations,  arising in different degree of heating inner and outer surfaces of double-layer wall during device operation.', p.application_date = '2015-03-11 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'RU159316U1', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/32', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'RU2014129860'}) SET p.application_no = 'RU2014129860', p.title_cn = '天然气重整装置和方法', p.title_en = 'DEVICE AND METHOD FOR REFORMING NATURAL GAS', p.abstract_cn = '装置包括催化剂室(6，6a)含有气体和催化剂颗粒，其分离从氧气室(4a)含氧气体透气的壁(11)。独立权利要求还包括用于催化转化气态烃类转化为合成气使用氧，包括调整该气体填充室之间的压力差催化剂和氧气室，使得气体交换发生。', p.abstract_en = 'Apparatus comprises a catalyst chamber (6,  6a) containing the gas and catalyst particles,  which is separated from an oxygen chamber (4a) containing oxygen by a gas-permeable wall (11). An independent claim is also included for catalytically converting gaseous hydrocarbons into synthesis gas using oxygen,  comprising adjusting the pressure difference between the gas-filled chamber catalyst and the oxygen chamber,  such that gas exchange takes place.', p.application_date = '2012-12-18 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'RU2014129860A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CA2690836'}) SET p.application_no = 'CA2690836', p.title_cn = '转化二氧化碳至甲醇利用的双转化甲烷或天然气', p.title_en = 'CONVERSION OF CARBON DIOXIDE TO METHANOL USING BI-REFORMING OF METHANE OR NATURAL GAS', p.abstract_cn = '本发明提供了一种用于\\结合形成甲醇的方法甲烷的混合物， 水和二氧化碳的反应条件下足以形成氢和一氧化碳的混合物。 氢和碳氧化硅-IDE的条件下反应足以形成甲醇。 氢与一氧化碳的摩尔比至少两个摩尔氢气对一摩尔的碳 一氧化碳和整体甲烷的摩尔比，水和二氧化碳为大约3 : 2 : 1。 甲烷，二氧化碳和水的双重整催化剂上。 该催化剂包括单金属， 金属氧化物， 混合催化剂的金属和金属氧化物或混合至少两种金属氧化物的催化剂。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention provides for \\ a method of forming methanol by combining a mixture of methane,  water and carbon dioxide under reaction conditions sufficient to form a mixture of hydrogen and carbon monoxide. Hydrogen and carbon monox-ide are reacted under conditions sufficient to form methanol. The molar ratio of hydrogen to carbon monoxide is at least two moles of hydrogen to one mole of carbon monoxide and the overall molar ratio between methane,  water and carbon dioxide is about 3 : 2 : 1. Methane,  carbon dioxide and water are bi-reformed over a catalyst. The catalyst includes a single metal,  a metal oxide,  a mixed catalyst of a metal and a metal oxide or a mixed catalyst of at least two metal oxides.', p.application_date = '2008-06-19 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CA2690836C', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CA2833696'}) SET p.application_no = 'CA2833696', p.title_cn = '氢与高输出蒸汽的生产工艺', p.title_en = 'HYDROGEN PRODUCTION PROCESS WITH HIGH EXPORT STEAM', p.abstract_cn = '催化蒸汽-烃重整制造氢的方法含产品和输出蒸汽，其中第一流的化妆利用烟气加热水从重整器和第二流，使补充水加热被引入之前来自该重整装置的重整产物到除氧器中。', p.abstract_en = 'A catalytic steam-hydrocarbon reforming process for producing a hydrogen- containing product and export steam where a first stream of make-up water is heated by flue gases from the reformer and a second stream of make-up water is heated by reformate from the reformer prior to being introduced into a deaerator.', p.application_date = '2013-11-18 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CA2833696C', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'ES05106614'}) SET p.application_no = 'ES05106614', p.title_cn = '反应气体-固相', p.title_en = 'Reaction gas-solid phase', p.abstract_cn = '准连续执行化学反应，由至少两个顺序的可逆步骤包括并行操作两个辐射加热的反应室和循环调节交流反应室中的反应条件。独立权利要求包括用于执行的准连续光反应器从两个顺序可逆化学反应的执行步骤。', p.abstract_en = 'The quasi-continuous execution of a chemical reaction,  consisting of at least two sequential reversible steps comprises parallely operating two radiation heated reaction chambers and cyclically adjusting alternating reaction conditions in the reaction chambers. INDEPENDENT CLAIM is included for photoreactor for the execution of quasi-continuous execution of chemical reaction from two sequential reversible steps.', p.application_date = '2005-07-19 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'ES2558865T3', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/06', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2012513403'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2012513403', p.title_cn = '氢气提纯装置和一种使用其的燃料电池系统', p.title_en = 'The hydrogen purification device and a fuel cell system using the same', p.abstract_cn = '氢气净化器(100)包括 : 一种变换催化剂(5a)减少，通过变换反应，所含的一氧化碳在含氢气体；和甲烷化催化剂(6a)，可以减少，通过甲烷化反应，所含的一氧化碳在含氢气体是通过变换转化催化剂(5a)。变换转化催化剂(5a)和甲烷化催化剂(6a)通过第一相互换热隔板壁(8)，和含氢气体的流动方向通过变换转化催化剂(5a)相反一种含氢气体的流动方向穿过所述甲烷化催化剂(6a)。', p.abstract_en = 'A hydrogen purifier (100) includes :  a shift conversion catalyst (5a) which reduces,  through a shift reaction,  carbon monoxide contained in a hydrogen-containing gas;  and a methanation catalyst (6a) which reduces,  through a methanation reaction,  carbon monoxide contained in the hydrogen-containing gas that has passed through the shift conversion catalyst (5a). The shift conversion catalyst (5a) and the methanation catalyst (6a) are heat exchangeable with each other via a first partition wall (8),  and a flow direction of the hydrogen-containing gas that passes through the shift conversion catalyst (5a) is opposite to a flow direction of the hydrogen-containing gas that passes through the methanation catalyst (6a).', p.application_date = '2011-08-24 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP5853137B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2012010481'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2012010481', p.title_cn = '碱颗粒夹带在含氢气体处理装置和方法', p.title_en = 'Alkali particles entrained in a hydrogen containing gas processing device and method', p.abstract_cn = '要解决的问题 : 从所述的碱衍生的颗粒氢发生器与一种碱性摩尔。重量。碱氢气体中夹带的颗粒被除去，从所述的碱性摩尔。重量。以有效地产生氢气净化。溶液 : 设置在所述密封壳体2100与入口2320和出口2420的含氢气体和一种含氢-气体，和气体-液体分离膜2600是该外壳内延伸的分隔而形成气体通道从该入口口到出口的端口所述含氢气体含氢气体在所述的横向方向，用于该水和蒸汽雾化机构2500以提供用于喷射蒸汽以一种气体流动路径从上游侧到气体-液体分离膜，一种含氢气体是用碱颗粒夹带。选自拉拔 : 图。2。', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To refine generated hydrogen by removing efficiently alkaline particles and alkaline molecules from hydrogen gas accompanied by the alkaline particles and alkaline molecules led out from a hydrogen generation apparatus.SOLUTION :  An alkaline particle-accompanied hydrogen-containing gas is passed through a treatment apparatus having,  in the closed casing 2100 having the inlet port 2320 of the hydrogen-containing gas and the outlet port 2420 of the hydrogen-containing gas :  gas-liquid separation membranes 2600 zoning in the traverse direction a gas circulation path formed in a casing interior from an inlet port of the hydrogen-containing gas to an outlet port of the hydrogen-containing gas;  and water or steam spray mechanisms 2500 to spray water or steam to the gas-liquid separation membranes from upstream sides of the gas circulation path.', p.application_date = '2012-01-20 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP5854424B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/56', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2012034581'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2012034581', p.title_cn = '该储氢材料', p.title_en = 'The hydrogen storage material', p.abstract_cn = '所要解决的问题 : 本发明提供一种负载金属的碳材料具有高的储氢容量，能可逆存储氢和释放氢的解决手段如下 : 一种负载金属的碳材料由碳材料中引入金属络合物引入一个具有孔。在负载金属的碳材料，通过允许形成的磷配位体的金属配合物或协调氮配体铜(Cu)或使用元素周期表第8-10族的金属M为配位中心。金属配合物为配体的金属络合物选自一组包括三苯基膦；三苯胺，吡啶，联吡啶和邻菲罗啉可以有取代基，或金属络合物，其中至少允许两个磷原子或氮原子坐标的金属M。', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To provide a metal-carrying carbon material having high hydrogen storage capacity,  capable of storing and releasing hydrogen reversibly.SOLUTION :  A metal-carrying carbon material is formed by introducing a metal complex into a carbon material having pores. In the metal-carrying carbon material,  the metal complex is formed by allowing a phosphorus ligand or a nitrogen ligand to coordinate to copper (Cu) or a metal M of groups 8-10 used as a coordination center. The metal complex is a metal complex having a ligand selected from a group comprising triphenylphosphine,  triphenylamine,  pyridine,  bipyridine and phenanthroline which may have a substituent,  or a metal complex in which at least two phosphorus atoms or nitrogen atoms are allowed to coordinate to the metal M.', p.application_date = '2012-02-20 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP5854427B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2013519123'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2013519123', p.title_cn = '电极包括塑料变形操作，所述储氢材料的制造方法', p.title_en = 'Electrode including a plastic deformation operation,  method of manufacturing the hydrogen storage material', p.abstract_cn = '制备的储氢材料的方法，包括极塑料变形操作选自冷轧，快锻，挤压弯上进行金属材料选自金属和合金含有所述金属，或在含金属的化合物材料选自金属和含所述金属的合金其中所述金属的氢化物或所述合金的氢化物已经被添加，当极端塑料变形金属材料上进行操作，接着是通过加入的操作，以金属材料，所述金属的氢化物或所述合金的氢化物，以及通过分散操作。', p.abstract_en = 'A material for storing hydrogen is prepared by a method including an extreme plastic deformation operation selected from cold-rolling,  quick-forging and extrusion-bending performed on a metallic material selected from among a metal and an alloy containing said metal,  or on a compound containing a metal material selected from among a metal and an alloy containing said metal and to which a hydride of said metal or a hydride of said alloy has been added. When the extreme plastic deformation operation is carried out on the metallic material,  it is followed by an operation of adding,  to the metal material,  a hydride of said metal or a hydride of said alloy,  as well as by a dispersing operation.', p.application_date = '2011-07-11 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP5855649B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14551664'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14551664', p.title_cn = '气化装置合成气的处理', p.title_en = 'Treatment of synthesis gases from a gasification facility', p.abstract_cn = '一种从各种固体燃料或液体燃料气化工艺的粗煤气生产合成气的技术。 为了限制随后的强放热CO变换反应中的温度以调节H2/CO比，已除去灰尘的粗煤气流过串联布置的两个变换反应器。 第一反应器具有特定的反应动力学受限的催化剂，第二反应器具有常规的酸性气体催化剂。 在第一反应器中使用的特定催化剂将放热变换反应限制到这样的程度，使得第一和第二反应器中的反应温度保持得如此低，以避免即使不引入外部蒸汽也对催化剂造成热损伤，并且获得所需的气体组成。', p.abstract_en = 'A technology for producing synthesis gas from crude gas from various gasification processes for solid or liquid fuels. To limit the temperatures in a subsequent strongly exothermic CO shift reaction to adjust the H2/CO ratio,  the crude gas which has been freed of dust flows through two shift reactors arranged in series. The first reactor has a specific reaction-kinetically limited catalyst and the second reactor has a conventional sour gas catalyst. The specific catalyst used in the first reactor limits the exothermic shift reaction to such an extent that the reaction temperatures in the first and second reactors remain so low to avoid thermal damage to the catalysts even without introduction of external steam,  and the desired gas composition is achieved.', p.application_date = '2014-11-24 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9254469B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 5, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14387644'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14387644', p.title_cn = '连续制氢法', p.title_en = 'Continuous production method of hydrogen', p.abstract_cn = '本发明提供了一种连续生产氢气的方法，该方法能够在不使用氨的情况下简单且连续地生产清洁能源氢气。 本发明的氢的连续生产方法包括氢生产步骤，包括将钙钛矿(Ca12Al14O33)和氢氧化钙[Ca(OH)2]引入水中并使它们与水反应，从而产生氢并还形成钾长石[Ca3Al2(OH)12]； 再生步骤，包括焙烧所形成的红土以再生镁橄榄石和氢氧化钙； 和氢氧化钙返回到制氢步骤的循环步骤。 制氢步骤中的水温优选为50-100°C，并且亚油酸钙与氢氧化钙的摩尔比为1/9。 此外，再生步骤中红土的焙烧温度优选为300-500°C。', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention provides a continuous production method of hydrogen which is able to produce hydrogen,  which is clean energy,  simply and continuously without using ammonia. The invention of the continuous production method of hydrogen includes a hydrogen production step comprising introducing mayenite (Ca12Al14O33) and calcium hydroxide [Ca(OH)2] into water and allowing them to react with water,  thereby generating hydrogen and also forming katoite [Ca3Al2(OH)12];  a regeneration step comprising baking the formed katoite to regenerate mayenite and calcium hydroxide;  and a circulation step comprising returning the regenerated mayenite and calcium hydroxide into the hydrogen production step. It is preferable that a temperature of water in the hydrogen production step is from 50 to 100° C.,  and a molar ratio of mayenite to calcium hydroxide is 1/9. In addition,  it is preferable that a baking temperature of katoite in the regeneration step is from 300 to 500° C.', p.application_date = '2013-01-11 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9255004B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/06', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 3, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14115831'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14115831', p.title_cn = '同时制氢的零排放硫磺回收工艺', p.title_en = 'Zero emissions sulphur recovery process with concurrent hydrogen production', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种从含H2S的气体物流中同时生产氢和硫的方法，该方法具有减少的、优选为零的排放。 该方法包括H2S催化氧化裂解形成H2和S2。 优选地，使用富氧空气，优选纯氧进行氧化。 该方法在包括双官能催化剂材料的反应室中进行，以便有利于H2S的部分氧化及其解离。', p.abstract_en = 'Disclosed is a process for the concurrent production of hydrogen and sulphur from a H2S-containing gas stream,  with reduced,  and preferably zero,  emissions. The method comprises the catalytic oxidative cracking of H2S so as to form H2 and S2. Preferably,  the oxidation is conducted using oxygen-enriched air,  preferably pure oxygen. The process is conducted in a reaction chamber comprising a bifunctional catalyst material,  so as to favor both the partial oxidation of H2S and the dissociation thereof.', p.application_date = '2012-05-07 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9255005B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2014149170'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2014149170', p.title_cn = '蒸发器和具有其的燃料电池装置', p.title_en = 'EVAPORATOR AND FUEL CELL DEVICE COMPRISING THE SAME', p.abstract_cn = '要解决的问题 : 所述蒸汽供应到重整器能够抑制蒸发器的波动，和提供一种燃料电池装置具有相同。方法 : 蒸发器301上，蒸发空间(第一空间(1)381，第二空间(2)382)中出来的蒸汽的流动方向的整个端上游侧，水存储在储水段形成WS。选择的绘图 : 图。4', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To provide an evaporator and a fuel cell device comprising the same that can suppress the variation in supply quantity of steam to a reformer. SOLUTION :  The evaporator 301 comprises a water storage portion WS for pooling water,  formed over the entire end part of the upstream side in the direction of the flowing steam within the evaporation space (a first space 381,  a second space 382). SELECTED DRAWING :  Figure 4 COPYRIGHT :  (C)2016, JPO&INPIT', p.application_date = '2014-07-22 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP2016023106A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2014151029'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2014151029', p.title_cn = '氢生成装置及燃料电池系统', p.title_en = 'Hydrogen generator and fuel cell system', p.abstract_cn = '要解决的问题 : 估计原燃料的组合物，氢气发生器以精确控制中产生的富氢的燃料气体的量。方法 : 该重整原料燃料和产生燃料气体发生器1，和燃料供给装置(2)，供水单元3和重整，与原燃料的至少一个通过燃烧燃料的燃烧气体的气体，一种燃烧装置(4)用于加热重整单元1和，燃烧器4供应燃烧空气和燃烧空气供给单元5，用于测量燃烧空气的流量和助燃空气流量测量装置6，燃烧废气流动通道8设置在燃烧废气的氧浓度测量，测量的氧浓度检测器7，原料燃料供应燃烧空气的控制，使恒定和燃烧时，测得的氧浓度测量装置7基于燃烧废气的氧浓度，一种重整装置1的目标值量的原料燃料供给，和，一种重整装置1供给量的目标值重整的至少一个控制单元9和控制参数设置，提供选择的绘图 : 图。1', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To correctly control a fuel gas amount rich in hydrogen generated in a hydrogen generator by estimating the composition of raw fuel. SOLUTION :  Provided is a hydrogen generator comprising :  a modifier 1 where raw fuel is modified to generate fuel gas;  a raw fuel feeder 2;  a modified water feeder 3;  a combustor 4 where at least either combustion gas in the raw fuel or the fuel gas is combusted to heat the modifier 1;  a combustion air feeder 5 where the combustion air is fed to the combustor 4;  a combustion air flow rate measuring instrument 6 where the flow rate of the combustion air is measured;  an oxygen concentration measuring instrument 7 provided in a combustor exhaust gas flow passage 8 and measuring the oxygen concentration of the combustion exhaust gas;  and a controller 9 where,  in the case the feed amounts of the raw fuel and the combustion air are controlled so as to be the fixed ones and combustion is caused,  based on the oxygen concentration of the combustion exhaust gas measured with the oxygen concentration measuring instrument 7,  at least one control parameter among the target value of the feed amount of the raw fuel to the modifier 1 and the target value of the feed amount of the modified water to the modifier 1 is set. SELECTED DRAWING :  Figure 1 COPYRIGHT :  (C)2016, JPO&INPIT', p.application_date = '2014-07-24 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP2016023127A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2013552047'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2013552047', p.title_cn = '氢生成装置及燃料电池系统', p.title_en = 'Hydrogen generator and fuel cell system', p.abstract_cn = '原料和使用蒸汽重整反应生成含氢气体和重整装置(130)，含氢气体中CO降低变换反应和变压器(140)，和变压器(140)的上游侧相邻设置的热交换器，和水蒸发的蒸发器(120)，变压器(下游侧的热交换器(140)和邻接设置，原料中的硫化合物除去脱硫反应hydrogenetion hydrogenetion脱硫剂(110)和，一种制氢装置(100)。', p.abstract_en = 'A hydrogen generator (100) includes a reformer (130) configured to cause a reforming reaction using a material and steam to generate a hydrogen-containing gas;  a shift converter (140) configured to reduce CO in the hydrogen-containing gas by a shift reaction;  an evaporator (120) provided adjacent to the shift converter (140) so as to perform heat exchange with an upstream side of the shift converter (140) and configured to evaporate water :  and a hydro-desulfurizer (110) provided adjacent to the shift converter (140) so as to perform heat exchange with a downstream side of the shift converter (140) and configured to remove a sulfur compound in the material by a hydrodesulfurization reaction.', p.application_date = '2013-06-21 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JPWO2013190851A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'FR13050445'}) SET p.application_no = 'FR13050445', p.title_cn = '气态燃料的制备方法', p.title_en = 'PROCESS FOR THE PREPARATION OF A GASEOUS FUEL', p.abstract_cn = '该方法包括加热混合物包括液态燃料和水，以得到混合物的汽化燃料和蒸汽，余量为水和液态燃料，和过热稀释燃料和蒸汽的混合物。过热步骤包括将干蒸汽与饱和混合物的量足以使燃油的温度，得到的气体达到或超过预定值，从而避免水和液态燃料成型的所获得的燃料气体。第一步骤进行在容器(R)，该方法包括加热混合物包括液体燃料和水，以得到汽化燃料和蒸汽的混合物和余量为水，液态燃料，过热稀释燃料和蒸汽的混合物。过热步骤包括将干蒸汽与饱和混合物的量足以使燃油的温度，得到的气体达到或超过预定值，从而避免水和液态燃料成型的所获得的燃料气体。第一步骤进行在容器(R)，它的温度保持在选定值，从而使压力的饱和容器中的混合物允许一个传输燃料的下游的气体从容器。得到的燃气过热的步骤的结束处具有预定蒸汽的含量或温度超过预定的变化相对于其烃露点的温度和/或预定的变化相对于其温度水露点。该方法以连续方式进行。容器在连续或间歇方式供电，以使其永久和同时存在的水和液体燃料。一个水和液态燃料被连续地输送通过第一阀(V1)中的线(L)包括混合器在入口的干蒸汽的加入。第一的开口阀控制保持恒压混合器的下游。加入的流量通过控制控制蒸汽的开口第三的开口喷射阀第一的阀以维持恒定的蒸汽的流量比率和水合燃气燃料。将得到的二次水合燃气燃料输出通过第二阀(V2)，保证了弛豫的规定压力。该方法还包括将得到的燃料气体与燃料气体或惰性气体。装置中进行，该方法包括 : 所述容器供给液体燃料和水，包括温度控制单元；第一阀，阀的开启控制线中的压力保持恒定；所述线包括混合器，压力变送器，第二阀，阀的开启控制的水合燃气燃料在出口的方法，和第三阀输送过热蒸汽到上游的混合器的线，包括开口第一阀的控制，并将二次水合燃气燃料的输出在其出口处过热。热源的容器包括过热的水，蒸汽，或线圈电或交叉遍历通过热流体。下部分离的容器包括两个隔室由垂直隔板(W)，其上缘是水平的。第一隔室包含水和液态燃料。第二隔室永久地充满水直到该隔板的上边缘。驱动装置永久性地提取水从第一室和转第二隔间内，以便使永久的溢流水的第二隔室在隔板的上边缘。蒸汽引入容器用于渴求的水容器通过蒸汽喷射器，注入蒸汽与水混合风洞内的气氛的容器。水引入到容器注入通过下喷雾压力容器的大气中的使用管。水或蒸气注入进行在特定容器室连通的出口腔容器通过设置竖直挡板，旨在保证惯性作用通过止液囊泡。', p.abstract_en = 'The method comprises heating a mixture including a liquid fuel and water so as to obtain a mixture of vaporized fuel and steam and the balance of water and liquid fuel,  and overheating and diluting the mixture of fuel and steam. The overheating step comprises adding dry steam with sufficient quantity to the saturated mixture so that the temperature of fuel gas obtained reaches or exceeds a predetermined value so as to avoid the water and liquid fuel formation the obtained fuel gas. The first step is carried out in a container (R). The method comprises heating a mixture including a liquid fuel and water so as to obtain a mixture of vaporized fuel and steam and the balance of water and liquid fuel,  and overheating and diluting the mixture of fuel and steam. The overheating step comprises adding dry steam with sufficient quantity to the saturated mixture so that the temperature of fuel gas obtained reaches or exceeds a predetermined value so as to avoid the water and liquid fuel formation the obtained fuel gas. The first step is carried out in a container (R) whose temperature is maintained at a selected value so that the pressure of the saturated mixture in the container allows a transfer of fuel gas downstream from the container. The obtained fuel gas at the conclusion of the overheating step has a predetermined content of steam or a temperature exceeding a predetermined variation compared to its temperature of hydrocarbon dew point and/or a predetermined variation compared to its temperature of aqueous dew point. The method is carried out in a continuous mode. The container is powered in continuous or intermittent mode so as to ensure the permanent and simultaneous presence of the water and liquid fuel. One of the water and the liquid fuel is continuously transferred through a first valve (V1) in a line (L) that includes a mixer at the entry of which the dry steam is added. The opening of the first valve is controlled to keep a constant pressure downstream from th', p.application_date = '2013-01-18 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'FR3001210B1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/34', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'IN9257DELNP2015'}) SET p.application_no = 'IN9257DELNP2015', p.title_cn = '生产合成气的方法和系统使用基于氧输送膜与二次重整的重整系统', p.title_en = 'METHOD AND SYSTEM FOR PRODUCING A SYNTHESIS GAS USING AN OXYGEN TRANSPORT MEMBRANE BASED REFORMING SYSTEM WITH SECONDARY REFORMING', p.abstract_cn = '用于生产合成气的方法和系统，在氧输送膜公开了一种基于重整系统进行初次转化过程，二次重整过程。', p.abstract_en = 'A method and system for producing a synthesis gas in an oxygen transport membrane based reforming system is disclosed that carries out a primary reforming process ,  a secondary reforming process.', p.application_date = '2015-10-07 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'IN9257DELNP2015A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'KR1020150093042'}) SET p.application_no = 'KR1020150093042', p.title_cn = '氢的制造装置使用蒸汽等离子体和及其制造方法', p.title_en = 'Apparatus for manufacturing hydrogen using a steam plasma and method for manufacturing the same', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及石墨电弧电极的氢气制造装置使用蒸汽等离子体制造方法涉及一种 和氢气， 本发明根据石墨电弧电极的氢气制造装置使用蒸汽等离子体形成 具有方向性的微波激活氢自由基和氧自由基的等离子体状态在其之后(式1)， 气化反应器煤在所述材料中碳或有机氢基的等离子体状态， 氧自由基或部分一氧化碳反应的水汽和很美的活性， (式2， 3， 4)并生成二氧化碳和氢气， 与气体产生所述气体反应器中，在氢自由基以彼此接合，在所产生的氢气的 (式5)制成的合成气中的一氧化碳转换器(CO转换器)中的蒸汽进一步的氢气通过对 一种金属与一氧化碳会给出生到出口上转换成二氧化碳包括以下步骤 :  (式6)。 本发明涉及一种蒸汽等离子体气化器栅平行六面体形的反应器蒸汽设计为大容量配置 便于连接的等离子炬和， 通过简化的放大和焊炬， 10～1001的气化反应器蒸汽等离子炬下将其由商业规模的一端 制造半导体设置进行蒸汽等离子体气化反应器具有效果。', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention relates to hydrogen manufacturing apparatus and method using steam plasma. According to the present invention,  the hydrogen manufacturing apparatus using steam plasma comprises a process of activating steam by microwaves to generate hydrogen radicals and oxygen radicals in a plasma state(chemical formula 1),  making a carbon material such as coal,  organic matter,  etc. react with the hydrogen radicals and the oxygen radicals in a plasma state or non-activated steam in a gasification reactor to generate carbon monoxide,  carbon dioxide and hydrogen (chemical formula 2,  3,  4),  and injecting syngas composed of the generated gases and hydrogen (chemical 5) generated as hydrogen radicals is combined with each other in the gasification reactor into a carbon monoxide shifter (CO shifter) with steam,  thereby supplementally producing hydrogen and converting carbon monoxide into carbon dioxide to be discharged (chemical 6). According to the present invention,  a gasification reactor of a steam plasma gasification apparatus is designed into a hexahedral large-capacity structure,  thereby facilitating attachment of a steam plasma torch and enlarging and simplifying a torch installation area. Accordingly,  10-100 steam plasma torches can be attached to one gasification reactor,  thereby having an effect of providing a large-capacity steam plasma gasification reactor on a commercial scale.COPYRIGHT KIPO 2016', p.application_date = '2015-06-30 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'KR101594350B1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/48', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'DE102014011213'}) SET p.application_no = 'DE102014011213', p.title_cn = '用于生产合成气的方法', p.title_en = 'Method for the production of synthesis gas', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种方法用于生成2-含H和CO的合成气(100)，包括如下步骤 : 提供进给流(10)，包含甲烷和CO2，和甲烷的转化(k)2在合适的第一催化剂的存在下和CO生产的合成气体流(100)，包括H2和Co，其中H0.5到3.0的范围内的2/共比。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a method for generating a 2- H and CO-containing synthesis gas (100),  comprising the steps of :  providing a feed stream (10),  comprising methane and CO 2,  and reforming of methane (K) 2 in the presence of a suitable first catalyst and CO to produce a synthesis gas stream (100) comprising H 2 and CO,  wherein the H 0.5 to 3.0 is in the range of 2/ CO-ratio.', p.application_date = '2014-07-29 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'DE102014011213A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'KR1020097025818'}) SET p.application_no = 'KR1020097025818', p.title_cn = '用于生产合成气的方法', p.title_en = 'METHOD FOR PRODUCING SYNTHESIS GAS', p.abstract_cn = '一种的制备方法和将合成气， 具有多个不同的工作状态，其基本上由相互交替的(i)白天操作和(ii)夜间 操作， 白天操作(i)主要包括干重整和蒸汽重整与可再生能源的供给， 和夜间操作(ii)包括主要部分氧化的烃， 和产生的合成气用于生产产品的价值。', p.abstract_en = 'A process for preparing and converting synthesis gas,  which has a plurality of different operating states which consist essentially of mutually alternating (i) daytime operation and (ii) nighttime operation,  daytime operation (i) comprising principally dry reforming and steam reforming with supply of renewable energy,  and nighttime operation (ii) comprising principally the partial oxidation of hydrocarbons,  and the synthesis gas produced being used to produce products of value.', p.application_date = '2008-05-09 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'KR101594188B1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WOCN14090233'}) SET p.application_no = 'WOCN14090233', p.title_cn = '微氢元素纳米分子燃料配方和氢气燃料产生器', p.title_en = 'MICRO-HYDROGEN ELEMENT NANO-MOLECULAR FUEL FORMULATION AND HYDROGEN FUEL GENERATOR', p.abstract_cn = '提供了一种微氢元素纳米分子燃料配方和氢气燃料产生器。燃料配方按重量百分数为己烷55%至65%、甲醇25%至35%和水5%至15%。所述氢气燃料产生器内设置有上述的微氢元素纳米分子燃料配方。本发明提供的微氢元素纳米分子燃料配方和氢气燃料产生器节能环保。', p.abstract_en = 'Provided are a micro-hydrogen element nano-molecular fuel formulation and a hydrogen fuel generator. The fuel formulation,  by weight percentage,  is :  55% to 65% of hexane,  25% to 35% of methanol and 5% to 15% of water. The above-mentioned micro-hydrogen element nano-molecular fuel formulation is arranged in the hydrogen fuel generator. The micro-hydrogen element nano-molecular fuel formulation and the hydrogen fuel generator provided by the present invention are energy-saving and environment friendly.', p.application_date = '2014-11-04 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016015396A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/32', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WOEP15067289'}) SET p.application_no = 'WOEP15067289', p.title_cn = '集成SCT-melc[CPO/Sr生产合成气的方法', p.title_en = 'INTEGRATED SCT-CPO/SR PROCESS FOR PRODUCING SYNTHESIS GAS', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种生产合成气的集成方法包括以下阶段 : a)将一种气态烃类流分为第一和第二流，优选包含天然气和/或炼厂气，b)发送第一流，与蒸汽混合后，以蒸汽重整段和从而产生第一的流合成气，c)发送第二流至接触时间短，催化部分氧化段，与含氧料流混合后，蒸汽和任选CO2，和第三物流包含液体和/或气态化合物，其中所述气态化合物，选自烃以外的天然气和/或炼厂气，或气态化合物衍生自生物质量块之间，和其中所述液体化合物选自烃，或各种性质的化合物衍生自生物物质，或其混合物，从而产生第二的流合成气。', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention relates to an integrated process for producing synthesis gas which comprises the following stages :  a) dividing a gaseous hydrocarbon stream into a first and a second stream,  preferably comprising natural gas and/or refinery gas,  b) sending the first stream,  after mixing with steam,  to a Steam Reforming section and thereby producing a first stream of synthesis gas,  c) sending the second stream to a short contact time -catalytic partial oxidation section,  after mixing with a stream containing oxygen,  steam and optionally CO2,  and a third stream containing liquid and/or gaseous compounds,  in which said gaseous compounds are selected from hydrocarbons other than natural gas and/or refinery gas,  or among gaseous compounds deriving from bio-masses,  and wherein said liquid compounds are selected from hydrocarbons,  or compounds of various nature deriving from bio-masses,  or mixtures thereof,  and thus producing a second stream of synthesis gas.', p.application_date = '2015-07-28 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016016251A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WOEP15067292'}) SET p.application_no = 'WOEP15067292', p.title_cn = '集成接触时间短，催化部分氧化/气体加热的重整生产合成气的方法', p.title_en = 'INTEGRATED SHORT CONTACT TIME CATALYTIC PARTIAL OXIDATION/GAS HEATED REFORMING PROCESS FOR THE PRODUCTION OF SYNTHESIS GAS', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种生产合成气的集成方法包括以下阶段 : a)将气态烃流，优选包含天然气和/或炼厂气，为第一和第二流，b)将所述第二物流与含氧料流，水蒸汽和可能含有CO2，和可能的第三物流包含液体和/或气态的化合物，其中所述气态化合物，选自烃另比天然气和/或炼厂气，或从也衍生自生物质的那些化合物，和其中所述液体化合物，选自烃或各种天然衍生自生物质的化合物，或其混合物，c)使所述混合物obtainedin(b)中的反应接触时间短，催化部分氧化段形成第一合成气，d)使第一气态物流，优选选自天然气和/或炼厂气，反应气体加热的重整段中的蒸汽以产生第二的合成气，和对流加热气体加热重整反应器第一中得到的合成气接触时间短，催化部分氧化段。', p.abstract_en = 'This invention relates to an integrated process for the production of synthesis gas comprising the following stages :  a) dividing a gaseous hydrocarbon stream,  preferably comprising natural gas and/or refinery gas,  into a first and a second stream,  b) mixing the said second stream with a stream containing oxygen,  water vapour and possibly CO2,  and possibly a third stream containing liquid and/or gaseous compounds in which the said gaseous compounds are selected from hydrocarbons other than natural gas and/or refinery gas,  or from those compounds which also derive from biomass,  and in which the said liquid compounds are selected from hydrocarbons or compounds of various nature deriving from biomass,  or mixtures thereof,  c)causing the mixture obtainedin (b) to react in a short contact time Catalytic Partial Oxidation section to form a first synthesis gas,  d) causing the first gaseous stream,  preferably selected from natural gas and/or refinery gas,  to react with steam in a Gas Heated Reforming section to produce a second synthesis gas,  and convectively heating the Gas Heated Reforming reactor with the first synthesis gas obtained in the short contact time Catalytic Partial Oxidation section.', p.application_date = '2015-07-28 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016016253A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WOEP15067297'}) SET p.application_no = 'WOEP15067297', p.title_cn = '集成SCT-melc[CPO/ATR合成气的生产方法', p.title_en = 'INTEGRATED SCT-CPO/ATR PROCESS FOR THE PRODUCTION OF SYNTHESIS GAS', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种生产合成气的集成方法包括以下阶段 : a)将气态烃流，优选包含天然气和/或炼厂气，为第一和第二流，b)发送第一流，混合后与蒸汽和含氧料流，给自热重整段形成第一流合成气，c)发送第二流至接触时间短，混合后的部分催化氧化段与流含氧，蒸汽和任选CO2，和第三物流包含液体和/或气态化合物，其中所述气态化合物，选自烃以外的天然气和/或炼厂气，或从那些气态化合物也可来自生物质，和其中所述液体化合物，选自烃或多种衍生自生物质的化合物，或其混合物，从而产生第二的流合成气。', p.abstract_en = 'This invention relates to an integrated process for the production of synthesis gas comprising the following stages :  a) dividing a gaseous hydrocarbon stream,  preferably comprising natural gas and/or refinery gas,  into a first and a second stream,  b) sending the first stream,  after mixing with steam and a stream containing oxygen,  to an Autothermal Reformer section to form a first stream of synthesis gas,  c) sending the second stream to a short contact time partial catalytic oxidation section after mixing it with a stream containing oxygen,  steam and optionally CO2,  and a third stream containing liquid and/or gaseous compounds,  in which the said gaseous compounds are selected from hydrocarbons other than natural gas and/or refinery gas,  or from those gaseous compounds which can also be derived from biomass,  and in which the said liquid compounds are selected from hydrocarbons or compounds of various kinds deriving from biomass,  or mixtures thereof,  thus producing a second stream of synthesis gas.', p.application_date = '2015-07-28 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016016256A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WOEP15067300'}) SET p.application_no = 'WOEP15067300', p.title_cn = '集成SCT-melc[CPO/痘生产合成气的方法', p.title_en = 'INTEGRATED SCT-CPO/POX PROCESS FOR PRODUCING SYNTHESIS GAS', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种集成生产合成气的方法从含碳化合物，液体原料，气态原料，或其组合包括导电的步骤在平行一级接触时间短，催化部分氧化(SCT r-CPO)和级的非催化部分氧化(痘)。', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention relates to an integrated process for producing synthesis gas from carbonaceous compounds,  liquid feedstock,  gaseous feedstock,  or combinations thereof which comprises the step of conducting in parallel one stage of short contact time catalytic partial oxidation (SCT-CPO) and a stage of non-catalytic partial oxidation (POx).', p.application_date = '2015-07-28 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016016257A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WOIB15001767'}) SET p.application_no = 'WOIB15001767', p.title_cn = '性能平衡的弹性氢反应器', p.title_en = 'PERFORMANCE BALANCING ELASTOMERIC HYDROGEN REACTOR', p.abstract_cn = '制氢反应器具有丸芯在弹性封闭容器的出口喷嘴和具有路线传送流体至所述颗粒上。一个或多个弹性绕组可以放置封闭容器周围。容纳压缩围绕燃料球团为它使用。氢和其它反应器生产的产品盒内，经具有无堵塞过滤器和基本上纯氢气输出。', p.abstract_en = 'A hydrogen producing reactor having a pellet core within an elastomeric containment vessel with an exit nozzle and having a line to deliver fluid to the pellet. One or more elastomeric windings may be placed around the containment vessel. The containment compresses around the fuel pellet as it is used. Hydrogen and other products produced by the reactor within a cartridge is filtered with a clog-less filter and substantially pure hydrogen is output.', p.application_date = '2015-07-28 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016016720A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/06', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WOJP14069780'}) SET p.application_no = 'WOJP14069780', p.title_cn = '采暖炉', p.title_en = 'HEATING FURNACE', p.abstract_cn = '提供一种加热炉通过加热的均匀性在轴向方向的每一个的多个可提高加热管，从而提高了加热效率。加热炉上设有如下 : 外周燃烧器5，其设置在周壁部(1a)的炉本体1；和中心燃烧器6设置在封闭端(2c)燃烧2，中心燃烧器6喷射燃气的Ge向所述燃烧筒的开口端O2。燃烧筒2上设置为内散热筒7辐射的辐射热量从外周表面。环形加热管阵列之间L，其中多个加热管4设置在圆，和内散热筒7，外散热筒8具有圆柱形的形状，带有内直径大于所述的外直径内散热筒7上设置以同心或基本上同心的与炉主体1在状态，在该外辐射缸从开口端延伸7a O内的散热筒7两侧的内散热筒7在轴向方向。外辐射室的端部8相对于开口端外侧7a O的内散热筒7，在轴向方向的内散热筒7，由外部封闭的辐射筒封闭部件(30)。', p.abstract_en = 'Provided is a heating furnace by which uniformity of heating in the axial direction of each of a plurality of heating tubes can be improved,  and heating efficiency can thereby be improved. The heating furnace is provided with the following :  an outer circumferential burner 5 that is disposed in a circumferential wall portion 1a of a furnace main body 1;  and a central burner 6 that is disposed at a closed end 2c of a combustion 2,  the central burner 6 injecting combustion gas Ge towards an open end 2o of the combustion cylinder 2. The combustion cylinder 2 is provided as an inner radiation cylinder 7 that radiates radiation heat from an outer circumferential surface. Between a circular heating tube array 4L,  in which a plurality of heating tubes 4 are arranged in a circle,  and the inner radiation cylinder 7,  an outer radiation cylinder 8 having a cylindrical shape with an inner diameter larger than the outer diameter of the inner radiation cylinder 7 is provided so as to be concentric or substantially concentric with the furnace main body 1 in a state in which the outer radiation cylinder extends from an open end 7o of the inner radiation cylinder 7 to both sides of the inner radiation cylinder 7 in the axial direction. An end of the outer radiation chamber 8 with respect to the outside of the open end 7o of the inner radiation cylinder 7,  in the axial direction of the inner radiation cylinder 7,  is closed off by an outside radiation cylinder closing member 30.', p.application_date = '2014-07-28 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016016919A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201180035645.3'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201180035645.3', p.title_cn = '用超纯高压氢气生成甲醇的方法', p.title_en = 'Ultra-pure for a method of high pressure hydrogen produces methanol', p.abstract_cn = '使用含CO和H2的合成气生产甲醇(38)，该合成气是由POX(4)与EHTR(53)的组合或ATR与EHTR的组合在70-100巴压力下在正确的甲醇合成化学计量比下制得的，因此不需要进料气压缩机为甲醇合成反应器回路提供进料。', p.abstract_en = 'In various implementations,  methanol is produced using a (CO+H2) containing synthesis gas produced from a combined PDX plus EHTR or a combined ATR plus EHTR at a pressure of 70 bar to 100 bar at the correct stoichiometric composition for methanol synthesis so that no feed gas compressor is required for the feed to the methanol synthesis reactor loop.', p.application_date = '2011-05-25 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN103003192B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/36', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 2, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201180063295.1'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201180063295.1', p.title_cn = '制氢方法', p.title_en = 'Method for hydrogen production', p.abstract_cn = '提供由水制造氢的方法。本发明的制氢方法包括将水裂解成氢和氧，其中本发明的方法包括通过利用太阳热能经下式(X1)表示的反应将硫酸分解为水、二氧化硫和氧，其中至少一部分下式(X1-1)的元反应利用太阳热能进行，至少一部分下式(X1-2)的元反应利用非太阳热能的另外热能进行，并且其中所述另外热能的加热温度比所述太阳热能的加热温度高10℃或更高，并且在反应容器中产生至少一部分另外热能：(X1)H2SO4→H2O+SO2+1/2O2，(X1-1)H2SO4→H2O+SO3，和(X1-2)SO3→SO2+1/2O2。', p.abstract_en = 'A method for producing hydrogen from water is provided. The hydrogen production process includes splitting water into hydrogen and oxygen,  wherein the process includes decomposing sulfuric acid into water,  sulfur dioxide and oxygen through a reaction of formula (X1) by using solar thermal energy,  wherein at least a part of the elementary reaction of formula (X1-1) is performed using thermal solar energy,  and at least a part of the elementary reaction of formula (X1-2) is performed using additional thermal energy other than solar thermal energy,  and wherein the heating temperature by the additional thermal energy is higher by 10° C. or more than the heating temperature by the solar thermal energy,  and at least a part of the additional thermal energy is generated in a reaction vessel :  (X1) H2SO4→H2O+SO2+1/2O2,  (X1-1) H2SO4→H2O+SO3,  and (X1-2) SO3→SO2+1/2O2.', p.application_date = '2011-12-07 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN103298734B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/06', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201310610374.0'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201310610374.0', p.title_cn = '一种硼烷氨复合储氢材料及其制备方法', p.title_en = 'A borane-ammonia composite hydrogen storage material and method of producing the same', p.abstract_cn = '本发明属于新能源氢能的储存运输技术领域，特别涉及一种硼烷氨复合储氢材料及其制备方法。所述材料为采用浸渍法将硼烷氨负载到多孔配位聚合物中。本发明复合材料降低了硼烷氨的热分解放氢温度，加快了放氢动力学，避免了挥发性副产物的生成，解决了硼烷氨作为氢源材料的技术障碍，为氢能源应用于车载以及工业方面提供了可能性。同时制备方法简单易行，成本低，效果好。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention belongs to the technical field of storage and transportation of a new energy source namely hydrogen energy,  and in particular relates to an ammonia borane composite hydrogen storage material and a preparation method thereof. The ammonia borane composite hydrogen storage material is prepared by loading ammonia borane into a porous coordination polymer by adopting an impregnation method. The composite material disclosed by the invention reduces the thermal decomposition hydrogen release temperature of ammonia borane,  accelerates hydrogen release kinetics,  avoids generation of volatile byproducts,  solves technical obstacles for taking ammonia borane as a hydrogen source material,  and provides probability of applying a hydrogen energy source to vehicles and industries. Meanwhile,  the preparation method is simple and feasible,  low in cost and good in effect.', p.application_date = '2013-11-26 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN103613068B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201510671152.9'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201510671152.9', p.title_cn = '高温气冷核反应堆氢氧制造工厂', p.title_en = 'High-temperature gas-cooled nuclear reactor hydrogen and oxygen manufacturing plant', p.abstract_cn = '高温气冷核反应堆氢氧制造工厂就是将1个或多高温气冷堆用多组热管插入堆芯将堆芯热量导出，利用约950摄氏度的温度制造氢(请阅实质审查参考资料中的《美研制出制氢新法以核能取代石油降低成本利用高温气冷核反应堆提供的高温来将核能转换成氢能源》)，低于制氢温度用来做温差发电，这样会使核能转换有效率更加提高，在将高温气冷堆中的二回路蒸汽用于推进汽轮机，汽轮机驱动空气分离装置中的压缩机进行空气分离来制造氧气。有了氢氧高效清洁能源，用于各个领域。使各种发动机间接的使用上了核能，携同样重量的氢燃料，其蓄航能力可提高1倍已上。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention provides a high-temperature gas-cooled nuclear reactor hydrogen and oxygen manufacturing plant. Precisely,  a plurality of sets of heat pipes are inserted in reactor cores of one or more high-temperature gas-cooled reactors so that heat of the reactor cores can be guided out,  hydrogen is manufactured at the temperature about 950 DEG C (please read the file that America develops a new hydrogen manufacturing method through which petroleum is replaced with nuclear energy so that cost can be reduced and nuclear energy is converted into hydrogen energy through high temperature provided by high-temperature gas-cooled nuclear reactors in substantive examination and reference materials),  the temperature lower than the hydrogen manufacturing temperature is used for temperature difference power generation,  and therefore the effectiveness of nuclear energy conversion can be more improved,  two-loop steam in the high-temperature gas-cooled reactors is used for pushing a steam turbine,  and the steam turbine drives a compressor in an air separation device to perform air separation so that oxygen can be manufactured. Hydrogen and oxygen efficient clean energy is used for various fields. Various engines can indirectly use nuclear energy and carry hydrogen fuel with the weight the same as that of the nuclear energy,  and the endurance capacity of the engines can be improved by more than one time.', p.application_date = '2015-10-15 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105293430A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201510629658.3'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201510629658.3', p.title_cn = '利用深层海水制备低氘氚水的系统及方法', p.title_en = 'System and method for preparing low-deuterium tritiated water by using deep-layer seawater', p.abstract_cn = '本发明揭示了一种利用深层海水制备低氘氚水的系统及方法，所述系统包括深层海水抽取设备、海水提纯装置、制氢设备、氧气输送设备、水生成设备；所述深层海水抽取设备与海水提纯装置连接，经提纯后的海水输送至制氢设备，作为制氢设备的部分原料；制氢设备设有膜分离装置，通过膜分离装置将氢气中的氕分离出，而氢气中的氘、氚无法从膜分离装置过滤出；所述氧气输送设备通过制备而提供氧气，或者仅输送制备好的氧气；所述水生成设备接收制氢设备制备的氢气、氧气输送设备输送的氧气，制得健康水。本发明可制备不含具有放射性元素氘氚的轻水，提升人们的生活品质，满足人们对健康的需求。此外，本系统具有便携性，方便人们携带。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention discloses a system and method for preparing low-deuterium tritiated water by using deep-layer seawater. The system comprises deep-layer seawater pumping equipment,  a seawater purification device,  hydrogen production equipment,  oxygen conveying equipment and water generation equipment,  wherein the deep-layer seawater pumping equipment is connected with the seawater purification device;  purified seawater is conveyed into the hydrogen production equipment to be used as one part of raw material of the hydrogen production equipment;  the hydrogen production equipment is provided with a membrane separation device;  protium in hydrogen gas is separated by using the membrane separation device,  and deuterium and tritium in the hydrogen gas cannot be filtered by the membrane separation device;  the oxygen conveying equipment provides oxygen gas through preparation or only conveys the prepared oxygen gas;  the water generation equipment is used for receiving the hydrogen gas prepared by the hydrogen production equipment,  and the oxygen gas conveyed by the oxygen conveying equipment to prepare healthy water. The system and method,  provided by the invention,  can be used for preparing light water without radioactive elements including the deuterium and the tritium,  so that the living quality of people is improved and the requirements on health by people are met. Furthermore,  the system has portability and is convenient for people to carry.', p.application_date = '2015-09-29 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105293431A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/32', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201510754381.7'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201510754381.7', p.title_cn = '一种甲醇水重整制氢机及其制氢方法', p.title_en = 'Methanol water reforming hydrogen production machine and hydrogen production method thereof', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种甲醇水重整制氢机及其制氢方法，其中，甲醇水重整制氢机包括甲醇水储存容器、输送泵、变频器、换热器及重整器，其中：变频器，用于将低频电压或直流电压转换为电磁加热器之电磁线圈所需要的高频电压，所述变频器设置有液冷散热器，所述甲醇水原料在输送泵的泵送过程中，流经该液冷散热器，使变频器产生的热量被甲醇水原料带走；重整器，设有重整室、电磁加热器及氢气纯化装置，所述电磁加热器包括电磁线圈及金属受磁体，所述电磁线圈输入高频电压后能产生高频磁场，使金属受磁体受磁场感应而发热，为重整室提供热能。本发明的变频器噪音低、散热效果好、耗能低，并且本发明能够有效地利用变频器所产生的热量。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention discloses a methanol water reforming hydrogen production machine and a hydrogen production method thereof. The methanol water reforming hydrogen production machine comprises a methanol water storage container,  a delivery pump,  a frequency converter,  a heat exchanger and a reformer,  wherein the frequency converter is used for converting a low-frequency voltage or a direct current voltage into a high-frequency voltage required for an electromagnetic coil of an electromagnetic heater,  the frequency converter is provided with a liquid cooling radiator,  and a methanol water raw material flows through the liquid cooling radiator in the pumping process of the delivery pump,  so that heat generated by the frequency converter is taken away by the methanol water raw material. The reformer is provided with a reforming chamber,  the electromagnetic heater and a hydrogen purification device. The electromagnetic heater comprises the electromagnetic coil and a metal magnetized body. A high frequency magnetic field can be generated after the high-frequency voltage is input into the electromagnetic coil,  so that the metal magnetized body emits heat due to magnetic field induction and provides thermal energy for the reforming chamber. The frequency converter is low in noise,  good in cooling effect and low in energy consumption. According to the methanol water reforming hydrogen production machine,  heat generated by the frequency converter can be utilized effectively.', p.application_date = '2015-11-09 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105293432A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/32', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201510880962.5'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201510880962.5', p.title_cn = '一种调节氢碳比的方法', p.title_en = 'Method for regulating hydrogen/carbon ratio', p.abstract_cn = '本发明属于甲醇制备领域，具体涉及一种调节氢碳比的方法；采用的技术方案为：以焦炉煤气和水蒸气为原料，包括以下步骤，首先原料与CO2压缩机出口气源进行混合后，一并进入非催化转化部分氧化炉设备，然后在高温高压的条件下进行反应，通过调节系统配入CO2的用量，有效调节出口转化气的氢碳比，其工作条件为：CO2压缩机的压力为3.7 MPa，反应压力为3.0MPa，反应温度为1095℃；本发明不仅可以拓宽氢碳比的控制范围，同时充分利用反应产物，提高水碳比，进而提高经济效益。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention belongs to the field of methanol preparation and particularly relates to a method for regulating hydrogen/carbon ratio. The technical scheme is as follows :  coke oven gases and water vapor are used as raw materials,  and the method comprises the following steps of firstly,  mixing the raw materials and an outlet air source of a CO2 compressor,  and then,  enabling the mixture to simultaneously enter non-catalytic conversion partial oxidation furnace equipment;  reacting under the conditions of high temperature and high pressure;  and adding CO2 through a regulating system,  and effectively regulating the hydrogen/carbon ratio of an outlet conversion gas,  wherein the working conditions are as follows :  the pressure of the CO2 compressor is 3.7MPa,  the reaction pressure is 3.0MPa,  and the reaction temperature is 1095 DEG C. The method not only can be used for widening the control range of the hydrogen/carbon ratio,  but also can be used for increasing the water/carbon ratio through sufficiently utilizing reaction products,  and furthermore the economic benefit is increased.', p.application_date = '2015-12-07 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105293433A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/34', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201510726740.8'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201510726740.8', p.title_cn = '将烃类燃料转化为富氢气体的方法', p.title_en = 'Method for converting hydrocarbon fuel into hydrogen-rich gas', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种通过自热反应将烃类燃料转化为用于燃料电池和/或排气处理应用的富氢气体的方法，该方法使用重整反应器(1)，其具有：壳体(2)，壳体(2)具有两个侧表面(8a，8b)，这两个侧表面(8a，8b)形成重整反应器(1)的反应室(10)；燃料入口(22)，燃料入口(22)设置在所述两个侧表面中的一个侧表面(8a)中，以将烃类燃料提供到反应室(10)中；以及氧化剂入口(18)，氧化剂入口(18)用于将氧化剂提供到反应室(10)中，所述方法包括如下步骤：将氧化剂预热到与烃类燃料的沸点基本相等或高于沸点的温度；将烃类燃料预热到比烃类燃料的沸点略低的温度；以及将烃类燃料和氧化剂引入到反应室(10)中。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a method for converting hydrocarbon fuel into a hydrogen-rich gas which is applied to a fuel cell and/or exhaust treatment through autothermal reaction. A reform reactor (1) is utilized by the method;  the reform reactor (1) comprises a shell (2),  a fuel inlet (22) and an oxidant inlet (18),  wherein the shell (2) comprises two side surfaces (8a and 8b);  the two side surfaces (8a and 8b) form a reaction chamber (10) of the reform reactor (1);  the fuel inlet (22) is formed in one side surface (8a) of the two side surfaces to provide the hydrocarbon fuel to the reaction chamber (10);  the oxidant inlet (18) is used for providing an oxidant to the reaction chamber (10);  and the method comprises the following steps :  preheating the oxidant to the temperature which is basically equal to or higher than the boiling pint of the hydrocarbon fuel;  and preheating the hydrocarbon fuel to the temperature which is a little lower than the boiling point of the hydrocarbon fuel;  and introducing the hydrocarbon fuel and the oxidant into the reaction chamber (10).', p.application_date = '2008-07-02 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105293435A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201510624472.9'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201510624472.9', p.title_cn = '在压力下联合产生CO2流的氢吸附提纯法', p.title_en = 'PURIFICATION METHOD BY HYDROGEN ADSORBTION WITH COGENERATION OF CO2 STREAM PRESSURE', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及由主要含有所述氢气和次要部分的主要由二氧化碳、一氧化碳、甲烷和重质烃构成的杂质的进料制造极高纯度的氢的方法。这种采用在比进料压力低的压力下的解吸阶段的氢吸附提纯法，例如PSA法，其能够产生解吸流并特别能够在压力下回收二氧化碳和以高收率回收高纯度氢。通过将本发明的方法的连续阶段与新的吸附剂族的使用相结合，获得这些性能，所述新的吸附剂族在高解吸压力下的动态吸附容量高于传统吸附剂。', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention relates to a method of producing hydrogen of very high purity from a feed predominantly containing said hydrogen and a minor part of impurities mainly consisting of carbon dioxide,  carbon monoxide,  methane and heavier hydrocarbons. The purification method by hydrogen adsorption using a desorption stage at a lower pressure than the pressure of the feed,  such as a PSA method for example,  allows to produce the desorption stream and notably to recover the carbon dioxide under pressure and high-purity hydrogen,  with a high yield. These performances are obtained by combining the successive stages of the method according to the invention with the use of a new family of adsorbent whose dynamic capacity at a high desorption pressure is greater than that of conventional adsorbents.', p.application_date = '2007-11-30 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105293437A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/56', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201520156548.5'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201520156548.5', p.title_cn = '太阳能制氢装置', p.title_en = 'Solar energy hydrogen production device', p.abstract_cn = '太阳能制氢装置，由太阳能抛物面聚能器、反应炉、冷凝器、分离塔部件构成，其特征在于将多个太阳能抛物面聚能器的光纤束与反应炉连接起来，使会聚的太阳光束通过反应炉外壳照射里面的煤粉；反应炉上部设置有排气管，下部设置有喷嘴，内部设置有煤粉，侧面设置有炉门；冷凝器的一端连接在排气管，另一端连接在分离塔的进气口上；分离搭内中部位置设置有顶针、活塞组；分离塔外壳中部设置有进气管，上部设置氢气管、下部设置一氧化碳管；沿分离塔的轴线处设置有丝杆，并贯穿活塞组；丝杆伸出塔外的一端设置有活塞电机；塔内还设置有一条贯穿活塞组与丝杆平行的定位杆。该装置利用太阳辐射能大量获取氢气，从而实现制取氢气的工业化生产，成本低廉。', p.abstract_en = 'Solar energy hydrogen production device comprises the parabolic amplitude transformer of solar energy,  reacting furnace,  condenser,  knockout tower parts,  and its characterized in that couples together the optical fiber bundle of the parabolic amplitude transformer of a plurality of solar energy with the reacting furnace,  make the sun light beam of assembling shine the buggy of the inside through the reacting furnace shell,  reacting furnace upper portion is provided with the blast pipe,  and the lower part is provided with the nozzle,  and inside is provided with the buggy,  and the side is provided with the furnace gate,  the one end of condenser is connected at the blast pipe,  and the other end is connected on the air inlet of knockout tower,  the separation is taken inside the position and is put and be provided with thimble,  piston group,  knockout tower shell middle part is provided with the intake pipe,  and upper portion sets up the hydrogen pipe,  the lower part sets up the carbon monoxide pipe,  axis department along the knockout tower is provided with the lead screw to run through piston group,  the one end that the lead screw stretches out the tower outer is provided with the piston motor,  it runs through the piston group locating lever parallel with the lead screw still to be provided with one in the tower. The device utilizes solar radiation can acquire hydrogen in a large number to the industrial production of hydrogen,  low cost are prepared in the realization.', p.application_date = '2015-03-18 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN205011381U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201520691851.5'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201520691851.5', p.title_cn = '一种氨分解制氢设备', p.title_en = 'Ammonia decomposition hydrogen producer', p.abstract_cn = '本实用新型公开了一种氨分解制氢设备，属于工业制氢设备领域，包括外壳、换热器、分解炉，位于该换热器上设置有氨气进口管、氨气出口管、氢氮气体进口管、氢氮气体出口管和排污管；氨气进口管上设置氮压力表，且该氨气进口管与氨气供气源连接；氨气出口管与分解炉的进气管连接；氢氮气体进口管与分解炉上出气管连接，且位于该氢氮气体进口管设置有温度传感器；氢氮气体出口管上设置有氢氮压力表，且该氢氮气体出口管与氢氮气体存储罐连接；位于换热器底部设置有排污管。本实用新型通过将高热氢氮混合气和气态氨气在换热器内进行热交换，使得进入分解炉内的氨气温度提高，从而有利于气态氨气的分解，大大节约了加热炉的加热功率。', p.abstract_en = 'The utility model discloses an ammonia decomposition hydrogen producer belongs to industry hydrogen producer field,  including shell,  heat exchanger,  dore furnace,  be located and be provided with ammonia import pipe,  ammonia outlet pipe,  hydrogen nitrogen gas feed pipe,  hydrogen nitrogen gas outlet duct and blow off pipe on this heat exchanger,  set up the nitrogen manometer on the ammonia import pipe,  and this ammonia import pipe is connected with ammonia air feed source,  the intake -tube connection of ammonia outlet pipe and dore furnace,  the outlet duct is connected on hydrogen nitrogen gas feed pipe and the dore furnace,  just is located this hydrogen nitrogen gas feed and manages and be provided with temperature sensor,  be provided with hydrogen nitrogen manometer on the hydrogen nitrogen gas outlet duct,  and this hydrogen nitrogen gas outlet duct is connected with hydrogen nitrogen gas body storage jar,  it is provided with the blow off pipe to be located the heat exchanger bottom. The utility model discloses a carry out the heat exchange with high fever hydrogen nitrogen gas mixture and gaseous state ammonia in the heat exchanger for the ammonia temperature that gets into in the dore furnace improves,  thereby is favorable to the decomposition of gaseous state ammonia,  has practiced thrift the heating power of heating furnace greatly.', p.application_date = '2015-09-09 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN205011382U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201520595589.4'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201520595589.4', p.title_cn = '天然气部分氧化制合成气余热回收的系统', p.title_en = 'System for natural gas partial oxidation system synthetic gas waste heat recovery', p.abstract_cn = '本实用新型公开了天然气部分氧化制合成气余热回收的系统，包括：气化炉，具有反应气入口和次高温合成气出口；水夹套，设置于气化炉的外壳上；一级冷却器，具有一级合成气通道和一级冷却水通道，一级合成气通道的一端与次高温合成气出口相连，一级冷却水通道的一端与水夹套相连；汽包，具有汽水混合物入口、冷却水入口、液态水出口和饱和蒸汽出口，液态水出口与一级冷却水通道的另一端相连；二级冷却器，具有二级合成气通道和二级冷却水通道，二级合成气通道的一端与一级冷却合成气通道的另一端相连，二级冷却水通道的一端与冷却水入口相连；循环泵，与液态水出口和一级合成气通道的另一端相连；补水泵，其与二级冷却水通道的另一端相连。', p.abstract_en = 'The utility model discloses a system for natural gas partial oxidation system synthetic gas waste heat recovery,  include :  the gasifier has reaction gas entry and time high temperature synthetic gas export,  the water jacket sets up on the shell of gasifier,  the one -level cooler has one -level synthetic gas passageway and one -level cooling water passageway,  and the one end of one -level synthetic gas passageway links to each other with the export of inferior high temperature synthetic gas,  and the one end of one -level cooling water passageway links to each other with the water jacket,  the steam pocket has soda mixture entry,  cooling water inlet,  aqueous water export and saturated steam export,  and the aqueous water export links to each other with the other end of one -level cooling water passageway,  the second grade cooler has second grade synthetic gas passageway and second grade cooling water passageway,  and the one end of second grade synthetic gas passageway links to each other with the other end of one -level cooling synthetic gas passageway,  and the one end of second grade cooling water passageway links to each other with the cooling water inlet,  the circulating pump,  it is continuous with the other end of aqueous water export and one -level synthetic gas passageway,  the moisturizing pump,  its other end with second grade cooling water passageway links to each other.', p.application_date = '2015-08-07 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN205011383U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/34', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201520691706.7'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201520691706.7', p.title_cn = '一种工业废气氢回收处理系统', p.title_en = 'Industrial waste gas hydrogen recycling processed system', p.abstract_cn = '本实用新型公开了一种工业废气氢回收处理系统，包括水洗塔、分离器、罗茨风机、水冷机组、干燥塔和再生加热器，水洗塔的进料口与待回收的氢气管道连接，水洗塔的出料口与一组分离器连接，该组分离器由分离器a和分离器b串联连接；该组分离器的出料端与罗茨风机的进气端连接，罗茨风机的出气端与水冷机组连接，水冷机组的出料端与分离器c连接，该分离器c的出料端与一组干燥塔连接，该组干燥塔的出料端与再生加热器的进料端连接，该再生加热器的进料端还与钢瓶氢连接，该再生加热器的出料端与使用设备管道连接，且在该管道上设置有露点仪。解决了生产中的尾气排放处理，并将排放的氢气进行再次回收利用，节能环保节约生产成本。', p.abstract_en = 'The utility model discloses an industrial waste gas hydrogen recycling processed system,  including water wash column,  separator,  roots\'s fan,  water -cooled generator group,  drying tower and regenerative heater,  the feed inlet of water wash column and the hydrogen pipe connection of treating the recovery,  the discharge gate and a set of separator of water wash column are connected,  and this group separation ware is by separator an and separator b series connection,  the discharge end and the inlet end of roots\'s fan of this group separation ware are connected,  the give vent to anger end and the water -cooled generator group link of roots\'s fan,  and the discharge end of water -cooled generator group is connected with separator c,  and this separator c\'s discharge end and a set of drying tower are connected,  should organize the discharge end of drying tower and regenerative heater\'s feeding end connection,  and this regenerative heater\'s feed end still is connected with steel bottle hydrogen,  this regenerative heater\'s discharge end and the equipment of use pipe connection,  and be provided with the dew point hygrometer on this pipeline. It handles to have solved the exhaust emissions in the production to carry out recycle once more,  energy -concerving and environment -protective saving manufacturing cost with the hydrogen that discharges.', p.application_date = '2015-09-09 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN205011384U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/50', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2012512292'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2012512292', p.title_cn = '用于生产合成气的方法', p.title_en = 'Method for producing synthesis gas', p.abstract_cn = 'H2-和含有CO的合成气通过分离焦炭从焦炉荒煤气的方法为氢气和一种残余气体物流包含烃类和获得富含CO的合成气体流从顶部气体的高炉。从焦炉分离的氢气体进入富CO合成获得的气体物流从高炉的炉顶气，使合成气，和含烃的残余气体物流送入高炉作为原料。', p.abstract_en = 'An H2- and CO-containing synthesis gas is made by separating coke-oven gas from a coke-oven process into hydrogen and a residual gas stream containing hydrocarbons and obtaining a CO-rich synthesis-gas stream from a top gas of a blast furnace. The hydrogen separated from the coke-oven gas is fed into the CO-rich synthesis gas stream obtained from the top gas of a blast furnace to make the synthesis gas,  and the hydrocarbon-containing residual gas stream is fed into the blast furnace as feedstock.', p.application_date = '2010-05-06 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP5850831B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/50', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2014519267'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2014519267', p.title_cn = '该产生氢的氢净化装置和组件', p.title_en = 'The hydrogen generating hydrogen purification device and assembly', p.abstract_cn = '氢产生组件，氢纯化装置，和它们的成分，和制造这些组件的方法，装置，和部件。在一些实施例中，该装置可包括与膜承载结构的帧和/或可以包括微孔筛网结构被构造成防止金属间扩散。', p.abstract_en = 'Hydrogen generation assemblies,  hydrogen purification devices,  and their components,  and methods of manufacturing those assemblies,  devices,  and components are disclosed. In some embodiments,  the devices may include an insulation base having insulating material and at least one passage that extends through the insulating material. In some embodiments,  the at least one passage may be in fluid communication with a combustion region.', p.application_date = '2012-07-03 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP5851602B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/32', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2012009127'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2012009127', p.title_cn = '氢气发生器', p.title_en = 'The hydrogen generator', p.abstract_cn = '要解决的问题 : 提供一种氢气发生器用于产生氢可以稳定地和有效地用一种简单的结构。溶液 : 该中空反应细胞(1)和一种金属的材料制成的，本发明的一个端反应细胞用于加热和加热装置(2)，和该反应细胞的其它端(30)和一个冷却装置，用于冷却，为了除去该空气在该反应细胞和除气装置(50)和，是提供。选自拉拔 : 图。1。', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To provide a hydrogen generation apparatus capable of stably and efficiently generating hydrogen by a simple structure.SOLUTION :  A hydrogen generation apparatus has a reaction cell (1) composed of a metallic material,  a heating means (2) to heat one end portion of the reaction cell,  a cooling means (30) to cool the other end portion of the reaction cell,  and an air removing means (50) to remove air in the reaction cell.', p.application_date = '2012-01-19 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP5852891B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/06', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CA2854702'}) SET p.application_no = 'CA2854702', p.title_cn = '安全装置的压力超过值的', p.title_en = 'SAFETY MEANS AGAINST PRESSURE EXCEEDANCE', p.abstract_cn = '安全装置，用于保护植物部分，位于压力侧的一喷气压缩机连接推进剂系统抵御超出可容许的压力，包括受控安全阀致动由外部能量，其控制装置测量与植物连接段通过至少一个取压保护线路，所述安全阀的设置，使得在超出以后，保护植物段中的压力能通气推进剂从所述推进剂的系统。', p.abstract_en = 'A safety means for protecting a plant section located on the pressure side of a jet compressor connected with a propellant system against the exceedance of an admissible pressure,  comprising a controlled safety valve actuated by external energy,  whose control means measures is connected with the plant section to be protected via at least one pressure tapping line,  wherein the safety valve is arranged such that upon exceedance of the pressure in the protected plant section it can vent propellant from the propellant system.', p.application_date = '2013-02-21 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CA2854702C', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/34', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US13355562'}) SET p.application_no = 'US13355562', p.title_cn = '具有转化生物质和甲醇的液体燃料反应器、燃气涡轮发电机和过热CO2副产品的混合超临界动力循环', p.title_en = 'Hybrid supercritical power cycle having liquid fuel reactor converting biomass and methanol,  gas turbine power generator,  and superheated CO2 byproduct', p.abstract_cn = '一种产生废气的发电系统，所述废气提供二氧化碳和预热氢源两者，所述预热氢源用于从现在加热的氢与纤维素生物质的反应中产生液体燃料，其中所述氢源优选为甲醇。', p.abstract_en = 'A power generation system yielding exhaust providing both carbon dioxide and a preheated hydrogen source used to create liquid fuels from the reaction of the now heated hydrogen with cellulosic biomass,  preferably where the hydrogen source is methanol.', p.application_date = '2012-01-22 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9249018B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/22', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US13709010'}) SET p.application_no = 'US13709010', p.title_cn = '含氢气体燃料的多级生产方法及其实施的热气体发生器装置', p.title_en = 'Multistage method for producing hydrogen-containing gaseous fuel and thermal gas-generator setup of its implementation', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种生产含烃气体燃料的方法，包括至少三个阶段。 在第一阶段中，进入水用于加热和水蒸汽形成。 在第二阶段中，烃组分被进入并通过喷射与水蒸汽混合，混合物被加热并被引导到第三和随后的阶段，以额外加热用于燃料生产。 汽轮发电机被做成两个汽缸管，在孤立的部分分开。 第一段采用感应热源启动系统，第二段采用喷射器式混合器启动系统。 内管腔形成点火室。 在工艺气缸中，多级部件和混合物被加热并在随后的部分中被附加加热，直到形成含氢气体燃料。 燃烧室进口安装有燃烧系统、人工燃烧器、启动燃烧器。 工作炬形成元件安装在点火室出口上。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a method for producing hydrocarbon-containing gaseous fuel comprises at least three stages. In the first stage water is entered for heating and water steam forming. In the second stage hydrocarbon component is entered and mixed with water steam by injecting The mixture is heated and directed to third and subsequent stages to additional heating for fuel producing. Turbo generator is made as two cylinder tubes,  divided on isolated sections. The first section is made with induction heat source for system start-up,  the second section is made with injector type mixer. The inner tube cavity forms the firing chamber. In technological cylinder multistage components and mixture heated and additional heating in subsequent sections are realized until forming of hydrogen-containing gaseous fuel. Burning system,  worker burner,  start-up burner are installed on the firing chamber inlet. Working torch forming element is installed on the firing chamber outlet.', p.application_date = '2012-12-09 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9249019B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/36', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 2, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US13624993'}) SET p.application_no = 'US13624993', p.title_cn = '一种生产合成气的方法和系统', p.title_en = 'Method and system for producing synthesis gas', p.abstract_cn = '一种生产合成气的方法，包括 : 1)预处理生物质原料； 2)将生物质原料热解，得到热解气体和碳粉； 3)将热解气体与碳粉和固体热载体分离； 4)通过固-固分离器将碳粉从固体热载体中分离出来；5)将产生的热解气体输送到冷凝液罐进行喷雾冷凝，冷凝热解气体中的可冷凝部分产生生物燃料油，高压油泵对产生的生物燃料油加压，送入气化炉气化；6)将一部分不可冷凝的热解气体送入燃烧床与空气一起燃烧，另一部分不可冷凝的热解气体作为流化介质输送到热解床。', p.abstract_en = 'A method for producing synthesis gas,  including :  1) pre-processing a biomass raw material;  2) pyrolyzing the biomass raw material to yield a pyrolysis gas and a carbon powder;  3) separating the pyrolysis gas from the carbon powder and a solid heat carrier;  4) separating the carbon powder away from the solid heat carrier via a solid-solid separator;  5) conveying the generated pyrolysis gas to a condensate tank for spray condensation,  condensing a condensable part in the pyrolysis gas to generate biological fuel oil,  pressurizing the generated biological fuel oil by a high pressure oil pump and feeding to a gasification furnace to be gasified;  and 6) feeding one part of non-condensable pyrolysis gas to a combustion bed to combust with air,  and conveying the other part of the non-condensable pyrolysis gas to the pyrolysis bed as a fluidizing medium.', p.application_date = '2012-09-24 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9249358B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/36', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US13497730'}) SET p.application_no = 'US13497730', p.title_cn = '氢生成装置、燃料电池系统和氢生成装置操作方法', p.title_en = 'Hydrogen generation apparatus,  fuel cell system,  and hydrogen generation apparatus operation method', p.abstract_cn = '一种氢气发生装置(150)，包括 : 第一脱硫器(13)，其被配置为通过吸附除去要供应到重整器的原料气体中的硫化合物； 第二脱硫器(21)，所述第二脱硫器(21)被配置为加氢脱硫将被供应到重整器的原料气体中的硫化合物； 第一通道(16)，原料气体通过该第一通道(16)通过第一脱硫器(13)供应到重整器； 第二通道(17)，原料气体通过第二脱硫器(21)供给重整器，而不通过第一脱硫器(13)； 开关，其被配置为在所述第一通道(16)和所述第二通道(17)之间切换所述原料气体流过的通道； 和一个控制器。 所述控制器控制所述开关，使得所述原料气体在压力补偿操作和原料气体吹扫操作中的至少一个中流过所述第一通道(16)，所述压力补偿操作是供应所述原料气体以补偿在停止产生含氢气体的操作之后发生的内部压降的操作，并且所述原料气体吹扫操作是用所述原料气体吹扫所述氢气产生装置内部的操作。', p.abstract_en = 'A hydrogen generation apparatus (150) includes :  a first desulfurizer (13) configured to remove,  through adsorption,  a sulfur compound in a raw material gas that is to be supplied to a reformer;  a second desulfurizer (21) configured to hydrodesulfurize a sulfur compound in the raw material gas that is to be supplied to the reformer;  a first passage (16) through which the raw material gas is supplied to the reformer through the first desulfurizer (13);  a second passage (17) through which the raw material gas is supplied to the reformer through the second desulfurizer (21),  without passing through the first desulfurizer (13);  a switch configured to switch a passage through which the raw material gas flows between the first passage (16) and the second passage (17);  and a controller. The controller controls the switch such that the raw material gas flows through the first passage (16) in at least one of a pressure compensation operation and a raw material gas purge operation,  the pressure compensation operation being an operation of supplying the raw material gas in order to compensate for an internal pressure drop that occurs after an operation of generating a hydrogen-containing gas is stopped,  and the raw material gas purge operation being an operation of purging the inside of the hydrogen generation apparatus with the raw material gas.', p.application_date = '2010-12-24 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9252443B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 3, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'DE602010034684'}) SET p.application_no = 'DE602010034684', p.title_cn = '水煤气转换反应过程', p.title_en = 'WATER GAS SHIFT REACTION PROCESS', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种提高氢气含量的合成气含有氢和碳氧化物和具有碳≧CO的含量45摩尔%的干气的基础上，包括以下步骤 : (i)将合成气与蒸汽形成富蒸汽进料气体混合物(Ⅱ)中使原料气体混合物在220-370℃范围内的温度下在铁基水-气变换催化剂形成富含氢气的气体混合物，其具有一氧化碳含量10摩尔%的干气的基础上，和(iii)回收所述富含氢气的气体混合物，其中富含氢气的气体混合物的一部分再循环到进料气体混合物。', p.abstract_en = 'A process for increasing the hydrogen content of a synthesis gas including hydrogen and carbon oxides and having a carbon monoxide content ≧45 mole % on a dry-gas basis,  including the steps of :  (i) combining the synthesis gas with steam to form a steam-enriched feed gas mixture (ii) passing the feed gas mixture at an inlet temperature in the range 220-370° C. over an iron-based water-gas shift catalyst to form a hydrogen-enriched shifted gas mixture having a carbon monoxide content 10 mole % on a dry gas basis,  and (iii) recovering the hydrogen-enriched shifted gas mixture,  where a portion of the hydrogen-enriched shifted gas mixture is recycled to the feed gas mixture.', p.application_date = '2010-10-14 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'DE602010034684T2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/32', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2014139172'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2014139172', p.title_cn = 'CO选择性甲烷化反应器', p.title_en = 'CO SELECTIVE METHANIZATION REACTOR', p.abstract_cn = '提供一种CO选择性甲烷化反应器，即使在入口CO浓度较高的情况下，也能够将出口CO浓度长期维持在较低值。根据本发明，提供了一种用于使含有CO和CO2的富氢气体中的CO甲烷化的CO选择性甲烷化反应器，其中该反应器从CO选择性甲烷化反应器内的富氢气体流的上游侧依次包括前级催化剂和后级催化剂，并且所述前级催化剂在入口CO浓度为0.5%时具有比后级催化剂高的最佳工作温度。精选图纸：图4版权所有：(C)2016，JPO&INPIT', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To provide a CO selective methanization reactor that can maintain the outlet CO concentration at a lower value over a long period of time even for the case where the inlet CO concentration is high. SOLUTION :  According to the present invention,  provided is a CO selective methanization reactor for methanizing CO in a hydrogen rich gas containing CO and CO2 and in which the reactor includes a front stage catalyst and a rear stage catalyst in order from the upstream side of the hydrogen rich gas flow within the CO selective methanization reactor and said front stage catalyst has an optimal working temperature at inlet CO concentration of 0.5% higher than the rear stage catalyst. SELECTED DRAWING :  Figure 4 COPYRIGHT :  (C)2016, JPO&INPIT', p.application_date = '2014-07-04 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP2016017004A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2015548775'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2015548775', p.title_cn = '一种吸氢微丸', p.title_en = 'A hydrogen absorbing pellet', p.abstract_cn = '在涂布的小球氢吸留，所述含有氢储存材料，涂层，小于平均厚度50μm的包括氢渗透聚合物。选择的绘图 : 图。1', p.abstract_en = 'A coated hydrogen storage pellet;  wherein the pellet comprises a hydrogen-storage material;  the coating comprises a hydrogen-permeable polymer and the coating has a mean thickness of less than 50 μm.', p.application_date = '2013-12-20 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP2016502968A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'TW102145763'}) SET p.application_no = 'TW102145763', p.title_cn = '使用触媒床制造氰化氢之方法', p.title_en = 'PROCESSES FOR PRODUCING HYDROGEN CYANIDE USING CATALYST BED', p.abstract_cn = '本发明系关於制造氰化氢之经改良反应器及方法，其包括触媒床，该触媒床包含波纹触媒支撑件及用以贴合该波纹触媒支撑件之波形之针织触媒', p.abstract_en = 'An improved reactor and process for hydrogen cyanide production,  including a catalyst bed comprising a corrugated catalyst support and a knitted catalyst to conform to the wave shape of the corrugated catalyst support.', p.application_date = '2013-12-12 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'TWI519470B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'EA200900734'}) SET p.application_no = 'EA200900734', p.title_cn = '用于生产合成气的方法', p.title_en = 'PROCESS FOR PRODUCING SYNTHESIS GAS', p.abstract_cn = '生产合成气的方法(70)通过催化自热重整处理的进料气体流(50)。含有烃，与获得部分转化的气体(65)和合成气(70)，其特征在于 : 它包括操作步骤 : 一种混合第第一部分(23)的进料气体流(50)，其包括与气态烃流(60)包含氧，将得到的混合物部分燃烧，与获得的气体流(25)的至少部分燃烧气体，一种混合第第二部分(55)的气体的含烃流体与气态流(25)的至少部分燃烧气体，有利地，以得到稀释的烃的浓度存在于其中并将得到的混合物转化(14)在气相中于所述的催化自热重整，(14)，从而防止形成烟炱。', p.abstract_en = 'A process for producing synthesis gas (70) by means of catalytic autothermal reforming treatment of a feed gaseous flow (50) comprising hydrocarbons,  with the obtainment of partially transformed gas (65) and synthesis gas (70),  is characterized in that it comprises the operative steps of :  mixing a first portion (23) of the feed gaseous flow (50) comprising hydrocarbons with a gaseous flow (60) comprising oxygen,  subjecting the resulting mixture to partial combustion,  with the obtainment of a gaseous flow (25) of at least partially combusted gases,  mixing a second portion (55) of the gaseous flow comprising hydrocarbons with the gaseous flow (25) of at least partially combusted gases,  so as to advantageously attain a dilution of the concentration of the hydrocarbons present therein and feeding the resulting mixture of reforming (14a) in gaseous phase to the said catalytic autothermal reforming (14b),  so preventing the formation of soot.', p.application_date = '2007-11-21 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'EA22439B1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'EA201390286'}) SET p.application_no = 'EA201390286', p.title_cn = '方法和装置用于生产工艺蒸气和锅炉给水水蒸气的可加热重整反应器中生产合成气', p.title_en = 'METHOD AND DEVICE FOR PRODUCING PROCESS VAPOR AND BOILER FEED STEAM IN A HEATABLE REFORMING REACTOR FOR PRODUCING SYNTHESIS GAS', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种生产工艺蒸气和锅炉给水水蒸气的方法中的可加热重整反应器生产合成气的方法。通过根据本发明的方法，从烃类生产合成气的显热及蒸汽可以使两种蒸汽得到，其加热和蒸发过程中产生锅炉给水和工艺冷凝液，并且其中该方法还包括变换的合成气中所含的一氧化碳，并且其中所述方法包括任选地加热的锅炉给水利用烟道气从加热所述重整反应器。通过该方法，所述的合成气显热的烟道气来自加热可用于多种高效，其中，从烟气加热的缺点，其引起的波动的供热烟道气管道中，避免。本发明还涉及一种系统，通过该方法可以进行。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a method for producing process vapor and boiler feed steam in a heatable reforming reactor for producing synthesis gas. By means of the method according to the invention,  the sensible heat of a synthesis gas produced from hydrocarbons and steam can be used so that two types of vapor are obtained,  which are producing during the heating and evaporation of boiler feed water and process condensate,  and wherein the method also comprises a conversion of the carbon monoxide contained in the synthesis gas,  and wherein the method comprises an optional heating of the boiler feed water using the flue gas from the heating of the reforming reactor. By means of the method,  the sensible heat of the synthesis gas and of the flue gas originating from the heating can be used more efficiently,  wherein the disadvantages from the flue gas heating,  which are caused by the fluctuating heat supply in the flue gas duct,  are avoided. The invention further relates to a system by means of which said method can be carried out.', p.application_date = '2011-08-20 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'EA22467B1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/34', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'KR1020080052526'}) SET p.application_no = 'KR1020080052526', p.title_cn = '方法和装置用于分离氢的气体进出的流量使用交变压力吸附法', p.title_en = 'METHOD AND DEVICE FOR SEPARATING HYDROGEN OUT OF GAS FLOWS USING ALTERNATING PRESSURE ADSORPTION METHOD', p.abstract_cn = '该方法用于分离氢从具有氧的气体流， 氢， 氮， 二氧化碳， 一氧化碳， 甲烷和/或其它烃， 包括预加热热交换器上方气体的流动， 热转化氧无催化剂在300-500[℃]C， 分离出的氢气压力变化吸附过程， 和将分离的氢气催化除氧的方法。 与氧气的气体流处理部超过1体积。%的压力变化吸附 工艺。 独立权利要求包括用于装置用于分离氢从具有氧的气体流， 氢气，氮气，二氧化碳，一氧化碳，甲烷和/或其它烃类。', p.abstract_en = 'The method for the separation of hydrogen from a gas flow having oxygen,  hydrogen,  nitrogen,  carbon dioxide,  carbon monoxide,  methane and/or other hydrocarbons,  comprises pre-heating the gas flow over a heat exchanger,  thermally converting oxygen without catalyst at 300-500[deg] C,  separating hydrogen by a pressure change adsorption process,  and subjecting the separated hydrogen to a catalytic process for the removal of oxygen. The gas flow is processed with an oxygen portion of more than 1 vol.% by the change in pressure adsorption process. An independent claim is included for a device for the separation of hydrogen from a gas flow having oxygen,  hydrogen,  nitrogen,  carbon dioxide,  carbon monoxide,  methane and/or other hydrocarbons.', p.application_date = '2008-06-04 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'KR101591690B1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/50', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'PL09762737'}) SET p.application_no = 'PL09762737', p.title_cn = '一种利用生物质生产氢气的方法及设备', p.title_en = 'METHOD AND EQUIPMENT FOR PRODUCING HYDROGEN GAS UTILIZING BIOMASS', p.abstract_cn = '一种从生物质生产氢气的方法和设备，包括生物质的干燥，生物质的气化和水煤气转换反应阶段。 该方法还包括 : 使来自气化阶段的排出气体(CO[2]，N[2]和H[2]O)进行第一热交换，其中排出气体被冷却； 利用排出气体的热量蒸发水； 使蒸汽进行热交换，其中蒸汽被加热； 将蒸汽还原成合成气，其中冷却合成气并加热供给气化的空气； 将合成气分离成氢气流和一氧化碳流； 一氧化碳与水蒸汽反应生成一氧化碳和氢气； 还将这些次级流分离成氢气流和一氧化碳流； 以及将所述伯和仲氢气流合并成产物流。', p.abstract_en = 'A method and equipment for producing hydrogen from biomass includes the stages of drying of the biomass,  gasification of the biomass,  and water gas shift reaction. The method further includes :  subjecting the outgoing gases (CO2,  N2 and H2O) from the gasification stage to a first heat exchange,  wherein the outgoing gases are cooled;  evaporating water with heat from outgoing gases;  subjecting the steam to heat exchange wherein the steam is heated;  reducing the steam to synthesis gas,  wherein the synthesis gas is cooled and the air supply to the gasification is heated;  separating the synthesis gas into a hydrogen stream and a carbon monoxide stream;  reacting the carbon monoxide with water steam to carbon monoxide and hydrogen;  separating also these secondary streams into a hydrogen stream and a carbon monoxide stream;  and bringing together the primary and secondary hydrogen stream into a product stream.', p.application_date = '2009-06-11 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'PL2291492T3', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/16', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'PL09772087'}) SET p.application_no = 'PL09772087', p.title_cn = 'HTS反应器的操作方法', p.title_en = 'PROCESS FOR OPERATING HTS REACTOR', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种通过一氧化碳和蒸汽在含有锌和铝的氧化物以及一种或多种选自Na，K，Rb，Cs，Cu，Ti，Zr，稀土元素及其混合物的促进剂的催化剂上转化来富集氢气中的合成气的方法。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a process for enriching a synthesis gas in hydrogen by conversion of carbon monoxide and steam over a catalyst containing oxides of zinc and aluminum together with one or more promoters selected from Na,  K,  Rb,  Cs,  Cu,  Ti,  Zr,  rare earth elements and mixtures thereof.', p.application_date = '2009-06-15 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'PL2300359T3', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/16', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'PL12734811'}) SET p.application_no = 'PL12734811', p.title_cn = '生产合成气的方法', p.title_en = 'PROCESS FOR PRODUCTION OF SYNTHESIS GAS', p.abstract_cn = '一种生产合成气(3)的方法，其中将甲烷和二氧化碳(2)引入反应空间(R)中，并在固体(W)存在下在高温下反应以产生氢气和一氧化碳。 甲烷和二氧化碳通过含碳颗粒材料(W)并在高温区(H)中反应。', p.abstract_en = 'Process for the production of synthesis gas (3),  in which methane and carbon dioxide (2) are introduced into a reaction space (R) and reacted in the presence of a solid (W) at elevated temperatures to give hydrogen and carbon monoxide. Methane and carbon dioxide are passed through a carbon-containing granular material (W) and reacted in a high-temperature zone (H).', p.application_date = '2012-07-05 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'PL2729405T3', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/34', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'UZIAP20140289'}) SET p.application_no = 'UZIAP20140289', p.title_cn = '将二氧化碳转化为一氧化碳的方法和系统', p.title_en = 'Method and system for converting carbon dioxide into carbon monoxide', p.abstract_cn = '使用领域：石油和天然气行业。任务：提供一种CO2转化方法，其中该方法应适用于工业过程中二氧化碳释放量的有效回收和所需化工产品的生产。本发明的实质：提出了根据本发明的使用烃将CO2二氧化碳转变成CO一氧化碳的方法和装置。在本发明的另外的变型中，描述了使用CO2和烃生产合成气的方法和装置以及将合成气转化成合成官能化和/或非官能化烃的方法和装置。这些方法和装置适用于改变工业过程中排放的CO2，从而减少释放到大气中的二氧化碳量。', p.abstract_en = 'Field of use :  oil and gas industry. Task :  to provide a CO2 conversion method,  in which this method should be suitable for the efficient recovery of the amount of carbon dioxide released in industrial processes and for the production of required chemical products. The essence of the invention :  a method and a device for changing CO2 carbon dioxide into CO carbon monoxide using hydrocarbons according to the invention are proposed.In additional variants of the invention,  a method and device for producing synthesis gas using CO2 and hydrocarbons and a method and device for converting synthesis gas into synthetically functionalized and/or non-functionalized hydrocarbons are described. These methods and devices are suitable for changing the CO2 emitted during industrial processes,  thus reducing the amount of carbon dioxide released into the atmosphere.', p.application_date = '2012-12-20 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'UZIAP20140289B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/24', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'DE502012005488'}) SET p.application_no = 'DE502012005488', p.title_cn = '分切装置的化学化合物，和相关的方法', p.title_en = 'DEVICE FOR SPLITTING A CHEMICAL COMPOUND,  AND ASSOCIATED METHOD', p.abstract_cn = '分切装置的化学化合物(3)，包括温度控制装置(4)，两独立气室(6，7)，和元件(8)包括热释电材料，具有至少两个表面(10，11)具有不同的电荷的极性，并至少部分地接触所述化学化合物的被分体式。至少两个表面(10，11)每面一个所述分开的气室(6，7)，和气体(12)，13)在表面(10，11)分别到达气室与各自的相关表面(10，11)。', p.abstract_en = 'Device for splitting a chemical compound (3),  comprising a temperature control device (4),  two separate gas chambers (6,  7),  and an element (8) which comprises a pyroelectric material and has at least two surfaces (10,  11) that have charges of different polarity and are at least partially in contact with the chemical compound to be split. At least two of the surfaces (10,  11) each face one of the separate gas chambers (6,  7),  and the gases (12,  13) produced on the surfaces (10,  11) separately reach the gas chamber associated with the respective surface (10,  11).', p.application_date = '2012-02-07 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'DE502012005488T2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'DE602009035278'}) SET p.application_no = 'DE602009035278', p.title_cn = '生产氨的方法和设备使补充合成气与空气分离单元为氮源', p.title_en = 'PROCESS AND EQUIPMENT FOR THE PRODUCTION OF AMMONIA MAKE-UP SYNGAS WITH AN AIR SEPARATION UNIT AS NITROGEN SOURCE', p.abstract_cn = '一种方法和一种用于生产化妆合成气(6)用于氨的合成，其中烃原料在主重整器(10)和在自热重整器(14)在平行于所述初级重整器；氮由空气分离单元(13)，和O2的富氧空气(8)中产生的所述空气分离装置被供给至自热重整器中。一种方法用于改造的氨厂的前端还公开了。', p.abstract_en = 'A process and a plant for producing a makeup synthesis gas (6) for the synthesis of ammonia where a hydrocarbon feedstock is reformed in a primary reformer (10) and in an autothermal reformer (14) in parallel with said primary reformer;  nitrogen is furnished by an air separation unit (13),  and O 2 -enriched air (8) produced in said air separation unit is fed to the autothermal reformer. A method for the revamping of the front-end of an ammonia plant is also disclosed.', p.application_date = '2009-10-09 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'DE602009035278T2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'HU1400227'}) SET p.application_no = 'HU1400227', p.title_cn = '从金属硼氢化物制氢过程与催化剂，通过水解', p.title_en = 'Process for producing hydrogen from metal borohydride with catalyst by hydrolysis', p.abstract_cn = '', p.abstract_en = '', p.application_date = '2014-05-06 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'HU1400227A2', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/08', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2014135517'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2014135517', p.title_cn = '生产氢气的供给', p.title_en = 'METHOD FOR PRODUCING HYDROGEN DONOR', p.abstract_cn = '要解决的问题 : 甲烷水合物为原料，利用得到的氢供氢体可高效地制造可抑制排气量的二氧化碳生产供氢。溶液 : 该甲烷水合物和回收甲烷从甲烷的回收方法，沼气中的甲烷回收方法和含氧气体反应，含一氧化碳和氢气的合成气得到，转化步骤，重整方法和合成气中所含的水通过使一氧化碳，含氢和二氧化碳气体得到变换反应步骤，转移反应，得到的氢通过一种方法包括二氧化碳和二氧化碳分离 arating方法从气体二氧化碳，二氧化碳和二氧化碳arating过程中分离d含氢气体和氢气供给氢存储体得到的加氢方法，二氧化碳分离 arating阶段的甲烷回收方法中循环二氧化碳的二氧化碳回收过程使用二氧化碳和甲烷和氢气的供给与循环工艺。选择的绘图 : 图。1', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To provide a method for producing a hydrogen donor which enables efficient production of a hydrogen donor by using hydrogen obtained from methane hydrate as a raw material,  and can reduce carbon dioxide emissions. SOLUTION :  The method for producing a hydrogen donor comprises :  a methane recovery step of recovering methane from methane hydrate by using carbon dioxide;  a modification step of obtaining a synthesis gas containing hydrogen and carbon monoxide by reacting methane recovered in the methane recovery step with a gas containing oxygen;  a shift reaction step of obtaining a gas containing hydrogen and carbon dioxide by reacting carbon monoxide contained in the synthesis gas obtained in the modification step with water;  a carbon dioxide separation step of separating carbon dioxide from the gas containing hydrogen and carbon dioxide obtained in the shift reaction step;  a hydrogenation step of obtaining a hydrogen donor by reacting the gas from which carbon dioxide has been separated in the carbon dioxide separation step and which contains hydrogen,  with a hydrogen storage body;  and a carbon dioxide circulation step of circulating carbon dioxide separated in the carbon dioxide separation step into the methane recovery step to serve as carbon dioxide used in the methane recovery step. COPYRIGHT :  (C)2016, JPO&INPIT', p.application_date = '2014-07-01 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP2016013937A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'MYPI2011004931'}) SET p.application_no = 'MYPI2011004931', p.title_cn = '用于从废气体中隔离二氧化碳的方法和设备', p.title_en = 'METHOD AND APPARATUS FOR SEQUESTERING CARBON DIOXIDE FROM A SPENT GAS', p.abstract_cn = '一种用于从废气中封存二氧化碳并将其作为再循环气体再利用而没有排放问题的方法和设备，包括：给定被分成工艺气体和废气的气体源：将工艺气体与烃混合，并将所得进料气体进料到重整器(24)中，用于重整进料气体并形成还原气体; 以及将至少一部分废气送入二氧化碳洗涤器(28)，用于从废气中除去至少一些二氧化碳，并形成与还原气体混合的贫二氧化碳气体。任选地，该方法还包括将废气的至少一部分供给到二氧化碳洗涤器(28)中，以从废气中除去至少一些二氧化碳，并在添加烃之后形成燃料气体，烃被供给到重整器(24)中。任选地，所述气源和所述还原气体与用于在还原炉中将氧化铁转化为金属铁的直接还原工艺相关联，所述还原炉任选地在一些改性之后利用所述还原气体并产生所述气源。图1', p.abstract_en = 'A METHOD AND APPARATUS FOR SEQUESTERING CARBON DIOXIDE FROM A WASTE GAS AND REUSING IT AS A RECYCLED GAS WITHOUT EMISSIONS CONCERNS,  INCLUDING :  GIVEN A GAS SOURCE DIVIDED INTO A PROCESS GAS AND A WASTE GAS :  MIXING THE PROCESS GAS WITH A HYDROCARBON AND FEEDING A RESULTING FEED GAS INTO A REFORMER (24) FOR REFORMING THE FEED GAS AND FORMING A REDUCING GAS;  AND FEEDING AT LEAST A PORTION OF THE WASTE GAS INTO A CARBON DIOXIDE SCRUBBER (28) FOR REMOVING AT LEAST SOME CARBON DIOXIDE FROM THE WASTE GAS AND FORMING A CARBON DIOXIDE LEAN GAS THAT IS MIXED WITH THE REDUCING GAS. OPTIONALLY,  THE METHOD ALSO INCLUDES FEEDING AT LEAST A PORTION OF THE WASTE GAS INTO THE CARBON DIOXIDE SCRUBBER (28) FOR REMOVING AT LEAST SOME CARBON DIOXIDE FROM THE WASTE GAS AND FORMING A FUEL GAS AFTER THE ADDITION OF A HYDROCARBON THAT IS FED INTO THE REFORMER (24). OPTIONALLY,  THE GAS SOURCE AND THE REDUCING GAS ARE ASSOCIATED WITH A DIRECT REDUCTION PROCESS FOR CONVERTING IRON OXIDE TO METALLIC IRON IN A REDUCTION FURNACE THAT UTILIZES THE REDUCING GAS,  OPTIONALLY AFTER SOME MODIFICATION,  AND PRODUCES THE GAS SOURCE. FIGURE 1', p.application_date = '2010-04-19 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'MY155610A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'MYPI2011005033'}) SET p.application_no = 'MYPI2011005033', p.title_cn = '合成气共混物的生产及其在费-托法中的用途', p.title_en = 'PRODUCTION OF A SYNTHESIS GAS BLEND AND USE IN A FISCHER-TROPSCH PROCESS', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种用于由包含甲烷的原料生产烃产物的方法，其包括以下步骤：-在合成气制造方法中制备包含具有氢气/一氧化碳摩尔进料比的氢气和一氧化碳的进料合成气，和-在费-托法中使用所述进料合成气，所述费-托法使用存在于一个或多个合成气转化反应器中的一个或多个固定床催化剂床，从而获得所述烃产物和残余尾气。-所述制造工艺包括两个并行操作的合成气制造工艺，所述两个并行操作的合成气制造工艺从相同的包含气态甲烷的原料开始。-一种合成气制造工艺是部分氧化(POX)工艺，其制备具有低于摩尔进料比的氢/一氧化碳[H？/CO]摩尔比的合成气，和-第二合成气制造工艺是热交换重整(HER)工艺，其制备具有高于摩尔进料比的氢/一氧化碳[H？/CO]摩尔比的合成气。', p.abstract_en = 'THE INVENTION IS DIRECTED TO A PROCESS FOR THE PRODUCTION OF HYDROCARBON PRODUCTS FROM A METHANE COMPRISING FEEDSTOCK COMPRISING OF THE STEPS OF :  - PREPARING A FEED SYNGAS COMPRISING HYDROGEN AND CARBON MONOXIDE HAVING A HYDROGEN/CARBON MONOXIDE MOLAR FEED RATIO IN A SYNGAS MANUFACTURING PROCESS AND - USING THE FEED SYNGAS IN A FISCHER-TROPSCH PROCESS USING ONE OR MORE FIXED BED CATALYST BEDS AS PRESENT IN ONE OR MORE SYNGAS CONVERSION REACTORS THEREBY OBTAINING THE HYDROCARBON PRODUCT AND AN RESIDUAL TAIL GAS. - THE MANUFACTURING PROCESS COMPRISES OF TWO PARALLEL OPERATED SYNGAS MANUFACTURING PROCESSES STARTING FROM THE SAME GASEOUS METHANE COMPRISING FEEDSTOCK. - ONE SYNGAS MANUFACTURING PROCESS IS A PARTIAL OXIDATION (POX) PROCESS WHICH PREPARES A SYNGAS HAVING A HYDROGEN/CARBON MONOXIDE [H?/CO] MOLAR RATIO BELOW THE MOLAR FEED RATIO AND - THE SECOND SYNGAS MANUFACTURING PROCESS IS A HEAT EXCHANGE REFORMING (HER) PROCESS,  WHICH PREPARES A SYNGAS HAVING A HYDROGEN/CARBON MONOXIDE [H?/CO] MOLAR RATIO ABOVE THE MOLAR FEED RATIO.', p.application_date = '2010-04-20 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'MY155715A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14389683'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14389683', p.title_cn = '用于将醇转化为包括氢的气体混合物的醇重整器', p.title_en = 'Alcohol Reformer for Reforming Alcohol to Mixture of Gas Including Hydrogen', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种重整酒精。 将醇引入到醇重整器的导管中，使得醇流过导管内的催化剂级。 催化剂级包括醇重整催化剂和包括导热材料的传热构件。 传热构件与导管和醇重整催化剂热接触。 同时，废气从内燃机引入排气通道。 排气通道中的排气接触从导管向外延伸的翅片，使得来自排气的热量通过翅片、导管和传热构件传递到醇重整催化剂。', p.abstract_en = 'Reforming alcohol is disclosed. Alcohol is introduced into a conduit of an alcohol reformer so that the alcohol flows through a catalyst stage within the conduit. The catalyst stage includes an alcohol reforming catalyst,  and a heat transfer member comprising thermally conductive material. The heat transfer member is in thermal contact with the conduit and the alcohol reforming catalyst. Simultaneously,  exhaust gas is introduced from an internal combustion engine into an exhaust channel. The exhaust gas in the exhaust channel contacts fins extending outward from the conduit so that heat from the exhaust gas is transferred through the fins,  the conduit,  and the heat transfer member to the alcohol reforming catalyst.', p.application_date = '2013-03-29 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US20160023898A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/22', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 3, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WOGB15050980'}) SET p.application_no = 'WOGB15050980', p.title_cn = '储存气体的方法，特别是氢', p.title_en = 'METHOD OF STORING A GAS,  IN PARTICULAR HYDROGEN', p.abstract_cn = '我们描述了一种储存气体的方法，特别是氢，包括 : 提供聚合物海绵，其中所述聚合物海绵，包括多个催化纳米粒子；提供一种反应物的溶液，催化被所述纳米粒子以产生所述气体；吸收所述溶液加入到所述聚合物海绵，使得所述所述聚合物海绵内的反应物反应产生所述的气体；其中所述的气体保持在所述聚合物海绵；和其中所述聚合物海绵，包括一热响应高分子具有体积减少与温度的变化，使得所述的气体保持在所述聚合物可通过改变温度的所述聚合物海绵。', p.abstract_en = 'We describe a method of storing a gas,  in particular hydrogen,  comprising :  providing a polymer sponge,  wherein said polymer sponge comprises a plurality of catalytic nanoparticles;  providing a solution of reactants,  catalysed by said nanoparticles to produce said gas;  absorbing said solution into said polymer sponge such that said reactants react within said polymer sponge to produce said gas;  wherein said gas is held within said polymer sponge;  and wherein said polymer sponge comprises a thermally responsive polymer having a volume which reduces with a change in temperature,  such that said gas held within said polymer is extractable by changing a temperature of said polymer sponge.', p.application_date = '2015-03-31 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2015150777A3', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WOAT15050177'}) SET p.application_no = 'WOAT15050177', p.title_cn = '用于生产氢的方法', p.title_en = 'METHOD FOR PRODUCING HYDROGEN', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种装置用于制造压缩氢，包括耐压反应器(1)与反应器腔室具有一含金属的接触物质(2)，所述反应器(1)包括至少一个给料管线(3)用于将流体输送到反应器室，至少一个放电线(4)，用于从反应器排出流体的室，所述至少一个排放管路上设有装置(5a，5b，5C，5d)用于控制或调节流量，优选具有阀，用于调节反应器内的压力室，所述输送单元设置在至少一个含进给管线用于将水介质引入反应器室中，并且其中至少一个排出管道(4)伸入到所述反应室或直接通到所反应器室，通过压缩氢气从反应器排出室，所述反应器室具有至少两个区域被彼此分离和连接在气体导通方式，的至少一个区域包括含金属的接触物质(2)和至少一个附加区域包括至少一个惰性材料(7，13)。', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention relates to a device for producing compressed hydrogen,  comprising a pressure-resistant reactor (1) with a reactor chamber having a metal-containing contact mass (2),  wherein the reactor (1) comprises at least one feed line (3) for feeding fluids into the reactor chamber and at least one discharge line (4) for discharging fluids from the reactor chamber,  wherein the at least one discharge line is provided with a device (5a,  5b,  5c,  5d) for controlling or regulating the flow rate,  preferably having a valve,  for adjusting the pressure within the reactor chamber,  wherein a conveyance means is provided on at least one feed line for introducing a water-containing medium into the reactor chamber and wherein at least one discharge line (4) protrudes into the reactor chamber or opens directly into the reactor chamber,  through which the compressed hydrogen is discharged from the reactor chamber,  wherein the reactor chamber exhibits at least two areas that are separate from each other and connected in a gas-conducting manner,  of which at least one area comprises the metal-containing contact mass (2) and at least one additional area comprises at least one inert material (7,  13).', p.application_date = '2015-07-27 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016011473A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/06', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WOCA15050686'}) SET p.application_no = 'WOCA15050686', p.title_cn = '利用生物方法二氧化碳衍生自非化石有机材料', p.title_en = 'PROCESS FOR USING BIOGENIC CARBON DIOXIDE DERIVED FROM NON-FOSSIL ORGANIC MATERIAL', p.abstract_cn = '本发明提供了一种方法，用于形成生物碳基燃料或燃料中间体从生物碳二氧化碳和氢气。来源于氢的方法，产生氢气和化石二氧化碳从化石燃料烃分离化石二氧化碳从氢。该方法可以进一步包括进行或安排在一个或更多方进行至少一个步骤是 : 有助于减少温室气体排放的生物碳基燃料，或制成燃料从燃料中间，至少20%相对于汽油的基线。在各种实施例中，这包括 : (a)将化石地下的二氧化碳，和/或(b)利用生物碳基产品选自化学和能量生产的产品从非化石有机材料以置换的使用或生产对应的化石基产品。', p.abstract_en = 'The present disclosure provides a process for forming a biogenic carbon-based fuel or a fuel intermediate from biogenic carbon dioxide and hydrogen. The hydrogen is sourced from a process that produces hydrogen and fossil carbon dioxide from a fossil-fuel hydrocarbon and separates the fossil carbon dioxide from the hydrogen. The process may further comprise carrying out or arranging for one or more parties to carry out at least one step that contributes to a reduction in the GHG emissions of the biogenic carbon-based fuel,  or a fuel made from the fuel intermediate,  of at least 20% relative to a gasoline baseline. In various embodiments this includes (a) introducing the fossil carbon dioxide underground,  and/or (b) using a biogenic carbon-based product selected from a chemical and energy product produced from the non-fossil organic material to displace the use or production of a corresponding fossil-based product.', p.application_date = '2015-07-22 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016011554A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/34', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WOJP15071095'}) SET p.application_no = 'WOJP15071095', p.title_cn = '用于生产氢的方法从含氨氮废氨分解', p.title_en = 'METHOD FOR PRODUCING HYDROGEN FROM AMMONIA NITROGEN-CONTAINING WASTE BY AMMONIA DECOMPOSITION', p.abstract_cn = '本发明提供了一种氨分解制氢的方法的目的是提供一种方法，有效的利用废弃的含有氨氮和取氢能的氨水。该氨分解制氢的方法包括 : arating 分离 a步骤从废含氨的氨氮；浓缩步骤获得氨的水通过浓缩氨分离d 分离中的步骤；和氨分解步骤分解氨的水成氢和氮通过喷淋氨水在催化剂层。', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention provides a method for producing hydrogen by decomposing ammonia for the purpose of providing a method for effectively utilizing waste that contains ammonia nitrogen and taking a hydrogen energy out of ammonia water. This method for producing hydrogen by ammonia decomposition comprises :  a separation step for separating ammonia from waste that contains ammonia nitrogen;  a concentration step for obtaining ammonia water by concentrating the ammonia separated in the separation step;  and an ammonia decomposition step for decomposing the ammonia water into hydrogen and nitrogen by spraying the ammonia water on a catalyst layer.', p.application_date = '2015-07-24 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016013652A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201080012818.5'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201080012818.5', p.title_cn = '氢产生催化剂、氢产生方法、氢产生装置', p.title_en = 'Hydrogen generation catalyst,  hydrogen generation method,  hydrogen generation device', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种催化剂的寿命长，在低温下可以将水大量分离成氢和氧的氢产生用催化剂。该催化剂为如下催化剂：碱金属氢氧化物例如NaOH、KOH、碱土金属氢氧化物例如Ba(OH)2、Sr(OH)2的熔融盐中，熔融用于切断水蒸气的氢和氧之间的键的金属元素(Ni、Pd、Pt)，以及辅助该金属元素的元素(Cr、Mo、W、Fe、Co、Cu、Rh)，加热至所述氢氧化物的熔点以上，并使微粒群飞散在该熔融盐的液面上，与水蒸气进行接触。或者该催化剂为如下催化剂：使碱金属氢氧化物和金属氧化物混合，加热混合后的物质至碱金属氢氧化物的熔点以上，制作复合金属化合物，并在该复合金属化合物中熔入至少2种以上的金属元素，使微粒群从金属化合物表面飞散，与水蒸气进行接触。', p.abstract_en = 'There is provided a kind of catalyst which has a long life span and can separate efficiently hydrogen from water. A first metal element (Ni,  Pd,  Pt) for cutting the combination of hydrogen and oxygen and a second metal element (Cr,  Mo,  W,  Fe) for helping the function of the first metal element are melted in alkaline metal hydroxide such as NaOH and KOH or alkaline earth metal hydroxide such as Ba(OH) 2 and Sr(OH) 2 to make a mixture which is heated at a temperature above the melting point of the hydroxide to eject fine particles from the liquid surface so that steam is brought into contact with the fine particles. Instead of this,  a mixture of alkaline metal hydroxide and metal oxide is heated at a temperature above the melting point of the alkaline metal hydroxide to make metal compound in which at least two kinds of metal elements are melted,  and fine particles are ejected from the surface of the metal compound to be brought into contact with steam.', p.application_date = '2010-01-06 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN102369155B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/06', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201310686390.8'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201310686390.8', p.title_cn = '带星型微凸台阵列的层叠自热型醇类制氢微反应器', p.title_en = 'With star-shaped array of micro-boss system hydrogen micro reactor laminated self-heating of alcohol', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种带星型微凸台阵列结构的层叠自热型醇类制氢微反应器。反应器由上盖板、壳体和n层反应载体组成。反应载体具有双面的星型微凸台阵列，叠合形成各反应腔。在相邻的反应腔中，交替进行吸热和放热反应，以实现自热重整。气体的入口在上盖板上，通过不同的流道，进入到反应腔中进行反应，最后流出反应腔。在放热反应中，利用氢气等燃烧气体在放热腔内燃烧产生热量，通过金属反应板将热量传递到醇类重整的反应腔，以满足醇类制氢所需要的大量热量，实现自热重整制氢。本发明采用带有星型微凸台阵列的层叠式反应载体，减小了反应过程中的压降，提高了醇类反应的转化率和制氢效率，可以为氢燃料电池等提供足够的氢燃料。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention discloses a stacked self-heating alcohol hydrogen-production micro-reactor with a star-type micro-lug boss array. The reactor is composed of an upper cover board,  a shell and n layers of reaction carriers,  wherein reaction carriers comprise double-sided star-type micro-lug boss arrays,  which are stacked to form reaction cavities;  endothermic reaction and exothermic reaction are alternatively carried out in adjacent reaction cavities,  so as to form self-heating rearrangement. A gas inlet is formed in the upper cover board,  and gas enters the reaction cavities to react through different runners,  and finally flows out of the reaction cavities. Combustion gas such as hydrogen is utilized to burn inside a heating chamber to generate heat in the exothermic reaction,  and the heat is transmitted to the reaction cavity for alcohol rearrangement through a metal reaction plate,  so as to supply a lot of heat required for alcohol hydrogen-production. Thus,  self-heating arrangement hydrogen-production is realized. By adopting the stacked reaction carriers with the star-type micro-lug boss arrays,  a pressure drop in the reaction process is reduced,  the transformation rate and the hydrogen-production efficiency of the alcohol reaction are improved,  and enough hydrogen fuel can be provided for a hydrogen cell and the like.', p.application_date = '2013-12-16 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN103693617B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201510740558.8'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201510740558.8', p.title_cn = '光解水制氢装置及方法', p.title_en = 'Device and method for manufacturing hydrogen by photolyzing water', p.abstract_cn = '这种光解水制氢装置包括密封容器、光解水槽和外加电场三部分。它利用振荡电子近区场能量使水分解，制造氢气。密封容器用玻璃或透明塑料薄膜制成，密封容器内充满电子气。制氢时，光解水槽内充注水，密封容器一侧浸没在水中，另一侧受太阳光照射。在太阳光照射下，密封容器内电子作受迫振动，类似于振荡电偶极子，并将发射次级电磁波。在次级电磁波照射下，带正电氢原子和带负电氧原子将会作受迫振动，振荡氢原子和振荡氧原子处于彼此的近区场，当次级电磁波的电场强度方向与振荡氢原子和振荡氧原子的电矩在同一径向直线上且反向时，振荡氢原子和振荡氧原子之间产生径向排斥力，当径向排斥力大于带正电氢原子和带负电氧原子之间的吸引力时，氢氧键断裂，产生H+和O2-，外加电场使H+向负极移动生成H2，O2-向正极移动生成O2。', p.abstract_en = 'A device for manufacturing hydrogen by photolyzing water comprises three parts,  i.e. an airtight container,  a photolyzing water tank and an external electric field. The water is decomposed by the near-zone field energy of oscillating electrons to manufacture the hydrogen. The airtight container is made of glass or a transparent plastic thin film,  and electron gas is fully filled in the airtight container. During hydrogen production,  the water is filled into the photolyzing water tank,  and one side of the airtight container is soaked in the water,  and the other side of the airtight container is irradiated by sunlight. Under the irradiation of the sunlight,  the electrons in the airtight container are subjected to forced vibration like oscillating electric dipoles and about to emit secondary electromagnetic waves. Under irradiation of the secondary electromagnetic waves,  hydrogen atoms with positive charges and oxygen atoms with negative charges are subjected to forced vibration,  and the oscillating hydrogen atoms and the oscillating oxygen atoms are in respective near-zone fields of each other;  when the electric field intensity direction of the secondary electromagnetic waves,  the electric moment of the oscillating hydrogen atoms and the electric moment of the oscillating oxygen atoms are on the same radial straight line and are opposite in directions,  a radial repelling force is generated between the oscillating hydrogen atoms and the oscillating oxygen atoms;  when the radial repelling force is greater than the attracting force between the hydrogen atoms with positive charges and the oxygen atoms with negative charges,  oxyhydrogen bonds are broken,  H+ and O2- are generated,  the H+ is driven by the external electric field to move to the cathode to generate H2,  and the O2- is driven by the external electric field to move to the anode to generate O2.', p.application_date = '2015-10-28 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105271111A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201510680110.1'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201510680110.1', p.title_cn = '一种复合储氢材料及其制备方法', p.title_en = 'Composite hydrogen storage material and preparation method thereof', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种复合储氢材料及其制备方法，属于储氢材料技术领域。该复合储氢材料由硼氢化锂和非晶态镁-稀土-镍合金氢化物组成，两者的摩尔比为6～7 : 1，所述镁-稀土-镍合金为Mg10LaNi或Mg10SmNi。制备时，先以单质镁、稀土和镍为原料，通过熔炼和甩带工艺获得非晶态镁-稀土-镍合金，再通过球磨和低温氢化获得非晶态镁-稀土-镍合金氢化物，最后将硼氢化锂和非晶态镁-稀土-镍合金氢化物进行混合。本发明所提供的复合储氢材料具有低的放氢温度和高的放氢量，制备工艺简单，安全可靠。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention discloses a composite hydrogen storage material and a preparation method thereof and belongs to the technical field of hydrogen storage materials. The composite hydrogen storage material comprises lithium borohydride and amorphous-state magnesium-rare earth-nickel alloy hydride in the mole ratio being (6-7) : 1,  wherein a magnesium-rare earth-nickel alloy is Mg10LaNi or Mg10SmNi. During preparation,  elementary magnesium,  rare earth and nickel are taken as raw materials,  an amorphous-state magnesium-rare earth-nickel alloy is obtained through a smelting and melt-spinning technology,  amorphous-state magnesium-rare earth-nickel alloy hydride is obtained through ball milling and low-temperature hydrogenation,  and finally,  lithium borohydride and amorphous-state magnesium-rare earth-nickel alloy hydride are mixed. The provided composite hydrogen storage material has low hydrogen desorption temperature and high hydrogen desorption capacity,  and a preparation process is simple,  safe and reliable.', p.application_date = '2015-10-16 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105271113A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/08', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201510624663.5'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201510624663.5', p.title_cn = '带超声辅助汽化的重整制氢微反应器', p.title_en = 'Reforming hydrogen production micro-reactor with ultrasonic assisted vaporization', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种带超声辅助汽化的重整制氢微反应器。从下至上依次包括下盖板、蒸发单元、预热单元、重整制氢微反应单元和上盖板；从下至上依次组成雾化蒸发腔、预热腔、重整制氢反应腔和产物气体缓冲腔。本发明反应物液体通过进料孔进入雾化腔后在超声换能器的作用下雾化成飘逸气雾，使反应物分散均匀，雾化液滴接触蒸发单元后迅速吸热蒸发成气体，提高工质液体的蒸发效率；反应物液体雾化蒸发压强迅速增大，能减小反应器所需入口压力；调节超声换能器的功率达到调节重整反应腔入口气体流量的目的；通过超声波换能器的雾化作用，反应物液化蒸发过程连续，能显著减小重整制氢单元入口气体的流量脉动，提高反应腔内流速分布均匀度，提高反应效率。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention discloses a reforming hydrogen production micro-reactor with ultrasonic assisted vaporization. The reforming hydrogen production micro-reactor sequentially comprises a lower cover plate,  an evaporation unit,  a preheating unit,  a reforming hydrogen production micro-reaction unit and an upper cover plate from bottom to top;  and an atomization and evaporation chamber,  a preheating chamber,  a reforming hydrogen production reaction chamber and a product gas buffering chamber are sequentially formed from bottom to top. A reactant liquid goes through a material feeding hole,  enters the atomization chamber and is atomized under the action of an ultrasonic transducer to form flowing aerosol in order to uniformly disperse the reactant,  and atomized liquid drops are in contact with the evaporation unit and rapidly absorbs heat and evaporates to form a gas,  so the evaporation efficiency of a working medium liquid is improved;  the atomization and evaporation pressure of the reactant liquid is rapidly increased,  so the required inlet pressure of the reactor is reduced;  the power of the ultrasonic transducer is adjusted to adjust the flow amount of the gas at the inlet of the reforming reaction chamber;  and the reactant liquefaction and evaporation process is continuous through the atomization effect of the ultrasonic transducer,  so the flow fluctuation of the gas at the inlet of the reforming hydrogen production unit is substantially reduced,  the flow velocity distribution uniformity in the reaction chamber is improved,  and the reaction efficiency is improved.', p.application_date = '2015-09-25 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105271114A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/32', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201480034538.2'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201480034538.2', p.title_cn = '氧化反应中的烟灰控制', p.title_en = 'Soot control in oxidation reactions', p.abstract_cn = '通过控制氧化剂流的动量相对于含碳进料流的动量来控制在含碳进料的部分氧化中的烟灰形成。', p.abstract_en = 'Soot formation in the partial oxidation of carbonaceous feed is controlled by controlling the momentum of the oxidant stream relative to the momentum of the carbonaceous feed stream.', p.application_date = '2014-06-17 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105283411A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/36', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201520712114.9'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201520712114.9', p.title_cn = '合成氨二氧化碳脱出系统', p.title_en = 'Synthetic ammonia carbon dioxide deviates from system', p.abstract_cn = '本实用新型公开了一种合成氨二氧化碳脱出系统，包括低变气废锅炉、再生塔和吸收塔，再生塔的下部设有贫液回流管，贫液回流管的上端位于半贫液出口的下方，贫液回流管上设有再沸器，低变气废锅炉的低变气出口通过管道与再沸器的热源进口相连，再沸器的热源出口与换热器的热源进口相连，换热器的热源出口与水分离器相连，水分离器的气体出口与吸收塔的低变气进口相连；流量控制阀的出口设有三通，该三通其中一支管通过管道与再生塔中上部的洗涤段的冷凝液进口相连，再生塔洗涤段的溢流口通过冷凝液管道与低变气废锅的脱盐水进口相连，三通的另一支管通过管道与冷凝液管道相连，在该管道上设有阀门。能将余热充分合理利用，操作方便。', p.abstract_en = 'The utility model discloses a synthetic ammonia carbon dioxide deviates from system,  including low gas waste boiler stove,  regenerator column and the absorption tower of becoming,  the lower part of regenerator column is equipped with the lean solution back flow,  and the upper end of lean solution back flow is located the below of half lean solution export,  is equipped with the reboiler on the lean solution back flow,  and the low low change gas export that becomes gas waste boiler stove links to each other through the heat source import of pipeline with the reboiler,  and the heat source export of reboiler links to each other with the heat source import of heat exchanger,  and the heat source export of heat exchanger links to each other with water separator,  and water separator\'s gas outlet links to each other with the import of the low change gas on absorption tower,  flow control valve\'s export is equipped with the tee bend,  and the condensate import that the washing section on upper portion in pipeline and the regenerator column was crossed to one of them lateral duct of this tee bend links to each other,  and the overflow mouth of regenerator column washing section passes through the condensate pipeline and the low desalinized water import that becomes gas waste boiler links to each other,  and another lateral duct of three -way is crossed the pipeline and is linked to each other with the condensate pipeline,  is equipped with the valve on this pipeline. Can be with the abundant rational utilization of waste heat,  convenient operation.', p.application_date = '2015-09-15 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN204999608U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'EP09827373'}) SET p.application_no = 'EP09827373', p.title_cn = '操作氢气发生器的方法', p.title_en = 'Method of operating a hydrogen generator', p.abstract_cn = '氢发生器包括 : 重整器(102)，被配置为生成含氢气体的重整反应中使用原料；燃烧器(104)被配置为加热重整器；空气供给装置(106)，配置成供给燃烧空气的燃烧器；第第一热交换器(108)配置成从烟道排出的气体中回收热量从燃烧器；第第一热介质通道(110)通过第第一热介质流过，第一热介质接收从烟气中回收的热量第一热交换器；第第一泵(112)配置成使第一第一热介质通道中的热介质流动；蓄热体(140)被配置成存储由第一回收的热量的热介质；和控制器(114)配置成使第一泵上的冷却步骤中的操作步骤降温至少重整器供给空气从空气供应装置连接，以在燃烧器状态下，不进行燃烧的燃烧器停止期间处理', p.abstract_en = 'A hydrogen generator includes :  a reformer (102) configured to generate a hydrogen-containing gas by a reforming reaction using a raw material;  a combustor (104) configured to heat the reformer;  an air supplying device (106) configured to supply combustion air to the combustor;  a first heat exchanger (108) configured to recover heat from a flue gas discharged from the combustor;  a first heat medium passage (110) through which a first heat medium flows,  the first heat medium receiving the heat recovered from the flue gas in the first heat exchanger;  a first pump (112) configured to cause the first heat medium in the first heat medium passage to flow;  a heat accumulator (140) configured to store the heat recovered by the first heat medium;  and a controller (114) configured to cause the first pump to operate in a cooling step that is a step of cooling down at least the reformer by supplying the air from the air supplying device to the combustor in a state where the combustor is not carrying out combustion during a stop processing', p.application_date = '2009-11-20 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'EP2351703B1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'EP10765566'}) SET p.application_no = 'EP10765566', p.title_cn = '初级重整器具有可变的烟气流量', p.title_en = 'PRIMARY REFORMER HAVING VARIABLE SMOKE GAS FLOW', p.abstract_cn = '一种方法，公开了一种用于催化初级重整烃与蒸汽在升高的压力下通过分体管反应器和燃烧室。在分体式管系统，可以使用催化剂材料，待重整的烃水蒸汽转换合成气。分体式管系统由多个点火加热设施之间的分体式管包括多个串联布置燃烧器，燃烧器产生主要的向下指向的火焰。相关烧制设施提供与燃料和空气，与空气在被从相关送料器。烟道气体从而演化穿过所述烧制室从上至下进入下部区域中烧室中的水平设置的陶瓷烟气隧道彼此平行延伸并垂直于竖直分流管和被分配给一个烧制设施。烟气进入通过侧壁中的孔的烟气隧道。烟气在燃烧室的出口通入热回收装置。在每个烟气隧道的附加气体进入隧道的前侧，在烟气流动方向，所述含氧气体和非可燃气体，使得附加气体经过烟气隧道在整个长度的燃烧室。体积的附加气体通入到烟气隧道的调节。', p.abstract_en = 'A method is disclosed for catalytic primary reformation of hydrocarbons with steam at elevated pressure by means of a split tube reactor and a firing chamber. In the split tube system which can use a catalyst material,  hydrocarbons to be reformed are converted by water steam to synthesis gas. The split tube system is heated by a plurality of firing facilities between the split tubes which include a plurality of burners arranged in series,  the burners generating mainly downwardly directed flames. The relevant firing facilities are supplied with fuel and air,  with the air being withdrawn from the relevant feeders. The flue gas thus evolving passes through the firing chamber from top to bottom and enters in the lower area of the firing chamber into horizontally arranged ceramic flue gas tunnels extending in parallel to each other and perpendicular to the vertical split tubes and being allocated to one firing facility each. The flue gas enters through apertures in the lateral walls of the flue gas tunnels. The flue gas at the exit of the firing chamber is passed into heat recovery devices. In each flue gas tunnel an additional gas is fed into the tunnel\'s front side,  in flue gas flow direction,  wherein the gas containing oxygen and a non-combustible gas,  so that the additional gas passes the flue gas tunnels over the entire length of the firing chamber. The volume of the additional gas passed into the flue gas tunnels is regulated.', p.application_date = '2010-06-24 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'EP2445830B1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2011146959'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2011146959', p.title_cn = '制氢方法', p.title_en = 'Hydrogen production method', p.abstract_cn = '所要解决的问题是，在有效地使用乙醇制造氢的方法中，提供一种利用小型便携式设备以低能耗和低成本制造氢的方法。解决方案：制造氢的方法的特征在于，将空气或氮气和乙醇气体供给到大气等离子体发生器中，以分解乙醇分子而产生氢。 在大气等离子体发生器中，在等离子体反应器中的内部电极和等离子体反应器外部的外部电极之间施加高频波。 在等离子体反应器的内壁和内电极之间引发等离子体放电，并且使待处理气体与等离子体接触，通过等离子体激发和与等离子体区域的强制接触以及等离子体中和等离子体外的催化剂的活化的协同作用，待处理气体被分解。', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To provide a method for producing hydrogen with a small sized portable type of device at low energy consumption and low cost in a method of producing hydrogen using ethanol effectively.SOLUTION :  The method of producing hydrogen is characterized by supplying air or nitrogen gas and ethanol gas to an atmospheric plasma generator to decompose ethanol molecules to generate hydrogen. In the atmospheric plasma generator,  high frequency waves are applied between an inner electrode in a plasma reactor and an outer electrode in outside of the plasma reactor. Plasma discharge is induced between the inner wall of the plasma reactor and the inner electrode,  and a gas to be treated is allowed to become contact with plasma,  the gas to be treated is decomposed by a synergistic effect of plasma excitation and compulsive contact to plasma region,  and activation by a catalyst in plasma and outside of plasma.', p.application_date = '2011-07-01 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP5848533B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/22', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'RU2013140178'}) SET p.application_no = 'RU2013140178', p.title_cn = '生产合成气的装置和方法以及由此获得的产品', p.title_en = 'APPARATUS AND METHOD OF PRODUCING SYNTHESIS GAS AND PRODUCTS THEREFROM', p.abstract_cn = '领域 : 化学物质 : 方法包括燃烧膨胀排气从涡轮和第一内部的燃料第一转化器，以生成废气体。碳氢化合物就在第一转化器，以生成重整烃。从废气热量传递到第一介质。冷却装置加电，通过热能从加热的第一介质和第二介质进行冷却。热量从一个或多种氧化剂传递到冷却的第二介质以产生冷却的第一和第二的氧化剂。在冷却后的第一氧化剂和第二燃料分别通入燃气涡轮单元，以产生扩展过的气体从涡轮和机械能。在冷却后的第二氧化剂中压缩的压缩机，压缩机致动由机械能量。压缩第二的氧化剂和重整的烃送入第二转化器，以生成合成气。效果 : 高输出的合成气和产品therefrom.20Cl，1的DWG', p.abstract_en = 'FIELD :  chemistry. SUBSTANCE :  method includes burning an expanded exhaust from a turbine and a first fuel inside a first reformer to produce spent gas. Hydrocarbon is reformed in the first reformer to produce reformed hydrocarbon. Heat is transferred from the spent gas to a first medium. A cooling apparatus is powered by heat energy from the heated first medium and cools a second medium. Heat is transferred from one or more oxidants to the cooled second medium to produce cooled first and second oxidants. The cooled first oxidant and second fuel are fed into a gas turbine unit to produce expanded spent gas from the turbine and mechanical energy. The cooled second oxidant is compressed in a compressor which is actuated by the mechanical energy. The compressed second oxidant and the reformed hydrocarbon are fed into a second reformer to produce synthesis gas. EFFECT :  high output of synthesis gas and products therefrom. 20 cl,  1 dwg', p.application_date = '2012-01-16 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'RU2573877C2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/24', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CA2706394'}) SET p.application_no = 'CA2706394', p.title_cn = '生产氨合成气的方法', p.title_en = 'PROCESS FOR PRODUCING AMMONIA SYNTHESIS GAS', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种生产氨合成气的方法从重整烃类与蒸汽在主重整器(1)设有多个从外部加热的催化管，然后再在二次重整器(2)在一起与氧化剂气体。在该方法中，所述烃的反应与所述蒸汽在所述主重整器(1)处执行的操作压力至少45巴，在催化管和流量基本纯净的氧或富氧的空气加入到所述二次重整装置作为氧化剂气体基本上与所述重整在一起的所有烃含量的所述产物气体流出主重整器(1)。在壳体基本纯净的氧作为氧化剂气体，氮气的流量在下游添加的二次重整器(2)达到N2/H2相对应的摩尔比或接近化学计量比用于氨合成。该方法允许获得高合成气生产的能力和较低的投资和能源成本。', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention concerns a process for producing ammonia synthesis gas from the reforming of hydrocarbons with steam in a primary reformer (1) equipped with a plurality of externally heated catalytic tubes and then in a secondary reformer (2) together with an oxidant gas. In this process,  the reaction of said hydrocarbons with said steam in said primary reformer (1) is performed at an operating pressure of at least 45 bar in the catalytic tubes and a flow of essentially pure oxygen or oxygen-enriched air is added to said secondary reformer as oxidant gas for substantially reforming together with said all the hydrocarbons content of said product gas exiting the primary reformer (1). In the case essentially pure oxygen is used as oxidant gas,  a flow of nitrogen is added downstream the secondary reformer (2) to reach a N2/H2 molar ratio corresponding to or close to the stoichiometric ratio for ammonia synthesis. This process allows to obtain high synthesis gas production capacities and lower investment and energy costs.', p.application_date = '2008-11-06 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CA2706394C', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CA2841231'}) SET p.application_no = 'CA2841231', p.title_cn = '生产氢气的方法通过多步铜氯的热化学循环', p.title_en = 'HYDROGEN PRODUCTION METHOD BY MULTI-STEP COPPER-CHLORINE THERMOCHEMICAL CYCLE', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种氢气和氧气的热化学生产方法从水由低温度，多步，关闭，环状铜氯(铜Ci)工艺，该工艺包括铜和含氯化合物的反应。用于生产氢的方法，采用Cu DVB-CI热化学循环由四个热反应和一个电化学反应一个单元操作。所述周期包括六个步骤 : (1)氢生产步骤；(2)铜生产步骤；(3)干燥步骤；(4)氯化氢生产步骤；(5)分解步骤；(6)氧生产步骤。净反应顺序的过程分解成氢气和氧气。生产铜的氧化物的方法，包括使氯化铜颗粒与氧气的过热蒸汽，生产包括铜氧化物的反应与干燥氯气为通过热化学制氢的一部分铜氯(铜Ci)周期。反应中进行穿流式石英反应器为固定床式在高温度和气氛压力。', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention discloses a method for thermochemical production of hydrogen and oxygen from water by a low temperature,  multi-step,  closed,  cyclic copper-chlorine (Cu-CI) process involving the reactions of copper and chlorine compounds. A method for production of hydrogen via Cu-CI thermochemical cycle consists of four thermal reactions and one electrochemical reaction and one unit operation. The cycle involves six steps :  (1) hydrogen production step;  (2) copper production step;  (3) drying step;  (4) hydrogen chloride production step;  (5) decomposition step;  (6) oxygen production step. The net reaction of the sequential process is the decomposition of water into hydrogen and oxygen. The methods for production of copper oxide which comprises contacting copper chloride particles with superheated steam and production of oxygen comprises reaction of copper oxide with dry chlorine as a part of hydrogen production by thermochemical Copper-Chlorine (Cu-CI) cycle. The reactions are performed in a flow through type quartz reactor as fixed bed type at high temperature and atmospheric pressure.', p.application_date = '2012-07-09 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CA2841231C', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/08', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14640362'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14640362', p.title_cn = '天然气部分氧化工艺处理其他燃料气化产生的合成气', p.title_en = 'Process using natural gas partial oxidation to condition syngas from gasification of other fuels', p.abstract_cn = '一种处理合成气的方法，通过使用水煤气变换反应来有效地增加氢与一氧化碳(H2 : CO)的摩尔比，从而改善合成气的质量。 将具有第一较高摩尔比H2 : CO的热天然气基合成气的第一蒸汽与具有第二较低摩尔比H2 : CO的淬火合成气的第二物流合并，以提供具有第三摩尔比H2 : CO的合成气混合物，该第三摩尔比H2 : CO在第一和第二摩尔比之间。 非催化水煤气变换反应增加H2 : CO与高于第三摩尔比的第四摩尔比的摩尔比，并且可以在不提供外部热的情况下约等于或大于第一摩尔比。', p.abstract_en = 'A method of processing synthesis gas improves the quality of the synthesis gas by using a water gas shift reaction to increase the molar ratio of hydrogen to carbon monoxide (H2 : CO) in an efficient manner. A first steam of hot natural gas-based synthesis gas having a first higher molar ratio of H2 : CO is combined with a second stream of quenched synthesis gas having a second lower molar ratio of H2 : CO to provide a blend of synthesis gas having a third molar ratio of H2 : CO that is between the first and second molar ratios. A non-catalytic water gas shift reaction increases the molar ratio of H2 : CO to a fourth molar ratio that is higher than the third molar ratio,  and can be about equal to or greater than the first molar ratio without supplying external heat.', p.application_date = '2015-03-06 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9243196B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'OA1201400296'}) SET p.application_no = 'OA1201400296', p.title_cn = '联产甲醇和尿素。', p.title_en = 'Co-production of methanol and urea.', p.abstract_cn = '由烃原料共生产甲醇和尿素而不将大量二氧化碳排放到大气中的方法。', p.abstract_en = 'Process for the co-production of methanol and urea from a hydrocarbon feed without venting large amounts of carbon dioxide to the atmosphere.', p.application_date = '2012-12-21 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'OA16947A', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'FR14056949'}) SET p.application_no = 'FR14056949', p.title_cn = '用于生产二氢方法', p.title_en = 'METHOD FOR PRODUCING DIHYDROGEN', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种从甲酸二氢的制造方法。它还涉及使用该本发明的方法生产的二氢，在燃料电池，在燃烧发动机，在生产氨和甲醇，炼油，和在冶金，电子，食品行业。本发明还涉及一种能量生产工艺，包括从甲酸二氢生产步骤由根据本发明的方法。', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention relates to a process for producing dihydrogen from formic acid. It also relates to the use of the dihydrogen produced by the process of the invention,  in a fuel cell,  in a combustion engine,  in the production of ammonia and methanol,  in oil refining,  and in the metallurgy,  electronics and food sectors. The invention also relates to an energy production process comprising a step of producing dihydrogen from formic acid by the process according to the invention.', p.application_date = '2014-07-18 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'FR3023839A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/22', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'IN5655DELNP2015'}) SET p.application_no = 'IN5655DELNP2015', p.title_cn = '封存二氧化碳的方法和装置从废气', p.title_en = 'METHOD AND APPARATUS FOR SEQUESTERING CARBON DIOXIDE FROM A SPENT GAS', p.abstract_cn = '一种方法和设备用于从废气中分离二氧化碳并重新利用为再生气体在不产生排放顾虑的，包括 : 给定气体源分为工艺气体和废气 : 将工艺气体与烃进料产生的气体供给到重整器重整进料气体并形成还原气体；和将至少一部分所述废气进入二氧化碳洗涤器除去至少一些废气中的二氧化碳形成的贫二氧化碳气体与还原气体混合。任选地，所述方法还包括将至少一部分所述废气进入二氧化碳洗涤器中的去除至少一些废气中的二氧化碳并形成燃气后加入碳氢化合物被供给到重整器。任选地，气源和相关联的还原性气体直接还原成金属铁的转化方法利用还原气体还原炉中的铁，也可以做一些改进，并产生气源。', p.abstract_en = 'A method and apparatus for sequestering carbon dioxide from a waste gas and reusing it as a recycled gas without emissions concerns,  including :  given a gas source divided into a process gas and a waste gas :  mixing the process gas with a hydrocarbon and feeding a resulting feed gas into a reformer for reforming the feed gas and forming a reducing gas;  and feeding at least a portion of the waste gas into a carbon dioxide scrubber for removing at least some carbon dioxide from the waste gas and forming a carbon dioxide lean gas that is mixed with the reducing gas. Optionally,  the method also includes feeding at least a portion of the waste gas into the carbon dioxide scrubber for removing at least some carbon dioxide from the waste gas and forming a fuel gas after the addition of a hydrocarbon that is fed into the reformer. Optionally,  the gas source and the reducing gas are associated with a direct reduction process for converting iron oxide to metallic iron in a reduction furnace that utilizes the reducing gas,  optionally after some modification,  and produces the gas source.', p.application_date = '2015-06-26 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'IN5655DELNP2015A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/24', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'AU2011257038'}) SET p.application_no = 'AU2011257038', p.title_cn = '柴油自热重整反应器', p.title_en = 'Reactor for the autothermal reforming of diesel', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种方法用于自热重整的烃进料在催化重整反应器，包括 : 包括 : a)将烃进料与水蒸汽，蒸发如果尚未汽化的烃进料；b)预分配的蒸发混合的烃进料和水穿过该段的重整反应器中使用多点喷射器网络；c)将气态的氧化流，优选纯氧，进入预分配来自步骤(b)的混合物在喷射器从步骤(b)；d)分配，在自热重整催化剂的存在下，在步骤(c)中得到的混合物均匀地横跨段的重整反应器；和e)的混合物重整为分布在步骤(d)在重整反应器的催化区。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a method for the autothermal reforming of a hydrocarbon feed in a catalytic reforming reactor,  including the steps that consist of :  a) mixing the hydrocarbon feed with water vapour,  and vaporising the hydrocarbon feed if not already vaporised;  b) pre-distributing the vaporised mix of hydrocarbon feed and water across the section of the reforming reactor using a multipoint injector network;  c) injecting a gaseous oxidising flow,  preferably pure oxygen,  into the pre-distributed mixture from step (b) at the injectors from step (b);  d) distributing,  in the presence of an autothermal reforming catalyst,  the mixture obtained in step (c) homogeneously across the section of the reforming reactor;  and e) reforming the mixture distributed in step (d) in the catalytic zone of the reforming reactor.', p.application_date = '2011-06-23 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'AU2011257038B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'TR201517332'}) SET p.application_no = 'TR201517332', p.title_cn = '气固相反应。', p.title_en = 'Gas-solid phase reaction.', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种用于在气固相反应中在至少一种金属氧化物的表面上由水蒸气产生氢气的热方法以及用于实施该方法的反应器，其中在第一反应室中，在第一阶段中，引入水蒸气。在比第一阶段更高的温度下进行的第二阶段中，通过在金属氧化物上施加氧进行热分解来释放氢， 金属氧化物被再生，使得金属氧化物用于进一步的反应并且结合的氧被释放', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention relates to a thermal method for generating hydrogen from water vapor on a surface of at least one metal oxide in a gas-solid phase reaction and a reactor for carrying out the method,  wherein in a first reaction chamber,  in a first stage,  water vapor is induced. Hydrogen is released by thermally decomposing by applying oxygen on the metal oxide,  and in a second stage carried out at a higher temperature than the first stage,   The metal oxide is regenerated so that the metal oxide is used for further reactions and the bound oxygen is released.', p.application_date = '2005-07-19 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'TR201517332T4', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/06', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'TW102116652'}) SET p.application_no = 'TW102116652', p.title_cn = '储氢复材及其制造方法', p.title_en = 'HYDROGEN STORAGE COMPOSITES AND METHODS FOR PRODUCING THE SAME', p.abstract_cn = '一种储氢复材，包括储氢材料以及触媒该触媒系与该储氢材料接合，且该触媒系位於该储氢材料之表面及晶界一种储氢复材的制造方法，包括：混合该储氢材料与该触媒以获得混合物；将该混合物压成坯体(compact)；以及，烧结该坯体形成烧结体(sintered body)以获得该储氢复材', p.abstract_en = 'A hydrogen storage composite comprises a hydrogen-storage material and a catalyst. The catalyst is bonded with the hydrogen storage material and the catalyst is on the surface and the grain boundary of the hydrogen storage material.', p.application_date = '2013-05-10 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'TWI518030B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'TW103115867'}) SET p.application_no = 'TW103115867', p.title_cn = '氢之制造方法', p.title_en = 'Method for producing hydrogen', p.abstract_cn = '本发明系一种氢之制造方法，其系进行甲醇之部分氧化反应及分解反应而生成氢者，且该制造方法可延长触媒寿命，并且可长期稳定地制造氢氢之制造方法包含原料气体制备步骤(s1)及氢生成步骤(s2)於原料气体制备步骤(s1)中，制备预先调整为规定之可反应温度之包含甲醇、水及氧之原料气体於氢生成步骤(s2)中，使调整为可反应温度之原料气体流过填充有粒子状之触媒之反应器(2A)内而与触媒接触，藉此进行甲醇之部分氧化反应及分解反应，从而生成氢於该氢生成步骤(s2)中，藉由控制流过反应器(2A)内之原料气体之流量，而将原料气体所接触之触媒表面之最高温度控制为300℃以下', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention is a method for producing hydrogen by allowing a partial oxidation reaction and decomposition reaction of methanol to proceed in order to generate hydrogen,  wherein it is possible to extend catalyst service life and to stably produce hydrogen over the long term. The method for producing hydrogen includes a starting material gas preparation step (s1) and a hydrogen generation step (s2). In the starting material gas preparation step (s1),  a starting material gas containing methanol,  water,  and oxygen and adjusted to a predetermined reactable temperature is prepared. In the hydrogen generation step (s2),  the starting material gas that has been adjusted to the reactable temperature is caused to flow through the inside of a reactor (2A) that is filled with a particulate catalyst,  causing contact with the catalyst,  and thereby allowing a partial oxidation reaction and decomposition reaction of methanol to proceed,  generation hydrogen. In the hydrogen generation step (s2),  the highest temperature of the catalyst surface contacting the starting material gas is controlled to be no greater than 300°C by means of controlling the flow rate of starting material gas flowing within the reactor (2A).', p.application_date = '2014-05-02 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'TWI518031B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/32', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WOAU15000050'}) SET p.application_no = 'WOAU15000050', p.title_cn = '隔膜式电解槽和用于生产氢的方法从单极电解水', p.title_en = 'A DIAPHRAGM TYPE ELECTROLYTIC CELL AND A PROCESS FOR THE PRODUCTION OF HYDROGEN FROM UNIPOLAR ELECTROLYSIS OF WATER', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种隔膜式电解槽及工艺生产商业量的氢气从电解水。利用碱性和酸性电解槽内的电解质溶液帮助提高生产氢和氧。另外，电解槽的效率增加了消除不希望的副反应。', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention relates to a diaphragm type electrolytic cell and process of production of commercial quantities of hydrogen from the electrolysis of water. The utilization of both alkaline and acidic electrolyte solutions within the electrolytic cell assists to increase the production of hydrogen and oxygen. Additionally,  the efficiency of the electrolytic cell is increased due to the elimination of unwanted side reactions.', p.application_date = '2015-02-03 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016007983A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WODK15000026'}) SET p.application_no = 'WODK15000026', p.title_cn = '用于燃料电池系统的重整器', p.title_en = 'A REFORMER FOR A FUEL CELL SYSTEM', p.abstract_cn = '一种燃料电池系统，包括燃料电池堆，蒸发器用于蒸发待转发的甲醇和水的混合物通过催化重整器，用于生成部，无氢的。燃料电池堆由许多质子交换膜燃料电池，各电极在形成阳极和阴极，用于传递电流。该系统提供了增强的催化用于燃料电池系统的重整器，使所述重整器集成的紧凑设计成扁平，支架安装系统。', p.abstract_en = 'A fuel cell system comprising a fuel cell stack,  an evaporator for evaporating a mixture of methanol and water to be forwarded through a catalytic reformer for producing portions of free hydrogen. The fuel cell stack being composed of a number of proton exchange membrane fuel cells each featuring electrodes in form of an anode and a cathode for delivering an electric current. The system provides an enhanced catalytic reformer for a fuel cell system,  which enables a compact design of the reformer for integration into a flat,  rack mountable system.', p.application_date = '2015-07-16 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016008487A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/32', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WODK15000027'}) SET p.application_no = 'WODK15000027', p.title_cn = '用于燃料电池系统的蒸发器', p.title_en = 'AN EVAPORATOR FOR A FUEL CELL SYSTEM', p.abstract_cn = '一种燃料电池系统，包括燃料电池堆，蒸发器用于蒸发待转发的甲醇和水的混合物通过催化重整器，用于生成部，无氢的。燃料电池堆由许多质子交换膜燃料电池，各电极在形成阳极和阴极，用于传递电流。该系统提供了增强的系统用于蒸发液体燃料的预蒸发器，部分地蒸发燃料，接着喷嘴，雾化燃料成细雾，在被传递到最终蒸发区。这种结构确保最小的系统内燃料的堆积和快速负荷过渡的。', p.abstract_en = 'A fuel cell system comprising a fuel cell stack,  an evaporator for evaporating a mixture of methanol and water to be forwarded through a catalytic reformer for producing portions of free hydrogen. The fuel cell stack being composed of a number of proton exchange membrane fuel cells each featuring electrodes in form of an anode and a cathode for delivering an electric current. The system provides an enhanced system for evaporating the liquid fuel using a pre-evaporator,  which partly evaporates the fuel,  followed by a nozzle,  which atomizes the fuel into a fine mist,  before being passed to the final evaporation zone. This configuration ensures minimal fuel accumulation in the system and fast load transition\'s.', p.application_date = '2015-07-16 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016008488A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/32', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WOEP15066438'}) SET p.application_no = 'WOEP15066438', p.title_cn = '氨前体产生系统，用于车辆中的使用', p.title_en = 'AMMONIA PRECURSOR GENERATING SYSTEM FOR USE IN A VEHICLE', p.abstract_cn = '氨前体产生系统，用于车辆中使用的氨前体生成系统，包括 : 存储室(110)，存储至少氨前体颗粒；罐(100)储存氨前体溶液；溶解室(120)一种用于储存氨前体溶液，和用于将氨溶解于前驱体颗粒在氨前体溶液；一转移装置(130)配置成用于将氨前体颗粒从所述储存室，以溶解室；一种流体转移装置(122)配置成用于将所述氨前体溶液从所述罐，所述溶解室。', p.abstract_en = 'Ammonia precursor generating system for use in a vehicle Ammonia precursor generating system comprising :  • a storage compartment (110) storing at least ammonia precursor granules;  • a tank (100) storing an ammonia precursor solution;  • a dissolving compartment (120) adapted for storing an ammonia precursor solution,  and for dissolving ammonia precursor granules in the ammonia precursor solution;  • a transfer means (130) configured for transferring ammonia precursor granules from the storage compartment to the dissolving compartment;  • a fluid transfer device (122) configured for transferring the ammonia precursor solution from said tank to said dissolving compartment.', p.application_date = '2015-07-17 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016009055A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WOIB15055392'}) SET p.application_no = 'WOIB15055392', p.title_cn = '二氢生产工艺', p.title_en = 'DIHYDROGEN PRODUCTION PROCESS', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种从甲酸二氢的制造方法。它还涉及使用该本发明的方法生产的二氢，在燃料电池，在燃烧发动机，在生产氨和甲醇，炼油，和在冶金，电子，食品行业。本发明还涉及一种能量生产工艺，包括从甲酸二氢生产步骤由根据本发明的方法。', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention relates to a process for producing dihydrogen from formic acid. It also relates to the use of the dihydrogen produced by the process of the invention,  in a fuel cell,  in a combustion engine,  in the production of ammonia and methanol,  in oil refining,  and in the metallurgy,  electronics and food sectors. The invention also relates to an energy production process comprising a step of producing dihydrogen from formic acid by the process according to the invention.', p.application_date = '2015-07-16 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016009384A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/22', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WOKR15000841'}) SET p.application_no = 'WOKR15000841', p.title_cn = '用于产生氢气的方法和装置从甲酸', p.title_en = 'METHOD AND APPARATUS FOR GENERATING HYDROGEN FROM FORMIC ACID', p.abstract_cn = '本发明提供了一种氢气产生装置和氢气产生方法，所述氢气产生装置产生氢的脱水甲酸，包括 : 含有水和非均相催化剂的反应器；甲酸送料机送料甲酸加入到反应器中；和水分去除器，用于去除从反应器中产生的水分。', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention provides a hydrogen generating apparatus and a hydrogen generating method,  wherein the hydrogen generating apparatus generates hydrogen by dehydrating formic acid,  and comprises :  a reactor for containing water and a heterogeneous catalyst;  a formic acid feeder for feeding formic acid into the reactor;  and a moisture remover for removing moisture generated from the reactor.', p.application_date = '2015-01-27 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016010222A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/22', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WOKR15004339'}) SET p.application_no = 'WOKR15004339', p.title_cn = '使用固体化学氢化物氢气产生方法', p.title_en = 'HYDROGEN GENERATING METHOD USING SOLID CHEMICAL HYDRIDE', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种使用固体化学氢化物氢气产生方法，该方法包括步骤 : 存储固态化学氢化物氢发生器内；将碳酸氢钠(NaHCO3)内的氢发生器，在该化学氢化物存储；和产生氢气的反应的化学氢化物与碳酸氢钠。本发明的目的是提供一种使用固体化学氢化物氢气产生方法，该方法使氢气的产生，通过存储固态化学氢化物氢发生器内，和提供碳酸氢钠水溶液中当燃料电池操作是必要的，从而直接降解的固态化学氢化物。', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention relates to a hydrogen generating method using solid chemical hydride,  the method comprising the steps of :  storing solid-state chemical hydride inside a hydrogen generator;  supplying sodium bicarbonate (NaHCO3) inside the hydrogen generator in which the chemical hydride is stored;  and generating hydrogen by reacting the chemical hydride with the sodium bicarbonate. The purpose of the present invention is to provide a hydrogen generating method using solid chemical hydride,  the method enabling the generation of hydrogen by storing solid-state chemical hydride inside a hydrogen generator,  and supplying a sodium bicarbonate aqueous solution when fuel cell operation is necessary,  thereby directly degrading the solid-state chemical hydride.', p.application_date = '2015-04-29 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016010241A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/06', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WOUS15040516'}) SET p.application_no = 'WOUS15040516', p.title_cn = '生产直接还原铁的方法和系统和钢厂的燃料气体', p.title_en = 'METHODS AND SYSTEMS FOR PRODUCING DIRECT REDUCED IRON AND STEEL MILL FUEL GAS', p.abstract_cn = '用于制备还原气使用的方法在生产直接还原铁(DRI)和燃料气体用于使用在钢厂，包括 : 压缩焦炉气(COG)流中的压缩机；将所压缩的焦炉煤气物流通过活性炭床，以除去焦油从压缩焦炉气体物流；arating富氢气体流从·压缩净化后的焦炉气体流采用变压吸附单元；提供富氢气体流，以直接还原竖炉作为还原气体；和提供剩余气体流从压力回转吸附单元对钢厂作为燃料气体。一次通过和再循环选择，被呈现。任选地，碱性氧气炉气(bofg)加入到还原气体。', p.abstract_en = 'A process for producing reducing gas for use in the production of direct reduced iron (DRI) and fuel gas for use in a steel mill,  comprising :  compressing a coke oven gas (COG) stream in a compressor;  passing the compressed coke oven gas stream through an activated charcoal bed to remove tars from the compressed coke oven gas stream;  separating a hydrogen-rich gas stream from the · compressed cleaned coke oven gas stream using a pressure swing absorption unit;  providing the hydrogen-rich gas stream to a direct reduction shaft furnace as reducing gas;  and providing a remaining gas stream from the pressure swing absorption unit to a steel mill as fuel gas. Both once through and recycle options are presented. Optionally,  basic oxygen fumace gas (BOFG) is added to the reducing gas.', p.application_date = '2015-07-15 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016011122A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'ARP140102293'}) SET p.application_no = 'ARP140102293', p.title_cn = '氧化反应中烟灰控制', p.title_en = 'CONTROL OF SOOT IN THE OXIDATION REACTIONS', p.abstract_cn = '控制烟灰的形成在部分氧化含碳原料氧化剂的监测时间的流相对于时间的碳质原料物流', p.abstract_en = 'Soot formation in the partial oxidation of carbonaceous feed is controlled by controlling the momentum of the oxidant stream relative to the momentum of the carbonaceous feed stream.', p.application_date = '2014-06-17 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'AR096635A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/36', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201110415675.9'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201110415675.9', p.title_cn = '一种锂水反应制备氢气的方法', p.title_en = 'A lithium water reaction process of preparing hydrogen', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种锂水反应制备氢气的方法，其特点是：包括堵住装置底部的排水口，装置顶部的出氢口连接在用氢设备上，顶部的注水口中注入纯净水，纯净水经装置中微晶陶瓷隔膜与锂锭反应产生氢气。本发明由于采用了锂，由微晶陶瓷隔膜与水隔离反应获得高纯度氢气，方法简单、装置携带和操作方便，成本低廉，安全性好，氢气产量高，适于配套于小型燃料电池的使用。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a method for preparing hydrogen gas by a lithium water reaction. The method is characterized by comprising a water outlet which seals the bottom part of a device,  wherein a hydrogen gas outlet on the top part of the device is connected on a hydrogen gas using device;  a water filling hole on the top part is filled with pure water;  and the pure water reacts with lithium ingot by a microcrystal ceramic diaphragm in the device to generate hydrogen gas. Lithium is adopted to react with the water by the microcrystal ceramic diaphragm in an isolated manner to acquire pure hydrogen gas;  the method is simple,  the device is convenient to carry and operate;  the cost is low,  the safety is good,  and the hydrogen gas yield is high,  thus,  the method can be matched to the use of a small fuel cell.', p.application_date = '2011-12-13 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN102491266B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/08', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201080039336.9'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201080039336.9', p.title_cn = '利用深冷净化制取氨补充合成气', p.title_en = 'Using cryogenic purification preparing ammonia supplementary synthesis gas', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种用于制取氨补充合成气的方法以及相关设备，其中：转化烃原料，获得粗氨补充合成气的流；在通过在空气分离单元中产生的富氮气流制冷的深冷净化段中净化所述粗合成气；所述深冷段的输出处的富氮气流还用于调节净化过的补充合成气的氢气/氮气比；还在所述空气分离单元中产生富氧气流，并将其送入转化段。', p.abstract_en = 'A process and a related equipment for making ammonia make-up synthesis gas are disclosed,  where :  a hydrocarbon feedstock is reformed obtaining a raw ammonia make-up syngas stream;  said raw syngas is purified in a cryogenic purification section refrigerated by a nitrogen-rich stream produced in an air separation unit;  the nitrogen-rich stream at output of said cryogenic section is further used for adjusting the hydrogen/nitrogen ratio of the purified make-up syngas;  an oxygen-rich stream is also produced in said air separation unit and is fed to the reforming section.', p.application_date = '2010-08-25 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN102498058B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201210299512.3'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201210299512.3', p.title_cn = '氢气发生系统', p.title_en = 'Hydrogen gas generating system', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种氢气发生系统，包括氢气原料箱、氢气发生器、氢气过滤催化器、氢气冷却装置、氢气储存室和氢气分配系统，氢气原料箱连接氢气发生器和发动机排气管余热氢气发生器，其产生出氢气经激发后送至氢气过滤催化器，经过滤、化学反应的氢气便于低温点燃进行动力供给，经过滤、化学反应后到氢气冷却装置，冷却后氢气进入氢气储存室进行储存，最后进入氢气分配系统，由氢气分配系统智能分配直接用于发动机产生动力或能源的运用。本氢气发生系统使用乙醇和水经过系统处理产生的氢气可直接提供各种动力所需，用于驱动汽车、动力发电等，可以直接取代汽油、柴油等其它能源系统，是一种无污染安全节能环保成本低廉的新型能源系统。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention discloses a hydrogen generating system which comprises a hydrogen raw material box,  a hydrogen generator,  a hydrogen filtering catalyst,  a hydrogen cooling device,  a hydrogen storing chamber and a hydrogen distributing system,  wherein the hydrogen raw material box is connected with the hydrogen generator and an engine exhaust pipe waste heat hydrogen generator,  the generated hydrogen is fed to the hydrogen filtering catalyst after stimulated,  the hydrogen performed with filtering and chemical reactions is favorable for low-temperature igniting to supply power,  the hydrogen is fed to the hydrogen cooling device after the filtering and the chemical reactions,  the cooled hydrogen enters the hydrogen storing chamber for storing and finally enters a hydrogen distributing system,  and the hydrogen is directly used for application of generating power or energy for an engine after intelligently distributed by the hydrogen distributing system. The hydrogen generated by the hydrogen generating device is prepared through alcohol and water after system treatment,  can directly meet various power requirements,  is applied to automobile driving,  dynamic power generation and the like,  can directly replace other energy systems such as gasoline and diesel and is a novel energy system which is free of pollution,  safe,  energy-saving,  environment-friendly and low in cost.', p.application_date = '2012-08-22 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN102765699B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/32', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201180033895.3'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201180033895.3', p.title_cn = '通过使用膜技术的合成气生产', p.title_en = 'Through the use of membrane technology production of synthesis gas', p.abstract_cn = '被二氧化碳污染的天然气流(11)可用以产生合成气(16)。将可用的烟道气的源(1)和负载CO2的天然气流(11)合并以将几乎等量的甲烷与CO2的混合物的复合物递送到将产生合成气的等离子体反应器(15)等。当与费-托反应器(40)联合时，整个方法提供了用于产生合成液烃的方法。', p.abstract_en = 'Streams (11) of natural gas contaminated with significant amounts of carbon dioxide can be efficiently and economically processed to create Syngas (16). An available source (1) of flue gas that might otherwise be dispersed into the atmosphere in conjunction with such a CO2-laden natural gas stream (11) renders the process even more economical and efficient through the creation of multiple feedstreams (14,  27,  34) that are combined to deliver a composite near equal mixture of methane and CO2 to a plasma reactor (15) or the like that will generate Syngas. When coupled with a Fischer-Tropsch reactor (40),  the overall process provides a particularly efficient and economical process for producing synthetic liquid hydrocarbons.', p.application_date = '2011-06-29 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN103108831B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/34', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201180038064.5'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201180038064.5', p.title_cn = '用于制备合成气的方法', p.title_en = 'For process for the preparation of synthesis gas', p.abstract_cn = '用于从包含烯烃、氢气和一氧化碳的基本干燥的烃进料(1)制备合成气的方法，所述方法包括以下步骤：(a)在60至190℃之间的温度下选择性地氢化(2)所述烃进料中的烯烃以获得包含氢气、一氧化碳和饱和烃的氢化烃进料(3)，(b)？加入蒸汽(4)至所述氢化烃进料，(c)在蒸汽存在下对所述氢化烃进料进行水煤气变换反应(6)以获得经变换的氢化烃混合物，以及(d)转化(8)所述经变换的氢化烃混合物以获得合成气。', p.abstract_en = 'Process for the preparation of synthesis gas from a substantially dry hydrocarbon feed (1) comprising olefins,  hydrogen and carbon monoxide,  said process comprising the steps of :  (a) selectively hydrogenating (2) the olefins in said hydrocarbon feed at a temperature between 60 and 190 DEG C to obtain a hydrogenated hydrocarbon feed (3) comprising hydrogen,  carbon monoxide and saturated hydrocarbons,  (b)? Adding steam (4) to the hydrogenated hydrocarbon feed,  (c) subjecting the hydrogenated hydrocarbon feed to a water gas shift reaction (6) in the presence of steam to obtain a shifted hydrogenated hydrocarbon mixture,  and (d) converting (8) the shifted hydrogenated hydrocarbon mixture to obtain a synthesis gas.', p.application_date = '2011-05-13 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN103189307B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/36', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201280004811.8'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201280004811.8', p.title_cn = '用于启动自热重整反应器的方法', p.title_en = 'Used for starting the method of auto-thermal reforming reactor', p.abstract_cn = '启动一种自热反应器的方法，该方法用于通过在进行氧化反应和重整反应的反应室中重整含烃的原料气、通过进料一种含烃的原料气和水蒸汽来生产合成气，其中该水蒸汽含量是基于含碳原料气按体积计0-80%，并且将具有按体积计10%-100%氧含量的氧化剂进料并且产生了一种产物气体，其中触发了一个用于启动的点火过程，其中首先通过一种惰性介质将该自热反应器预加热到&gt; 600°C用于启动，并且随后通过引入一种气体或气体混合物以及引入一种氧化剂触发该点火过程，这种气体或气体混合物具有足够低的着火点并且具有低于该含烃原料气的着火温度并且具有按体积计至少40%的组分比例，该组分具有低着火点，该氧化剂具有按体积计10%-100%的氧含量，并且随后通过引入该含烃原料气和水蒸汽开始该自热重整。', p.abstract_en = 'A method of starting up an autothermal reactor for the production of synthesis gas by reforming of hydrocarbon-containing feed gases in a reaction chamber in which oxidation reactions and reforming reactions are carried out,  by feeding a hydrocarbon containing feed gas,  steam and an oxidant.', p.application_date = '2012-03-13 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN103354801B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201310403855.4'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201310403855.4', p.title_cn = '一种合成气洗涤处理工艺', p.title_en = 'A synthetic gas scrubbing treatment process', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种合成气洗涤处理工艺，它是将出气化炉激冷室的黑水过滤灰渣后入缓冲罐，出缓冲罐的激冷水过循环泵后入气化炉激冷室，合成气经洗涤塔与通入的洗涤水接触后，再经与变换冷凝水和脱盐除氧水接触除尘后去后续变换工段，出洗涤塔的洗涤水一部分入气化炉激冷室，出洗涤塔的黑水经过滤器滤渣后与另一部分洗涤水合并后入缓冲罐，出缓冲罐的洗涤水经循环泵加压后一部分入文丘里洗涤器，其余部分入洗涤塔循环使用。本发明黑水不外排，可减轻污染和水消耗，可减少废水排放0.36吨和减少设备投资11万元，提高了装置运行周期，灰水处理简单常用，灰水不用降温处理，使系统有更高的水蒸气含量，提高了合成气的温度，更有利于后续变换工段。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention discloses a washing treatment process for synthesis gas. The washing treatment process comprises the following steps :  after black water from a shock chilling chamber of a gasification furnace is filtered and ash dreg is removed,  the black water enters a buffering pot;  after shock chilling water from the buffering pot passes through a circulating pump,  the shock chilling water enters the shock chilling chamber of the gasification furnace;  after synthesis gas is contacted with introduced washing water by a washing tower and enters a follow-up conversion working section after being contacted with converted condensing water and desalting and oxygen-removing water for dust removal;  part of the washing water from the washing tower enters the shock chilling chamber of the gasification furnace;  after dreg is filtered by a filter,  the black water from the washing tower and the other part of the washing water are combined and then enter the buffering pot;  after the washing water from the buffering pot is pressurized by a circulating pump,  part of the washing water enters a venturi scrubber and the other part of the washing water enters the washing tower to be circularly used. According to the washing treatment process for the synthesis gas,  the black water is not discharged out so that the pollution and the water consumption can be relieved;  the wastewater discharge is reduced by 0.36 ton;  the operation period of a device is prolonged and the treatment of ash water is very simple and common;  the ash water does not need to be subjected to temperature reduction treatment so that the system has the relatively high water vapor content and the temperature of the synthesis gas is increased;  the washing treatment process of the synthesis gas is good for the follow-up conversion working section.', p.application_date = '2013-09-06 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN103435005B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 2, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201280009887.X'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201280009887.X', p.title_cn = '包括操作条件可选择地被调节的重整步骤的用于由碳质材料生产甲醇或烃的方法', p.title_en = 'Including the operating condition can be selectively adjusted the reforming step of the carbonaceous material used for the method of producing methanol or hydrocarbon', p.abstract_cn = '本发明的生产方法包括以下步骤：根据包括至少一个重整步骤的方法，由碳质材料生产合成气，所述合成气在用于重整操作的第一操作条件下具有氢气与一氧化碳的第一摩尔比；由氢化的原料和第一消耗的电功率生产氢气流，所述氢气流具有用于所述第一消耗的电功率的第一摩尔流率；将用于生产所述氢气流所消耗的电功率降低至低于第一电功率的第二电功率，并且转变为不同于用于重整操作的所述第一操作条件的第二操作条件以补偿所述氢气流降低的摩尔流率，在所述第二操作条件下，所述合成气具有大于所述氢气与一氧化碳的第一摩尔比的氢气与一氧化碳的第二摩尔比。', p.abstract_en = 'A method for producing methanol or hydrocarbons is provided. The production method comprises producing a synthesis gas from carbonaceous material,  according to a method comprising at least one reforming step,  the synthesis gas having a first hydrogen/carbon monoxide molar ratio under the first operating conditions for the reforming operation;  producing a stream of hydrogen from a hydrogenated raw material and from a first consumed electric power,  the hydrogen stream having a first molar flow rate for said first consumed electric power;  and lowering the consumed electric power for producing the hydrogen stream,  down to a second electric power below the first electric power and transitioning to second operating conditions different from the first for the reforming operation in order to compensate for the lowering of the molar flow rate of the hydrogen flow,  the synthesis gas having a second hydrogen/carbon monoxide molar ratio greater than the first under the second operating conditions.', p.application_date = '2012-02-22 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN103476704B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/32', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201210385882.9'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201210385882.9', p.title_cn = '一种重油移动床制氢方法和反应系统', p.title_en = 'A heavy oil moving bed reaction system and method for hydrogen production', p.abstract_cn = '一种重油移动床制氢方法和反应系统，包括：重油和水蒸气预热后由底部进入移动床反应器，与平均粒径0.1～5毫米的含氧化镍、氧化镁的小球催化剂逆流接触反应，在温度为900～980℃、压力为0.1～3.0MPa的条件下反应；产物气气固分离后引出移动床反应器，换热后进入后续提纯分离系统获得高纯度氢气；催化剂由移动床反应器底部流出进入再生器与含氧气体烧焦再生，再生后的催化剂返回移动床反应器上部循环使用。本发明提供的方法重油原料转化和产氢效率高、反应温度控制平稳、系统热量传输效率高、装置和操作更加简化和安全，整套装置结构简单、紧凑、并且不需要预先脱除原料中的硫。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention discloses a method for producing hydrogen from heavy oil by a moving bed reactor,  and a reaction system. The method comprises the following steps that heavy oil and vapor are preheated,  the preheated heavy oil and vapor are fed into a moving bed reactor from the bottom of the moving bed reactor,  the preheated heavy oil and vapor countercurrently contacts with a small-ball catalyst which contains nickel oxide and magnesium oxide and has the average particle size of 0.1-5mm and the mixed system undergoes a counter-current contact reaction at a temperature of 900-980 DEG C under the pressure of 0.1-3.0MPa;  product gas is separated by gas-solid separation and then is led out of the moving bed reactor,  and the product gas is subjected to heat exchange and then is fed into a follow-up purification separation system so that high-purity hydrogen is obtained;  and the catalyst is discharged from the bottom of the moving bed reactor,  flows into a regenerator and is subjected to oxygen-containing gas-based scorching regeneration,  and the regenerated catalyst is returned to the upper part of the moving bed reactor for recycle. The method has the advantages of high heavy oil raw material conversion efficiency,  high hydrogen-production efficiency,  stable reaction temperature control,  high system heat transmission efficiency,  and simpleness and safety of the device and processes. The whole reaction system has a simple and compact structure and is free of pre-removal of sulfur in the raw material.', p.application_date = '2012-10-12 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN103723679B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/42', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201210563325.1'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201210563325.1', p.title_cn = '一种高单位产氢量的铝基复合制氢材料及其制备和应用', p.title_en = 'A high unit of the aluminum-based composite hydrogen to the hydrogen material and its preparation and use', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种高单位产氢量的铝基复合制氢材料及其制备方法，属于能源技术领域。本发明提供一种新型的单位产氢量高的铝基复合材料，此材料通过机械球磨法制备。在制备过程中选用Al和LiBH4作为原料，通过对组分含量与球磨条件进行优化提高产品与水反应的活性。本发明所制得的铝基复合制氢材料在常温下即可与水迅速反应释放出氢气，且材料的最佳产氢量高达2020mL(H2，298K)/g(铝基复合材料)。该铝基复合制氢材料解决了在所能携带材料质量不多时又对氢气有大量需求的情况，并且制氢方法简单、快速，产品易于携带，可为燃料电池、移动器件等器械提供氢气。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to an aluminum-based composite hydrogen production material with high unit hydrogen production and a preparation method thereof,  and belongs to the technical field of energy The present invention provides a new-type aluminium-base composite material with high unit hydrogen yield,  and said material is made up by using mechanical ball-milling process Al and LiBH4 are selected as raw materials during the preparation process,  and the activity of the product reacting with water is improved by optimizing the component content and ball milling conditions. The aluminum-based composite hydrogen production material prepared by the invention can quickly react with water at room temperature to release hydrogen,  and the optimal hydrogen production of the material is as high as 2020mL (H2,  298K)/g (aluminum-based composite material) The aluminum-based composite hydrogen production material solves the problem that there is a large demand for hydrogen when the quality of the material it can carry is not much,  and the hydrogen production method is simple and fast,  and the product is easy to carry,  and can provide hydrogen for fuel cells,  mobile devices and other instruments.', p.application_date = '2012-12-21 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN103879959B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/06', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201410220676.1'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201410220676.1', p.title_cn = '从炼厂干气中高收率、高纯度回收氢气的方法', p.title_en = 'High yield in dry gas from a refinery,  high purity method for recovering hydrogen', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种从炼厂干气中高收率、高纯度回收氢气的方法，包括以下步骤：一段变压吸附再生步骤；二段变压吸附再生步骤；膜分离步骤；并将膜分离步骤中的含氢气体返回一段变压吸附再生步骤，将脱氢气体作为燃料气体排出。本发明的优点在于：结合吸附分离法和膜分离法，能够高收率、高纯度的回收氢气，氢气收率达到90-95%以上，氢气的纯度达到99.9%。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention discloses a method for recovering high-yield high-purity hydrogen gas from refinery dry gas,  which comprises the following steps :  carrying out primary pressure swing adsorption regeneration;  carrying out secondary pressure swing adsorption regeneration;  carrying out membrane separation;  and returning the hydrogen-containing gas in the membrane separation step to the primary pressure swing adsorption regeneration step,  and discharging the dehydrogenated gas as fuel gas. By combining the adsorptive separation process and the membrane separation process,  the method can recover high-yield high-purity hydrogen gas,  wherein the hydrogen gas yield is up to higher than 90-95%,  and the hydrogen gas purity is up to 99.9%.', p.application_date = '2014-05-23 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN104030244B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/50', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201410359110.7'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201410359110.7', p.title_cn = '一种甲醇水蒸气重整制氢反应装置', p.title_en = 'A methanol steam reforming hydrogen production reaction device', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种甲醇水蒸气重整制氢反应装置，包括一反应器本体，该反应器本体内设有一反应腔，所述反应腔的横截面为圆形，并从左到右分为一蒸发部和一重整部，所述蒸发部的左端设有甲醇水溶液进料口，该蒸发部内从左到右依次设有一第一蒸发板、一第二蒸发板和一第三蒸发板，且三个蒸发板之间通过环形垫圈相间隔，其中第一蒸发板上设有相互平行的条状通槽，第二蒸发板和第三蒸发板上均环形阵列分布有圆形通孔；所述重整部的右端设有氢气出料口，该重整部内从左到右依次设有至少二金属载体反应板，即金属载体反应板层叠放置。本发明的反应装置大大减小反应压降，使流体分布更加均匀。并可有效避免反应中冷点现象的存在，提高制氢效率和甲醇转化率。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention discloses a reaction device for reforming and producing hydrogen from methanol vapor. The reaction device comprises a reactor body,  wherein the reactor body is internally provided with a reaction chamber;  the cross section of the reaction chamber is circular and is divided into an evaporation part and a reforming part from left to right;  a methanol solution feeding hole is formed in the left end of the evaporation part;  a first evaporation plate,  a second evaporation plate and a third evaporation plate are sequentially arranged from left to right inside the evaporation part;  the three evaporation plates are partitioned through annular gaskets;  stripy through grooves parallel to one another are formed in the first evaporation plate;  circular through holes which are distributed in an annular array are formed in the second evaporation plate and the third evaporation plate;  a hydrogen discharge hole is formed in the right end of the reforming part;  and at least two metal carrier reaction plates are sequentially arranged from left to right inside the reforming part,  that is,  the metal carrier reaction plates are arranged in an overlapped manner. By adopting the reaction device,  the reaction pressure drop is greatly reduced,  and the fluid can be distributed uniformly. In addition,  the phenomenon of cold point in the reaction is effectively avoided,  and the hydrogen production efficiency and the methanol conversion rate are improved.', p.application_date = '2014-07-25 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN104118848B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/32', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201410436632.2'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201410436632.2', p.title_cn = '一种油页岩干馏气化学链制氢联合发电系统及工艺', p.title_en = 'A kind of oil shale retorting gasification studies the chain joint power generation system and process for hydrogen production', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种油页岩干馏气化学链制氢联合发电系统及工艺。所述系统包括依次连接的油页岩破碎筛分单元、油页岩干馏单元、干馏气冷凝回收单元，还包括燃料反应器、蒸汽反应器、发电单元及空气反应器。本发明将现有油页岩干馏炼油过程的低热值剩余煤气用于生产高经济价值和高化学价值的氢气，回收干馏气制氢过程中的余热用于发电和产生蒸汽，通过热量集成，实现化学循环过程中的热量平衡，在提高现有油页岩干馏过程中资源利用率和能量效率的同时，较大幅度提高了过程经济效益。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention discloses a combined oil shale dry distillation gas chemical chain hydrogen producing and power generating system and process. The combined oil shale dry distillation gas chemical chain hydrogen producing and power generating system comprises an oil shale crushing and screening unit,  an oil shale dry distillation unit,  a dry distillation gas condensing and recycling unit which are sequentially connected and also comprises a fuel reactor,  a steam reaction,  a generating unit and an air reactor. According to the combined oil shale dry distillation gas chemical chain hydrogen producing and power generating system and process,  residual coal gas with low heating value in the existing oil shale dry distillation oil refining process is used for producing hydrogen with high economic value and high chemical value,  waste heat in a dry distillation gas recycling and hydrogen producing process is used for generating and producing steam,  heat balance in a chemical cyclic process is realized by virtue of integration of heat,  resource utilization rate and energy efficiency in the existing oil shale dry distillation process are improved,  and process economic benefit is greatly increased.', p.application_date = '2014-08-29 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN104192800B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/34', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201510736031.8'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201510736031.8', p.title_cn = '一种水氢智能家居系统', p.title_en = 'Water-hydrogen intelligent home system', p.abstract_cn = '本发明揭示了一种水氢智能家居系统，包括智能家居控制系统、甲醇制氢系统、氢气发电系统，甲醇制氢系统、氢气发电系统、智能家居控制系统依次连接；所述智能家居控制系统包括主控中心、环境参数调节系统；所述环境参数调节系统包括窗户打开角度调节装置、窗帘控制装置、湿度调节装置、温度调节装置、亮度调节装置、氧气释放装置、空气净化装置；所述甲醇制氢系统利用甲醇水蒸气重整制备氢气，氢气通过镀有钯银合金的膜分离装置获得高纯度的氢气，获取的氢气通过氢气发电系统发电，发出的电能供智能家居控制系统工作。本发明提出的水氢智能家居系统，可利用甲醇制得氢气发电作为智能家居系统的能源，可以将智能家居系统用于没有交流电的场所。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention discloses a water-hydrogen intelligent home system. The water-hydrogen intelligent home system comprises an intelligent home control system,  a methanol hydrogen production system and a hydrogen generation system,  wherein the methanol hydrogen production system,  the hydrogen generation system and the intelligent home control system are connected in sequence;  the intelligent home control system comprises a master control center and an environment parameter adjusting system;  the environment parameter adjusting system comprises a window open angle adjusting device,  a curtain control device,  a humidity control device,  a temperature adjusting device,  a brightness adjusting device,  an oxygen releasing device and an air purification device;  the methanol hydrogen production system is used for preparing hydrogen by utilizing methanol stream reforming,  high-purity hydrogen is obtained by a membrane separation device coated with palladium-silver alloy,  the obtained hydrogen is used for generating power by the hydrogen generation system,  and the generated electricity is supplied to the intelligent home control system to operate. According to the water-hydrogen intelligent home system,  the electricity generated from the hydrogen prepared from methanol is used as an energy source of the intelligent home system,  and the intelligent home system can be used in a place without alternating current.', p.application_date = '2015-11-03 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105253855A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/32', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201520729265.5'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201520729265.5', p.title_cn = '一种采用流化床进行深度脱除CO的优先氧化装置', p.title_en = 'Adopt fluidized bed to carry out degree of depth desorption CO\'s preferential oxidation unit', p.abstract_cn = '本实用新型公开了一种采用流化床进行深度脱除CO的优先氧化装置，包括反应器筒体、水蒸汽夹套；水蒸汽夹套套设于反应器筒体的外部，水蒸汽夹套内壁与反应器筒体外壁之间的空隙形成水蒸汽夹套层；反应器筒体及水蒸汽夹套的上端均通过一盖板密封，在盖板上设有一合成气引出管伸入反应器筒体内；所述反应器筒体的下端开口，依次安装有用于将催化剂承载在其上的原料气分布器和具有一原料进气管的下封头；本方法及装置可直接对接化石燃料重整制氢产生的富氢合成气进行CO的深度脱除。与传统的固定床反应器相比，本实用新型具有床层温度均匀、催化效率高、床层阻力小等优点。', p.abstract_en = 'The utility model discloses an adopt fluidized bed to carry out degree of depth desorption CO\'s preferential oxidation unit,  press from both sides the cover including reactor barrel,  steam,  the steam presss from both sides the outside that the reactor barrel was located to the ways,  and the void formation steam that the steam pressed from both sides between cover inner wall and the reactor barrel outer wall presss from both sides the jacket layer,  it is all sealed through an apron that reactor barrel and steam press from both sides the upper end of cover,  is equipped with on lapping in a synthetic gas fairlead stretches into the reactor barrel,  the lower extreme opening of reactor barrel is installed in proper order and is used for bearing the catalyst of above that feed gas distributor and the low head that has a raw materials intake pipe,  this method and device can directly dock the degree of depth desorption that hydrogen -rich synthetic gas that fossil fuel reformation hydrogen manufacturing produced carries out CO. Compare with traditional fixed bed reactor,  the utility model has the advantages of the bed temperature is even,  catalysis is efficient,  the bed resistance is little.', p.application_date = '2015-09-18 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN204981129U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/58', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'EP14732943'}) SET p.application_no = 'EP14732943', p.title_cn = '可再生能源系统中用于产生氢气和氢气产品', p.title_en = 'RENEWABLE ENERGY SYSTEM FOR GENERATING HYDROGEN AND HYDROGEN PRODUCTS', p.abstract_cn = '产生氢气的装置包括一个可再生能量源，用于产生电能和氢气发生模块供电的至少部分地由电能产生的可再生能源。氢生成模块生成氢的电解水。氢可用于通过一个化学生成模块形成含氢化学产品如氨，甲醇和/或烯烃。在优选实施例中，所述可再生能源包括高空风系统。', p.abstract_en = 'An apparatus for generating hydrogen includes a renewable energy source for generating electrical energy and a hydrogen generation module powered at least partially by electrical energy generated by the renewable energy source. The hydrogen generation module generates hydrogen through electrolysis of water. The hydrogen may be used by a chemical generation module to form hydrogen containing chemical products such as ammonia,  methanol and/or an olefin. In a preferred embodiment,  the renewable energy source comprises a high altitude wind system.', p.application_date = '2014-03-05 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'EP2969921A2', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'EP14717586'}) SET p.application_no = 'EP14717586', p.title_cn = '集成发电和碳捕获燃料电池的使用', p.title_en = 'INTEGRATED POWER GENERATION AND CARBON CAPTURE USING FUEL CELLS', p.abstract_cn = '系统和方法被提供用于捕获CO2从燃烧源应用熔融碳酸盐燃料电池(MCFC)。至少一部分所述阳极排气中可回收用作燃料的燃烧源。任选地，第第二部分的阳极废气的一部分可循环使用的阳极输入流的装置。这样能够允许用于减少燃料电池所需要的量从燃烧分离CO2源耗尽和/或燃料电池中如何修改即可操作。', p.abstract_en = 'In various aspects,  systems and methods are provided for operating a molten carbonate fuel cell,  such as a fuel cell assembly,  with increased production of syngas while also reducing or minimizing the amount of CO2 exiting the fuel cell in the cathode exhaust stream. This can allow for improved efficiency of syngas production while also generating electrical power.', p.application_date = '2014-03-13 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'EP2969922A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/34', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'EP14719450'}) SET p.application_no = 'EP14719450', p.title_cn = '熔融碳酸盐燃料电池的集成在费-托合成', p.title_en = 'INTEGRATION OF MOLTEN CARBONATE FUEL CELLS IN FISCHER-TROPSCH SYNTHESIS', p.abstract_cn = '在各个方面，系统和方法提供用于集成的熔融碳酸盐燃料电池与费-托合成工艺。熔融碳酸盐燃料电池的可集成与费-托合成工艺的各种方式中，包括提供合成气生产烃类中使用的碳。此外，熔融碳酸盐燃料电池的集成与费-托合成过程排放的工艺气流的方便进一步加工或合成工艺中产生的二次产物流。', p.abstract_en = 'In various aspects,  systems and methods are provided for operating a molten carbonate fuel cell,  such as a fuel cell assembly,  with increased production of syngas while also reducing or minimizing the amount of CO2 exiting the fuel cell in the cathode exhaust stream. This can allow for improved efficiency of syngas production while also generating electrical power.', p.application_date = '2014-03-13 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'EP2969924A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'EP14720330'}) SET p.application_no = 'EP14720330', p.title_cn = '熔融碳酸盐燃料电池的集成在费-托合成', p.title_en = 'INTEGRATION OF MOLTEN CARBONATE FUEL CELLS IN FISCHER-TROPSCH SYNTHESIS', p.abstract_cn = '在各个方面，系统和方法提供用于集成的熔融碳酸盐燃料电池与费-托合成工艺。熔融碳酸盐燃料电池的可集成与费-托合成工艺的各种方式中，包括提供合成气生产烃类中使用的碳。此外，熔融碳酸盐燃料电池的集成与费-托合成过程排放的工艺气流的方便进一步加工或合成工艺中产生的二次产物流。', p.abstract_en = 'In various aspects,  systems and methods are provided for operating a molten carbonate fuel cell,  such as a fuel cell assembly,  with increased production of syngas while also reducing or minimizing the amount of CO2 exiting the fuel cell in the cathode exhaust stream. This can allow for improved efficiency of syngas production while also generating electrical power.', p.application_date = '2014-03-13 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'EP2969926A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'EP14720329'}) SET p.application_no = 'EP14720329', p.title_cn = '集成电力生产中的NOx的缓解', p.title_en = 'MITIGATION OF NOX IN INTEGRATED POWER PRODUCTION', p.abstract_cn = '在各个方面，系统和方法提供用于集成的熔融碳酸盐燃料电池与费-托合成工艺。熔融碳酸盐燃料电池的可集成与费-托合成工艺的各种方式中，包括提供合成气生产烃类中使用的碳。此外，熔融碳酸盐燃料电池的集成与费-托合成过程排放的工艺气流的方便进一步加工或合成工艺中产生的二次产物流。', p.abstract_en = 'In various aspects,  systems and methods are provided for operating a molten carbonate fuel cell,  such as a fuel cell assembly,  with increased production of syngas while also reducing or minimizing the amount of CO2 exiting the fuel cell in the cathode exhaust stream. This can allow for improved efficiency of syngas production while also generating electrical power.', p.application_date = '2014-03-13 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'EP2969933A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/50', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'MX2015004534'}) SET p.application_no = 'MX2015004534', p.title_cn = '联合加氢处理。', p.title_en = 'INTEGRATED HYDROPROCESSING.', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种方法和系统的变换气以液体和精馏粗油或冷凝物。有利的是，它包括加氢处理该分馏产品的至少一部分和至少一部分所述费-托法产品在相同的加氢处理器。在其它优点中，本发明提供了改进的输出质量对柴油和/或石脑油，降低了运输和/或储存成本，和/或提高的能量效率。', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention relates to a method and system for converting gas to liquids and fractionating crude oil or condensate. Advantageously,  it includes hydroprocessing at least a portion of the fractionated product and at least a portion of the Fischer-Tropsch products in the same hydroprocessor. Among other advantages the present invention provides for improved output quality for diesel and/or naphtha,  reduced transportation and/or storage costs,  and/or enhanced energy efficiency.', p.application_date = '2013-10-08 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'MX2015004534A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/34', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'RU2014147118'}) SET p.application_no = 'RU2014147118', p.title_cn = '生产合成气的方法', p.title_en = 'METHOD OF PRODUCING SYNTHESIS GAS', p.abstract_cn = '领域 : 化学物质 : 启动该气体混合物包含甲烷和二氧化碳的混合物送入反应器中存在催化剂。使用的催化剂为复合氧化物，其包含钴(Co)，镍(Ni)，铜(Cu)，钕(Nd)和钙(Ca)离子，所述物质的摩尔比在催化剂相应于通式ndacabcucnidcoeof，其中a=0，1，2；b=0，1，2；c=0，1；d=0，1，2；e=0，1，2；f=3，4，5。该催化剂通过将起始剂物质在水中，蒸发形成的溶液增稠，干燥得到的产物在马弗炉中在250～°C煅烧$time，在900100a～°C。作为起始物质的水溶性化合物Nd，Ca，Co，Ni，Cu，形成所述金属的氧化物，煅烧。效果 : 甲烷的转化率高，最终产品的输出，进行该方法的工艺简单和进行了切割成本在没有惰性的方法气体，使用该所得到的催化剂使用较为简单的方法通过避免复杂步骤，研磨固体起始试剂和低催化剂焙烧过程temperature.10Cl，41EX，1TBL内。', p.abstract_en = 'FIELD :  chemistry. SUBSTANCE :  starting gas mixture containing a mixture of methane and carbon dioxide is fed into a reactor in which there is a catalyst. The catalyst used is a composite oxide which includes cobalt (Co),  nickel (Ni),  copper (Cu),  neodymium (Nd) and calcium (Ca) ions,  wherein the molar ratio of substances in the catalyst corresponds to the formula NdaCabCucNidCoeOf,  where a=0,  1,  2;  b=0,  1,  2;  c=0,  1;  d=0,  1,  2;  e=0,  1,  2;  f=3,  4,  5. The catalyst is obtained by dissolving starting substances in water,  evaporating the formed solution to thickening,  drying the obtained product in a muffle furnace at 250-350°C and calcining for 4-6 hours at 900-1000°C. As the starting substances water-soluble compounds of Nd,  Ca,  Co,  Ni,  Cu are used,  which form oxides of the said metals when calcined. EFFECT :  high conversion of methane and output of the end product,  simple technique of carrying out the method and cutting costs by carrying out the process in the absence of inert gases,  using the catalyst obtained using a simpler method by avoiding a complex step of grinding solid starting reagents and low catalyst calcination temperature. 10 cl,  41 ex,  1 tbl', p.application_date = '2014-11-25 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'RU2572530C1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'RU2013134616'}) SET p.application_no = 'RU2013134616', p.title_cn = '过程输入的自热反应器为操作', p.title_en = 'PROCEDURE FOR INPUT OF AUTOTHERMAL REACTORS INTO OPERATION', p.abstract_cn = '领域 : 油和天然气工业。物质 : 本发明涉及一种程序输入的自热反应器投入到运行中，以产生合成气的重整含碳进料气体在反应室。用于输入操作的目的的自热反应器的惰性流体预热达到温度更比600a°C，然后点火操作被启动，通过引入气体的气体混合物与各自的点火温度低，其低于点火温度的含碳进料气体。气体含量与着火温度低，在上述气体/气体混合物不低于40体积%。还启动的自热重整含碳原料气和水的蒸汽输送。含碳原料气和水的蒸汽输入与内容0-80体积%的水的蒸汽以以含碳进料气体。氧化剂送入氧含量为10-100体积%。结果产生的气态产物。效果 : 简单替换，提供了一种方法，用于输入关于启动操作设备和时间，不所需的附加时间用于启动和停止自热reactor.7Cl，1的DWG', p.abstract_en = 'FIELD :  oil and gas industry. SUBSTANCE :  invention relates to procedure for input of autothermal reactors into operation in order to produce synthetic gas by reforming of carbonaceous feed gases in the reaction chamber. For the purpose of input into operation the autothermal reactor is preheated by inert fluid up to temperature of more than 600°C. Then ignition operation is initiated by introduction of gas of gas mixture with the respective low ignition temperature,  which is below ignition temperature of carbonaceous feed gases. Content of the gas with low ignition temperature in the above gas/gas mixture is not less than 40 vol %. Further autothermal reforming is started by delivery of carbonaceous feed gas and water steam. Carbonaceous feed gas and water steam are delivered with content of water steam of 0-80 vol % in regard to carbonaceous feed gas. Oxidiser is delivered with oxygen content of 10-100 vol %. In result gaseous product is produced. EFFECT :  simpler alternative method is provided for input into operation in regard to start-up equipment and time,  without additional time required for start-up and stop of the autothermal reactor. 7 cl,  1 dwg', p.application_date = '2012-03-13 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'RU2572832C2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/34', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'RU2014147119'}) SET p.application_no = 'RU2014147119', p.title_cn = '生产合成气的方法', p.title_en = 'METHOD OF PRODUCING SYNTHESIS GAS', p.abstract_cn = '领域 : 化学物质 : 启动该气体混合物包含甲烷和分子氧的混合物送入反应器。催化剂置于反应器和空体积中充有惰性帽。所述的催化剂为复合氧化物通式ndacabcucnidcoeof，其中a=0，1，2；b=0，1，2；c=0，1；d=0，1，2；e=0，1，2；f=3，4，5。该催化剂通过将起始剂物质在水中，蒸发形成的溶液增稠，干燥得到的产物在马弗炉中在250～°C煅烧$time，在900100a～°C。作为起始物质的水溶性化合物Nd，Ca，Co，Ni，Cu，形成所述金属的氧化物，煅烧。效果 : 甲烷的转化率高和输出一氧化碳和氢气，进行该方法的工艺简单，成本低，process.10的Cl，1TBL，48EX', p.abstract_en = 'FIELD :  chemistry. SUBSTANCE :  starting gas mixture containing a mixture of methane and molecular oxygen is fed into a reactor. A catalyst is placed in the reactor and the empty volume is filled with an inert cap. The catalyst is a composite oxide of general formula NdaCabCucNidCOeOf,  where a=0,  1,  2;  b=0,  1,  2;  c=0,  1;  d=0,  1,  2;  e=0,  1,  2;  f=3,  4,  5. The catalyst is obtained by dissolving starting substances in water,  evaporating the formed solution to thickening,  drying the obtained product in a muffle furnace at 250-350°C and calcining for 4-6 hours at 900-1000°C. As the starting substances water-soluble compounds of Nd,  Ca,  Co,  Ni,  Cu are used,  which form oxides of the said metals when calcined. EFFECT :  high conversion of methane and output of carbon monoxide and hydrogen,  simple technique of carrying out the method and low cost of the process. 10 cl,  1 tbl,  48 ex', p.application_date = '2014-11-25 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'RU2573005C1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'BRPI0910164'}) SET p.application_no = 'BRPI0910164', p.title_cn = '使用胶态悬浮液，制氢过程，装置产生装置以产生氢的氢和使用', p.title_en = 'USE OF COLLOIDAL SUSPENSION,  PROCESS OF HYDROGEN PRODUCTION,  DEVICE TO GENERATE HYDROGEN AND USE OF DEVICE TO GENERATE HYDROGEN', p.abstract_cn = '描述了使用胶态悬浮体包括2和60%之间的碱性金属的颗粒上的 悬浮在中性疏水稀释剂用于制备气态氢，以及用于生产氢的方法。 还描述了一种氢生成装置及其使用。', p.abstract_en = 'Described is the use of a colloidal suspension that includes between 2 and 60% of alkaline metal particles that are suspended in a neutral hydrophobic diluent for producing gaseous hydrogen,  as well as a process for producing hydrogen. Also described is a hydrogen-generating device and its use.', p.application_date = '2009-06-23 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'BRPI0910164A2', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/08', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CA2694585'}) SET p.application_no = 'CA2694585', p.title_cn = '烃的部分氧化', p.title_en = 'PARTIAL OXIDATION OF HYDROCARBONS', p.abstract_cn = '烃的催化部分氧化的方法，特别是甲烷和/或天然气以形成含氢和一氧化碳的产品其中第一在催化剂入口具有更高的导热率比第第二催化剂更靠近出口。第二催化剂更靠近所述出口具有更高的表面积比第一在催化剂入口。', p.abstract_en = 'A process of catalytic partial oxidation of hydrocarbons,  particularly methane and/or natural gas to form a product containing hydrogen and carbon monoxide where the first catalyst at the inlet has a higher thermal conductivity than that of a second catalyst closer to the outlet. The second catalyst closer to the outlet has a higher surface area than that of the first catalyst at the inlet.', p.application_date = '2008-05-24 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CA2694585C', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2014127977'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2014127977', p.title_cn = '所述氢气产生装置，操作方法，及燃料电池系统', p.title_en = 'HYDROGEN GENERATOR AND METHOD FOR OPERATING THE SAME,  AND FUEL CELL SYSTEM', p.abstract_cn = '要解决的问题 : 从燃烧器中的燃烧气体在相对较短的停止时间，此外，无外部空气温度的影响，零点进行校正，提供一种装置，用于产生氢。方法 : 和从燃烧器12排出的废气和热回收介质在热交换器13，燃烧器12停止燃烧，在燃烧时空气供给单元14和16并通过驱动冷却水泵和空气供给到热回收介质和从换热供给空气所述CO传感器15，CO传感器15时，输出零的点存储为零点校正操作进行，CO传感器15在操作过程中零的点校正的供给的空气的温度，供给到热交换器13的热回收介质和可控制在温度范围。选择的绘图 : 图。1', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To provide a hydrogen generator capable of performing the zero point correction in a relatively short time from the stop of combustion in a combustor without being affected by the outside air temperature. SOLUTION :  Air and a heat recovery medium are supplied to a heat exchanger 13 for heat exchange between exhaust gas discharged from a combustor 12 and the heat recovery medium by driving a combustion air supply device 14 and a cooling water pump 16 during the stop of the combustor 12 to be heat-exchanged,  and then the air is supplied to a CO sensor 15 to perform zero point correction operation for storing the output of the CO sensor 15 at the time as a zero point,  whereby the temperature of the air supplied to the CO sensor 15 during the zero point correction operation can be controlled within a temperature range of the heat recovery medium supplied to the heat exchanger 13. COPYRIGHT :  (C)2016, JPO&INPIT', p.application_date = '2014-06-23 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP2016008147A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'TW104132584'}) SET p.application_no = 'TW104132584', p.title_cn = '氢或重氢的制造方法', p.title_en = 'Process for producing hydrogen or heavy hydrogens,  and hydrogenation (protiation,  deuteration or tritiation) of organic compounds using same', p.abstract_cn = '本发明之目的在於提供下述方法：在无须大规模的装置之情形下，简单地取得氢或重氢之方法；和可在不利用高价的反应试剂和特殊触媒之情形下，简单地实施氢化反应或重氢化反应之方法该方法为下述方法：一种氢或重氢的制造方法，其特徵在於：在触媒金属存在下，使水或重水进行机械化学反应；以及一种氢化有机化合物或重氢化有机化合物的制造方法，其特徵在於：在触媒金属存在下，使有机化合物与水或重水进行机械化学反应', p.abstract_en = 'An object is to provide a process for providing hydrogen or heavy hydrogens conveniently without the necessity of large-scale equipment and a process capable of performing hydrogenation (protiation,  deuteration or tritiation) reaction conveniently without the use of an expensive reagent and a special catalyst. The production process includes a process for producing hydrogen or heavy hydrogens,  containing subjecting water or heavy water to mechanochemical reaction in the presence of a catalyst metal,  and a process for producing a hydrogenated (protiated,  deuterated or tritiated) organic compound,  containing subjecting an organic compound and water or heavy water to mechanochemical reaction in the presence of a catalyst metal.', p.application_date = '2011-08-16 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'TW201601994A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'ATE765463'}) SET p.application_no = 'ATE765463', p.title_cn = '生产氨的方法和设备使补充合成气与空气分离单元为氮源', p.title_en = 'PROCESS AND EQUIPMENT FOR THE PRODUCTION OF AMMONIA MAKE-UP SYNGAS WITH AN AIR SEPARATION UNIT AS NITROGEN SOURCE', p.abstract_cn = '一种方法和一种用于生产化妆合成气(6)用于氨的合成，其中烃原料在主重整器(10)和在自热重整器(14)在平行于所述初级重整器；氮由空气分离单元(13)，和O2的富氧空气(8)中产生的所述空气分离装置被供给至自热重整器中。一种方法用于改造的氨厂的前端还公开了。', p.abstract_en = 'A process and a plant for producing a makeup synthesis gas (6) for the synthesis of ammonia where a hydrocarbon feedstock is reformed in a primary reformer (10) and in an autothermal reformer (14) in parallel with said primary reformer;  nitrogen is furnished by an air separation unit (13),  and O 2 -enriched air (8) produced in said air separation unit is fed to the autothermal reformer. A method for the revamping of the front-end of an ammonia plant is also disclosed.', p.application_date = '2009-10-09 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'ATE765463T1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'ATE765464'}) SET p.application_no = 'ATE765464', p.title_cn = '分切装置的化学化合物，和相关的方法', p.title_en = 'DEVICE FOR SPLITTING A CHEMICAL COMPOUND,  AND ASSOCIATED METHOD', p.abstract_cn = '分切装置的化学化合物(3)，包括温度控制装置(4)，两独立气室(6，7)，和元件(8)包括热释电材料，具有至少两个表面(10，11)具有不同的电荷的极性，并至少部分地接触所述化学化合物的被分体式。至少两个表面(10，11)每面一个所述分开的气室(6，7)，和气体(12)，13)在表面(10，11)分别到达气室与各自的相关表面(10，11)。', p.abstract_en = 'Device for splitting a chemical compound (3),  comprising a temperature control device (4),  two separate gas chambers (6,  7),  and an element (8) which comprises a pyroelectric material and has at least two surfaces (10,  11) that have charges of different polarity and are at least partially in contact with the chemical compound to be split. At least two of the surfaces (10,  11) each face one of the separate gas chambers (6,  7),  and the gases (12,  13) produced on the surfaces (10,  11) separately reach the gas chamber associated with the respective surface (10,  11).', p.application_date = '2012-02-07 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'ATE765464T1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'DE602006049541'}) SET p.application_no = 'DE602006049541', p.title_cn = '氢气纯化方法和系统', p.title_en = 'HYDROGEN PURIFICATION PROCESS AND SYSTEM', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种氢气发生系统，其包括燃料重整反应器产生富氢的重整气体的温度大于150℃，一种变压吸附(PSA)将重整气体中的氢精制装置成较纯的氢气流和一种废气流中，所述变压吸附单元，催化反应器的下游，其将含一氧化碳(CO)和氢气(H2)中相对纯的氢气物流转变成甲烷(CH4)和水蒸汽(H2O)。所述净化方法包括 : 产生富氢重整气中，在温度大于150℃燃料重整反应器，重整气体中分离成较纯的氢气流和废气流中的压力摆动吸附(psa)的氢精制装置，转换中所含一氧化碳(CO)和氢气(H2)的相对纯的氢气物流转变成甲烷(CH4)和水蒸汽(H2O)催化反应器中PSA装置的下游。所述氢可进一步纯化包括二次净化段下游的变压吸附装置和催化所述二次净化反应器级具有被水吸附材料吸附床的水汽H2O和氢吸收材料下游的优先吸水材料的吸氢气体，从而浓缩所述非氢气组分，例如CH4，进入排气流排出该层，所述吸收氢气再解吸出来以创建出非常纯的氢气流。', p.abstract_en = 'A hydrogen generation system is disclosed that includes a fuel reforming reactor generating a hydrogen-rich reformate gas at a temperature greater than 150 C,  a pressure swing adsorption (PSA) hydrogen purification unit that separates the reformate gas into a relatively pure hydrogen stream and an off-gas stream,  and a catalytic reactor down stream of the PSA unit that converts carbon monoxide (CO) and hydrogen (H2) contained in the relatively pure hydrogen stream into methane (CH4) and water vapor (H2O). The method of purification involves generating a hydrogen-rich reformate gas at a temperature greater than 150 C in a fuel reforming reactor,  separating the reformate gas into a relatively pure hydrogen stream and an off-gas stream in a pressure swing adsorption (PSA) hydrogen purification unit,  and converting carbon monoxide (CO) and hydrogen (H2) contained in the relatively pure hydrogen stream into methane (CH4) and water vapor (H2O) in a catalytic reactor down stream of the PSA unit. The hydrogen can be further purified by including a secondary purification stage downstream of the PSA unit and the catalytic reactor wherein the secondary purification stage has a water adsorbent material bed that adsorbs the water vapor H2O and a hydrogen absorbent material downstream of the water absorbent material that absorbs hydrogen gas preferentially,  thus concentrating the non-hydrogen components,  such as CH4,  into an exhaust stream that exits the bed,  wherein the absorbed hydrogen gas is then desorbed to create an exiting very pure hydrogen stream.', p.application_date = '2006-09-28 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'DE602006049541T2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/34', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'IDW00201304378'}) SET p.application_no = 'IDW00201304378', p.title_cn = '无水卤化氢和无水二氧化碳的合成方法', p.title_en = 'A process for synthesizing anhydrous hydrogen halide and anhydrous carbon dioxide', p.abstract_cn = '一种从有机卤化物流体合成无水卤化氢流体的方法，例如全氟化碳流体和制冷剂流体，以及用于其环境安全处置的无水二氧化碳。', p.abstract_en = 'A process for the synthesis of anhydrous hydrogen halide fluids,  such as perfluorocarbon fluids and refrigerant fluids,  and anhydrous carbon dioxide for environmentally safe disposal thereof,  from organic halide fluids.', p.application_date = '2013-09-24 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'IDW00201304378A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/16', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'KR1020157034353'}) SET p.application_no = 'KR1020157034353', p.title_cn = '氨和氢中使用的排出管线植物', p.title_en = 'VENT LINE FOR USE IN AMMONIA AND HYDROGEN PLANTS', p.abstract_cn = '脱硫室，修改的段和移位氨气或氢气中植物包括隔室，移隔室低温度变换转换器和机顶盒并在中间温度包括转炉移，变换炉低压力(典型为3至约7巴)的工艺气体重新是被加热为了允许温度漂移小，转换形成，作为在下中温变换炉侧通气管的设置。在本方式中的工艺气体避免了水蒸气的冷凝。为通气管的生产方法之后，施加用于重新生产暂停的周向驱动之间的长度，更特别地8约24时间节省，再循环相同的LTS/三氟化氮中的MTS可以避免由于SiGe膜加热转换器。', p.abstract_en = 'In an ammonia or hydrogen plant comprising a desulfurisation section,  a reforming section and a shift section,  where the shift section comprises a low temperature shift converter and a medium temperature shift converter,  a vent line is arranged downstream from the low temperature shift converter and the medium temperature shift converter in order to allow the shift converters to be re-heated with process gas at a low pressure (typically 3-7 bar). This way condensation of water vapour in the process gas is avoided. By applying this vent line it becomes possible to save significant time,  more specifically 8-24 hours,  for restarting the production after temporary shut-down thereof,  because a heat-up of the LTS/MTS converter in circulating nitrogen is avoided.', p.application_date = '2014-04-16 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'KR1020160005732A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'AU2013201704'}) SET p.application_no = 'AU2013201704', p.title_cn = '用于氢生产的装置和方法和其应用', p.title_en = 'APPARATUS AND METHOD FOR HYDROGEN PRODUCTION AND USE OF SAME', p.abstract_cn = '代理人REF。h43-004d(au)抽象制氢的装置和方法，和使用同一本发明涉及一种用于生产含氢5的气体，包括反应器通常有水平管状型材。反应器设有第一进送的含烃气体到反应器，第第二入口，它用于引入催化剂反应器便于含烃的裂化气和氢气，固体碳，用于容纳催化剂的反应区操作时，第第一出口，该出口允许产品气体出口0反应器，加热区和/或预热区，和冷却区和/或加热区，以及用于输送或以其它方式运送催化剂从加热区和/或冷却区的预热区和/或加热区。40', p.abstract_en = 'Attorney Ref. H43-004D(AU) Abstract Apparatus and Method for Hydrogen Production,  And Use of Same The present invention is concerned with an apparatus for production of a hydrogen 5 containing gas,  comprising a reactor generally with a horizontal tubular profile. The reactor is provided with a first inlet for feeding a hydrocarbon-containing gas to the reactor,  a second inlet for introducing a catalyst to the reactor facilitating cracking of the hydrocarbon-containing gas to hydrogen and solid carbon,  a reaction zone for accommodating the catalyst during operation,  a first outlet allowing product gas to exit 0 the reactor,  a heating zone and/or a preheating zone,  and a cooling zone and/or a heating zone,  and means for conveying or otherwise transporting the catalyst from the heating zone and/or the cooling zone to the preheating zone and/or the heating zone. 40', p.application_date = '2013-03-20 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'AU2013201704B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/26', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'DE202015007876'}) SET p.application_no = 'DE202015007876', p.title_cn = '[…]用于生产含氢气体从液化气', p.title_en = 'Compact reformer for the production of a hydrogen-containing gas from liquefied petroleum gas', p.abstract_cn = '液气证明[…]，其特征在于紧凑的重整炉单元由至少一个，优选两个组合具有更高烃化合物的至少单级蒸汽重整℃裂解(任选地)运行，随后的气体净化。', p.abstract_en = 'liquid gas-claimant[...] ,  characterized in that a compact reformer unit consisting of at least one,  preferably two combined with a higher hydrocarbon compounds at least single-stage steam reforming [...] for cleavage (optionally) Running and subsequent gas purification.', p.application_date = '2015-11-12 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'DE202015007876U1', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/32', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'DE502005015026'}) SET p.application_no = 'DE502005015026', p.title_cn = '用于产生氢的方法和装置', p.title_en = 'METHOD AND DEVICE FOR THE GENERATION OF HYDROGEN', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种方法和一种装置用于产生氢，在内燃机中燃料的燃烧或炉窑使用。按本发明，装置(7，8)提供受试者的燃料和/或进气声音，由此产生氢气。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a method and a device for the generation of hydrogen,  on the combustion of fuels in internal combustion engines or furnaces. According to the invention,  means (7,  8) are provided which subject the fuel and/or the inlet air to sound,  whereupon hydrogen is generated.', p.application_date = '2005-02-18 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'DE502005015026T2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'SG2013095765'}) SET p.application_no = 'SG2013095765', p.title_cn = '还原气体发生器和用于产生还原气体的方法', p.title_en = 'REDUCING GAS GENERATORS AND METHODS FOR GENERATING REDUCING GAS', p.abstract_cn = '本发明的一个实施例是独特的还原气体发生器。 另一个实施方案是用于产生还原气体的独特方法。 其他实施例包括用于产生还原气体的装置、系统、设备、硬件、方法和组合。 本申请的其他实施例、形式、特征、方面、益处和优点将从本文提供的描述和附图中变得显而易见。', p.abstract_en = 'One embodiment of the present invention is a unique reducing gas generator. Another embodiment is a unique method for generating a reducing gas. Other embodiments include apparatuses,  systems,  devices,  hardware,  methods,  and combinations for generating reducing gas. Further embodiments,  forms,  features,  aspects,  benefits,  and advantages of the present application will become apparent from the description and figures provided herewith.', p.application_date = '2012-06-26 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'SG195950B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/36', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14772944'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14772944', p.title_cn = '甲酸制氢气的方法', p.title_en = 'METHOD FOR PRODUCING HYDROGEN GAS FROM FORMIC ACID', p.abstract_cn = '一种由甲酸生产氢气的方法，其特征在于使用至少一种多相催化剂将甲酸转化为氢气。 所述至少一种多相催化剂包含多相钌。 根据本发明的第一方面，所述至少一种多相催化剂包含至少一种亲水性膦配体，所述亲水性膦配体是M-TPPTS(间三磺化三苯基膦)。 所述至少一种多相催化剂优选通过将RuCl3的水溶液与亲水性膦混合而获得，所述亲水性膦首先通过与甲酸进行均相反应并通过加入至少一种固体结构而活化。', p.abstract_en = 'A method for producing A hydrogen gas from formic acid,  characterized in that at least one heterogeneous catalyst is used to transform the formic acid into hydrogen gas. The at least one heterogeneous catalyst contains heterogenised ruthenium. According to a first aspect of the invention,  the at least one heterogeneous catalyst contains at least one hydrophilic phosphine ligand which is m-TPPTS (meta-trisulfonated triphenylphosphine). The at least one heterogeneous catalyst is preferably obtained by mixing an aqueous solution of RuCl3 with hydrophilic phosphine,  firstly activated by carrying out a homogeneous reaction with formic acid and by adding at least one solid structure.', p.application_date = '2013-03-06 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US20160009553A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/22', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 2, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14771218'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14771218', p.title_cn = '熔融金属气化炉', p.title_en = 'MOLTEN METAL GASIFIER', p.abstract_cn = '一种用于将至少一种含碳的进料燃料材料气化成合成气的设备， 在超过大气压的总压力下，包括用于容纳熔融金属的坩埚装置，所述坩埚包括用于在熔融金属的表面下方喷射至少一种进料燃料材料、氧化剂气体或其组合的喷射装置，连接到所述坩埚装置的排气管，用于从所述坩埚装置排出合成气，冷却连接到所述排气管的所述合成气以与所述坩埚装置形成密封单元的冷却装置，以及用于从所述坩埚装置排出炉渣的出钢装置。', p.abstract_en = 'An apparatus for gasification of at least one feed fuel material containing carbon into syngas,  under a total pressure which exceeds atmospheric pressure comprises a crucible means for containing molten metal,  said crucible including injection means for injecting at least one feed fuel material,  oxidant gas,  or a combination thereof,  beneath the surface of the molten metal,  an exhaust pipe connected to said crucible means for discharge of syngas therefrom,  cooling means for cooling said syngas connected to said exhaust pipe to form a sealed unit with said crucible means,  and tapping means for discharge of slag from said crucible means.', p.application_date = '2014-02-28 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US20160009554A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/24', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WODK15050206'}) SET p.application_no = 'WODK15050206', p.title_cn = '用于生产氢的工艺', p.title_en = 'PROCESS FOR PRODUCING HYDROGEN', p.abstract_cn = '氢的制造方法，其中尾气从arate植物用于生产汽油或柴油加入下游的蒸汽甲烷重整阶段和水煤气变换级的上游制氢装置。', p.abstract_en = 'Process for producing hydrogen in which tail gas from a separate plant for production of gasoline or diesel is added downstream the steam methane reforming stage and upstream the water gas shift stage of a hydrogen production plant.', p.application_date = '2015-07-08 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016004955A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/34', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WOEP15065332'}) SET p.application_no = 'WOEP15065332', p.title_cn = '用于生产合成气物流的方法', p.title_en = 'A METHOD FOR PRODUCING A SYNGAS STREAM', p.abstract_cn = '本发明提供了一种合成气物流的生产方法，该方法至少包括步骤 : (a)提供含烃物流；(b)提供含反应器加热的固体在温度至少100A～°C；(c)裂解所述含烃流在步骤(a)中的反应器含有加热固体物设置在步骤(b)中，从而至少得到C和H2；(d)除去含H2的物流从反应器；(e)将步骤(c)中得到的C在反应器中以H2O/CO2体积。%的进料比大于零，从而获得含CO\\H2流；(f)去除CO/H2含流从反应器；含H2的物流除去结合(g)在步骤(d)中与CO/H2含流，在步骤(f)，从而去除获得合成气料流。', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention provides a method for producing a syngas stream,  the method at least comprising the steps of :  (a) providing a hydrocarbon-containing stream;  (b) providing a reactor containing a heated mass of solids at a temperature of at least 1000°C;  (c) cracking the hydrocarbon-containing stream provided in step (a) in the reactor containing the heated mass of solids provided in step (b),  thereby at least obtaining C and H2;  (d) removing an H2-containing stream from the reactor;  (e) converting the C obtained in step (c) in the reactor at an H2O/CO2 vol.% feed ratio of greater than zero,  thereby obtaining a CO/H2-containing stream;  (f) removing the CO/H2-containing stream from the reactor;  (g) combining the H2-containing stream removed in step (d) with the CO/H2-containing stream removed in step (f) thereby obtaining a syngas stream.', p.application_date = '2015-07-06 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016005317A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/24', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201110354140.5'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201110354140.5', p.title_cn = '制氢装置', p.title_en = 'Hydrogen production device', p.abstract_cn = '本发明提供了一种能源效率良好、能够高效地制备氢气、能够适用于小型制氢装置的制氢方法、以及用于该方法的装置。本发明提供的制氢方法用于由甲醇制备氢气，其特征在于，其包括：原料气体制备工序，通过使甲醇和水气化来制备原料气体；反应气体制备工序，通过使原料气体与含氧气体反应来制备反应气体；氢气分离工序，从反应气体中分离该反应气体中所含的氢气；以及残留气体燃烧工序，使从反应气体中分离出氢气后的残留气体燃烧，并且，在原料气体制备工序中利用在残留气体燃烧工序中燃烧残留气体时产生的热使甲醇和水气化，并且在反应气体制备工序中，利用在残留气体燃烧工序中燃烧残留气体时产生的热使原料气体与含氧气体反应。', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To provide a hydrogen gas production method which is excellent in energy efficiency,  enables hydrogen gas to be efficiently produced,  and can be applied to a miniaturized hydrogen gas production apparatus,  and to provide an apparatus used in the method.SOLUTION :  The hydrogen gas production method for producing hydrogen gas from methanol includes :  a raw material gas production step of producing a raw material gas by vaporizing methanol and water;  a reaction product gas production step of producing a reaction product gas by reacting the raw material gas with an oxygen-containing gas;  a hydrogen gas separation step of separating hydrogen gas contained in the reaction product gas from the reaction product gas;  and a residual gas combustion step of combusting residual gas left by separating the hydrogen gas from the reaction product gas,  wherein,  by heat generated during combusting the residual gas in the residual gas combustion step,  methanol and water are vaporized in the raw material gas production step and the resulting raw material gas is reacted with an oxygen-containing gas in the reaction product gas production step. The apparatus used in the method is also provided.', p.application_date = '2011-11-10 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN102530866B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/36', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201180035235.9'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201180035235.9', p.title_cn = '使合成气和合成气衍生产物的产率最大化的气化系统和工艺', p.title_en = 'The synthesis gas and the synthesis gas derived product to maximize the yield of the gasification system and process', p.abstract_cn = '气化系统和方法。该系统可包括气化器和流体偶联到气化器的净化单元，该净化单元接收来自气化器的粗合成气并产生废气和合成气产物。该系统还可包括流体偶联到净化单元的第一重整器，该第一重整器接收所述废气的第一部分并产生重整烃。该系统可进一步包括第二重整器，其具有流体偶联到净化单元的第一入口、流体偶联到第一重整器的第二入口和流体偶联到净化单元的出口。该第二入口从第一重整器接收重整烃，该第一入口接收来自净化单元的所述废气的第二部分。第二重整器可产生导入净化单元的回收粗合成气。', p.abstract_en = 'A gasification system and method. The system can include a gasifier and a purification unit fluidly coupled to the gasifier,  with the purification unit receiving raw syngas from the gasifier and producing waste gas and a syngas product. The system can also include a first reformer fluidly coupled to the purification unit,  with the first reformer receiving a first portion of the waste gas and producing reformed hydrocarbon. The system can further include a second reformer having a first inlet fluidly coupled to the purification unit,  a second inlet fluidly coupled to the first reformer,  and an outlet fluidly coupled to the purification unit. The second inlet can receive the reformed hydrocarbon from the first reformer,  and the first inlet can receive a second portion of the waste gas from the purification unit. The second reformer can produce a recovered raw syngas that is directed to the purification unit.', p.application_date = '2011-05-04 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN102985355B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201180040072.3'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201180040072.3', p.title_cn = '氢或重氢的制造方法及利用该制造方法而进行的有机化合物的氢化或重氢化', p.title_en = 'Hydrogen or deuterium and method of manufacturing by the manufacturing method of an organic compound by hydrogenation or Deuteration', p.abstract_cn = '本发明的目的在于提供下述方法：在无须大规模的装置的情形下，简单地取得氢或重氢的方法；可在不利用高价的反应试剂和特殊催化剂的情形下，简单地实施氢化反应或重氢化反应的方法。该制造方法为下述方法：一种氢或重氢的制造方法，其特征在于在催化剂金属的存在下使水或重水进行机械化学反应；以及一种氢化有机化合物或重氢化有机化合物的制造方法，其特征在于在催化剂金属的存在下使有机化合物与水或重水进行机械化学反应。', p.abstract_en = 'An object is to provide a process for providing hydrogen or heavy hydrogens conveniently without the necessity of large-scale equipment and a process capable of performing hydrogenation (protiation,  deuteration or tritiation) reaction conveniently without the use of an expensive reagent and a special catalyst. The production process includes a process for producing hydrogen or heavy hydrogens,  containing subjecting water or heavy water to mechanochemical reaction in the presence of a catalyst metal,  and a process for producing a hydrogenated (protiated,  deuterated or tritiated) organic compound,  containing subjecting an organic compound and water or heavy water to mechanochemical reaction in the presence of a catalyst metal.', p.application_date = '2011-08-16 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN103068721B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201110449278.3'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201110449278.3', p.title_cn = '一种移动床轻烃蒸汽转化制氢方法和装置', p.title_en = 'A moving bed hydrocarbon steam reforming hydrogen production method and apparatus', p.abstract_cn = '一种移动床轻烃蒸汽转化制氢方法和装置，包括：轻烃和水蒸气预热后由底部进入反应器，与粒径不同的重整催化剂和吸附催化剂逆流接触，轻烃和水蒸气在蒸汽重整条件下反应生成H2、CO和CO2，CO2与吸附催化剂中的CaO反应转化为CaCO3；反应生成的产物气体由反应器顶部气固分离后进入后续提纯分离装置获得高纯度氢气；混合催化剂由反应器底部进入筛分分离器按粒径大小分离，分离出的重整催化剂返回移动床反应器中循环使用，分离出的吸附催化剂经再生后返回移动床反应器循环使用。本发明提供的方法和装置省去了重整活性组元Ni频繁高温氧化为NiO后在还原器中还原成金属Ni过程，简化了工艺过程，延长催化剂的寿命并降低了系统能耗。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a method for hydrogen production by light hydrocarbon steam reforming in a moving bed and a device. The method includes :  preheating light hydrocarbon and steam,  then leading them into a reactor from the bottom to undergo countercurrent contact with a reforming catalyst and a adsorption catalyst with different particle sizes,  making the light hydrocarbon and steam react under steam reforming conditions to generate H2,  CO and CO2,  with the CO2 reacting with CaO in the adsorption catalyst to convert to CaCO3;  subjecting the product gas generated by the reaction to gas-solid separation at the reactor top,  then bringing the gas into a subsequent purification separation apparatus so as to obtain high purity hydrogen;  letting the mixed catalyst enter a screening separator to undergo separation according to particle size,  returning the separated reforming catalyst to the moving bed reactor to realize cycle use,  and regenerating the separated adsorption catalyst and returning it to the moving bed reactor to realize cycle use. With the method and the device provided in the invention,  the process of reducing NiO into metal Ni in a reducer after frequent high temperature oxidation of the reforming active component Ni into NiO can be omitted,  the technological process is simplified,  the catalyst service life is prolonged,  and the system energy consumption is reduced.', p.application_date = '2011-12-29 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN103183318B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201310426155.7'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201310426155.7', p.title_cn = '四氢噻吩作为水合物促进剂的应用', p.title_en = 'Tetrahydrothiophene as hydrate promoter application', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了四氢噻吩作为水合物促进剂的应用，四氢噻吩作为不溶于水且沸点高的水合物促进剂极大地降低了水合物生成条件，提高水合物形成温度，可使气体水合物生成温度在相同压力下提高20～29℃，极大地促进了气体水合物生成，水合物生成速率在0.1～0.5mol·min-1·m-3，且四氢噻吩可作为水合物促进剂回收再利用。', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention discloses the application of tetrahydrothiophene as hydrate promoter Tetrahydrothiophene,  as a water-insoluble and high-boiling hydrate accelerator,  greatly reduces the hydrate formation conditions Increasing the hydrate formation temperature can increase the gas hydrate formation temperature by 20 to 29 °C under the same pressure,  which greatly promotes the formation of gas hydrates. The hydrate formation rate is 0.1 to 0.5 mol.min-1. m-3. And tetrahydrothiophene can be recycled as a hydrate accelerator.', p.application_date = '2013-09-17 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN103466547B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/50', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201310690269.2'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201310690269.2', p.title_cn = '一种利用高温水蒸气气化生物质制取氢气的方法及装置', p.title_en = 'A use of high-temperature vapor and gasifying biomass method and apparatus for producing hydrogen', p.abstract_cn = '一种利用高温水蒸气气化生物质制取氢气的方法及装置，属于生物质气化技术领域。它高温气化反应器、多流体热交换器、H2分离器装置、燃气燃烧器、氢氧燃烧器等构成。气化需要的高温水蒸气来自纯O2和H2的燃烧，在反应器加热夹套中通入燃气燃烧维持反应器内的温度。氢氧燃烧器喷出的高温水蒸气的温度高于1600℃，高温气化反应器中的温度为1300～1500℃。排放烟气和合成气的废热通过多流体热交换器回收用于加热H2和O2，通过分离器装置将气化合成气分离为H2和燃气两部分。本气化装置具有：产氢率高、不需要催化剂、直接输出纯H2等特点。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention discloses a method and a device for preparing hydrogen by gasifying biomass through high temperature steam,  which belong to the technical field of biomass gasification. The device is composed of a high temperature gasification reactor,  a multi-fluid heat exchanger,  an H2 separator device,  a gas burner,  an oxygen-hydrogen burner and the like. High temperature steam necessary for gasification comes from combustion of pure O2 and H2,  and a fuel gas is filled in a heating jacket of the reactor to maintain the temperature in the reactor;  the temperature of the high temperature steam ejected from the oxygen-hydrogen burner is higher than 1600 DEG C,  and the temperature in the high temperature gasification reactor is 1300-1500 DEG C;  waste heat of exhausted flue gas and a synthesis gas is recycled by the multi-fluid heat exchanger for heating the H2 and O2,  and the gasification synthesis gas is separated into H2 and a fuel gas by the separator device. The gasification device has the advantages that the hydrogen production rate is high,  no catalyst is needed,  and pure H2 is directly output,  and the like.', p.application_date = '2013-12-16 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN103708417B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/22', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201310060237.4'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201310060237.4', p.title_cn = '一种制氢过程变换气脱除二氧化碳的方法', p.title_en = 'A hydrogen production process,  the method of removing carbon dioxide conversion gas', p.abstract_cn = '本发明属于气体分离领域，涉及一种制氢过程变换气脱除二氧化碳的方法。本发明采用的技术方案是：需要脱除CO2的制氢过程变换气先进入物理吸收塔的下部进行初步吸收后，进入化学吸收塔的下部进行二次吸收，吸收过的物理溶剂经富液泵送入低压闪蒸罐进行再生，再生后的物理溶剂贫液经物理溶剂贫液泵返回物理吸收塔；化学吸收液富液经化学吸收液富液泵送入再生塔进行再生，再生后的化学吸收液贫液经化学吸收液贫液泵返回化学吸收塔；再生塔塔顶CO2气体经再生塔冷凝器气液分离后和从闪蒸罐顶部分离出来的CO2一起经加压储存利用。本发明采用物理吸收和化学吸收相结合，在提高二氧化碳脱除效率的同时尽可能降低过程能耗。', p.abstract_en = 'Belonging to the field of gas separation,  the invention relates to a method for removal of CO2 from shift gas during hydrogen production. According to a technical scheme adopted by the invention,  a hydrogen production process shift gas needing removal of CO2 firstly enters the lower part of a physical absorption tower to undergo preliminary absorption,  then enters the lower part of a chemical absorption tower to undergo secondary absorption,  an absorbed physical solvent is sent into a low pressure flash tank by a rich solution pump to undergo regeneration,  and a regenerated physical solvent barren solution is returned to the physical absorption tower by a physical solvent barren solution pump;  a chemical absorption liquid rich solution is sent into a regeneration tower by a chemical absorption liquid rich solution pump to undergo regeneration,  and a regenerated chemical absorption liquid barren solution is returned to the chemical absorption tower by a chemical absorption liquid barren solution pump;  the regeneration tower top CO2 gas undergoes gas-liquid separation by a regeneration tower condenser,  and then undergoes pressurized storage utilization together with the CO2 separated from the flash tank top. By combining physical absorption and chemical absorption,  the method provided by the invention improves the CO2 removal efficiency and simultaneously lowers the process energy consumption as much as possible.', p.application_date = '2013-02-19 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN103991845B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/50', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201510589625.0'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201510589625.0', p.title_cn = '一种硼氢化钠水解供氢方法及其装置', p.title_en = 'Sodium-borohydride hydrolysis hydrogen-supplying method and apparatus thereof', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种硼氢化钠水解供氢方法及其装置，包括硼氢化钠存储室(3)、制氢室(7)、空心接头(2)；所述硼氢化钠存储室(3)与制氢室(7)通过分隔板盘(4)连接；所述分隔板盘(4)包括分隔衬板、转盘以及旋钮(5)，供氢时，旋转旋钮(5)，使得转盘与分隔衬板相互转动，将硼氢化钠存储室(3)内存储的硼氢化钠溶液通过第一通孔与第二通孔形成的通道流入到制氢室(7)内；当硼氢化钠溶液与制氢室(7)内的催化剂接触时，产生氢气；氢气经由第一通孔与第二通孔形成的通道进入到硼氢化钠存储室(3)内，再通过空心接头(2)进入到用氢设备。本发明不仅成本低廉，而且实现了高纯氢的现场制取与利用。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention provides a sodium-borohydride hydrolysis hydrogen-supplying method and an apparatus thereof. The apparatus comprises a sodium borohydride storage chamber (3),  a hydrogen-producing chamber (7) and a hollow joint (2);  the sodium borohydride storage chamber (3) is connected with the hydrogen-producing chamber (7) via a separation plate (4);  the separation plate (4) comprises a separation lining plate,  a rotary disk and a button (5),  when hydrogen is supplied,  the button (5) is turned for enabling the rotary disk rotates relative to the separation lining plate,  thus a sodium borohydride solution stored in the sodium borohydride storage chamber (3) flows into the hydrogen-producing chamber (7) via a channel formed by a first through hole and a second through hole;  when the sodium borohydride solution is contacted with a catalyst in the hydrogen-producing chamber (7),  hydrogen is generated;  and hydrogen enters the sodium borohydride storage chamber (3) via the channel formed by the first through hole and the second through hole,  and then enters hydrogen using equipment via the hollow joint (2). According to the technical scheme,  the cost is low,  and also on-site preparation and utilization of high-purity hydrogen are realized.', p.application_date = '2015-09-16 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105236351A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/06', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201510800901.3'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201510800901.3', p.title_cn = '直接耦合微波液相等离子体醇类制氢装置及方法', p.title_en = 'Direct coupling microwave liquid-phase plasma alcohol hydrogen production device and method', p.abstract_cn = '本发明提供一种直接耦合微波液相等离子体醇类制氢装置及方法，包括：微波发生器、矩形波导管、液相放电电极、反应器、进料管、排气管、收气管、原料罐、复合真空计和金属套管，所述反应器为石英材料、陶瓷材料或者其混合物；所述反应器的上部连接所述复合真空计、所述进料管和所述排气管，所述进料管和所述排气管的另一端连接于所述原料罐，所述反应器的下部垂直穿过所述矩形波导管并嵌套于所述金属套管，所述金属套管焊接在所述矩形波导下部，所述液相放电电极置于所述金属套管内，所述矩形波导一端连接于所述微波发生器，所述原料罐顶部与所述收气管连接。本发明提高了液相微波等离子体醇类制氢的工作效率。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention provides a direct coupling microwave liquid-phase plasma alcohol hydrogen production device and method. The device comprises a microwave generator,  a rectangular waveguide tube,  a liquid-phase discharge electrode,  a reactor,  a feed tube,  an exhaust tube,  a gas collecting tube,  a raw material tank,  a composite vacuum gauge and a metal sleeve. The reactor is made of a quartz material or a ceramic material or a mixture of the quartz material and the ceramic material. The upper portion of the reactor is connected with the composite vacuum gauge,  the feed tube and the exhaust tube. The other end of the feed tube and the other end of the exhaust tube are connected to the raw material tank. The lower portion of the reactor vertically penetrates through the rectangular waveguide tube and is nested in the metal sleeve,  and the metal sleeve is welded to the lower portion of the rectangular waveguide tube. The liquid-phase discharge electrode is arranged in the metal sleeve. One end of the rectangular waveguide tube is connected to the microwave generator. The top of the raw material tank is connected with the gas collecting tube. By the adoption of the device and method,  working efficiency of liquid-phase microwave plasma alcohol hydrogen production is improved.', p.application_date = '2015-11-19 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105236352A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/32', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201520544537.4'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201520544537.4', p.title_cn = '一种连续式秸秆超临界水制氢装置', p.title_en = 'Continuous type straw supercritical water hydrogen plant', p.abstract_cn = '本实用新型涉及一种连续式秸秆超临界水制氢装置，属于化学反应装置技术领域。本实用新型包括进料斗、阀门Ⅰ、阀门Ⅱ、料腔Ⅱ、活塞Ⅱ、水腔Ⅱ、送料装置、阀门Ⅳ、阀门Ⅲ、料腔Ⅰ、活塞Ⅰ、阀门Ⅴ、阀门Ⅶ、水腔Ⅰ、阀门Ⅵ、阀门Ⅷ、高压计量泵、水箱、集液罐、反应环管、预热管、气液分离器、提纯器、集气罐。本实用新型在一个送料装置中实现了切换连续送料，节省了设备；反应环管设计成环形是为了在将反应产物送回预热器时减少热量损失；环管内加热丝的均匀布置保证管内温度均一；预热管的设计使反应产物的热量得到回收利用，同时预热反应物能使其在反应时迅速达到所需温度；本装置具有结构简单、使用方便、热利用率高以及生产效率高等特点。', p.abstract_en = 'The utility model relates to a continuous type straw supercritical water hydrogen plant belongs to chemical reaction device technical field. The utility model discloses a feeder hopper,  valve I,  valve II,  material chamber II,  piston II,  water cavity II,  material feeding unit,  valve IV,  valve III,  material chamber I,  piston I,  valve V,  valve VII,  water cavity I,  valve VI,  valve VIII,  high pressure measurement pump,  water tank,  liquid -collecting tank,  reaction ring canal,  economizer bank,  vapour and liquid separator,  purifier,  gas collection jar. The utility model discloses realized switching continuous pay -off in a material feeding unit,  saved equipment,  it is in order to reduce calorific loss when sending reaction product back to pre -heater that the design of reaction ring canal circularizes,  intraductal temperature homogeneous is guaranteed in evenly arranging of ring canal internal heating silk,  the design of economizer bank makes reaction product\'s heat obtain recycle,  preheats the reactant simultaneously and enables it reach the desired temperature rapidly when the reaction,  this device has characteristics such as simple structure,  convenient to use,  heat utilization efficiency height and production efficiency height.', p.application_date = '2015-07-27 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN204958381U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201520688604.X'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201520688604.X', p.title_cn = '一种变换冷凝液入洗涤塔的装置', p.title_en = 'Device of scrubbing tower is gone into to transform condensate', p.abstract_cn = '一种变换冷凝液入洗涤塔的装置，除氧器通过管线连接高压灰水泵，高压灰水泵的出口分为两路，分别通过自调阀连接在洗涤塔入口处；变换装置缓冲罐的有高温冷凝液泵，高温冷凝液泵的出口分为两路，一路通过自调阀连接在洗涤塔入口处，另一路通过凝液管线经自调阀与手阀后连接洗涤塔的入口处；变换装置的凝液经过高温冷凝液泵加压后，管道输送进洗涤塔，经过洗涤塔预留口进洗涤塔，经处理后的灰水经高压灰水泵加压后管道输送至洗涤塔，不与高温冷凝液泵加压的变换装置凝液进洗涤塔中部管线汇合；本实用新型具有结构简单，造价低廉，确保变换装置能够稳定运行，减少系统需水量及外排水量，保证系统稳定运行的特点。', p.abstract_en = 'The utility model provides a device of scrubbing tower is gone into to transform condensate,  oxygen -eliminating device pass through the grey water pump of pipeline connection high pressure,  and high -pressure buck delivery side of pump is divided into two the tunnel,  connect in the scrubbing tower entrance through the self -modulation valve respectively,  the converting means buffer tank have a high temperature condensation liquid pump,  high temperature condensate delivery side of pump is divided into two the tunnel,  connects in the scrubbing tower entrance through the self -modulation valve all the way,  the scrubbing tower is connected to the lime set pipeline behind self -modulation valve and hand valve entrance is crossed to another sweetgum fruit,  converting means\'s lime set is after the pressurization of high temperature condensation liquid pump,  and the pipe -line transportation advances the scrubbing tower,  reserves the mouth through the scrubbing tower and advances the scrubbing tower,  through pipe -line transportation to the scrubbing tower after high -pressure grey water pump pressurizes of the buck after handling,  does not advance scrubbing tower middle part pipeline with the pressor converting means lime set of high temperature condensation liquid pump and converges,  the utility model has the characteristics of simple structure,  low in cost ensures that converting means can the steady operation,  reduces system\'s water requirement and outer displacement,  assurance system steady operation.', p.application_date = '2015-09-07 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN204958382U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201520578541.2'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201520578541.2', p.title_cn = '一种甲醇合成氢回收尾气的回收利用系统', p.title_en = 'Recycle system of tail gas is retrieved to methanol synthesis hydrogen', p.abstract_cn = '本实用新型公开了一种甲醇合成氢回收尾气的回收利用系统，包括氢回收装置2、锅炉6、流量计8、中变炉13、低变炉14、脱碳装置16、氢氮气压缩机17、氨合成塔18、氢气压缩机20，其特征在于所述氢回收装置2渗透气出口2a连接至氢气压缩机20，所述氢回收装置2尾气出口2b依次连接流量计8、减压阀10、中变炉13、低变炉14、脱碳装置15、甲烷化炉16、氢氮气压缩机17、氨合成塔18，所述氢回收装置2尾气出口2b还依次连接减压阀5、锅炉6。本实用新型改变了甲醇合成氢回收装置尾气送至锅炉掺烧的传统方式，通过将其改送至中变炉入口，并入天然气制氨生产系统，经变换、净化、压缩及氨合成工序，将尾气中的H2、CO等有效气加以回收并用以生产合成氨。通过以上措施，使得由原料煤经过气化、变换等一系列工序产生的具有较高利用价值的有效气得以回收利用，天然气制氨系统吨氨天然气耗量明显下降。', p.abstract_en = 'The utility model discloses a recycle system of tail gas is retrieved to methanol synthesis hydrogen,  including hydrogen recovery unit 2,  boiler 6,  flowmeter 8,  well changes stove 13,  low change stove 14,  decarbonization device 16,  hydrogen nitrogen compressor 17,  ammonia converter 18,  hydrogen compressor 20,  its characterized in that hydrogen recovery unit 2 infiltration gas export 2a is connected to hydrogen compressor 20,  hydrogen recovery unit 2 tail gas export 2b connects gradually flowmeter 8,  relief pressure valve 10,  well changes stove 13,  low change stove 14,  decarbonization device 15,  methanation stove 16,  hydrogen nitrogen compressor 17,  ammonia converter 18,  hydrogen recovery unit 2 tail gas export 2b still connects gradually relief pressure valve 5,  boiler 6. The utility model discloses change methanol synthesis hydrogen recovery unit tail gas and delivered to traditional mode that the fever is mixed to the boiler,  delivered to the well stove entry that becomes through changing it to go into natural gas system ammonia production system,  through transform,  purification,  compression and ammonia synthesis process,  with the H2 in the tail gas,  CO etc. Effectively gas retrieve and be used for producing synthetic ammonia. Through above measure for by the raw materials coal through the productions of a series of processes such as gasification,  transform have a higher value be so incensed that effectively with recycle that natural gas system ammonia system ton ammonia natural gas consumption obviously descends.', p.application_date = '2015-08-05 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN204958383U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/50', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201520675943.4'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201520675943.4', p.title_cn = '一种混合煤气净化系统', p.title_en = 'Mix coal gas clean system', p.abstract_cn = '本实用新型公开了一种混合煤气净化系统，包括变换冷却装置、至少两个预洗装置、低温甲醇洗脱硫塔、低温甲醇洗脱碳塔、液氮洗装置、变压吸附装置、甲烷蒸汽转化/CO变换装置；所述预洗装置与变换冷却装置连通，所述脱硫塔的进气口与各预洗装置连通，所述脱硫塔的出气口分别与变压吸附装置和脱碳塔连通，所述甲烷蒸汽转化/CO变换装置的进气口分别与变压吸附装置和液氮洗装置的连通；该系统通过加大预洗阶段混合煤气的处理量，并将预洗后的煤气经脱硫处理后分两路进行净化处理，通过调整预洗装置的数量、开度就可以提高混合煤气净化系统的煤气处理量，有效提高混合煤气净化为H2的能力，无需对后续设备进行改动，避免了并联第二套低温甲醇洗和液氮洗装置的庞大投资。', p.abstract_en = 'The utility model discloses a mix coal gas clean system,  wash device,  pressure swing adsorption unit,  methane steam reforming CO converting means including transform cooling device,  two at least prewashing devices,  low temperature methanol washing desulfurizing tower,  low temperature methanol washing decarbonization tower,  liquid nitrogen,  prewashing device and transform cooling device intercommunication,  air inlet and each prewashing device intercommunication of desulfurizing tower,  the gas outlet of desulfurizing tower communicates with pressure swing adsorption unit and decarbonization tower respectively,  the intercommunication of device is washed respectively to methane steam reforming CO converting means\'s air inlet with pressure swing adsorption unit and liquid nitrogen,  the all mistakes of this department increase the handling capacity of mixed coal gas of prewashing stage to divide two the tunnel to carry out purification treatment behind desulfurization process the coal gas after the prewashing,  through the quantity of adjustment prewashing device,  the gas conditioning volume that the aperture just can improve mix coal gas clean system,  effective ability of mixing the gas purifying and being H2 that improves need not to change follow -up equipment,  has avoided parallelly connected second to overlap the huge investment that the device was washed to low temperature methanol washing and liquid nitrogen.', p.application_date = '2015-09-02 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN204958384U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/50', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'EP13717413'}) SET p.application_no = 'EP13717413', p.title_cn = '用于生产氢的气体从甲酸的方法', p.title_en = 'METHOD FOR PRODUCING HYDROGEN GAS FROM FORMIC ACID', p.abstract_cn = '生产氢气的方法从甲酸， 其特征在于 : 至少一个多相催化剂用于转化甲酸为氢气。 所述至少一种多相催化剂含有多相化了的钌。 根据本发明的第一方面， 所述至少一种多相催化剂含有至少一种亲水的膦配体，为m(TPPTS=三(间-三磺酸化三苯三苯基膦)。 所述至少一个多相催化剂优选通过将RuCl3混合水溶液与亲水性膦， 首先通过进行活化反应均匀，甲酸，加入至少一个固体结构。', p.abstract_en = 'A method for producing A hydrogen gas from formic acid,  characterized in that at least one heterogeneous catalyst is used to transform the formic acid into hydrogen gas. The at least one heterogeneous catalyst contains heterogenized ruthenium. According to a first aspect of the invention,  the at least one heterogeneous catalyst contains at least one hydrophilic phosphine ligand which is m-TPPTS (meta-trisulfonated triphenylphosphine). The at least one heterogeneous catalyst is preferably obtained by mixing an aqueous solution of RuCl3 with hydrophilic phosphine,  firstly activated by carrying out a homogeneous reaction with formic acid and by adding at least one solid structure.', p.application_date = '2013-03-06 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'EP2964570A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/22', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'KR1020140082712'}) SET p.application_no = 'KR1020140082712', p.title_cn = '潜艇供氢装置和供氢方法，使用该', p.title_en = 'HYDROGEN SUPPLY APPARATUS FOR SUBMARINE AND HYDROGEN SUPPLY METHOD USING THE SAME', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及与电解质溶液反应生成氢和供料单元，用于将原料材料金属；从所述材料与所述金属原料供应单元供应具有预定厚度的卷部；和所述卷从卷成接收所供应的所述金属原料的化学活性与电解质溶液用于产生氢的反应段提供了一种多用供氢装置包括水。此外，所述纱线还提供其中本发明是指水广告牌供氢方法。', p.abstract_en = 'Provided is a hydrogen supply apparatus for submarines,  which comprises :  a material supplying unit which supplies metal raw material which generates hydrogen by making a reaction with an electrolyte solution;  a rolling unit to receive the metal raw material from the material supplying unit and roll the metal raw material into a preset thickness;  and a reacting unit which generates hydrogen by making the rolled metal raw materials react with an electrolyte solution. According to the present invention,  provided is a hydrogen supply method for submarines. The hydrogen supply apparatus,  according to the present invention,  can increase the amount of generated hydrogen by having a large reaction surface area between the rolled metal and the electrolyte solution.COPYRIGHT KIPO 2016', p.application_date = '2014-07-02 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'KR1020160004493A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/10', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'KR1020157027509'}) SET p.application_no = 'KR1020157027509', p.title_cn = '用于生产氢的方法', p.title_en = 'METHOD FOR PRODUCING HYDROGEN', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及其中的进度反应的化合物，卤素化合物甲醇部分氧化以产生氢的氢的制造方法，用于延长了催化剂寿命该装置可稳定地产生的氢气和可在上制造方法。氢的制造方法(S1)与氢气生成过程的原料气制备工艺包括(S2)。不会原料气体制备工序(S1)调整到甲醇中反应预定的温度，水和氧气，并包括a。制备的原料气。制氢工序(S2)中供应原料调节温度的反应性催化剂颗粒的气体的反应器填充与(2a)接触催化剂由厂家在部分氧化反应的甲醇在其中的进度化合物和卤素化合物产生氢。所述制氢工序(S2)中反应器(2a)中流动的原料原料的流量控制材料气体通过触点300°C以下的最高温度的催化剂表面控制的。', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention is a method for producing hydrogen by allowing a partial oxidation reaction and decomposition reaction of methanol to proceed in order to generate hydrogen,  wherein it is possible to extend catalyst service life and to stably produce hydrogen over the long term. The method for producing hydrogen includes a starting material gas preparation step (s1) and a hydrogen generation step (s2). In the starting material gas preparation step (s1),  a starting material gas containing methanol,  water,  and oxygen and adjusted to a predetermined reactable temperature is prepared. In the hydrogen generation step (s2),  the starting material gas that has been adjusted to the reactable temperature is caused to flow through the inside of a reactor (2A) that is filled with a particulate catalyst,  causing contact with the catalyst,  and thereby allowing a partial oxidation reaction and decomposition reaction of methanol to proceed,  generation hydrogen. In the hydrogen generation step (s2),  the highest temperature of the catalyst surface contacting the starting material gas is controlled to be no greater than 300°C by means of controlling the flow rate of starting material gas flowing within the reactor (2A).', p.application_date = '2014-04-25 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'KR1020160005015A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/32', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'MX2012010052'}) SET p.application_no = 'MX2012010052', p.title_cn = '储存和运输氢的制造方法。', p.title_en = 'METHOD FOR PRODUCING HYDROGEN FOR STORAGE AND TRANSPORTATION.', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种用于储存和运输氢的制造方法，通过在氢的储存和运输所必需的顺畅促进有机化学氢化物可高效地制造方法在工业规模上以成本低。本发明的方法制造的氢的储存和运输用有机化学氢化物的方法，其特征在于 : 反应气体，通过调节氢气的浓度而得到的重整反应的合成气合成30-70通过变换反应体积%，作为反应氢源的芳族化合物氢化的步骤；并且氢化芳族化合物从反应混合物中分离纯化得到的氢化步骤。', p.abstract_en = 'Disclosed is a method for producing hydrogen for storage and transportation,  by which hydrogen for storage and transportation necessary for smoothly promoting an organic chemical hydride method can be efficiently produced on a commercial scale at low cost. Specifically disclosed is a method for producing hydrogen for storage and transportation by an organic chemical hydride method,  which is characterized in that :  a reaction gas,  which is obtained by adjusting the hydrogen concentration of a synthesis gas synthesized by a reforming reaction to 30-70 vol% by a shift reaction,  is used as a hydrogen source for a reaction in a hydrogenation step of an aromatic compound;  and that a hydrogenated aromatic compound is separated and purified from the reaction mixture that is obtained in the hydrogenation step.', p.application_date = '2011-03-24 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'MX336316B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'BRPI0923428'}) SET p.application_no = 'BRPI0923428', p.title_cn = '集成气精炼', p.title_en = 'INTEGRATED GAS REFINERY', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种一体式合成气精炼设备以及方法，用于同时生产由单合成气氢流的流X时可用于生产氨，富氢合成气物流用于生产甲醇，和贫含氢气的合成气体流可用于生产烃的汽油和/或柴油。', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention relates to an integrated synthesis gas refinery plant and a process for the simultaneous production from a single synthesis gas stream X of a hydrogen stream useful for the production of ammonia,  a hydrogen rich synthesis gas stream useful for the production of methanol,  and a hydrogen depleted synthesis gas stream useful for the production of hydrocarbons like gasoline and/or diesel.', p.application_date = '2009-12-10 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'BRPI0923428A2', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CA2705690'}) SET p.application_no = 'CA2705690', p.title_cn = '合成气的生产方法和氢气从液体或气态烃的', p.title_en = 'PROCESS FOR THE PRODUCTION OF SYNTHESIS GAS AND HYDROGEN STARTING FROM LIQUID OR GASEOUS HYDROCARBONS', p.abstract_cn = '描述了一种用于生产合成气的方法和氢气从液态烃原料中，POS sibly还混合有气态烃流，包括至少以下操作 : 1)雾化/汽化液体烃原料流由一个或多个以下的烃 : 石脑油，各种气体油，LCO等，CO32-和VGO，其它精炼周期和油的产品分级，如DAO，其它重质残基，在温度为50～2°C，压力50大气压，雾化还完成，借助一种气态推进剂，可能与CO2加入，选自汽相和/或气态烃类和导致形成雾化/气化液态烃流；2)将雾化/汽化的液态烃料流来自阶段1)具备 : a)氧化剂流，可能与水蒸汽混合后，b)可能的气态烃流在温度为50～2°C和压力50大气压，与可能的两相液体-气体的形成反应混合物；3)将来自阶段2)的反应混合物通过至少第一结构化催化床与地层混合物的反应产物包括H2和CO，所述结构化的催化床包括催化部分氧化催化剂，设置在一个或多个层，反应混合物流过每个所述层的接触时间从0.01变化到100ms，优选地从0.1到10ms；4)冷却反应产物的混合物来自阶段3)。用于实施所述方法的相关设备还描述了。', p.abstract_en = 'A process is described for producing synthesis gas and hydrogen starting from liquid hydrocarbon feedstocks,  pos-sibly also mixed with gaseous hydrocarbon streams,  comprising at least the following operations :  1) nebulizing/vaporizing a stream of a liquid hydrocarbon feedstock consisting of one or more of the following hydrocarbons :  naphthas,  various kinds of gas oils,  such as LCO,  HCO and VGO,  other products of refining cycles and oil up-grading,  such as DAO,  other heavy residues,  at a temperature ranging from 50 to 500.degree.C and a pressure of 2 to 50 atm,  the nebulization also being effected with the help of a gaseous propellant,  possibly with the addition of CO2,  selected from vapour and/or a gaseous hydrocarbon and resulting in the formation of a nebulized/vaporized liquid hydrocarbon stream;  2) mixing the nebulized/vaporized liquid hydrocarbon stream coming from phase 1) with :  a) an oxidizing stream,  possibly mixed with vapour,  b) possibly a gaseous hydrocarbon stream at a temperature ranging from 50 to 500.degree.C and a pressure of 2 to 50 atm,  with the formation of a possibly biphasic liquid-gas reaction mixture;  3) passing the reaction mixture coming from phase 2) through at least a first structured catalytic bed with the formation of a mixture of reaction products comprising H2 and CO,  said structured catalytic bed comprising a catalytic partial oxidation catalyst,  arranged on one or more layers,  the reaction mixture flowing through each of the layers with a contact time varying from 0.01 to 100 ms,  preferably from 0.1 to 10 ms;  4) cooling the mixture of reaction products coming from phase 3). The relative equipment for effecting said process is also described.', p.application_date = '2008-11-17 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CA2705690C', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US13782747'}) SET p.application_no = 'US13782747', p.title_cn = '制备金属氢化物浆料的方法和系统', p.title_en = 'Methods and systems for making metal hydride slurries', p.abstract_cn = '一种制备金属氢化物浆料的方法，包括将金属加入到液体载体中以产生金属浆料，以及将金属浆料中的金属氢化以产生金属氢化物浆料。 在一些实施方案中，在氢化金属之前，将金属氢化物添加到金属浆料的液体载体中。 金属可以是镁，金属氢化物可以是镁氢化物。', p.abstract_en = 'A method for making a metal-hydride slurry includes adding metal to a liquid carrier to create a metal slurry and hydriding the metal in the metal slurry to create a metal-hydride slurry. In some embodiments,  a metal hydride is added to the liquid carrier of the metal slurry prior to hydriding the metal. The metal can be magnesium and the metal hydride can be magnesium hydride.', p.application_date = '2013-03-01 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9233847B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US13495237'}) SET p.application_no = 'US13495237', p.title_cn = '延迟焦化装置重质渣油颗粒焦气化工艺', p.title_en = 'Process for the gasification of heavy residual oil with particulate coke from a delayed coking unit', p.abstract_cn = '一种生产含氢和一氧化碳的合成气的方法，使用具有预定灰分含量的磨碎焦炭与炼油厂残余烃油进料物流相结合，用于在管壁膜部分氧化气化反应器的燃烧室中在存在预定量的氧的情况下气化； 焦炭和渣油可以混合形成单一进料流或作为单独进料引入反应器。 任选地，将产物合成气作为进料物流引入水煤气变换反应器以提高最终产物物流的氢含量。', p.abstract_en = 'A process for the production of a synthesis gas containing hydrogen and carbon monoxide utilizes ground coke having a predetermined ash content in combination with a refinery residual hydrocarbon oil feedstream for gasification in the combustion chamber of a tubular wall membrane partial oxidation gasification reactor in the presence of a predetermined amount of oxygen;  the coke and residual oil can be mixed to form a single feedstream or introduced into the reactor as separate feeds. Optionally,  the product synthesis gas is introduced as the feedstream to a water-gas shift reactor to enhance the hydrogen content of the final product stream.', p.application_date = '2012-06-13 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9234146B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/12', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US11720493'}) SET p.application_no = 'US11720493', p.title_cn = '贮氢用镁合金', p.title_en = 'Magnesium alloys for hydrogen storage', p.abstract_cn = '一种制造储氢材料的方法，包括以下步骤 : 形成具有高达50wt%镍的镁-镍熔体； 在非氧化气氛下向熔体中加入至多2wt%的精炼元素，所述精炼元素的原子半径在镁原子半径的1～1.65倍的范围内，例如选自Zr、Na、K、Ba、Ca、Sr、La、Y、Yb、Rb和Cs中的至少一种元素； 以及固化所述熔体以产生所述储氢材料。', p.abstract_en = 'A method of producing a hydrogen storage material including the steps of :  forming a magnesium-nickel melt having up to 50 wt % nickel;  adding up to 2 wt % of a refining element to the melt under a non-oxidizing atmosphere,  the refining element having an atomic radius within the range of 1-1.65 times the atomic radius of magnesium,  such as at least one element selected from the group consisting of Zr,  Na,  K,  Ba,  Ca,  Sr,  La,  Y,  Yb,  Rb and Cs;  and solidifying the melt to produce the hydrogen storage material.', p.application_date = '2005-12-02 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9234264B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 3, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US13126964'}) SET p.application_no = 'US13126964', p.title_cn = '产氢燃料电池盒', p.title_en = 'Hydrogen-generating fuel cell cartridges', p.abstract_cn = '本申请涉及一种气体发生装置(10)。 氢气在气体发生装置内产生并被输送到燃料电池。 根据气体发生装置的反应室(28)内的压力，通过催化剂(48)选择性地暴露于燃料混合物来自动调节氢的产生。 催化剂密封机构(40，42)至少部分地设置在反应室内，以调节氢压力并使燃料电池接收的氢的压力波动最小。', p.abstract_en = 'The present application is directed to a gas-generating apparatus (10). Hydrogen is generated within the gas-generating apparatus and is transported to a fuel cell. The generation of hydrogen is regulated automatically by the selective exposure of a catalyst (48) to the fuel mixture depending on the pressure inside the reaction chamber (28) of the gas-generating apparatus. Catalyst sealing mechanisms (40,  42) are provided at least partially within the reaction chamber to regulate the hydrogen pressure and to minimize the fluctuations in pressure of the hydrogen received by the fuel cell.', p.application_date = '2009-11-03 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9236626B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/50', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 2, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'ES11811168'}) SET p.application_no = 'ES11811168', p.title_cn = '程序氢生产', p.title_en = 'Procedure hydrogen production', p.abstract_cn = '从水生产氢气的方法。产氢过程包括将水分解为氢气和氧气，其中该方法包括分解硫酸加入水中，二氧化硫和氧气通过反应的式(X1)利用太阳能热能，其中至少一部分的基元反应，式(x1-1)进行使用光热太阳能，和至少一部分的基元反应，式(x1-2)使用额外的热能进行其它比太阳能热能，和其中所述附加热能的加热温度通过10a°C或更高以上的加热通过太阳能热能温度，和至少一部分所述产生额外的热能在反应容器中 : (X1)H2SO4a→H2O+so2+13x，(x1-1)H2SO4a→H2O+SO3，和(x1-2)3a→SO2的+1]。', p.abstract_en = 'A method for producing hydrogen from water is provided. The hydrogen production process includes splitting water into hydrogen and oxygen,  wherein the process includes decomposing sulfuric acid into water,  sulfur dioxide and oxygen through a reaction of formula (X1) by using solar thermal energy,  wherein at least a part of the elementary reaction of formula (X1-1) is performed using thermal solar energy,  and at least a part of the elementary reaction of formula (X1-2) is performed using additional thermal energy other than solar thermal energy,  and wherein the heating temperature by the additional thermal energy is higher by 10° C. or more than the heating temperature by the solar thermal energy,  and at least a part of the additional thermal energy is generated in a reaction vessel :  (X1) H2SO4→H2O+SO2+1/2O2,  (X1-1) H2SO4→H2O+SO3,  and (X1-2) SO3→SO2+1/2O2.', p.application_date = '2011-12-07 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'ES2555866T3', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/06', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'MYPI2017702463'}) SET p.application_no = 'MYPI2017702463', p.title_cn = '一种合成氨的方法', p.title_en = 'A PROCESS FOR THE SYNTHESIS OF AMMONIA', p.abstract_cn = '空', p.abstract_en = '', p.application_date = '2016-01-11 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'MYPI2017702463A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/32', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'TW101134220'}) SET p.application_no = 'TW101134220', p.title_cn = '燃料性能提升剂', p.title_en = 'Fuel performance booster', p.abstract_cn = '於超临界之温度及压力条件下且较佳地不含催化剂，藉由甲醇及水产生氢利用热源，例如内燃引擎之排气系统，以达成超临界温度，可於内燃引擎原处生成氢', p.abstract_en = 'Hydrogen is produced from methanol and water under supercritical temperature and pressure conditions desirably without any catalyst. The hydrogen can be produced in situ on an internal combustion engine using a heat source such as the exhaust system of the internal combustion engine to achieve the supercritical temperature.', p.application_date = '2012-09-19 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'TWI516441B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/32', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'IN7337DELNP2015'}) SET p.application_no = 'IN7337DELNP2015', p.title_cn = '可再生能源系统中用于产生氢气和氢气产品', p.title_en = 'RENEWABLE ENERGY SYSTEM FOR GENERATING HYDROGEN AND HYDROGEN PRODUCTS', p.abstract_cn = '用于产生氢气的装置包括可再生能量源，用于产生电能和氢气发生模块供电的至少部分地由可再生能源产生的电能。通过电解水产生氢气的氢气发生模块。氢气可用于含一个化学生成模块，生成氢气的化学产品如氨，甲醇和/或烯烃。', p.abstract_en = 'An apparatus for generating hydrogen includes a renewable energy source for generating electrical energy and a hydrogen generation module powered at least partially by electrical energy generated by the renewable energy source. The hydrogen generation module generates hydrogen through electrolysis of water. The hydrogen may be used by a chemical generation module to form hydrogen containing chemical products such as ammonia,  methanol and/or an olefin.', p.application_date = '2015-08-19 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'IN7337DELNP2015A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'AU2012278043'}) SET p.application_no = 'AU2012278043', p.title_cn = '烃类进行重整的方法', p.title_en = 'Process for reforming hydrocarbons', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种用于生产合成气的方法，通过使用自热重整的，来自下游费-托合成取得热量的尾气被氢化，然后加入至自热重整阶段。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a process for the production of synthesis gas by the use of autothermal reforming in which tail gas from downstream Fischer-Tropsh synthesis is hydrogenated and then added to the autothermal reforming stage.', p.application_date = '2012-06-20 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'AU2012278043B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'AU2012280631'}) SET p.application_no = 'AU2012280631', p.title_cn = '方法用于平行制备氢气和含碳产品', p.title_en = 'Method for the parallel production of hydrogen and carbon-containing products', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种平行制备氢气的方法(3)和一个或多个含碳产品(8)。在该方法中，烃(2)引入反应室(R)中并热分解成碳和氢的存在下，一种富碳的颗粒状材料(W)。本发明的特征在于，至少一部分所述用于分解所需的热能的烃引入反应室(R)中经由气态热转印介质上。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a method for the parallel production of hydrogen (3) and of one or a plurality of carbon-containing products (8). In the method,  hydrocarbons (2) are introduced into a reaction chamber (R) and are thermally decomposed into carbon and hydrogen in the presence of a carbon-rich granulated material (W). The invention is characterised in that at least a portion of the thermal energy necessary for the decomposition of the hydrocarbons is introduced into the reaction chamber (R) via a gaseous heat transfer medium.', p.application_date = '2012-07-05 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'AU2012280631B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/28', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'AU2013326478'}) SET p.application_no = 'AU2013326478', p.title_cn = '生产氢气和产生动力的方法', p.title_en = 'Process for producing hydrogen and generating power', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种生产氢气和产生功率的方法包括以下步骤 : (a)使气态烃原料到吸热蒸汽重整反应通过使烃原料，在蒸汽重整反应区，在蒸汽存在下，有蒸汽重整催化剂在蒸汽重整条件得到气态混合物含有氢气和一氧化碳；(b)从混合物中回收氢；(C)将燃料和氧化剂一种涡轮，涡轮包括串联的压缩机，燃烧室和膨胀涡轮，所述压缩机驱动地连接到膨胀涡轮，其中，所述氧化剂是在压缩机中压缩，得到压缩的氧化剂和燃料一起燃烧，燃烧室中压缩的氧化剂得到燃烧气体流，(d)将至少部分燃烧气体流的膨胀涡轮发电，获得涡轮烟道气体；以及(e)提供吸热的重整反应的热量通过使步骤(c)中产生的热气体流和/或步骤(d)中热交换接触，与蒸汽重整反应区；和(f)在步骤(b)中回收氢的液化通过将氢回收到液化循环，该循环包括冷却和压缩氢气。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a process for producing hydrogen and generating power comprising the following steps :  (a) subjecting a gaseous hydrocarbon feedstock to an endothermic steam reforming reaction by contacting the hydrocarbon feedstock,  in a steam reforming reaction zone,  in the presence of steam,  with a steam reforming catalyst under steam reforming conditions to obtain a gaseous mixture comprising hydrogen and carbon monoxide;  (b) recovering hydrogen from the mixture;  (c) feeding a fuel and an oxidant to a turbine comprising in series a compressor,  a combustion chamber and an expansion turbine,  wherein the compressor is drivingly coupled to the expansion turbine,  wherein the oxidant is compressed in the in the compressor to obtain compressed oxidant and the fuel is combusted with the compressed oxidant in the combustion chamber to obtain a stream of combusted gas;  (d) feeding at least part of the stream of combusted gas to the expansion turbine to generate power and to obtain a turbine flue gas;  and (e) providing heat for the endothermic reforming reaction by bringing a hot gas stream generated in step (c) and/or step (d) in heat exchange contact with the steam reforming reaction zone;  and (f) liquefaction of the hydrogen recovered in step (b) by subjecting the hydrogen recovered to a liquefaction cycle comprising cooling and compressing the hydrogen.', p.application_date = '2013-10-03 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'AU2013326478B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'AU2013335985'}) SET p.application_no = 'AU2013335985', p.title_cn = '饱和器和天然气重整系统设有相同', p.title_en = 'Saturator and natural gas reforming system provided with same', p.abstract_cn = '提供了一种饱和器和天然气重整系统，使得可以更有效地回收利用热量从热源和水蒸汽的加入量最大化流体。饱和器(20)包括 : 第第一流体流路的内部流动；一种第一换热单元(22)，其使第一流体和第二之间的热交换流体；一种第二换热单元(23)，其使第第三流体之间的热交换和第一后流体第一流体通过第一换热单元(22)；加湿单元(26)添加水至第一上游的流体从第一换热单元(22)，第二换热单元(23)；和传送路径传送第三换热后的流体从第二换热单元(23)上游侧的第第一换热单元(22)，并使所述第三流体流入流量路径第一的流体。第一流体加热并加湿的在第一换热单元(22)，第二流体冷却系统的排出到外部，第一流体进行加热，在第二换热单元(23)加湿到之前的饱和蒸汽压力。该系统的排出到外部，和第三流体，冷却。', p.abstract_en = 'Provided are a saturator and a natural gas reforming system that make it possible to more efficiently recover and use heat from a heat source and to maximize the amount of water vapor added to a fluid. The saturator (20) comprises :  a flow path inside of which a first fluid flows;  a first heat exchange unit (22) that causes heat exchange between the first fluid and a second fluid;  a second heat exchange unit (23) that causes heat exchange between a third fluid and the first fluid after the first fluid has passed through the first heat exchange unit (22);  a humidifying unit (26) that adds water to the first fluid upstream from the first heat exchange unit (22) and the second heat exchange unit (23);  and a conveyance path that conveys the third fluid after heat exchange from the second heat exchange unit (23) to the upstream side of the first heat exchange unit (22) and causes said third fluid to flow into the flow path as the first fluid. The first fluid is heated and humidified at the first heat exchange unit (22),  the second fluid is cooled and discharged to outside of the system,  the first fluid is heated at the second heat exchange unit (23) and humidified to saturation vapor pressure before being discharged to outside of the system,  and the third fluid is cooled.', p.application_date = '2013-09-05 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'AU2013335985B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CA2953960'}) SET p.application_no = 'CA2953960', p.title_cn = '系统和用于干燥压缩增湿氢气吸收剂床的再生方法', p.title_en = 'SYSTEM AND METHOD FOR REGENERATING ABSORBER BED FOR DRYING COMPRESSED HUMIDIFIED HYDROGEN', p.abstract_cn = '用于压缩和干燥系统提供氢。该系统可以具有配置成接收并增湿的加湿器和产生浓缩氢流第一加湿氢气流，该系统还可以具有配置成接纳并且压缩的压缩机第一对增湿氢气流，增湿氢气和产生加压流。该系统还可具有一干燥器，包括 : (第一)生产模式中配置成接收加压加湿床氢气流，湿度吸收至少一部分，并产生产物氢气流。第一层可以进一步被配置为在再生模式中浓缩氢流的接收部分第一再生床，并产生第二的增湿氢气流。', p.abstract_en = 'A system for compressing and drying hydrogen is provided. The system may have a humidifier configured to receive and humidify a concentrated hydrogen stream and produce a first humidified hydrogen stream,  The system may also have a compressor configured to receive and compress the first humidified hydrogen stream,  and produce a pressurized humidified hydrogen stream. The system may further have a dryer including a first bed configured to in production mode receive the pressurized humidified hydrogen stream,  absorb at least a portion of the humidity,  and produce a product hydrogen stream. The first bed may further be configured to in regeneration mode receive a portion of the concentrated hydrogen stream to regenerate the first bed,  and produce a second humidified hydrogen stream.', p.application_date = '2015-06-30 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CA2953960A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/56', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'DE102012109154'}) SET p.application_no = 'DE102012109154', p.title_cn = '用于生产氢的方法', p.title_en = 'Method for production of hydrogen', p.abstract_cn = '获得高纯度氢气的方法从粗煤气，其中原料在压力下的气体压力容器(1)中通过该压力容器(1)内区域(3)具有，内部空间(2)的压力容器(1)充分完全，该内区域(3)至少部分地与半透材料，所述半透性材料为金属或金属合金，所述内部(2)的压力容器(1)和所述高纯度氢气在该半透性材料限定，在内部区域(3)被淀积时，其特征在于 : 所述半透材料，通过施加电电流，用于短时间仅在开始的工艺加热一段时间达100秒增加，压下充分量的氢气。', p.abstract_en = 'A method for obtaining highly pure hydrogen from a raw gas begins with heating and/or treating a semipermeable material made of metal or a metal alloy,  preferably,  conducting an electric current through the semipermeable material at the beginning of the method in order to increase the quantity of hydrogen passing through the material. A device for obtaining highly pure hydrogen from the raw gas includes a semipermeable material which forms a boundary between the interior of a pressure vessel and the outer region of the pressure vessel and which is permeable to hydrogen. The device is designed such that is can be heatable or treatable at least in sections,  in particular,  by means of electric energy.', p.application_date = '2012-09-27 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'DE102012109154B4', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/50', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2014121809'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2014121809', p.title_cn = '装置用于生产氢气和氢生产方法', p.title_en = 'HYDROGEN PRODUCTION APPARATUS AND HYDROGEN PRODUCTION METHOD', p.abstract_cn = '要解决的问题 : 该产品由于供应氢和氢分离的氢分离处理，降低所需的能量用于处理，和制氢装置可以制成紧凑为一体和氢产生装置以产生氢。方法 : MCH加热分解成氢和脱氢材料10和脱氢反应器，反应器10的脱氢的脱氢反应产物分离产生的氢气从氢气分离器30和，位于前的氢分离器30，氢气分离器30和压差氢中氢气的分离造成的分离器30和压力氢的分离通过脱氢反应至压力高于压力增压压缩机P3和v30，设置。选择的绘图 : 图。1', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To provide a hydrogen production apparatus and a hydrogen production method by which energy required for a hydrogen separation process by a hydrogen separator and a supply process of product hydrogen can be reduced and a hydrogen production apparatus as a whole can be made compact. SOLUTION :  The hydrogen production apparatus includes :  a dehydrogenation reactor 10 that decomposes MCH (methyl cyclohexane) into hydrogen and a dehydrogenated substance by heating;  a hydrogen separator 30 that separates hydrogen from a dehydrogenation reaction product produced by the dehydrogenation reactor 10;  and a compressor P3 that is positioned at a front stage of the hydrogen separator 30 and pressurizes the dehydrogenation reaction product V30 to a pressure higher than the sum pressure of a differential pressure generated by the hydrogen separation in the hydrogen separator 30 and a pressure of hydrogen separated by the hydrogen separator 30. COPYRIGHT :  (C)2016, JPO&INPIT', p.application_date = '2014-06-12 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP2016000677A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/26', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2014121810'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2014121810', p.title_cn = '装置用于生产氢气和氢生产方法', p.title_en = 'HYDROGEN PRODUCTION APPARATUS AND HYDROGEN PRODUCTION METHOD', p.abstract_cn = '要解决的问题 : 用于在脱氢反应，以改善能量效率，通过提高整个装置的能量效率可生产氢和制氢装置。方法 : MCH加热分解成氢和脱氢材料10和脱氢反应器，脱氢反应器10中排出的加热介质从脱氢反应器容器10的输入端之前对蒸发器12和蒸发所述MCH(L2)，设置在蒸发器(12)的前级，所述脱氢反应容器10和含氢物质产生的氢和脱氢反应v4输入到脱氢反应器容器10之前，MCH(L1)和预热器11，被提供。选绘制 : 图1', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To provide a hydrogen production apparatus and a hydrogen production method by which energy efficiency of the apparatus as a whole can be improved by improving efficiency of energy used for a dehydrogenation reaction. SOLUTION :  The hydrogen production apparatus includes :  a dehydrogenation reactor 10 that decomposes MCH (methyl cyclohexane) into hydrogen and a dehydrogenated substance by heating;  an evaporator 12 that evaporates MCH (L2) prior to being input to the dehydrogenation reactor 10 by using a heat medium discharged from the dehydrogenation reactor 10;  and a preheater 11 that is positioned at a front stage of the evaporator 12 and preheats MCH (L1) prior to being input into the dehydrogenation reactor 10 by using a dehydrogenation reaction product V4 comprising the hydrogen and the dehydrogenated substance produced by the dehydrogenation reactor 10. COPYRIGHT :  (C)2016, JPO&INPIT', p.application_date = '2014-06-12 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP2016000678A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/26', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2014121868'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2014121868', p.title_cn = '装置用于生产氢气和氢生产方法', p.title_en = 'HYDROGEN PRODUCTION APPARATUS AND HYDROGEN PRODUCTION METHOD', p.abstract_cn = '要解决的问题 : dehydrooxidation相对于抑制催化剂的结焦的发生，转化率高，可用于长时间保持氢和氢生产装置。方法 : MCH和分解成氢和脱氢的物质的脱氢反应器10和脱氢催化剂，含有v30氢和氢的脱氢反应产物，至少，小于第一基准值在含1的速率。v31和氢气中所含的氢气在含率小于第一基准值。2中所含的氢气的氢分离器30分离成offgass g31，脱氢反应器10在入口侧的MCH，用于引入含氢产品offgass g31ln1和入口管线，提供。选择绘制 : 图。1', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To provide a hydrogen production apparatus and a hydrogen production method by which generation of a caulking phenomenon in a dehydrogenation catalyst can be suppressed and a high conversion rate can be maintained for a long time. SOLUTION :  The hydrogen production apparatus includes :  a dehydrogenation reactor 10 including a dehydrogenation catalyst that decomposes MCH (methyl cyclohexane) into hydrogen and a dehydrogenated substance;  a hydrogen separator 30 that separates a dehydrogenation reaction product V30 comprising the hydrogen and the dehydrogenated substance into hydrogen V31 as a first hydrogen-containing substance containing hydrogen by a reference ratio or more,  and off-gas G31 as a second hydrogen-containing substance containing hydrogen by less than the reference ratio;  and a hydrogen-containing substance introduction line LN1 for introducing the off-gas G31 to an entrance side of the MCH in the dehydrogenation reactor 10. COPYRIGHT :  (C)2016, JPO&INPIT', p.application_date = '2014-06-12 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP2016000679A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/26', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14744307'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14744307', p.title_cn = '一种同时生产碳纳米管和氢气装置', p.title_en = 'DEVICE FOR SIMULTANEOUSLY PRODCING CARBON NANOTUBES AND HYDROGEN', p.abstract_cn = '根据本发明的同时生产碳纳米管和氢的方法是同时生产碳纳米管和氢的方法， 其中使用含有碳原子和氢原子并在加热状态下分解的碳源， 以及用于从碳源生产碳纳米管和H2的催化剂，将上述碳纳米管以加热状态在载体上合成，置于反应器中，同时，从上述碳源合成上述H2，该方法包括合成步骤，使包含上述碳源的源气体在其上负载有上述催化剂的上述载体上流动，以在上述载体上合成上述碳纳米管，同时在气流中合成上述H2。', p.abstract_en = 'A method for simultaneously producing carbon nanotubes and hydrogen according to the present invention is a method for simultaneously producing carbon nanotubes and hydrogen,  in which using a carbon source containing carbon atoms and hydrogen atoms and being decomposed in a heated state,  and a catalyst for producing carbon nanotubes and H2 from the carbon source,  the above carbon nanotubes are synthesized on a support in a heated state,  placed in a reactor,  and simultaneously,  the above H2 is synthesized from the above carbon source,  the method comprising a synthesis step of flowing a source gas comprising the above carbon source over the above support,  on which the above catalyst is supported,  to synthesize the above carbon nanotubes on the above support and simultaneously synthesize the above H2 in a gas flow.', p.application_date = '2015-06-19 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US20160002033A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/26', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14854490'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14854490', p.title_cn = '蒸汽甲烷重整器系统和执行蒸汽甲烷重整过程方法', p.title_en = 'STEAM METHANE REFORMER SYSTEM AND METHOD OF PERFORMING A STEAM METHANE REFORMING PROCESS', p.abstract_cn = '一种设备，包括具有至少一个卡口重整管的炉。 所述炉适于经由所述卡口重整管接收包括烃以及蒸汽和二氧化碳中的至少一种的气体，加热所述气体并使其催化反应以在第一温度下形成合成气，将所述合成气冷却到低于所述第一温度的第二温度，并从所述管中排出所述合成气。 该炉具有包括烟气的第一流出物流和包括合成气的第二流出物流。 所述设备还包括第一热回收部分和第二热回收部分，所述第一热回收部分适于将热量从所述第一流出物流传递到包括空气、水和蒸汽中的一种的第一热负载，所述第二热回收部分适于将热量从所述第二流出物流传递到第二热负载。', p.abstract_en = 'An apparatus includes a furnace having at least one bayonet reforming tube. The furnace is adapted to receive a gas including a hydrocarbon and at least one of steam and carbon dioxide via the bayonet reforming tube,  heat and catalytically react the gas to form syngas at a first temperature,  cool the syngas to a second temperature lower than the first temperature,  and eject the syngas from the tube. The furnace has a first effluent stream including flue gas and a second effluent stream including syngas. The apparatus also includes a first heat recovery section adapted to transfer heat from the first effluent stream to a first heat load including one of air,  water,  and steam,  and a second heat recovery section adapted to transfer heat from the second effluent stream to a second heat load.', p.application_date = '2015-09-15 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US20160002035A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14772619'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14772619', p.title_cn = '辐射壁催化反应器和在该反应器中进行化学反应方法', p.title_en = 'RADIATING WALL CATALYTIC REACTOR AND PROCESS FOR CARRYING OUT A CHEMICAL REACTION IN THIS REACTOR', p.abstract_cn = '公开了一种辐射壁催化反应器，用于通过辐射16从反应室(1)的内壁表面(8)提供热量以支持在反应室(1)中发生的整体吸热气相化学反应，以及在反应器中进行化学反应的方法。 反应室(1)设置有用于将气态反应物连续地引入到室(1)中的入口(2)和使气态产物能够连续地离开室(1)的出口(3)。 反应室(1)包括多个催化剂段(A)5，催化剂段(A)5两侧各有一个空隙段(B)6； 并且反应室(1)由适于抵抗700°C或更高温度的一种(多种)材料制成。', p.abstract_en = 'Disclosed are a radiating wall catalytic reactor for providing heat from the inside wall surface 8 of a reaction chamber 1 by radiation 16 to support an overall endothermic gas phase chemical reaction taking place in the reaction chamber 1,  and a process for carrying out a chemical reaction in the reactor. The reaction chamber 1 is provided with an entrance port 2 for introducing a gaseous reactant(s) in a continuous manner into the chamber 1 and an exit port 3 to enable the gaseous product(s) to leave the chamber 1 in a continuous manner. The reaction chamber 1 includes a plurality of catalyst segments (A)5,  which has one void segment (B)6 on either side of it;  and the reaction chamber 1 is made of a material(s) that is (are) suitable to resist a temperature of 700° C. or more.', p.application_date = '2014-03-04 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US20160002036A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WOCN15077343'}) SET p.application_no = 'WOCN15077343', p.title_cn = '甲醇水制氢设备的重整器及其制造工艺', p.title_en = 'REFORMER OF METHANOL WATER HYDROGEN PRODUCTION DEVICE,  AND MANUFACTURING PROCESS THEREOF', p.abstract_cn = '提供一种甲醇水制氢设备的重整器及其制造工艺。该重整器包括重整器壳体，所述重整器壳体从内至外依次包括不锈钢内壳、保温棉层及云母外壳，重整器壳体直径与不锈钢内壳厚度的比为150 : 0.8～150 : 2.5，重整器壳体直径与保温棉层厚度的比为150 : 10～150 : 20，重整器壳体直径与云母厚度的比为150 : 1.5～150 : 3.5。该重整器不仅耐高温、强度大，而且保温性能好、耐腐蚀、耐氧化、防水、不导电、重量轻。', p.abstract_en = 'Provided are a reformer of a methanol water hydrogen production device,  and a manufacturing process thereof. The reformer comprises a reformer shell. The reformer shell sequentially comprises a stainless steel inner shell,  a thermal insulation cotton layer and a mica outer shell from inside to outside. The ratio of the diameter of the reformer shell to the thickness of the stainless steel inner shell is 150 : 0.8 to 150 : 2.5,  the ratio of the diameter of the reformer shell to the thickness of the heat insulation cotton layer is 150 : 10 to 150 : 20,  and the ratio of the diameter of the reformer shell to the thickness of the mica is 150 : 1.5 to 150 : 3.5. The reformer not only is high-temperature resistant and great in strength,  but also is good in thermal insulation property,  corrosion resistance,  and oxidization resistance,  waterproof,  non-conductive and light in weight.', p.application_date = '2015-04-24 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016000480A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/32', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WOUS15038297'}) SET p.application_no = 'WOUS15038297', p.title_cn = '生物质加氢热解含原料', p.title_en = 'HYDROPYROLYSIS OF BIOMASS-CONTAINING FEEDSTOCKS', p.abstract_cn = '各种技术公开了用于城市固体垃圾(MSW)的预处理和其它含生物质原料可以的质量较差，因此更加困难，或甚至不可能，转化为高价值的液体产物(如，运输燃料)使用常规方法。常规方法否则可令人满意地用于转化生物质的原料单独的部分。含生物质的预处理原料通常可包括步骤之前进行加氢热解步骤，和任选地进一步步骤，以改变一个或多个所述原料的特性，使其更容易的可升级。', p.abstract_en = 'Various techniques are disclosed for pretreating municipal solid waste (MSW) and other biomass-containing feedstocks that may be of a poorer quality and consequently more difficult,  or even impossible,  to convert to higher value liquid products (e.g.,  transportation fuels) using conventional processes. Such conventional processes may otherwise be satisfactory for the conversion of the biomass portion of the feedstock alone. The pretreatment of biomass-containing feedstocks may generally include steps carried out prior to a hydropyrolysis step and optionally further steps,  in order to change one or more characteristics of the feedstock,  rendering it more easily upgradable.', p.application_date = '2015-06-29 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016003892A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/34', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'WOUS15038550'}) SET p.application_no = 'WOUS15038550', p.title_cn = '用于再生吸收剂床的系统和方法用于干燥压缩增湿氢气', p.title_en = 'SYSTEM AND METHOD FOR REGENERATING ABSORBER BED FOR DRYING COMPRESSED HUMIDIFIED HYDROGEN', p.abstract_cn = '用于压缩和干燥氢气的系统。该系统可以具有配置成接收并增湿加湿器浓缩氢流和产生第一增湿氢气流，该系统还可具有压缩机配置成接收并压缩第一增湿氢气流，和产生加压增湿氢气流。该系统还可具有一种干衣机，包括第一床生产模式中配置成接收加压加湿氢气流，湿度吸收至少一部分，和产生产物氢气物流。第一床可以进一步被配置为在再生模式中接收浓缩氢流的一部分再生第一床，并产生第二增湿氢气流。', p.abstract_en = 'A system for compressing and drying hydrogen is provided. The system may have a humidifier configured to receive and humidify a concentrated hydrogen stream and produce a first humidified hydrogen stream,  The system may also have a compressor configured to receive and compress the first humidified hydrogen stream,  and produce a pressurized humidified hydrogen stream. The system may further have a dryer including a first bed configured to in production mode receive the pressurized humidified hydrogen stream,  absorb at least a portion of the humidity,  and produce a product hydrogen stream. The first bed may further be configured to in regeneration mode receive a portion of the concentrated hydrogen stream to regenerate the first bed,  and produce a second humidified hydrogen stream.', p.application_date = '2015-06-30 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'WO2016004036A1', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/56', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201310119321.9'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201310119321.9', p.title_cn = '一种利用热等离子体裂解甘油制备合成气的方法', p.title_en = 'By using thermal plasma cracking glycerin process for the preparation of synthesis gas', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了一种利用热等离子体裂解甘油制备合成气的方法，包括以下步骤：首先将电离气体通入等离子体炬中电离生成热等离子体；然后，将纯甘油或甘油水溶液加入等离子体炬中进行裂解反应，反应时间为0.1～50ms，裂解产物为合成气。本发明的合成气制备方法采用高温热等离子体进行甘油裂解，不用添加催化剂，有效避免了传统合成气制备方法中的催化剂老化问题，反应速度快，效率高，副产物少，可高效的进行合成气的制备，适用于大规模工业化生产。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention discloses a method for preparing synthesis gas by using hot plasma pyrolysis glycerin,  which comprises the following steps of :  firstly,  feeding ionized gas into a hot plasma torch to ionize so as to obtain a hot plasma;  and then,  adding a pure glycerol or glycerine aqueous solution into the plasma torch to carry out pyrolysis reaction,  wherein the reaction time is 0.1-50 ms,  and the pyrolysis product is synthesis gas. The synthesis gas preparation method disclosed by the invention is implemented by carrying out glycerin pyrolysis by using a high-temperature hot plasma without adding a catalyst,  thereby effectively avoiding the catalyst aging problem in traditional synthesis gas preparation methods;  and the method is high in reaction speed,  high in efficiency and less in by-products,  and can be used for effectively preparing synthesis gas,  therefore,  the method is suitable for large-scale industrial production.', p.application_date = '2013-04-08 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN103204471B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/24', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201310323092.2'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201310323092.2', p.title_cn = '合成氨甲醇溶液活化方法', p.title_en = 'Activation method for synthesizing ammonia methanol solution', p.abstract_cn = '本发明提供一种合成氨甲醇溶液活化方法，包括：闪蒸步骤，将含油甲醇溶液进行闪蒸，除去含油甲醇溶液中的溶解气；缓冲步骤，将经闪蒸步骤处理后的含油甲醇溶液；萃取步骤，将混合后的含油甲醇溶液进行萃取，使轻质油和水反应与甲醇溶液分离；脱水步骤，将萃取步骤分离出来的甲醇水溶液进行脱水。本发明的合成氨甲醇溶液活化方法可以有效的对合成氨低温甲醇洗工艺所使用的甲醇溶液进行有效的活化，同时还可以对活化的副产品轻质油进行有效的回收利用。通过本方法可以有效的延长甲醇溶液的使用寿命，从而降低生产成本，降低环境污染的风险。另外通过回收轻质油还可以有效的提高生产效益。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention provides an activating method for synthesis ammonia methanol liquor. The method comprises the following steps of :  a flash step,  flashing oily methanol liquor to remove solution gas in the oily methanol liquor;  a buffer step,  buffering the oily methanol liquor after treatment in the flash step;  an extraction step,  extracting the mixed oily methanol liquor,  and performing reaction of light oil and water to separate the methanol liquor;  a dehydrating step,  dehydrating the methanol aqueous liquor separated from the extraction step. The activating method for synthesis ammonia methanol liquor provided by the invention can be used for effectively activating the methanol liquor used in a synthesis ammonia low temperature methanol washing process,  and meanwhile effectively recovering an activated byproduct light oil. According to the method,  the service life of the methanol liquor is effectively prolonged,  so that the production cost is lowered and the risk of environmental pollution is reduced. In addition,  the production benefit can be effectively improved by recovering light oil.', p.application_date = '2013-07-29 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN103342342B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/52', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201280039436.0'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201280039436.0', p.title_cn = '制氢装置和氢纯化设备', p.title_en = 'Hydrogen producing device and the hydrogen purification apparatus', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开了制氢装置、氢纯化设备和其组件以及制造那些装置、设备和组件的方法。在一些实施方式中，所述装置可包括带有填充材料的汽化区和/或绝热底座，其中所述汽化区构造为将热从加热排出流传递到含液体进料流，所述绝热底座临近燃烧区并构造为降低外壳的外部温度。', p.abstract_en = 'Hydrogen generation assemblies,  hydrogen purification devices,  and their components,  and methods of manufacturing those assemblies,  devices,  and components are disclosed. In some embodiments,  the devices may include an insulation base having insulating material and at least one passage that extends through the insulating material. In some embodiments,  the at least one passage may be in fluid communication with a combustion region.', p.application_date = '2012-07-03 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN103732532B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/26', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 2, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201410034027.2'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201410034027.2', p.title_cn = 'MgH2-BiVO4储氢复合材料及其制备方法', p.title_en = 'MgH 2-BiVO 4 hydrogen storage composite material and its preparation method', p.abstract_cn = '一种MgH2-BiVO4储氢复合材料，它是由MgH2与BiVO4组成，其中BiVO4含量占复合材料总质量的10～40%。上述储氢复合材料的制备方法是：在氩气保护的手套箱中，将MgH2粉末和BiVO4置于球磨罐中进行球磨，球料质量比为15～35 : 1，转速为450～550r/min, 在0.1～0.5MPa氩气的保护下，球磨1～3h，每球磨20～45min，间歇15～25min，待球磨结束后自然冷却至室温，得到MgH2-BiVO4储氢复合材料。本发明的储氢复合材料在相对较低的温度下，吸氢速率以及最大吸氢量比未添加BiVO4的MgH2提高了1倍以上，同时制备方法简单，制备成本低，适用于工业化规模制备。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention discloses an MgH2-BiVO4 hydrogen storage composite material which consists of MgH2 and BiVO4,  wherein the content of the BiVO4 accounts for 10-40% of the total mass of the composite material. A preparation method of the hydrogen storage composite material comprises the following steps :  in a glove box protected by argon,  putting the MgH2 powder and the BiVO4 in a ball milling tank,  and performing ball milling in the presence of 0.1-0.5MPa argon at a ball-material mass ratio of (15-35) : 1 and the revolving speed of 450-550r/min for 1-3 hours,  wherein 15-25 minutes of intermittence is spaced between every two times of 20-45 minutes of ball milling;  after the ball milling,  naturally cooling to the room temperature so as to obtain the MgH2-BiVO4 hydrogen storage composite material. Under relatively low temperature,  compared with the MgH2 without the addition of BiVO4,  the hydrogen absorption rate and maximum hydrogen absorption amount of the hydrogen storage composite material are improved by more than one time;  at the same time,  the preparation method is simple,  the preparation cost is low and the hydrogen storage composite material is suitable for industrialization-scale preparation.', p.application_date = '2014-01-23 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN103864012B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/04', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201280058313.1'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201280058313.1', p.title_cn = '合成气净化系统和方法', p.title_en = 'The synthesis gas purification system and method', p.abstract_cn = '一个用于处理未处理合成气的系统和方法，首先去除固体和半挥发性有机化合物(SVOC)，然后去除挥发性有机化合物(VOC)，再然后从合成气中去除至少一种含硫化合物。根据以下因素例如被处理的合成气的来源，希望形成、捕捉或循环的产品、副产品和中间产物，以及环境的考虑，可以进行额外的步骤。', p.abstract_en = 'A system and method for processing unconditioned syngas first removes solids and semi-volatile organic compounds (SVOC),  then removes volatile organic compounds (VOC),  and then removes at least one sulfur containing compound from the syngas. Additional processing may be performed depending on such factors as the source of syngas being processed,  the products,  byproducts and intermediate products desired to be formed,  captured or recycled and environmental considerations.', p.application_date = '2012-09-27 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN103958398B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201410312568.7'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201410312568.7', p.title_cn = '利用低压蒸汽完成2.4MPa变换的合成装置开车方法', p.title_en = 'Completed using low pressure steam 2.4 MPa starting process of the synthesizing device', p.abstract_cn = '一种利用低压蒸汽完成2.4MPa变换的合成装置开车方法，涉及化工技术领域，用邻近公司压力为1.0MPa的蒸汽，完成了造气、系统的制惰置换、开车工作；完成变换触媒的升温硫化工作，使其具备生产能力，然后把变换系统压力控制在0.8MPa，用1.0MPa蒸汽加入制取合格的变换气；在0.8MPa压力下完成CO2脱除工作，制得合格的净化气，以满足醇烷化系统触媒升温还原需要。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention discloses a synthesizer starting method completing 2.4 MPa shift by utilization of low-pressure steam,  and relates to the technical field of chemical engineering. Gas making,  system inert gas displacement and starting are achieved by utilization of steam having a pressure of 1.0 MPa of a neighbor company. Heating sulfuration of a shift catalytic agent is performed so as to allow the catalytic agent to have production capability. Then the pressure of a shift system is controlled to be 0.8 MPa,  and prepared qualified shift gas is added by utilization of the steam having a pressure of 1.0 MPa. CO2 removing is performed under a pressure of 0.8 MPa to prepare qualified purified gas so as to meet requirements of heating reduction of catalytic agents in alcohol alkylation systems.', p.application_date = '2014-07-02 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN104118847B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/16', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201410402253.1'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201410402253.1', p.title_cn = '高温冶金渣颗粒催化气化生物质制取富氢气体装置及方法', p.title_en = 'High-temperature metallurgical slag particles of biomass of catalytic gasification device and method for producing hydrogen-rich gas', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及高温冶金渣颗粒催化气化生物质制取富氢气体装置及方法，该装置包括下降管反应器，位于其上并与其顶部连通的高温渣粒贮存室和生物质原料螺旋给料器，位于其下并与其底部连通的分离器及位于其两侧并分别与其连通的蒸汽发生器和富氢气体收集器。应用该装置的方法分别通过熔渣旋转粒化装置、生物质原料螺旋给料器和蒸汽发生器向下降管反应器中加入高温冶金渣颗粒、生物质原料和水蒸气，使生物质原料在高温冶金渣颗粒的催化下发生气化反应，生成富氢气体储存在富氢气体收集器内。该方法将冶金渣的余热以化学能的形式加以回收利用，具有较高的余热回收率，解决了冶金渣干法处理工艺余热回收率低、回收品质低的问题。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a device for preparing hydrogen-rich gas by gasifying a biomass under the catalysis of high-temperature metallurgical slag particles and a method. The device comprises a downer reactor,  a high-temperature slag particle storage chamber,  a spiral biomass raw material feeder,  a separator,  a steam generator and a hydrogen-rich gas collector,  wherein the high-temperature slag particle storage chamber and the spiral biomass raw material feeder are located above the downer reactor and are communicated with the top of the downer reactor;  the separator is located below the downer reactor and is communicated with the bottom of the downer reactor;  and the steam generator and the hydrogen-rich gas collector are located at two sides of the downer reactor and are respectively communicated with the downer reactor. The method in which the device is applied comprises the steps of respectively adding high-temperature metallurgical slag particles,  biomass raw materials and steam into the downer reactor through a rotary molten slag granulating device,  the spiral biomass raw material feeder and the steam generator;  carrying out gasification reaction on the biomass raw materials under the catalysis of the high-temperature metallurgical slag particles to generate hydrogen-rich gas;  and storing the hydrogen-rich gas into the hydrogen-rich gas collector. By using the method,  waste heat of metallurgical slag is recycled in a chemical energy way,  so that the recovery rate of the waste heat is relatively high,  and the problems of low waste heat recovery rate and low recovery quality of a dry-method metallurgical slag treatment process are solved.', p.application_date = '2014-08-15 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN104192799B', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/32', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201510517562.8'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201510517562.8', p.title_cn = '合成氨生产中脱碳制备液体二氧化碳的尾气回收利用方法', p.title_en = 'Recycling method of tail gas from decarburization preparation of liquid carbon dioxide in synthetic ammonia production', p.abstract_cn = '本发明公开一种合成氨生产中脱碳制备液体二氧化碳的尾气回收利用方法，在脱碳常解气工段，常解气经压缩、脱硫、干燥、冷凝、精馏后得到的液相为液体二氧化碳，气相为放空尾气，放空尾气中富含大量合成氨的有效气体，其特征在于，将所述放空尾气引入吸附塔进行变压吸附脱碳净化，然后经压缩机压缩送到氨合成工段。有益效果：本发明通过回收放空尾气中富集的大量合成氨有效气体，经过净化处理送至后工段氨合成，达到减少放空污染，降低生产成本，增加企业效益的目的。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention discloses a recycling method of tail gas from decarburization preparation of liquid carbon dioxide in synthetic ammonia production. In the workshop section of decarburization of carbon dioxide gas released from a synthetic ammonia apparatus,  the carbon dioxide gas released from a synthetic ammonia apparatus undergoes compression and desulfuration,  and the compression and desulfuration product successively undergoes drying,  condensation and rectification so as to obtain a liquid phase and a gas phase. The liquid phase is liquid carbon dioxide,  and gas phase is vented tail gas. The vented tail gas is rich in lots of available gas of synthetic ammonia. The method is characterized in that the vented tail gas is introduced into an adsorption tower to undergo pressure swing absorption for decarburization purification;  and then a compressor is used for compression and a product is sent to the workshop section of ammonia synthesis. The invention has beneficial effects as follows :  by recovering lots of available gas of synthetic ammonia that is enriched in the vented tail gas and by purifying and sending the purification product to the back workshop section of ammonia synthesis,  the purposes of minimizing vent pollution,  reducing production cost and increasing enterprise benefit are achieved.', p.application_date = '2015-08-22 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105217571A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/50', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201480024838.2'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201480024838.2', p.title_cn = '燃料供给装置', p.title_en = 'Fuel supply apparatus', p.abstract_cn = '一种燃料供给装置包括：反应室，其用于主办在燃料产生流体和燃料产生物质被放在一起时产生燃料的反应；多个分立的燃料产生流体室，每个室是单独可破裂的；以及加热器组件，其适于在使用时选择性地使所述燃料产生流体室破裂以将燃料产生流体供给到所述反应室。', p.abstract_en = 'A fuel supply apparatus comprising;  a reaction chamber for hosting a reaction when a fuel generating fluid and a fuel generating substance are brought together to generate fuel,  a plurality of discrete fuel generating fluid chambers,  each chamber being separately rupturable;  and,  a heater assembly adapted to,  when in use,  selectively rupture the fuel generating fluid chambers to supply fuel generating fluid to the reaction chamber.', p.application_date = '2014-05-01 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105228947A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/06', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201480027055.X'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201480027055.X', p.title_cn = '使用燃料电池的综合发电和碳捕集', p.title_en = 'Integrated power generation and carbon capture using fuel cells', p.abstract_cn = '提供了使用熔融碳酸盐燃料电池(MCFCs)捕集来自燃烧源的CO2的系统和方法。运行燃料电池以具有降低的阳极燃料利用率。任选地，将至少一部分阳极排气再循环用作燃烧源的燃料。任选地，将阳极排气的第二部分再循环用作阳极输入料流的一部分。这可允许由燃烧源排气分离CO2所需的燃料电池面积量降低和/或在如何运行燃料电池中的改进。', p.abstract_en = 'Systems and methods are provided for capturing CO2 from a combustion source using molten carbonate fuel cells (MCFCs). The fuel cells are operated to have a reduced anode fuel utilization. Optionally,  at least a portion of the anode exhaust is recycled for use as a fuel for the combustion source. Optionally,  a second portion of the anode exhaust is recycled for use as part of an anode input stream. This can allow for a reduction in the amount of fuel cell area required for separating CO2 from the combustion source exhaust and/or modifications in how the fuel cells are operated.', p.application_date = '2014-03-13 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105228948A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/50', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201480027350.5'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201480027350.5', p.title_cn = '熔融碳酸盐燃料电池与发酵工艺的集成', p.title_en = 'Integration of molten carbonate fuel cells with fermentation processes', p.abstract_cn = '在各种方面中，提供了在提高的功率密度下运行熔融碳酸盐燃料电池组件的系统和方法。这部分可通过以集成方式进行燃料电池堆内的有效量的吸热反应实现。这可以在仍保持燃料电池组件内的所需温差的同时实现提高的功率密度。', p.abstract_en = 'In various aspects,  systems and methods are provided for operating a molten carbonate fuel cell assembly at increased power density. This can be accomplished in part by performing an effective amount of an endothermic reaction within the fuel cell stack in an integrated manner. This can allow for increased power density while still maintaining a desired temperature differential within the fuel cell assembly.', p.application_date = '2014-03-13 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105228949A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/50', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201480028075.9'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201480028075.9', p.title_cn = '使用燃料电池的综合发电和化学生产', p.title_en = 'Integrated power generation and chemical production using fuel cells', p.abstract_cn = '在各个方面中，提供运行熔融碳酸盐燃料电池的系统和方法，其中可重整燃料相对于在燃料电池的阳极中进行氧化的量过量。代替选择燃料电池的运行条件来改进或使燃料电池的电效率最大化，可以将过量的可重整燃料送入燃料电池的阳极以提高燃料电池的化学能量输出。这可导致基于燃料电池的组合的电效率和化学效率的燃料电池总效率提高。', p.abstract_en = 'In various aspects,  systems and methods are provided for operating a molten carbonate fuel cell with an excess of reformable fuel relative to the amount of oxidation performed in the anode of the fuel cell. Instead of selecting the operating conditions of a fuel cell to improve or maximize the electrical efficiency of the fuel cell,  an excess of reformable fuel can be passed into the anode of the fuel cell to increase the chemical energy output of the fuel cell. This can lead to an increase in the total efficiency of the fuel cell based on the combined electrical efficiency and chemical efficiency of the fuel cell.', p.application_date = '2014-03-13 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN105228950A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/50', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201520700247.4'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201520700247.4', p.title_cn = '一种变压吸附氢气分离装置', p.title_en = 'Pressure swing adsorption hydrogen separator', p.abstract_cn = '本实用新型涉及一种变压吸附氢气分离装置，包括空压机，空气储罐，活性炭过滤器，吸附器，除尘过滤器，分离器，氢气储罐，节流阀，放空口和纯氢出口，空压机上设有阀门，其为第一阀门，第一阀门上设有第一接收器，吸附器包括第一和第二吸附器，第一和第二吸附器上均设有阀门，其分别为第二和第三阀门，第二和第三阀门上均设有接收器，其分别为第二和第三接收器，第一，第二和第三接收器上均包括接收器壳体和电路板；本实用新型的变压吸附氢气分离装置，通过装置内部各设备设置接收器，实现了无线控制相应设备的运转，从而方便控制，提高了工作效率，节约了工作时间。', p.abstract_en = 'The utility model relates to a pressure swing adsorption hydrogen separator,  including the air compressor machine,  air reservoir,  an activated carbon filter,  the adsorber,  the dust removal filter,  the separator,  the hydrogen storage tank,  the choke valve,  drain and the export of pure hydrogen,  be equipped with the valve on the air compressor machine,  it is first valve,  be equipped with first receiver on the first valve,  the adsorber includes first and second adsorbers,  all be equipped with the valve on first and second adsorbers,  it is second and third valve respectively,  all be equipped with the receiver on second and the third valve,  it is second and third receiver respectively,  it is first,  all include receiver casing and circuit board on second and the third receiver,  the utility model discloses a pressure swing adsorption hydrogen separator sets up the receiver through installing inside each equipment,  has realized the operation of the corresponding equipment of wireless control to convenient control has improved work efficiency,  has practiced thrift operating time.', p.application_date = '2015-09-11 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN204938971U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/50', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CN201520628516.0'}) SET p.application_no = 'CN201520628516.0', p.title_cn = '一种氢气分离装置', p.title_en = 'Hydrogen separator', p.abstract_cn = '本实用新型公开了一种氢气分离装置，所述的氢气分离装置包括管状氢气分离膜、外壳、嵌入件、混合气体进气管、滤后气体排出管、氢气排出管，所述外壳底部安装有混合气体进气管和滤后气体排出管，混合气体进气管直接延伸至外壳内部，外壳顶部安装有氢气排出管，所述外壳内部设置有氢气分离膜，氢气分离膜上端与封板、下端用底板密封连接，氢气分离膜内部设置有嵌入件，嵌入件包括嵌入件内壁、嵌入件外壁、嵌入件顶壁和嵌入件底壁，嵌入件外壁与嵌入件底壁连接，嵌入件外壁与底板之间形成一个通孔，氢气分离膜采用铜钯合金制作而成，底板与混合气体进气管之间设置有滤后气体排出道，滤后气体排出道与滤后气体排出管贯通。', p.abstract_en = 'The utility model discloses a hydrogen separator,  hydrogen separator include tubulose hydrogen diffusion barrier,  shell,  embedment,  mist intake pipe,  strain back gas outgoing pipe,  hydrogen discharge pipe,  shell bottom is installed the mist intake pipe and is strained back gas outgoing pipe,  and inside the mist intake pipe directly extended to the shell,  the hydrogen discharge pipe was installed at the shell top,  the inside hydrogen diffusion barrier that is provided with of shell,  hydrogen diffusion barrier upper end and shrouding,  bottom plate sealing connection for the lower extreme,  the inside embedment that is provided with of hydrogen diffusion barrier,  the embedment includes the embedment inner wall,  the embedment outer wall,  embedment roof and embedment diapire,  the embedment outer wall is connected with the embedment diapire,  form a through -hole between embedment outer wall and the bottom plate,  the hydrogen diffusion barrier adopts the preparation of copper palldium alloy to form,  be provided with between bottom plate and the mist intake pipe and strain back gas outgoing way,  strain back gas outgoing way and strain back gas outgoing pipe and link up.', p.application_date = '2015-08-20 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CN204938972U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/56', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'EP08738503'}) SET p.application_no = 'EP08738503', p.title_cn = '氢生成装置，燃料电池系统和氢气形成装置的控制方法', p.title_en = 'HYDROGEN FORMING APPARATUS,  FUEL CELL SYSTEM AND METHOD OF CONTROLLING HYDROGEN FORMING APPARATUS', p.abstract_cn = '氢气产生装置能够稳定地供给的重整水，稳定产生氢气和防止降解的重整器。所述氢气产生装置包括重整器1进行重整反应中使用材料和蒸汽生成含氢气体；水蒸发器1a产生的蒸汽供给到重整器1；一种第一水通路5，通过该重整水供给到水蒸发器1a流动；泵6，其提供的重整水到水蒸发器1a；一种第二水通路7分支从第一水通路在泵6的下游侧；第一水箱(2)，其通过第二水流动的水通路7的流动；一种第一流量控制器8设置在第二水通路7；和控制器9，其可以操作泵6和控制器第一，流量控制器8使水流经第二水通路7。', p.abstract_en = 'A hydrogen generating apparatus is capable of stably supplying reforming water,  stably generating hydrogen and preventing degradation of the reformer thereof. The hydrogen generating apparatus comprises a reformer 1 which performs a reforming reaction using a material and steam to generate hydrogen-containing gas;  a water evaporator 1a which generates the steam supplied to the reformer 1;  a first water pathway 5 through which reforming water to be supplied to the water evaporator 1a flows;  a pump 6 which supplies the reforming water to the water evaporator 1a;  a second water pathway 7 branching from the first water pathway on the downstream side of the pump 6;  a first water tank 2 to which the water flowing through the second water pathway 7 flows;  a first flow rate controller 8 provided on the second water pathway 7;  and a controller 9 which operates the pump 6 and controls the first flow rate controller 8 so that water flows through the second water pathway 7.', p.application_date = '2008-04-07 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'EP2042469B1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2012006060'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2012006060', p.title_cn = '氢气发生器，氢气发生器，和发电装置和驱动装置', p.title_en = 'A hydrogen generator,  a hydrogen generator,  and a power generating device and a driving device', p.abstract_cn = '氢产生元件，其供氢高效，稳定， 安全，具有低环境负荷。 进一步，氢产生装置的氢生成元件提供了一种应用。 此外， 一种发电装置和驱动装置，其中每个所述氢气产生装置施加被提供。 一种氢气发生元件，其中，针状或穹顶状的硅微小结构可以将与基底的上方形成 使用与水反应，从而使氢高效的产生。 该氢气产生元件可以应用于本发明的氢生成装置。 该氢生成装置可以应用于发电装置和驱动装置。', p.abstract_en = 'A hydrogen generating element which can supply hydrogen efficiently and stably,  is safe,  and has low environmental load is provided. Further,  a hydrogen generation device to which the hydrogen generating element is applied is provided. Furthermore,  a power generation device and a driving device to each of which the hydrogen generation device is applied are provided. A hydrogen generating element in which a needle-like or dome-like silicon microstructure is formed over a base may be used and reacted with water,  whereby hydrogen is efficiently generated. The hydrogen generating element may be applied to a hydrogen generation device. The hydrogen generation device may be applied to a power generation device and a driving device.', p.application_date = '2012-01-16 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP5840507B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/06', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2012229336'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2012229336', p.title_cn = '氢气储存和释放装置', p.title_en = 'The hydrogen storage and release device', p.abstract_cn = '要解决的问题 :  提供一种储氢/释放装置能够减轻压实和固结的储氢合金因 膨胀/收缩， 同时延伸的含氢气体的流动通道在储氢合金填充层，同时抑制短接 含氢气体的路径， 加速热量的传导填料， 和， 作为结果， 显著提高储氢/净化的效率。方法 :  氢储存/释放装置1包括 :  圆柱形罐2具有， 在一个终端侧， 一种含氢气体供给口6和， 在其它终端侧，离气体排放口7； 填料5填入该罐2和包括氢存储合金； 和温度控制装置4，用于加热和冷却填料5； 具有翅片3构造成抵靠从罐内平面2以调节 气体在锯齿状或螺旋状相对于轴向方向的循环模式。', p.abstract_en = 'PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED :  To provide a hydrogen storage/release apparatus capable of mitigating the compaction and consolidation of a hydrogen storage alloy due to the expansion/contraction thereof,  of simultaneously extending flow channels of a hydrogen-containing gas within a hydrogen storage alloy-filled layer while inhibiting short-circuited paths of the hydrogen-containing gas,  of accelerating the conduction of heat to the filler,  and,  as a result,  of significantly improving hydrogen storage/purification efficiencies.SOLUTION :  A hydrogen storage/release apparatus 1 includes :  a cylindrical tank 2 having,  on one terminal side thereof,  a hydrogen-containing gas supply port 6 and,  on the other terminal side thereof,  an off-gas discharge port 7;  a filler 5 filled into this tank 2 and including a hydrogen storage alloy;  and temperature control means 4 for heating and cooling the filler 5;  and possesses fins 3 configured to abut from the inner plane of the tank 2 so as to regulate the gas in a zigzag or spiral circulatory pattern in relation to the axial direction thereof.', p.application_date = '2012-10-16 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP5840591B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'JP2011161738'}) SET p.application_no = 'JP2011161738', p.title_cn = '中间的吹扫压力在生产氢气的方法', p.title_en = 'The purging of the intermediate pressure in the hydrogen production method', p.abstract_cn = '从烃原料和蒸汽生产氢气的包括 :  生产合成气的蒸汽重整单元中的烃原料在蒸汽存在下， 燃料提供反应所需的热量； 所获得的转化合成气的蒸汽生产氢气流具有甲烷和二氧化碳； 捕获得到的流量中的二氧化碳蒸汽分离二氧化碳从氢流； 收集和回收利用， 向蒸汽重整的氢气流中的杂质， 包括减压相在压力0.2-1.4兆帕。', p.abstract_en = 'Producing hydrogen from a hydrocarbon feedstock and steam comprises :  producing a synthesis gas in a steam reforming unit of hydrocarbon feedstock in presence of steam,  fuel providing needed heat to the reaction;  converting synthesis gas to the obtained steam to produce a hydrogen flow having methane and carbon dioxide;  capturing carbon dioxide in the obtained flow to steam to separate carbon dioxide from the hydrogen stream;  and collecting and recycling,  towards the steam reforming of impurities in the hydrogen stream,  including a decompression phase at a pressure of 0.2-1.4 MPa.', p.application_date = '2011-07-25 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'JP5840884B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/38', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CA2626537'}) SET p.application_no = 'CA2626537', p.title_cn = '用于原位去除焦油的气化的方法和系统', p.title_en = 'PROCESS AND SYSTEM FOR GASIFICATION WITH IN-SITU TAR REMOVAL', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种用于在间接加热式气化器中气化生物质或其它含碳原料的方法和系统，并提供了一种用于从所得产物气体中消除可冷凝有机材料(焦油)的方法，该方法具有集成的焦油去除步骤。更具体地，该焦油去除步骤利用循环的热载体来裂解有机物并产生额外的产物气体。作为上述过程的益处。并且因为热载体在工艺中通过交替的蒸汽区和氧化区循环。消除了裂化反应的失活。', p.abstract_en = 'The present invention relates to a process and system for gasifying biomass or other carbonaceous feedstocks in an indirectly heated gasifier and provides a method for the elimination of condensable organic materials (tars) from the resulting product gas with an integrated tar removal step. More specifically,  this tar removal step utilizes the circulating heat carrier to crack the organics and produce additional product gas. As a benefit of the above process. and because the heat carrier circulates through alternating steam and oxidizing zones in the process. deactivation of the cracking reactions is eliminated.', p.application_date = '2006-10-23 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CA2626537C', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/36', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'CA2668723'}) SET p.application_no = 'CA2668723', p.title_cn = '方法和装置用于提高燃料电池中的水平衡功率单元', p.title_en = 'METHOD AND APPARATUS FOR IMPROVING WATER BALANCE IN FUEL CELL POWER UNIT', p.abstract_cn = '一种方法和设备用于提高功率单元中的水平衡，通过提供废气从燃料电池的阴极侧作为进料气体燃烧系统，冷凝至少一部分流出物中存在的水从冷凝器中的燃烧系统，然后将水蒸气从未冷凝部分的流出物从冷凝器至气体送入阴极侧的燃料电池。水从排气气体从燃料电池的阴极侧被捕获在所述冷凝器，或所述进料气体中重复使用的阴极侧的燃料电池。加湿的空气送入系统与废气中存在的水蒸气，水从系统中不丢失。相反，空气被送入该系统在该水中进行加湿，这又允许加湿器工作在较高的温度和/或使用较小的散热器和风扇和/或撷取较少的寄生功率，从而提高系统的整体效率。', p.abstract_en = 'A method and apparatus for improving the water balance in a power unit by providing the exhaust gas from the cathode side of the fuel cell as a feed gas to the combustion system,  condensing at least a portion of water present in the effluent from the combustion system in a condenser,  and then transferring water vapor from the uncondensed portion of the effluent from the condenser to the gas fed to the cathode side of the fuel cell. Water from the exhaust gas from the cathode side of the fuel cell is either captured in the condenser,  or is reused in the feed gas of the cathode side of the fuel cell. By humidifying the air fed into system with the water vapor present in the exhaust gas,  water is not lost from the system. Instead,  the air is being fed into the system is humidified with this water,  which in turn allows the humidifier to operated at higher temperatures and/or use smaller radiators and fans and/or draw less parasitic power,  thereby increasing overall system efficiency.', p.application_date = '2007-11-05 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'CA2668723C', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'US14686382'}) SET p.application_no = 'US14686382', p.title_cn = '用于产生氢气催化剂和产生氢气的方法', p.title_en = 'Catalyst for generating hydrogen and method for generating hydrogen', p.abstract_cn = '用于产生氢的催化剂，所述氢包含至少一种选自铂和镍的复合金属和铱和镍的复合金属的复合金属，所述催化剂用于选自肼及其水合物的至少一种化合物的分解反应； 以及一种产生氢气的方法，包括使用于产生氢气的催化剂与选自肼及其水合物的至少一种化合物接触。 在利用肼分解反应产生氢的方法中，可以以改进的选择性有效地产生氢。', p.abstract_en = 'A catalyst for generating hydrogen containing at least one composite metal selected from the group consisting of a composite metal of platinum and nickel and a composite metal of iridium and nickel,  the catalyst being used in a decomposition reaction of at least one compound selected from the group consisting of hydrazine and a hydrate thereof;  and a method for generating hydrogen,  including contacting the catalyst for generating hydrogen with at least one compound selected from the group consisting of hydrazine and a hydrate thereof. Hydrogen can be efficiently generated with improved selectivity in the method for generating hydrogen that utilizes the decomposition reaction of hydrazine.', p.application_date = '2015-04-14 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'US9227178B2', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 1, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'FR10004242'}) SET p.application_no = 'FR10004242', p.title_cn = '蒸汽重整制氢的方法的馏分与蒸汽发生优化。', p.title_en = 'METHOD FOR PRODUCING HYDROGEN BY STEAM REFORMING OF A FRACTION WITH STEAM GENERATION OPTIMIZED.', p.abstract_cn = '该方法包括中冷却合成气体的一系列热交换器(13)，冷却的烟气在另一系列的换热器用于产生蒸汽的水，将蒸汽与烃原料(1)在蒸汽重整反应器，控制蒸汽的流量，以调节比的蒸汽在烃进料的值1.5-2，压缩吹扫气体以形成燃烧气体送入燃烧室，和将合成气转化为单元的筛aration用于生产氢的具有纯度大于99.9wt。%。该方法包括中冷却合成气体的一系列热交换器(13)，冷却的烟气在另一系列的换热器用于产生蒸汽的水，将蒸汽与烃原料(1)在蒸汽重整反应器，控制蒸汽的流量，以调节比的蒸汽在烃进料的值1.5-2，压缩吹扫气体以形成燃烧气体送入燃烧室，和将合成气转化为单元的筛aration用于生产氢的具有纯度大于99.9wt。%。所述的热烟气进入压力通过压缩机(32)，其中热从热烟气提供给交换反应器在烃的蒸汽重整反应饲料与蒸汽进行混合和反应流出物。所产生的蒸汽供应到蒸汽涡轮与压缩机相关联。一种气流送料压缩机控制通过阀(36)的下游的放置在电路该换热器使压缩机的工作压力3-5绝对巴之间的配合保持在所述压缩机特性曲线。蒸汽重整反应器进料为石油馏分具有1-。', p.abstract_en = 'The process comprises cooling synthesis gas in a series of heat exchangers (13),  cooling fumes in another series of heat exchangers for generating steam from water,  sending the steam mixed with hydrocarbon feedstock (1) in the steam reforming reactor,  controlling a flow rate of steam to adjust a ratio of the steam on the hydrocarbon feed to a value of 1.5-2,  compressing a purge gas to form a combustion gas that is fed to a combustion chamber,  and introducing the synthesis gas into a unit of sieve separation for producing hydrogen having a purity of greater than 99.9 wt.%. The process comprises cooling synthesis gas in a series of heat exchangers (13),  cooling fumes in another series of heat exchangers for generating steam from water,  sending the steam mixed with hydrocarbon feedstock (1) in the steam reforming reactor,  controlling a flow rate of steam to adjust a ratio of the steam on the hydrocarbon feed to a value of 1.5-2,  compressing a purge gas to form a combustion gas that is fed to a combustion chamber,  and introducing the synthesis gas into a unit of sieve separation for producing hydrogen having a purity of greater than 99.9 wt.%. The hot fumes are brought into pressure by a compressor (32),  where a heat from the hot fumes is supplied to an exchange reactor within which steam reforming reactions of hydrocarbon feed is carried out by mixing with the steam and reaction effluent. The generated steam is supplied to a steam turbine associated with the compressor. An air flow feeding the compressor is controlled through a valve (36) placed on a circuit of a downstream of the exchangers so that an operating pressure of the compressor fits between 3-5 bars absolute to stay on a characteristic curve of the compressor. The steam-reforming reactor feed is a petroleum fraction having 1-5C.', p.application_date = '2010-10-28 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'FR2966814B1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/24', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'FR13062751'}) SET p.application_no = 'FR13062751', p.title_cn = '方法用于净化合成气与洗涤的水性胺溶液', p.title_en = 'METHOD FOR PURIFICATION OF SYNTHESIS GAS WITH WASHING AQUEOUS SOLUTIONS OF AMINES', p.abstract_cn = '本发明涉及一种合成气的纯化方法，包括至少一个步骤，分馏粗合成气被处理成至少两个流出物，第第一部分和补充部分，其中，所述第一部分进行的步骤将一氧化碳转变成蒸汽和所述互补部分经催化水解COS和HCN的步骤，产生的气体的流量各自然后arately处理在两个专用步骤用于除去酸性气体，如CO2和H2S，洗涤使用的特定水性氨基溶液，重组步骤之前端部处的所述步骤。', p.abstract_en = 'The invention relates to a process for purifying synthesis gas,  comprising at least one stage for separating the crude synthesis gas to be treated into at least two effluents,  namely a first part and a complementary part,  in which the said first part is subjected to a carbon monoxide conversion stage with steam and the said complementary part is subjected to a COS and HCN catalytic hydrolysis stage,  the two gas flows,  namely the first part and complementary part,  are then each treated separately in two stages intended to remove acid gases such as CO2 and H2S,  by washing with aqueous solutions of specific amines,  before a recombination stage of the two treated effluents.', p.application_date = '2013-12-17 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'FR3014862B1', p.patent_type = '发明授权', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/58', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'IN1854CHE2014'}) SET p.application_no = 'IN1854CHE2014', p.title_cn = '除氢和一氧化碳的气体中的杂质流', p.title_en = 'REMOVAL OF HYDROGEN AND CARBON MONOXIDE IMPURITIES FROM GAS STREAMS', p.abstract_cn = '从干氢和一氧化碳除去杂质的杂质气体，所述干气至少基本上不含二氧化碳，通过将干气与停留足够长的时间，例如，至少1.5S，通过催化剂层包括锰氧化物，铜氧化物的混合物。使用昂贵的贵金属催化剂除去氢气，从而可以避免。另外，再生该催化剂以含氧的再生气体不降低催化剂的有效性。', p.abstract_en = 'Hydrogen and carbon monoxide impurities are removed from a dry gas comprising the impurities,  wherein the dry gas is at least substantially free of carbon dioxide,  by passing the dry gas with sufficient residence time,  e.g. at least 1.5 s,  through a layer of catalyst comprising a mixture of manganese oxide and copper oxide. The use of expensive noble metal catalysts to remove hydrogen may thereby be avoided. In addition,  regeneration of the catalyst using oxygen-containing regeneration gas does not reduce the effectiveness of the catalyst.', p.application_date = '2014-04-08 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'IN1854CHE2014A', p.patent_type = '发明申请', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/00', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;
MERGE (p:Patent {application_no: 'TW104215110'}) SET p.application_no = 'TW104215110', p.title_cn = '模组化氢溶液产制设备', p.title_en = 'Modular production equipment of hydrogen solution', p.abstract_cn = '本创作系有关於一种「模组化氢溶液产制设备」，该设备主要包括有一水箱、一产氢单元与一混合器将纯水由水箱输入，经由产氢单元制造氢气，再将该氢气与一饮用水经混合器混合後，即能取得氢溶液本案特别是将该水箱之液面高度设定成高於该产氢单元回流口介於1~15cm，其具有水流顺畅且产氢效能高之优点本案以模组化方式制造，体积小、组装便利且维护简易，适合於居家设置与使用', p.abstract_en = 'On the periphery of the the creation of a "module derived solution prepared apparatus",  the device mainly comprises a water tank,  a hydrogen-producing unit and a mixer. The input of the water tank the pure water,  producing hydrogen gas by the hydrogen production unit,  then the hydrogen with a drinking water after being mixed by the mixer,  can be solution obtains the hydrogen. In this case the height of the liquid level of the water tank is set to be higher than the hydrogen producing unit return port between 1-15cm,  the water flow is smooth and has the advantages of high efficiency hydrogen. Making modularized manner in this case,  the volume is small,  convenient assembly and simple maintenance,  and is suitable for home use.', p.application_date = '2015-09-18 00:00:00', p.publication_date = 'None', p.publication_no = 'TWM514996U', p.patent_type = '实用新型', p.ipc_main = 'C01B3/02', p.tech_domain = '制氢技术', p.transfer_count = 0, p.license_count = 0, p.pledge_count = 0, p.litigation_count = 0;